"of the many bandit attacks along the connecting routes, I return the "
"Blackwell family locket to Carrad the Mage as agreed. I suppose that Carrad "
"will now hand over the locket to the Blackwell family."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4147"
msgstr ""
"I have located the dead body of Eleanor Wilde, after accepting Talaod the "
"Blacksmiths request to search for her. All I can do now is return to "
"Sanguine and hand over to Talaod the signet ring that Eleanor was wearing."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4148"
msgstr ""
"I have handed over to Talaod the Blacksmith in Sanguine, the signet ring I "
"found on Eleanor Wilde's dead body. Talaod was greatly saddened to hear the "
"news, and believes that it was partially his fault for her death."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4150"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Lord Shadowpain as requested by Kaelat the Mage, "
"and retrieved the Shadowpain family locket."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4151"
msgstr ""
"I found the body of Lord Shadowpain and retrieved the Shadowpain family "
"locket, as instructed by Kaelat the Mage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4153"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Anashek Blackstorm as requested by Mardahan the "
"Blacksmith, and retrieved Anashek's signet ring as proof of his death."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4154"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered Anashek's signet ring to Mardahan the Blacksmith, after "
"finding Anashek's dead body along the route connecting Deep Yishku with "
"Dulguna. It was as Mardahan had feared."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4156"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Lady Silverheart, and retrieved the Silverheart "
"family locket."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4157"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Silverheart family locket to Elathar the Mage, after "
"locating Lady Silverheart's dead body. Apparently, Lady Silverheart was "
"ambushed by bandits on her way back to Beladin's Rest while returning from "
"the nearby town of King's Holdfast."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4159"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Ferendir Nightsong, and retrieved Ferendir's "
"signet ring."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4160"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered Ferendir's signet ring to Dinuil the Blacksmith as proof of "
"Ferendir's death, after finding Ferendir's body along the route that "
"connects King's Holdfast with Krisathel. Dinuil was obviously shaken by the "
"sudden news of Ferendir's death."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4162"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Ynna-tel Moonhunter, and retrieved the Moonhunter "
"family locket."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4163"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Moonhunter family locket to Lenyi the Mage, after "
"finding Ynna-tel Moonhunter's body as requested by Amauron. Apparently Ynna-"
"tel, one of the nobles of Leenglow, was killed by bandits while returning "
"from the nearby town of Silverspear."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4165"
msgstr ""
"I have located Vestianna as requested by Felalon the Blacksmith, but "
"unfortunately too late. All I can do is to return to Felalon the signet ring "
"worn by Vestianna, as proof of her death."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4166"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the bad news to Felalon the Blacksmith, that Vestianna was "
"killed in the bandit ambush on her way back to Hunter's Moon from "
"Nightspire. I handed Vestianna's signet ring to Felalon as proof of her "
"death."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4168"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Lady Wildbrew, and retrieved the Wildbrew family "
"locket."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4169"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Wildbrew family locket to Draupnar the Mage, after "
"locating the dead body of Lady Wildbrew as instructed by Draupnar. "
"Apparently, Lady Wildbrew was killed on her way back to Eirhjelm, while "
"returning form the nearby town of Wintercrown."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4171"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Iorrid Snowhelm, and retrieved Iorrid's signet "
"ring."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4172"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the signet ring I found on Iorrid Snowhelm's body, after "
"Alvmund the Blacksmith ask me to search for her.  Alvmund was very upset to "
"discover that poor Iorrid did not survive the bandit attack."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4174"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Lord Bloodskull, and retrieved the Bloodskull "
"family locket."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4175"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Bloodskull family locket to Manglar the Mage, after "
"finding the body of Lord Bloodskull ask instructed by Manglar. Lord "
"Bloodskull was killed while returning to Metal Heart form the nearby town of "
"Swampton."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4177"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Malgorag Stonecutter, and retrieved Malgorag's "
"signet ring."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4178"
msgstr ""
"After finding the dead body of Malgorag Stonecutter, I delivered Malgorag's "
"signet ring to Bigthug the Blacksmith as proof of his death. Bigthug seemed "
"annoyed by Malgorag's death. I guess they weren't that much of friends."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4180"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor instructed me to report to Ayrdyr-dan the Mage, and "
"to hand over to him a copy of the demonic writing from the tombstone. "
"Tivasta believes that Ayrday-dan should be able to decipher writings."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4182"
msgstr ""
"I have traveled to Hintenfau after Ayrdyr-dan's request, to meet Varlia-yne "
"the Witch and to see if it is possible to acquire from her the scroll of "
"Demon Speaking. According to Ayrdyr-dan the Mage, this scroll should give "
"him the ability to speak and ready the ancient demonic language, and "
"therefor decipher the demonic writings for the tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4184"
msgstr ""
"I have found the powerful necromantic artifact known as the Skull of Gems in "
"the demonic city of {$p16}. All that remains is to deliver the skull to "
"Varlia-yne the Witch in {$n16}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4185"
msgstr ""
"I have found the powerful necromantic artifact known as the Skull of Gems in "
"the demonic city of {$p16}. It is this item that Varlia-yne the Witch wants "
"in exchange for the scroll of Demon Speaking that  Ayrdyr-dan has requested."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4187"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully acquired the scroll of Demon Speaking for Ayrdyr-dan the "
"Mage, after doing a little work for Varlia-yne in Hintenfau.  Ayrdyr-dan was "
"pleased to receive the scroll, although he didn't mention anything about "
"Varlia-yne's remark that he owes her."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4189"
msgstr ""
"I have traveled to {$i10} and delivered a package with arcane equipment to "
"Nomri the Mage, while waiting for Ayrdyr-dan the Mage to complete the "
"deciphering of the demonic writings."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4190"
msgstr ""
"I have returned to Red Moon after delivering a package with arcane equipment "
"to Nomri the Mage in {$i10}, as instructed by Ayrdyr-dan the Mage. All that "
"remains is to see if Ayrdyr-dan has managed to decipher the demonic writing "
"while I was away."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4192"
msgstr ""
"Ayrdyr-dan handed me a letter to deliver to Mardem-kai the Loyal of the "
"Wolfmasks, with all the information he had discovered about the Dark Lord an "
"the demonic tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4194"
msgstr ""
"I have executed the first step of many written by Ayrdyr-dan the Mage, in "
"possibly disabling the powers of the demon tombstone, by placing seven units "
"of sulfur and seven units of resin upon the demon tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4195"
msgstr ""
"The second step in disabling the demon tombstone has been executed. The rend "
"has been cast upon the tombstone, which should bring out and expose the "
"tombstone's powers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4196"
msgstr ""
"Step three in disabling the tombstone is completed. Seven units of blood, "
"five bones and one heart have been placed upon the demon tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4197"
msgstr ""
"Step four completed. The Flesh Curse spell did its work and had definitely "
"weakened the powers of the tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4198"
msgstr ""
"Ten units of ash have been placed upon the demon tombstone, to complete the "
"fifth step in disabling the magical properties of the demon tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4199"
msgstr ""
"After casting the Mana Drain spell upon the demon tombstone, the sixth and "
"final step, the tombstone has been successfully disabled. I returned to "
"Mardem-kai the Loyal in {$l14}, and reported my success in disabling the "
"powers of the demon tombstone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4201"
msgstr ""
"I have traveled all the way from the Knights of Malregard in Chilbourne, to "
"the city of Ottenhal near the central plains. Sir Jeremiah Grace has asked "
"me to meet Cournelius the Merchant, and learn anything I can about a "
"mysterious group of humans that might be involved in the theft of a "
"Lightbringer greatsword from the Knights of Malregard."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4203"
msgstr ""
"I have located Cornelius's hidden wine stash. All that remains is to bring "
"one bottle of extra fine wine to Cornelius, and to get him to give me any "
"information he might have on the theft of the Lightbringer from the Knights "
"of Malregard."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4204"
msgstr ""
"After successfully locating Cornelius's hidden wine stash in Ottenhal, I "
"delivered one bottle of extra fine wine to Cornelius. Now it is up to "
"Cornelius to drink that wine, and to remember all he can about the "
"mysterious human, and the theft of the Lightbringer greatsword from the "
"Knights of Malregard."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4206"
msgstr ""
"I have informed Sir Jeremiah Grace that it was the ex-Knight of Malregard "
"Cornelius Oakenheart, now known as Cornelius the Merchant in Ottenhal, who "
"unknowingly helped the mysterious group of humans to infiltrate the Knights "
"of Malregard, and steal the Lightbringer greatsword. I couldn't tell if Sir "
"Jeremiah Grace was saddened more about the theft of the Lightbringer "
"greatsword, or that he had just been informed that a once brave Knight of "
"Malregard, is now a lonely drunk merchant in some rouge city somewhere."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4208"
msgstr ""
"Karharias the Mage is willing to share some information with me regarding "
"the mysterious robe-wearing humans, if I first do a minor task for him. "
"Bring him the book “Blood Potions of the Full Moon” from Malren-Dor the "
"Arcanist."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4209"
msgstr ""
"Another minor task. Malren-Dor the Arcanist has asked me to gather six units "
"of Hellbore, Archangelica, Baneberry, Snakeweed and Blood, in exchange for "
"the book “Blood Potions of the Full Moon”, that Karharias the Mage has asked "
"for."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4210"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered all the materials that Malren-Dor the Arcanist had "
"requested, and now have acquired the book “Blood Potions of the Full Moon”. "
"All that remains is to deliver the book to Karharias the Mage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4211"
msgstr ""
"I have completed Karharias's little run around task, which was to fetch for "
"him the book “Blood Potions of the Full Moon”. Karharias did keep his word, "
"and revealed to me that it has he who had lead the mysterious robe-wearing "
"humans to Cornelius."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4212"
msgstr ""
"Cornelius didn't seems that surprised after I informed him that it was "
"Karharias the Mage who had given him away to the mysterious robe-wearing "
"humans that got him into so much trouble. I wonder what Cornelius will do "
"now."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4214"
msgstr ""
"According to tradition, five units of sulfur is all that is needed for one "
"to be part of the Ember Fest Celebrations. Allan the Councillor informed me "
"that Sanguine will definitely be celebrating Ember Fest. Let the "
"celebrations begin."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4216"
msgstr ""
"As I was informed by Ensharra the Councillor, that according to tradition it "
"is required to bring five units of sulfur to take part in the Ember Fest "
"Celebrations in Shoal. Let the celebrations begin."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4218"
msgstr ""
"Sylanae the Councillor was kind enough to inform me about the Ember Fest "
"celebrations taking place in Charybdis. And as tradition has it, five units "
"of sulfur is all that is required to partake in the celebrations."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4220"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor explained to me that it is tradition to bring five "
"units of sulfur to the Ember Fest celebrations. All that remains is to sit "
"and enjoy the celebrations that have been prepared here in Red Moon."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4222"
msgstr ""
"I have handed over to Ordgrim the Councillor five units of sulfur as "
"tradition has it, to participate in the Ember Fest celebrations taking place "
"in Ymir's Tear."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4224"
msgstr ""
"As tradition has it, I delivered five units of sulfur to Izkruul the "
"Councillor to take part of the Ember Fest Celebrations in Flaming Skull. Let "
"the celebrations begin."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4226"
msgstr ""
"It seems that Espenhal has decided to take part in the Ember Fest "
"Celebrations that are occurring across Agon. And according to tradition, I "
"delivered five units of sulfur to Lord of Strife to participate in "
"Espenhal's Ember Fest Celebrations."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4228"
msgstr ""
"I have desecrated the goblin shrine as instructed by Carrad the Mage, in an "
"effort to destroy the confidence of the goblin shamans in their own "
"abilities, but also that of their faith in their god Ngobil. The goblins "
"shamans are the ones guiding and inspiring the rest of the goblins attacking "
"Sandbrook, therefor through the goblin shamans we can strike at the hearts "
"of all goblins."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4230"
msgstr ""
"I have killed four goblin shamans as instructed by Carrad the Mage. If the "
"goblin shamans are the ones coordinating the goblin attacked onto Sandbrook "
"as Carrad believes, attacking the shamans should weaken the goblin attacks. "
"Time will show."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4232"
msgstr ""
"jonn the Mage instructed me to find and destroy the goblin shrine dedicated "
"to the goblin god Ngobil. Because the shamans believe it is Ngobil who has "
"given them their spellcasting powers, by desecrated the goblin shrine, the "
"shamans might believe they have lost their powers, therefor becoming less "
"dangerous for the defenders of Monkfield."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4234"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully killed four goblin shamans as requested by Jonn the "
"Mage. The shamans seem to be leading the goblin attacks against Monkfield, "
"so it is only natural that we attack the shamans."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4236"
msgstr ""
"I located the goblin shrine dedicated to the goblin god Ngobil, and "
"desecrate it. According to Caradwen the Mage, damaging the goblin shrine is "
"in fact a way to damage the goblin shamans faith in their god, and that of "
"their status among the goblins. This way, without the confident shamans to "
"guide the goblin hordes, the goblins will be nothing more than lost children."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4238"
msgstr ""
"Four goblin shamans have been killed as instructed by Caradwen the Mage. "
"Caradwen informed me that the shamans have been coordinating the goblin "
"attacks against Heart of Eanna. Therefor, the shamans must be destroyed."

