msgid "diary_text_quest_4300"
msgstr ""
"I has successfully located the body of Adrian Strong, and retrieved the "
"mighty blow horn. All that remains is the return the blow horn to Kai the "
"Fighter."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4301"
msgstr ""
"Adrain Strong's mighty blow horn has returned to Heart of Eanna. Still, the "
"loss of the town's hero was obvious in Kai's voice, as he held the blow horn "
"and sadly looked at it."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4303"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Adalia Ghostscream as instructed by Zulgal the "
"Fighter, and retrieved Adalia's mighty blow horn."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4304"
msgstr ""
"Adalia's mighty blow horn has returned to Onghral. Unfortunately, the same "
"cannot be said for Adalia Ghostscream. From the little I could tell from "
"Zulgal's reaction, Onghral will miss Adalia."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4306"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Narandir Frostwind, and retrieved Narandir's fine "
"longsword."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4307"
msgstr ""
"Narandir's fine longsword, although broken, has returned to Leafhelm. "
"Unfortunately, the same cannot be said for Narandir himself, who fell "
"defending Leafhelm from the many goblin attacks."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4309"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Kilenran, the hero of Silverspear, and retrieved "
"the keen longsword."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4310"
msgstr ""
"Kilenran's keen longsword, although broken, has returned to Silverspear. "
"Unfortunately the same cannot be said for Kilenran, the hero of Silverspear "
"who fell defending his people from the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4312"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Drogan Greybeard, and retrieved Drogan's heavy "
"shield."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4313"
msgstr ""
"Drogan's heavy shield has returned to Hammerdelve. Unfortunately, the same "
"cannot be said for Drogan Greybeard, who sacrificed his life defending "
"Hammerdelve from the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4315"
msgstr ""
"I have located the body of Galtanok Ironhead, and retrieved Galtanok's "
"mighty blow horn."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4316"
msgstr ""
"Galtanok's mighty blow horn has returned to New Flayed Elf. Unfortunately, "
"the same cannot be said for Galtanok Ironhead, who fell while defending the "
"townsfolk of New Flayed Elf from the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4318"
msgstr ""
"The flying snakes called Sarnahk, are truly strange and mysterious "
"creatures. I managed to harvest from the Sarnakh four units of Snake "
"Greanleaf, and deliver them to Carrad the Mage. I seems the Carrad will be "
"using the Snake Greenleaf for creating enchanted items."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4320"
msgstr ""
"The appearance of the undead wondering withing the old mining site near "
"Monkfield has troubled the council. I accepted to gather four units of "
"corpseflesh from the undead, so that Jonn the Mage can analyze the samples "
"and determine if these poor souls were once the miners that worked within "
"the old mines."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4322"
msgstr ""
"There are those who are disgusted and threatened by the recent spider "
"sightings near Heart of Eanna, and then there are those that could benefit "
"greatly by these eight legged visitors. Caradwen the Mage politely requested "
"that four units of Baleful Venom Sacs be harvest from the spiders and "
"delivered to her, so she may experiment with creating various enchanted "
"items."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4324"
msgstr ""
"The flying snakes called Sarnahk, are truly strange and mysterious "
"creatures. I harvested four units of Greanleaf from the Sarnakh, and deliver "
"them to Kaelat the Mage. Kaelat will be using the Greenleaf for "
"manufacturing enchanted items."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4326"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered four units of Corpseflesh from the undead that have risen "
"inside the ruins of the swamplands east of Onghral. The Corpseflesh will be "
"analyzed be Valseri the Mage, in an effort to determine what powers might "
"have contributed in rising of the dead."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4328"
msgstr ""
"Four units of Baleful Venom Sac have been harvested from the spiders that "
"have appeared east of Deep Yishku, near the trade route. Is was a good "
"opportunity to not only clear the route, but to collect some enchanting "
"materials which Haenlithe the Mage was so eager to get a hold of."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4330"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, flying snakes called Sarnakh have appeared on the "
"shores of the sacred river. Although many were the citizens of Beladin's "
"Rest that were shaken by the appearance of these magical creatures, Elethar "
"the Mage found it a good opportunity to gather some more enchanting "
"materials. I successfully gathered four units of Greenleaf for Elethar the "
"Mage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4332"
msgstr ""
"The appearance of the undead within the ancient forest of the Forest of "
"Whispers, has greatly disturbed and horrified the people of King's Holdfast. "
"I accepted to go to the Forest of Whispers and to harvest four units of "
"Corpseflesh from the undead, so that Ailton the Mage can analyze the samples "
"and discover if these poor souls were once people of Leafhelm."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4334"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the spiders that "
"have gathered southwest of Leafhelm's walls, and deliver them to Ilith the "
"Mage. According to Ilith, the Baleful Venom Sacs can be used to enchant "
"various items such as weapons and armors."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4336"
msgstr ""
"I gathered four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the spiders that have "
"gathered on the far side of the river to the east-northeast of Leenglow, and "
"deliver them to Lenyi the Mage. Lenyi will be using the Baleful Venom Sacs "
"to to experiment with enchanting various items."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4338"
msgstr ""
"The woodlands next to the path that leads to Moonclaw, have become infested "
"with magical creatures called Sarnakh. Ialynna the Councillor ask of me if I "
"would harvest from the Sarnakh four units of Greenleaf and deliver them to "
"Livina the Mage, I task I gladly accepted."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4340"
msgstr ""
"The appearance of zombies within the vicinity of the strange stone "
"structures on the south side of Hunter's Moon, is something that has puzzled "
"the council of Hunter's Moon. The only one that seems pleased by the "
"visiting zombies was Darinna the Mage, who had requested for four units of "
"corpseflesh be gathered and delivered to her."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4342"
msgstr ""
"I gathered four units of Baleful Venom Sac for Rothrin the Mage. As Arngard "
"the Councillor put it to me, Rothrin has always been there for Hammerdelve, "
"and to assist Rthrin with his research is the least we can do."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4344"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to gather four units of zombie corpseflesh from the undead that "
"have risen from withing the swamps, and deliver them to Draupnar the Mage. "
"Draupnar will try to discover why the undead are rising, but also try to "
"find answered to why the once beautiful forest of the region has turned into "
"the swamplands it is today."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4346"
msgstr ""
"The Sarnahk, are truly strange and mysterious creatures. I harvested four "
"units of Greenleaf from the Sarnakh, and deliver them to Carrad the Mage. "
"Carrad seems to be fascinated by these magical creatures, and wants to study "
"them and learn more about them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4348"
msgstr ""
"Four units of Venom Sac were successfully harvested from the mysterious "
"Sarnakh that have appeared on Grimclaw Island, and delivered to Skullgor the "
"Mage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4350"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to enter the swamp pit, and gather four units of corpseflesh from "
"the zombies that have recently risen from within. All that remains is for "
"Manglar the Mage to determine is these zombies are the mercians that once "
"offered so much entertainment to the citizens of Metal Heart."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4352"
msgstr ""
"I gathered four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the spiders that have now "
"infested the  ruin village of Broken Skull, and delivered them to Bloodzkull "
"the mage. According the Bloodzkull, the Baleful Venom Sacs will be used by "
"Bloodzkull as enchanting materials."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4375"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the letter that I found in the possession of the humans "
"bandits in Kekerdan to Mardem-kai of the Wolfmasks as Symyr-dan of the "
"Elders of Red Moon instructed of me. Apparently the information these human "
"bandits seem to have was much to important to ignore, and since the "
"Wolfmasks are investigating why the humans are in the Tribelands, it was "
"obvious that is information should be delivered to them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4377"
msgstr ""
"More Gray Orks, and especially high ranking Gray Orks such as Gray Ork "
"Chieftains, were sighted withing the Tribelands, this time near the {$j14} "
"dungeon portal. Mardem-kai instructed of me to enter the {$j14} dungeon, "
"located these Gray Orks and kill two Gray Ork Chieftains. I completed this "
"dangerous task, and as Merdem-kai said, it is a very good opportunity for "
"the Wolfmasks to show their commitment to their alliance with the Orks of "
"Morak."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4379"
msgstr ""
"After discovering the Gray Ork hideouts within the Tribelands, and "
"collecting all the information possible on the Gray Ork, the Wolfmasks "
"decided it was time to deliver this information to their allies the Orks of "
"Morak. I accepted to travel across Agon and deliver the Wolfmaks letter to "
"the Iron Ork in Naergur. It was a long trip."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4381"
msgstr ""
"I have found a chest containing a letter written in some secret code, within "
"the human bandits hideout in the Nightspire ruins. All that remains is to "
"report this find to Mardem-kai."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4383"
msgstr ""
"After carefully searching the human bandits hideout in the Nightspire ruins, "
"I found a coded letter that could possibly reveal vital information about "
"the human bandits allies within the Tribelands. All that remains is to break "
"to code."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4385"
msgstr ""
"I have discovered a mysterious magical altar among the ruins of Neithstone "
"Hall. According to Isinda-dai, this magical altar could be the reason why "
"the Menhir have gathered at Neithstone Hall. More information needs to be "
"gathered regarding this strange ancient magical altar."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4387"
msgstr ""
"I have found fragments of an old map, together with instructions to search "
"for an ancient artifact called the Night Stone, in the possession of the "
"hobgoblins inside the hobgoblin cave in {$l12}. All that remains is to "
"deliver these finds to Isinda-dai."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4388"
msgstr ""
"I found fragments of an old map, together with instructions to search for an "
"ancient artifact called the Night Stone, in the possession of the hobgoblins "
"inside the hobgoblin cave in {$l12}. After bringing these finds to Isind-"
"dai, I imagine the next steps would be to locate not only this artifact, but "
"who it is that is financing this treasure hunt. One thing is for sure, the "
"hobgoblins are definitely not going on a treasure hunt just for the fun of "
"it."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4394"
msgstr ""
"The Gnolls on Hunter's Run have been punished for daring to form an alliance "
"with the Ogres, in an attempt to control the region of Hunter's Moon. I have "
"killed four Gnolls as instructed by the Wolfmasks."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4396"
msgstr ""
"The pathetic alliance that the Ogres were trying to put together with the "
"Gnolls of Hunter's Run, has been destroyed. I successfully killed three "
"Ogres as instructed by Mardem-kai. How could the dim-witted Ogres dream of "
"even taking over Hunter's Run?"

msgid "diary_text_quest_4398"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Tamari the Arcanist of the Wolfmasks, to "
"assist the Wolfmasks in discovering the troublemakers behind the recent "
"problems of Hornwood forest."

msgid "diary_text_quest_44"
msgstr ""
"In order to strengthen and expand the Sanguine's walls, to protect from the "
"goblin attacks, basics building materials must first be collected. I have "
"just competed gathering five units of stone just as Talaod had requested."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4400"
msgstr ""
"I have found a beast totem symbolizing a raging bear inside Hornwood Forest. "
"Maybe this beast totem is the symbol of the Forest Prophets that are "
"creating the recent problems within the forest."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4401"
msgstr ""
"According to Tamari the Arcanist, the bear totem I found within Hornwood "
"Forest is the symbol of the Forest Prophets of the Raging Bear. Tamari "
"explained that it has been a very long time since anybody had heard from "
"this Circle of Forest Prophets. At least now, the Wolfmasks know the "
"identity of the group of Forest Prophets that is responsible for the attacks "
"within Hornwood Forest."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4403"
msgstr ""
"Two Black Knights have been removed from the strange floating island in "
"{$n25}. According to Dekazu Fearweaver, the Shadow Masters of the Shadow "
"Salient, have plans for this islands. What exactly I am not sure, but that "
"seems to be the way of the Shadow Salient."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4405"
msgstr ""
"The Akathars and Windlords seem to have returned to {$o11}, up high in the "
"mountains. And although they have only returned in small numbers, they have "
"already begun attacking the locals of the nearby regions. I killed six "
"Akathars and one Windlord as instructed by Thain Strongforge, to make it "
"clear to them that although they have returned to {$o11}, the Order of the "
"Axe will not  tolerate any attacks from them in the future."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4407"
msgstr ""
"Killing the Forest Prophets that murdered the workers at the logging camp in "
"{$p12} will not bring them back. But as Thain Strongforge puts it, it might "
"bring a small sense of justice to the victims families. Thain could be "
"correct in calling the Forest Prophets a bunch of cold blooded murderers, "
"that will kill anybody without a second thought in their so called crusade "
"as Agon's protectors of the Forests."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4409"
msgstr ""
"I have arrived in Sanguine, and it seems that the town is under attack by "
"goblins. Allan the Councillor has asked for my help to repel the goblins. "
"But first, I must begin my combat training with Torgard the fighter to make "
"sure that I can help Sanguine."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4411"
msgstr ""
"I have completed my basic melee combat training with Torgard. Although "
"nothing special, Torgard seemed pleased with my progress. Next I will begin "
"my archery training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4413"
msgstr "According to Stonegar, I seem to have grasped the basics of archery."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4415"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Sprint skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4416"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Parry skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4417"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Crouch Walk skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4418"
msgstr ""
"After completing my basic melee and archery training, Stonegar the Fighter "
"shared a few extra combat tips with me. Although very simple, I am sure they "
"are very important.\r\n"
"Sprinting – SHIFT key, Parry – V key, Crouching – C key, and Resting – Rest "
"Skill under General Skills."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4420"
msgstr ""
"After completing all my basic combat training with Torgard the Fighter, I "
"reported for duty with Jonn the Mage to begin by magic training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4422"
msgstr ""
"First on Jonn's list for magic training, was the casting of the simple "
"offensive spell Mana Missile. Using the mage staff I was given, I "
"successfully cast five Mana Missiles onto the mage totem."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4424"
msgstr ""
"Magic is not all about casting offensive spells. As Selensha showed me, "
"magic can also be used to aid oneself. I succeeded in casting a Self Heal "
"spell, a spell that will definitely come in handy in the future."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4426"
msgstr ""
"Simeon explained to me the benefits of using the banking facilities to store "
"as many of my belonging as I wish. It seems that carrying all my belongings "
"around with me is not a wise thing to do."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4427"
msgstr ""
"Before returning back to Allan the Councillor once I had completed both my "
"combat and magic training, Jonn asked me to visit Simeon the Merchant to "
"explain to me how to use the local bank."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4429"
msgstr ""
"I have report back to Allan the Councillor to complete my basic training in "
"Sanguine, after completing my training with Torgard the Fighter, jonn the "
"Mage, and Simeon the Merchant. Now I can help Sanguine by beginning with "
"those goblins that have surrounded the town."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4431"
msgstr ""
"As I arrived in Sandbrook, I was informed by William the Councillor that the "
"town has been under attack by goblins, and that he fears that the situation "
"could get worse. William the Councillor asked of me to report for duty with "
"Catherine the Fighter so I may begin my combat training, to make sure I am "
"prepared to help Sandbrook with the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4433"
msgstr ""
"My basic melee combat training has successfully come to an end, and "
"Catherine the Fighter has informed me that next I will begin my archery "
"training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4435"
msgstr ""
"With the completion of my archery training, I have come to the end of my "
"combat training. Catherine the Fighter commented that with a little "
"practice, I could become a great archer."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4437"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Sprint skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4438"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Parry skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4439"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Crouch Walk skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4440"
msgstr ""
"Catherine the Fighter took some time to share some very useful combat tips "
"with me, that are very vital to ones survival.\r\n"
"Sprinting – SHIFT key, Parry – V key, Crouching – C key, and Resting – Rest "
"Skill under General Skills."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4442"
msgstr ""
"With the completion of my basic combat training with Catherine the Fighter, "
"I have now reported for duty with Carrad the Mage. Carrad will be showing me "
"the basics of magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4444"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully executed Carrad's first training exercise, which was to "
"cast five Mana Missiles onto the mage totem. Simple, but effective."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4446"
msgstr ""
"I have managed to cast a Heal Self spell onto myself, as part of Carrad's "
"basic magic training. Using a basic mage staff, and can cast spells to "
"either damage my enemies, or spells to aid me in battle."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4448"
msgstr ""
"Before returning back to William the Councillor once I had completed both my "
"combat and magic training, Carrad asked me to visit Thora the Merchant to "
"explain to me how to use the local bank."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4449"
msgstr ""
"I visited Thora the Merchant and received some very useful information. "
"Thora explained to me how to use the banking facilities that could be found "
"in almost every town and city in Agon, and that it would be smart to store "
"some of my belonging there, before I get them stolen."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4451"
msgstr ""
"I have completed my basic training in Sandbrook, after learning valuable "
"lessons from Catherine the Fighter, Carrad the Mage, Thora the Merchant and "
"of course William the Councillor. With the basic knowledge of combat and "
"magic I have gained, I should be able to begin helping Sandbrook deal with "
"the goblin attacks."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4453"
msgstr ""
"I have agreed to go through the basic training in the Heart of Eanna, as it "
"is obvious that I must prepare myself to help the town deal with the recent "
"goblin infestation. Aidan the Councillor instructed me to report to Kai the "
"Fighter where I will begin my combat training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4455"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully completed my basic melee combat training with Kai the "
"Fighter, and soon I will begin my archery training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4457"
msgstr "You have hit the archery targets # times."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4459"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Sprint skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4460"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Parry skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4461"
msgstr "I have successfully executed the Crouch Walk skill."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4462"
msgstr ""
"Once my basic combat training was over, Kai the Fighter shared some simple, "
"yet very useful tips with me.\r\n"
"Sprinting – SHIFT key, Parry – V key, Crouching – C key, and Resting – Rest "
"Skill under General Skills."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4464"
msgstr ""
"Combat training completed, and now time to begin magic training. I have "
"already reported for duty with Caradwen the Mage, who will be teaching me "
"the basics of magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4466"
msgstr ""
"I have succeeded in casting five Mana Missiles onto the mage totem as part "
"of Carrad's basic magic training."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4468"
msgstr ""
"After the Mana Missiles, Caradwen the Mage showed me how to use staff to "
"cast a Heal Self spell. Seems like not all magic is about offensive magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_447"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully killed four goblins, as Ialynna the Councillor requested "
"from all in Silverspear. Apparently the goblins that have settled in the "
"abandoned mirdain village to the west have been breeding out of control, and "
"now threaten to overwhelm Silverspear with their numbers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4470"
msgstr ""
"Before returning back to Aidan the Councillor once I had completed both my "
"combat and magic training, Caradwen asked me to visit Isabel the Merchant to "
"explain to me how to use the local bank."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4471"
msgstr ""
"I received a brief but very important lecture from Isabel the Merchant on "
"how to use the banking facilities, before returning to Aidan the Councilor "
"to complete my basic training. Isabel explained to me the benefits of using "
"the banking facilities. Carrying all my belonging around with me all the "
"time is not a wise thing to do."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4474"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully completed my basic training here in the Heart of Eanna. "
"Thanks to Kai the Fighter, Caradwen the Mage, Isabel the Merchant and, Aidan "
"the Councillor I have acquired enough basic knowledge of combat and magic, "
"to aid the Heart of Eanna in their fight against the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_449"
msgstr ""
"I have looted two goblin axes from the fallen goblins. By doing this, we are "
"preventing other goblins from recovering these weapons and using them "
"against Silverspear in the future."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4500"
msgstr ""
"I killed 2 Cave Hags inside the Banegorge caves to prove to Halbein Grimpeak "
"of the Fangs of Ottenhal, that I could be of further use to the Fangs of "
"Ottenhal in the future."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4502"
msgstr ""
"I accepted Halbein Grimpeak's offer to take part in the Banegorge Dungeon "
"Cave Hag Hunt, and kill 15 Cave Hags. It was a hard hunt, but worth it too. "
"Halbein informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 hours after its "
"completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4504"
msgstr ""
"I destroyed 4 Crypt Guards within Mabria Dungeon, after speaking to Mordhan "
"Blackridge of the Simiran Order. According to Mordhan, the Crypt Guards "
"could be to former occupants of the dungeon that were once known as the "
"Knight of Mabria."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4506"
msgstr ""
"I agreed to take part in the Mabria Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt, and "
"successfully killed 30 Crypt Guards. Mordhan Blackridge informed me that the "
"hunt will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4508"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to assist Damantia Dreamwalker of the Hintenfau Sisterhood by "
"removing 3 Sarlid Darkweavers from Larethain dungeon. It seems that the "
"Darkweavers are interfering with the Sisterhood's plans."

msgid "diary_text_quest_451"
msgstr ""
"In order to strengthen and expand the walls around Silverspear to protect "
"from future goblin attacks, basics building materials must first be "
"collected. I have just competed gathering five units of stone just as Sa-"
"Imdor had requested."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4510"
msgstr ""
"Somehow Damantia Dreamwalker convinced me to take part in the Larethain "
"Dungeon Sarlid Darkweaver Hunt, that the Hintenfau Sisterhood have declared. "
"I successfully completed the hunt by killing 25 Sarlid Darkweavers. Damantia "
"informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 hours after its "
"completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4513"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Fotel-ayn the Calm of the Hintenfau Sisterhood, to help them "
"uncover the strange event of the Tomb Iklit migration into the  Ahu Ishtra "
"caves. I successfully located the Tomb Iklits and killed one of them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4515"
msgstr ""
"Tomb Iklits are extremely hard and fearless, one thing I discovered while "
"taking part in the Ahu Ishtra Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt that was hosted by the "
"Hintenfau Sisterhood. I managed to complete the hunt by killing 10 Tomb "
"Iklits. Fotel-ayn the Calm of the Sisterhood informed me that the hunt will "
"be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4517"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to kill one Tomb Iklit inside Istind dungeon, in an effort to "
"assist the researchers of Espenhal in their effort to begin exploring the "
"dungeon for signs of a lost city."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4519"
msgstr ""
"The Istind Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt proved to be a difficult challenge, one I "
"managed to complete after killing 10 Tomb Iklits. Ultunuk Heartstabber of "
"the Lords of Espenhal, informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 "
"hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4521"
msgstr ""
"I destroyed 3 Crypt Guards inside Meldanyr dungeon, as I agreed to assist "
"the Fangs of Ottenhal in their search of some lost documents within the "
"dungeon, that might reveal information about the dark activities of a group "
"of mad wizards called the Circle of Death and Fire."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4523"
msgstr ""
"Kandra Dragonaxe of the Fangs of Ottenhal offered me the opportunity to take "
"part in the Meldanyr Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt, an offer I gladly accepted. I "
"successfully completed the hunt by destroying 30 Crypt Guards within the "
"dungeon. Kandra informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 hours "
"after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4525"
msgstr ""
"After speaking with Urdan-tai the Tough, I accepted to assist the White "
"Hunters by destroying 2 of the many Undead Dwarves that continue to haunt "
"the Otredale mines."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4527"
msgstr ""
"Although long dead now, the Undead Dwarves that haunt the Otredale mines "
"still offer a good challenge for those willing to go up against them, as I "
"found out by taking part in the Otredale Dungeon Undead Dwarf Hunt. After "
"successfully killing 15 Undead Dwarves, Urdan-tai the Tought informed me "
"that the hunt will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4529"
msgstr ""
"I accepted a task from Muruk Blackspike of the Silverswords, to kill 4 Cave "
"Trolls inside Scarbourne Dungeon. According to Muruk,the Silverswords had "
"decided to offer me that unique opportunity to earn that extra something. "
"How nice of them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_453"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the timber Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith requested for the "
"construction of the guard towers. With the goblin attacks upon Silverspear "
"and the trade routes, it has been decided to construct a series of guard "
"towers along the road which connects Silverspear to the mahirim capital of "
"{$j12}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4531"
msgstr ""
"I managed to kill 40 Cave Trolls after being convinced by Muruk Blackspick "
"to take part in the Scarbourne Dungeon Cave Troll Hunt, that is hosted by "
"the Silverswords. Somehow I think that the only winner here are the "
"Silverswords, and that I'm only doing their dirty work. The hunt will be "
"available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4533"
msgstr ""
"I managed to pass Stelak the Tall's small test, after successfully killing 2 "
"Cave Hags inside Sirith Dain dungeon. Stelak is a member of the Mirrorsea "
"Union, and simply explained that the Hags Hags are in the way of the Union's "
"plans."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4535"
msgstr ""
"Stelek the Tall who represents the Mirrorsea Union, asked me to take part in "
"the Sirith Dain Dungeon Cave Hag Hunt. I successfully completed the hunt "
"after killing 15 Cave Hags. The hunt will be available again 21 hours after "
"its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4537"
msgstr ""
"I met Parras Darkblood of the Lords of Espenhal, who explained to me that "
"the Lords wish to explore the Nithron dungeon located in Kaerdan. I accepted "
"to assist them by killing 3 Cave Spiders that have infested the once "
"glorious Nithron dungeon."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4539"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to take part in the Kaerdan Dungeon Cave Spider Hunt that is "
"organized by the Lords of Espenhal after speaking with Parras Darkblood. The "
"hunt was for 30 Cave Spiders, a task I had no problem completing. The hunt "
"will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4543"
msgstr ""
"After locating the strange fire pillar within the severii stronghold in "
"{$j23}, Hanthar Blackfrost asked of me to travel to the Harn Mandean "
"headquarters in Dulguna, and report this find to Hanthar the Mage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4545"
msgstr ""
"I destroyed 3 Shadow Spirits within Hardruk Dungeon, after speaking to "
"Thanial Nightlight of the Loremasters of Janhalek. According to Thanial, the "
"Shadow Spirits could be to former occupants of the dungeon, a mystical group "
"of female spellcasters."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4547"
msgstr ""
"Somehow Thanial Nightlight convinced me to take part in the Hardruk Dungeon "
"Shadow Spirit Hunt, that the Loremasters of Janhalek have declared. I "
"successfully completed the hunt by killing 20 Shadow Spirits. Thanial "
"informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 hours after its "
"completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4549"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Corsal Greyhouse of the Lords of Espenhal, by accepting to "
"kill 3 Shade Salamanders inside the Velmuna Caves."

msgid "diary_text_quest_455"
msgstr ""
"It amazes me how a simple herb such a mandrake, is used to cast spells. "
"After gathering and delivering the five mandrake herbs to Murion-tai the "
"Arcanist, stretching my back a little will help to recover from all that "
"scrounging about in the undergrowth."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4553"
msgstr ""
"I accepted Carsal Greyhouse's offer to take part in the Velmuna Dungeon "
"Shade Salamander Hunt. I successfully completed the hunt after killing 25 "
"Shade Salamanders. The hunt will be available again 21 hours after its "
"completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4555"
msgstr ""
"I stumbled upon Sira Deathcry of the Hintenfau Sisterhood inside the "
"Winterworth Cave, who had an interesting proposition for me. She explained "
"that if I accept to kill 3 Cave Spiders inside the caves, I would be allowed "
"to take part in some sort of hunt organized by the Sisterhood. I accepted "
"the task and killed 3 Cave Spiders."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4557"
msgstr ""
"30 Cave Spiders was the goal of the Winterworth Dungeon Cave Spiders Hunt, a "
"task I successfully completed. Sira Deathcry informed me that the hunt will "
"be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4559"
msgstr ""
"Inside Mynthran dungeon, I came across a strange fella called Balac "
"Stonetooth. Balac informed me that the Fangs of Ottenhal seek adventures to "
"remove the Cave Trolls form the dungeon. I accepted to assist them, by first "
"proving my value by successfully killing 4 Cave Trolls."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4561"
msgstr ""
"Once more hunting Cave Trolls inside Myntharn dungeon, but this time as part "
"of the Myntharn Dungeon Cave Troll Hunt organized by the Fangs of Ottenhal. "
"Balac Stonetooth, from whom I accept the hunt from, informed me that the "
"hunt will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4563"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Sanguine deal with the Scumling infestation of the city sewer "
"system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 "
"Scumling Guard. According to Allan the Councillor, occasional sewer sweeps "
"are necessary, to maintain the Scumling population as low as possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4565"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Shoal deal with the Scumling infestation of the city sewer "
"system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 "
"Scumling Guard.  According to Ensharra the Councillor, occasional sewer "
"sweeps are necessary, to keep the Scumling population as low as possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4566"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Charybdis deal with the Scumling infestation of the city sewer "
"system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 "
"Scumling Guard. According to Sylanae the Councillor, occasional sewer sweeps "
"are necessary, to maintain the Scumlings population as low as possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4568"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Red Moon deal with the Scumling infestation of the city sewer "
"system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 "
"Scumling Guard. According to Tivasta the Councillor, occasional sewer sweeps "
"will be issued, to keep the Scumlings population as low as possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_457"
msgstr ""
"The art of imbuing items with magical properties is quite amazing. I have "
"gathered four Tooth as Ialynna the Councillor requested of me. These simple "
"Tooth will be used to craft magical items. Incredible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4570"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Ymir's Tear deal with the Scumling infestation of the city "
"sewer system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers "
"and 1 Scumling Guard. According to Ordgrim the Councillor, occasional sewer "
"sweeps will be issued, to keep the Scumlings population as low as possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_4572"
msgstr ""
"I have helped Flaming Skull deal with the Scumling infestation of the city "
"sewer system, by accepting to enter the sewers and kill 4 Scumling Workers "
"and 1 Scumling Guard.  According to Izkruul the Councillor, occasional sewer "
"sweeps are necessary, to maintain the Scumlings population as low as "
"possible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_459"
msgstr ""
"I am sure that the goblins fear of the mahirim has grown after those twenty "
"mana missiles I cast against them. Since the goblins fear magic, every trick "
"available to us must be used in our attempt to expel them from Silverspear."

msgid "diary_text_quest_46"
msgstr ""
"One of the tasks that Anton needed help with was the gathering of stone, to "
"strengthen and expand the walls around Sandbrook. I have just completed "
"gathering five units of stone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_461"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Hunter's Moon deal with the goblin threat by killing four "
"goblins just, as requested by Andor-Kai the Councillor. The goblins are "
"many, and I am not sure if this alone will be enough."

msgid "diary_text_quest_463"
msgstr ""
"I have retrieved two goblin axes from the slain goblins. According to Andor-"
"Kai the Councillor, by looting the axes from the fallen goblins, we are "
"preventing other goblins from retrieving them and using them to attack "
"Hunter's Moon. Time will show."

msgid "diary_text_quest_465"
msgstr ""
"It was a hard job, but I did it for the good of my people. I have done my "
"part in helping with the construction of the guard houses. I have gathered "
"the amount of stone Felonon had asked for, stone that would be used for the "
"construction of the guard houses at Hunter's Moon."

msgid "diary_text_quest_467"
msgstr ""
"Felanon the Blacksmith has requested that we gather enough timber for the "
"construction of the guard towers. After the goblin attacks, it is obvious "
"that Hunter's Moon's defenses will improve with the addition of the guard "
"towers. I have gathered and delivered five units of timber."

msgid "diary_text_quest_469"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered five units of mandrake as requested by Celene the Arcanist. "
"Mandrake is one of the spell reagents. It is to be used by Hunter's Moon's "
"spellcasters against the goblin infestation."

msgid "diary_text_quest_471"
msgstr ""
"I have completed the bloody task of extracting four teeth from the slain "
"goblins. From what I have been told, different ingredients taken from the "
"bodies of slain monsters such as teeth, are used in the art of imbuing items "
"with magical properties. Very interesting."

msgid "diary_text_quest_473"
msgstr ""
"Sword and bows may be good against the goblins, but magic also has its "
"benefits. I was given the task by Andor-Kai to cast twenty mana missile "
"against the goblins that are attacking Hunter's Moon. It would seem that the "
"goblins, like many of the monsters of Agon, have an innate fear of magic, "
"and this is something that we must take full advantage of."

msgid "diary_text_quest_475"
msgstr ""
"Arkelia the Councillor was pleased to hear that I successfully killed four "
"of the many goblins that surrounded Leenglow. It seems that the goblins are "
"using an old mine to the north of Leenglow as a base for their attacks. "
"These goblins are many and very annoying"

msgid "diary_text_quest_477"
msgstr ""
"According to Arkelia the Councillor in Leenglow, the majority of goblins are "
"too stupid to craft any weapons. By looting the axes from the fallen goblins "
"before others can retrieve them, we are in fact disarming the goblins. I "
"have just looted two goblin axes from the dead goblins."

msgid "diary_text_quest_479"
msgstr ""
"One of the tasks that Molangar needed help with was the gathering of stone, "
"to strengthen and expand the walls around Leenglow as the council had "
"requested. I have just completed gathering five units of stone."

msgid "diary_text_quest_481"
msgstr ""
"Another task Molangar needed help with was collecting timber. It seems that "
"the goblin attacks have somehow halted the logging operations in Leenglow, "
"and now the town is in need of timber. I did my part and gathered five units "
"of timber as Molangar had requested of me."

msgid "diary_text_quest_483"
msgstr ""
"Not that difficult, but very tedious. I have gathered five mandrake herbs "
"according to Amauron's request. Mandrake is one of the reagents used by "
"spellcasters for casting spells."

msgid "diary_text_quest_485"
msgstr ""
"I have completed the task of extracting four teeth from the slain goblins, "
"as instructed by Arkelia the Councillor. Who would have known that simple "
"teeth can be used for crafting items imbued with magical properties."

msgid "diary_text_quest_487"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that goblins have a great fear of magic. I have complete the "
"strange task of casting twenty mana missiles against the goblins that have "
"surrounded Leenglow. Hopefully this will remind the goblins that they should "
"definitely fear us mahirim and our magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_490"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully killed four goblins, just as Taelis the Councillor "
"requested from all in Onghral. Apparently the goblins that have settled in "
"the abandoned stone quarries have been breeding out of control, and now "
"threaten to overwhelm Onghral with their numbers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_493"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully gathered two goblin axes from the fallen goblins. "
"Although these axes are of no use to our warriors or craftsmen, they will "
"surely be put to good use as tools by the slaves in Onghral. The slaves will "
"have no more excuses to not work."

msgid "diary_text_quest_495"
msgstr ""
"In order to strengthen and expand Onghral's walls, to protect from the "
"future goblin attacks, basics building materials must first be collected, "
"such as stone. I have competed gathering five units of stone as requested by "
"Nirgan the Blacksmith."

msgid "diary_text_quest_497"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the timber Nirgan the Blacksmith requested for the "
"construction of the guard towers. With the goblin attacks upon Onghral and "
"the trade routes, it has been decided to construct a series of guard towers "
"along the road which connects Onghral to the alfar capital of {$n23}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_499"
msgstr ""
"It is amazing that a simple herbs such a mandrake is used to cast spells. "
"After gathering five mandrake herbs that Kalshar the Arcanist requested, "
"stretching my back will help to recover from all that scrounging about in "
"the undergrowth."

msgid "diary_text_quest_50"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered the timber Talaod the Blacksmith requested for the "
"strengthening of Sanguine's walls. The goblin attacks have forced Sanguine "
"to repair and expand the walls."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5000"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Dulog Painchopper of the Blades of Tolenque, to help them "
"uncover the strange event of the going on in the Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon. I "
"successfully located a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5002"
msgstr ""
"The Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, one I "
"managed to complete after killing 15 Menhir Custodian, 10 Menhir Stoneguard "
"and 5 Thainlord. Dulog Painchopper of the Blades of Tolenque, informed me "
"that the purge will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5004"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Busi the Explorer of the Simiran Order, to help them uncover "
"the strange event of the going on in the Southwestern Serruk Dungeon. I "
"successfully located a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5006"
msgstr ""
"The Southwestern Serruk Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, "
"one I managed to complete after killing 20 Minotaur Shaman and 10 Minotaur "
"Hero. Busi the Explorer of the Simiran Order, informed me that the purge "
"will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5008"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Leto Elithir of the Jhali Raiders, to help them uncover the "
"strange event of the going on in the Ahbelaj Dungeon. I successfully located "
"a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_501"
msgstr ""
"The art of imbuing items with magical properties is something quite amazing. "
"I have just gathered four teeth as Taelis the Councillor requested of me. "
"These simple teeth will be used to craft magical items. Incredible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5010"
msgstr ""
"The Ahbelaj Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, one I managed "
"to complete after killing 24 Arthain Hump, 10 Chosen of Khamset, 8 Fire "
"Giants and 8 Fire Elements. Leto Elithir of the Jhali Raiders, informed me "
"that the purge will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5012"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Ashue Cynn of the White Hunters, to help them uncover the "
"strange event of the going on in the khanruk Dungeon. I successfully located "
"a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5014"
msgstr ""
"The Khanruk Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, one I managed "
"to complete after killing 10 Frostjarl, 10 Icejarl, 10 Yeti, 10 Lesser Water "
"Elemental And 10 Water Elemental. Ashue Cynn of the The White Hunters, "
"informed me that the hunt will be available again 21 hours after its "
"completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5016"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Anail Winterstaff Dagorithe of the Blades of Tolenque, to "
"help them uncover the strange event of the going on in the Ubelenfau "
"Dungeon. I successfully located a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5018"
msgstr ""
"The Ubelenfau Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, one I "
"managed to complete after killing 15 Black Lords, 10 Deathless Mage and 1 "
"Demon. Anail Winterstaff Dagorithe of the Blades of Tolenque, informed me "
"that the purge will be available again 21 hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5020"
msgstr ""
"I have assisted Glumstein Snowbeard of the White Hunters, to help them "
"uncover the strange event of the going on in the svartvann Dungeon. I "
"successfully located a series of monsters and killed them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5022"
msgstr ""
"The svartvann Dungeon purge proved to be a difficult challenge, one I "
"managed to complete after killing 20 Svartdvergir Summoner, "
"20 Svartdvergir Nightaxe, 20 Svartdvergir Initiate, "
"7 Svartdvergir General and 5 Svartdvergir Doombringer. Glumstein Snowbeard "
"of the White Hunters, informed me that the purge will be available again 21 "
"hours after its completion."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5024"
msgstr ""
"It was a day of cold winds and immense bloodshed. In the end, you and your "
"party were the last ones standing. Ironbeard Heavyfist and Hjor the Great "
"have been vanquished. (Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours "
"after its completion)"

msgid "diary_text_quest_5026"
msgstr ""
"In a quest spanning across Yssam you managed to fell both Ironbark the "
"Ancient and Grand Tikoloshe. Many drinks were had. Many stories were told. "
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "diary_text_quest_5028"
msgstr ""
"In a day you will never forget, you and your mates slaughtered both "
"Chieftain Khalos and Warlord Choppah. This may go down in history as your "
"finest victories, and many songs are sure to be sung in your honor. "
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "diary_text_quest_503"
msgstr ""
"I am sure that the goblins fear of the alfar has grown after the twenty mana "
"missiles I cast against them. Since the goblins fear magic, every trick "
"available to us must be used in our attempt to expel the goblins from "
"Onghral."

msgid "diary_text_quest_5030"
msgstr ""
"You were tasked with slaying the champions Vlad Duskward and Fenris Alpha "
"and emerged victorious. Barely. (Warning: This quest will be available "
"again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "diary_text_quest_5032"
msgstr ""
"Amidst the sweltering sands of Rubaiyat you defeated both Siharo Darkbinder "
"and Hellfire Juggernaught. The memories of your victory are almost as "
"satisfying as the feast that followed them. (Warning: This quest will be "
"available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "diary_text_quest_505"
msgstr ""
"Deep Yishku has seen an increase of goblin attacks along its trade routes. I "
"have helped Deep Yishku deal with the goblin bands by killing four of the "
"filthy vermin."

msgid "diary_text_quest_507"
msgstr ""
"I have retrieved two goblin axes from the fallen goblins that have been "
"attacking Deep Yishku. According to Nirgash the Councillor, by looting the "
"axes from the fallen goblins before the other goblins can retrieve them, we "
"are in fact disarming the goblin army. Time will show."

msgid "diary_text_quest_509"
msgstr ""
"I have done my part in helping with the construction of the guard houses. "
"The amount of stone needed for the construction of the Deep Yishku's new "
"guard houses has been gathered."

msgid "diary_text_quest_511"
msgstr ""
"Mardahan the Blacksmith has asked of all of us to gather enough timber for "
"the construction of the guard towers. After the goblin attacks, it is "
"obvious that Deep Yishku's defenses will improve with the addition of the "
"guard towers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_513"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered the five units of mandrake Ilrak the Arcanist had requested. "
"Mandrake to be used by Deep Yishku's spellcasters in the battle against the "
"pathetic mirdain. Those spellcasters better do a god job, because my back "
"still hurts from all the scrounging about in the undergrowth."

msgid "diary_text_quest_515"
msgstr ""
"This was something I was not expecting. I have returned to Deep Yishky after "
"completing the bloody task of extracting four teeth from the slain goblins. "
"From what I have been told, different ingredients taken from the bodies of "
"slain monsters such as teeth, are used in the art of imbuing items with "
"magical properties. Very interesting."

msgid "diary_text_quest_517"
msgstr ""
"Swords and bows may be good against the goblins, but magic also has its "
"benefits. I was given the opportunity by Nirgash to cast twenty mana missile "
"against the goblins that are attacking Deep Yishku. It would seem that the "
"goblins, like many of the monsters of Agon, have an innate fear of magic, "
"and this is something that we must take full advantage of."

msgid "diary_text_quest_519"
msgstr ""
"The lands surrounding Akathos seem to have recently become infested with "
"goblins. Irshanta the Councillor asked of me clear the surrounding lands by "
"killing four goblin, a task I willingly and easily completed."

msgid "diary_text_quest_52"
msgstr ""
"Another material needed for the strengthening of Sandbrook's wall was "
"timber. I did my part and gathered five units of timber as requested by "
"Anton the Blacksmith."

msgid "diary_text_quest_521"
msgstr ""
"I have retrieved two goblin axes from the slain goblins, as instructed by "
"Irshanta the Councillor in Akathos. These axes will do fine as tools in the "
"hands of our slaves."

msgid "diary_text_quest_523"
msgstr ""
"One of the tasked that Neissur needed assistance with, was the gathering of "
"stone to expand the slave pens in Akathos, in order to accommodate the "
"captured goblins. From what I understand, one can never have enough slaves."

msgid "diary_text_quest_525"
msgstr ""
"Neissur the Blacksmith has requested from all in Akathos, to gather enough "
"timber for the construction a series of new watchtowers along the roads to "
"{$n23} and Yishku. After the annoying goblin attacks, it is obvious that "
"Akathos's defenses will improve with the addition of these new guard towers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_527"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that the invading goblins have driven off the herb gatherers, "
"and now Akathos is running low on several key ingredients, one of them being "
"mandrake. With mandrake being one of the reagents used by spellcasters for "
"casting spells, Thielit the Arcanist asked of me to gather five mandrake "
"herbs, which I did."

msgid "diary_text_quest_529"
msgstr ""
"I have completed removing four teeth from the slain goblins, as instructed "
"by Irshanta the Councillor. I am amazed that simple teeth can be used in the "
"art of crafting items imbued with magical properties."

msgid "diary_text_quest_531"
msgstr ""
"According to Irshanta the Councillor, goblins have a great fear of magic. I "
"have complete casting twenty mana missiles against the goblins that have "
"surrounded Akathos. This will definitely remind the goblins that they should "
"fear us alfar and our superior magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_538"
msgstr ""
"Silawen the Councillor has requested of all to assist Leafhelm rid itself of "
"the goblin bands seen wandering on the outskirts of the town, before they "
"start creating any serious problems. I have done my part my successfully "
"killing four of the filthy greenskins."

msgid "diary_text_quest_540"
msgstr ""
"I have retrieved two goblin axes from the fallen goblins. According to "
"Silawen the Councillor, by looting the axes from the fallen goblins before "
"other goblins can retrieve them and use them to attack Leafhelm, we are in "
"fact disarming the goblins. Time will show."

msgid "diary_text_quest_542"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered the amount of stone Ciredan requested, stone that would be "
"used to strengthen Leafhelm's walls."

msgid "diary_text_quest_544"
msgstr ""
"Ciredan the Blacksmith had requested of all to gather enough timber for the "
"construction of the guard towers. After the goblin attacks, it is obvious "
"that Leafhelm's defenses along the trade routes will improve with the "
"addition of the guard towers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_546"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered five units of mandrake to Eredil the Arcanist as requested. "
"Mandrake is a reagent for casting spells, and is to be used by Leafhelm's "
"spellcasters in the fight against the goblin hordes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_548"
msgstr ""
"I have completed the bloody task of extracting four teeth from the slain "
"goblins. It seems that teeth are one of the many materials that can by used "
"in the art of imbuing items with magical properties."

msgid "diary_text_quest_550"
msgstr ""
"Swords and bows may be good against the goblins, but magic also has its "
"benefits. I was given the task by Silawen the Councillor to cast twenty mana "
"missile against the goblins that were attacking Leafhelm. It would seem that "
"the goblins, like many of the monsters of Agon, have an innate fear of magic "
"and this is something that we must take full advantage of."

msgid "diary_text_quest_552"
msgstr ""
"Lysandir the Councillor was pleased to hear that I had successfully killed "
"four goblins. Apparently goblin bands have entered the beautiful lake "
"district near Beladin's Rest, and are polluting the waters of the sacred "
"river."

msgid "diary_text_quest_554"
msgstr ""
"According to Lysandir the Councillor, the majority of goblins are not smart "
"enough to craft any weapons. By looting the axes from the fallen goblins "
"before others can retrieve them, we are in fact disarming the goblins, and "
"stopping them from destroying our beautiful forests near Beladin's Rest. I "
"have successfully retrieved two goblin axes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_556"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered five units of stone, just as Tiyawen the Blacksmith "
"requested for the construction of the guard houses in Beladin's Rest."

msgid "diary_text_quest_558"
msgstr ""
"Once the new guard towers are built and ready, the hunting grounds near "
"Beladin's Rest will be safe from any enemies. I have gathered five units of "
"timber that will be used in the construction of these new guard towers."

msgid "diary_text_quest_56"
msgstr ""
"It amazes me how a simple herb such a mandrake, is used to cast spells. "
"After gathering five mandrake herbs that Jonn the Mage requested, stretching "
"my back a little will help to recover from all that scrounging about in the "
"undergrowth."

msgid "diary_text_quest_560"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered the five mandrake herbs that Gelwain the Arcanist requested. "
"Mandrake is one of the reagents used by spellcasters for casting spells."

msgid "diary_text_quest_562"
msgstr ""
"I have extracted four teeth from the slain goblins according to Lysandir the "
"Councillor's request. Who would have known that simple teeth can be used for "
"crafting items imbued with magical properties."

msgid "diary_text_quest_564"
msgstr ""
"Goblins seem to have a great fear of magic. I have complete the strange task "
"of casting twenty mana missiles against the goblins that have surrounded "
"Beladin's Rest. Hopefully this will remind the goblins that they should "
"definitely fear us humans and our magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_566"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully killed four goblins as requested by Elvallie the "
"Councillor. Apparently the goblins groups that have been seen around King's "
"Holdfast, have been staging raids against local farms and villages."

msgid "diary_text_quest_568"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered two goblin axes from the fallen goblins. By doing this, we "
"are stopping other goblins from recovering these weapons and using them "
"against King's Holdfast in the future. We are in fact disarming the goblins."

msgid "diary_text_quest_570"
msgstr ""
"In order to strengthen and expand the walls around King's Holdfast, basics "
"building materials must first be collected. I have gathering and delivered "
"five units of stone to Dinuil the Blacksmith as requested."

msgid "diary_text_quest_572"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered and delivered the amount of timber Dinuil the Blacksmith "
"requested for the construction of the guard towers. The goblin attacks have "
"forced King's Holdfast to upgrade its defenses."

msgid "diary_text_quest_574"
msgstr ""
"It amazes me how a simple herb such a mandrake, can be used to cast spells. "
"After gathering five mandrake herbs for Aergeir the Arcanist, stretching my "
"back a little will help me recover from all that scrounging about in the "
"undergrowth."

msgid "diary_text_quest_576"
msgstr ""
"The art of imbuing items with magical properties is quite fascinating. I "
"have gathered four teeth as Elvallie the Councillor requested of me. These "
"simple teeth will be used to craft magical items. Incredible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_578"
msgstr ""
"The goblins fear of the mirdain has definitely grown after the barrage of "
"mana missiles cast against them. Since the goblins fear magic, we must use "
"every trick available to us in our attempt to expel the goblins from King's "
"Holdfast."

msgid "diary_text_quest_58"
msgstr ""
"Not that difficult, but very tedious. I have gathered five mandrake herbs "
"just as Carrad the Mage requested. Mandrake is one of the reagents used by "
"spellcasters for casting spells."

msgid "diary_text_quest_617"
msgstr ""
"As an organization, the Wolfmasks are all serious business. Immediately when "
"the human were located within the Tribelands, the hunt was on. I accepted to "
"kill four of the humans bandits that were hiding in the ruins in Nightspire, "
"as instructed by Mardem-kai the Loyal."

msgid "diary_text_quest_619"
msgstr ""
"The Centaurs of Hornwood forest have been punished for attacking the "
"Wolfmask patrols. I removed Timeless Blood from the Centaurs, as instructed "
"by Mardem-kai the Loyal. That should teach them."

msgid "diary_text_quest_62"
msgstr ""
"The art of imbuing items with magical properties is quite fascinating. I "
"have gathered four teeth as Allan the Councillor requested of me. These "
"simple teeth will be used to craft magical items. Incredible."

msgid "diary_text_quest_621"
msgstr ""
"The Cult of the Moonbeast will go to any lengths to destroy the work of the "
"Elders of Red Moon. They have gone as far as attacking the occupants of the "
"forest, while posing as Elders. Luckily the Wolfmask agents uncovered these "
"disturbing events just in time. Two Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Shamans have been killed."

msgid "diary_text_quest_623"
msgstr ""
"I have killed two Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast Berserkers. Blinded "
"by their faith in the ancient deity the Moonbeast, these traditionalist "
"mahirim who fear progress, and oppose everything the Elders of Red Moon do, "
"are becoming a threat to the mahirim race. The Cult of the Moonbeast must be "
"stopped."

msgid "diary_text_quest_625"
msgstr ""
"Their was no other way to deal with the problem. The forests dwellers were "
"blinded by rage, after the torturing of their kin by the cultists. They "
"could not be reasoned with. Two Forest Prophets, two Ciel Fey Druids and two "
"Ciel Fey Foresters had to be killed, to bring peace back to the forest."

msgid "diary_text_quest_627"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Isinda-dai in {$k13}. The Wolfmasks have "
"chosen me to restore their pride, after their defeat by the hobgoblins in "
"{$l12}. I will receive details of my mission from Isinda-dai."

msgid "diary_text_quest_629"
msgstr ""
"No longer should the Wolfmasks be scared by the memory of the lost battle at "
"Issar Ruins to the Hobgoblins. Seven hobgoblins at Issar Ruins have been "
"killed, and the pride of the Wolfmasks restored."

msgid "diary_text_quest_631"
msgstr ""
"The site of {$k14} has been cleared of the Windlords, and should be ready to "
"be used once more by the Wolfmasks. According to Isinda-dai, it is a site of "
"strategical value, and one to prove useful now in their war against the Cult "
"of the Moon-Beast."

msgid "diary_text_quest_633"
msgstr ""
"The most powerful of the Cult of the Moonbeast, the Moonbeast Ravager is "
"dead! Killing the  Moonbeast Ravager will definitely install doubt and fear "
"into the members of the cult. They will come to see that they are not as "
"strong as they believe they are."

msgid "diary_text_quest_635"
msgstr ""
"I powerful blow has been dealt to the Cult of the Moonbeast. Once one of "
"their bases was discovered, all that was left, was to enter and destroy "
"them. I completed my mission for the Wolfmask, and killed four Moonbeast "
"Officers. A win for the Woflmasks, in their battle against the Cult of the "
"Moonbeast."

msgid "diary_text_quest_637"
msgstr ""
"Before the Circle of Neith could entrust me with one of their major "
"missions, they tested my abilities with a small but important task. I "
"successfully gathered two units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Ghost Spiders."

msgid "diary_text_quest_639"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Avarran-yth, a researcher of the Circle of "
"Neith, to help find an ancient scroll, somewhere hidden in the Nithron city "
"in {$h11}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_64"
msgstr ""
"I have extracted four teeth from the slain goblins, as instructed by William "
"the Councillor. Who would have known that simple teeth can be used for "
"crafting items imbued with magical properties."

msgid "diary_text_quest_641"
msgstr ""
"After killing four of the Jackal Revenants guardians of the Nithron city in "
"{$h11}, Avarran-yth found enough time to continue his search of the ancient "
"scroll."

msgid "diary_text_quest_643"
msgstr ""
"Avarran-yth sent me to gather a Quartz, while he continued his search for "
"the ancient scroll in the Nithron city in {$h11}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_645"
msgstr ""
"Not a scroll, but writing on a wall. Avarran-yth had found his ancient "
"scroll, except for one final piece that was guarded by four Oathbound "
"guardians. After killing the four Oathbound guardians, the last of the text "
"was revealed to me, and the ancient text was complete."

msgid "diary_text_quest_647"
msgstr ""
"A letter containing the ancient writing Avarran-yth and I found in the "
"Nithron city in {$h11}, has been delivered to Celetia the White of the "
"Circle of Neith. Apparently Avarran-yth was unable to read the ancient "
"wittings."

msgid "diary_text_quest_649"
msgstr ""
"I successfully intercepted the Svartvergir in {$h13}, killed six of them, "
"and stopped their march towards Moonclaw. Nobody interferes with the Circle "
"of Neith."

msgid "diary_text_quest_651"
msgstr ""
"The two Vile Horns I delivered to Celetia the White, are the final "
"ingredients need to complete the deciphering of the ancient writing from the "
"Nithron city. Now, we wait."

msgid "diary_text_quest_653"
msgstr ""
"Until the agents of the Circle of Neith discover why the Ogres were "
"approaching Moonclaw, something had to be done. I intercepted the Ogres and "
"killed four Ogre Bullies and two Ogre Bosses, as instructed by Celetia the "
"White."

msgid "diary_text_quest_655"
msgstr ""
"I have found the Moonstaff of Knowledge, the artifact the the Circle of "
"Neith so desires. Holding it, I can see images of Agon's past. It is truly a "
"magnificent artifact."

msgid "diary_text_quest_656"
msgstr ""
"The Moonstaff of Knowledge has been delivered to the Circle of Neith. "
"Celetia the White was very pleased to see the staff with her own eyes. In "
"her own words, a glorious moment for the Circle of Neith."

msgid "diary_text_quest_658"
msgstr ""
"I have cleared some land in {$l24} of the Revenants, so the mages of the "
"Radiant Circle may have room to test and experiment their new spells."

msgid "diary_text_quest_660"
msgstr ""
"I gathered three units of troll blood for Shulazu Nightshade of the Radiant "
"Circle as instructed. According to Shulazu, the trolls blood is one of the "
"ingredients that will be used in the creation of a powerful disease."

msgid "diary_text_quest_662"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Naelah Ghostshard, to assist the Radiant "
"Circle in locating the legendary book of necromancy written by the powerful "
"necromancer Kalruk."

msgid "diary_text_quest_664"
msgstr ""
"I have found Kalruk's book of necromancy, the Book of Greater Necromancy, "
"inside the severii citadel in Fahral. All that remains is to deliver the "
"book to Naelah Ghostshard."

msgid "diary_text_quest_665"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Book of Greater Necromancy to Naelah Ghostshard. It is "
"truly a powerful book. Holding it, one can feel the dark necromantic powers "
"that are locked within it."

msgid "diary_text_quest_667"
msgstr ""
"Naelah Ghostshard seemed to be very annoyed with the trolls in {$m24}, that "
"would not leave her alone to do her work. She asked of me to kill six Trolls "
"and two Troll Shamans, a task I gladly did."

msgid "diary_text_quest_669"
msgstr ""
"As Shulazu Nightshade said, the necromancer has returned. The Book of "
"Greater Necromancy has been delivered to the Radiant Circle. The work of the "
"powerful necromancer Kalruk now belongs to the Alfar."

msgid "diary_text_quest_671"
msgstr ""
"Five manscorpions have been removed from the {$l23} region. The region with "
"its acid lake is very important to the Radiant Circle's work, so outsiders "
"are not welcomed."

msgid "diary_text_quest_673"
msgstr ""
"Shulazu was very pleased to receive the two unit of Nightmare Bile he "
"requested. Apparently the Nightmare Bile will be used for the creation of a "
"powerful staff, the Staff of Rotting Flesh."

msgid "diary_text_quest_675"
msgstr ""
"I have found the tomb of the traitorous necromancer Kalruk, and have removed "
"the necromancer's skull. All that remains is for the skull to be delivered "
"to Shulazu Nightshade in Dun Amsharra."

msgid "diary_text_quest_676"
msgstr ""
"The skull of the traitorous necromancer has been delivered to Shulazu "
"Nightshade. Kalruk has returned to the alfar, and no longer serves the "
"Skeleton Dragon God Cyriacus. This is definitely something Cyriacus will "
"remember for a very long time. Revenge is always sweet."

msgid "diary_text_quest_678"
msgstr ""
"I have proven my worth to the Temple of the God King, after successfully "
"passing the Temple's trail. I entered the Severii city in Sorgom, and killed "
"four Severii in less than an hour as instructed by Nathar Blackorb."

msgid "diary_text_quest_68"
msgstr ""
"The goblins fear of the mercians has definitely grown after the barrage of "
"mana missiles cast against them. Since the goblins fear magic, we must use "
"every trick available to us, in our attempt to expel them from Monkfield."

msgid "diary_text_quest_680"
msgstr ""
"The Temple believes that the forest dwellers near Sorgom lake, are "
"responsible for the human slaves escape. I killed three Centaurs and three "
"Ciel Fey of the forest, to create a diversion for the Temple's agents to "
"move in and gather information."

msgid "diary_text_quest_682"
msgstr ""
"I have report for duty with Kaldahan Deepshadow, a field agent of the Temple "
"of the God King, who is located in Zahnal."

msgid "diary_text_quest_684"
msgstr ""
"I removed the hobgoblin guards from the guardhouse in {$p23}, three "
"Hobgoblin Grunts and one Hobgoblin Veteran, enough for Kaldahan's men to "
"move in and gather information on the hobgoblin village. If the hobgoblins "
"are preparing for an attack, we must be prepared."

msgid "diary_text_quest_686"
msgstr ""
"The Temple of the God King should be able to use the Nithron ruins in "
"Zahnal, now that many of the nithron guardians have been removed. Three "
"Jackal Revenants, three Hawk Revenants and two Oathbound have been removed "
"from the site."

msgid "diary_text_quest_688"
msgstr ""
"I successfully killed five Hobgoblin Grunts, one Hobgoblin Veteran and one "
"Hobgoblin Officer, and ended any plans the hobgoblins had of attacking the "
"Temple of the God King. The hobgoblins are no match for the Alfar!"

msgid "diary_text_quest_690"
msgstr ""
"Kaldahan's report letter has been delivered to Nathar Blackorb, after "
"assisting Kaldahan with the hobgoblins in {$p23} and clearing out the "
"Nithron ruins in {$p22}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_692"
msgstr ""
"Once it was discovered that the Oaklords were the ones that planned the "
"slave's escape, Nathar Blackorb instructed me to kill one of the Oaklords, "
"sending a clear message to the rest, to never again interfere in the "
"Temple's affairs."

msgid "diary_text_quest_696"
msgstr ""
"I completed the test given to me by Eredethil Swiftarrow of the Arrowhead. I "
"managed to destroy four skeletons in less than an hour."

msgid "diary_text_quest_698"
msgstr ""
"The latest Ciel Fey attacks have forced the Arrowhead to adjust their policy "
"regarding the Ciel Fey. I accepted to kill four Ciel Fey, while other "
"Arrowhead agents search for the causes behind the Ciel Fey's violent "
"behavior."

msgid "diary_text_quest_70"
msgstr ""
"Goblins seem to have a great fear of magic. I have complete the strange task "
"of casting twenty mana missiles against the goblins that have surrounded "
"Sandbrook. Hopefully this will remind the goblins that they should "
"definitely fear us humans and our magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_700"
msgstr ""
"I have killed four of the hobgoblins that have fortified themselves into "
"Heneldon, as instructed by Eredethil Swiftarrow of the Arrowhead. The "
"hobgoblins have become a serious threat for the nearby communities."

msgid "diary_text_quest_702"
msgstr ""
"Once it was discovered that the Forest Prophets were the ones behind the "
"Ciel Fey attacks, it was only logical that the Arrowhead would want them "
"removed from the area. I accepted to attack the Forest Prophets and to kill "
"four of them, hoping this would put an end to the Ciel Fey attacks."

msgid "diary_text_quest_704"
msgstr ""
"After the information that was gathered, the Arrowhead decided it was time "
"to strike out at the hobgoblins in {$i20}. Agents had discovered tunnels "
"that led underground to the main hideout. I accepted to partake in the "
"strike, and managed to kill four Hobgoblin Grunts, one Hobgoblin Veteran and "
"one Hobgoblin Officer."

msgid "diary_text_quest_706"
msgstr ""
"I am a true Arrowhead. According to Eredethil Swiftarrow, if one succeed in "
"killing four Beastmen alone, then he or she is considered a true Arrowhead. "
"Luckily for me, there was a Beastman village located not far north of the "
"Arrowhead headquarters."

msgid "diary_text_quest_708"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Seirinna the Mage, of the Arrowhead. I am to "
"assist her solve the mystery of an illness that has been slowly spreading "
"throughout the lands."

msgid "diary_text_quest_710"
msgstr ""
"I entered Siledin's castle in {$j18}, and killed six of Ciel Fey that have "
"taking it over. This was done to create enough fuss, for the Arrowhead "
"agents to enter the castle and to search for any clues regarding the new "
"illness that has stuck the surrounding lands."

msgid "diary_text_quest_712"
msgstr ""
"I have found the Orb of Disease, magically hidden away inside a statue with "
"Siledin's castle. All that remains is to deliver the orb to Seirinna the "
"Mage in Krisathel."

msgid "diary_text_quest_713"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the Orb of Disease to Seirinna the Mage. Seirinna informed "
"me that she will  follow all the instructions written in Siledin's diary, on "
"how to destroy the orb."

msgid "diary_text_quest_715"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered Seirinna's report letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow. Eredethil "
"seemed confident that Seirinna will find a cure for the mysterious illness."

msgid "diary_text_quest_717"
msgstr ""
"I gathered and delivered three units of timeless blood for Aelathil "
"Silverleaf of the Serene Spire in Iriendir."

msgid "diary_text_quest_719"
msgstr ""
"I accepted to kill four of the wild centaurs in {$g16}, in an attempt to "
"stop their rampage, and to sent the rest running into the Serene Spires's "
"ambush. The Serene Spire want to discover the cause of the centaurs "
"irrational behavior."

msgid "diary_text_quest_721"
msgstr ""
"I killed four of the Sadayel near {$f18} lake, so that the researchers of "
"the Serene Spire may study the huge crystal formations near the lake. The "
"Serene Spire suspects that the crystals could be responsible for the magical "
"fluctuations that have been reported throughout Mirendil."

msgid "diary_text_quest_723"
msgstr ""
"From the moment the Serene Spire discovered that the centaurs had been "
"magically infected with madness, all fingers were pointing at the Forest "
"Prophets in Myntharn as the most likely suspects responsible for this "
"madness. I accepted to go to Myntharn, kill four Forest Prophets, and have "
"the agent of the Spire move in and begin their interrogations."

msgid "diary_text_quest_725"
msgstr ""
"I have located the Sacred tree within the ancient lair of the green dragon "
"in {$f16}. The forest prophets were not lying, and the Sacred tree does seem "
"to be ill. Could the illness of the sacred tree be the true cause of the "
"centaurs madness? Is there really a connection between the sylvan creature "
"and the Sacred tree?"

msgid "diary_text_quest_727"
msgstr ""
"I found the Ring of Crystal, in the possession of the undead dwarves in "
"{$e18}. All that remains is the return to ring to Aelathil Silverleaf in "
"Iriendir."

msgid "diary_text_quest_728"
msgstr ""
"Aelathil Silverleaf was relieved to have the Ring of Crystal brought back to "
"the Serene Spire. It looks like she will have to keep a closer eye at her "
"researchers, before allowing them to wander off with items like this, and "
"almost getting themselves killed."

msgid "diary_text_quest_730"
msgstr ""
"Besides all the damage that has been done by the awakening of Firedreamer, "
"the only volcano found in Mirendil, some little good has come out of this "
"too. Lesser Fire Elementals have appeared near the volcano in {$f17}, and I "
"accepted to extract three units of Elemental Cinder from the elementals for "
"the Serene Spire."

msgid "diary_text_quest_732"
msgstr ""
"Six of the Giant Skeletons that have risen at the base of Firedreamer, have "
"been destroyed and put back to rest. Neither I or Aelathil Silverleaf are "
"sure if this is the end of the Giant Skeletons, but at least for now, the "
"region of {$f17} is a little safer."

msgid "diary_text_quest_734"
msgstr ""
"Five beastmen have fallen by my hand, and the agents of the Serene Spire "
"have managed to retrieve the dangerous shard from their village. The powers "
"of the shard are unknown, and the Spire must know discover how the shard was "
"able to caused so much damage."

msgid "diary_text_quest_736"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Red Moon should soon begin their mining operation in {$f13}, "
"now that the Hill Giants of the region have received the Elders message. "
"Four of the Hill Giant Sluggers have been killed, and more are to follow if "
"they continue to interfere with the Elders plans."

msgid "diary_text_quest_737"
msgstr ""
"While punishing the Human Guildmasters in {$l14} for attacking the mahirim "
"patrols, I found a letter in there possession, a letter that contains "
"information regarding specific patrol routes and locations."

msgid "diary_text_quest_738"
msgstr ""
"While punishing the Human Guildmasters in {$l14} for attacking the mahirim "
"patrols, I found a letter in there possession containing vital information "
"regarding mahirm patrol routes and other defensive locations. Symyr-dan the "
"Firm of the Elders of Red Moon was clearly disturbed with the fact that the "
"humans has access to such information."

msgid "diary_text_quest_740"
msgstr ""
"I decided to try out the Elder's troll hunt in Amurranyr, and I succeeded. "
"Three Troll Lords in less than half an hour."

msgid "diary_text_quest_742"
msgstr ""
"Progress is paramount to the Elders of Red Moon. Nothing is to obstruct the "
"progress of the mahirim race, and that applies to the Svartdvergir too. Five "
"Svartdvergir have died by my hand for attacking the mahirim trade routes."

msgid "diary_text_quest_744"
msgstr ""
"I have removed four Night Hags from the Elders old burial grounds. It is "
"unfortunate that the burial site is now haunted by these disgusting "
"creatures. We should not neglect are dead."

msgid "diary_text_quest_746"
msgstr ""
"Hidden in a chest on top of the Lone Tower, I found the lost half of the "
"sacred stone tablet. All that remains is for the broken tablet piece to be "
"delivered to Symyr-dan the Firm in {$h14}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_747"
msgstr ""
"I have delivered the broken tablet piece to Symyr-dan the Firm of the Elders "
"of Ed Moon. As  Symyr-dan himself said, the sacred tablet will be whole "
"again, once more for all Mahirim to read the Words of Amurran."

msgid "diary_text_quest_750"
msgstr ""
"The ancient hunting grounds will always be sacred to the mahirim. It is part "
"of their history, and part of their way of live. I accepted to clear the "
"hunting grounds in {$g14}, of the many undead that now haunt them. I "
"destroyed two Skeletons, two Zombies and one Gravelord, as requested by "
"Symyr-dan the Firm of the Elders of Red Moon."

msgid "diary_text_quest_752"
msgstr ""
"I have gathered two quartz from the crogs in {$g13}, as instructed by Symyr-"
"dan the Firm. The quartz will be sent to the Circle of Neith, to aid the "
"spellcasters with their experiments and research in the art of magic."

msgid "diary_text_quest_754"
msgstr ""
"First mission for the Harn Mandean, and successful. Two of the Night Hags "
"that were roaming near the Harn Mandean's headquarters in Dulgana has been "
"killed, as instructed by Aeshanta Darkspire."

msgid "diary_text_quest_756"
msgstr ""
"The Ogres of {$l21} have received  Aeshanta Darkspire's message. Stay away "
"from the Harn Mandean patrols, or many more Ogres will die."

msgid "diary_text_quest_758"
msgstr ""
"I have reported for duty with Lashur Wraithglider, a Harn Mandean field "
"agent. The Severii could be up to something."

msgid "diary_text_quest_760"
msgstr ""
"I gathered enough information about the Severii as Lashur Wraithglider "
"instructed me, after battling and destroying six of the undead servants of "
"Cyriacus."

msgid "diary_text_quest_762"
msgstr ""
"The Holy Symbol of Melek has been found within the Severii stronghold in "
"{$o21}, together with a detailed map Shoal."

msgid "diary_text_quest_763"
msgstr ""
"The lost Holy Symbol of Melek together with a detailed map of Shoal that "
"were found in the Severii city in {$o21}, have been delivered to Lashur "
"Wraithglider."

msgid "diary_text_quest_765"
msgstr ""
"I have killed enough Severii upon the isle dedicated to their god Cyriakos "
"in {$n21}, to create the illusion of an attack, to buy enough time for the "
"Harn Mandean to search for the traitor among their ranks, and to prepare for "
"the real attack."

msgid "diary_text_quest_767"
msgstr ""
"While the Severii have fallen for the fake attack, I returned to the Harn "
"Mandean headquarters and informed  Aeshanta Darkspire about the possible "
"traitor among the Harn Mandean ranks, and about the map of Shoal found in "
"within the Severii stronghold."

msgid "diary_text_quest_769"
msgstr ""
"The Ogres in {$l21} had it coming, especially when a group of Hill Giants "
"joined them. Aeshanta demanded two Hill Giant Sluggers and four Ogre Bosses "
"to be killed. Message delivered."

msgid "diary_text_quest_771"
msgstr ""
"In order for the Radiant Circle to completed the creation of a powerful "
"disease, all factions were asked to gather various ingredients. Three units "
"of Timeless Blood were requested from the Harn Mandean, which I ended up "
"gathering."

msgid "diary_text_quest_773"
msgstr ""
"A military operation against the Severii has begun, and the Harn Mandean are "
"part of it. I successfully executed the orders given to me by Aeshanta "
"Darkspire, which were to destroy seven Severii and one Gravelord."

msgid "diary_text_quest_781"
msgstr ""
"I killed four gnolls as requested by Caradial Elmheart of the Emerald "
"Throne. The gnolls had been using the ruins along the banks of the river "
"Sirith, as a base for launching raids against the trading vessels. This was "
"something the Elflords would not tolerate."

msgid "diary_text_quest_782"
msgstr ""
"Five Akathars have been removed from the lands of one of the Elflords in "
"{$f19}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_783"
msgstr ""
"I destroyed four of the revenants guarding the Nithron ruins in {$g20}. "
"Hopefully this will create enough time for the scholars of the Emerald "
"Throne, to explore the Nithron ruins."

msgid "diary_text_quest_784"
msgstr ""
"Five forest prophets who were interfering with the construction of the new "
"trading port along the northern banks of the river Sirith, had to die. The "
"Elflords would not have the anybody interfering with their plans."

msgid "diary_text_quest_785"
msgstr ""
"I have found the Orb of Mirdain History, an ancient mirdain artifact capable "
"of recording historical events of the past. All that remains is to deliver "
"the orb to Caradial Elmheart."

msgid "diary_text_quest_786"
msgstr ""
"The Orb of Mirdain History has been delivered to the Emerald Throne. "
"Caradial Elmheart could not believe his eyes, while holding the ancient "
"mirdain artifact in his hands."

msgid "diary_text_quest_787"
msgstr ""
"Three Bonecrew Mutineers and one Bonecrew Mariner, have been removed from "
"the island at the mouth of the river Sirith. These thieving undead pirates, "
"have created enough problems for the Emerald Throne, with the attacks upon "
"the merchants whips."

msgid "diary_text_quest_788"
msgstr ""
"I have found the second orb of history, the Orb of Mirendil's History. All "
"that remains is to bring it to Caradial Elmheart in Imathir."

msgid "diary_text_quest_789"
msgstr ""
"The Orb of Mirendil's History has been delivered to the Emerald Throne. "
"Caradial Elmheart was pleased that the Emerald Throne has both of the orbs "
"of history. Its scholars may now begin to acquire information about what "
"truly lead to the darkest years in mirdain history."

msgid "diary_text_quest_790"
msgstr ""
"After killing two Raven Standard Grunts and one Raven Standard Veteran, I "
"returned to Imathir, where I gave a full report of my assessment of the "
"hobgoblins strengths to to Caradial Elmheart of the Emerald Throne. Caradial "
"Elmheart seemed very trouble with the fact, that the Raven Standard Army "
"might have returned."

msgid "diary_text_quest_799"
msgstr ""
"I have help the Longclaw by removing three Doom Spiders from the new mining "
"site. Now the mining operations may begin."

msgid "diary_text_quest_800"
msgstr ""
"The Gnolls should will create any more problems for the Longclaw and their "
"new mining site. I killing four Gnolls and sent a clear message to the rest. "
"Stay away from the Longclaw."

msgid "diary_text_quest_801"
msgstr ""
"The Longclaw's caravans should begin traveling once again along the northern "
"trade routes. I have assisted the Longclaw by removing four Ogre Bullies and "
"two Ogre Bosses, that had been attacking the northern trade routes in {$k10}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_802"
msgstr ""
"I have successfully killed four Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Berserkers as instructed by  Yaleria-Sai the Able, and aided the Elders in "
"the fight against the Cult of the Moon-Beast. The days of the Cult of the "
"Moon-Beast are numbered."

msgid "diary_text_quest_803"
msgstr ""
"I have killed six of the Bonecrew Mutineers that occupy the mahirim fishing "
"village of Ebonyth, and assisted the Longclaw in not only reclaiming it, but "
"also extracting revenge for those brave villagers that died alone fighting."

msgid "diary_text_quest_804"
msgstr ""
"Four Should Knight have been removed from the ancient ruin site in "
"Yithmoore. A task with a double purpose. One, the Circle of Neith would like "
"to explore the ruins, and two, the Longclaw wish to start mining for ore. A "
"job well done."

msgid "diary_text_quest_805"
msgstr ""
"I harvest two Tribal Lifeforce from the Menhir Custodians in Yithmoore, as "
"requested by Yaleria-Sai. These will be sent off to the Elders of Red Moon, "
"to discover what these strange creatures are, and why they are guarding "
"these strange ancients sites."

msgid "diary_text_quest_806"
msgstr ""
"Five Hobgoblin Veterans and two Hobgoblin Officers have been removed from "
"the island of Fangwall. Now the Longclaw can build their first camp on the "
"island, one of many on their way to exploring the ice continent of Niflheim."

msgid "diary_text_quest_815"
msgstr ""
"I have encountered the Raven Standard hobgoblins, and successfully killed "
"three of them. According to the Elders of Red Moon, somebody is reassembling "
"the legendary Raven Standard Army after hundreds of years. Who and why "
"remains a mystery."

msgid "diary_text_quest_817"
msgstr ""
"I completed my first mission for the mysterious Shadow Salient. Four "
"manscorpions have been removed from the connecting islands in Niasha."

msgid "diary_text_quest_818"
msgstr ""
"I gathered an elemental quartz for Dekazu Fearweaver of the Shadow Salient. "
"The quartz is supposed to be used in the ritual of the fire, which will be "
"conducted by the Shadow Masters."

msgid "diary_text_quest_819"
msgstr ""
"I have destroyed five of the undead dwarves that have mysteriously risen "
"within the ancient dwarven city of Fire's Edge. Now the Shadow Salient must "
"discover why and how the dwarves have risen after hundreds of years."

msgid "diary_text_quest_820"
msgstr ""
"I have located the strange artifact that was hidden inside the shrine of the "
"unknown god in the city of Fire's Edge. All that remains is for the artifact "
"to be delivered to Dekazu Fearweaver in Niasha."

msgid "diary_text_quest_821"
msgstr ""
"I handed the strange artifact of the unknown god that I located in Fire's "
"Edge, to Dekazu Fearweaver. Now it is up to the Shadow Salient and the "
"Shadow Masters to discover if this artifact is responsible for the rising of "
"the undead dwarves, and who is this new unknown god."

msgid "diary_text_quest_822"
msgstr ""
"I have found Durganon's Flame, the legendary dwarven artifact that was "
"hidden within the Chamber of Fire in mount {$o25}."

msgid "diary_text_quest_823"
msgstr ""
"The dwarven artifact known as Durganon's Flame, has been delivered to Dekazu "
"Fearweaver in Niasha. With this artifact, the blacksmiths of the Shadow "
"Salient should be able to craft superior weapon similar to those of the "
"legendary dwarven blacksmith Durganon."

msgid "end_text_quest_20000"
msgstr ""
"Great work, I will inform our farmers that they can head back out.  Please "
"take this gold and cooking supplies as compensation for your help."

msgid "end_text_quest_20001"
msgstr ""
"Well done, that should slow them down!  While you were fighting the Goblins "
"a shipment of raw materials from Sandbrook was able to sneak by. Here you go!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20002"
msgstr ""
"Congratulations. You have now earned the title of The Limber. By activating "
"this title, you will gain a small bonus to your dexterity. Well done."

msgid "end_text_quest_20003"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#!  I'm Simeon the Merchant, purveyor of fine trade goods here in "
"Sanguine. Thank you for bringing these raw materials in this troubling time, "
"I will see that they are distributed effectively.  News of the Goblin raid "
"and your help has already reached me.  Since, you've proven yourself useful, "
"naturally I have more for you to do!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20004"
msgstr ""
"Good work.  You have demonstrated that you are at least capable of basic "
"Cooking tasks. Take this Gold and some extra Wheat I had.  Hold on to that "
"till you really learn how to cook."

msgid "end_text_quest_20005"
msgstr "What a fine specimen!  Thank you."

msgid "end_text_quest_20006"
msgstr ""
"Can I help you?  Oh, another passerby who got hooked into some work by Allan "
"and Simeon.  Well, since you are here, I have some things you could do.  "
"Take these raw materials, you're gonna need them."

msgid "end_text_quest_20007"
msgstr ""
"Everything looks to be in order here.  Ingots are well shaped, the Wood "
"hasn't splintered, and the Leather isn't ruined.  Good job."

msgid "end_text_quest_20008"
msgstr ""
"Excellent work apprentice!  If I didn't know any better I would say these "
"were made by someone who knew what they were doing..."

msgid "end_text_quest_2001"
msgstr "Greetings."

msgid "end_text_quest_20014"
msgstr ""
"Thank you!  These well help a lot with all the hungry troops we have coming "
"back in from the field."

msgid "end_text_quest_20015"
msgstr ""
"Congratulations. You have now earned the title of The Quick. By activating "
"this title, you will gain a small bonus to your quickness. Well done."

msgid "end_text_quest_20016"
msgstr ""
"Now that was some good hard work!  You've definitely earned this title, as "
"well as the enchanted badge."

msgid "end_text_quest_20017"
msgstr ""
"What is that smell?  Oh sorry didn't see you there...  You cleared out those "
"rodents from the sewer?  Well done! Here's what I can give you for the "
"work.  What, you wanted gold?  Too bad!. Talaod will continue sending groups "
"to sweep the sewers, and I will keep paying them with whatever I can.  Funny "
"how that works..."

msgid "end_text_quest_20018"
msgstr ""
"Do you mind!?  You just got sewer muck all over my carpet!  Oh Talaod sent "
"you?  Ah yes, the corpseflesh I needed!  Thank you...and what was that you "
"said about a robed necromancer?  Very interesting...Take these items, you "
"can help me with something else..."

msgid "end_text_quest_20019"
msgstr "Feels sturdy enough!  Here, take this as payment."

msgid "end_text_quest_2002"
msgstr ""
"I see you have returned successful. The Gnolls are no match for us. Here is "
"a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_20020"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for these potions, I'm sure the city guards will appreciate it "
"next time there is a brawl! Here is some payment to cover your time and "
"effort."

msgid "end_text_quest_20021"
msgstr ""
"Ah, another fine student coming from Jonn the Mage with an an enchantment "
"captured in a gem.  Thank you! Maintaining Sanguine's weapon stockpile is "
"one of my responsibilities, and I always try to keep them good and Keen!  "
"Take this as a reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20022"
msgstr ""
"Great work!  I really hate those pesky little rodent looking creatures, "
"always disrupting my shipments from Sandbrook.  Your reward is well deserved!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20023"
msgstr ""
"Yes?  Oh right, the zombie killing task I gave you for that title badge.  "
"Well good work!  Can never have too many people re-killing zombies! Here you "
"go."

msgid "end_text_quest_20024"
msgstr ""
"Good work! You have done the people of Sanguine a service on this day, and I "
"bestow upon you the title of The Brawny, and give you this badge of service."

msgid "end_text_quest_20025"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for your help traveler!  I was starting to get worried that these "
"Goblins would effectively block our route to Sanguine."

msgid "end_text_quest_20026"
msgstr ""
"Jonn the Mage sent you!?  Perfect timing.  I had just used my last "
"enchantment on a mace for some Militiamen.  That Jonn sure is on top of "
"things...I could probably stand to enchant some staves...Sorry, was there "
"something else?  Oh yes, your reward.  Here, take this."

msgid "end_text_quest_20027"
msgstr ""
"Fresh Armor?  Thank Auros!  I've been doing my best patching the boys up and "
"sending them back out in piecemeal armor, but this will help out a ton.  "
"Take this as compensation."

msgid "end_text_quest_20028"
msgstr ""
"These are perfect for our Rangers.  Thank you!  They prefer to wear light "
"armor as they mainly focus on fighting with bows and magic.  Here is your "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20029"
msgstr ""
"What great quality!  These Rapiers will skewer these pesky Goblins with "
"ease.  Thank you!  Please take this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20030"
msgstr ""
"Thank you!  I will make sure our next batch of recruits gets one of these "
"great staves to start working on their magic skills.  Please take this."

msgid "end_text_quest_20031"
msgstr ""
"You have no idea how badly we needed these.  The boys keep coming back from "
"the field with nasty gashes from those Goblin Axes, and I was running out of "
"healing potions to help!  Here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20032"
msgstr ""
"Raw materials!  Thank Auros.  I'll get these distributed to our crafters.  "
"Please take this as a reward, and see if our craftsman inside need help "
"using these materials."

msgid "end_text_quest_20033"
msgstr ""
"I could hear the Mana Missiles smashing into those greenskins from all the "
"way back here.  Good work!  Here take this upgraded Goblin staff and some "
"armor I had left over from a trade deal."

msgid "end_text_quest_20034"
msgstr ""
"Great work!  The boys were all coming back in telling of Goblins that looked "
"like right proper pin cushions! Nothing better than some Goblin-ke-babs to "
"lighten the mood."

msgid "end_text_quest_20035"
msgstr ""
"You have killed 5 Goblin Shamans, but feel an evil aura pulsating from the "
"large shrine in the back of the village. Destroy it."

msgid "end_text_quest_20036"
msgstr ""
"The Shrine has been destroyed and the Goblins pause for a second, as if they "
"are unsure what to do.  Kill the Cultists so they can't re-establish control "
"over these Goblins."

msgid "end_text_quest_20037"
msgstr ""
"Malaut Acolytes built a dark altar that was influencing the Goblins?!  I "
"would never have thought this Goblin raid had such sinister roots...  Please "
"take this reward.  Since Mercian stockpiles are low on materials, we have "
"been instructed to pay adventurers in Platinum when possible.  This is a "
"valuable resource that can be sold quite easily on the Markets at Sanguine."

msgid "end_text_quest_20038"
msgstr ""
"You killed the Zombies outside the tunnel, but you hear the rattling of "
"bones from up the mountain...There are more undead."

msgid "end_text_quest_20039"
msgstr ""
"You killed the Skeletons, but see that Malaut Cultists are the cause of this "
"attrocity at the mine."

msgid "end_text_quest_2004"
msgstr ""
"Well done. We could have easily killed all the humans, but I suspect the the "
"authorities of {$j12} have other plans for them. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20040"
msgstr ""
"It is becoming all too clear that the demi-god Malaut has dark designs for "
"this region.  Thank you for finding the source of the evil at the mine, and "
"putting the souls of our miners to rest."

msgid "end_text_quest_20041"
msgstr ""
"Good work!  Nothing feels as solid in your hands as a well crafted "
"Greataxe.  Bet this one would split a Goblin head like a melon!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20042"
msgstr ""
"Perfect!  These should help augment the Militia's gear nicely.  Here is your "
"payment."

msgid "end_text_quest_20043"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful work!  No more sore ankles for the militia!  Please take this as "
"payment."

msgid "end_text_quest_20044"
msgstr ""
"There we go.  I imagine it will be a lot easier to wave those magic staves "
"around when they don't have heavy chainmail on their arms!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20045"
msgstr ""
"Perfect!  Hopefully those novice mages will be careful enough with these so "
"they last for awhile.  Someone really needs to teach them that these staves "
"are not just blunt weapons to be swung around!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20046"
msgstr ""
"So how did it go?  I hope you utilized the peircing vulnerability by "
"following up on the spell with some archery attacks from a distance.  "
"Lowering your targets resistances is one of the most important roles of "
"magic in our world."

msgid "end_text_quest_20047"
msgstr ""
"We appreciate your help with these unrelenting attacks on our city.  Your "
"brave attack against the Maualt camps to the West gave our scouts precious "
"time to go out and gather more information about what is going on."

msgid "end_text_quest_20048"
msgstr ""
"That was quite a performance you put on down there.  I was watching from the "
"cliffs, and the way you hacked those Goblins apart was absolute artistry!  "
"You've earned this!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20049"
msgstr ""
"Thank you.  I feel much better knowing those people aren't in anguish "
"anymore, and those horrible Malaut followers have been punished."

msgid "end_text_quest_2005"
msgstr "Greetings. You have news from Isenda. I thank you."

msgid "end_text_quest_20050"
msgstr ""
"Well I think that is all we will be seeing in terms of organized attacks "
"coming out of Lainstone for awhile now.  I took out a few stragglers, one of "
"whom mentioned something about an \"Archduke Stabby\", and some \"Count\" or "
"something who were going to get us.  Could just be crazy talk, but you never "
"know."

msgid "end_text_quest_20051"
msgstr ""
"I must say, what you have done for our city is absolutely amazing.  We will "
"forever be in your debt.  I am very concerned about what Arduin said "
"regarding two apparent leaders who escapted.  This Goblin who gave himself "
"the title of \"Archduke\", and that there appears to be another leader, this "
"mysterious \"Count\"."

msgid "end_text_quest_20052"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Eleanor Wilde.  It looks like these Mercian "
"Outlaws killed her.  Their trail leads West."

msgid "end_text_quest_20053"
msgstr ""
"You killed some Outlaws, but you hear what sounds like chanting from deeper "
"in the castle.  You should investigate."

msgid "end_text_quest_20054"
msgstr ""
"You killed a large number of Malaut Cultists, but hear angry yelling and "
"what sounds like a Goblin barking something from the turret nearby."

msgid "end_text_quest_20055"
msgstr ""
"Eleanor dead? Count Grayvale a monster and a traitor?  Had this news come "
"from anyone else, I would not believe it.  I thank you for all you have "
"done.  However, I fear this is a dark tiding of things to come.  We do not "
"know how far Malaut's corruption extends throughout Mercian society.  Though "
"we must find out."

msgid "end_text_quest_20056"
msgstr ""
"That is a truly remarkable tale, and it seems like you are owed much thanks "
"by the people of our lands.  You have come a long way in a very short time."
"\r\n"
"  \r\n"
"  \rI'm afraid there is no need to bring this to the King though.  Robert IV "
"is a far-cry from our founder John Malregard.  Many insiders call him "
"\"Robbie the Whale\" due to his poor eating habbits, and we generally rely "
"on his wife, Queen Morgaine, to oversee important matters.  I'll reach out "
"to her courtiers and inform them of the situation."

msgid "end_text_quest_20057"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. You truly do deserve the title of The Agile. Here, accept "
"your well earned reward, and wear you achievement badge with pride."

msgid "end_text_quest_20058"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. You have successfully killed 100 Raptors, and earned the title of "
"The Dextrous."

msgid "end_text_quest_20059"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. You truly do deserve the title of The Hardy. Here, accept "
"your well earned reward, and wear you achievement title with pride."

msgid "end_text_quest_20060"
msgstr ""
"Incredible. You actually have managed to kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords, "
"and claim the title of The Tough for yourself. Well done."

msgid "end_text_quest_20061"
msgstr ""
"That was some solid magery!  Elementals can really be very deadly creatures, "
"and fighting them helps hone your own mastery over the elements."

msgid "end_text_quest_20062"
msgstr ""
"I knew you were special from the moment you walked into this tower.  Amazing "
"work!  You are well on your way to becoming a master mage in your own "
"right.  The title of The Smart is yours."

msgid "end_text_quest_20063"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. You truly do deserve the title of The Muscular. Here, accept "
"your well earned reward, and wear you achievement badge and title with pride."

msgid "end_text_quest_20064"
msgstr ""
"That was an impressive feat #PlayerName#!  Not only have you definitely "
"earned your badge upgrade and title of The Strong, you have done a service "
"to all free people of Agon by killing so many of the Raven Standards."

msgid "end_text_quest_20065"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. You truly do deserve the title of The Knowledgeable. Here, "
"accept your well earned reward, and wear you achievement title with pride."

msgid "end_text_quest_20066"
msgstr ""
"Great work.  Mastery over crafting skills puts you in a very strong position "
"here in Sanguine.  Your abilities will be both desired by clans fighting for "
"power, and by merchants looking to make coin."

msgid "end_text_quest_20067"
msgstr ""
"I would make some bad joke about birds in the hand worth two in the bush, "
"but I imagine you are quite tired of birds at the moment!  Good work, you "
"earned this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20068"
msgstr ""
"Amazing! I really didn't know whether or not you would be coming back from "
"this task.  Eodrin are nasty buggers!  Well, here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20069"
msgstr ""
"Did you notice how the spell knocks enemies up a bit?  Stronger spells you "
"will learn later do that even more!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20070"
msgstr ""
"Smells delicious!  Did you use any special seasonings?  Well, no matter.  "
"The troops will gobble these up!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20071"
msgstr "Solid work!  Here you go."

msgid "end_text_quest_20072"
msgstr ""
"Good work.  Even though you can already cast some spells in the Greater "
"Magic school, it is important to keep studying Lesser Magic so you can cast "
"the more powerful spells in that school."

msgid "end_text_quest_20073"
msgstr ""
"These will go along way to making sure our soldiers all stay battle-ready in "
"the days coming."

msgid "end_text_quest_20074"
msgstr "These have a good heft to them, and feel solid as steel!  Great work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20076"
msgstr ""
"Hopefully you were able to use the spell in combat so you could really see "
"how big of a difference it makes.  You will be using that spell for years to "
"come, trust me!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20077"
msgstr "The quality of these looks great!  Thank you for delivering them."

msgid "end_text_quest_20079"
msgstr ""
"Smells great!  Let me package them up so they will still be fresh when you "
"reach Sanguine."

msgid "end_text_quest_20081"
msgstr ""
"Look sturdy enough, and all the seams appear to be well stitched.  Good work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20083"
msgstr ""
"Let me give them a swirl or two to look at the coloration...Not bad!  Let me "
"crate these up for you."

msgid "end_text_quest_20085"
msgstr ""
"Nice work!  Always an ugly business extracting the teeth, but the end result "
"should fetch a nice price!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20087"
msgstr ""
"I can feel the power in these humming nicely.  Just what I would expect of "
"an enchantment of this level."

msgid "end_text_quest_20089"
msgstr "These have a good heft to them, and feel solid as steel!  Great work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20091"
msgstr ""
"Now that was some solid chopping!  Good work, you'll be an Axe master before "
"you know it."

msgid "end_text_quest_20092"
msgstr ""
"Good thumping out there!  Bet there are some sore heads in your wake..."

msgid "end_text_quest_20093"
msgstr "Slice and Dice!  Great job swordsman in training."

msgid "end_text_quest_20094"
msgstr "Solid bladework trainee.  There is hope for you yet!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20095"
msgstr "Wow, I could hear those bones breaking!  Good job."

msgid "end_text_quest_20096"
msgstr "Is that intestines on your shoes?  Well good work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20097"
msgstr "You are covered in blood...Cool!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20098"
msgstr "You look exhausted.  Polearms are heavy aren't they!  Good job though."

msgid "end_text_quest_20099"
msgstr "Ah the sweet smell of burning flesh.  Good work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20100"
msgstr "Electrifying!  Solid zapping out there apprentice."

msgid "end_text_quest_20101"
msgstr "Some may say you have a...CAUSTIC tongue.  Get it?"

msgid "end_text_quest_20102"
msgstr "Well you really gave them the...COLD shoulder.  Get it?"

msgid "end_text_quest_20103"
msgstr ""
"That should help make the roads a bit safer.  Thank you, here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_20104"
msgstr ""
"Well I bet you made a lot of monsters bleed with all that needling.  Good "
"work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_20105"
msgstr "That should keep the roads clear for a bit, thank you!"

msgid "end_text_quest_2011"
msgstr "Welcome."

msgid "end_text_quest_2012"
msgstr ""
"A job well done. We need to keep the hivekin numbers under control. Here is "
"a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2013"
msgstr ""
"Well done, indeed. These ingredients will be used in the creation of "
"weapons. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2014"
msgstr ""
"You have done well. I shall prepare a report to be sent off to the Wolfmasks."

msgid "end_text_quest_2015"
msgstr "Welcome. A message from Isinda-Dai. Thank you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2021"
msgstr ""
"Troll slaying you say! We also have kobolds here too. Yes, we will enjoy "
"this."

msgid "end_text_quest_2022"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. I can see with your help, we will definitely succeed in clearing "
"the region of these pests."

msgid "end_text_quest_2023"
msgstr ""
"Yes. Killing those trolls and their nasty little kobold friends must have "
"felt good. Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2024"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. This blood will be put in good use, in the making of magical "
"items. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2025"
msgstr "Yes? I see. A message from Aurmon the Brave. Thank you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2031"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. I am sure with time, we will destroy all these undead. Accept "
"this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2032"
msgstr ""
"Excellent, you have done well. We will continue our search for the source "
"behind the undead. Here is a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2033"
msgstr ""
"Well done. At least there is one thing the zombies can do for us, and that "
"is providing us with ingredients for enchantments. Please, accept this "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2035"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Silverleaf Aelathil of the Serene Spire. I see you have "
"brought us a report letter  regarding the recent outbreak in the {$g19}. "
"Thank you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2041"
msgstr "Welcome. You are here to help with the kobold infestation. Wonderful."

msgid "end_text_quest_2042"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. It looks like we will be able to slowly get rid of the kobolds. "
"Please, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2043"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. The last thing we need is trolls interfering with our work. "
"Accept this reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2044"
msgstr ""
"You've managed to collect the Timeless Blood I asked for. Thank you very "
"much. Please accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2045"
msgstr ""
"Yes? A message you say, from Lysandir about the kobold infestation. "
"Excellent. Thank you for delivering this to us."

msgid "end_text_quest_2051"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Larwain Crystaldew. I have been assigned here to gather "
"information on these ork visitor."

msgid "end_text_quest_2052"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. It seems that they are not as organize as I thought. Here is a "
"reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2053"
msgstr ""
"I thank you. I could not have done this myself. Please, accept this reward "
"for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2055"
msgstr ""
"So, these orks pose no threat what so ever. This is wonderful news. Thank "
"you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2056"
msgstr ""
"Yes. You have confronted the Ghoul Devour you say. Excellent. We are "
"gathering all the information we can on all undead. Here, accept this reward "
"for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2063"
msgstr "From Onghral you say, to help with the Hivekin. Very well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2064"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. I see that the hivekin posed not problem for you. Here, accept "
"this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2065"
msgstr ""
"Well done, indeed. These claws will be put to good use. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2066"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. You have delivered a critical blow to the core of the hivekin. "
"Yes, you deserve this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2067"
msgstr ""
"This is very good news. So, the hivekin are nothing to worry about. I will "
"send a report to the authorities at the Shoal. Once more, you have performed "
"well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2068"
msgstr ""
"Yes. A gift from my dear friend Taelis. How wonderful that he has thought of "
"us."

msgid "end_text_quest_2075"
msgstr ""
"Greetings. So, you have been chosen to assist us with the Harn Mandean's "
"request. Very well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2076"
msgstr ""
"What chance have these pathetic weak creatures of surviving in Nagast? None! "
"You have done well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2077"
msgstr ""
"Good work. I will prepare my report of the gnolls right away. Here is your "
"well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2078"
msgstr ""
"No very impressive as a weapons, but still do manage to deliver some amount "
"of damage. Here is a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2079"
msgstr "You have made contact with Nirgash the Councillor."

msgid "end_text_quest_208"
msgstr "Not bad. Here's the reward I promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2080"
msgstr ""
"A report from Nirgash of Deep Yishku. Yes, I have been expecting this. You "
"have done well delivering this to us. Here is a little something for your "
"efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2088"
msgstr ""
"Greetings. So, you have been assigned here to assist me. Very well then."

msgid "end_text_quest_2089"
msgstr ""
"You have done well. Still many skeleton remain, but it is a start. Here, "
"accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2090"
msgstr "Excellent. Here is a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2091"
msgstr ""
"Amazing. You've managed to destroy the Bone Knights. You definitely have "
"earned this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2092"
msgstr "Greetings. Ah, the report from the mines. You have done well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2098"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Dis Fatespinner. It seems we might have an undead outbreak in "
"the area."

msgid "end_text_quest_2099"
msgstr ""
"Good work. You are proving to be quite useful. I will start analyzing the "
"sample very soon. Please, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_210"
msgstr "Thank you. Here is a reward for bringing back the axes."

msgid "end_text_quest_2100"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. We must do our best to rid the lands of these undead. Here is a "
"reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2101"
msgstr ""
"So, you have managed to destroy the strongest of these undead. I am "
"impressed. It would seem that these undead will not pose a great threat "
"after all. You have done well. Accept this reward for all you have done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2102"
msgstr "A report from Dis Fatespinner. I thank you for delivering it to me."

msgid "end_text_quest_2108"
msgstr "It is time to reclaim the mines. I am glad you are here to help."

msgid "end_text_quest_2109"
msgstr "Excellent. Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2110"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. At this rate, we will have the kobolds removed from the "
"mines very soon."

msgid "end_text_quest_2112"
msgstr "Excellent, you found it. Here, please accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2113"
msgstr ""
"The Horn of the Five. This is most pleasant news. I thank you for finding it "
"and delivering it to us. Please, do accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2119"
msgstr "Welcome. I am Magnus Forkbeard. Are you ready to do a bit of slaying?"

msgid "end_text_quest_212"
msgstr "Ah good, more stone for the Small Stair. Here is a small reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2120"
msgstr ""
"Good work. With heroes like you, we will have the kobolds fleeing in no time."

msgid "end_text_quest_2121"
msgstr ""
"Ha! Is that all they are worth. Nothing. We have nothing to fear from them. "
"Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2122"
msgstr ""
"That's what i like to see. The blood of my enemy. Well done. Here is a "
"reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2123"
msgstr ""
"A report from Magnus Forkbeard about the trolls situation within the {$p10} "
"region. I thank you for delivering this report to us."

msgid "end_text_quest_2129"
msgstr "Yes? Ah, I see! Troll Blood. You have done well. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2130"
msgstr ""
"You return victorious and with the information we seek. It was as we "
"suspected. I will pass this information to my superiors. You have done well. "
"Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2132"
msgstr ""
"A report from Stranglar Bloodaks. You have done well delivering this to us."

msgid "end_text_quest_2133"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. You are proving to be most useful. Accept this reward for your "
"efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2139"
msgstr "Greeting, I am Ugruk Elfstabber."

msgid "end_text_quest_214"
msgstr "Ah, fresh fuel for the pyres. Here is the reward I promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2140"
msgstr ""
"Let this be a lesson to all who would turn against the might of the orks. "
"You have done well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2141"
msgstr ""
"Well done. The hivekin are a plague. If we hadn't acted now, very soon this "
"area would be filled with the disgusting hivekin. Yes, you have earned this "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2142"
msgstr ""
"You've managed to storm into the enemy's headquarters, slaughter the "
"leaders, and return to fight another day. I am impressed. Here, accept this "
"reward. You have done well."

msgid "end_text_quest_2143"
msgstr "Excellent. I see the bandit orks have been dealt with."

msgid "end_text_quest_2149"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am  Amhard Blackfists. If you are here to participate in the "
"troll slaughter, or any other slaughter, you have come to the right place."

msgid "end_text_quest_2150"
msgstr ""
"Yes, wonderful. There is nothing like a bit of troll slaughtering to make "
"your day. I only wish there were more trolls around."

msgid "end_text_quest_2151"
msgstr ""
"You have done well. Soon all of the kobolds will be chained and put to work. "
"Here is a reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2152"
msgstr ""
"Yes! That what I like to see. You have participated in the troll slaughter, "
"and also returned with the blood of our enemies. Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2153"
msgstr ""
"And you are? Yes, you will do just fine. I am Bigork Blacktoungue and you "
"are now in the domain of the Dragonbound."

msgid "end_text_quest_216"
msgstr "Here is the reward that I promised you for the mandrakes."

msgid "end_text_quest_2163"
msgstr ""
"Here is the reward for your valiant efforts on behalf of the citizens of "
"Heart of Eanna."

msgid "end_text_quest_2164"
msgstr ""
"Ah, the goblin axes. Thank you very much, #PlayerName# . Here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2165"
msgstr ""
"Thank you, #PlayerName#. Hopefully, we'll be able to use these resources to "
"safeguard the trade which is our lifeblood."

msgid "end_text_quest_2166"
msgstr "Thank You, #PlayerName# , for helping us protect our town."

msgid "end_text_quest_2167"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, more of our warriors will fight under the protection "
"of a Magic Shield."

msgid "end_text_quest_2168"
msgstr ""
"These teeth will be very useful to our enchanters, who are busy creating "
"magical items which will be used in the defense of our trade routes."

msgid "end_text_quest_2169"
msgstr "Thank you for giving the goblins that reminder."

msgid "end_text_quest_2177"
msgstr ""
"Well done. However, there is one more test that you must face in order to be "
"deemed worthy of our trust."

msgid "end_text_quest_2178"
msgstr ""
"You ventured into the dragon's caves and emerged victorious. Well done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2179"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Leengate. As you may have heard, this port suffers at the hands "
"of a particularly fierce band of pirates. We are thankful for any help in "
"fighting this threat to our village and to Dvergheim's northern trade."

msgid "end_text_quest_218"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for collecting those teeth for me. Here is the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_2180"
msgstr ""
"Well done. There can be no mercy for those who partake of Sahul's taint."

msgid "end_text_quest_2181"
msgstr ""
"This vile matter will be destroyed in a ritual of cleansing. Thank you for "
"dealing so thoroughly with the svartdvergir threat to this region."

msgid "end_text_quest_2182"
msgstr ""
"This is excellent news. Leengate is vital to Dvergheim's northern trade."

msgid "end_text_quest_2184"
msgstr ""
"The Lion Deformed is an ancient symbol of Ur-Khamset, an immortal tyrant "
"whose long-sleeping hordes recently rose from the sands and laid waste to "
"the continent of Rubaiyat. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir will investigate why a structure bearing Ur-Khamset's "
"symbol has appeared from nothing, in the middle of Dvergheim."

msgid "end_text_quest_2185"
msgstr "Well done. Here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2186"
msgstr "Well done. Here is your reward for bringing me the Dull Sparkstone."

msgid "end_text_quest_2187"
msgstr "Well done. Perhaps now the Order's first knights can rest in peace."

msgid "end_text_quest_2188"
msgstr ""
"Sending those Undead Dwarves back to sleep was an act of mercy. Here is the "
"reward I promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2190"
msgstr ""
"I will give Blackpeak's last blade to the best smiths in Stonevault. "
"Hopefully, they will be able to complete the master's last work."

msgid "end_text_quest_2191"
msgstr ""
"You have dealt a potentially crippling blow to the Fire Standard hobgoblins. "
"Here is the reward I promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2192"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to the efforts of you and others, the military expedition against the "
"ogres should now run smoothly."

msgid "end_text_quest_2194"
msgstr ""
"It seems that young DeQuincey met a sad end at the hands and teeth of the "
"Stormlord valley ogres. I will give the sad news to his father."

msgid "end_text_quest_2196"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Hopefully, this means that the pass through Waneride will be "
"opened again soon."

msgid "end_text_quest_2197"
msgstr ""
"You have done well. Only death can remove Sahul's taint from a dwarf once he "
"has become infected. #PlayerName#, please accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2198"
msgstr ""
"I am grateful for the bravery and effort you have shown on behalf of the "
"citizens of Leengate."

msgid "end_text_quest_2199"
msgstr "Thank you. Here is the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_220"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Hopefully, all goblins will learn soon enough that freedom is an "
"impossible goal."

msgid "end_text_quest_2200"
msgstr ""
"Well done. With no way of returning north, those Arctic Bears were doomed to "
"a slow death."

msgid "end_text_quest_2201"
msgstr ""
"As soon as the svartdvergir have been eradicated, we can begin the work of "
"resettling the once prosperous mining community of Blacktrove."

msgid "end_text_quest_2202"
msgstr ""
"Eradicating the svartdvergir will be much easier now that their guardian "
"creatures is gone."

msgid "end_text_quest_2203"
msgstr ""
"It is good to know that those poor souls have finally found rest. Here is "
"the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_2204"
msgstr "Well done. Here is a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2205"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Soon the Whitebough forest will be cleared of rebels and we will "
"be able to proceed with large-scale logging operations."

msgid "end_text_quest_2206"
msgstr "Well done. Here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2207"
msgstr ""
"Excellent news. The path through Waneride Gorge must be kept open at all "
"costs."

msgid "end_text_quest_2209"
msgstr ""
"I will give the Occluded Mirror to a Five Beards member who reads Nithron. "
"If he finds anything useful, I will pass it on to you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2210"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I have already been informed about all you have done for us. "
"We are all honored to have worked with you. The Five Beards Trading Company "
"will like to give you this reward for all you have done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2211"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. So you are #PlayerName#. I have heard about you. I am Vestri, the "
"local Blacksmith. I think you might be able to help me out with something."

msgid "end_text_quest_2212"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. The Voice of Ymir would like to thank you for all you have "
"done. These are strange times we are living in, and we can all do with able "
"strong individuals like yourself. Accept this reward for all you have done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2213"
msgstr "You have done well. Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_222"
msgstr "Well done. Those poor goblins never had a chance."

msgid "end_text_quest_224"
msgstr "Well done. Here is a small reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2247"
msgstr "Well done. You may well have what it takes to become an Iron Ork."

msgid "end_text_quest_2248"
msgstr ""
"Welcome back. Reports indicate that you dispatched those Raptors in a most "
"commendable manner. I no longer doubt that you have  the skills and the "
"mettle required to perform missions for the Iron Orks."

msgid "end_text_quest_2249"
msgstr "Very well done. It seems that the time has come to take the town back."

msgid "end_text_quest_2250"
msgstr ""
"Yes. That's what I want to see. Pain, lots of pain to our enemies. Accept "
"this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2252"
msgstr ""
"This copy of the Endemoniad seems completey intact. An amazing find, which I "
"will hand directly over to scholars of Nithron history."

msgid "end_text_quest_2253"
msgstr ""
"I see... If their numbers grow too numerous, these guardian creatures could "
"pose a considerable threat to the stability of Morak. I will pass your "
"information on to the authorities in {$v13}."

msgid "end_text_quest_2255"
msgstr ""
"Yes, I believe this may be the item we sought. It is clearly of Nithron "
"origin, and it seems to be a spellbook of some kind. Well done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2256"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to the efforts of you and others, Silmah is doomed to fall in the "
"near future."

msgid "end_text_quest_2257"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. You have done well in disposing of the Hill Giants Sluggers. "
"Here, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2258"
msgstr ""
"Well done. I will send a report off to the authorities in Flaming Skull, to "
"inform them about the growing hobgoblin army. #PlayerName#, you have "
"performed well, and the Iron Orks are pleased with your work. Accept this "
"well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_226"
msgstr ""
"At this rate, we will have our own Small Stair in no time at all. Here is "
"the reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2269"
msgstr "Good. We cannot tolerate Swamp Hags that close to our headquarters."

msgid "end_text_quest_2270"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Elfkill Keep. Using this stronghold as a base, we will drive the "
"Ciel Fey out of Morak."

msgid "end_text_quest_2271"
msgstr "Well done. Here is the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_2273"
msgstr ""
"Doesn't look like much, does it, this so-called Sacred Bough? Still, Big "
"Head Uzrok will enjoy feeding it to the fires of {$v13}."

msgid "end_text_quest_2274"
msgstr "Well done. Here is the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_2275"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to {$v15}. The good news is that we may have located entrance to the "
"so-called Shrine of Memory. The bad news is that the entrance is guarded by "
"a large Sadayel village, which will have to be dealt with before any further "
"exploration can take place."

msgid "end_text_quest_2276"
msgstr "Well done. Here is the reward I promised."

msgid "end_text_quest_2277"
msgstr "Here is the reward for killing the guardians of the shrine."

msgid "end_text_quest_2278"
msgstr ""
"Well done. I will make sure that the Big Head himself learns the name of the "
"brutish and brave adventurer who destroyed the Shrine of Memory."

msgid "end_text_quest_2279"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. #PlayerName#, you truly are a strong and capable ally. Here is a "
"well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_228"
msgstr "Just in the nick of time. Here is the reward I promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2280"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. The humans must be taught that nothing of theirs is sacred to the "
"orks."

msgid "end_text_quest_2292"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Let us hope the stream of victims will flow more freely from now "
"on."

msgid "end_text_quest_2294"
msgstr ""
"Ah yes. I can feel the hatred of the dark god Sahul emanating from the "
"liquid within this terrible artifact. The Banegrail will doubtlessly become "
"a treasured possession of the Fire Dragon."

msgid "end_text_quest_2295"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to {$x11}. Arxanthos is impatient for treasures which he saw in the "
"Fire Dragon's most recent dream, and we must not keep the Grand Messenger "
"waiting. Those who disappoint Arxanthos tend to end their days tumbling down "
"the side of the Great Stairs in Emberhall."

msgid "end_text_quest_2296"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to you efforts, our excavation teams are now ready to continue their "
"work on the northernmost and southernmost islands of the archipelago."

msgid "end_text_quest_2298"
msgstr ""
"This must be the far-famed Amber Harp of {$x11}. It will make a fine "
"addition to the Fire Dragon's hoard, which is already the largest "
"accumulation of treasure in the world."

msgid "end_text_quest_2299"
msgstr ""
"Other heroes have reported similar success in other parts of Morak. Once "
"again the sadayel have been revealed as a pathetic race who are doomed to be "
"massacred into extinction by the far superior orks."

msgid "end_text_quest_230"
msgstr "Thank you. Here is a small reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2300"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Bad Dog. This is a small outpost which consists of little more "
"than a keep, a bank and a general store."

msgid "end_text_quest_2302"
msgstr ""
"The damp conditions have left their mark on this book but it is still by far "
"the most complete copy we have of the Fecund Leaf. Here is the reward I "
"promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_2304"
msgstr ""
"I can almost smell the corruption emanating from this vile orb, which will "
"become a prized part of the Fire Dragon's hoard."

msgid "end_text_quest_2306"
msgstr ""
"Yes, this matches the description of a Mark of Morneid. It seems that most "
"of its power was drained or used up a long time ago. #PlayerName#, here is "
"your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2317"
msgstr ""
"Your efforts have greatly reduced the centaur threat against Mercian farmers "
"who live near the {$t21}."

msgid "end_text_quest_2318"
msgstr ""
"The fallen Knights of Malregard have been avenged. Hopefully, the villagers "
"of {$t21} will have learned by now that rebellion against our overlordship "
"is a futile endeavor."

msgid "end_text_quest_2319"
msgstr ""
"With the source of the taint removed, the Wychwode spring should soon return "
"to its pristine state. and when the sacred spring is clear once more, the "
"madness of the forest guardians should abate. Please, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_232"
msgstr ""
"Thank you. The local enchanters will know what to do with your macabre "
"harvest."

msgid "end_text_quest_2320"
msgstr ""
"With all the Air Elementals gone, Cloudhenge will no longer generate power "
"for the Dark Arannog. This is the beginning of the end of their rebellion in "
"the {$t21} region."

msgid "end_text_quest_2321"
msgstr "Well done. You richly deserve this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2322"
msgstr "Well done. You richly deserve this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2323"
msgstr "Well done. You richly deserve this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2324"
msgstr ""
"A powerful blow has been dealt to Malaut and theTwilight Kingdom. "
"#PlayerName#, the Knights of Malregard are honored and proud to have met "
"you. You have been of great help in our war against the Malaut and his "
"Twilight Kingdom. Please accept this well earned reward for all you have "
"done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2333"
msgstr "Well done. Please accept this reward as a token of our gratitude."

msgid "end_text_quest_2334"
msgstr "Well done. Please accept this reward as a token of our gratitude."

msgid "end_text_quest_2335"
msgstr "Here is the reward for your bold actions."

msgid "end_text_quest_2336"
msgstr ""
"Most impressive. You dealt with that situation in an admirable manner. "
"#PlayerName#, please accept this reward for all that you have done."

msgid "end_text_quest_2337"
msgstr ""
"It seems that the hobgoblins are preparing for a war. You have done well. I "
"will send a report imminently to the authorities in Sanguine. Please accept "
"this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_2338"
msgstr "Thank you. Here is a reward for your efforts."

msgid "end_text_quest_2339"
msgstr "Here is the reward for your bold actions."

msgid "end_text_quest_234"
msgstr ""
"For their own sake, those stupid little goblins had better learn to keep "
"their distance from Metal Heart."

msgid "end_text_quest_2340"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Please accept this reward as a token of the White Order's "
"gratitude."

msgid "end_text_quest_2349"
msgstr ""
"Well done, friend. Without sarlid guidance, the giant spiders can be hunted "
"down one by one."

msgid "end_text_quest_2351"
msgstr ""
"The diadem! It is… magnificent. The runes along its side are in Nithronese, "
"no doubt about that, and it seems to be entirely made from the rare and "
"magical metal called neithal. With my colleagues, I will begin researching "
"this object immediately. Hopefully, we will be able to learn much about the "
"magic and enchantment techniques of the ancient Nithron."

msgid "end_text_quest_2352"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, the Sons if Riada will now resume our excavations in "
"Theyril Hall."

msgid "end_text_quest_2353"
msgstr ""
"From what you say, it sounds like the Sons of Riada may indeed have "
"unearthed the Diadem of Dawn. Before I give you the Wainfold Tapestry, "
"however, I'm afraid I must insist that you help us with an urgent local "
"crisis."

msgid "end_text_quest_2354"
msgstr ""
"Hopefully, this means that herbalists can work in peace in the southern "
"parts of Cranwyn Bay."

msgid "end_text_quest_2355"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Hopefully, this means that herbalists will once again be able to "
"gather herbs in the glens and glades of northern Cranwyn Bay."

msgid "end_text_quest_2356"
msgstr ""
"Ah, the Tapestry! Hopefully, this unique book will help us unlock the "
"mysteries of the strange crown that you found in the troll hollow."

msgid "end_text_quest_2358"
msgstr ""
"So, the Dragontorc had indeed reappeared in the{$t22} ruins. As the old "
"sources say, it is truly a magnificent work of art, and when holding it, I "
"can feel that it hums with hidden power. We will start researching its "
"nature and abilities right away."

msgid "end_text_quest_2359"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for helping with the war effort. We now have almost all the "
"enchantment ingredients we need, and the production of armor and weapons is "
