msgid "end_text_quest_4196"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of blood, five bones and one heart upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the third step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast the Flesh Curse spell "
"onto the tombstone to weaken the powers of the tombstone."

msgid "end_text_quest_4197"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Flesh Curse spell onto the demon tombstone, "
"weakened its powers, and completed the fourth step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place ten units of ash upon "
"the tombstone."

msgid "end_text_quest_4198"
msgstr ""
"You have placed ten units of ash upon the demon tombstone, and completed the "
"fifth step to disabling the magical properties of the demon tombstone. Now "
"you must cast the Mana Drain spell onto the tombstone to remove all magical "
"properties from it."

msgid "end_text_quest_4199"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. This is good news. It would seem that the sequence of steps that "
"Ayrdyr-dan the Mage gave us to disable the demon tombstone actually work. I "
"will immediately send a report to {$j12}. Here is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4201"
msgstr ""
"Oh! The Lightbringer you say. I should have never spoken to that traveling "
"merchant about the Lightbringer. Damn wine."

msgid "end_text_quest_4204"
msgstr "Thank you. This beautiful wine will be my downfall."

msgid "end_text_quest_4206"
msgstr ""
"So, this mysterious group managed to get inside our headquarters disguised "
"as on of our own, wearing one of the cloaks of the Knights of Malregard. And "
"they acquired this cloak from Cornelius the Merchant, who is actually "
"Cornelius Oakenheart? Cornelius Oakenheart, who has once one of the bravest "
"of the Knights of Malregard. I never knew what had become of Cornelius, "
"after the battle of Drydale. And if that wasn't enough, Cornelius must now "
"live with the guilt of the theft of the Lightbringer, the Lightbringer of "
"Rowan Brightwood. Poor Cornelius."

msgid "end_text_quest_4208"
msgstr ""
"The Knights of Malregard want to know if I have seen or heard anything about "
"a strange group of robe-wearing humans, that passed through Ottenhal several "
"days ago. I might have, I might have not. But, I'll tell you what "
"#CharacterRace#. If you can convince that wolfman Malren-Dor the Arcanist to "
"lend me that book of his, “Blood Potions of the Full Moon”, I might be able "
"to remember a thing or two that might interest you. What do you think? It "
"sounds like a fair deal to me. Can you get that book for me?"

msgid "end_text_quest_4209"
msgstr ""
"That sneaky Karharias still wants to borrow my book. And now he has sent you "
"to try to convince me. Very well, help me gather the ingredients I need for "
"my latest Blood Moon potion, and I shall give you the book.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I need to complete my potion are six units of the following materials. "
"Hellbore, Archangelica, Baneberry, Snakeweed and Blood. Bring me six of "
"each, and Karharias can have the damn book."

msgid "end_text_quest_4210"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. You have gathered the ingredients needed for my new potion. And "
"as agreed, he is a signed copy of my book, “Blood Potions of the Full Moon”. "
"I hope Karharias enjoys it, and never bothers my again."

msgid "end_text_quest_4211"
msgstr ""
"You have returned with the book. A signed copy just for me! Wonderful. Now I "
"shall tell you what I know about these humans the Knights of Malregard are "
"so interested in.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A robe-wearing group of humans did pass through Ottenahal asking questions "
"about an ex-knight of the Knights of Malregard called Cornelius. In the "
"beginning I didn't believe them that poor old Cornelius, the drunk merchant "
"of Ottenhal, was once a Knight of Malregard. Anyhow, I played along "
"pretending I knew in the hopes of discovering what these mysterious humans "
"were really after.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I began my usual mind games, trying to trick them into spewing out any "
"kind of information, I quickly discovered that these humans were here on "
"serious business. I could see they weren't impressed with my little mind "
"games. The leader of the group immediately handed me pouch.  There was so "
"much gold inside, I just couldn't refuse such a beautiful offer. It was "
"either no gold but warn Cornelius that somebody had come looking for him, or "
"keep the gold and lead my new friends to Cornelius."

msgid "end_text_quest_4212"
msgstr ""
"It was that alfar mage Karharias who gave me away to those robe-wearing "
"thieves. He should have informed me that a strange group of humans had come "
"asking questions about me, instead of informing them of my drinking habits "
"and leading them to me. But as you see my friend, everybody has a price, "
"especially in a lawless city such as Ottenhal. Thank you for bringing this "
"to my attention. Karharias will pay for this one day. Here is the reward I "
"promised you."

msgid "end_text_quest_4214"
msgstr ""
"Thank you  #PlayerName#! Now your sulfur can be added to the celebrations! "
"Your spark too will light up the sky in a flash of brilliance! Thus your own "
"ember sings out to the glory that is Agon!"

msgid "end_text_quest_4216"
msgstr ""
