msgid "end_text_quest_4301"
msgstr ""
"Strong's mighty blow horn. The cries coming forth from this blow horn, have "
"become somewhat legendary to the townsfolk of Heart of Eanna. You have done "
"well #PlayerName#. There is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4304"
msgstr ""
"Adalia's mighty blow horn. The cries coming forth from this blow horn, have "
"become somewhat legendary to the citizens of Onghral. You have done well "
"#PlayerName#. There is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4307"
msgstr ""
"Narandir's fine longsword. The image of the longsword leading every attack "
"against our enemies, will never be forgotten by the people of Leafhelm. You "
"have done well #PlayerName#. Here is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4310"
msgstr ""
"Kilenran's keen longsword. The image of the longsword leading every attack "
"against our enemies, will never be forgotten by the people of Silverspear. "
"You have done well #PlayerName#. Here is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4313"
msgstr ""
"Drogan's heavy shield. The cries coming forth from this blow horn, have "
"become somewhat legendary to the townsfolk of Hammerdelve. You have done "
"well #PlayerName#. There is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4316"
msgstr ""
"Galtanok's mighty blow horn. The cries coming forth from this blow horn, "
"have become somewhat legendary to the townsfolk of New Flayed Elf. You have "
"done well #PlayerName#. There is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4318"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Snake Greenleaf from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do "
"just fine."

msgid "end_text_quest_4320"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for accepting to carry out this task. I shall for analyze these "
"sample, to determine if these poor souls rising withing the old mining site "
"were once Mercians or not. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4322"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested.  I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments."

msgid "end_text_quest_4324"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Greenleaf from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do just "
"fine."

msgid "end_text_quest_4326"
msgstr ""
"Ah, the samples I had requested. Excellent. I shall analyze these units of "
"Corpsflesh to see if I can determine what powers might be responsible for "
"the rising of these undead guardians."

msgid "end_text_quest_4328"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested. I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4330"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Greenleaf from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do just "
"fine. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4332"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for accepting to carry out this task. I shall do my best to "
"discover if these poor souls were once our people."

msgid "end_text_quest_4334"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested.  I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments."

msgid "end_text_quest_4336"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested. I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments."

msgid "end_text_quest_4338"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Greenleaf from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do just "
"fine. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4340"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for accepting to gather the Corpseflesh I requested. I must admit, "
"I am curious to find out if the zombies are somehow connected to the strange "
"stone structures."

msgid "end_text_quest_4342"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested. I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments."

msgid "end_text_quest_4344"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for accepting to carry out this task. I shall for analyze these "
"sample, and try to discover that happened to the forest, and why these "
"undead are now rising from withing the swamps."

msgid "end_text_quest_4346"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Greenleaf from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do just "
"fine."

msgid "end_text_quest_4348"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Venom Sac from the mysterious Sarnakh. Yes, this will do just "
"fine."

msgid "end_text_quest_4350"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Let us see if these zombies are the mercians that once offered us "
"so much entertainment."

msgid "end_text_quest_4352"
msgstr ""
"Wonderful. Four units of Baleful Venom Sac as requested. I may now continue "
"experimenting with my enchantments."

msgid "end_text_quest_4375"
msgstr ""
"Interesting. A letter with information about our patrols. These humans are "
"definitely not working alone. Somebody from inside the Tribelands is using "
"them. We must discover who. You have done well in finding this information "
"and bringing it to us. Accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4377"
msgstr ""
"Once more you return victorious! I see you have managed to kill two of the "
"ever-feared Gray Ork Chieftains. Excellent. Our allies the Ork of Morak will "
"surely be pleased to hear this. Here is your well earned reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4379"
msgstr ""
"A letter from our allies the Mahrim of the Tribelands. Ah, this is god news! "
"The Wolfmasks not only found and attacked the Gray Ork camp in {$m13}, but "
"also discovered an even bigger Gray Ork hideout within the {$j13} dungeon "
"and managed to kill even an Gray Ork Chieftain. You! You killed the "
"Chieftain! Good work!"

msgid "end_text_quest_4383"
msgstr ""
"Ah, you have returned with evidence. A coded letter. Excellent. All that "
"remains is to break this code, and learn who the humans bandits are working "
"for."

msgid "end_text_quest_4385"
msgstr ""
"A magical altar, perfectly intact on top of Neithstone Hall. Yes, this could "
"be the reason to the appearance of the Menhir. We must discover more about "
"this altar. You have done well, Here is your reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4388"
msgstr ""
"A map, together with instruction to search for the Night Stone, an ancient "
"artifact. So, it seems that these hobgoblins have been hired to go on a "
"treasure hunt. What troubles me, is who has the power and the time to "
"convince these hobgoblins to go an a treasure hunt?"

msgid "end_text_quest_4394"
msgstr "Excellent. I see that the Gnolls were no match for you."

msgid "end_text_quest_4396"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Nobody, and especially those dumb Ogres, will ever take control "
"of Hunter's Run."

msgid "end_text_quest_4398"
msgstr ""
"The Forest Prophets have made Hornwood Forest into a very dangerous place, "
"and for that alone they must be stopped!"

msgid "end_text_quest_44"
msgstr ""
"Thank you, #PlayerName# , for helping us prepare against the goblin threat."

msgid "end_text_quest_4401"
msgstr ""
"A totem showing a raging bear. Yes. It has been a very long time since "
"anybody had heard from the Forest Prophets of the Raging Bear."

msgid "end_text_quest_4403"
msgstr ""
"You have done well. The Shadow Masters are surely to be pleased with your "
"work. #PlayerName#, accept this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4405"
msgstr ""
"Very well done. Our goal here is not to completely eradicate the Akathars "
"and Windlords that have returned to {$o11}, but to only make it clear to "
"them that we will not tolerate any more attacks from them in the future."

msgid "end_text_quest_4407"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Although this will not bring back the murdered workers, it will "
"bring some form of justice to the victims families. #PlayerName#, accept "
"this reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4409"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Sanguine. I am Torgard the Fighter, and I will be teaching you "
"combat basics."

msgid "end_text_quest_4411"
msgstr ""
"Well done #PlayerName#. I see you have completed your melee training. Accept "
"this reward. Next, we will continue training in archery."

msgid "end_text_quest_4413"
msgstr ""
"Well done. You seem to have grasped the basics of archery. Accept this "
"reward. Next I shall share a few useful tips with you."

msgid "end_text_quest_4415"
msgstr ""
"Well done. You will need to do a lot of sprinting if you are to survive out "
"there.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Then, there is Parrying. You can use Parry to deflect incoming attacks such "
"as melee and ranged attacks. To Parry, just simply press your V key.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Alright, lets just try using Parry. First, you must equip yourself with any "
"melee weapon. Next, just simple press the V key button and show me that you "
"can Parry."

msgid "end_text_quest_4416"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Now, not only can you attack your enemies, but you can also parry "
"their attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, lets talk about stealth. Using your C key you will be able to simply "
"Crouch, or even better be able to Crouch Walk. Crouching can be used either "
"to sneak up on an opponent, or to simply hide from one.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Let's give this skill a go. Use the C key to crouch, and then slowly start "
"moving forward to show me that you can move using stealth."

msgid "end_text_quest_4417"
msgstr ""
"Good. Now you can use the Crouch Walk skill to either hide from your enemies "
"or even sneak up to them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The last and most important tip that I would like to share with you, is the "
"benefit of resting. Resting is the most basic way of healing yourself. When "
"you are sure you have found a safe spot, just sit down and rest, regaining "
"any lost health, stamina and mana at a faster rate than normal.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Skills, and under General Skills search for the Rest skill. Next drag "
"Rest onto your hotbar. To use the Rest skill, first you must make sure you "
"are not holding anything. Sheathe any weapon or staff you might be holding "
"by pressing R. Next, select the Rest skill by pressing the number key that "
"corresponds to the slot where you placed the Rest skill. Then, just simply "
"press your left mouse button to activate it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go ahead and rest."

msgid "end_text_quest_4418"
msgstr "Very good. Never underestimate the benefits of simply resting."

msgid "end_text_quest_4420"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Jonn the Mage, and I will be teaching you the basics of magic."

msgid "end_text_quest_4422"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Now you can cast Mana Missiles against your enemies. Accept this "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4424"
msgstr "Yes! That's it. Now you can also use your staff to heal yourself."

msgid "end_text_quest_4426"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Never forget to bank often. It is not wise to carry all of your "
"belongings around with you all of the time."

msgid "end_text_quest_4427"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Simeon the Merchant, and I would like to talk to you about "
"using the bank."

msgid "end_text_quest_4429"
msgstr ""
"Welcome back. I trust that both Torgard and Jonn have prepared you well "
"while leading you through the basics of combat and magic. I have also been "
"informed that Simeon the Merchant has also explained to you how to use the "
"bank. Excellent. Now one last bit of information from me and you will have "
"completed your basic training.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Some of the most basic and important structures you will come across in Agon "
"are the Bindstones. You will easily recognize them from the bright white "
"beam that shoots out of them straight up into the skies, just like the one "
"that is positioned over there in front of me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When you die, you will respawn at the location where you last bound yourself "
"to a Bindstone. For now, you are bound to the Bindstone here in Sanguine. "
"This means that whenever and wherever you may die in Agon, you will respawn "
"right next to the Bindstone here in this town. But, as you travel throughout "
"Agon and visit new locations, you will discover more Bindstones. If you wish "
"to remain in one of those locations, then you can just simply bind to that "
"Bindstone. Every town and city has its own stone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To bind yourself to a Bindstone, all you need to do is to simply walk up "
"close to it, and while facing it to press the F key. Immediately you will be "
"informed that you have become bound to that location.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"With this last little bit of information, I believe we have reached the end "
"of your basic training.  \r\n"
"#PlayerName#, Agon can be a dangerous yet wonderful place. Walk carefully, "
"and keep training to better yourself."

msgid "end_text_quest_4431"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Sandbrook. I am Catherine the Fighter, and I will be showing you "
"the basics of combat."

msgid "end_text_quest_4433"
msgstr ""
"Excellent #PlayerName#. I see you have completed your melee training. Accept "
"this reward. Next, we will continue training in archery."

msgid "end_text_quest_4435"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. I can see you have the potential with a little training to become "
"a great archer."

msgid "end_text_quest_4437"
msgstr ""
"Very good. You will need to do a lot of sprinting if you are to survive out "
"there.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Then there is Parrying. You can use Parry to deflect incoming attacks such "
"as melee and ranged attacks. To Parry, just simply press your V key.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Lets practice Parrying. First, you must equip yourself with any melee "
"weapon. Next, just simply press the V key and show me that you can Parry."

msgid "end_text_quest_4438"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Now, not only can you attack your enemies, but you can also parry "
"their attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Next, there is the use of stealth. Using your C key you will be able to "
"Crouch, or even better be able to Crouch Walk. Crouching can be used either "
"to sneak up on an opponent, or to simply hide from one.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Use the C key to crouch, and then slowly start moving forward to show me "
"that you can move using stealth."

msgid "end_text_quest_4439"
msgstr ""
"Very good. Now you can use the Crouch Walk skill to either hide from your "
"enemies or even sneak up to them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The last and most important tip that I would like to share with you, is the "
"benefits of simply resting. Resting is the most basic way of healing "
"yourself. When you are sure you have found a safe spot, just sit down and "
"rest, slowly regaining any lost health, stamina and mana.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Skills, and under General Skills search for the Rest Skill. Next drag "
"the Rest skill onto your hotbar. To use the Rest skill, first you must make "
"sure you are not holding anything. Sheathe any weapon or staff you might be "
"holding. Next, select the Rest skill by pressing the number key button that "
"corresponds to the slot were you placed the Rest skill. Then, just simply "
"press your left mouse button.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go ahead and rest."

msgid "end_text_quest_4440"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Resting is the best way to recover. Just never forget to make "
"sure you have found a safe spot first."

msgid "end_text_quest_4442"
msgstr "I am Carrad the Mage, and I will be teaching you the basics of magic."

msgid "end_text_quest_4444"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Now you can cast Mana Missiles against your enemies. Accept this "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4446"
msgstr "Yes. That's it. Now you can also use your staff to heal yourself."

msgid "end_text_quest_4448"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Thora the Merchant, and I would like to talk to you about "
"using the bank."

msgid "end_text_quest_4449"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Never forget to bank. It is not wise to carry all of your "
"belongings around with you all of the time."

msgid "end_text_quest_4451"
msgstr ""
"Welcome back. I trust that both Catherine and Carrad have prepared you well, "
"while leading you through the basics of combat and magic. Now one more last "
"bit of information from me and you have finished with basic training.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Some of the most basic and important structures you will come across in Agon "
"are the Bindstones. You will easily recognize them from the bright white "
"beam that shoots out of them straight up into the skies, just like the one "
"that is positioned over there in front of me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When you die, you will respawn at the location where you last bound yourself "
"to a Bindstone. For now, you are bound to the Bindstone here in Sandbrook. "
"This means that whenever and wherever you may die in Agon, you will respawn "
"right next to the Bindstone here in this town. But, as you travel throughout "
"Agon and visit new locations, you will discover more Bindstones. If you wish "
"to remain in one of those locations, then you can just simply bind to that "
"Bindstone. Every town and city has its own stone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To bind yourself to a Bindstone, all you need to do is to simply walk up "
"close to it, and while facing it to press the F key. Immediately you will be "
"informed that you have become bound to that location.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"With this last little bit of information, I believe we have reached the end "
"of your basic training. #PlayerName#, Agon can be a dangerous yet wonderful "
"place. Walk carefully, and keep training to better yourself."

msgid "end_text_quest_4453"
msgstr ""
"I am Kai the Fighter, and together we will be going over the combat basics "
"you need to know."

msgid "end_text_quest_4455"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. I see you successfully completed your melee combat training. "
"Accept this reward. Now we will continue your combat training with a little "
"archery."

msgid "end_text_quest_4457"
msgstr ""
"Very good. You seem to have grasped the basics of archery. Accept this "
"reward. Next I shall share a few useful tips with you."

msgid "end_text_quest_4459"
msgstr ""
"Very good. You will need to do a lot of sprinting if you are to survive out "
"there.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Then there is Parrying. You can use Parry to deflect incoming blows such as "
"melee and ranged attacks. To Parry, just simply press your V key.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Let’s practice Parrying. First, you must equip yourself with any melee "
"weapon. Next, just simply press the V key and show me that you can Parry."

msgid "end_text_quest_4460"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Now, not only can you attack your enemies, but you can also parry "
"their attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Next, there is Crouching. Using your C key you will be able to simply "
"Crouch, or even better be able to Crouch Walk. Crouching can be used either "
"to sneak up on an opponent, or to simply hide from one.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Let's give this skill a go. Use the C key to crouch, and then slowly start "
"moving forward to show me that you can move using stealth."

msgid "end_text_quest_4461"
msgstr ""
"Well done. Use the Crouch Walk skill to sneak up to your enemies, or quietly "
"disappear.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The last and most important tip that I would like to share with you, is the "
"benefit of resting. Resting is the most basic way of healing yourself. When "
"you are sure you have found a safe spot, just sit down and rest, regaining "
"any lost health, stamina and mana at a faster rate than normal.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Skills, and under General Skills search for the Rest skill. Next drag "
"Rest onto your hotbar. To use the Rest skill, first you must make sure you "
"are not holding anything. Sheathe any weapon or staff you might be holding "
"by pressing R. Next, select the Rest skill by pressing the number key that "
"corresponds to the slot where you placed the Rest skill. Then, just simply "
"press your left mouse button to activate it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go ahead and have a rest."

msgid "end_text_quest_4462"
msgstr "ever underestimate the benefits of simply resting."

msgid "end_text_quest_4464"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Caradwen the Mage, and together we will be learning the basics "
"of magic."

msgid "end_text_quest_4466"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Now you can cast Mana Missiles against your enemies. Accept this "
"reward."

msgid "end_text_quest_4468"
msgstr "Very good. Now you can also use your staff to heal yourself."

msgid "end_text_quest_447"
msgstr "Well done, indeed. Here is the reward I promised you."

