msgid "start_text_quest_10000"
msgstr ""
"Greetings! I'm Allan, head of the Sanguine City Council.\r\n"
"  \rIn the months since the minions of the dark mage Oncylus began spreading "
"out from the middle of Agon, the various races have declared a ceasefire to "
"their age old blood feud. Since then, Sanguine has become a hub of refugees "
"fleeing the violence, and we've been struggling to keep up with feeding "
"everyone.\r\n"
"  \rOn top of that, I just received word that a party of Goblins is raiding "
"the farm straight South of here. Can you believe it? Goblins haven't been "
"this close to Sanguine in generations! You look sturdier and more capable "
"than most coming through here, could you help us out? I've been authorized "
"to offer payment to anyone who provides the city with invaluable services "
"during these dark times, and we'd be in your debt if you could thin out this "
"raiding party so our farmers could get back to work.\r\n"
"  \rGo South and Kill 10 Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_10001"
msgstr ""
"A lone Goblin is pretty pathetic, but in large numbers, and with axes and "
"full bellies, they can be deadly.  Aside from just killing them, disarming "
"and de-supplying the Goblins is effective as well.\r\n"
"  \rWhile most Goblins lack the basic intelligence required to craft "
"weapons, they are notorious for scavenging them off the still-warm corpses "
"of their companions. If you could grab some of those weapons, specifically "
"their nasty looking Goblin Axes, it would really help.\r\n"
"  \rThe other part of my request is not for those with a weak stomach.  One "
"Goblin delicacy is a barely cooked lizard skewered on a pointy stick. A "
"hungry Goblin is a Goblin that doesn't want to fight, so the more of these "
"you can take away from this group the better.\r\n"
"  \rGather 5 goblin axes and 3 lizard on sticks."

msgid "start_text_quest_10002"
msgstr ""
"You have proven yourself quite capable in combat.  One of the other "
"authorities given to myself and other upstanding members of our community is "
"the ability to bestow titles on deserving allies.\r\n"
"  \rThese titles include a special magical badge that grants a bonus to one "
"of the key attributes of all Agonians.  The title which I can grant is that "
"of \"The Limber\".  The item included with this title gives the holder a "
"small boost to their Dexterity. However, these items will serve as the "
"starting point for future titles which can be earned, and then your badge "
"can be upgraded to eventually provide a fairly powerful enchantment.\r\n"
"  \rThe task required of you to receive the title of \"The Limber\", is to "
"slay a large number of skeletal sharpshooters.  Both the standard Skeleton "
"Archers, and the stronger Deadeyes.  Good luck!\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_10003"
msgstr ""
"Now that you have given us time to formulate a plan of attack against these "
"Goblin raiders, I would like you to help us prepare better for what I assume "
"will be a prolonged fight.\r\n"
"  \rSimeon is the chief Merchant in Sanguine, and is also responsible for "
"maintaining the city's strategic stockpile of resources. If you could please "
"head East towards the water and harvest some resources it would really help "
"us out. If the area seems picked over you can head North to look for more."
"\r\n"
"  \rGather 15 Iron Ore, 15 Timber, 15 Stone, 10 Cotton and catch 5 Fish then "
"bring them to Simeon the Merchant in the city."

msgid "start_text_quest_10004"
msgstr ""
"With all these extra mouths to feed from people fleeing Oncylus, we barely "
"have enough to give to our troops.\r\n"
"  \rI know that a bunch of the soldiers mentioned missing the cooking of "
"their mothers, so could you please make them some warm Berry Oatmeal to "
"remind them of home\r\n"
"  \rUse the Campfire to cook 5 Berry Oatmeals."

msgid "start_text_quest_10005"
msgstr ""
"Since you've shown that you have at least some basic skills, and have been "
"pretty helpful overall, your next step is to talk to Talaod the Blacksmith."
"\r\n"
"  \rHe is the grumpiest council member, but he usually has a lot of "
"available work.\r\n"
"  \rHead North and talk to Talaod the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_10006"
msgstr ""
"So, you already did some work for Simeon? Bah! He does nothing but buy and "
"sell the crafts of others.  What does he know about real labor?\r\n"
"  \rI, on the other hand, am responsible for arming and armoring all the "
"warriors of Sanguine.  Now THAT takes hard work! It also takes a lot of "
"Iron, Wood and Leather...\r\n"
"  \rFirst I'm going to have you process some raw materials into something "
"more refined. Specifically I find myself needing a few Iron Ingots, wood "
"planks, and leather to fill this latest request for equipment from the "
"Sanguine Guard.\r\n"
"  \rUse the Smelter to the East to do 3 crafts of Iron Ingots, then use the "
"Workbench to North to make 3 crafts of Wood Planks, and 3 crafts of Tanning "
"for Leather."

msgid "start_text_quest_10007"
msgstr ""
"Once you are done making your rounds in Sanguine, I have a task that will "
"take you West to the neighboring city of Monkfield. I've received reports "
"that the Monkfield Militia has been deployed to combat the Goblins. I'm sure "
"the brave people serving in the Militia would fight better on a full stomach."
"\r\rI'd like for you to use a Fishing Pole to catch some fish from the "
"waters around Sanguine, then cook up a few different fish dishes for the "
"militia, just like you cooked that Berry Oatmeal. You can bring the fish to "
"Eanna the Merchant in Monkfield and she will distribute it and compensate "
"you for your troubles.\r\r\rBring 5 Cooked Cod, 5 Cooked Trout, and 5 Tasty "
"Herring to Eanna the Merchant in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10008"
msgstr ""
"As a Merchant, there are few skills more important than speed.  Quickly "
"delivering goods from town to town, or being able to outrun an ambush from "
"Goblins or Bandits.\r\n"
"  \rBeing a member of the Sanguine City Council, I am able to give worth "
"adventurers the title of The Quick.  The badge that comes with this title "
"will give you a slight increase to your overall quickness, and can be "
"upgraded.  To attain the title of The Quick, you must exterminate hundreds "
"of Akathars and prove you are quicker than an avian.  These crazy bird men "
"are a nuisance.\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_10009"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without "
"complaining?  Those who gather materials that are needed to build these "
"grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect us?\r\n"
"  \rI give out a title for all those who are the real backbone of our "
"society, the harvesters and crafter. The title of The Thoughtful, comes with "
"badge that grants a small Wisdom bonus.\r\n"
"  \rTo attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather large "
"quantites of iron ore, stone, timber and fish. Once you have gathered a "
"small horde of those, bring them to me to claim your reward.\r\n"
"  \rGather 200 Iron Ore, 300 Stone, 300 Timber and 200 Fish."

msgid "start_text_quest_10010"
msgstr ""
"Underneath us is a massive sewer system, mostly used to help divert water "
"during the spring floods. The downside of having a damp underground system "
"like this is that it attracts disgusting rodent-like creatures called "
"Scumlings.\r\n"
"  \rJust like their surface cousins the Hivekin, Scumlings multiply at an "
"alarming rate and are ruled by a massive Scumling Queen. Left unchecked the "
"sewers would be completely overrun in a matter of weeks. I need you to help "
"me by going down there and clearing a bunch of Scumlings out, especially "
"their Queen, who is likely well hidden in the back. Niane the Arcanist can "
"provide you with payment afterwards.\r\n"
"  \rIt probably wouldn't be a bad idea to craft yourself a full gear set and "
"put any extra items in the bank before you go in. Weighing yourself down in "
"the Sewer is a bad idea.\r\n"
"  \rUse the Sewer entrance, by the Bank, to the Northeast of here, and Kill "
"10 Scumling Workers, 5 Scumling Guards and the Scumling Queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_10011"
msgstr ""
"The last time I sent a crew down into the sewers they reported some very "
"unusual sounds and smells. Well, I guess more unusual than what you would "
"normally expect in a sewer system...\r\n"
"  \rPoint is, based on their reports I suspect there are some sort of undead "
"currently taking up residence down there. While it isn't unheard of for "
"someone tinkering with necromancy to accidentally spawn a few zombies here "
"and there, it would be best if we cleared them out. Come to think of it, "
"Jonn the Mage was looking for some Corpseflesh to do some Enchanting work.  "
"Maybe you could kill two birds with one stone here and help us both out?\r\n"
"  \rGo into the backmost drainage basin in the sewers, kill the zombies, and "
"collect 6 Corpseflesh to bring to Jonn the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_10012"
msgstr ""
"Part of my service to the Sanguine City Council is as a teacher of arcane "
"crafting skills. Staff Crafting has long been a noble pursuit of those "
"looking to work in the ways of magic. With all the rabble coming in and out "
"of town these days, I can never keep basic staves in stock!\r\n"
"  \rIf you are interested in some quick money, use the nearby Workbench and "
"craft me a Troll Staff. They sell like hotcakes!\r\n"
"  \rUse your Staff Crafting skill at the Workbench to craft a Trollstaff."

msgid "start_text_quest_10013"
msgstr ""
"Every major city on Agon has its own mage. We generally act as advisors on "
"any and all magical threats, and also help provide much needed Enchanting "
"services. As part of my Enchanting training program, I would like you to go "
"to the Enchanting Ring to the West of here, and create a Crystal of "
"Keenness. This enchantment increases the damage weapons do, and can be "
"stored in a Crystal for use on a weapon later.\r\n"
"  \rFirst use the Enchanting Ring, then position the ingredients in the "
"specific order before applying the enchantment to the Crystal.\r\n"
"  \rThe order for the Keen enchanment is Darktaint, Bile and Cinder, with a "
"catalyst of Numen. Once completed please bring the gem to Torgard the "
"Fighter as he is always in need of more enchanments for the Sanguine's "
"weapon stockpile.\r\n"
"  \rCreate a Magic Crystal with the Keen Enchant and bring it to Torgard the "
"Fighter"

msgid "start_text_quest_10014"
msgstr ""
"As the city Arcanist, I have the responsibility of giving out a badge for "
"The Stout title, which has a minor Vitality enchantment meant for those who "
"have completed a feat requiring some impressive stamina.\r\n"
"  \rYour task is to kill a large number of annoying Kobolds.  Not the "
"toughest of creatures, but they breed in large numbers and can use some "
"basic weapons.  They tend to live around old ruins and will swarm anything "
"they think they can overwhelm.\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_10015"
msgstr ""
"It is only fitting that as the Sanguine city Mage I would be the one to hand "
"out the title badge for The Clever. Having this enchanted badge will grant "
"you a small bonus to intelligence, which will come in handy for any "
"spellcasting you do.\r\n"
"  \rTo prove yourself worthy of this title you must go out and slaughter "
"countless undead.  Don't worry, not the tougher ones, but zombies can still "
"be dangerous if you get surrounded!\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Zombies, 100 Zombie Warriors and 20 Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_10016"
msgstr ""
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title. I "
"myself am responsible for giving out the title of The Brawny for any brave "
"souls that wish to prove themselves. The badge that comes with this title "
"has a minor Strength enchantment on it.\r\n"
"  \rTo attain this title, all you need to do is to kill lots and lots of "
"filthy Greenskins. So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The "
"Brawny?\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_10017"
msgstr ""
"Our sister city of Monkfield has been surrounded on two sides by goblin "
"camps.\r\n"
"  \rYou have shown yourself to be very capable of both combat and crafting. "
"At this point I think your skills would be of more assistance to the people "
"of Monkfield than Sanguine. Head West, killing as many Goblins as you can "
"along the way, and talk to their councillor Cearl.\r\n"
"  \rKill 25 Goblins outside of Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10018"
msgstr ""
"I try to keep myself well apprised of all goings-on in Mercia. The talk "
"right now is that Monkfield is getting hit pretty hard by a swarm of Goblin "
"raiders. The city Mage in Monkfield is Selensha. I would wager that he could "
"use a bit of help right now.\r\rA very useful enchantment is that of Mana "
"Efficiency. It reduces how much mana it takes to cast a spell, and is always "
"in demand with mages. The ingredient order for this enchantment is Claw, "
"Lifeforce, Sparkstone, and a catalyst of Nith. If you could bring some "
"enchanted Crystals over to Selensha in Monkfield you will be paid well for "
"your services.\r\r\rCreate 5 Enchanted Crystals and bring them to Selensha "
"the Mage in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10019"
msgstr ""
"I recently received a request from Wyl the Blacksmith over in Monkfield, to "
"the West of here. He says that they have been quickly going through their "
"armor stockpiles in outfitting their militia to fight the surge in Goblin "
"raiders.\r\rCould you please craft some Chainmail Hauberks and bring them "
"over to Wyl? It could be the difference between a militiamen getting "
"skewered with a Goblin arrow, and having the armor he needs to walk away "
"from the fight.\r\r\rCreate 5 Chain Hauberks and bring them to Wyl the "
"Blacksmith in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10020"
msgstr ""
"While some people will protect themselves completely with heavy armor, the "
"more heavy armor you wear, the harder it becomes to cast spells and shoot a "
"bow.\r\rThe Monkfield Militia has a company of rangers and spell casters who "
"wear lighter armor. Could you please craft them some Cloth Hats to help them "
"get ready for combat?\r\r\rCreate 5 Cloth Hats for Eanna the Merchant in "
"Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10021"
msgstr ""
"I just received a request from Stonegar over in Monkfield to provide them "
"with some much needed weapons.  Unfortunately our stockpile is just enough "
"for ourselves right now, and I can't afford to send over even a single "
"sword. Would you be able to help by crafting some weapons for them?  "
"Stonegar will surely pay you well for them.\n"
"\t\r\n"
"\t\r\n"
"\t\r\n"
"\tCollect 5 Rapiers and bring them to Stonegar the Fighter in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10022"
msgstr ""
"It seems as though the Monkfield Militia is working on recruiting more able-"
"bodied mages to their numbers. Currently their main issue is that they can't "
"afford to issue a magic staff to every apprentice who volunteers.\r\rIn "
"order to help the Monkfield Militia be better prepared for magical combat, "
"could you please craft them some staves?\r\r\rCollect 5 Troll Staves and "
"bring them to Alric the Arcanist in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10023"
msgstr ""
"Alric, the Arcanist over at Monksfield, had a courier sent to me begging for "
"more healing potions. Their warehouses are just about empty following the "
"last few forrays out into the surrounding Goblin camps.\r\rI've only just "
"managed to get the Sanguine stockpile back up to a respectable level. Could "
"you please craft some Minor Healing Potions and bring them over to Alric in "
"Monkfield?\r\r\rCollect 5 Minor Healing Potions and bring them to Alric the "
"Arcanist in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10024"
msgstr ""
"Normally when the odd raiding party would attack a city the townspeople "
"would come inside, and the militia would take to the walls with bows to "
"drive them back. This current attack has been going on for so long that "
"Monkfield is running very low on supplies.\r\rI'm afraid that I would need "
"to seek council authorization to open up our stockpile to Monkfield, which "
"would take way too long. Could you please get them a good supply of raw "
"materials to use for their defenses?\r\r\rCollect 15 Iron Ore, 15 Timber, "
"and 15 Stone for Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10025"
msgstr ""
"Part of my City Council responsibilities in Sanguine dictate that I work to "
"bolster our local magical community.\r\n"
"  \rWhat better way is there to build community than by blasting Goblins!?  "
"Use your Mana Missile spell and blast a whole bunch of the little buggers "
"for me. Afterwards talk to Selensha in Monkfield for the next part of your "
"training.\r\n"
"  \rUse Mana Missile 20 times against Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_10026"
msgstr ""
"Nothing teaches you how to become a better archer than shooting at a target "
"that shoots back! And since we seem to have so many available targets around "
"Monkfield, it seems only natural I start sending trainees out there to do "
"some shooting.\r\n"
"  \rLook for the Goblin camps between Sanguine and Monkfield, and find "
"yourself a few nice sniping spots. Then I want you to rain death upon the "
"Goblin scum! Get your next task from Stonegar the Fighter afterwards.\r\n"
"  \rHit Goblins 20 times using Archery."

msgid "start_text_quest_10027"
msgstr ""
"Nothing about this Goblin raid is ordinary.  It is way too organized, and "
"has been going on for far too long.  There has to be some force behind it "
"driving these stupid greenskins forward.\r\n"
"  \rOur scouts have reported seeing some Goblin Shamans up in the mountains "
"to the North and East of the city. Unlike common raiders, the Shamans "
"possess more intelligence, as well as some magical aptitude. It is possible "
"that they are responsible for the severity of this raid. I need you to head "
"up that mountain pass, determine what is causing the raid on our city, and "
"stop it.\r\n"
"  \rHead Northeast and find and destroy whatever is behind the Goblin raid."

msgid "start_text_quest_10028"
msgstr ""
"The city of Monkfield has long been the mining and smelting capital of "
"Mercia.  Our mine, Northwest up the mountain, has some of the richest iron "
"veins in all of Agon.\r\n"
"  \rI hadn't received a report from our foreman in two days, so I sent a "
"scout up to check on them.  What he found was horrifying... they're all "
"dead...sort of. As of now there is an undead infestation throughout our "
"entire operation. I don't understand what could have happened, but I need "
"someone to go take care of these monsters, and find some answers.\r\n"
"  \rHead North up the mountain and find out what happened with the miners."

msgid "start_text_quest_10029"
msgstr ""
"Owing to our history as a mining hub, the men of Monkfield have long wielded "
"Greataxes in combat since they handle like a Pickaxe.  In fact, that "
"standard issue weapon of the Monkfield Militia is a special Great Axe known "
"as the Aernaran. Seeing as these dark times don't appear to be ending "
"anytime soon, I could stand to keep the city stockpile full of mighty axes."
"\r\n"
"  \rCraft me a bunch of Aernarans, and I will pay you handsomely, and make "
"some other work available to you as well.\r\n"
"  \rCraft 25 Aernaran Greataxes."

msgid "start_text_quest_10030"
msgstr ""
"Cearl and Stonegar would have you believing that the Monkfield Militia is an "
"elite military unit.  In reality they are just farmers and merchants with "
"clubs.\r\n"
"  \rThey need all the help they can get.  Especially the magical kind.  A "
"very useful enchantment is that of \"Feather\".  It magically makes armor "
"lighter to help with spellcasting and archery.  The Enchanting component "
"order is Horn, Quartz, and Cinder, with a catalyst of Numen.\r\n"
"  \rCraft me a Enchanted Crystal that will help give our brave militiamen an "
"edge over whatever monsters they face, and I'll pay you well for them.\r\n"
"  \rCraft 1 Enchanted Crystal."

msgid "start_text_quest_10031"
msgstr ""
"One interesting fact not many people know about Goblins...They bite!\r\n"
"  \rI can't tell you how many of our militia members have been coming back "
"in here with nasty bites all over their legs from downed Goblins making a "
"last ditch effort to fight back. If you could hammer out a few pairs of "
"Chainmail Chausses that I could give to the militia I would really "
"appreciate it, and I am sure the guys will thank you too!\r\n"
"  \rCraft 25 Chain Chausses."

msgid "start_text_quest_10032"
msgstr ""
"It is no secret that the \"Mages\" in the Monkfield Militia are just "
"whichever of the locals could afford a basic magic staff, and have at least "
"enough intelligence to create some magic light.\r\n"
"  \rWhat doesn't help is the fact they wear the same armor as the rest of "
"the troops going out to fight the Goblins and whatever else attacks the "
"town. Lighter sleeves would go a long way in helping our magic users to be "
"more effective.  Can you please craft them some?\r\n"
"  \rCraft 25 Cloth Arms."

msgid "start_text_quest_10033"
msgstr ""
"The rate at which the Militia is burning through my Magic Staff stockpile is "
"alarming. I don't know if they are really casting that many spells against "
"the Goblins, or if they just have no idea how to use the things properly!\r\n"
"  \rIn any case, I really need to get a bunch more as fast as possible.  "
"Would you be able to help out with this?  I'll give you fair value for "
"whatever you make.\r\n"
"  \rCraft 25 Troll Staves."

msgid "start_text_quest_10034"
msgstr ""
"Once you have progressed far enough in the Lesser Magic school, you will "
"gain the ability to Greater Magic spells.\r\n"
"  \rOne of the earliest, and also most useful, spells in this school is "
"called Rend.  This spell fires a fast moving bolt out at your enemies which "
"causes them to bleed over time, and also makes them more vulnerable to "
"piercing attacks like Arrows and Polearms.Show me you have mastered this "
"spell by using it against your enemies and you can progress on to the next "
"stage of mage training.\r\n"
"  \rUse Rend 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10035"
msgstr ""
"Seems that not long after you had destroyed that temple in the mountains, a "
"few groups of Malaut Cultists along with undead abominations started coming "
"in from the West.\r\n"
"  \rMy guess would be that your elimination of their plans directly North of "
"the city have forced them to move more quickly with their originally planned "
"attack.\r\n"
"  \rWe need you to go out and meet these dark mages and their undead pets "
"before they get too close to the city so we have more time to organize and "
"gather more intelligence.\r\n"
"  \rHead West and Kill 5 Malaut Acolytes, 2 Malaut Beguilers and 10 Greater "
"Servants."

msgid "start_text_quest_10036"
msgstr ""
"The extra time you bought us by stopping those early attacks on Monkfield "
"have paid off. Our scouts to the North have found the Goblin army which is "
"poised to charge down onto our city.\r\n"
"  \rWhile their initial plan of a multi-pronged assault has been thoroughly "
"dashed, this sizeable swarm of greenskins still poses a very real threat.\r\n"
"  \rI need you to head up North and wipe them all out.  Afterwards report to "
"our militia captain in the area, Arduin Strayshadow.\r\n"
"  \rHead Northeast past the mountain and kill 35 Goblin Marauders at their "
"staging area around the lake."

msgid "start_text_quest_10037"
msgstr ""
"Before you came through like a whirlwind and started chopping Goblins to "
"bits, I observed a group of Malaut heading to a destroyed homestead "
"Southwest of this outpost.\r\n"
"  \rA few seasons ago the family who lived there got caught in an "
"unfortunate Goblin raid, and none of them survived.  Those dark cultists "
"appeared to have shovels, and started casting some necromantic spells, so I "
"think we both know what that means.\r\n"
"  \rPlease go and clear that filth out of here, and put the souls of that "
"poor family to rest.\r\n"
"  \rHead Southwest and kill the Malaut and Undead at the ruins."

msgid "start_text_quest_10038"
msgstr ""
"While you were taking care of those rogue necromancers, I was North over "
"this hill taking a look at this very finely put together fort.  Much too "
"well built to be the doing of Goblins.\r\n"
"  \rSure enough, there has been a steady stream of the Malaut Cultists, as "
"well as a few hideous looking things in red robes, alongisde what I would "
"consider the meanest looking greenskins I've seen around here.\r\n"
"  \rThis is going to be one hell of a fight, but that fort represents the "
"leadership of this attacking army. I don't care if you have to call in some "
"friends, just take them out.\r\n"
"  \rGo North and Kill 5 Goblin Warlords, and 5 Below."

msgid "start_text_quest_10039"
msgstr ""
"Well we have done some really great work out here, and I think our leaders "
"over in Monkfield need an update so they can figure out what, if any, other "
"threats are out there.\r\n"
"  \rPlease go back to Cearl the Councillor and give him a thorough account "
"of what happened here.\r\n"
"  \rGo South back to Monkfield and talk to Cearl the Councillor"

msgid "start_text_quest_10040"
msgstr ""
"While you were fighting up North I sent one of my best scouts, Eleanor "
"Wilde, to survey the road South out of town and make sure no other attack "
"was imminent.\r\n"
"  \rRight now we need some more manpower though, and Eleanor is of a noble "
"lineage related to the Grayvales, our cities oldest family.  Count Grayvale "
"maintains a fairly large household guard, and I was hoping that Eleanor and "
"you could convince him to have his troops defend our Southern flank while we "
"focus back West where these Malaut Cultists seem to be coming from. Please "
"head South and link up with Eleanor, and then go West to Castle Grayvale.\r\n"
"  \rGo South and talk to Eleanor Wilde."

msgid "start_text_quest_10041"
msgstr ""
"We have been so focused on reacting to the immediate threat, I'm afraid we "
"have done a terrible job in keeping the greater authorities back in Sanguine "
"apprised of the situation here.\r\n"
"  \rI can think of no person more suited to give a full accounting of "
"everything than you.  Please head East back to Sanguine and tell Allan the "
"Councillor everything that happened here.  I would also think that he should "
"inform the King to make sure that he can make any larger decisions that may "
"impact the entire Mercian Empire.\r\n"
"  \rHead East and talk to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10042"
msgstr ""
"Since you successfully earned the first Dexerity title, I can now make "
"available to you a way to enhance your badge with even more power.  Mind you "
"this challenge will be substantially harder than the first.\r\n"
"  \rFirst you must go into the camps of the feral Centaur and slaughter a "
"great many of them.  Centaur use bows and spears and will swarm and charge "
"anyone entering their forests.  After that, you have to hunt down several "
"dozen deadly Nalaeds.  They are the stronger form of Lizardmen, and use "
"deadly acid attacks on their enemies and have terribly sharp claws.\r\n"
"  \rKill 100 Centaurs and 25 Nalaeds."

msgid "start_text_quest_10043"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"  \rThis challenge will be far tougher than the last two.  You will need to "
"hunt down one of the deadliest hunters of all, pre-historic Raptors.  They "
"prowl in packs on the sub-continent of Yssam, and tear their prey apart with "
"claws and teeth, ambushing with surprising speed.  I wish you the best of "
"luck in this, and hope to see you again!\r\n"
"  \rKill 100 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_10044"
msgstr ""
"The next of the Vitality titles, The Hardy, requires that you muster all the "
"courage you have and face a large number of Re-Animated Skeletons.  These "
"monsters were raised from the dead with dark magic, and care only about "
"destroying the living.\r\n"
"  \r#PlayerName#, are you ready to go hunting in dark dungeons and corrupted "
"graveyards to slay these undead in order to enhance your Vitality title "
"badge?\r\n"
"  \rKill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_10045"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready for the final upgrade for your "
"Vitality title badge.  Be warned, this will be a more dangerous task than "
"the previous ones.\r\n"
"  \rYou will first have to go delving into ancient ruins in search of deadly "
"Revenants, survive their magical attacks and powerful melee weapons.  "
"Afterwards you will need to head into the sacred forests of Agon and hunt "
"down massive Oak Lords, who have massive limbs and thundering attacks.\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Revenants and 25 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_10046"
msgstr ""
"Many people consider Mages to be masters of the elements.  It is only "
"fitting then that to upgrade your Intelligence title badge you must go out "
"and slay beings who are truly masters of the elements.\r\n"
"  \rYou will find Elementals, of Earth, Air, and Fire all around Mercia in "
"areas where there are particularly strong focal points for the raw "
"elements.  Be they Volcanos or Mountains, that is where you must go to "
"battle these beings of pure natural fury.  Do this and you will have earned "
"your title for The Sharp.\r\n"
"  \rKill 100 Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_10047"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to Tackle your toughest obstacle yet.  "
"In order to receive the final upgrade to your Intelligence badge, and the "
"title of The Smart, you must slay some of the most powerful evil creatures "
"on Agon.\r\n"
"  \rThese monsters are both deadly magic users, and powerful in melee range "
"as well.  You will have to travel far and wide and down into dark dungeons, "
"but if you can slay Crypt Guards, Deathless Mages, Black Knight and "
"Gravelords, the final Intelligence title will be yours.\r\n"
"  \rKill 10 Crypt Guards, 10 Deathless Mages, 10 Black Knights and 10 "
"Gravelords."

msgid "start_text_quest_10048"
msgstr ""
"Since you have proven yourself a reasonable accomplished brawler, I have "
"another challenge for you if you want to work towards upgrading your "
"Strength badge and get the title of The Brawny.\r\n"
"  \rI hope you brought some fire axes or something, because you'll need "
"them.  I want you to kill a ton of trolls.  The buggers are all over swamps "
"and ruins around Agon, and are always a menance.  In each large Troll camp "
"you will also find a Troll Lord.  These massive creatures are much deadlier "
"than their smaller brethren, and should be handled cautiously.\r\n"
"  \r#PlayerName#, are you ready to go off on this Troll hunt and earn your "
"next title?\r\n"
"  \rKill 200 Trolls and 30 Troll Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_10049"
msgstr ""
"The third and final title and badge upgrade avaialable for Strength is that "
"of The Strong.\r\n"
"  \rIn order to earn this you will have to wage war against one of the "
"deadliest foes Mercia has ever seen.  The Hobgoblin armies of The Raven "
"Standard are just as organized and militaristic as normal Hobgoblins, but "
"they are far deadlier.  The strongest amongst them are called Raven Standard "
"Officers, and are deadly with bows as well as melee weapons.\r\n"
"  \rI wish you luck, and that you take care.  Many an adventurer has been "
"lured into an ambush and slaughtered by these vicious Raven Standard "
"Hobgloblins.\r\n"
"  \rKill 100 Raven Standard Grunts, 50 Raven Standard Veterans and 20 Raven "
"Standard Officers."

msgid "start_text_quest_10050"
msgstr ""
"It is great to see people like yourself interested in the harvesting of raw "
"materials, but the next step is equally important.  Once you have collected "
"the items, you need to refine them into a state where they can be used.  "
"Whether this is cutting wood down into planks before they are used to built "
"a boat, smelting ingots which will become a suit of armor, or baking some "
"bread that will keep a hungry soldier well fed.  A true crafter must master "
"these steps as well.\r\n"
"  \rTo upgrade your Wisdom badge and get the title of The Knowledgeable, you "
"will have to prove your mastery over the arts of Woodcutting, Smelting, and "
"Cooking.\r\n"
"  \rSmelt 100 iron ingots, Cut 200 Oak Planks and Cook 200 food items."

msgid "start_text_quest_10051"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you have shown that you are well versed in the harvesting, and "
"intermediate preperatory steps of crafting.  Now you have your truest test, "
"creating finished products that can be used or sold.\r\n"
"  \rThe major fields of crafting are Armorsmithing, Bowyery, and Cooking. I "
"want you to create for me more complex items from each of these "
"professions.  Then you will have earned the 3rd Wisdom title of The Wise, "
"and the upgraded service badge as well.\r\n"
"  \rCraft 20 Plate Helms, 20 Longbows, and 20 Cheesesteaks."

msgid "start_text_quest_10052"
msgstr ""
"Most Merchants will tell you, the faster you can move, the better.  I find "
"this applies to all things in life as well.  If you are to earn the second "
"Quickness title, The Fleet, and get the upgraded enchanted badge, you have "
"to prove your speed by defeating an enemy that is fast as lightning.\r\n"
"  \rWindlords are large bird-men who are believe that the Goddess Rizurn, "
"the bird turned diety, was wronged by the God Auros, and as such it is their "
"duty to punish all the mortal races of Agon.  I know, pretty crazy right?  "
"But they are fast, deadly, and have a strong mastery over Lightning magic. "
"So good luck killing a few dozen nests full of them!\r\n"
"  \rKill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_10053"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to attempt to get the third and final "
"Quickness title and badge upgrade. But be warned, this challenge will "
"require more time and effort and the previous two combined.\r\n"
"  \rOne the island sub-continent of Yssam, there lives the fastest creature "
"in all of Agon, the Eodrin. These large, long-legged creatures are known for "
"being extremely territorial, and will chase prey down for miles once the "
"attack begins. I want to you track down these beasts and kill a few.  Then "
"you will have your final title reward.\r\n"
"  \rKill 20 Eodrin."

msgid "start_text_quest_10054"
msgstr ""
"Another usefull spell in the Greater Magic school is Missile Fury.  This "
"spell sends out a barrage of mana missiles, that do a good bit of damage, "
"and also slightly knocks-up your targets.  This is helpful for slowing down "
"attackers and allowing you to land additional spells more easily.\r\n"
"  \rNote that in order to advance your skills in Greater Magic you must use "
"a staff that is a higher rank than your dawnstaff.  You may need to work on "
"your Rend spell a bit before you can attempt Missile Fury.\r\n"
"  \rUse Missile Fury 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10055"
msgstr ""
"Killing Goblins sure does make you hungry!\r\n"
"  \rFeeding our troops when the come off the field is one of my top "
"priorities.  Could you please head out West to the lake, catch some fish, "
"and cook them up for me so I can give them to our brave militia?\r\n"
"  \rBring 5 Cooked Cod, 5 Cooked Trout, and 5 Tasty Herring to Eanna the "
"Merchant in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_10057"
msgstr ""
"Even though you can start casting some Greater Magic spells, you should "
"still work on more of the Lesser Magic spells that you can now cast as well."
"\r\n"
"  \rEldritch Sphere a stronger damage spell than Mana Missile, and requires "
"no reagents to cast. It has helped many a mage out in a bind!\r\n"
"  \rUse Eldritch Sphere 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10059"
msgstr ""
"The smiths of Monkfield have long been famous for their Great Mauls.  My "
"family has been providing them to all of Mercia for three generations now.  "
"Unfortunately I haven't really had the time to work on any orders outside of "
"what the Militia needs lately.\r\n"
"  \rIt seems like you are a pretty decent Weaponsmith.  Would you want to "
"give it a try and handle a few orders for me?  After you craft them bring "
"them back here so I can inspect them and prepare them for delivery to "
"Sanguine.  Once you are done I can give you some more work.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 Great Mauls, then bring them to Torgard the Fighter.."

msgid "start_text_quest_10060"
msgstr ""
"One of the most useful spells you will ever get is part of the Greater Magic "
"school.  Unburden is a spell that makes all your armor lighter for a short "
"period of time, so your spells will be much more effective.  Even a warrior "
"fully clad in heavy armor can cast a spell effectively if they use a high "
"level Unburden spell.\r\n"
"  \rI want you to start using this spell, and also try to do so in combat as "
"you will gain much more mastery over it that way.\r\n"
"  \rCast Unburden 20 times"

msgid "start_text_quest_10061"
msgstr ""
"One of my best selling items at the Market in Sanguine is Banded Helmets.  "
"They are very popular with either warrior trainees, or adventurers who are "
"just starting out in their career.  I haven't been able to get around to "
"crafting some for sale, but I can hand this order over to you since you've "
"shown you have some skill as an Armorsmith.\r\n"
"  \rThe money should be pretty good, so if you have the time you should "
"craft some Banded Helms and then bring them for sale in Sanguine.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 Banded Helms, then bring them to Talaod the Blacksmith in "
"Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10062"
msgstr ""
"Sanguine is probably the busiest place in all of Agon.  That means their "
"inns and restaurants are always busy too, so the chefs and bakers in the "
"city rarely have time to make their own dough.\r\n"
"  \rI've made quite a name for myself as a great baker, but I have been "
"impressed by the cooking skills you've shown me so far.  Would you be "
"interested in filling this large order for Dough that I have received from "
"Sanguine?  The pay is decent, and it may open up opportunities for you down "
"the road.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 portions of Dough, then bring them to Simeon the Merchant in "
"Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10063"
msgstr ""
"While light armor doesn't provide a ton of protection, it is lightweight, "
"and pretty cheap to produce as well.  One of the most popular items I've "
"sold over the years for adventurers on a budget is Padded Chest Armor.\r\n"
"  \rGenerally speaking, I can sell out an order to Sanguine every few days "
"depending on the season.  Want to deliver an order?\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 Padded Armor Chest Pieces, then bring them to Simeon the "
"Merchant in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10064"
msgstr ""
"So long as there are wars being fought, and dungeosn for adventurers to "
"explore, there will be a need for healing potions.  Alchemy is truly a never "
"ending business!\r\n"
"  \rI've been so focused on supporting the Monkfield Militia that I haven't "
"had time to fulfill my normal orders to Sanguine.  Are you interested in "
"picking up some of this work?  After you make this delivery you can put "
"together another for me.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 25 Minor Healing Potions, then bring them to Niane the Arcanist "
"in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10065"
msgstr ""
"One of the benefits of being so close to historical Goblin breeding grounds "
"is the availability of Goblin Teeth for Staff Crafting.  Monkfield has long "
"been the main supplier of Goblin Angrystick Staves to Sanguine, and I see no "
"change in that tradition given recent Goblin activity.\r\n"
"  \rWhile my current stockpile needs to be used by the Militia, if you are "
"able to, you could take over a few shipments for me and craft these staves "
"and deliver them to Sanguine. You can do another order for me soon as you "
"get back from delivering the first!\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 Goblin Angrysticks, then bring them to Niane the Arcanist in "
"Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10066"
msgstr ""
"For every set of gear that an adventurer or clan warrior puts together, you "
"can bet they are going to need a handful of enchantments.  I've made myself "
"a nice little fortune working enchantments into Crystals to sell in "
"Sanguine, but figure I may as well share some of the wealth.\r\n"
"  \rSince you seem to be at least a partially competent Enchanter, if you "
"can work some magic on a few dozen Crystals I will gladly give them my mark "
"of approval so you can sell them in Sanguine.  One of my best sellers is the "
"Magnitude enchantment for staves.  The ingredient order for that enchantment "
"is Tooth, Venom Sac, Eye and a catalyst of Nith.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 10 Magic Crystals, then bring them to Jonn the Mage in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10067"
msgstr ""
"Monkfield's woodsman have long harvested fine timber from the trees to the "
"South and West.  From that wood our craftsman create fine bows that we sell "
"at the markets in Sanguine.\r\n"
"  \rMost of my Bowyers are working on getting our Militia well armed, but if "
"you have time and materials I can give you some orders to fill and bring to "
"the capital for sale.  Right now Flatbows are what Torgard in Sanguine was "
"looking to buy in bulk.\r\n"
"  \rCollect 20 Flatbows, then bring them to Torgard the Fighter in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_10068"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a big world, so having to travel around on foot everywhere is not "
"ideal. On my last trip a group of Goblins killed my mount, so I am in "
"desparate need of a new mount.\r\n"
"  \rThink you could tame one for me? Probably a good idea to make one for "
"yourself as well.\r\n"
"  \rHarvest 2 Steedgrass from bushes and use your Taming skill to create 2 "
"Mount Figurines."

msgid "start_text_quest_10069"
msgstr ""
"Once you have turned base materials into something usable, then you get to "
"the real fun of crafting!\r\n"
"  \rWe've been running through equipment at an alarming rate lately, so I "
"could use some help crafting some armor and weapons.\r\n"
"  \rUse my Anvil to craft a Chainmail Hauberk and a Short Sword. No slacking "
"either!\r\n"
"  \rCraft a Chainmail Hauberk and a Short Sword."

msgid "start_text_quest_10070"
msgstr ""
"When you are in the midst of a battle that is going poorly, few things are "
"more welcome than a potion of healing. The Sanguine Guards have been going "
"through quite a few these last weeks.\r\n"
"  \rIf you could use the Laboratory to the West to make a few potions,and "
"then head North to the Barracks, Torgard will reward you. He always carries "
"a few on him for the city guards.\r\n"
"  \rUse your Alchemy skill at the Laboratory to make 3 Minor Healing "
"Potions.  When you are done talk to Torgard the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_10071"
msgstr ""
"Axes have a shorter range than your one-handed swords, but they also pack "
"more of a punch.\r\n"
"  \rUsing your Axe and Shield with a Polearm is a favorite of some Alfar "
"weapons masters as when you get Axe Power-Attack it lowers resistances of "
"your opponent.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Axes"

msgid "start_text_quest_10072"
msgstr ""
"Clubs and Maces are strong and fast bludgeoning weapons, but you need to get "
"in real close to use em!\r\n"
"  \rBludgeoning damage hits well against heavy armor, and the Club Power-"
"Attack drains Stamina, so it is a good weapon for those who like a brawl.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Clubs and Maces"

msgid "start_text_quest_10073"
msgstr ""
"A Sword and Shield has been the warrior's mainstay for ages.  They are fast, "
"can hit pretty hard, and common all over the world.\r\n"
"  \rAdditionally, the Sword Power-Attack can bleed an enemy dry, and helps "
"in a pinch.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Swords"

msgid "start_text_quest_10074"
msgstr ""
"Greatswords are the most common weapon you will see on the battle-fields of "
"Agon.  They have a balanced mix of speed, range and slashing damage.\r\n"
"  \rAdditionally, the stabbing Power-Attack of a GreatSword can kill an "
"enemy well after the initial blow.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Greatswords"

msgid "start_text_quest_10075"
msgstr ""
"If you want to do a lot of damage from close up, a Greatclub will be your "
"best friend.\r\n"
"  \rGreatclubs do heavy Bludgeoning damage, and a Power-Attack from one will "
"tire out even a veteran.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Greatclubs"

msgid "start_text_quest_10076"
msgstr ""
"Hacking and Slashing in the front-lines is where you will find GreatAxe "
"users.\r\n"
"  \rA greataxe puts out a lot of damage, and has a devastating power-attack "
"that leaves an enemy more vulnerable to attacks, but takes more skill to "
"land your hits than a greatsword.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Greataxes"

msgid "start_text_quest_10077"
msgstr ""
"For close quarters combat there is nothing better than a sharp pair of "
"daggers.\r\n"
"  \rKnives require you to be right on top of your enemy, but put out a ton "
"of damage.  They are also favored by assassins for the Poison application of "
"their Power-Attack.\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 40 times using Knives"

msgid "start_text_quest_10078"
msgstr ""
"People looking to keep their distance while dealing a lot of damage with a "
"single swing prefer Polearms.\r\n"
"  \rPolearms are useful for keeping an enemy at distance, and combo nicely "
"with other piercing weapons.  Their Power-Attack also packs a nice punch!\r\n"
"  \rHit Monsters 20 times using Polearms"

msgid "start_text_quest_10079"
msgstr ""
"The first damage spell you will learn from the school of Fire Magic is "
"Firebolt.\r\n"
"  \rThis attack shoots a tiny bolt of fire in a straight line, and it moves "
"very quickly.  It does a good amount of damage, and is very effective "
"against many weaker and frost based monsters.\r\n"
"  \rUse Firebolt 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10080"
msgstr ""
"Ball Lightning is the initial damage spell you learn in the Air Magic school."
"\r\n"
"  \rWhen you cast it, a Ball of Lightning flies towards your target.  This "
"spell is very effective against water and metal based monsters.\r\n"
"  \rUse Ball Lightning 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10081"
msgstr ""
"Against bone or rock based enemies, Acid attacks are very strong.\r\n"
"  \rAcid Arrow is a rapid moving projectile which can also be used with "
"great effect against fleeing enemies.\r\n"
"  \rUse Acid Arrow 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10082"
msgstr ""
"Nothing works better against Fire Elementals, or other monsters of the Fire "
"domain, than water magic.\r\n"
"  \rIcicle fires a fast moving spike of ice which stabs into enemies with "
"great force.\r\n"
"  \rUse icicle 20 times against Monsters."

msgid "start_text_quest_10083"
msgstr ""
"A group of Trolls seem to have taken advantage of the situation with the "
"Malaut Cultists and Goblins all over.  Our scouts report that at least two "
"caravans were attacked by these Trolls, and several mounts were killed.\r\n"
"  \rWhile I don't think these creatures are involved with the larger attacks "
"on our city, they still need ot be dealth with.\r\n"
"  \rHead South and Kill 10 Trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_10084"
msgstr ""
"The first spell you will learn from the WithcCraft school is Needles.  This "
"spell allows you do fire a magical swarm of needles that explodes on impact."
"\r\n"
"  \rIt is best used against groups of enemies, and will help you master "
"WitchCraft so you can learn more useful spells afterwards.\r\n"
"  \rCast Needles 20 times on monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20000"
msgstr "Go South and Kill 10 Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_20001"
msgstr "Gather 5 goblin axes and 3 lizard on stick."

msgid "start_text_quest_20002"
msgstr "Kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_20003"
msgstr ""
"Gather 15 Iron Ore, 15 Stone, 15 Timber, 10 Cotton and catch 5 Fish then "
"bring them to Simeon the Merchant in the city."

msgid "start_text_quest_20004"
msgstr "Craft 5 Berry Oatmeals for Simeon"

msgid "start_text_quest_20005"
msgstr "Craft 2 Mounts for Simeon.  One for you, one for him."

msgid "start_text_quest_20006"
msgstr "Head North and talk to Talaod the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_20007"
msgstr ""
"Use the Smelter to the East to make 6 Iron Ingots, then use the Workbench to "
"North to make 6 Wood Planks, and Tan 6 pieces of Leather."

msgid "start_text_quest_20008"
msgstr "Craft a Chainmail Hauberk and a Short Sword."

msgid "start_text_quest_2001"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialynna the Councilor. Report to Isenda the "
"Clever in the {$i13} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_20014"
msgstr ""
"Bring 5 Cooked Cod, 5 Cooked Trout, and 5 Tasty Herring to Eanna the "
"Merchant in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20015"
msgstr "Kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_20016"
msgstr "Gather 200 iron ore, 300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish."

msgid "start_text_quest_20017"
msgstr ""
"Use the Sewer entrance, by the Bank, to the Northeast of here, and Kill 10 "
"Scumling Workers, 5 Scumling Guards and the Scumling Queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_20018"
msgstr ""
"Go into the backmost drainage basin in the sewers, kill the zombies, and "
"collect 6 Corpseflesh to bring to Jonn the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_20019"
msgstr "Use your Staff Crafting skill at the Workbench to craft a Trollstaff."

msgid "start_text_quest_2002"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Isenda the Clever. Kill three Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_20020"
msgstr ""
"Use your Alchemy skill at the Laboratory to make 3 Minor Healing Potions.  "
"When you are done talk to Torgard the Fighter for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_20021"
msgstr ""
"Use the Enchanting Ring to the West, and apply the Keen enchantment to a "
"Crystal."

msgid "start_text_quest_20022"
msgstr ""
"Kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_20023"
msgstr "Kill 200 Zombies, 100 Zombie Warriors and 20 Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_20024"
msgstr "Kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_20025"
msgstr "Kill 25 Goblins outside of Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20026"
msgstr ""
"Create 5 Enchanted Crystals and bring them to Selensha the Mage in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20027"
msgstr ""
"Create 5 Chain Hauberks and bring them to Wyl the Blacksmith in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20028"
msgstr "Create 5 Cloth Hats for Eanna the Merchant in Monkfield"

msgid "start_text_quest_20029"
msgstr "Collect 5 Rapiers and bring them to Stonegar the Fighter in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20030"
msgstr ""
"Collect 5 Troll Staves and bring them to Alric the Arcanist in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20031"
msgstr ""
"Collect 5 Minor Healing Potions and bring them to Alric the Arcanist in "
"Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20032"
msgstr "Collect 15 Iron Ore, 15 Timber, and 15 Stone for Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20033"
msgstr "Use Mana Missile 20 times against Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_20034"
msgstr "Hit Goblins 20 times using Archery."

msgid "start_text_quest_20035"
msgstr "Head Northeast up the mountain and kill 5 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_20036"
msgstr "Find the Dark Shrine and destroy it with your Melee Weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_20037"
msgstr ""
"Kill the Malaut Cultists so they cannot build another altar and re-organize "
"the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_20038"
msgstr "Head North up the mountain and Kill 5 Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_20039"
msgstr "Continue Northwest up the path and Kill 6 Skeletons"

msgid "start_text_quest_2004"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isenda the Clever. Kill four Guildmasters in "
"{$i14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_20040"
msgstr "Kill the Malaut Acolytes and avenge the Monkfield Miners."

msgid "start_text_quest_20041"
msgstr "Craft 25 Aernaran Greataxes"

msgid "start_text_quest_20042"
msgstr "Craft 1 Enchanted Crystal"

msgid "start_text_quest_20043"
msgstr "Craft 25 Chain Chausses"

msgid "start_text_quest_20044"
msgstr "Craft 25 Cloth Arms"

msgid "start_text_quest_20045"
msgstr "Craft 25 Troll Staves"

msgid "start_text_quest_20046"
msgstr "Use Rend 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20047"
msgstr ""
"Head West and Kill 5 Malaut Acolytes, 3 Malaut Beguilers and 10 Greater "
"Servants"

msgid "start_text_quest_20048"
msgstr ""
"Head Northeast past the mountain and kill 35 Goblin Marauders at their "
"staging area around the lake"

msgid "start_text_quest_20049"
msgstr "Head Southwest and kill the Malaut and Undead at the ruins"

msgid "start_text_quest_2005"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isenda the Clever. Report to Celetia the "
"White of the Circle of Neith."

msgid "start_text_quest_20050"
msgstr "Go North and Kill 5 Goblin Warlords, and 5 Below"

msgid "start_text_quest_20051"
msgstr "Go South back to Monkfield and talk to Cearl the Councillor"

msgid "start_text_quest_20052"
msgstr "Go South and talk to Eleanor Wilde"

msgid "start_text_quest_20053"
msgstr ""
"Go West and Kill the Outlaws who murdered Eleanor and find out more about "
"what happened."

msgid "start_text_quest_20054"
msgstr ""
"Move towards Back and the climb Up the Castle to search for and Kill the "
"Malaut Cultists."

msgid "start_text_quest_20055"
msgstr "Head up the ladder to the top of the turret and Kill the Evil Leaders"

msgid "start_text_quest_20056"
msgstr "Head East and talk to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_20057"
msgstr "Kill 100 Centaurs and 25 Nalaeds."

msgid "start_text_quest_20058"
msgstr "Kill 100 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_20059"
msgstr "Kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 20 Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_2006"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, we now have the goblin infestation under control "
"here in Silverspear.   \r\n"
"\r\n"
"An old enemy from the past has appeared within the tribelands once more. It "
"is the Gnolls. Mahirim and Gnoll have always been at war since ancient "
"times. Many times have we defeated and driven the Gnolls out of the "
"tribeland. This time the Gnolls have been sighted to the south of here in "
"the {$i13} region. Silverspear must do its part in driving this enemy out of "
"the tribelands once more. If you wish to assist us, go report to Isenda the "
"Clever."

msgid "start_text_quest_20060"
msgstr "Kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20061"
msgstr "Kill 100 Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_20062"
msgstr ""
"Kill 10 Crypt Guards, 10 Deathless Mages, 10 Black Knights and 10 Gravelords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20063"
msgstr "Kill 200 Trolls and 30 Troll Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20064"
msgstr ""
"Kill 100 Raven Standard Grunts, 50 Raven Standard Veterans and 20 Raven "
"Standard Officers."

msgid "start_text_quest_20065"
msgstr "Smelt 100 iron ingots, Cut 200 Oak Planks and Cook 200 food items."

msgid "start_text_quest_20066"
msgstr "Craft 20 Plate Helms, 20 Longbows, and 20 Cheesesteaks."

msgid "start_text_quest_20067"
msgstr "Kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20068"
msgstr "Kill 20 Eodrin."

msgid "start_text_quest_20069"
msgstr "Use Missile Fury 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_2007"
msgstr ""
"We are currently organizing a campaign against the Gnolls. The fact that the "
"Gnolls may be racial relatives to us, does not change a thing. The "
"tribelands belong to the Mahirim, and as the strongest race we are, shall "
"continue to rule these lands. Our scouts have discovered that the Gnolls "
"have set up camps to the west of here. We must act swiftly before they "
"managed to strengthen their presence in the area. You are to go into their "
"camps and kill at least three Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_20070"
msgstr ""
"Bring 10 Cooked Cod, 10 Cooked Trout, and 10 Tasty Herring to Eanna the "
"Merchant in Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_20071"
msgstr "Collect 25 Shortbows and bring them to Stonegar the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_20072"
msgstr "Use Eldritch Sphere 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20073"
msgstr "Craft 25 Minor Healing Potions."

msgid "start_text_quest_20074"
msgstr "Collect 20 Great Mauls"

msgid "start_text_quest_20076"
msgstr "Use Unburden 20 times"

msgid "start_text_quest_20077"
msgstr "Collect 20 Banded Helms"

msgid "start_text_quest_20079"
msgstr "Collect 20 portions of Dough"

msgid "start_text_quest_20081"
msgstr "Collect 20 Padded Armor Chest Pieces"

msgid "start_text_quest_20083"
msgstr "Collect 25 Minor Healing Potions"

msgid "start_text_quest_20085"
msgstr "Collect 20 Goblin Angrysticks"

msgid "start_text_quest_20087"
msgstr "Collect 2 Magic Crystals"

msgid "start_text_quest_20089"
msgstr "Collect 20 Flatbows"

msgid "start_text_quest_2009"
msgstr ""
"To the south of here, in the {$i14} region, there are several small human "
"settlements. \r\n"
"The humans have always kept to themselves and their pathetic little lives, "
"and always stayed within their settlements. This is the only reason why they "
"still live. Now it seems the humans have grown too arrogant and comfortable "
"here within the tribelands. The humans have now started attacking our "
"caravans along the trade routes. This is far beyond their normal behavior "
"and what we allow. The weak humans need to be reminded where they are. \r\n"
"It is the Guildmasters that have authorize the attacks upon our caravans. It "
"is time for somebody to pay them a visit. Kill four of their Guildmasters. "
"That should be a clear enough message."

msgid "start_text_quest_20091"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_20092"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Clubs."

msgid "start_text_quest_20093"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Swords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20094"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Greatswords."

msgid "start_text_quest_20095"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Greatclubs."

msgid "start_text_quest_20096"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Greataxes."

msgid "start_text_quest_20097"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 40 times with Knives."

msgid "start_text_quest_20098"
msgstr "Hit Monsters 20 times with Polearms."

msgid "start_text_quest_20099"
msgstr "Use Firebolt 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_2010"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , you have been of tremendous help. I need somebody to go to "
"the Circle of Neith. I trust that you could do this for me. You shall go and "
"find Celetia the White of the Circle of Neith and report to her about all "
"that has happened here.  You will find the Circle of Neith to the northwest "
"of here in the {$h12} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_20100"
msgstr "Use Ball Lightning 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20101"
msgstr "Use Acid Arrow 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20102"
msgstr "Use Icicle 20 times against Monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20103"
msgstr "Head South and Kill 10 Trolls"

msgid "start_text_quest_20104"
msgstr "Cast Needles 20 times on monsters"

msgid "start_text_quest_20105"
msgstr "Attack Goblins 8 Times While Mounted"

msgid "start_text_quest_2011"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Andor-Kai. Report to Isinda-Dai in the {$k13} "
"region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2012"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isinda-Dai. Kill four Hivekin Foragers and "
"two Hivekin Soldiers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2013"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isinda-Dai. Extract four claws from the "
"hivekin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2014"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isinda-Dai. Kill three Centaurs inside {$l13} "
"forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_2015"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isinda-Dai. Report to Mardem-kai at the "
"Wolfmasks headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2016"
msgstr ""
"With your help, we have successfully halted the goblin threat. It will be a "
"while before the goblins become a problem again. There are reports of "
"another threat brewing further to the south of here. The region of {$k13}, "
"has become infested by hivekin. The hivekin are a race of foragers, whose "
"instincts and appetites lead them to invade territories that contain large "
"amounts of edible material. We must stop them before they destroy the lands."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help fight the Hivekin infestation, report to Isinda-Dai. You "
"will find her in the {$k13} region to the south of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2017"
msgstr ""
"This region is overrun by a numberless horde of Hivekin, stripping the land "
"of anything that is considered edible. The Hivekin will breed at an almost "
"inconceivable pace. If they continue multiplying and expanding at this race, "
"soon all of the region will turn into a wasteland.\r\n"
"I want you to reduce the threat by killing four Hivekin Foragers and two "
"Hivekin Soldiers. Groups of them can be found west and south of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2018"
msgstr ""
"As you may already know, magical items are made using ingredients which are "
"extracted from the bodies of slain monsters. Most monsters contain something "
"that may be of use, including the hivekin, whose claws and eyes are prized "
"by enchanters.\r\n"
"I want you to harvest four hivekin claws, from the hivekin. The closest "
"hivekin are a group of Foragers who are found to the south of here. There is "
"also a mixed group of Foragers and slightly tougher Soldiers has been "
"spotted to the west of here. You will need a skinner to extract the claws "
"from these pests. Four claws will do."

msgid "start_text_quest_2019"
msgstr ""
"The Forest of {$l13} is located to the east of here. Centaur and the Ciel "
"Fey are among the many residents of the forest. The tribe of Centaurs based "
"at {$l13} forest have been attacking many of our scouting parties entering "
"the forest. \n"
"\n"
"The Wolfmask have asked for somebody to do a bit of scouting on their behalf "
"and assess their strength. I believe you can do this. I want you to go to "
"{$l13} forest and slay three centaurs. Return to me when you are done, with "
"your assessment for their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2020"
msgstr ""
"I need you to deliver a message to the Wolfmasks headquarters. Once there, "
"seek out Mardem-Kai, and report to him, about how things are progressing in "
"the region. The Wolfmasks headquarters is located in the southest of here, "
"in the {$l14} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2021"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arkelia the Councilor. Report to Aurmon the "
"Brave."

msgid "start_text_quest_2022"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aurmon the Brave. Kill six kobolds found in "
"Lake {$k11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2023"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aurmon the Brave. Kill three Trolls and three "
"Kobolds upon the three plateaus in {$k11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2024"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aurmon the Brave. Harvest four units of troll "
"blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_2025"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aurmon the Brave. Report to Yaleria-Sai the "
"Able at the Longclaw headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2026"
msgstr ""
"Now that the goblins have been put back into their place, it is time to deal "
"with some other annoying intruders. A group of trolls and kobolds have been "
"making themselves quite comfortable in the {$k11} region. These are the "
"tribelands, and nobody makes themselves comfortable unless we say to. So, if "
"you feel the need for a little troll slaying, go report for duty with Aurmon "
"the Brave."

msgid "start_text_quest_2027"
msgstr ""
"We are currently organizing a large-scale military campaign, the goals of "
"which are to decimate the  growing troll and kobold population in the "
"region. If you wish to participate, you could start by helping us by "
"cleaning out Lake {$k11} from the kobolds. The lake lies southeast of here. "
"For your part, six kobolds will do."

msgid "start_text_quest_2028"
msgstr ""
"Slimy trolls and filthy kobolds have made their home just to east of here. "
"How sweet. Now, let's get to work. There is an ancient city just to the east "
"of here, that is situated upon three plateaus. That is where the trolls and "
"their kobolds friends have decided to suddenly call home. Unfortunately for "
"them, the Longclaw which I am a member of, have other plans for the area. "
"The three plateaus need to be cleared out. You can help the Longclaw by "
"killing three trolls and three kobolds."

msgid "start_text_quest_2029"
msgstr ""
"As you may already know, magical items are made using ingredients which are "
"extracted from the bodies of slain monsters. Most monsters contain something "
"that may be of use, including the blood of trolls. I want you to harvest "
"blood from the trolls. What better way to make good use of these stinking "
"trolls. Four units of troll blood should be enough. You will need a skinner "
"to extract the blood from the trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2030"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver a message to the Longclaw headquarters, about all that "
"we have achieved here. The Longclaw are very interested in hearing about our "
"progress. Report to Yaleria-Sai the Able at the Longclaw headquarters. You "
"will find Yalerai-Sai northwest of here in the {$i10} mountains."

msgid "start_text_quest_2031"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Kill six skeletons in "
"{$g19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2032"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Kill six Zombies in "
"{$g19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2033"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Extract four "
"Corpseflesh from the zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2035"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Report to Aelathil "
"Silverleaf of the Serene Spire."

msgid "start_text_quest_2036"
msgstr ""
"It seems we now have the goblin situation under control here in Leafhelm, "
"thanks to you. Unfortunately we have received word of another threat growing "
"to the south of here. In the {$g19} region, the natural beauty of the lands "
"has been polluted by unnatural forces. Zombies and skeletons are now roaming "
"the lands, infesting them with their unnatural life. This horrid event, must "
"be dealt with immediately.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until we discover what twisted powers have brought these tormented souls "
"back to Agon, we need to contain these undead as much as possible. If you "
"wish to help us, please start by attacking the group of skeleton to the "
"southeast of here. You may help by destroying six skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_2037"
msgstr ""
"We need to continue the cleansing of the lands by removing more of the "
"undead that infested the region of {$g19}. It is an insult to any civilized "
"race to allow undead to walk upon its lands, and on the lands of its "
"ancestors.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The time has come to deal with the zombies. These zombies are completely "
"under the control of their creators and will attack and kill anything that "
"approaches them. We cannot simple allow these lifeless bodies to exist. "
"Until we find the source behind this raising of the dead, we must do our "
"best to reduce their numbers. You can help by killing six of these zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2038"
msgstr ""
"Zombies are horrid disgusting creatures that must always be destroyed at any "
"cost. Still, it is possible to make use of them. Once a zombie is destroyed, "
"it is possible to harvest from its body Corpseflesh, an ingredients that can "
"be used  in the art of enchanting items and weapons. \n"
"\n"
"I want you to go and harvest four units Zombie Corpseflesh from the zombies "
"that have infested the lands to the south of here. You will need a skinner "
"to extract the Corpseflesh from the zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2040"
msgstr ""
"The Serene Spire is an ancient circle of mages, which is said to have "
"existed even before the Mirdain clans were united in a single nation. \n"
"\n"
"I need for you to go to the Serene Spire, and deliver this letter I have "
"written. It is a report about the zombies ans skeletons you had encountered "
"earlier. The Serene Spire is very interested in hearing about all we have "
"discovered about this recent undead outbreak. \n"
"\n"
"The Serene Spire is located in Iriendir, which is to the north of here. Once "
"there, hand this letter to Aelathil Silverleaf."

msgid "start_text_quest_2041"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lysandir the Councillor. Report to Naianir "
"Treedancer in the {$i17} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2042"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Naianir Treedancer. Kill six of the many "
"kobold that have taken over the {$i17} mines."

msgid "start_text_quest_2043"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Naianir Treedancer. Kill four of the trolls "
"that have taken over the small ancient site in {$i17}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2044"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Naianir Treedancer. Gather three units of "
"Timeless Blood, and deliver them to Lysandir the Councillor at Beladin's "
"Rest."

msgid "start_text_quest_2045"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lysandir the councillor. Deliver Lysandir's "
"letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow at the Arrowheads headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2046"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, we now have the goblin situation under control. "
"Beladin's Rest may continue it's peaceful way of life for now. \n"
"\n"
"The region of {$i17} is experiencing as sudden increase in its kobold "
"population, and the Arrowhead have requested out help. If you wish to help "
"us once more, please go and report to Naianir Treedancer who is already "
"gathering information about the kobolds in the region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2047"
msgstr ""
"The {$i17} region was once known for its great mines. Many mirdain had "
"worked here mining for rare gems and superior metals. \n"
"\n"
"Around fifty years ago, an unnatural flooding hit the mines, that eventually "
"resulted in the mines being abandoned and never used again. Once the waters "
"slowly drained away, kobolds started moving in establishing small villages, "
"and over the years transforming the old mines into a stronghold.\n"
"\n"
"Now the kobolds have become a problem in the area. With their numbers "
"increasing they have become a plague. We must do our best to contain them, "
"and eventually eradicate them. We could definitely do with the extra help. "
"If you wish to assist, you can start by killing six kobolds."

msgid "start_text_quest_2048"
msgstr ""
"To the west of where we are standing now, there is an ancient site. The "
"authorities of Charybdis plan to start excavations there very soon, since "
"many scholars from the capital believe that the site may hold hidden "
"powerful artifacts. Our job is to assist the scholars by removing the trolls "
"that seems to have taken over the ancient site. I will ask of you to go to "
"the site, and kill at least four trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2049"
msgstr ""
"Lysandir the Councillor at Beladin's Rest has asked if it is possible that "
"we collect some troll blood. Ingredients like this is used when creating "
"enchanted magical items such as weapons. A group of trolls can be found to "
"the west of here, roaming among the ancient ruins in the lake. Using your "
"skinner, go gather three units of troll blood. Once you have collected the "
"troll blood, please deliver them to Lysandir the Councilor at Beladin's "
"Rest. I will remain here to continue my work. Thank you, for all you have "
"done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2050"
msgstr ""
"I need to send a message to the Arrowhead headquarters, to inform them about "
"the kobold infestation in the {$i17} mines. The Arrowhead had specifically "
"asked us to look into this problem for them, and send them a report. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I see no reason why you should not be the one to deliver this "
"letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow at the Arrowhead headquarters. If you accept, "
"you will find the Arrowhead headquarters to the southeast of here in {$j19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2051"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the councillor. Report to Larwain "
"Crystaldew."

msgid "start_text_quest_2052"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Larwain Crystaldew. Kill five ork bandits."

msgid "start_text_quest_2053"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Larwain Crystaldew. Kill six zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2055"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Larwain Crystaldew. Report to Elvallie the "
"Councillor at King's Holdfast."

msgid "start_text_quest_2056"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the councillor. Destoy the Ghoul "
"Devouer and report to Caradial Elmheart at the Emerald Throne."

msgid "start_text_quest_2057"
msgstr ""
"Now that the goblin threat has been dealt with, King's Holdfast may return "
"to a more peaceful way of life, thanks to you and a many more brave "
"adventures. Unfortunately, the same cannot be said for other neighboring "
"regions within Mirendil. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the east of King's Holdfast, in the {$i19} region, bandit orks have "
"appeared. We do not know yet if they are just bandits who plan to loot our "
"caravans, or an ork scouting party gathering information.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Larwain Crystaldew, has been sent to the region to investigate. If you wish "
"to assist us once more, please report to Larwian Crystaldew."

msgid "start_text_quest_2058"
msgstr ""
"It is very strange and worrying indeed, that orks have appeared within "
"Mirendil. We believe that these orks are planning to move into the area and "
"establish a stronghold, somewhere that they can use as a base for future "
"raids against our caravans and settlements. \n"
"\n"
"The enormous ancient crater that lies here in the {$i19} region, is a "
"perfect location for what these orks are looking for. So far I have "
"discovered that they are positioned at two locations. One group on this side "
"of the crater, northwest of us, and one other group on the far opposite side "
"from us. \n"
"\n"
"We must quickly attack them, before they really become a threat and "
"strengthen their hold in the area. You can help by killing at least five of "
"these orks. When you are done, report back to me with your assessment of "
"their strengths."

msgid "start_text_quest_2059"
msgstr ""
"Many years ago, there existed a small mining community situated at the "
"center of the crater northeast of here. At some point a mysterious illness "
"broke out, taking the lives of all that lived in the small mining village."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now very little remains of this once prosperous mining community. A few old "
"houses and a small graveyard, where the once local residents now rest in "
"peace. Or should I say, did rest in peace. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently, for some unknown reason, the residents have risen from their "
"graves as zombies, and walk once more among their old dwellings. This is "
"most unnatural, and it is our duty to put these miserable souls back to rest."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help by venturing down into the old settlement, and killing at least "
"six of these tormented souls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2061"
msgstr ""
"Now that we have confronted the ork bandits and have assessed their "
"strength, I would ask of you to return to Elvallie the Councillor and "
"deliver a message. These orks do not pose a threat to Mirendil, and will be "
"easily dealt with in the near future. We have nothing to fear from them. \n"
"\n"
"#PlayerName#, I thank you for all you have done. If you may, please deliver "
"this simple message to Elvallie the Councillor at King's Holdfast, that we "
"have nothing to fear from these orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2062"
msgstr ""
"The Emerald throne has asked for our assistance. They have been looking into "
"the recent outbreak of undead that have been reported throughout Mirendil. "
"The Emerald Throne is collecting information on all undead that can been "
"found. We have received information about a Ghoul Devouer been sighted "
"within an abandoned mine to the southwest of here. I would ask for you to "
"locate this ghoul, destroy it, and then go straight to the Emerald Throne to "
"report your assessment of it. Once you arrive at the Emerald Throne, report "
"to Caradial Elmheart."

msgid "start_text_quest_2063"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taelis the Councillor. Report to Marhek "
"Darkfrost."

msgid "start_text_quest_2064"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marhek Darkfrost. Kill six of the hivekin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2065"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marhek Darkfrost. Extract four claws from the "
"hivekin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2066"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marhek Darkfrost. Kill four hivekin "
"broodguards and the hivekin queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2067"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marhek Darkfrost. Report to Taelis the "
"Councillor at Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_2068"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taelis the Councillor. Deliver the human ear "
"to Shulazu Nightshade at the Radiant Circle headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2069"
msgstr ""
"With your help, we have successfully dealt with the goblin infestation. You "
"have proven yourself to be quite a valuable and capable ally. It will be a "
"while before the greenskins ever bother us again. Onghral has nothing to "
"fear. But beware. Just because we have repelled the goblins, it does not "
"mean that we will sit here and wait for the next enemy to arrive at our door "
"step. We must always be ready to strike out first.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Reports have arrived of another intruder. It is the Hivekin. The Hivekin are "
"a race of foragers, whose instincts and appetites lead them to invade "
"territories that contain large amounts of edible material and consume them. "
"They are a pest, they are a plague. We must stop the hivekin before their "
"destructive appetite reaches Onghral.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you believe you can continue to be of service to us, report to Marhek "
"Darkfrost. You will find him to the north of here in the {$m22} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2070"
msgstr ""
"These rat-like creatures called the hivekin, are becoming quiet a  problem. "
"Only recently have their numbers started rapidly to increase. The hivekins "
"only purpose in life is to multiply and consume the land. And when they have "
"destroyed everything, they then move on to elsewhere, and repeat their "
"destructive cycle. They are a plague. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The best solution is to round them all up, and dump them onto mirdain soil. "
"Unfortunately, that is not possible at the moment, so the only thing left "
"for us to do, is to reduce their numbers as much as possible. I want you to "
"go and kill six of those hivekin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2071"
msgstr ""
"I am sure by now, that you have heard of the art of enchantment, the "
"creating of magical items. Magical items are made using various ingredients "
"that can be extracted from the bodies of slain monsters. This means that "
"even the annoying hivekin, can provide specific enchanting ingredients to be "
"used in the enchanting of items such as weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest four hivekin claws. The closest hivekin group can be "
"found to the south of here. It is a group of hivekin foragers. You will need "
"a skinner to extract the claws from these pests. Four claws will do."

msgid "start_text_quest_2072"
msgstr ""
"The only way to eradicate this annoying hivekin plague, is to take down the "
"queen herself. This pathetic useless bag of flesh, is the center of all our "
"problems. Her only purpose in life is to bread and eat. Mind you, the queen "
"is always guarded by her lawful guardians, the broodguards, who are always "
"nearby. I want you to kill four broodguards and the hivekin queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2073"
msgstr ""
"Now that we have engaged and damaged the Hivekin, and clearly know they pose "
"no threat, I need of you to return to Onghral and deliver a simple message. "
"You are to report to Taelis the Councillor and inform him of our assessment "
"of the hivekin situation."

msgid "start_text_quest_2074"
msgstr ""
"The region of {$l24} to the southwest of here, is home to the Radiant "
"Circle, a mystical group of spellcasters that specialize in creating magical "
"items and researching new spells. The Radiant Circle is always interested in "
"acquiring materials that can be used in the creation of magical items. "
"Because of the power they wield, and their ties with Shoal, it is in our "
"best interest to keep on good terms with them. I want you to deliver this "
"human ear to the Radiant Circle. I believe you can manage this simple task, "
"yes?"

msgid "start_text_quest_2075"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Report to Laeseri "
"Poisonglow."

msgid "start_text_quest_2076"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Laeseri Poisonglow. Kill six kobolds."

msgid "start_text_quest_2077"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Laeseri Poisonglow. Kill three gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2078"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Laeseri Poisonglow. Gather three Gnoll "
"Stompers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2079"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Laeseri Poisonglow. Deliver Laesari's report "
"to Nirgash the Councillor at Deep Yishku."

msgid "start_text_quest_208"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Uzrok's quest. First kill four goblins, then return to "
"Chopping Necks for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2080"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Deliver Nirgash's "
"report letter to Aeshanta Darkspire at the Harn Mandean headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2081"
msgstr ""
"With your help and that of a few other gifted adventures, the goblins have "
"been sent back to the holes where they came from. Now it's time to deal with "
"other minor problems. To the east of here in the {$o22} region, kobolds and "
"gnolls have been establishing small villages. The Harn Mandean has "
"instructed us to look into this on their behalf. An order from the Harn "
"Mandean is something nobody takes likely. You are to report to Laeseri "
"Poisonglow. You will find Laesari to the northeast of here, in the {$o22} "
"region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2082"
msgstr ""
"The Harn Mandean has ordered us to assess the situation with the kobolds and "
"gnolls within the {$o22} region. It is a grand honor to be chosen by the "
"Harn Mandean to assist in one of their operations. Our orders are to gather "
"information on the gnolls and kobolds that have gathered in this region.\r\n"
"First, we will engage the kobolds. The kobolds are a races of inferior "
"pathetic little creatures, even more pathetic than the gnolls. These "
"physically weak and poorly equipped maggots, should not pose any difficulty "
"to you.\r\n"
"The kobold have build two villages to the east of here. Both of these "
"villages are not well fortified, so it should not be much of a problem for "
"you to engage them. Your mission is to infiltrate the kobold villages and "
"kill at least six kobolds."

msgid "start_text_quest_2083"
msgstr ""
"Now that we have dealt with the kobolds, it is time to move on to our next "
"target, the gnolls. The gnolls have built a small pathetic village to the "
"northeast of here. Based on the reports from the Harn Mandean, the gnolls "
"have started attacking our trade routes. Our task is to assess the strength "
"of these gnolls. The rest will be taken care of by the agents of the Harn "
"Mandean, once we have sent our report to them. You are to go to the gnoll "
"village and kill three of these gnolls. That should be enough to give us a "
"clear picture of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2084"
msgstr ""
"We need to gather all sorts of information about our enemies. One is to "
"discover their weapon of choice. Our agents have spotted that many of the "
"gnolls prefer to use a rather crude bludgeoning weapon, called a gnoll "
"stomper. The gnolls can be found to the northeast of here. I need for you to "
"go and bring me at least three gnoll stompers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2085"
msgstr ""
"We have successfully completed all that the Harn Mandean has asked of us. It "
"is not wise to keep the Harn Mandean waiting. It is time to send a report "
"back with our estimation of the situation. I need for you return to Deep "
"Yishku and to report to Nirgash the Councillor. Please deliver this report "
"to Nirgash. Nirgash will decide what to do with this information. You have "
"done quite enough, now go!"

msgid "start_text_quest_2086"
msgstr ""
"The Harn Mandean are expecting a report from us. We must not keep them "
"waiting. #PlayerName# , you have performed well. I was correct in trusting "
"you with this mission. I see it only fitting that you deliver the final "
"report to the Harn Mandean headquarters. The Harn Mandean headquarters are "
"located northwest of here in the {$m21} region. Once there, deliver this "
"report to Aeshanta Darkspire."

msgid "start_text_quest_2088"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Irshanta the Councillor. Report to Mugash "
"Blackhaunt."

msgid "start_text_quest_2089"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Mugash Blackhaunt. Kill six skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_209"
msgstr ""
"There are some goblins who don't know their place in the world, which is to "
"always do what the orks tell them. Two days ago, a goblin slave gang "
"overwhelmed and killed their masters before fleeing into a nearby swamp. We "
"must hunt down each and every one of these rebels, thereby showing all "
"goblins that insubordination carries a terrible cost.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Luckily, goblins are helplessly lost without an ork to whip them around and "
"shout orders at them. In fact, some of the escaped slaves have already begun "
"to drift back towards Chopping Necks in search of food and shelter. "
"Yesterday, travelers reported seeing small, green-skinned creatures which "
"were skulking about the swamps to the north of town, and to the east near "
"and old abandoned site.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to teach the escaped goblins a lesson by killing four of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2090"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mugash Blackhaunt. Extract three units of "
"Corpseflesh from the zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2091"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mugash Blackhaunt. Destroy four Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_2092"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mugash Blackhaunt. Deliver Mugash's report "
"letter to Nathar Blackorb at the Temple of the God-King."

msgid "start_text_quest_2093"
msgstr ""
"Now that the goblin infestation has been dealt with, it is time to focus on "
"other problems. The Temple of the God King has requested our help. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many years ago, several mining camps were planned to be built in the {$o24} "
"region to the south of here. It was an operation overseen by the Temple of "
"the God King. As the mining camps were completed, and the mining was about "
"to begin, the slaves that were to work at the mines mysteriously died all in "
"the same day, to only return back a few years later as undead. Now the "
"mining camps are overrun by skeletons and zombies. The Temple of the God "
"King wants to clear the mining camps of these lifeless shells. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You are to go to the {$o24} region and report to Mugash Blackhaunt. Mugash "
"will give you the details on what is needed to be done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2094"
msgstr ""
"Years ago the Temple of the God King decided to build mining camps in the "
"region. The reason was the enormous crystal structure that existed in the "
"southern part of the region. Many believe that the crystal is the result of "
"extremely powerful magic, from a long forgotten race that once walk the "
"surface of Agon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Temple of the God-King had organized and set up mining camps in the "
"area, to begin the mining of this giant crystal. The goal was to create the "
"highest quality armor and weapons Agon has ever seen, but also to unlock any "
"magical properties the crystal might hold. Just about as the mining was "
"about to begin, all the slaves that where assigned to work in the mines, "
"died. Many believed this was the work of the skeleton Dragon God Cyriacus, "
"who wanted to use the crystal for his own needs. Whatever the reason, our "
"task now is to start clearing out the mines. You will begin by destroying "
"six of the skeletons occupying the mines to the north."

msgid "start_text_quest_2095"
msgstr ""
"It is a good opportunity for us, to collect ingredients that can be used in "
"the creation of magical items. The bodies of many slain monsters can provide "
"us with such ingredients. A group of zombie warriors has been sighted to the "
"northeast of here. By slaying them, it is possible to extract from their "
"bodies corpseflesh. Corpseflesh can be used for enchanting items. \n"
"\n"
"I want you to go and extract three units of corpseflesh from the zombies. "
"You will need a skinner for this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2096"
msgstr ""
"The largest of the mining camps is located southeast of here, right next to "
"the giant crystal. It is there that the largest number of the undead are "
"gathered, not to mention some of the strongest. It is that mining camp, that "
"the Temple of the God-King is most interest in cleaning up. \n"
"\n"
"You are to go there and destroy the strongest of the undead, the Bone "
"Knights. Your mission is to destroy four Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_2097"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mugash Blackhaunt. Deliver Mugash's report "
"letter to Nathar Blackorb at the Temple of the God-King."

msgid "start_text_quest_2098"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skuldvard the Councillor. Report to Dis "
"Fatespinner."

msgid "start_text_quest_2099"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dis Fatespinner. Gather four units of "
"corpseflesh."

msgid "start_text_quest_210"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Uzrok the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2100"
msgstr ""
"You  have accepted a quest from Dis Fatespinner. Kill six skeletons in "
"{$o10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2101"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dis Fatespinner. Kill three Dire Zombies in "
"{$o10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2102"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dis Fatespinner. Report to Garin Silvervault "
"at the Voice of Ymir headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2103"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, we now have the goblin situation under control in "
"Eirhjelm. The goblins will not be troubling our village, or attack our "
"trading routes anymore. You have done well.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A request has arrived from the Voice of Ymir, asking us to choose somebody "
"we can trust to assist them. The Voice of Ymir is disturbed with the recent "
"sighting of undead  in {$o10}, to the south of here. Until their agents can "
"discover to cause behind this unnatural event, they need able heroes like "
"yourself to help detain the undead in the region. Dis Fatespinner is already "
"located in the area, gathering information. Please report to her. She will "
"inform you of what is needed to be done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2104"
msgstr ""
"We shall continue now with another type of undead that have appeared in the "
"swamps, the awful zombies. What I need is a few samples of their rotting "
"flesh. I want you to go and extract four units of corpseflesh. You will need "
"to use a skinner for this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2105"
msgstr ""
"I have been assigned by the Voice of Ymir, to gather information about the "
"undead outbreak in this region. The undead have spawned out of nowhere, and "
"for the time being occupy the swampy waters of this region. I will need of "
"you to help me gather as much information possible, so we may understand "
"what exactly is happening here. We can begin from the group of skeleton that "
"is near by. \n"
"\n"
"These fleshless remains now walk aimlessly here within the swamps, attacking "
"anybody. If we allow them to move beyond this area, who knows what damage "
"they might do to the local communities. We must do are best to contain them. "
"You can help be destroying six of the skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_2106"
msgstr ""
"The next task I have for you is to help me assess the strength of these "
"undead. If we are to eliminate them, first we must know everything we can "
"about them. From the little scouting I have done, I have discovered that the "
"strongest of these undead are the Dire Zombies. So far the Dire Zombies seem "
"to be concentrated at the far end of the swamp area, southwest of here. I "
"would ask of you to go and engage this group of Dire Zombies, kill at least "
"three of them, and return to me with your assessment."

msgid "start_text_quest_2107"
msgstr ""
"I believe we have now gathered enough information on the undead, to send a "
"report to the Voice of Ymir. #PlayerName#, I want you to deliver my report "
"to their headquarters. The Voice of Ymir's headquarters is located to the "
"northwest of here. Once you reach them, seek out Garin Silvervault, and hand "
"the report to him. I will remain here to gather what other information I can."

msgid "start_text_quest_2108"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arngard the Councillor. Report to Skathi "
"Shieldmaiden."

msgid "start_text_quest_2109"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skathi Shieldmaiden. Destroy six skeletons in "
"{$q08}."

msgid "start_text_quest_211"
msgstr ""
"A group of goblin slaves ran away two days ago, taking with them axes they "
"had been using to cut firewood for sacrificial pyres. While the escaped "
"goblins are cheap to replace, the axes are quite pricey, which is why I want "
"you to retrieve them for me. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes. The closest goblins are a group of "
"Scouts who are foraging  to the east of town. There is also another group to "
"the north of here, among the ruins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2110"
msgstr ""
"YYou have accepted a quest from Skathi Shieldmaiden. Kill six kobolds in "
"{$q08}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2111"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skathi Shieldmaiden. Search the kobold camp "
"in Otredale for the Horn of the Five."

msgid "start_text_quest_2112"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Horn of the Five. Bring it to Skathi Shieldmaiden, and "
"claim your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2113"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skathi Shieldmaiden. Deliver the Horn of the "
"Five to Garn Runeshield at the Five Beards Trading Company's headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2114"
msgstr ""
"The goblins have been driven back to the mountains, back into the filthy "
"holes that spawned them. Hammerdelve is grateful for all you have done. Now "
"it is time to deal with other issues. There is always some other enemy to "
"battle, or obstacle to overcome.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many years ago, to the east of here, the great dwarven mines of Otredale "
"would echo throughout the lands. Long has it been since anybody has heard "
"the sound of  pickaxes and hammers echoing throughout the mountains. Now the "
"mines are deserted, and home to skeletons and kobolds. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The time has come to reclaim the mines back. Skathi Shieldmaiden is already "
"in the area, assessing the situation. If you believe you could be of help to "
"us once more, report to Skathi Shieldmaiden."

msgid "start_text_quest_2115"
msgstr ""
"The dwarven mines of Otredale were once the pride of northern Dvergheim. "
"Fine armors and weapons would be crafted from the superior metals that would "
"be extracted from the legendary mines, and many master blacksmiths "
"throughout northern Dvergheim would have their hands fulls with orders. Now, "
"these once great mines are only a mere shadow of their glorious past.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mines to the north of here are overrun by skeletons, while the mines to "
"the east are home to a clan of filthy koblods. An operation has began to "
"clean out the mines. You may help by destroying six skeletons in the mines "
"to the north of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2116"
msgstr ""
"We will continue now with the mines to the east of here, which are located "
"just across the waters. A clan of kobolds have set camp just outside the "
"entrance to the mines, making it impossible for the miners to work.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These kobold have been a nuisance for a long time now. It is time to "
"demolish their little camp, and send them running back from wherever they "
"came from. You can help by slaying six of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2117"
msgstr ""
"A letter has arrived from the Five Beards Trading Company. One of their "
"caravans was ambushed by a group of kobolds, and in that ambush most of the "
"cargo was lost. Amongst all the cargo that was stolen, was one very "
"important item. An item that has been with the Five Beards Trading Company "
"from the beginning of their founding. This important item is the Horn of the "
"Five. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Horn of the Five was used by the founders of the Five Beards Traders to "
"announce the arrival of a caravan as it was approaching its final "
"destination. The sounding of the Horn of the Five was a much welcomed sound "
"at every trading post. It would let the merchants know that is was the "
"caravan of the Five approaching, especially when the weather was bad and "
"visibility was low because of the fog.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Horn of Five is an item mostly of historical value to the Five Beards, "
"and that is why they are very keen in having it return to their "
"headquarters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our agents have located the kobold bandits that now have the horn in their "
"possession. This bandit kobolds have set their base on the island in "
"Otredale to the southeast of here, and we believe that the Horn of the Fives "
"should be located at the heart of their camp. If you accept this mission, I "
"suggest you search for a chest. Once you locate it, use the action button to "
"investigate more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_2118"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you have been most helpful. Not only have you helped with the "
"cleaning of the mines, but also successfully retrieved the legendary Horn of "
"the Five.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now that we have the Horn of the Five in our possession, it is time to "
"deliver it to the Five Beards Trading Company. I would ask of you to deliver "
"it. You will find the Five Beards Trading Company in the Ringfain region to "
"the north of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, do you accept?"

msgid "start_text_quest_2119"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hrafnid the Councillor. Report to Magnus "
"Forkbeard."

msgid "start_text_quest_212"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigthug the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2120"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Magnus Forkbeard. Kill six kobolds in {$p10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2121"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Magnus Forkbeard. Kill four trolls {$p10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2122"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Magnus Forkbeard. Gather four three units of "
"Timeless Blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_2123"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Magnus Forkbeard. Report to Thain Strongforge "
"at the Order of the Axe."

msgid "start_text_quest_2124"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to you, Valfather's Edge is open to trade once more. Our caravans are "
"safely traveling along the road which connects Valfather's Edge to the "
"dwarven capital of Ymir's Tear. #PlayerName#, you have done well, but our "
"problems do not seem to end here. With the goblins out of the way, reports "
"have arrived about a tribe of kobolds that plans to continue from where the "
"goblin left off.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Magnus Forkbeard has been assigned to the {$p10} region which is to the west "
"of Valfather's edge, to look into this new problem. I ask of you to report "
"to Magnus and assist him in any way possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_2125"
msgstr ""
"So, you helped Valfarther's Edge deal with the goblins that were attacking "
"the trade routes. I am glad you are here now, to help with this new threat. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"With the goblins out of the way, our little kobold friends have decided to "
"take over attacking the trade routes. Ridiculous. We must rid our lands of "
"these pests as soon as possible. The kobolds can be found roaming among the "
"ruins to the north of here. You an help by slaying six of these annoying "
"kobolds."

msgid "start_text_quest_2126"
msgstr ""
"A report has arrived from the Order of the Axe. There seems to be more to "
"the kobolds than we thought. The kobolds have gathered here because they "
"have teamed up with a band of trolls. These trolls are the real problem. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A little further to the north of here, there are three massive stone towers. "
"These structures where once home to a clan of orks until the moment we "
"discovered them, and a campaign was launch against them. Ruins are all that "
"remains of the ork base, and not one ork to see. It is these same ruins now "
"that are being used by the trolls as a base for their attacks. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, once more we shall do battle within the stone towers. I need of you to "
"venture up into the stone towers, and assess the strength of the trolls. You "
"will need to find the elevator which is located on the far west of the three "
"towers to get up there. Once there, killing four trolls should give us a "
"clear picture of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2127"
msgstr ""
"Now that the Order of the Axe has informed us that the trolls are planning "
"to start attacks on our trade routes, and to steal our precious goods, I "
"believe that we could do a little stealing too. I would like of you to kill "
"enough of these trolls, to gather, no no, to steal three units of troll "
"blood. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you would know by now, the bodies of slain monsters can provide us with "
"ingredients that can be used in the creation of magical items, such as "
"weapons. By gathering this ingredient, this troll blood, the trolls will "
"actually be contributing to the growth of our trade. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The trolls are gathered in the ruins, up high in the stone towers, which "
"means they have nowhere to run to. All I ask is that you kill as many as you "
"need to, to successfully extract from their bodies three units of troll "
"blood. You will need a skinner to complete this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2128"
msgstr ""
"I need to get word as soon as possible to the Order of the Axe. I have "
"prepared a report here with my assessment of the situation regarding the "
"trolls. I would like you to deliver this report. You will find the Order of "
"the Axe to the south of here in {$p11}. Once there, seek out Thain "
"Strongforge.  #PlayerName#, I thank you for all you have done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2129"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Uzrok the Councillor. Harvest three units of "
"troll blood and deliver them to Stranglar Bloodaks in {$u12}. To complete "
"the mission, you will need a skinner."

msgid "start_text_quest_213"
msgstr ""
"In the heart of the orkish capital of {$v13} rises the Big Stair, a giant "
"altar from which dozens of sacrifices are thrown every day. Since the death-"
"thirst of the Fire Dragon is unquenchable, we now plan to increase our rate "
"of sacrifice here in Chopping Necks by building our own, slightly smaller "
"version of the Big Stair.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Since many of our local goblin slaves escaped recently, we could use some "
"help with gathering stones for this project. In order to collect stone, you "
"first need to hold a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may "
"buy one from Grabgold the Merchant's shop near the center of Chopping Necks. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2130"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Stranglar Bloodaks. Kill five trolls in "
"{$u12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2132"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Stranglar Bloodaks. Deliver the report letter "
"to Krushar Breakskull at the Iron Orks headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2133"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Stranglar Bloodaks. Collect a Ravager from "
"the Troll Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_2134"
msgstr ""
"The goblins slaves have been put back into their place, and life as we know "
"it here in Chopping Neck's is almost back to normal. #PlayerName#, you have "
"done well. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A report has arrived from the Iron Orks about a large number of trolls "
"entering the {$u12} region to the north of here. Among the Trolls, some of "
"their stronger units have been seen, such as the Troll Shamans and the "
"Trolls Lords. This is a clear indication that we are not just dealing with a "
"simple group of trolls who just happen to be wandering into Morak. It is as "
"if the last campaign against the trolls didn't teach them anything. But, "
"what else can you expect from stupid creatures like the trolls. Ten years "
"have past and they are back for more. All the better I say. Slaughter time "
"once again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stranglar Bloodaks is already in the region gathering information. You are "
"to go and report to him, and see how you may be useful once more. But before "
"you leave, I would ask of you to encounter the weakest of these trolls, and "
"extract from them three units of troll blood. You see, Stranglar has a "
"fondness of collecting the blood of his enemies. It's smart to be on his "
"good side. You will need a skinner to complete this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2135"
msgstr ""
"Time to kick these Trolls around, so we may get a clear indication of their "
"strength. Hmmmm you, yes you. You go and kill five Trolls, and then report "
"back to me with your assessment of their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2136"
msgstr ""
"The Troll Lords are the strongest, and I want to gather all the information "
"I can. According to our scouts, most Troll Lords are usually equipped with a "
"two handed weapon called the Ravager. You are to bring one of these weapons "
"back to me, so I may examine the weapon myself and see what we are up "
"against. Go now, and bring me a Ravager."

msgid "start_text_quest_2138"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , you have performed quite well. You have definitely helped me "
"gather enough information about these trolls that have appeared lately in "
"our lands. I have a report here, that I need to be delivered to the Iron "
"Orks. Since I will remain here to continue overlooking the situation, I need "
"you to deliver this report for me to the Iron Orks. Their headquarters are "
"located to the southwest of here. Once there seek out Krushar Breakskull and "
"hand the report to him. Go now."

msgid "start_text_quest_2139"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bossork the Councillor. Report to Ugruk "
"Elfstabber in the {$u14} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_214"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used to fuel "
"sacrificial pyres in Chopping Necks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2140"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ugruk Elfstabber. Kill three Ork Thugs and "
"three Ork Bruisers in {$u14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2141"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest form Ugruk Elfstabber. Kill five Hivekin Foragers "
"in {$u14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2142"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ugruk Elfstabber. Kill two Ork Thug and two "
"Ork Beastmasters in {$u14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2143"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ugruk Elfstabber. Deliver a letter to "
"Bigclubs Trollmangler at the headquarters of the Defenders of the Swamp."

msgid "start_text_quest_2144"
msgstr ""
"Now that you have dealt with the pathetic goblins, and have proven your "
"worth to us, there is another problem you might help with. Goblin slaves "
"rebelling is one thing, but orks turning against their own kind is another. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These bandit orks, these traitors that could not handle the greatness of the "
"ork empire, are now attacking our caravans along the trade route between "
"Metal Heart and the headquarters of the Defenders of the Swamp. If this is "
"some kind of way to make up for their weakness or to prove something, they "
"are simple pathetic. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These traitors, are an insult to the orks, our allies, and above all to the "
"King. The Defenders of the Swamp have demanded we put an end to these bandit "
"orks, and their activities.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will go to the {$u14} region and report to Ugruk Elfstabber. He is "
"currently looking into this problem. Go now and report to Ugruk Elfstabber."

msgid "start_text_quest_2145"
msgstr ""
"The bandit orks have become too much of a nuisance lately.  We simple cannot "
"allow them to continue disrupting our trade routes. It is only because of "
"other pressing issues, that we haven't dealt with them earlier. Now, the "
"Defenders of the Swamp demand that we put an end to this nonsense. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This pathetic band of bandits is using jolly names to distinguish their "
"ranks, such as, Thug, Bruiser, Beastmaster and Warmonger. The ones doing the "
"dirty work are the Thugs and Bruisers, while the Warmonger together with the "
"support of the Beastmasters are the leaders. We will begin by attacking the "
"lower ranks of their little operation. I want you to kill three Ork Thugs "
"and three Ork Bruiser. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The bandits are using old abandoned military outposts for the base for their "
"operations. You will find them to the south and southwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2146"
msgstr ""
"Before we continue dealing with the bandits, a report has just arrived. Our "
"scouts have spotted a group of Hivekin Foragers to the northwest of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The hivekin are a pathetic race of rat-like creatures, who live to strip the "
"land of anything vaguely edible, to please the unstoppable hunger of their "
"queen. The hivekin queen is a horrid creature that resembles a bloated "
"wrinkled bag of flesh, that lives only eat and give birth. So far, our "
"agents have not spotted the Hivekin Queen among them. This means that this "
"group of hivekin have been sent here to search for a suitable location to "
"establish a new lair for their Queen. We must not allow this to happen. The "
"last thing we need is the hivekin to establish a new lair here in Morak. We "
"must act quickly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to intercept this group of hivekin and kill at least five of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2147"
msgstr ""
"Back to dealing with the ork bandits. It is time to strike against the "
"leaders of this jolly band of bandits. Our scouts have discovered that the "
"bandit leaders, the Warmongers and Beastmasters, are located at the highest "
"level of the old military outpost, that is to the south of here. I want you "
"to storm into their headquarters, and kill two Ork Thug and two Ork "
"Beastmasters. That will surely be a major blow to the pathetic operation. "
"And if anybody survives, we'll clean up. Well, what are you waiting for? Go!"

msgid "start_text_quest_2148"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, we have successfully dealt with the bandit orks. I "
"want you to deliver this report to Bigclubs Trollmangler at the Defenders of "
"the Swamp. It is a progress report on all that we have achieved here. \n"
"\n"
"#PlayerName#, do not waste time. You will find their headquarters in the "
"Ondmark region to the south of here. Go now!"

msgid "start_text_quest_2149"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Vilethug the Councillor. Report to Amhard "
"Blackfists in the {$w14} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_215"
msgstr ""
"Sacrifice victims must be fed to the Fire Dragon on large pyres. Recently, "
"many of our gatherer goblin escaped into the swamp, and as a result, the "
"local priests are running short on firewood . You could give them a hand by "
"collecting timber from the swampy woodlands near town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To harvest timber, you must use a tool called a Wood Axe. If you don't "
"already own a Wood Axe, you can buy one from Grabgold the Merchant's shop, "
"which lies in the heart of Chopping Necks village. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gather five units of timber and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_2150"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amhard Blackfists. Kill five Trolls in {$w14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2151"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amhard Blackfists. Kill six Kobolds in {$w14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2152"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amhard Blackfists. Harvest three units of "
"Timeless Blood, and deliver them to Vilethug the Councillor at New Flayed "
"Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_2153"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amhard Blackfists. Report to Bigork "
"Blacktongue at the Dragonbound headquarters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2154"
msgstr ""
"A few years ago, a  military campaign was launched to eradicate all trolls "
"from Morak. The Trolls had increased so much in numbers, that it became "
"almost impossible to travel between the settlements without a daily "
"skirmish. Trolls are fearless and tireless hunters, who never stop trying to "
"kill an enemy until the last of them lies dead on the ground. The campaign "
"came to be known as the troll slaughter.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Reports have arrived of trolls being sighted within the {$w14} region. The "
"time has come for another troll slaughter. If you feel that you are ready to "
"participate in the troll slaughter which is about to begin once more, report "
"for duty with Amhard Blackfists. You will find Amhard Blackfists in the "
"{$w14} region south of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2155"
msgstr ""
"Ten years ago, a military campaign was launched against all the troll tribes "
"within Morak. Wherever you looked, the only thing you would see would be "
"slaughtered trolls. What glorious days. The trolls are one of those races "
"that would not submit to the almighty orks. They would just keep on fighting "
"to the very last one. A quality I admire. It made the campaign so much more "
"entertaining. Eventually, the campaign was known as the troll slaughter.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many years later, the trolls have returned. Time for another troll slaughter "
"to begin! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Trolls have been sighted in this region, not far from here. One group north "
"of were we are standing, and another further north across the river. If you "
"feel the need for some troll slaughtering, go kill at least five trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2156"
msgstr ""
"To the east of here, there is a swamp lake with an island in the middle. The "
"island is home to a pathetic tribe of kobolds. The kobolds very rarely leave "
"their island, and hardly ever create problems in the region. So until now, "
"they have been allowed to live out their pathetic lives.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently two agents from Flaming Skull had been sent to the island. Their "
"mission was to gather a number of kobolds to work in one of the mines. It "
"was a good agreement. The kobolds would provide labor for the mines, and the "
"we would not attack their pathetic island.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, the two agents where slaughtered by the kobolds. This is and "
"outrage and an insult. It seems that the kobolds have forgotten who it is "
"that allows them to even breath. It is time to put the kobolds back in their "
"place, and remind them of what it is like to live in Morak. Go to the kobold "
"island to the east of here, and kill six of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2157"
msgstr ""
"Trolls have returned, and another troll slaughter has begun. But, it "
"wouldn't be much of a slaughter without a little troll blood harvesting. "
"Yes, something like a trophy. After you have killed enough trolls, and your "
"heart is full of troll killing, using a skinner you can attempt to harvest "
"from the slain bodies of the trolls, troll blood. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you really want to impress and make a name for yourself, I suggest you "
"harvest at least three units of troll blood, and then deliver them to "
"Vilethug the Councillor. So  #PlayerName#, do you feel like a little troll "
"blood harvesting?"

msgid "start_text_quest_2158"
msgstr ""
"Word has arrived from the Dragonbound headquarters. It seems that the "
"Dragonbound have got their hands full with the local bandits, and could use "
"the extra help at the moment. #PlayerName# , I believe that you could be of "
"some use to the Dragonbound.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Dragonbound headquarters are located to the north of here in the {$w12} "
"region. Once their, report to Bigork Blacktoungue. He will give you all the "
"details."

msgid "start_text_quest_2159"
msgstr ""
"Normally, Sandbrook is a peaceful place, where timber from the inland "
"forests is sawed into lumber for the near-insatiable Mercian shipbuilding "
"industry. Recently, however, the once scattered monster groups of the region "
"have gained a new boldness, raiding farms and ambushing wayfarers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Groups of goblins have been sighted to the north of Sandbrook, and south "
"across the river near the Nithron ruins. There are also rumors of a goblin "
"village further northwest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help us reduce the threat the goblins pose to Sandbrook and "
"other nearby communities. Kill four goblins, then return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_216"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Bloodzkul's quest. In order to complete it, you must "
"return to her with five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2160"
msgstr ""
"For many years, these walls have protected our town. And it is up to us to "
"keep maintaining these walls, so they may continue to protect our town for "
"many more years to come.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The walls around Sandbrook need strengthening. I want you to bring me some "
"suitable lengths of timber from the forests around town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To accumulate timber, you need to cut down trees using a tool called a Wood "
"Axe. If you don't already own such an axe, you may buy one from Thora the "
"Merchant's shop, which lies near the center of Sandbrook.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your "
"woodaxe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_2161"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sandbrook currently faces a growing goblin threat. The only good aspect of "
"this situation, is that  goblins contain parts that may be used to make low "
"powered versions of certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinning knife and use "
"it on their corpses. Should you lack a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Thora the Merchant here in Sandbrook. Assuming that "
"you are a novice skinner, you should be able to successfully extract intact "
"teeth from around half of the fallen goblins.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The nearest goblins are a group of scouts who have been spotted to the north "
"of here. Larger concentrations of greenskins are found to the southwest and "
"northwest of Sandbrook.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to harvest four goblin teeth which we may then put to "
"somewhat ironic use in our defense against the goblin horde."

msgid "start_text_quest_2162"
msgstr ""
"One thing we can use to our advantage against the goblins, is the fact that "
"they have an exaggerated fear of human spellcasters. It seems that their "
"ancestors were blasted by one too many fireballs, and now the entire goblin "
"race has an ingrained fear of Mercian spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We wish to remind the goblins of the ubiquity of spellcasting ability among "
"humans. Every human who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast "
"twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to jog their racial memory.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Leen's here in Sandbrook. Once you own a staff, you "
"may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Goblins have been spotted to the northwest and southwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2163"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill four goblins in the mountains northeast of Heart of "
"Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_2164"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Aidan's challenge. Gather two axes to claim his reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2165"
msgstr ""
"You have promised to return to Jeremiah the Blacksmith with five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2166"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used in "
"strengthening Heart of Eanna's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2167"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Caradwen's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to her with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_2168"
msgstr "You have accepted Aidan's quest. Return to him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2169"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Aidan's mission. Cast twenty Mana Missiles against the "
"Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_217"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm very busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\n"
"\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Grabgold the Merchant, here "
"in Chopping Necks. Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any "
"kind. If your chosen bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your "
"crosshair target, informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. "
"Once you have determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may "
"begin the procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt "
"is successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \n"
"\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2170"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Heart of Eanna, one of the largest and busiest ports in all of "
"Mercia. Exotic goods from all corners of Agon arrive here, and in return, "
"Mercian products are shipped out to every foreign market.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently, hordes of goblins began pouring out of the mountains to the north, "
"and through the strength of their numbers, they have severely disrupted the "
"transport of goods to and from Heart of Eanna. Needless to say, the local "
"merchant houses are eager to see this threat to their livelihood removed. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The closest greenskins can be found raiding along the road north to "
"Silverley, while more goblins have been sighted in the mountain range east "
"of town, which is most easily entered through passes which lie to the "
"southeast and northeast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four goblins then return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2171"
msgstr ""
"The flint used in goblin axes is rare in this part of Mercia, and since "
"their tools are primitive and their skills rudimentary, goblins are unable "
"to make weapons from other, harder types of material. For these reasons, "
"looting goblin axes is an effective way of limiting the size of their armies."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The closest goblins are a band of scouts who forage along the road to the "
"north of here. Bigger groups are found among the mountains to the east.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2172"
msgstr ""
"To safeguard the trade which is our lifeblood, we need to build guard houses "
"along the roads leading to and from our town. We are, however, short on raw "
"materials, and I want you to help us by gathering stone from boulders found "
"in the wilderness around town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Isabel the Merchant, or from any other general "
"store.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to succeed every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please gather five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2173"
msgstr ""
"To guard our trade routes, we need to build guard towers along the roads "
"leading to town. In order to build such structures, we need plenty of sturdy "
"wood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help us with this, you need to bring a tool called a Wood Axe "
"to the trees around town. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy "
"one from Isabel the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your "
"woodaxe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_2174"
msgstr ""
"With the exception of a few simple incantations, such as Mana Missile, all "
"spells are fueled by ingredients which are expended during casting. New "
"spell ingredients are acquired as byproducts of harvesting processes, such "
"as skinning, mining and woodcutting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We are preparing to cast Magic Shield on as many members of our militia as "
"possible, as part of our defense against an imminent goblin attack. However, "
"we are running short of a spell ingredient called mandrake, which is a "
"byproduct of herb gathering.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest five mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Isabel the Merchant's shop, which lies in the central part "
"of Heart of Eanna. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2175"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The trade routes into Heart of Eanna are currently under siege by marauding "
"goblin bands. The only good aspect of this situation, is that goblins "
"contain parts that may be used to make low powered versions of certain "
"enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinning knife and use "
"it on their corpses. Should you lack a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Isabel the Merchant's here in Heart of Eanna. If "
"you are a novice skinner, you should be able to successfully extract intact "
"teeth from around half of the fallen goblins. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The nearest goblins are a group of scouts who are raiding along the road to "
"the north. Larger groups in the mountains to the east are best reached by "
"first traveling north, then turning east along the edge of the mountain "
"range. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to harvest four goblin teeth from these threats to our "
"trade and future."

msgid "start_text_quest_2176"
msgstr ""
"One thing we can use to our advantage against the goblins, is the fact that "
"they have an exaggerated fear of human spellcasters. It seems that the "
"ancestral goblins were blasted by one too many human-administered fireball, "
"and now the entire race has an ingrained fear of Mercians in pointy hats.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We wish to remind the goblins of the ubiquity of spellcasting ability among "
"humans. Every human who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast "
"twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to jog their racial memory. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from Melia the "
"arcanist. Once you own a staff, you may equip it by dragging it from your "
"inventory and onto your character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. Twenty Mana Missiles should do the "
"trick."

msgid "start_text_quest_2177"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garin Silvervault. Kill three Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_2178"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garin Silvervault. Kill two Windgraives."

msgid "start_text_quest_2179"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Garin Silvervault. Travel to Leengate and "
"talk to Thargal {$n09}."

msgid "start_text_quest_218"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Uzrok's quest. In order to complete it, you must return to "
"him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2180"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thargal {$n09}. Kill six Svartdvergir in "
"{$n08}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2181"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thargal {$n09}. Gather three units of Staunch "
"Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_2182"
msgstr ""
"Thargal {$n09} has asked you to travel to Wintercrown, and to deliver the "
"message to Garin Silvervault, that Leengate will be very soon open once more "
"for trade."

msgid "start_text_quest_2183"
msgstr ""
"Garin Silvervault has asked you to search for clues to the nature and "
"heritage of a strange pyramid that has risen in {$n10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2184"
msgstr ""
"Return to Wintercrown, and report your finding of the strange mural your "
"discovered inside the pyramid to Garin Silvervault."

msgid "start_text_quest_2185"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garin Silvervault. Kill six Slaves of Khamset."

msgid "start_text_quest_2186"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garin Silvervault. Gather three Dull "
"Sparkstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2187"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill four Ghouls inside "
"the Tomb of the First Knights, that is located directly underneath Stonevault"

msgid "start_text_quest_2188"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill four Undead Dwarves "
"in Fire Hall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2189"
msgstr ""
"Thain Strongforge has asked you travel to the region of Fire Hall, and "
"search for the ruins of Veilron Hall for Ardin Blackpeak's last blade."

msgid "start_text_quest_219"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of putting magic into things like weapons and armor. "
"Dozens of different enchantments exist, each of which requires four "
"different ingredients taken from the corpses of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you know, escaped goblin slaves are hiding out in the swamps near "
"Chopping Necks. If you are engaged in hunting these rascals, it pays to "
"simultaneously collect their teeth, which are used to make puny versions of "
"certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from dead goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't own a skinner, you can buy one from Grabgold the "
"Merchant. If you are new to skinning, you can expect to get a whole tooth "
"about every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The nearest goblins are a group of Scouts who are scrounging for food just "
"to the east of town. If you run out of goblins, there are more fugitives to "
"the north.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please collect four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_2190"
msgstr ""
"You have in your possession the last blade of the legendary dwarven "
"weaponsmith, Ardin Blackpeak. Deliver the blade to Thain Strongforge of the "
"Order of the Axe."

msgid "start_text_quest_2191"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill five hobgoblins "
"grunts in Fire Hall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2192"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill four Ogres that have "
"set camp in {$o11}. You must complete the quest in less than two hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_2193"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Travel to {$o11}, and "
"search the ogre camps for the missing DeQuincey scion."

msgid "start_text_quest_2194"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the DeQuincey signet ring to Thain Strongforge, so he may return it "
"to the DeQuincey family."

msgid "start_text_quest_2196"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill six Troll Lords and "
"two Swamp Hags in {$r11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2197"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thain Strongforge. Kill eight Svartdvergir in "
"{$r10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2198"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Thargal {$n09}. Kill five Bonecrew."

msgid "start_text_quest_2199"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thargal {$n09}. Gather ten units of Darktaint "
"from the Bonecrew."

msgid "start_text_quest_220"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Uzrok's latest mission. Cast twenty Mana Missiles against "
"the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_2200"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Kill three Arctic Bears."

msgid "start_text_quest_2201"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Garn Runeshield. Kill four Svartdvergir "
"located in Svartvann."

msgid "start_text_quest_2202"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Kill one Basalt Golem."

msgid "start_text_quest_2203"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Kill four Undead Dwarves "
"located in Nordakyst."

msgid "start_text_quest_2204"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Kill three Frostwalkers and "
"one Windgraive. When your task is complete, claim your reward from Gardar "
"Stonevalley."

msgid "start_text_quest_2205"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gardar Stonevalley. Kill three Ciel Fey and "
"five Centaurs located in the Whitebough forest in Uvdal."

msgid "start_text_quest_2206"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gardar Stonevalley. Gather three Timeless "
"Blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_2207"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gardar Stonevalley. Kill five Oathbound that "
"can be found in the Nithron ruins in Waneride Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_2208"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Gardar Stonevalley. Search the Nithron "
"Ruins in Waneride Edge for the Occluded Mirror."

msgid "start_text_quest_2209"
msgstr ""
"You now have the Occluded Mirror in your possession. Claim a reward by "
"bringing it to Gardar Stonevalley in Nordakyst."

msgid "start_text_quest_221"
msgstr ""
"Many goblins grow up in communities that are ruled by cruel shamans, and as "
"a consequence, they are afraid of all magic wielders. Sometimes one little "
"spell is enough to send the toughest , relatively speaking of goblin "
"warriors crying home to mother.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Some slave owners here in Chopping Necks believe that the escaped goblins "
"will return meekly to their pens if they are convinced of the hopelessness "
"of their situation. I want you to help us achieve this by casting twenty "
"Mana Missile spells on the fugitive Goblins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to hold a magestaff. If "
"you don't own one of these items already, you can buy one from Dragonmastar "
"the arcanist. Once you own a staff, it can be quipped by dragging it from "
"your inventory and onto the paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2210"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gardar Stonevalley. Report to Garn Runeshield "
"at the headquarters of the Five Beards Trading Company."

msgid "start_text_quest_2211"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garin Silvervault. Report to Vestri the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2212"
msgstr ""
"Vestri the Blacksmith has informed you that Garin Silvervault wishes to "
"speak to you. Report to Garin Silvervault."

msgid "start_text_quest_2213"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Garn Runeshield. Remove two units of "
"Staunch Heart from the Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_2214"
msgstr ""
"Thousands of years ago, the prophet Ymir laid out a path to perfection for "
"the dwarven race. The Voice of Ymir are shepherds who guide the dwarven race "
"along this path, making sure that no element of society strays too far from "
"it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The glacier-borne city that you see before you, called Wintercrown, is the "
"chief stronghold of the Voice of Ymir. For centuries, we have shared this "
"location with a tribe of windlords, birdlike humanoids who occupy ice caves "
"dug out of the glacier's walls. Recently, however, these creatures have "
"begun attacking merchants and other travellers along the roads leading into "
"Wintercrown. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to prove your worth to the custodians of Ymir's Path, you could "
"begin by dispatching a few of the newly belligerent windlords, who live in a "
"mountain valley to the west of here. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill three windlords the return to me for a mission that will further test "
"your potential."

msgid "start_text_quest_2215"
msgstr ""
"Directly underneath Wintercrown, in the heart of the glacier itself, lie the "
"remains of a Winter Dragon who once terrorized this part of Dvergheim. "
"Embedded in the ice, this dragon's skeleton emits a strange magic that "
"causes creatures called Windgraives to manifest in tunnels and ice caves "
"near its frozen lair. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to prove your valor by killing two of the Windgraives that guard "
"the dead dragon's cave. You can find the the entrance into the ice caves by "
"following the road that leads west from here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2216"
msgstr ""
"You have proven yourself in combat against both the windlords and the "
"children of the ice. It is my belief that you deserve to be given important "
"missions for the Voice of Ymir.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your first task involves a group of pirates who are preying on trade ships "
"along Dvergheim's northern coast. I want you to travel to the port village "
"of Leengate and report for duty with Thargal {$n09}, the Voice of Ymir agent "
"on the north coast. Leengate lies to the northwest of here, on the shore of "
"the Frostgap sea."

msgid "start_text_quest_2217"
msgstr ""
"After slaughtering the previous inhabitants, a group of undead pirates "
"started using a small offshore fishing village as a base for attacks on "
"merchant vessels. It is imperative that we remove this threat to Dvergheim's "
"trade and to the livelihood of Leengate's merchants.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For the benefit of brave adventurers such as yourself, a ship still leaves "
"regularly for the pirate-infested island. Use that boat, or any other means "
"of transportation that you prefer, to reach the island, which lies just a "
"short distance offshore.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once there, I want you to kill five of these undead pirates, also known as "
"the Bonecrew."

msgid "start_text_quest_2218"
msgstr ""
"A small island to the north of here has become infested by undead pirates. "
"Afters slaughtering the northman inhabitants, the half-decayed buccaneers "
"started preying on merchant ships along Dvergheim's northern trade route. "
"Needless to say, they must be dealt with as quickly as possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The flesh on the bodies of these undead pirates, also known as the Bonecrew, "
"has decayed into a substance called corpseflesh, which is used in various "
"enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you decide to move against the Bonecrew, please take the time to gather "
"two units of corpseflesh from their fallen bodies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2219"
msgstr ""
"Throughout Dvergheim, misguided individuals and communities are falling "
"under the influence of Sahul, a sinister deity whose taint turns worshipers "
"into dark and twisted abominations called svartdvergir. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A short distance to the east of here lies a mining community which recently "
"fell under the influence of Sahul. The inhabitants have abandoned the Path "
"of Ymir, and are reveling in the dark glory of their new master. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We cannot allow such profanity upon Dvergheim's soil. The Voice of Ymir "
"calls upon you to deliver justice to the fallen villagers. Remember, they "
"are no longer dwarves in the eyes of Ymir.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, the Voice of Ymir wants you to kill six Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_222"
msgstr ""
"Bosork the Councillor has asked you to kill four goblin refugees in the "
"vicinity of Metal Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_2220"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, with your help, the port village of Leengate will be very soon "
"open once more for trade. I want you to return to Wintercrown and deliver "
"the good news to Garin Silvervault, that Leengate is once more safe and open "
"for trade. I will remain here to keep an eye on things."

msgid "start_text_quest_2221"
msgstr ""
"A strange pyramidal structure has risen from the depths of a nearby lake in "
"{$n10}, which was simultaneously transformed into a fetid swamp. Corruption "
"now seeps slowly outward from the structure, turning nature into wasteland "
"and peaceful animals into malevolent beasts. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir wants you to investigate this strange and unsettling "
"phenomenon. Travel to {$n10} and search the pyramid and its environs for any "
"clues to the structure's provenance, then return to me with a report of your "
"findings.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Upon discovering something that might offer insight into the pyramid's "
"nature, use the action button to investigate the object more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_2222"
msgstr ""
"To the south of here, the once beautiful region of {$n10}, is slowly rotting "
"away into a swampland. This unnatural transformation seems to be the result "
"of the strange pyramidal structure which has risen in the heart of the "
"slowly expanding swamp.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The source of this corruption is guarded by undead creatures which under the "
"structure's influence rise again and again from the waters of the swamp. If "
"we are to investigate the pyramid thoroughly, we must first decimate the "
"numbers of its undead protectors. Kill six Slaves of Khamset."

msgid "start_text_quest_2223"
msgstr ""
"Vestri, our local blacksmith has asked to speak with you. He has heard of "
"your exploits with the undead creatures guarding the pyramid in the swamp, "
"and believes you might be able to help him with something. Go pay him a "
"visit, and see how you might assist him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2224"
msgstr ""
"I have heard that you have battled the undead guardians of the strange "
"pyramid, and have returned victorious. Excellent. Just the person I need. "
"What I want, is for somebody to harvest from those Slaves of Khamset, three "
"Dim Stormrunes. I believe I can use the Dim Stormrunes to enchant some of my "
"wears."

msgid "start_text_quest_2225"
msgstr ""
"Garin Silvervault would like to have a word with you. I have no need of your "
"services anymore, so I suggest you go and talk to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2226"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Stonevault, a fortress town which is the chief stronghold of the "
"Order of the Axe, and a mighty bulwark against the enemies of the dwarven "
"race. Since the days of the First Teaching, knights of the Axe have ridden "
"forth from Stonevault to defend the peace and prosperity of Dvergheim. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Directly underneath Stonevault lies the tomb in which the Order's founding "
"knights were buried. Unfortunately, this sacred chamber has suffered some "
"neglect during recent years, and perhaps as a result, its dust-covered "
"graves have attracted a tribe of necromantic, flesh-eating ghouls. As a a "
"side-effect of this invasion, the ancient guardians of the tomb have awoken, "
"and these undead creatures now attack all who approach the chamber. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must show the first knights our respect by exterminating the ghoul "
"infestation, and by sending their ancient guardians back to their well-"
"earned sleep. Kill four Ghouls.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Tomb of the First Knights can be found by following a tunnel which leads "
"off from the southwestern corner of Stonevault."

msgid "start_text_quest_2227"
msgstr ""
"A few years back, the village of Veilron Hall was destroyed by the eruption "
"of a volcano which had lain dormant for so long that it was thought to be "
"dead. Unfortunately, the volcano announced its reawakening with a "
"cataclysmic blast that buried almost all of the villagers under lava and "
"falling rocks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps due to the suddenness of the catastrophe, some of the dwarves of "
"Veilron Hall have failed to realize that their lives are at an end. These "
"individuals have turned into Undead Dwarves who shamble pathetically through "
"the streets of their old town, vengefully attacking any living creatures "
"that enter within its walls.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, we must put an end to the misery of these lost souls. Travel "
"to Veilron Hall, known today as Fire Hall, and kill four Undead Dwarves."

msgid "start_text_quest_2228"
msgstr ""
"Until it was destroyed in a volcanic eruption, the nearby village of Veilron "
"Hall was home to Ardin Blackpeak, one of the finest weaponsmiths in all of "
"Dvergheim. According to the handful of people who survived the catastrophe, "
"Blackpeak had worked for months on a single blade when the catastrophe "
"struck and he was killed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to the region of Fire Hall, and to search the ruins of "
"Veilron Hall for Ardin Blackpeak's last blade. According to survivors, the "
"mastersmith's home stood in the eastern part of town."

msgid "start_text_quest_2229"
msgstr ""
"A tribe of fire-worshiping hobgoblins have settled in the foothills of Fire "
"Hall, an active volcano to the east of here. This particularly fierce group "
"of monsters have already launched several raids against nearby dwarven "
"communities, and they seem to be getting bolder with every passing day. It "
"is almost as if they draw strength from the steadily increasing activity of "
"the volcano which threatens to devour their conspicuously flammable wooden "
"camp.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While we wait for the volcano to do the inevitable to the camp, The Order of "
"the Axe wants you to reduce its strength by killing five hobgoblin grunts."

msgid "start_text_quest_223"
msgstr ""
"The goblins of this area tend to cower pathetically in their villages, where "
"they wait resignedly for us to come and grab some more of them for use as "
"slaves. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently however, some goblins seem to have forgotten their place, and have "
"slowly starting approaching Metal Heart. As a result, groups of goblin have "
"begun stealing livestock, obstructing traffic, and generally setting a bad "
"example for the goblins we have in captivity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Normally, we would take the little rascals in as slaves, but since the Metal "
"Heart pens are full at the moment, we have decided to solve the problem by "
"massacring the goblins instead. It's a bit of a waste, of course, but it "
"can't be helped.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four goblins, then return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2230"
msgstr ""
"A narrow valley to the northwest of here has been invaded by an ogre "
"warband. The ogres have established several fortified camps, both on the "
"valley floor and inside the mountains flanking it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A full-scale military expedition against the ogres is underway, but in the "
"meantime, the Order of the Axe has been asked to weaken the ogres by killing "
"as many of the invaders as possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help us in this effort by killing four ogres. Since the dwarven army "
"will soon be ready to move against the Valley of the Stormlords, we need you "
"to complete this mission before two hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_2231"
msgstr ""
"A band of ogres recently staged a devastatingly successful raid on a nearby "
"village. In addition to stealing or devouring all valuables and livestock, "
"the ogres took several people with them, including the eldest son of a human "
"merchant called DeQuincey.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This merchant has begged the Order of the Axe to search for his son, and he "
"has promised a sizable reward for the youth's recovery. Failing that, he is "
"willing to reward the recovery of a signet ring which was in the missing "
"boy's possession, and which the father will accept as proof of his son's "
"demise. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Since ogres have a great fondness for human flesh, I would begin by "
"searching for the ring in the bone piles of the ogre raider camps, which lie "
"in the Valley of the Stormlords, a short distance to the northwest of here "
"in {$o11}. Whenever you find a promising pile, use the action button to "
"rummage through it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Return with the youth or the DeQuincey family signet ring, and you will be "
"handsomely rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_2233"
msgstr ""
"An important pass through the Waneride Mountains has become closed due to "
"frequent ambushes by trolls and swamp hags. After a long search, our scouts "
"have now located the monsters lair inside a cave system which opens up "
"behind a waterfall in {$r11}. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We want you to strike against the raiders, before they have time to further "
"fortify an already formidable defensive position. The Order of the Axe wants "
"you to kill six Troll Lords and two Swamp Hags."

msgid "start_text_quest_2234"
msgstr ""
"In the {$r10} region, the dwarven city of Silverbound has fallen to the "
"armies of Sahul, a cruel deity who seeks to infect all dwarves in Dvergheim "
"with his mind-controlling taint. Digging and blasting their way from caverns "
"underneath the city, an army of svartdvergir attacked by night, taking "
"Silverbound's defenders utterly by surprise. Before dawn broke, half the "
"town's inhabitants had been slaughtered, while the rest had been forcefully "
"infected with Sahul's liquid curse and turned into svartdvergir themselves."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must annihilate the svartdvergir before they can spread their master's "
"taint to the surrounding region. Go the {$r10}, and kill eight Svartdvergir "
"that have taken over the city of Silverbound."

msgid "start_text_quest_2235"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Gemstone Reach, the chief stronghold of the Five Beards Trading "
"Company, a dwarven merchant house which controls trade routes and outposts "
"throughout Agon. A major power in Dvergheim society, the Five Beards is "
"ancient, incredibly wealthy, and deeply entrenched in the cities of the "
"dwarven north.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Agents of the Five Beards travel the world on behalf of the organization, "
"guarding our property and removing obstacles to free trade. But before being "
"given such challenging and important missions, you must prove your worth by "
"completing some rather less exotic missions here in northern Dvergheim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A group of Arctic Bears recently floated to a nearby island on a sheet of "
"drift ice. Hungry and desperate, the bears attack any creature that strays "
"too close to their lair, including the inhabitants of a small fishing "
"village which lies on the island's west coast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Take the small ferry across to the island. Kill three Arctic Bears, then "
"return to me for a reward and another mission."

msgid "start_text_quest_2236"
msgstr ""
"A mining village called Blacktrove, which is located to the west of here in "
"Svartvann, has fallen under the curse of Sahul, a cruel deity whose shadow "
"and faith is spreading quickly throughout Dvergheim. Worshipers of Sahul "
"drink his liquid taint, which turns them into twisted creatures called "
"Svartdvergir. Once they've completed this rite of passage, the only way to "
"free the fallen dwarves is by killing them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Since they began worshiping Sahul, the villagers have ceased delivery of ore "
"and ingots which are essential trade goods for the Five Beards Trading "
"Company. This is unacceptable. We must replace the current inhabitants of "
"Blacktrove with settlers who are wiling to resume production. The Five "
"Beards Trading Company want you to kill four Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_2237"
msgstr ""
"In twisted and hideous rituals, the Svartdvergir infuse the rock itself with "
"the liquid taint of their dark god Sahul. The resulting creatures, called "
"Basalt Golems, are used to guard the treasuries and shrines of Svartdvergir "
"communities. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Witnesses have reported seeing a Basalt Golem in the nearby Svartdvergir "
"village of Blacktrove, which is located to the west of here. I want you to "
"locate and destroy this abomination before it causes too much damage to the "
"local smithies and mining operations. The Five Beards Trading Company wants "
"you to kill one Basalt Golem."

msgid "start_text_quest_2238"
msgstr ""
"A village to the west of here has has fallen into the worship of Sahul, a "
"god of the dark and secret places at the center of the world. Sahul is a "
"cruel god, who physically transforms his flock into twisted, sub-dwarven "
"creatures called Svartdvergir.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Some such rituals of transformation take place near the village of "
"Blacktrove, in a crystal cave deep underground. According to eyewitness "
"reports, initiates drink liquid from the shrine's dark pool. Upon drinking "
"Sahul's liquid taint, these fallen dwarves become Svartdvergir, cursed "
"creatures whose only release lies in death. When they are slain, the taint "
"of Sahul may be extracted from their bodies and destroyed. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to remove two units of Sahul's Darktaint from the Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_2239"
msgstr ""
"The dwarven work ethic is legendary, and sometimes not even death can "
"convince a dwarven worker to down tools and rest at last. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the east of here lies the old dwarven mining village of Nordakyst, which "
"was abandoned when an iron mine became depleted. Unfortunately, some of the "
"village's inhabitants still rise confusedly every morning from their grave-"
"sleep, dragging their bodies off to continue the work they did in life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is our duty to help these Undead Dwarves by freeing them from this "
"endlessly repeated cycle. Put four Undead Dwarves to sleep by destroying "
"their decaying husks. When your task is complete, report to Gardar "
"Stonevally in Nordakyst, which lies opposite of the old dwarven mine."

msgid "start_text_quest_224"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Bosork the Councillor's quest. Bring him two goblin axes "
"to earn a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2240"
msgstr ""
"To the east of here lies Icespear Ridge, a rock formation which rises "
"dramatically out of the Frostgap sea. On the Icespear's tallest peak stands "
"a shrine which commemorates the second lesson of Ymir the Mastersmith, which "
"was taught there many centuries ago.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Icespear Ridge can only be reached through the dwarven mines of Nordakyst, "
"which was abandoned when the vein of ore it depended on ran out. Now that "
"the people of Nordakyst no longer defend the entrance to Icespear Ridge, it "
"has become infested by monsters, and in recent months, many pilgrims to this "
"sacred site have been forced to turn back.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Help clear out Icespear Ridge by killing three Frostwalkers and one "
"Windgraive. When your task is complete, claim your reward from Gardar "
"Stonevalley. He lives in Nordakyst, just across the water from the "
"abandoned  mines of Nordakyst."

msgid "start_text_quest_2241"
msgstr ""
"Just beyond the tunnel to our south lies a lush and ancient forest called "
"the Whitebough, which is home to several sylvan species that are rare "
"elsewhere in Dvergheim, such as centaurs and elves.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, some of these creatures are violently opposed to the "
"establishment of Five Beards logging operations in the Whitebough forest. We "
"need the lumber for trade and shipbuilding, and all obstacles to the "
"exploitation of the Whitebough must be removed. You can help the Five Beards "
"continue their operations, by killing three Ciel Fey and five Centaurs."

msgid "start_text_quest_2242"
msgstr ""
"A tribe of centaurs has declared war on the Five Beards logging operation in "
"the forest of Whitebough, which lies to the south of here. It is imperative "
"that these enemies of free trade are removed as quickly as possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Should you agree to move against the centaurs, I want you to take the time "
"to harvest their hearts, which are used in several magical enchantments. "
"Please bring me three centaur hearts."

msgid "start_text_quest_2243"
msgstr ""
"In recent weeks, several groups of merchants have been ambushed to the south "
"of here, in the region of Waneride Edge. The path through the gorge is an "
"important trade route, and the raiders must be annihilated before they cause "
"any further disruption. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It seems that monsters called Oathbound have made their lair in a Nithron "
"ruin overlooking the gorge. The Five Beards Trading Company wants you to "
"kill five of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2244"
msgstr ""
"To the south of here, ancient Nithron ruins overlook a mighty canyon called "
"the Waneride Edge. The original inhabitants of these ruins were famous for "
"their mastery of the occult arts and insight into hidden worlds. They are "
"said to have produced a codex called the Occluded Mirror, which contained "
"the essence of their philosophy and theories.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the right hands, the Occluded Mirror could be an invaluable source of "
"information about the Nithron culture. The Five Beards Trading Company would "
"like you to search the Nithron ruins in Waneride Edge for this book."

msgid "start_text_quest_2245"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, thanks to your efforts, we have successfully dealt with the "
"raiders along the trade route in Waneride Forge, fought the Ciel Fey and "
"Centaurs in Whitebough forest, and found the Occluded Mirror, the legendary "
"book which is an invaluable source of information about the past and about "
"Nithron culture. I have already send a report off to the Five Beards Trading "
"Company about all that we have accomplished here. \n"
"\n"
"I believe Garn Runeshield would like to have a word with you. Go report to "
"him at the headquarters of the Five Beards Trading Company."

msgid "start_text_quest_2246"
msgstr ""
"There are those dwarves who find the Path of Ymir to be too arduous, and who "
"abandon it in preference of the dark teachings of Sahul, a deity whose home "
"is the trackless and nameless caverns at the center of the world. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Upon drinking Sahul's liquid taint, these fallen dwarves become "
"svartdvergir, cursed creatures whose only release lies in death. When they "
"are slain, the taint of Sahul may be extracted from their bodies and "
"destroyed. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir wants you to remove three units of Sahul's Darktaint from "
"svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_2247"
msgstr ""
"You have been given a test by Krushar Breakskull. Kill two Lesser Fire "
"Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_2248"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Krushar Breakskull. Kill two Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_2249"
msgstr ""
"Krushar Breakskull has instructed you to go to the abandoned town of Stone "
"wall in {$u11}, and kill four Doom Spiders and two Sarlids."

msgid "start_text_quest_225"
msgstr ""
"Due to wear and tear, we need a few replacement axes for our goblin slaves. "
"Rather than spend money on new ones, we've decided to steal some axes from a "
"group of goblin who recently set up camp near Metal Heart. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help by collecting two goblin axes. To access a fallen goblin's "
"possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then while targeting the remains "
"use the action button. You may then drag items from his backpack and into "
"yours."

msgid "start_text_quest_2250"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Stranglar Bloodaks. Harvest two Baleful Venom "
"Sac from the Spiders and two units of Caustic Bile form the Sarlid."

msgid "start_text_quest_2251"
msgstr ""
"Krushar Breakskull has asked you to travel to the Nithron ruins in {$t13}, "
"and search for a complete copy of a book called the Endemoniad."

msgid "start_text_quest_2252"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the copy of the Endemoniad to Krushar Breakskull in Iron Maiden, and "
"collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2253"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to seek out and kill Nithron constructs in {$t13}. Kill "
"three Snake Revenants and three Oathbound."

msgid "start_text_quest_2254"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to travel to {$t14}, and search the sadayel village of "
"Silmah, for the sadayels new found magical power."

msgid "start_text_quest_2255"
msgstr ""
"Bring the Tome of Legend to Krushar Breakskull, so it may be determent if it "
"is the source of the new magical powers of the sadayel of Silmah."

msgid "start_text_quest_2256"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted another mission from Krushar Breakskull. Kill six Sadayel "
"Guardians, two Sadayel Shamans and two Sadayel Chieftains."

msgid "start_text_quest_2257"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Krushar Breakskull. Kill four Hill Giants "
"Sluggers in Azuk Nin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2258"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Krushar Breakskull. Enter the hobgoblin "
"camp, kill seven hobgoblins and return to  Krushar Breakskull with your "
"assessment of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2259"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Iron Maiden, the chief stronghold of the Iron Orks. We are an "
"elite unit of Morak's army, feared by all enemies of the orks, and famous "
"for our ironclad loyalty to the Big Head in {$v13}. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Those who wish to work for the Iron Orks must first show their valor in two "
"carefully husbanded proving grounds near Iron Maiden. The first of these is "
"a colony of fire creatures that live among among some lava pits just "
"southwest of town. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill two Lesser Fire Elementals, then return to me for instructions of the "
"next test."

msgid "start_text_quest_226"
msgstr ""
"You have promised to return to Strongar the Blacksmith with five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2260"
msgstr ""
"You performed quite admirably against the fire creatures, but now you must "
"face a far sterner test. In a wide verdant valley to the west of here, live "
"giant lizards of a kind which is usually only found on the jungle-clad "
"continent of Yssam. These ferocious predators, known as Raptors, are among "
"the most dangerous predators in Morak, and facing them is a fitting test for "
"prospective members of the Iron Orks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The raptor valley lies on the far side of the tall mountain range behind us. "
"The shortest way there is via a subterranean passageway which branches off "
"from the tunnel that connects the two sections of Iron Maiden.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill two Raptors then return here to receive your first proper mission for "
"the Iron Orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2261"
msgstr ""
"Located to the northeast of here in {$u11} is Stone Wall, a once busy "
"crowded mining town, that now is nothing more than an empty deserted town."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Five years ago, Stone Wall was struck by a sudden spider infestation. The "
"sudden spider infestation that hit the town found everybody unprepared. In "
"less that a week, everybody in Stone Wall was dead.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For many years, it was believed that the town was cursed, and nobody would "
"dare approach it. Now the time has come to claim Stone Wall back. Our agents "
"have scouted the perimeters of the town, and discovered that most of the "
"spiders are now gone, except for a few groups of Doom Spiders together with "
"their masters the Sarlid. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time to move. #PlayerName#, go to Stone wall and kill four Doom "
"Spiders and two Sarlids."

msgid "start_text_quest_2262"
msgstr ""
"The Sarlid Defendes and their pet Doom Spiders, have done enough damage to "
"town of Stone Wall. Now that we are taking the town back, it is time for "
"them to pay. I want you to go into Stone Wall and bring them pain. You are "
"to harvest two Venom Sacs from the Spiders and two units of Bile from the "
"Sarlid. Oh yes, they will know pain. Go now."

msgid "start_text_quest_2263"
msgstr ""
"The ruins of the Nithron civilization are found throughout Agon, cyclopean "
"in scale and opulent in architecture and decoration. It has long been "
"prophesied that the Nithron would one day return to Agon, and strange "
"stirrings in long-abandoned ruins seem to indicate that their return might "
"be at hand.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to prepare for this eventuality, we need to learn more about the "
"culture and history of this vanished race of giants. Supposedly, much of "
"their world view was encoded in an epic poem called the Endemoniad, which "
"today is known only through a few scattered fragments. Big Head Uzrok "
"Deathfist has asked us to scour all the Nithron ruins in Morak for a more "
"complete version of this legendary lost book. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Directly to the south of here stand the ruins of {$t13}. I hereby give you "
"the responsibility of searching this site thoroughly for any traces of the "
"Endemoniad. Once you reach the ruins, I suggest your either search for a "
"crate or a chest."

msgid "start_text_quest_2264"
msgstr ""
"Long before the rise of the orks, the world was ruled by a race of golden-"
"skinned giants called the Nithron. Few in number but godlike in longevity "
"and power, the Nithron assembled vast armies of  mortals and fought each "
"other in endless wars for territory, for honor, or just for the thrill of "
"battle.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"After a centuries-long reign, the Nithron appear to have vanished almost "
"overnight, leaving behind seemingly immaculate strongholds and cities. A few "
"months ago, these long-abandoned ruins began to stir. Strange guardian "
"creatures manifested from thin air, while books and artifacts began "
"appearing from thin air in dust-covered throne rooms and treasure vaults.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our first move should be to gauge the strength of the these strange new "
"guardian creatures, in case there is an army of them waiting to manifest, "
"with or without their long-absent masters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Travel to the nearest large Nithron ruin, which lies in the province of "
"{$t13}. Once there, kill three of the Snake Revenants who patrol the "
"perimeter of the Nithron ruin, and three Oathbound, who guard the city "
"itself. When you are done, return to me with an assessment of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2265"
msgstr ""
"All orkish attempts at taking a sadayel city called Silmah have failed, "
"largely because its inhabitants wield powerful protective spells which have "
"traditionally been beyond their magical reach.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This new magical strength might well originate with some artifact or "
"spellbook found in the nearby ruins of {$t14}. As you know, several strange "
"objects have appeared in that location recently, and it is quite possible "
"that the sadayel have stumbled upon something of interest.   \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Search the sadayel city of Silmah for the source of its new-found magical "
"strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2266"
msgstr ""
"Since time immemorial, orks have been locked in a struggle with the the "
"reptilian sadayel, with neither race able to destroy or subjugate the other. "
"After the rise of the Fire Dragon, however, the orkish armies won a string "
"of resounding victories, and now the sadayel have been driven out into the "
"peripheries of Morak. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Of all the once-proud cities of the sadayel, only one called Silmah still "
"stands. Sprawling across much of the region of {$t14}, this swamp-encircled "
"stronghold has repulsed all orkish attacks, and even launched retaliatory "
"raids against nearby orkish settlements\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This thorn in the orkish side will now be removed once and for all. In "
"preparation of a large-scale army siege, we are currently sending Iron Orks "
"operatives into the region to soften the sadayel defenses.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Silmah the region of Orodun and kill six Sadayel Guardians, two "
"Sadayel Shamans and two Sadayel Chieftains."

msgid "start_text_quest_2267"
msgstr ""
"In {$s12} to the west of here, our scouts have discovered a band of Hill "
"Giants that are slowly making their way into Morak, and towards our "
"headquarters. It seems that these Hill Giants Sluggers are the culprits "
"behind the latest attacks on our trade routes. We cannot afford to waste any "
"resources or times with these giant morons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to put an end to this nuisance. Go find this bandit "
"band of Hill Giants Sluggers, and kill four of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2268"
msgstr ""
"As the vanguard of Morak's army, the Iron Orks frequently deal with the "
"foreign enemies of our nation. At this particular moment, we are preparing a "
"campaign against a hobgoblin army which is slowly assembling to the north of "
"here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hobgoblins are a race of vagabond mercenaries whose sword-arms and loyalties "
"belong to the highest bidder. Occasionally, however, large hobgoblin armies "
"will unite, and when this happens, the hobgoblins pose a threat to all that "
"stand in their way. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To there north of here, in the {$t11} region, hobgoblins have been "
"fortifying. Our agents have sent reports about a steady income of hobgoblin "
"war parties arriving into the camp from beyond Morak. We still do not have "
"enough information on who is behind this growing hobgoblin army, but we do "
"know that the hobgoblin army is grown stronger by the day. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to gather more information on the growing strength of the "
"hobgoblins. This will be a dangerous mission. You are to go to the hobgoblin "
"camp, kill seven hobgoblins, and return back to us with your assessment of "
"their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_2269"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigclubs Trollmangler. Kill four Swamp Hags "
"who have infest the tar pits to the northwest of Swampton."

msgid "start_text_quest_227"
msgstr ""
"As the Dragonbound priests keep repeating, the Fire Dragon's awakening is "
"imminent, and we must increase the rate of sacrifice to a fever pitch. Here "
"in Metal Heart, we are planning a Small Stair, which is an altar on which we "
"can offer sacrifice to the infernal goddess.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The local goblin slaves are being worked very hard, but we still need more "
"material for the Small Stair. If you have time, you could help us by "
"collecting units of stone from boulders near the village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you need to hold a pickaxe. If you don't own such "
"a tool already, you may buy one from Gulgon the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stone can be taken from any boulder that is large enough. Pointing your "
"crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is suitable for "
"harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our great project by donating five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2270"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to seek out Sir Bonehard the Cruel, who is currently "
"stationed in Elfkill Keep."

msgid "start_text_quest_2271"
msgstr ""
"Sir Bonehard the Cruel has sent you on a mission against the centaurs of "
"{$t15}. Kill five Centaurs."

msgid "start_text_quest_2272"
msgstr ""
"Sir Bonehard has asked you to search the Ciel Fey village in {$t15} for the "
"artifact called the Sacred Bough."

msgid "start_text_quest_2273"
msgstr ""
"You have the Sacred Bough in your possession. Bring it to Sir Bonehard the "
"Cruel in Elfkill Keep."

msgid "start_text_quest_2274"
msgstr ""
"You accepted a mission offered by Sir Bonehard the Cruel. Kill six Ciel Fey "
"in Jakudun."

msgid "start_text_quest_2275"
msgstr "You have agreed to seek out Hardzkul Warmaster."

msgid "start_text_quest_2276"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Hardzkul Warmaster. Kill three Sadayel "
"Guardians and three Sadayel Shamans, that seem to be defending the entrance "
"into the House of Memory."

msgid "start_text_quest_2277"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hardzkul Warmaster. Kill four Sadayel "
"Chieftains that guard the entrance of the House of Memory."

msgid "start_text_quest_2278"
msgstr ""
"Hardzkul Warmaster has tasked you with destroying the Shrine of Memory in "
"{$v15}. Destroy it using physical force."

msgid "start_text_quest_2279"
msgstr ""
"Travel to the region of {$v16}. Once there, kill five Hill Giants. When you "
"have completed your mission, report back to Bigclubs Trollmangler in "
"Swampton."

msgid "start_text_quest_228"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used to keep "
"the sacrifice pyres burning steadily in Metal Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_2280"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Bigclubs Trollmangler. Disfigure a human "
"statue in {$v17}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2281"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Swampton, the chief stronghold of the Defenders of the Swamp, a "
"knightly order dedicated to protecting the heartlands of Morak against "
"monsters and foreign invaders.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Of all the creatures that threaten the mud-clad purity of Morak, Swamp Hags "
"are perhaps the most revolting. Fierce, foul-smelling and dark-hearted, they "
"will attempt to hunt down, torture, and finally eat any creature that is "
"smaller than a gargantua and larger than a bog rat.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"At a time when most of our knights are occupied with more distant threats, a "
"tar lake near Swampton has become infested by a coven of Swamp Hags. This is "
"an embarrassment to the Defenders of the Swamp, and we want the ugly horrors "
"exterminated as quickly as possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_2282"
msgstr ""
"Morak's western forests are home to a clan of Ciel Fey, fundamentalist elves "
"who will go to any length to defend their precious trees. Perhaps because of "
"this uncompromising attitude, the Ciel Fey of Morak have survived for "
"centuries, despite several orkish extermination initiatives.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, however, the luck of the long-ears is about to run out. Uzrok "
"Deathfist, the current Big Head of {$v13}, has asked the mighty Defenders of "
"the Swamp to deal with the Ciel Fey once and for all.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help us in this noble endeavor, please report for duty with "
"Sir Bonehard the Cruel, the Defenders knight who is in charge of the "
"extermination campaign. Bonehard is currently based in Elfkill Keep, a small "
"fortress which stands on the edge of the Ciel Fey forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_2283"
msgstr ""
"Here in Elfkill Keep we are preparing to annihilate a tribe of Ciel Fey "
"elves who live like squirrels in a forest to the west of here. But before we "
"can strike against the squirrel people, we must deal with their allies, a "
"group of centaurs who attack all non-sylvan creatures that enter the forest."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We will deal quickly and mercilessly with these equine mutants. You can to "
"do your part by killing five Centaurs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sir Bonehard the Cruel has sent you on a mission against the centaurs of "
"{$t15}. Kill five Centaurs."

msgid "start_text_quest_2284"
msgstr ""
"The Ciel Fey village here in {$t15} is very old, perhaps even older than the "
"first orkish settlements in the region. It is rumored that the original "
"elven settlers brought with them a bough from the Tree of All Seeds in "
"{$h18}, and the presence of such a powerful artifact would help to explain "
"the village's surprising defensive strength.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Search the Ciel Fey village for the Sacred Bough. It should look pretty much "
"like any other twig, but it is rumored to hold great magical power. I "
"suggest you look for some kind of container, maybe a crate or a chest."

msgid "start_text_quest_2285"
msgstr ""
"In the days before the Fire Dragon, elf-infested sylvan pockets were found "
"throughout Morak. In recent times, however, most green forests have been cut "
"down for use as building material or firewood, while the elves have been "
"slain or recruited into slavery. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Ciel Fey elves of {$t15} are the last of their kind in Morak. By killing "
"them or driving them off, we can remove a thorn that has been stuck in the "
"orkish side for centuries. You can contribute towards the realization of "
"this dream by killing six Ciel Fey.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You accepted a mission offered by Sir Bonehard the Cruel. Kill six Ciel Fey."

msgid "start_text_quest_2286"
msgstr ""
"Long before the rise of the ork, southern Morak belonged to the empire of a "
"race of  toga-clad humans known as the Thaelicians. Pathetically pacifistic, "
"the Thaelicians had a fondness for intellectual pursuits, and they would "
"philosophize and speculate endlessly about the nature of things. When the "
"time came to defend their empire against the mighty orks, the hilariously "
"unprepared Thaelicians were swiftly ushered into oblivion.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The ancient Thaelicians didn't believe in gods. Instead, they built shrines "
"in which they contemplated philosophical and ethical concepts, such as "
"humility and mercy. It is said that these shrines generated magical power "
"that could be tapped by Thaelician philospher-priests.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the most important Thaelician shrines was located in or near the "
"region of {$v15}. For unknown reasons, Big Head Uzrok Deathfist has asked "
"the Defenders of the Swamp to destroy this shrine, which supposedly was "
"dedicated to the contemplation of memory."

msgid "start_text_quest_2287"
msgstr ""
"Behind me lies the shore of a shallow, bowl-shaped lake which is home to an "
"exceptionally fierce Sadayel tribe. As you may know already, the Sadayel are "
"an advanced race of lizardmen who for centuries have fought the orks for "
"overlordship of Morak. Currently expelled into the murkiest swamps and the "
"most barren outskirts, the Sadayel will resist bitterly whenever the "
"opportunity presents itself. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The local Sadayel appear to be defending the entrance into the House of "
"Memory, an ancient site which Big Head Uzrok Deathfist want us to "
"investigate. I want you to help us get rid of this scaly obstacle by killing "
"three Sadayel Guardians and three Sadayel Shamans. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You have accepted a mission from Hardzkul Warmaster. Kill three Sadayel "
"Guardians and three Sadayel Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_2288"
msgstr ""
"By now you should be familiar with the local Sadayel village, as well as the "
"lake that supports its pathetically ramshackle hovels. As you may have "
"noticed, the lake is fed by a waterfall which issues from a cave opening "
"halfway up a near-vertical mountain wall. This opening leads into the Shrine "
"of Memory, the long-lost Thaelician temple with Big Head Uzrok wants us to "
"destroy. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, some very tough Sadayel Chieftains guard the entrance and the "
"shrine itself. While our focus should be on destroying the shrine itself, we "
"should also take the time to kill a few of these of these overprotective "
"nuisances. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four Sadayel Chieftain"

msgid "start_text_quest_2289"
msgstr ""
"The waterfall to the west of here issues from the entrance to the Shrine of "
"Memory, a site which was once sacred to the ancient and effeminate "
"Thaelicians. Big Head Uzrok Deathfist has asked us to destroy this shrine, "
"thereby removing one of the last  remnants of  a deservedly vanquished "
"people. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Make your way to the statue which constitutes the centerpiece of the shrine, "
"and destroy it using physical force. Perhaps due to some lingering "
"protective magic, the statue seems to be immune to the effects of all spells."

msgid "start_text_quest_229"
msgstr ""
"Since the Fire Dragon only accepts sacrifice that is burned to death, our "
"priests need a steady supply of fuel. Due to a shortage of axes here in "
"Metal Heart, our slaves are currently bringing in too little firewood, and "
"we could use some help with keeping the murder-fires burning. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to help, you could harvest timber by using a tool called a Wood "
"Axe on trees near town. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy "
"one from Gulgon the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are good for woodcutting. When you're facing such a tree "
"while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your "
"woodaxe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please gather five units of timber for the pyres."

msgid "start_text_quest_2290"
msgstr ""
"The Defenders of the Swamp are planning a raid against the human mining "
"village of {$v17}, which is an important supplier of iron ore to the human "
"capital. Unfortunately, {$v17} lies on the far side of a war-ravaged "
"wasteland which is controlled by a clan of ultra-violent Hill Giants. While "
"the strength and cruel instincts of these giants are to be respected, they "
"are wildly unpredictably, and must deal be dealt with before a military "
"force can marched through the region.\n"
"\n"
"Travel to the region of {$v16}. Once there, kill five Hill Giants. When you "
"have completed your mission, report back to Bigclubs Trollmangler in "
"Swampton."

msgid "start_text_quest_2291"
msgstr ""
"Just southwest of the human border village of {$v17} stands a small keep, "
"and outside this keep stands a statue of some weedy human knight or other. "
"For unknown reasons, the local humans consider this statue important, and "
"they will go to great lengths to defend it. This should provide motivation "
"enough for orks to make every effort to defile this statue, preferably in as "
"crude and insulting a manner as possible. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Fight or sneak your way to {$v17}. Once there, use your weapon to disfigure "
"the statue with some coarse and degrading insult. Once this is done, you "
"should retreat before Trinwood's defenders have time to react. Do not stray "
"too close to Trinwood itself, since this town is defended by a very "
"dangerous guardtower."

msgid "start_text_quest_2292"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigork Blacktongue. Kill six Ork Bandits. "
"This mission must be completed within a two hour time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2293"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Bigork Blacktongue's quest. Go to the dwarven town of "
"Selengard in {$x12}, and search for the Banegrail."

msgid "start_text_quest_2294"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Banegrail. Deliver it to Bigork Blacktongue in Emberhall, "
"if you wish to exchange the terrible artifact for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2295"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted yet another mission from Bigork Blacktongue, the "
"Dragonbound agent in Emberhall. Talk to Slayor Strongork in {$x11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2296"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Slayor Strongork's quest. Kill four Hawk Revenants and "
"three Leopard Revenants in Itak Laurgul."

msgid "start_text_quest_2297"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Slayor Strongork, the Dragonbound "
"representative in {$x11}. Search the ruins of {$x11} for the Amber Harp. If "
"you find it, take it to Bigork Blacktongue in Emberhall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2298"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the Amber Harp to Bigork Blacktongue, as instructed by Slayor "
"Strongork, the Dragonbound representative in {$x11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2299"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Bigork Blacktongue's latest mission. Destroy the sadayel "
"shrine in the {$v11}. You must use physical force to achieve complete this "
"task."

msgid "start_text_quest_230"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Manglar's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to her with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_2300"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to seek out Stranglar Bloodaks in the village of Bad Dog."

msgid "start_text_quest_2301"
msgstr ""
"Stranglar Bloodaks asked you to search the Nardath ruins for the Fecund "
"Leaf, and you accepted the mission."

msgid "start_text_quest_2302"
msgstr "Deliver the book called the Fecund Leaf to Stranglar Bloodaks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2303"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted another mission from Stranglar Bloodaks. Search the Troll "
"Lords Den for the Orb of Decay and bring it to Bigork Blacktongue in "
"Emberhall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2304"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Orb of Decay. Stranglar Bloodaks has instructed you to "
"deliver the orb to Bigork Blacktongue in Emberhall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2305"
msgstr ""
"You have embarked upon a search for an artifact known as the Mark of "
"Morneid. Search for the Mark of Morneid in the Kobold Strongman camps of "
"Laurgul."

msgid "start_text_quest_2306"
msgstr ""
"You have found a necklace which matches the description of a Mark of "
"Morneid. Bring it to Bigork Blacktongue in Emberhall to verify its "
"authenticity, and to collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2307"
msgstr ""
"All hail the Fire Dragon, bringer of death, destruction and orkish "
"supremacy. I am one of the Dragonbound, an order which serves the dragon-"
"goddess by furthering her catastrophic agenda.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Fire Dragon currently slumbers within the Great Stairs, a huge "
"sacrificial altar which stands in the center of the orkish capital of "
"{$v13}. When she awakes, the goddess will unleash the Great Burning, an "
"apocalyptic rampage during which Agon's soil will be scorched and all non-"
"orks will be either enslaved or annihilated.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As the recent earthquakes and volcanic eruptions have indicated, the hour of "
"the Fire Dragon's awakening draws nigh. In order to nourish and stir her at "
"this critical juncture, we have doubled the rate of sentient sacrifice here "
"in Emberhall. Day and night, the screams of the dying rise through the smoke "
"from burning corpses, while a steady stream of still-throbbing hearts are "
"devoured in honor of the Fire Dragon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, some very selfish bandits have chosen this time to begin "
"raiding the caravans which bring us the captives we need to maintain the "
"current rate of sacrifice. If we don't wipe out these maggots immediately, "
"their greed could delay or even imperil the Fire Dragon's reawakening. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The bandits in question inhabit several small villages which lie to the "
"south of here, among which is the village of Broken Tusk. Go and kill six of "
"these bandits. Since time is of the essence in this matter, I need you to "
"complete this mission before two hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_2308"
msgstr ""
"The Dragonbound's leader is Grand Messenger Arxanthos, a prophet who "
"channels and interprets the dreams of the Fire Dragon. As the goddess "
"finally stirs from her long slumber, Arxanthos calls for steadily larger and "
"more intricate sacrifice rituals, as well as magical or beautiful items "
"which are added to the Fire Dragon's hoard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Last night, I had the honor of being summoned into Arxanthos's lair, which "
"lies inside the Great Stair here in Emberhall. The Grand Messenger informed "
"me that the slumbering goddess craves the Banegrail, a lost artifact of "
"legendary darkness and power.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Banegrail was forged in desperation by the dwarves of Selengard, a small "
"mining community whose wealth and isolation attracted the attention of an "
"orkish pirate fleet. In a last, desperate attempt at saving their city, the "
"local dwarves called upon a malign dwarven god called Sahul, who instructed "
"them to make a grail of selentine which he would then fill with a liquid "
"that he promised would make the defenders invincible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sahul kept his promise, after a fashion. Drinking the liquid turned the "
"inhabitants of Selengard into Undead Dwarves who rise again and again, "
"doomed to defend their city and the cursed Banegrail forever. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Fire Dragon now craves that dark artifact for her hoard. I want you to "
"steal it from Selengard's undead defenders. I will mark the position of "
"Selengard on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_2309"
msgstr ""
"Centuries ago, Agon was ruled by a race of golden-skinned giants called the "
"Nithron. Godlike and immortal, these ancients were arrogant and sometimes "
"cruel in their treatment of lesser beings, and they seem to have derived "
"much pleasure from commanding armies of mortals in an endless series of wars."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The largest Nithron ruin in this part of Morak is {$x11}, a partially sunken "
"city which lies on a coastal island to the east of here. Grand Messenger "
"Arxanthos recently commanded the Dragonbound to excavate these largely "
"unexplored ruins, which may still hide magical items that are worthy of "
"inclusion in the Fire Dragon's hoard. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Agents of the Dragonbound have already begun searching the ruins, but they "
"have met resistance from well-entrenched monster populations. If you want to "
"help us increase the size and magnificence of the Fire Dragon's hoard, go to "
"Itak-Laurgul and report for duty with excavation leader Slayor Strongork."

msgid "start_text_quest_231"
msgstr ""
"All spells need ingredients which are used up when you cast them. New "
"ingredients must then be bought or collected as byproducts of harvesting "
"processes such as skinning, mining and woodcutting. I have run out of an "
"ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by people "
"engaged in herb gathering, and I'm willing to give you a reward if you help "
"me resupply. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To gather herbs you need to hold a tool called a sickle. If you don't own "
"one already, you can buy a sickle from Gulgon the Merchant here in Metal "
"Heart.  Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your "
"chosen bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. Repeat "
"this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2310"
msgstr ""
"The ruins around us were left by the Nithron, an ancient race of giants who "
"did not suffer age, and who were as powerful as minor deities. The "
"admittedly limited historical source material from the period indicates that "
"the Nithron disappeared almost overnight, leaving their cities in the hands "
"of advanced guardian constructs which maintain their vigil to this day.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As soon as we set foot on {$x11}, ancient creatures called revenants sprang "
"to life and began attacking our excavation teams. If we are to continue our "
"search for the artifacts which the Fire Dragon craves, we must first get rid "
"of these ancient yet untiring guardians.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four Hawk Revenants on the small island to the northwest of here, and "
"three Leopard Revenants on the island to the south."

msgid "start_text_quest_2311"
msgstr ""
"Our primary task here in {$x11} is to find ancient treasures that may be "
"added to the ever-increasing hoard on which the Fire Dragon sleeps. "
"According to Grand Messenger Arxanthos, who interprets the dreams and "
"desires of the slumbering goddess, the thing she most craves here in Itak-"
"Laurgul is an enchanted harp made entirely from amber. According to the "
"legends, the Nithron used this magical instrument to recruit sea monsters "
"such as matayin and irtych into their armies.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Though its strings haven't been plucked for centuries, soft sounds still "
"emanate from the Amber Harp, and a large group of matayin are still kept in "
"thrall by it. To obtain the harp, you must fight or sneak your way past "
"these guardians, who will defend the enchanted instrument with their lives."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would search for the Amber Harp in the sunken Nithron ruins. Should you "
"find the harp, please make haste to Emberhall and give it to Bigork "
"Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_2312"
msgstr ""
"The swamps of Morak are infested with a race that is so abominable, so "
"perverted that the only reasonable response to their presence is a campaign "
"of annihilation. Known as the sadayel, these loathsome swamp-vermin are more "
"resourceful and more culturally advanced relations of the common lizardman, "
"and they are the implacable and eternal blood-enemies of the orkish race. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The feather-clad shamans of the sadayel recently begun to prophesy the "
"rebirth of a legendary sadayel warlord called Antares, who they say will "
"sweep the orks out of their home-swamps and lead the sadayel into a new "
"golden age. All nonsense, of course, but the sadayel people seem to have "
"found courage and strength in the promise, and throughout Morak, they have "
"taken the offensive against orkish communities that occupy what they "
"consider to be their ancestral land.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Shrines have sprung up in sadayel villages throughout Morak, each containing "
"a sadayel egg that was laid on the same night as a meteor appeared in the "
"sky. According to the sadayel shamans, the warlord Antares will hatch and be "
"reborn from one of these eggs. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"By crushing these eggs, we can simultaneously destroy the resurgent morale "
"of the sadayel tribes. Agents have been dispatched to most sites, but we "
"recently learned of a hitherto unknown shrine in a region known as the "
"{$v11}. I want you to travel there and destroy both the egg and the shrine "
"that holds it. You must use physical force to achieve this, as the eggs seem "
"somehow impervious to magical damage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2313"
msgstr ""
"I want you to go and report for duty with Strangler Bloodaks, the "
"Dragonbound agent in the neighboring village of Bad Dog. Strangalar is "
"searching for a book called the Fecund Leaf, rumored to be hidden somewhere "
"in the ruin village of Nardath.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to help, start by reporting for duty with Strangler Bloodaks, "
"the Dragonbound agent in the neighboring village of Bad Dog, west of here in "
"the {$u12} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2314"
msgstr ""
"Before the armies of the Fire Dragon showed them the error of their ways, "
"the people of the nearby village of Nardath worshiped an abominable swamp "
"deity called Ul-Surgash, whose teachings were gathered in a book called the "
"Fecund Leaf. This book is said to contain information about the magical "
"properties of certain rare plants that grow in the innermost reaches of "
"Morak's swamps. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Dragonbound would like to add The Fecund Leaf to our library of heresies "
"in Emberhall. Rumor has it that the natives secreted away several copies "
"before Nardath fell, and we want you to search the ruins for one of these "
"books."

msgid "start_text_quest_2315"
msgstr ""
"The Fecund Leaf speaks of an artifact, sacred to Ul-Surgash, which slowly "
"corrupts all nature around it, eventually turning it into swampland. When "
"Nargash was sacked, its conquerors saw no trace of such an artifact, but "
"recent changes to the terrain of this region might offer a clue to its "
"whereabouts. Veterans who were present at the siege of Nargash claim that "
"the terrain to the south of the village was dry woodland, while now it "
"consists mostly of swamp. This might indicate that the people of Nargash "
"buried their precious orb in this location rather than see it fall into the "
"hands of their enemies.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The swampland in question is currently inhabited by a tribe of trolls. I "
"want you to search their swamp-clad territory for the Orb of Decay, which "
"according to the Fecund Leaf is a deep emerald color. Should you find it, I "
"want you to bring this artifact directly to Bigork Blacktongue in Emberhall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2316"
msgstr ""
"Demons are natives of some unknown, presumably infernal plane who only visit "
"Agon to harvest souls. When their hunger has been satisfied, demons depart "
"as abruptly as they came, leaving behind a trail of utter, catastrophic "
"destruction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When the demon Morneid departed Agon, after laying waste to large tracts of "
"central Morak, he left behind several magical items that he had distributed "
"among the officers of his army. One of these demonic artifacts, known as the "
"Mark of Morneid, eventually found its way into the hands of a tribe of "
"exceptionally capable and warlike kobolds who control parts of a region "
"called Laurgul.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This morning, Grand Messenger Arxanthos reported that he had received "
"another dream-decree from the Fire Dragon. In this dream the goddess "
"communicated a craving for the Mark of Morneid, an item which she feels "
"would make a nice addition to her hoard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Travel to Laurgul and search the Kobold Strongman camps for the Mark of "
"Morneid."

msgid "start_text_quest_2317"
msgstr "You have accepted Jeremiah Grace's mission. Kill four centaurs."

msgid "start_text_quest_2318"
msgstr ""
"Jeremiah Grace has asked you to strike a blow against the Wychwater rebels. "
"Kill five Human Renegades."

msgid "start_text_quest_2319"
msgstr "You have accepted Jeremiah Grace's mission. Kill four Trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_232"
msgstr "You have accepted Bosork's quest. Return to him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2320"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill Air Elementals on a floating island over Cloudhenge. "
"Kill three Air Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_2321"
msgstr "You have accepted Sir Jeremiah Grace's quest. Kill one Greater Below."

msgid "start_text_quest_2322"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Sir Jeremiah Grace's quest. Kill five Malaut Acolytes and "
"two Human Highwaymen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2323"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Sir Jeremiah Grace's quest. Kill three Malaut Beguilers "
"and three Human Highwaymen located in the village of Snowthorpe."

msgid "start_text_quest_2324"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Sir Jeremiah Grace's quest. Kill four Below and three "
"Malaut Beguilers inside the hidden valley in Darkmouth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2325"
msgstr ""
"The forest-clad region of {$t21} is in open revolt against Mercian rule. "
"Incited by traitorous druids called Dark Arannog, the local sylvan creatures "
"have mobilized against us, and the entire Wychwode now seems to sway and "
"moan with a thirst for Mercian blood. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The northern parts of the Wychwode is the domain of the Gallhorns, a "
"particularly bloodthirsty herd of centaurs. Fiercely xenophobic, the "
"Gallhorns have long attacked any outsider who strayed into their territory. "
"They have, however, tended to be quite reclusive, and in the past they "
"rarely strayed beyond the confines of the Wychwode. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Spurred by the Dark Arannog, the Gallhorns have now taken to raiding Mercian "
"communities that lie along the edge of the forest. The result is a trail of "
"dead farmers and razed villages, as well as a stream of refugees fleeing "
"towards {$u21} and {$u20}.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must put an end to the Gallhorn herd's ravages. Kill four centaurs."

msgid "start_text_quest_2326"
msgstr ""
"Situated on a lake in the eastern part of the forest, the village of "
"Wychwater is the largest human community in the {$t21} region. Wychwater "
"lies on an island in the middle of a lake, and it can only be reached by "
"crossing a narrow, easily defended causeway.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rebel have taken over Wychwater, and have killed the governor and his "
"guards. And just two days ago, the rebels repelled a punitive expedition, "
"killing several Knights of Malregard in the process. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Needless to say, this is a humiliation which cannot be allowed to stand. The "
"Wychwater rebellion must be crushed, and it must be crushed in a way that "
"discourages others rebels throughout Mercia that wish to follow the example "
"of the Wychwater rebels. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to the village of Wychwater and kill five Human Renegades."

msgid "start_text_quest_2327"
msgstr ""
"Deep in the southern reaches of the {$t21} stands a copse of tall pines, the "
"kind that normally grows only in more northern climes. These trees encircle "
"a small spring which, according to local beliefs, contains the spirit of the "
"Wychwode. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Renowned for being as clear as glass, this spring has now been turned into a "
"fetid swamp by a group of Trolls who have migrated into the Wychwode from "
"the south. Presumably, the Trolls were invited into the forest by the Dark "
"Arannog, in an attempt to destabilize Mercian rule.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Trolls are unspeakably vile creatures who corrupt nature by their mere "
"presence. Almost immediately following their arrival, the spring grew "
"stagnant, while around it a once beautiful part of Wychwode became darker "
"and drearier. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Even as we speak, The Trolls taint is spreading outward in ever-widening "
"circles. We must stop them before they do irreparable damage to the "
"venerable and sacred Wychwode forest. Kill four Trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2328"
msgstr ""
"In the heart of the {$t21} stands Cloudhenge, a circle of stones which is "
"permanently shrouded in mist. Long abandoned and overgrown, Cloudhenge was "
"once an important religious site, and during the wars of the Mercian "
"invasion, Imric druids are said to have drawn much power from it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Somehow, the Dark Arannog have reactivated Cloudhenge. In the manner of the "
"ancient druids which they emulate, they are now tuned into the magic which "
"emanates from the stone circle, and they are using it to increase the power "
"of their spells and magical processes. If we are to decisively defeat the "
"Dark Arannog in Wychwode, the power of Cloudhenge must first be broken.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cloudhenge is the domain of a group of Air Elementals who live on a floating "
"island directly above it. According to our sages, the stone circle's power "
"would fade if these arcane creatures were to be killed. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill three Air Elementals on the floating island over Cloudhenge. The island "
"is reached through a magical portal which stands in the center of the "
"Cloudhenge stone circle."

msgid "start_text_quest_2329"
msgstr ""
"Like all right-thinking Mercians, the Knights of Malregard believe that "
"justice and order emanate from Auros, a purely benevolent god who shines "
"light into an otherwise dark and chaotic world.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to our beliefs, Auros is locked in a constantly shifting struggle "
"with Malaut, a powerful deity who breathes greed, chaos and lies into the "
"world. Malaut's baneful influence on Agon is known as his shadow.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A powerful agent of Malaut recently crawled up from the nether regions and "
"established himself in a cave system in the region of {$s21}. Even as we "
"speak, he is working his insidious influence on the inhabitants of that "
"region, twisting their minds and luring them into Malaut's shadow with "
"promises of wealth and debauchery. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must kill this shade-spawned creature, called a Greater Below, before it "
"corrupts more innocent people. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The cavern system is located to the southeast of here. Once you reach the "
"small mountain range, search for one of the entrances that leads into the "
"large cavern underneath the mountain. The Greater Below's lair lies "
"somewhere within. Kill the Greater Below."

msgid "start_text_quest_233"
msgstr ""
"The region of Fire Run is overflowing with goblin. We have decided to kill "
"or drive off these homeless wretches, who have made quite a nuisance of "
"themselves lately. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While massacring goblins, it makes sense to harvest their teeth, which find "
"use as low powered ingredients in magical enchantments. To take the tooth "
"from a goblin, equip a skinner knife and use it on the goblin's corpse. If "
"you don't own a skinner, you can buy one from Gulgon the Merchant here in "
"Metal Heart. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2330"
msgstr ""
"The vast majority of Mercians live in the light of Auros. There are those, "
"however, who have fallen for Malaut's lies, and who dwell in his shadow, "
"wallowing in the sordid pleasures and hollow luxuries that he confers. "
"Congregations of Malaut worshipers are referred to as shaded coteries, while "
"Malaut's entire reach, flock and influence is referred to as his Twilight "
"Kingdom. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The inhabitants of a region called {$s21} recently fell under the sway of a "
"Greater Below. These creatures are powerful and malevolent lieutenants in "
"the armies of the Twilight Kingdom, capable of spreading Malaut's shadow "
"among mortals.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The shadow spun by a Greater Below is very potent, and it can corrupt "
"monsters and animals as well as humans and other civilized beings. Once a "
"creature has been infected with such a shadow, nothing can stop it from "
"slowly consuming the poor wretch, who then becomes a sick slave of pleasure "
"and excess. Death is the only escape and salvation for such a creature.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill five Malaut Acolytes and two Human Highwaymen, all of whom have fallen "
"into the shadow of the Twilight Kingdom."

msgid "start_text_quest_2331"
msgstr ""
"Malaut's shadow is spreading rapidly through Mercia, and only through "
"vigilance and stern action can the dark tide be turned. According to "
"government inquisitors, the entire village of Snowthorpe, which is located "
"to the north of here in the {$s20} region, has been lured into Malaut's "
"Twilight Kingdom. In their testimony, the inquisitors state that the "
"villagers are indulging in wild orgies and murderous rituals, while openly "
"worshiping Malaut.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The people of Snowthorpe have strayed into the Twilight Kingdom, and such is "
"the weight of Malaut's shadow, that there is no way back into the light. The "
"moment these poor people allowed their community to slip into the Twilight "
"Kingdom, they doomed themselves to eternal damnation. If the light of Auros "
"is to shine once again on the village of Snowthorpe, all tainted inhabitants "
"must be slain without mercy. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to be our instrument of cleansing. Travel to Snowthorpe and "
"once there, kill three Malaut Beguilers and three Human Highwaymen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2332"
msgstr ""
"Given the size of Snowthorpe's shaded coterie, as well as its level of "
"activity and organization, there is every reason to fear the subtle presence "
"of one or several Below. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These vile, insidious creatures are the nobles of the Twilight Empire. They "
"command its armies of human slaves and worshipers, and work tirelessly to "
"cover new communities with Malaut's shadow. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Below are tall and gaunt figures, who are presumed to have been human "
"once, but whose appearance has been twisted beyond recognition by Malaut's "
"influence. Though physically fragile, the Below are supremely intelligent, "
"and they tend to be skillful wielders of magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are no Below in the village of Snowthorpe itself, and our inquisitors "
"have so far been unable to extract relevant information from prisoners. All "
"the inquisitors can say is that there are whispers of a hidden valley in the "
"{$s20} region, to the west of the village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Find the hidden valley with the Malaut worshippers, and send four Below and "
"three Malaut Beguilers back into the shadows that spawned them."

msgid "start_text_quest_2333"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Maria Hawksgate's quest. Kill five Skeleton and five "
"Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2334"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Maria Hawksgate. You are cast a mana drain "
"spell on the foul shadow-tree in {$u18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2335"
msgstr "You have accepted Maria Hawksgate's quest. Kill four Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2336"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Maria Hawksgate's quest. Kill four Hill Giant Sluggers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2337"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Maria Hawksgate. You are to kill at least "
"four Hobgblins in {$w18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2338"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Maria Hawksgate. Kill five Melechar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2339"
msgstr "You have agreed to kill two Flesh Golems in Thelaessa."

msgid "start_text_quest_234"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Bosork's latest Mission. Cast twenty Mana Missiles against "
"the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_2340"
msgstr ""
"Maria Hawksgate has asked you to deal with the Giant Skeletons in {$u17}. "
"Kill four Giant Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_2341"
msgstr ""
"All that is good and just in Agon emanates from the god Auros, while chaos "
"and cruelty is breathed forth by Malaut, his ancient enemy. Malaut's reach "
"and influence, called his Shadow, is growing stronger in Mercia, and as a "
"result, his servants grow numerous and powerful. Even here, in the Mercian "
"heartland, the shadows are lengthening, and places that once were havens of "
"peace are now threatened by growing monster populations.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I belong to the White Order, a religious group which is dedicated to the "
"worship of Auros, and to dispersing Malaut's shadow wherever it falls. One "
"of the most important tasks performed by the Order, is the interment of the "
"dead and the subsequent guarding of their remains, which could otherwise "
"fall prey to threats such as ghouls and necromancers. Our graveyard here in "
"{$t18} is the largest in Mercia, and most citizens of Sanguine eventually "
"end up here, under the Order's protection. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the Order's horror, the dead of {$u18} graveyard have begun to claw their "
"way out of the ground at an astonishing rate. While we investigate the "
"causes behind this embarrassing and dangerous development, we need help with "
"containing the outbreak. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Help us control the number of undead by killing five Skeleton and five "
"Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2342"
msgstr ""
"As you know, a gentle river runs through {$u18}'s graveyard. Sacred to "
"Auros, this stream is said to wash away any vestige of shadow-taint from the "
"souls of those who are buried near it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In an act of the utmost profanity, agents of Malaut have tainted the river, "
"turning it into a conduit of the foulest necromancy. Instead of soothing the "
"dead in their sleep, the river's water now wakes them and fills their minds "
"with confused rage.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The source of the taint is a cursed tree which has been planted in the "
"center of the river's source-spring. Dark shadow-sap flows from the trunk of "
"this tree, tainting the entire flow of the river, and ultimately causing the "
"outbreak of undeath in the graveyard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to stop the shadow-tree from tainting the river, and therefor "
"raising the dead. You can achieve this by casting a mana drain spell onto "
"the shadow-tree, which will remove the foul tree's necromantic powers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2343"
msgstr ""
"A group of Dire Zombies recently infiltrated this region, establishing a "
"camp near the source of the river which runs through {$u18} graveyard. Here, "
"they planted and nourished a shadow-tree which now taints the river with "
"necromantic sparks which cause the dead of the graveyard to rise.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If this region is to return to tranquil normality, these dark gardeners must "
"be removed. Be warned, though, that they are much more formidable opponents "
"than regular zombies, and that they prefer long range spells to close combat."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_2344"
msgstr ""
"For centuries, the region of {$v16} has been a battlefield in the wars "
"between humans and orks. After countless looting, burnings and vengeful "
"razing, all civilians have long since been killed or displaced, while the "
"region itself has been reduced to a barren, spell-blasted wasteland. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In an attempt to gain indirect control over {$v16}, orkish authorities "
"recently convinced a gang of Hill Giants to move into the region. These "
"brutes have now settled in several abandoned orkish villages, and they hold "
"up their end of the agreement by attacking all humans who enter their "
"territory. Granted, they also attack orks, but you can only expect so much "
"loyalty and focus from a gang of Hill Giants.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We can't allow the orks and their allies to gain the upper hand in {$v16}. "
"It may be a shattered and broken no-man's-land, but due to its location, the "
"region is of vital strategic importance.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to kill four Hill Giants Sluggers in{$v16}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To get to {$v16}, first follow the dirt road to {$v17}, which starts at "
"{$u18}'s northern gate. From there, make your way still further north "
"through the wilderness."

msgid "start_text_quest_2345"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have discovered that the hobgoblins of {$w18} have not only been "
"busy fortifying their camp, but also increasing their numbers with a steady "
"income of small hobgoblin war bands arriving from the north.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have we battled the hobgoblins, and always have we "
"been successful in defeating them and destroying their plans for expansion "
"into Mercia.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hobgoblin are a brutal and privative race, who's loyalties belong to nobody. "
"Very rarely would hobgoblin armies unit, and only under the leadership of a "
"very powerful figure. We are not sure if the hobgoblins somehow have now "
"united behind some powerful figure, and are preparing an attack into Mercia. "
"Nor can we sit and wait to find out. We must strike quickly, and put a stop "
"to their plans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But before we issue the command to attack the hobgoblins, we must gather as "
"much information possible. The White Order would ask of you to go to the "
"hobgoblins camps, and assess their strength. Killing at least four of their "
"units should provide us with enough information. You will find their camps "
"in the {$w18} to the east of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2346"
msgstr ""
"Most mirdain elves live in the Forest Republic, a sylvan empire which "
"encompasses most of the sprawling and ancient Mirendil Forest. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Though peaceful on the surface, the Republic is a place of ancient politics "
"and layer upon layer of deception and intrigue. Those mirdain who find "
"themselves on the losing end of power struggles sometimes choose to leave "
"the forest, frequently in a hurry and with assassins in their wake. As a "
"result of this steady trickle of emigration, communities of expatriate "
"mirdain are found throughout Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until recently, a Mirdain village called Thelaessa thrived in the Mercian "
"region of {$w17}, which lies close to the orkish border. Recently, however, "
"this village was attacked under cover of night by a group of melechar who "
"killed many of the inhabitants and drove the rest off to a second refuge in "
"the human village of Summershard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The melechar are a race of evil surface elves who once worshiped the alfar "
"god king Melek. They worked constantly to further the nefarious, frequently "
"insane goals of their master. But in recent years, the melechar have fallen "
"from Melek's favor, and are now considered enemies of the alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Still, the now homeless and bitter melechar are still one of the most evil "
"races upon Agon, and are not a welcome presence within Mercia. We wish to "
"drive the melechar out of Thelaessa, and to resettle the mirdain, who have "
"served us well in the past as a buffer against Morak. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill five Melechar in the village of Thelaessa."

msgid "start_text_quest_2347"
msgstr ""
"A group of melechar elves recently conquered a mirdain village called "
"Thelaessa in the province of {$w17}. While the mirdain are our close allies, "
"the melechar are twisted wretches who serve Melek, the cruel and insane god-"
"king of the alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The melechar began their assault on Thelaessa by unleashing a group of Flesh "
"Golems on the mirdain, who were unable to resist the onslaught of those "
"undead monstrosities. If we are to drive the melechar out of Northern "
"{$w17}, we must first get rid of the Flesh Golems, who currently guard the "
"narrow stone bridge which joins the Thelaessa to the rest of the world. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Flesh Golems are constructs made from the flesh of still-living victims, who "
"are kept artificially alive by the magic of the creation process. Their "
"subsequent lives are ones of unending,  excruciating pain, and killing a "
"Flesh Golem is an act of mercy. Kill two Flesh Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_2348"
msgstr ""
"At a time when Mercia was torn apart by civil war, the orks of Morak took "
"the opportunity to invade from the north. Spearheaded by an elite unit of "
"giants, the orkish army seemed unstoppable, facing as it did only exhausted "
"and partially depleted human armies. When all serious opposition seemed to "
"have been swept aside, the orkish king ordered his giants to sack the human "
"capital.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The giants marched unopposed towards Sanguine, but as all seemed lost for "
"the humans, a nobleman called Skuld Snowfeather led a hastily assembled army "
"against the giants, and miraculously defeated them in a battle which took "
"place in {$u17}. To commemorate the unlikely victory, a war memorial was "
"built on the spot where Skuld Snowfeather single-handedly slew the giant "
"leader and turned the tide of battle.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sparked into life, no doubt, by tendrils of Malaut's shadow, these giants "
"have now risen to haunt the old battlefield in skeletal form. Several groups "
"of pilgrims to the Snowfeather monument have been attacked, and we are "
"beginning to fear for the safety of nearby human communities. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to return the old giants to their rest. Kill four Giant Skeletons "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2349"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Iain Deepwode. Kill three Sarlids and five "
"Spiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_235"
msgstr ""
"Most goblins are afraid of magic, which is why those sneaky little shamans "
"of theirs usually end up in charge. Sometimes, one little spell can be "
"enough to send the toughest goblin warrior running for the hills.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You could help clear Metal Heart of vermin by casting twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins who are infesting the region. Hopefully, this will make "
"them think twice about settling permanently near the village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to hold a magestaff. If "
"you don't own one of those already, you can buy one from any arcanist shop, "
"such as Uldug-ug's, which lies here in  Metal Heart. Once you own a staff, "
"you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your "
"character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2350"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Iain Deepwode. Search for the Diadem of Dawn "
"somewhere in the troll camp which lies in {$u22}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2351"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Diadem of Dawn. Bring it to Iain Deepwode and collect "
"your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2352"
msgstr "You have accepted Iain Deepwode's quest. Kill four Undead Dwarves."

msgid "start_text_quest_2353"
msgstr "You have agreed to seek out Eva Rainbird in {$w19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2354"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Eva Rainbird. Kill six salamanders."

msgid "start_text_quest_2355"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Eva Rainbird. Kill six lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2356"
msgstr ""
"You now have the Wainfold Tapestry in your possession. Bring it to Iain "
"Deepwode in {$u21}, so that he may continue his research into the nature and "
"provenance of the Nithron artifact which you retrieved from the Troll Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_2357"
msgstr ""
"Iain Deepwode has asked you to seek the Dragontorc. He believes that this "
"Nithron artifact may be hidden somewhere among the {$t22} ruins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2358"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Dragontorn, and now have it in your possession. Bring it "
"to Iain Deepwode and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2359"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Iain Deepwode. Gather three Menhir Hearts."

msgid "start_text_quest_236"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Vilethug the Councillor's mission. Kill four goblins, then "
"return to New Flayed Elf for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2360"
msgstr ""
"I represent the Sons of Riada, a group of powerful people who seek to hasten "
"the inevitable ascendancy of Mercia and the human race. Unlike many other "
"Mercians, we do not lean on religion's crutches, but seek power through "
"knowledge and the mastery of magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you are interested in aiding our noble cause, you are in luck. It so "
"happens that we're investigating a strange phenomenon in the region. The "
"valleys and forests around {$u21} were recently infiltrated by a group of "
"sarlids, sinister humanoids who form unnatural, venom-fueled symbiotic "
"relationships with spiders. The sarlids are currently gathering the local "
"spiders in one great colony, while staging steadily more frequent food "
"gathering raids against human farms and villages.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Under sarlid leadership, the spiders have gone from dangerous predators to "
"organized threat. We must stop them before their breeding programs bear "
"poisonous fruit, and before their great colony becomes too large to handle. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Without the guidance of their sarlid shepherds, the local spiders should "
"revert to their natural behavior patterns. I want you to kill three Sarlids "
"and five of their pet Spiders in the forests west of {$u21} village."

msgid "start_text_quest_2361"
msgstr ""
"Many centuries ago, the world was ruled by a race of immortal giants called "
"the Nithron. Haughty and warlike, the golden-skinned Nithron established "
"themselves as overlords throughout the world of Agon. Their reign was marked "
"by endless warfare, as they amassed huge armies of mortals and fought each "
"other for hegemony, over territory, or just for the sport and glory of "
"battle.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the Nithron age, this part of the world was ruled by an especially cruel "
"and ambitious queen called Iyarthessa the Frostbringer. Legend has it that "
"Iyarthessa wore a magical crown which granted her extraordinary powers, even "
"for a Nithron, and that this crown would emit a burning, blinding light "
"which shone like a malevolent halo around Iyarthessa when she rode into "
"battle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A group of adventurers recently came into possession of a crown which "
"closely matches the ancient descriptions of Iyarthessa's crown. The "
"adventurers claim that, when they found the diadem, it was floating in the "
"air over a broken throne in some nondescript ruin in the wasteland province "
"of {$t25}. Unable to activate the diadem, the adventurers later sold it to a "
"local agent of the Sons of Riada.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, this agent subsequently disappeared en route to {$u21}. After "
"exhausting all other alternatives, we now believe that he was ambushed and "
"killed by a band of Troll Lords who inhabit a secluded rocky hollow just "
"south of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to search the troll's hollow for the Diadem of Dawn. I suggest "
"you search for a some kind of container, such as a chest or a crate. Once "
"you locate it, use the action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_2362"
msgstr ""
"The Sons of Riada recently began excavations in Theyril Hall, an abandoned "
"dwarven mining village which lies just a short distance east of here. It is "
"dwarven custom to bury the dead with some choice possessions, and since the "
"inhabitants of Theyril Hall were famously rich until the eponymous theyril "
"ran out, we hope to find vast treasures in catacombs beneath the village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, the dwarven dead have reacted rather badly to our incursions. "
"Almost as soon as the first spade hit the ground, large numbers of dwarven "
"corpses began to emerge from the ground. Groaning and shambling around their "
"old home, these undead dwarves now attack anyone who enters Theyril Hall, "
"including archaeologists, and we have been forced to temporarily abandon the "
"site.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Theyril Hall lies within a mountain peak which, through centuries of "
"exploitation, was reduced to a hollow shell by dwarven miners and quarrymen. "
"One of the location's most interesting features, is a small rock island "
"which floats in the air directly above Theyril Hall. We can only assume that "
"this island is kept afloat by some sort of dwarven rock magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help us clear Theyril Hall site for excavation. Kill four "
"Undead Dwarves. According to our scouts, Undead Foremen are only found on "
"the floating island, which can only be reached via a teleportation portal."

msgid "start_text_quest_2363"
msgstr ""
"We have examined  the nithron crown thoroughly. There is no doubt that it is "
"a genuine Nithron artifact, and that vast and terrible power seems to reside "
"within it. However, we have not yet been able to determine unequivocally "
"that the crown is the legendary Diadem of Dawn, and we have been unable to "
"tap into or activate its power.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If our research is to progress, we need access to the Wainfold Tapestry, an "
"extremely rare and ancient book, which is filled with rambling prophecies, "
"and which contains a surprisingly detailed description of Iyarthessa the "
"Frostbringer and her realm.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As far as we know, the only extant copy of the Wainfold Tapestry is in the "
"possession of Eva Rainbird, the sage of {$w19}. I want you to go to {$w19}, "
"which is located to the northeast of here, and convince her that right now, "
"we need that book more than she does.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Return to me with the Wainfold Tapestry, and you will be rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_2364"
msgstr ""
"A group of salamanders and lizardmen recently moved south into Cranwyn Bay, "
"after hobgoblins conquered their home region of {$w18}. Normally quite timid "
"creatures, the salamanders in particular are desperately protecting their "
"new home territory against all trespassers, including the herb gatherers who "
"usually supply the alchemists of {$v19} with much needed raw materials.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The invading salamanders have settled along the shores of a sacred spring, "
"which also happens to be the part of Cranwyn Bay where herbs grow in the "
"greatest abundance. I want you to decimate the ranks of the salamanders so "
"that herbalists once again may gather ingredients along the shores of the "
"sacred lake.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill six salamanders. They are found near a sacred spring which lies south-"
"southeast of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2365"
msgstr ""
"The hobgoblins which recently invaded {$w18} are in the process of clearing "
"that region of rival monster populations. A band of beaten and bloodied "
"lizardmen recently wandered into this region from the north, seeking a new "
"place to live after being violently displaced by the hobgoblins. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Slow-witted but malevolent and quite aggressive, these lizardmen are - in "
"turn - chasing away the herbalists who would normally be searching this "
"bountiful sylvan region for various kinds of rare herbs. These herbs are "
"primarily used in the production of potions, and the alchemists of {$v19} "
"are currently experiencing a shortage of several essential ingredients. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help alleviate the situation by killing six lizardmen, "
"preferably in the forests to the north of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2366"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for dealing so efficiently with those monsters. Here is the "
"Wainfold Tapestry. Handle it with the utmost care, and tell the Sons of "
"Riada that I expect to share in the findings of their research."

msgid "start_text_quest_2367"
msgstr ""
"For some mysterious and vaguely disconcerting reason, long-lost Nithron "
"artifacts have started reappearing in ruins and dungeons throughout Agon. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hopefully, the Tapestry will confirm that you recently found the Diadem of "
"Dawn, and items of similar fame and power are being unearthed on an almost "
"daily basis. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Diadem's original owner, Iyarthessa the Frostbringer, was a famous "
"enchantress among the Nithron, and she is said to have possessed some of the "
"most powerful magical items ever made. When she was finally defeated by an "
"alliance of enemies, her conquerors divided these items among themselves and "
"brought them home to their respective strongholds.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to the ancient texts, one of Iyarthessa's conquerors was a warlord "
"called Arthreldir, whose citadel lay in the present-day region of {$t22}. He "
"is said to have taken an artifact called the Dragontorc from Iyarthessa's "
"fallen body, and he is later depicted as wearing a large, dragon-shaped "
"necklace which glowed with a reddish light.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is quite possible that the Dragontorc is among those Nithron artifacts "
"which have somehow reappeared on Agon. I want you to search among the {$t22} "
"ruins for it. I suggest you search for some kind of container, such as a "
"chest or a crate. Once you locate it, use the action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_2368"
msgstr ""
"Far to the southwest, a continent called Rubaiyat has been laid waste by an "
"ancient and malevolent entity called Ur-Khamset, or the Red Pharaoh. After "
"many centuries, the Red Pharaoh's huge pyramid rose slowly from the sands, "
"and simultaneously his long-buried armies rose to serve their master once "
"again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Traditionally, the native sharjad have controlled the enormously profitable "
"spice trade with Rubaiyat. Now that the sharjad have been almost entirely "
"exterminated by the Red Pharaoh's undead hordes, the flow of spice has dried "
"out. Needless to say, the potential profits would be enormous for any "
"organization that were able to reestablish the production of spice in "
"Rubaiyat.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In short, the Sons of Riada are planning to establish a human enclave on the "
"north coast of the ravaged continent. But before embarking on such a "
"momentous undertaking, we need to make sure that we have enough magical "
"weapons and equipment to wage an effective military campaign against the "
"undead hordes of the Red Pharaoh.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to increase our stock of several enchantment ingredients before "
"starting the production of magical items. Among those ingredients are the "
"Menhir Hearts, that can be gathered from the Menhir that inhabit the region "
"of {$s22}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gather three Menhir Hearts from the Menhir that inhabit the region of {$s22}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2369"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to report for goblin extermination duty with Arduin "
"Strayshadow in {$t18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_237"
msgstr ""
"After swarming out through a hatch that had carelessly been left unlocked, a "
"group of goblins managed to take control over a slave ship just as it left "
"the harbor here in New Flayed Elf. Swiftly grounding the ship, the goblins "
"then fled northward for a while, but they quickly lost their concentration "
"and began wondering along the coast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately for the goblins, the orkish navy has a zero tolerance policy "
"on mutineers. Those little sneaks must be hunted down and killed before they "
"become an inspiration to other slaves. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four goblins then return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2370"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to hunt down and kill four Goblin Scouts and four Goblin "
"Fighters in {$t18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2371"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to hunt down and kill three Goblin Shamans and two Goblin "
"Marauders in {$t18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2372"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill one Goblin Warlord and two Goblin Marauders in "
"{$t18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2373"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a request from Arduin Strayshadow. Travel to the Redburd, "
"and deliver Arduin's report to Maria Hawksgate."

msgid "start_text_quest_2374"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your efforts, and those of some other brave adventurers, we now "
"have the goblin situation under control here in {$t19}. Our next move will "
"be to clean out the breeding grounds which spawned the green-hued tidal wave "
"that threatened to engulf us. While completely exterminating an entrenched "
"goblin population is next to impossible, we can at least put the current "
"batch thoroughly to the sword, thus ensuring that the greenskins won't cause "
"any more trouble until the next generation matures in six or seven years.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In this part of Mercia, the most fecund goblin hatcheries are the swamps and "
"lakes of {$t18}, a waterlogged region which lies to the north of here. "
"Government operatives have already been sent into this region, in "
"preparation of a full-scale military operation against the local goblin "
"strongholds.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to participate in the slaughter which is about to ensue, please "
"report for duty with Arduin Strayshadow, who is coordinating the Mercian "
"government's efforts in {$t18}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Arduin Strayshadow in our small but well fortified outpost in "
"Lainstone, which is to the north of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2375"
msgstr ""
"This place is an island in a sea of goblins which covers the rest of {$t18}. "
"Lainstone is home to a deep-rooted goblin infestation which has proved "
"impossible to eradicate completely. To make matters worse, this year is "
"shaping up to be one of the worst goblin years in living memory, and "
"countless greenskins are swarming in the swamps and wetlands of this "
"blighted region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The White Order is currently organizing a large-scale military campaign, the "
"goals of which are to decimate the goblin population, and to contain it "
"within {$t18}. If you wish to participate, you could start by helping us "
"clean out Lake Vergus, a goblin-infested cesspool which lies just east of "
"here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four Goblin Fighters and four Goblin Scouts."

msgid "start_text_quest_2376"
msgstr ""
"Most goblins are irredeemably dim-witted creatures, barely intelligent "
"enough to build mud huts and hunt small lizards. Occasionally, though, an "
"individual is born with a glimmer of intelligence, and these goblins "
"sometimes become magic-wielding shamans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Though they are rare in this part of Mercia, a couple of Goblin Shamans have "
"been sighted in the villages along the northern shores of Lake Vergus, "
"together with some of those annoyingly hard Goblin Marauders. I want you to "
"search those villages until you've located and killed three Goblin Shamans "
"and two Goblin Marauders."

msgid "start_text_quest_2377"
msgstr ""
"All larger goblin tribes are ruled by warlords, who tend to be both "
"stronger, smarter and more resourceful than their subjects. According to the "
"White Order, the local warlord is an ambitious individual who has adorned "
"himself with the somewhat overstated title of Archduke Stabby XII.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The White Order believes that killing Stabby should seriously delay a full-"
"scale goblin invasion of the mining town of {$t19}, which lies to the south "
"of here, and it might even lead to a power struggle as pretenders scramble "
"to replace their fallen leader. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While agents have been sent out to locate and kill Archduke Stabby himself, "
"the White Order has asked that we locate able heroes to deal with Stabby's "
"henchmen. To the northwest of here, in the middle of a fetid fly-infested "
"swamp, resides a large palisaded goblin village. Located there are some of  "
"Archduke Stabby's strongest units, the Goblin Warlords and Goblin Marauders. "
"By killing at least one Goblin Warlord and two Goblin Marauders, we should "
"be able to weaken the resolve of the goblins within the region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill one Goblin Warlord and two Goblin Marauders."

msgid "start_text_quest_2378"
msgstr ""
"I have prepared a report regarding the goblin situation here in {$t18}, "
"which must be delivered to the White Order  in Copperdale. #PlayerName#, I "
"can think of no better individual to deliver this report to the White Order. "
"Once there, hand the report to Maria Hawksgate. I will remain here to "
"continue my work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2379"
msgstr "You have agreed to kill six Hivekin Foragers in {$t20}."

msgid "start_text_quest_238"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Vilethug the Councillor. Bring two goblin "
"axes to Vilethug the Councillor in New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_2380"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five claws on behalf of William the Councillor of "
"Sandbrook, before three hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_2381"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from William the Councillor. Kill four Hivekin "
"Broodguards and the Hivekin Queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2382"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from William the Councillor. Search the hivekins "
"nest for the necklace called the Noonday Moon, and deliver it to Sir "
"Jeremiah Grace of the Knights of Malregard."

msgid "start_text_quest_2383"
msgstr ""
"You have the Noonday Moon in your possession. Bring it to Sir Jeremiah "
"Grace, and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2384"
msgstr ""
"This region of {$t20} has been overrun by a numberless horde of hivekin, who "
"are busy stripping the land of anything that is considered edible by their "
"standards, which are very low indeed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Given half a chance, a group of hivekin will breed at an almost "
"inconceivable pace, swiftly overrunning any food sources in the vicinity of "
"their hive. They then continue their expansion in ever widening circles, "
"stripping each region they reach of anything which even vaguely resembles "
"edible matter. If we don't turn back the hivekin tide soon, every living "
"thing in {$t20} will either be eaten or driven off. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So far the Knights of Malregard have been able to keep the road to Sanguine "
"open, but the waves of Hivekin Foragers keep growing in size and frequency, "
"and if the situation gets much worse, we will have to withdraw our road "
"patrols.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sir Jeremiah Grace of the Knights of Malregard have asked if we could assist "
"in any way possible. I want you to reduce the threat by killing six Hivekin "
"Foragers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2385"
msgstr ""
"As you may know already, magical items are made using ingredients which are "
"extracted from the bodies of slain monsters. Most monsters contain something "
"that may be of use, including the hivekin, whose claws and eyes are prized "
"by enchanters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest hivekin claws, preferably but not necessarily from the "
"hivekin who infest {$t20}. The closest hivekin are a group of Foragers who "
"are found to the northwest of here, along the road to Sanguine. A mixed "
"group of Foragers and slightly tougher Soldiers has been spotted within the "
"forest to the west.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You need a skinner to extract the claws from these pests. If you don't "
"already own one, a skinner may be bought from Thora the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our resident enchanter has informed me that she needs the claws before three "
"hours have passed. Gather five hivekin claws before this time limit has "
"passed, then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2386"
msgstr ""
"The source of the Hivekin infestation appears to be a small swamp to the "
"southwest of here. All Foragers return to this location with their loot, "
"presumably feeding most of it to the local Hivekin Queen.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The swamp is guarded by the Queen's firstborn, who grow into warrior-"
"protectors called Broodguards. These elite hivekin never stray far from "
"their mother's side, and fight to the death to defend her from attackers. "
"Unlike their lesser relatives, Broodguards are half-decent fighters, and "
"they tend to be equipped with decent, though scrounged-together weapons and "
"armor. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to kill four Hivekin Broodguards and the Hivekin Queen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2387"
msgstr ""
"A request has arrived from Sir Jeremiah Grace of the Knights of Malregard. A "
"small mirdain village in {$t20} called Willowstone recently succumbed to the "
"hivekin onslaught. Though the mirdain defended their homes valiantly, they "
"were horrendously outnumbered, and stood no real chance against the invading "
"horde. Many died before the last handful of survivors retreated to the "
"relative safety of Wolfhall in the {$s21} region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Among the slain was Coruan Willowstone, who was the guardian of the Noonday "
"Moon, a lapis lazuli gemstone that is sacred to the Mirdain. Since it can't "
"be eaten, the hivekin presumably still keep this artifact somewhere, perhaps "
"in their queen's hoard. I suggest travel to {$t20}, and search the hivekin "
"nest for some kind of container, either a crate or a chest. Use the action "
"button to investigate. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you find the Noonday Moon, please deliver it to Sir Jeremiah Grace."

msgid "start_text_quest_2388"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to seek out Maren Winterspar, who is organizing the punitive "
"campaign against the rebel village of {$v20}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2389"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to reduce the undead population of {$v20} by killing four "
"Zombies and four Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_239"
msgstr ""
"Due to the incompetence of their recently executed slavemasters, goblins "
"were allowed to escape not only with their lives, but also with some nice "
"axes that were stored aboard the ship. While goblins are expendable, we "
"would like to get the stolen axes back. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To help us with this, you need to kill each goblin first, then access his "
"possessions. To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be "
"unarmed, and then while targeting the remains use the action button. You may "
"then drag items from its backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2390"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill three Human Brawlers and three Human Outlaws that "
"are hiding in Caldcote."

msgid "start_text_quest_2391"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to harvest three units of skeleton bone and one unit of "
"corpseflesh."

msgid "start_text_quest_2392"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Maren Winterspar. Harvest an baleful venom "
"sac from the ghost spiders in the {$u21} and deliver it to Iain Deepwode in "
"Hildershall."

msgid "start_text_quest_2393"
msgstr ""
"To the south of here lies the village of {$v20}, a thoroughly depraved and "
"dirty den of vice, crime and human degradation. For decades, the only real "
"authority in Caldcote has been that of the Unseen Hand, a despicable yet "
"powerful thieves guild, which rules the region from the shadows, pulling the "
"strings of local government officials who are little more than puppets.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"On grounds of ineptitude and corruption, the king recently relieved the old "
"Earl of Caldcote of his lands and duties, while simultaneously declaring a "
"state of emergency in the village and the region surrounding it. In "
"response, the Unseen Hand instigated a full-scale rebellion in Caldcote, "
"killing several officials and driving out the local army garrison, which was "
"both hopelessly outnumbered and woefully unprepared.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The king has now called for Mercian adventurers to move against the Unseen "
"Hand, promising generous rewards to those who join his campaign against the "
"rebel bandits. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to participate, report for duty with Maren Winterspar, who is "
"coordinating the first forays into Unseen Hand territory. You will find her "
"to the south of here in the {$v20} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2394"
msgstr ""
"Caldcote is a dark an unfriendly place, which has long felt the influence of "
"the Unseen Hand, a sinister organization with ties to the Church of Malaut, "
"the arch-enemies of Mercian civilization. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently, the king tried to stamp his authority on Caldcote, with lamentable "
"results. So far, his efforts have only succeeded in provoking a wildly "
"successful popular revolt. To make matters worse, the Unseen Hand has "
"assembled a large undead army, which it now uses as an unliving shield "
"around the rebel village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Before dealing with the Unseen Hand themselves, we need to deal with their "
"undead army. I want you to decimate the grave-spawned horde that is "
"gathering in the ruins on the opposite shore, by killing four Zombies and "
"four Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_2395"
msgstr ""
"As you massacre your way through {$v20}'s undead population, I want you to "
"put the skinning knife to use on your twice-slaughtered opponents. Please "
"bring me three units of bone and one unit of zombie corpseflesh."

msgid "start_text_quest_2396"
msgstr ""
"Beyond the undead-infested beach lies the village of {$v20}, which is almost "
"entirely populated by members of the Unseen Hand thieves guild. I want you "
"start cleaning out this bandit lair by killing three Human Brawlers and "
"three Human Outlaws."

msgid "start_text_quest_2397"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for all you have done here in Caldcote. I will conduct a report "
"and send it to Aidan the Councillor. You have been of great help.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one more request I have for you. I had promised Iain Deepwode in "
"Hildershall who is a very good friend of mine, that I would harvest an "
"arachnid venom sack from the ghost spiders that have appeared in {$u21}. But "
"I am finding it difficult to make time at the moment. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wouldn't mind, would you be able to do harvest the arachnid venom "
"sack from one of the ghost spiders for me, and deliver it to Iain Deepwode "
"in Hildershall. I am sure he will reward you for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_2398"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isenda the Clever. Harvest three units of "
"Bile from the Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2399"
msgstr ""
"The Circle of Neith is a group of Mahirim spellcasters, who take special "
"interest in magical item and ancient artifacts. They are always interest in "
"acquiring strange materials, that are used for enchanting items. Such "
"materials can be harvested from the bodies of slain monsters. Now that the "
"ever hated Gnolls have reappeared, what better opportunity than this to "
"harvest a bit of their lifeforce. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to slay enough Gnoll to harvest three units of feral lifeforce. "
"You should use your skinner to archive this."

msgid "start_text_quest_240"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Wolfork the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2400"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather two units of Bile from the gnolls that have set "
"camp in {$j10}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2401"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have located a gnoll camp to the east of here in {$j10}. Go to "
"their pathetic little camp, and remind them of how weak they are. Your "
"mission is to go and harvest two units of feral lifeforce from the gnolls. "
"You will need a skinner for this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2402"
msgstr ""
"Report to Talaod the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"Sanguine's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2403"
msgstr ""
"It is imperative for Sanguine to improve its defenses, to keep its people "
"safe from the goblin hordes. Talaod the Blacksmith is in charge of "
"fortifying the towns walls. I want you to report to Talaod the Blacksmith "
"and see how you might assist him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2404"
msgstr ""
"Report to Allan the Councillor, and deliver Talaod's message that "
"Monkfield's walls will not fall to the goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2405"
msgstr ""
"Soon we will have completed the fortification of our town's walls. I am "
"pleased with the progress we have made.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to Allan the Councillor and deliver a message to him, that "
"our walls will withstand any attack from the goblins. The greenskins will "
"not set foot inside Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2406"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Allan the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2407"
msgstr ""
"The goblin hordes continue to pour out of their tunnels, as if there is no "
"ending to their numbers. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many brave souls are now out there fighting the greenskin tide. We need to "
"move quickly, and kill as many goblins as we can. Now is the time for us to "
"attack, and drive these vermin back into their filthy holes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , are you prepared to help Monkfield one more time? We can "
"definitely use your help again. If you are willing to help, I would ask of "
"you to kill seven goblins in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2408"
msgstr "Allan the Councillor has asked you to report to Jonn the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2409"
msgstr ""
"Until now, Sanguine has been relying on it's solid walls to protect its "
"people, and brave heroes like yourself to fend off the goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not the only means we have to defeat the greenskins. Magic, in "
"the right hands can be a powerful weapon, and can definitely be of help in "
"defeating the goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Jonn our local mage, is doing his part in helping Sanguine defeat the goblin "
"hordes. At the moment Jonn is gathering up specific ingredients, materials "
"or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of "
"spellcasting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Report to Jonn the Mage, to see how you may help him collect the ingredients "
"our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_241"
msgstr ""
"We are building a breakwater which will help protect New Flayed Elf against "
"the savage winter storms we sometimes get here. If you wish to help us in "
"this work, please bring us raw material for the construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To gather stone, you first need to hold a pickaxe. If you don't own such a "
"tool already, you may buy one from Azog the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please gather five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2410"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Jonn the mage. Gather five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2411"
msgstr ""
"Since you were able to collect the mandrake I had asked for, I will ask you "
"to collect another ingredient also used in the art of spellcasting. Our "
"spellcasters are in need of sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Simeon the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2412"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Jonn the mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2413"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Simeon the Merchant's shop. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2414"
msgstr ""
"Jonn the Mage has asked you deliver his message to Allan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2415"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , I thank you for all you have done here. Our spellcasters are "
"ready to aid Sanguine any way possible. I want you to deliver this message "
"to Allan the Councillor, to inform him that Sanguine can rely on its "
"spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2416"
msgstr ""
"Report to Anton the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"Sandbrook's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2417"
msgstr ""
"It is very important for Sandbrook's walls to stand solid against the goblin "
"attacks. It is these walls that will keep the goblins out, and the citizens "
"of Sandbrook safe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anton the Blacksmith is overseeing the strengthening of our walls. If you "
"may, please report to Anton the Blacksmith, and see if you may assist him in "
"his task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2418"
msgstr ""
"Report to William the Councillor, and deliver Anton's message that "
"Monkfield's walls will not fall to the goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2419"
msgstr ""
"Please go report to William the Councillor and inform him that our walls "
"will stand firm and solid against any attacks from the goblin hordes. Tell "
"him that no goblin will set foot inside Sandbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_242"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used to build a "
"new ship."

msgid "start_text_quest_2420"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from William the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2421"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived that the goblins are moving towards Sandbrook. We must "
"counterattack immediately, and stop the momentum of the goblin hordes. It is "
"now that we must push the goblin horde back, and show them what we are truly "
"made of. Our attacks must be quick and deadly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to battle the goblins once more. Killing seven goblins in less "
"than an hour will do just fine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2422"
msgstr "William the Councillor has asked you to report to Carrad the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2423"
msgstr ""
"The heroic actions of brave warriors and the strength of our walls, are not "
"the only means we have to fight the greenskin hordes that are threatening "
"our town. Magic, in the right hands can be a powerful weapon, and in our "
"situation can definitely be of major help in defeating the goblin hordes. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Carrad our local mage, is doing his part in helping Sandbrook defeat the "
"goblin hordes. At the moment Carrad is gathering up specific ingredients, "
"materials or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of "
"spellcasting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Report to Carrad the Mage, to see how you may help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2424"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Carrad the mage. Gather five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2425"
msgstr ""
"The mandrake you had collected earlier is already being put to good use to "
"help our warriors fight off the goblin hordes. I need you to collect another "
"ingredient also used in the art of spellcasting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Thora the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2426"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Carrad the mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2427"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Thora the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2428"
msgstr ""
"Carrad the Mage has asked you deliver his message to William the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2429"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , the spellcasters of Sandbrook will soon be ready to do battle "
"against the goblin hordes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this message to William the Councillor, and inform him "
"that Sandbrook can rely on its spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_243"
msgstr ""
"The merchants of New Flayed Elf wish to replace a ship that was recently "
"sunk by combination of goblins and incompetence. You could help them in "
"their effort by collecting timber that is needed for the new vessel's hull. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering timber is done by using a tool called a Wood Axe. If you don't "
"already own a Wood Axe, you may buy one from Azog the Merchant's shop, which "
"lies in the western part of New Flayed Elf.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your "
"woodaxe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_2430"
msgstr ""
"Report to Jeremiah the Blacksmith to see how you may help with the building "
"of the guard towers and guard houses along the trade routes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2431"
msgstr ""
"Heart of Eanna is a trading town, so keeping the trading routes open is of "
"the utmost importance. Especially now that our town is being tested by the "
"greenskin hordes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Jeremiah the Blacksmith is coordinating the building of a series guard "
"towers and guard houses along the trade routes. I want you to go and report "
"to Jeremiah, and assist him as he sees fit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2432"
msgstr ""
"Report to Aidan the Councillor, and deliver Jeremiah's message that very "
"soon both guard towers and guard houses will be built along the towns trade "
"routes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2433"
msgstr ""
"We have now collected enough raw materials to start the construction of the "
"guard towers and guard houses along our trading routes. The filthy "
"greenskins will be in for a big surprise once our first guard towers along "
"the trade routes are up and functional. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to report to Aidan the Councillor, and deliver to "
"him the news, that we are about to start building the guard towers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2434"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aidan the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2435"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports that the goblin hordes have increased "
"their attacks along our trade routes. This has to stop. The moment has come "
"where we shall increase our attacks and drive the goblins back into the "
"mountain from where they came from. There is no time to waste. We attack now."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I ask of you to help us once more, by killing at least seven "
"goblin in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2436"
msgstr "Aidan the Councillor has asked you to report to Caradwen the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2437"
msgstr ""
"It seems that we are gaining ground in our battle against the goblin hordes. "
"But there is a little more that can help to win this war. And that little "
"something is magic. Magic, in the right hands can be a powerful weapon, and "
"in our situation can be that extra little something to finish off the goblin "
"hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Caradwen our local mage, is doing his part in helping Heart of Eanna defeat "
"the goblin hordes. At the moment Caradwen is gathering up specific "
"ingredients, materials or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in "
"the art of spellcasting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Report to Caradwen the Mage, to see how you may help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2438"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Caradwen the mage. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2439"
msgstr ""
"I need you to collect another ingredient that is also used in the art of "
"spellcasting, and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Isabel the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_244"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Skullgor's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to her with five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2440"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Caradwen the mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2441"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Isabel the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2442"
msgstr ""
"Caradwen the Mage has asked you deliver his message to Aidan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2443"
msgstr ""
"The time has come for Heart of Eanna's spellcasters to step forth and send "
"the goblin running back into their filthy holes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I thank you for helping us. I want you to deliver this "
"message to Aidan the Councillor, and inform him that Heart of Eanna can rely "
"on its spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2444"
msgstr ""
"Report to Bigthug the Blacksmith to assist with the construction of the "
"Small Stair."

msgid "start_text_quest_2445"
msgstr ""
"Dozens of sacrifices are made every day in the ork capital, at the giant "
"altar known as the Big Stair. It is through these sacrifices that we are "
"able to please the Fire Dragon's hunger for death and blood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have decided that it is time for Chopping Necks to build it's own version "
"of the Big Stair, the Small Stair,  therefor adding to the number of "
"sacrifices made for the pleaser of the Fire Dragon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bigthug our local Blacksmith, has been given the task to coordinate the "
"building of our own Small Stair. I want you to report to Bigthug, and assist "
"with the construction."

msgid "start_text_quest_2446"
msgstr ""
"Report to Uzrok the Councillor and deliver Bigthug's message that the Small "
"Stair will soon be ready."

msgid "start_text_quest_2447"
msgstr ""
"We have collected enough raw materials to start building our own version of "
"the Big Stair. I want you to report to Urzok the councillor, and tell him "
"that very soon our sacrificial pyres will be burning, ready for the "
"sacrifices to begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2448"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Uzrok the Councillor. Kill seven goblin in "
"less than an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2449"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that the construction of our own Big Stair is almost "
"complete, and very soon the sacrificial pyres will start burning for the "
"pleasure of the Fire Dragon. We must make sure that sacrifices to the Fire "
"Dragon are worthy of her power. We need to stock up on as many goblins as we "
"can, and as soon as possible. There can never be enough deaths to quench the "
"thirst of the Fire Dragon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now. You have one hour to kill seven goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_245"
msgstr ""
"Spells run on ingredients which are used up when you cast them. New "
"ingredients must then be bought or collected as byproducts of harvesting "
"processes. Since I am a very busy ork, I sometimes pay others to do this "
"collecting for me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Right now I need mandrakes, which are a side product of herb gathering. To "
"begin gathering herbs, you need to hold a tool called a sickle. If you don't "
"own one already, you may purchase one from Azog the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2450"
msgstr "Urzok the Councillor has asked you report to Bloodzkul the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2451"
msgstr ""
"We have received word from the orkish capital Flaming Skull, that a large "
"military campaign against the Humans of Mercia, is been planned. Chopping "
"Necks will partake in this campaign. While most of the militia forces are "
"ready, the campaign will not begin until all the forces of Morak have "
"reported ready for battle. This also includes the spellcasting abilities of "
"the Mages.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"However strong our armies may be, it is always wise to go into battle, with "
"a little magical support.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bloodzkul is in charge of organizing and preparing our mages. I want you to "
"report to her, and assist her with his task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2452"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bloodzkul the Mage. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2453"
msgstr ""
"You have done well so far in collecting the mandrake I had asked for. But it "
"seems we are in need of another ingredient, and that is sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Grabgold the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2454"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Bloodzkul the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2455"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Grabgold the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2456"
msgstr ""
"Bloodzkul the Mage has asked you to deliver his message to Urzok the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2457"
msgstr ""
"We have collected enough ingredients to support the military campaign "
"against the humans with our magic. I want you to deliver this message I have "
"written to Urzok the Councillor, to inform him that Flaming Skull can rely "
"on our spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2458"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bosork. Report to Strongar the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2459"
msgstr ""
"In the heart of the orkish capital of {$v13} rises the Big Stair, a giant "
"altar from which dozens of sacrifices are thrown every day. Since the death-"
"thirst of the Fire Dragon is unquenchable, we now plan to increase our rate "
"of sacrifice here in Metal Heart by building our own, slightly smaller "
"version of the Big Stair. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Strongar our local Blacksmith, is in charge of coordinating the construction "
"of our own Big Stair, the Small Stair. From what I understand, the "
"construction of the Small Stair is almost complete. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Strongar, and assist him with the construction of "
"the Small Stair."

msgid "start_text_quest_246"
msgstr "You have accepted Vilethug's quest. Return to him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_2460"
msgstr ""
"Strongar the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Bosork the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2461"
msgstr ""
"The construction of our own Small Stair is almost complete, thanks to your "
"help and that of a few others. I want you to report to Bossork the "
"Councillor, and tell him that very soon our sacrificial pyres will be "
"burning, ready for the sacrifices to begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2462"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bosork the Councillor. Kill seven goblin in "
"less than an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2463"
msgstr ""
"Since the construction of the Small Stair will soon be complete, the "
"Dragonbound priests have asked that we waste no time in gathering "
"sacrificial offers for the Fire Dragon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The goblin that can be found near Metal Heart would make excellent offerings "
"to the Fire Dragon, once the sacrificial pyres start burning. Go and kill at "
"least seven goblins in less that an hour. Once you are done, report to me "
"and I will send others to collect the bodies for the sacrifices to begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2464"
msgstr "Bosork the Councillor has asked you report to Manglar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2465"
msgstr ""
"We have been informed large military campaign against the humans of Mercia "
"is been prepared, and that Metal Heart is to prepare for war. We must "
"prepare all our forces, including our spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Manglar is organizing and preparing our mages for war. I want you to report "
"to him, and assist him with his task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2466"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Manglar the Mage. Gather five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2467"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have informed me that we are running low on sulfur. Sulfur "
"is also used as a regent for spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Gulgon the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2468"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Manglar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2469"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Gulgon the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_247"
msgstr ""
"All monsters carry within them ingredients that can be used to craft magical "
"items. The teeth of the lowly goblin, for instance, can come in handy when "
"creating low-powered versions of many types of enchantments. I want you to "
"help turn the ongoing massacre into something positive by harvesting this "
"resource. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To take the teeth from a goblin, equip your skinning knife and use it on its "
"corpse. If you don't already own a skinner, you can buy one from Azog the "
"Merchant. Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should be able to "
"extract whole teeth from around half of the goblins you kill. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth for me."

msgid "start_text_quest_2470"
msgstr ""
"Manglar the Mage has asked you to deliver a letter to Bosork the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2471"
msgstr ""
"The spellcasters of Metal Heart are ready to crush the humans of Mercia with "
"their powerful spells. Deliver this message to Bosork the Councillor so he "
"may be informed that we are ready."

msgid "start_text_quest_2472"
msgstr "Report to Wolfork the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2473"
msgstr ""
"Wolfork the Blacksmith has request an extra pairs of hands, to help out with "
"the large amount of work load. It seems that the merchants of New Flayed Elf "
"are eager to replace the ship that was recently lost after the goblin slave "
"mutiny.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Report to Wolfork the Blacksmith, and see how you may be of help to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2474"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Wolfork the Blacksmith. Report to Vilethug "
"the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2475"
msgstr ""
"I have just received a message from Vilethug the Councillor that he wishes "
"to speak with you. There seems to be trouble with the goblin mutineers that "
"had escaped from one of our ships. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go report to Vilethug the Councillor. Do not keep the Councillor waiting."

msgid "start_text_quest_2476"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Vilethug the Councillor. Kill seven goblins "
"in less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2477"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that the goblins that had escaped from "
"one of our slave ships, our now attacking caravans along our trade routes. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"New Flayed Elf is a trading town, and we cannot allow a these pathetic "
"escapee goblins to severely disrupted the transport of goods to and from New "
"Flayed Elf. The merchants of New  Flayed Elf have requested that we deal "
"with these annoying goblin immediately. I want you to kill at least seven of "
"them in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2478"
msgstr "Vilethug the Councillor has asked you report to Skullgor the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2479"
msgstr ""
"We have received word from the capital Flaming Skull, that a massive "
"military campaign against the Humans of Mercia is been planned. New Flayed "
"Elf has also been asked to partake in this campaign. While most of the "
"militia forces are ready, the campaign will not begin until all the forces "
"of Morak have reported ready for battle. This also includes the spellcasting "
"abilities of the Mages.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is always wise, to go into battle, with magic support, however strong our "
"armies might be. And we know, that the humans always use magic in their "
"battles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Skullgor the Mage is in charge of organizing and preparing our spellcaster "
"for battle. I want you to report to Skullgor, and assist her with her task."

msgid "start_text_quest_248"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Vilethug's latest Mission. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_2480"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skullgor the mage. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2481"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are running low on sulfur, another "
"ingredient that is used when casting spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Azog the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2482"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Skullgor the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2483"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, and that is "
"resin. Resin can be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you "
"have located a tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the "
"process of extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such "
"a tool, you may buy one from Azog the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin.."

msgid "start_text_quest_2484"
msgstr ""
"Skullgor the Mage has asked you to deliver his message to Vilethug the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2485"
msgstr ""
"The spellcasters of New Flayed Elf, are ready to report for duty. I want you "
"to deliver this message I have written to Vilethug the Councillor, to inform "
"him that Flaming Skull can rely on our spells to support the military "
"campaign against the humans."

msgid "start_text_quest_2486"
msgstr ""
"Report to Ragneid the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"Eirhjelm's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2487"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the Eirhjelm council has decided "
"to expand and improve the walls around our city. Defending and protecting "
"Eirhjelm, is always a priority.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Ragneid the Blacksmith is the one in charge of overseeing the rebuilding and "
"strengthening of the walls. I want you to report to Regneid, and assist him "
"with his work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2488"
msgstr ""
"Ragneid the Blacksmith has instructed you to report to Skuldvard the "
"Councillor, and inform him of the wall improvements."

msgid "start_text_quest_2489"
msgstr ""
"We are very close to completing the improvements on the walls. No goblin "
"horde or other enemy will be able to pass our solid walls. Our walls will "
"stand strong and tall against all who wish to harm Eirhjelm.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to Skuldvard the Councillor and inform him that the walls "
"are almost complete."

msgid "start_text_quest_249"
msgstr ""
"Some of the toughest survivors of the recent goblin mutiny are hiding along "
"the coast near New Flayed Elf. But as tough as they might be, goblins are "
"afraid of magic. The time has come to break their spirit by casting twenty "
"Mana Missile spells on them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to hold a magestaff. If "
"you don't own one of those already, you can buy one from any arcanist shop, "
"such as Azog's. Once you own a staff, you may equip it by dragging it from "
"your inventory and onto your character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2490"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skuldvard the Councillor. Kill seven goblins "
"in less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2491"
msgstr ""
"The Eirhjelm council has decided that the time has come to launch a swift "
"and deadly attack against the greenskin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , Eirhjelm can use your help once more. You can do your part by "
"killing at least seven goblins in less than an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2492"
msgstr ""
"Skuldvard the Councillor has asked you to report to Steingrima the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2493"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have reported that the latest attacks against the goblin hordes "
"seem to have weaken the their numbers considerably. But still, the goblins "
"continue to pour out of their holes. We will need the strength of our "
"spellcasters if we are to defeat the greenskins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Steingrima the Arcanist has asked for help, with preparing and organizing "
"Eirhjelm's spellcasters. I would ask of you to report to Steingrima, and "
"assist her with her work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2494"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Steingrima the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2495"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are in need of sulfur. Sulfur is also "
"another ingredient used in the art of spellcasting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Erling the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2496"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Steingrima the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2497"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Erling the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2498"
msgstr ""
"Steingrima the Arcanist has asked you deliver his progress report to "
"Skuldvard the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2499"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , you have been of great help to us. Our spellcasters are ready "
"drive back the goblin hordes with their spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter I have written to Skuldvard the "
"Councillor, to inform him that Eirhjelm can rely on its spellcasters for "
"support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2500"
msgstr ""
"Report to Tordar the Blacksmith to see how you may help with the "
"construction of the guard towers along the trade routes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2501"
msgstr ""
"Many of Hammerdelve's hunters and merchants rely on selling their goods to "
"the nearby larger communities to make a living. Therefor it is vital to keep "
"the trade routes safe and open, to and from Hammerdelve. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The latest goblin attacks onto our town have made this issue much more "
"obvious. The council has decided that we must begin constructing a series of "
"guard houses and guard towers along our trade routes. Tordar the Blacksmith "
"is in charge of the construction of these defenses along the trade routes. I "
"want you to go and help Tordar with his task. Please report to him as soon "
"as you can."

msgid "start_text_quest_2502"
msgstr ""
"Report to Arngard the Councillor, and deliver Tordar's message that very "
"soon, the construction of the guardtowers along the trade routes will begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2503"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your help and that of many more, we have now enough building "
"material to begin the construction of the guard towers. Let us hope that the "
"goblin hordes do not attacks the trade routes anytime soon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Arngard the Councillor, and deliver "
"to him the news, that we are about to start building the guard towers."

msgid "start_text_quest_2504"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arngard the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2505"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that goblin bands have now begun "
"attacking caravans along our trade routes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hammerdelve is a trading town, and allowing these pesky goblin to disrupt "
"the transport of goods to and from Hammerdelve, is just not an option. The "
"merchants of Hammerdelve have requested that we quickly deal with these "
"annoying goblin immediately. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you with the next hour, to kill at least seven of these annoying "
"goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_2506"
msgstr ""
"Arngard the Councillor has asked you to report to Gormfinn the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2507"
msgstr ""
"A report has arrived from Gormfinn our local Arcanist, that our spellcasters "
"are running low on magic ingredients. Without these ingredients, it will be "
"impossible for our spellcasters to support us in our battle against the "
"goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Gormfinn the Arcanist, and help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2508"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gormfinn the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2509"
msgstr ""
"I need you to collect another ingredient that is also used in the art of "
"spellcasting, and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Ulfrid the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2510"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Gormfinn the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2511"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, and that is "
"resin. Resin can be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you "
"have located a tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the "
"process of extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such "
"a tool, you may buy one from Ulfrid the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2512"
msgstr ""
"Gormfinn the Arcanist has asked you to deliver his message to Arngard the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2513"
msgstr ""
"I have written a report letter here, that I want you to deliver to Arngard "
"the Councillor. It's just a simple letter to inform him that our "
"spellcasters are ready to do their part against the goblin threat."

msgid "start_text_quest_2514"
msgstr "Report to Alvmund the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2515"
msgstr ""
"With the latest goblin attacks onto our town, we have been forced to hasten "
"some of our construction projects. Two of these projects are the repair and "
"restoration of our towns walls, and the construction of guard towers along "
"our trade routes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Alvmund the Blacksmith has been tasked with both of these projects. I want "
"you to report to him, and assist him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2516"
msgstr ""
"Hastily reconstructed after a volcanic eruption some years back, the "
"northeastern part of Valfather's Edge's walls are in dire need of repair and "
"restoration. This work is planned for the near future, but first we need to "
"make sure that we have all the raw materials that we need, such as blocks of "
"stone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Agnor the Merchant, or from any other general "
"store.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to succeed every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2517"
msgstr ""
"It has been decided to build a series of guard towers along the trade "
"routes. For this program to proceed smoothly, we need to make sure that we "
"have all the raw materials that we need for the construction of the guard "
"towers, including large quantities of timber. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire wood, you must cut down trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If "
"you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Agnor the Merchant."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_2518"
msgstr ""
"Alvmund the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Hrafnid the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2519"
msgstr ""
"I have just been informed from our master builders, that both the projects "
"are ahead of schedule. This is most encouraging news. The restoration of our "
"towns walls is almost complete, and we seem to have also collected enough "
"building materials to begin the construction of the guard towers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Hrafnid the Councillor and inform him "
"that both the walls and the guard towers will be completed on time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2520"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hrafnid the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2521"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports that the goblin hordes have begun "
"increasing their numbers. This can only mean that goblins are in the process "
"of organizing their army, and preparing for an all out attack onto our town."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The council has decided that it is now that we must launch our counter "
"attack against the greenskins, and disrupt any plans they have of organizing "
"a large army. The time has come to launch a swift and deadly attack against "
"the greenskin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
" #PlayerName#, I ask of you to help us once more. I want you to kill at "
"least seven goblin in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2522"
msgstr ""
"Hrafnid the Councillor has asked you to report to Yngfell the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2523"
msgstr ""
"Reports have just arrived from our scouts, indicating that our counter "
"attack against the goblin  hordes seems to have weaken their numbers "
"considerably. Still, the goblins are many, and it won't be long before more "
"greenskins start pouring out of their filthy holes, to join what is left of "
"their pathetic army. We will need the strength of our spellcasters if we are "
"to defeat the greenskins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Yngfell the Arcanist is doing his part to help us defeat the goblin hordes. "
"At the moment Yngfell is gathering up specific ingredients, materials or "
"regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of spellcasting. "
"Without these ingredients, it will be impossible for our spellcasters to "
"support us in our battle against the goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Yngfell the Arcanist, and help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2524"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Yngfell the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2525"
msgstr ""
"The mandrake you had collected earlier is already being put to good use, to "
"help our warriors fight off the goblin hordes. I need you to collect another "
"ingredient also used in the art of spellcasting,  and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Agnor the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2526"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Yngfell the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2527"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, and that is "
"resin. Resin can be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you "
"have located a tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the "
"process of extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such "
"a tool, you may buy one from Agnor the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2528"
msgstr ""
"Yngfell the Arcanist has asked you to deliver his letter to Hrafnid the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2529"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , the spellcasters of Valfather's Edge will soon be ready to do "
"battle against the goblin hordes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter to Hrafnid the Councillor, and inform him "
"that Valfather's Edge can rely on its spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2530"
msgstr ""
"Taelis the Councillor has asked you to report to Nirgan the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2531"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the Elders have come to the "
"conclusion that Onghral and the surrounding lands need to be better defended."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"They have decided to expand and improve the walls around our city, but also "
"build a series of guard towers along the road which connects our town to the "
"alfar capital of Shoal\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elders have assigned Nirgan the Blacksmith in charge of both of these "
"tasks. I want you to report to Nirgan the Blacksmith, and assist in the "
"improvement Onghral's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2532"
msgstr ""
"Nirgan the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Taelis the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2533"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Taelis the Councillor and inform him "
"that both the walls and the guard towers will be completed on time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2534"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taelis the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2535"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that the goblins are preparing to "
"launch an attack onto Onghral very soon. The notion that the dimwitted "
"goblins of even considering to putting together an army and attacking us is "
"at the very least insulting. Nevertheless, the Elders have decided that we "
"must attack immediately, and stop the momentum of the goblin horde. An end "
"must be put to this nonsense.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, now is the time to show us what you are truly made of. You "
"will deliver a swift and deadly message to the goblins. Go now, and kill at "
"least seven goblins in less than an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2536"
msgstr "Taelis the Councillor has asked you to report to Kalshar the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2537"
msgstr ""
"Reports have just arrived from our scouts, indicating that our counterattack "
"against the goblin  hordes seems to have weaken the their numbers "
"considerably. Still, the goblins are many, and it won't be long before more "
"greenskins start pouring out of their filthy holes, to join what is left of "
"their pathetic army. We will need the strength of our spellcasters if we are "
"to defeat the greenskins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kalshar the Arcanist is doing his part to help wipe out the goblin hordes. "
"At the moment Kalshar is gathering up specific ingredients, materials or "
"regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of spellcasting. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Kalshar the Arcanist, and help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2538"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kalshar the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2539"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are in need of sulfur. Sulfur is also "
"another ingredient used in the art of spellcasting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Arinthu the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2540"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Kalshar the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2541"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Arinthu the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin"

msgid "start_text_quest_2542"
msgstr ""
"Kalshar the Arcanist has asked you to deliver his letter to Taelis the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2543"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , I want you to deliver this letter I have written to Taelis "
"the Councillor, to inform him that our spellcasters will soon be ready to "
"eliminate the pathetic goblins once an for all."

msgid "start_text_quest_2544"
msgstr ""
"Report to Mardahan the Blacksmith to see how you may help with the building "
"of the guard towers and guard houses along the trade routes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2545"
msgstr ""
"As a result of the increased monster presence in this region, we plan to "
"build a number of guard towers and guard houses along the roads leading to "
"Shoal and other nearby communities.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Mardahan the Blacksmith is coordinating the construction of both towers and "
"houses along the trade routes. I want you to go and report to Mardahan the "
"Blacksmith, and assist him as he sees fit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2546"
msgstr ""
"Mardahan the Blacksmith has asked you to inform Nirgash the Councillor that "
"the construction of the guard towers will begin very soon."

msgid "start_text_quest_2547"
msgstr ""
"We have now collected enough raw materials to start the construction of the "
"guard towers and guard houses along our trade routes. The filthy greenskins "
"will be in for a big surprise once our first guard towers along the trade "
"routes are up and functional. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to report to Nirgash the Councillor, and deliver to "
"him the message, that the construction of the new defenses along the trade "
"routes will begin very soon."

msgid "start_text_quest_2548"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2549"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports that the goblins have increased their "
"attacks along our trade routes. This is unacceptable. The moment has come "
"where we shall drive the goblins back into the holes where they came from. "
"There is no time to waste. We attack now. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to kill at least seven goblin in less that an hour. "
"The quicker, the better."

msgid "start_text_quest_2550"
msgstr "Nirgash the Councillor has asked you report to Ilrak the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2551"
msgstr ""
"We have received word from the capital Shoal, that a massive military "
"campaign against the Mirdain of Mirendil is being planned. Deep Yishku has "
"also been asked to partake in this campaign. While most of the militia "
"forces are ready, the campaign will not begin until all the forces of Nagast "
"have reported ready for battle. This also includes the support of our "
"spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is always wise to go into battle with magical support, however strong our "
"armies may be. And we know that the Mirdain, always use magic in their "
"battles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Ilrak the Arcanist is in charge of organizing and preparing our spellcaster "
"for battle. I want you to report to Ilrak, and assist him with his task."

msgid "start_text_quest_2552"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ilrak the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2553"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are running low on sulfur, another "
"ingredient that is used when casting spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the bolder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Kaelit the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Five units of sulfur will do for now."

msgid "start_text_quest_2554"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Ilrak the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2555"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Kaelit the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2556"
msgstr ""
"Ilrak the Arcanist has asked you to deliver his letter to Nirgash the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2557"
msgstr ""
"The spellcasters of Deep Yishku, are ready to report for duty. "
"#PlayerName# , I want you to deliver this letter I have written to Nirgash "
"the Councillor, to inform him that Shoal can rely on our spells to support "
"the military campaign against the Mirdain."

msgid "start_text_quest_2558"
msgstr ""
"Irshanta the Councillor has asked you to report to Neissur the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2559"
msgstr ""
"Neissur the Blacksmith has been complaining about the amount of work he has "
"at the moment. He has put in a request, for an extra pair of hands to assist "
"him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Neissur the Blacksmith, and see how you may be of "
"help to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2560"
msgstr ""
"Irshanta the Councillor has requested to speak with you. Report to her as "
"soon as possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_2561"
msgstr ""
"A message has arrived saying that Irshanta the Councillor wishes to speak "
"with you. I suggest you go report to Irshanta the Councillor. Do not keep "
"her waiting."

msgid "start_text_quest_2562"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Irshanta the Councillor. Kill seven goblins "
"in less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2563"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that bands of greenskins have begun "
"attacking caravans along our trade routes. The idea that these pathetic "
"lifeforms could have the audacity to attack our caravans, is totally absurd. "
"Even so, we cannot afford to waste time with these dimwitted goblins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These goblins must be immediately taught a lesson, before I lose my "
"patience. I want you to attack these pathetic goblin bandits, and kill at "
"least seven of them in less than an hour. Do not waste time. Go!"

msgid "start_text_quest_2564"
msgstr "Irshanta the Councillor has asked you report to Thielit the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2565"
msgstr ""
"A letter has arrived from the authorities in the capital Shoal, that a "
"military campaign against the Mirdain of Mirendil is being planned. Akathos "
"is to partake in this campaign, with a group of spellcasters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Thielit the Arcanis is in charge of organizing and preparing our spellcaster "
"for battle. I want you to report to Thielit, and assist her with the "
"preparations."

msgid "start_text_quest_2566"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thielit the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2567"
msgstr ""
"I need you to collect another ingredient that is also used in the art of "
"spellcasting, and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Talduk the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2568"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Thielit the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2569"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Talduk the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2570"
msgstr ""
"Thielit the Arcanist has asked you to deliver her letter to Irshanta the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2571"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , I want you to deliver this letter I have written to Irshanta "
"the Councillor, to inform her that Shoal can rely on our spellcasters to "
"support the military campaign against the Mirdain."

msgid "start_text_quest_2572"
msgstr "Report to Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2573"
msgstr ""
"The latest goblin infestation in the area has made it quite obvious that "
"Silverspear needs to improve its defenses.  Although the goblin do not pose "
"a major threat to our town, rather more a nuisance, an attack from a much "
"stronger and organized enemy could prove to be disastrous for Silverspear. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elders of Silverspear have decided that it is time to improve the walls "
"that protect our town, but also to begin the construction of a series of "
"guard towers along the road which connects Silverspear to the mahirim "
"capital of {$j12}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith is in charge of both of these projects. Report to Sa-"
"Imdor, and assist Silverspear in improving its defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2574"
msgstr ""
"Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Ialynna the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2575"
msgstr ""
"We are progressing well on both of the construction projects the elders have "
"asked for. The wall improvements will be completed very soon, and we have "
"also collected enough material to begin the construction of the guard "
"towers. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Ialynna the Councillor, and inform "
"her that both the walls and the guard towers will be completed on time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2576"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialynna the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2577"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports, that there is an increase in the number "
"of goblin war bands approaching Silverspear. As laughable as it may sound, "
"it seems that the goblins are in the process of organizing an army, and "
"preparing for an all out attack onto our town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The elders has decided that we must attack the greenskins now, and stop any "
"plans they have of organizing a large army. We cannot afford to have a "
"goblin army anywhere near Silverspear.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, it is time to deliver a swift and deadly message to the "
"goblins. I want you to kill at least seven goblin in less that an hour. Go "
"now, do not waste time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2578"
msgstr ""
"Ialynna the Councillor has asked you to report to Murion-tai the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2579"
msgstr ""
"The reports that have just arrived from our scouts, indicate that our swift "
"and coordinated attack against the goblin hordes seems to have weaken the "
"their numbers considerably. Still, the goblins are many, and it won't be "
"long before more greenskins start pouring out of their filthy holes, to join "
"what is left of their pathetic army. We will need the strength of our "
"spellcasters if we are to defeat the greenskins, once and for all.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Murion-tai the Arcanist is doing her part to help us defeat the goblin "
"hordes. At the moment Murion-tai is gathering up specific ingredients, "
"materials or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of "
"spellcasting. Without these ingredients, it will be impossible for our "
"spellcasters to help us in our defeat the goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Murion-tai the Arcanist, and help her collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2580"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Murion-tai the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2581"
msgstr ""
"I need you to collect another ingredient that is also used in the art of "
"spellcasting, and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Isabel the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2582"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Murion-tai the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2583"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Omarandyr the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2584"
msgstr ""
"Murion-tai the Arcanist has asked you to deliver her letter to Ialynna the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2585"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#  , we have collected enough magical ingredients, and very soon "
"our spellcasters will be ready to battle the pathetic greenskins. It has "
"been a while since we've had such a good opportunity, to exercise our "
"spellcasting abilities. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter to Ialynna the Councillor, and inform her "
"that our spellcasters will soon be ready to deliver the final blow against "
"the goblin hordes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2586"
msgstr ""
"Arkelia the Councillor has asked you to report to Molangar the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2587"
msgstr ""
"Molangar the Blacksmith has put in a request, for an extra pair of hands to "
"assist him. I want you to report to Molangar, and help out with the large "
"amount of work load he has at the moment."

msgid "start_text_quest_2588"
msgstr ""
"Arkelia the Councillor has requested to speak with you. Report to her as "
"soon as possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_2589"
msgstr ""
"I have just been informed that Arkelia the Councillor wishes to speak with "
"you. You have done quite enough here, and I will not need your assistance "
"any more. Go now, and report to Arkelia the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2590"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arkelia the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2591"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that goblin bands have heightened "
"their attacks against our caravans along our trade routes. Trade is a vital "
"part of Leenglow's everyday life, and allowing these pathetic goblins "
"bandits to disrupt the transport of goods to and from Leenglow, is not an "
"option. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Leenglow council has asked that we deal with the goblins immediately. I "
"want you to deliver a deadly message to the greenskin bandits. Kill at least "
"seven of these goblins thieves within the next hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2592"
msgstr "Arkelia the Councillor has asked you report to  Amauron the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2593"
msgstr ""
"A report has arrived from Amauron our local Arcanist, that our spellcasters "
"are running low on magic ingredients. Without these ingredients, it will be "
"impossible for our spellcasters to support us in our battle against the "
"goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Amauron the Arcanist and help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2594"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amauron the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2595"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are in need of sulfur. Sulfur is also "
"another ingredient used in the art of spellcasting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Levasta-ine the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2596"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Amauron the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2597"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Levasta-ine the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2598"
msgstr ""
"Amauron the Arcanist has asked you to deliver his letter to Arkelia the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2599"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#  , our spellcasters will soon be ready to do battle against the "
"goblin hordes, or any other enemy that would be stupid enough to threaten "
"our town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter to Arkelia the Councillor, and inform him "
"that Leenglow can rely on its spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2600"
msgstr ""
"Andor-kai the Councillor has asked you to report to Felalon the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_2601"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the elders of Hunter's Moon have "
"decided that a series of guard towers and guard houses need to be built, to "
"better protect our hunting grounds. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Felalon the Blacksmith has been put is in charge of both of these projects. "
"I want you to report to him, and assist him with his work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2602"
msgstr ""
"Felalon the Blacksmith has asked you to report  Andor-Kai the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2603"
msgstr ""
"We have collected enough raw materials to start the construction of the both "
"the guard towers and guard houses. Soon, our hunting grounds will be well "
"protected, and no goblin hordes or other annoying pests will be aimlessly "
"roaming our grounds, stripping it of its vegetation or displacing the herds "
"of prey animals that inhabited the plains.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Andor-Kai the Councillor, and inform "
"her that the construction of both the guard towers and houses will soon "
"begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2604"
msgstr ""
"Andor-Kai the Councillor has asked you to kill seven goblin in less that an "
"hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2605"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports that the goblin hordes have increased "
"their presence within our hunting grounds. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The moment has come where we shall drive the goblins out of our lands, and "
"back into the mountains where they came from. We cannot afford to delay this "
"issue anymore, while the goblin hordes destroy our lands. The council has "
"demanded that we must rid ourselves of these annoying pests immediately. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I ask of you to help us once more. Kill at least seven goblins "
"in less than an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2606"
msgstr "Andor-Kai the Councillor has asked you report to Celene the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2607"
msgstr ""
"The reports that have just arrived from our scouts, indicate that our swift "
"and coordinated attack against the goblin hordes seems to have weaken the "
"their numbers considerably within our hunting grounds. Still, the goblins "
"are many, and it won't be long before more greenskins start pouring out of "
"their filthy holes, and go back to destroying our lands and our way of life. "
"We will need the strength of our spellcasters if we are to defeat the "
"greenskins once and for all.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Celene the Arcanist is doing her part to in this battle against the goblin "
"hordes. At the moment Celene is gathering up specific ingredients, materials "
"or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of "
"spellcasting. Without these ingredients, it will be impossible for our "
"spellcasters to help us in our eradicate the goblin pests."

msgid "start_text_quest_2608"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Celene the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2609"
msgstr ""
"I need you to collect another ingredient that is also used in the art of "
"spellcasting, and that is Sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Agrina the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2610"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Celene the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2611"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Agrina the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2612"
msgstr ""
"Celene the Arcanist has asked you to deliver her letter to Andor-Kai the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2613"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , we have collected enough magical ingredients, and very soon "
"our spellcasters will be ready to battle the pathetic greenskins. It has "
"been a while since we've had such a good opportunity to exercise our "
"spellcasting abilities. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter to Andor-Kai the Councillor, and inform "
"her that our spellcasters will soon be ready to deliver the final blow "
"against the goblin hordes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2614"
msgstr ""
"Report to Ciredan the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"Leafhelm's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2615"
msgstr ""
"As a result of the increased monster presence in this region, the Elflords "
"of Leafhelm have decided to improve our towns defenses. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Ciredan the Blacksmith has already begun working on several defensive "
"projects the Elflords have asked for. I want you to report to Ciredan the "
"Blacksmith and see how you might assist him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2616"
msgstr ""
"Ciredan the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Silawen the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2617"
msgstr ""
"Work on both of the defensive projects the elflords have requested, is "
"progressing well. The wall improvements will be completed very soon, and we "
"have also collected enough material to begin the construction of the guard "
"towers. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Silawen the Councillor, and inform "
"her that both the walls and the guard towers will be completed on time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2618"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Kill seven goblins in "
"less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2619"
msgstr ""
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that goblin bands have begun attacking "
"caravans along our trade routes. Trade is a vital part of Leafhelm's "
"everyday life, and allowing these filthy goblins bandits to disrupt the "
"transport of goods to and from Leafhelm, is not an option. The elflords of "
"Leafhelm have asked that we deal with the goblins immediately. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I would ask that you help Leafhelm once more. You can help "
"Leafhelm by killing seven goblins in less that an hour. We cannot delay."

msgid "start_text_quest_2620"
msgstr "Silawen the Councillor has asked you to report to Eredil the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2621"
msgstr ""
"A report has arrived from Eredil our local Arcanist, that our spellcasters "
"are running low on magic ingredients. Without these ingredients, it will be "
"impossible for our spellcasters to support us in our battle against the "
"goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Eredil the Arcanist and help him collect the "
"ingredients our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2622"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredil the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2623"
msgstr ""
"Since you were able to collect the mandrake I had asked for, I will ask you "
"to collect another ingredient also used in the art of spellcasting. Our "
"spellcasters are in need of sulfur.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Merthir the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2624"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Eredil the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2625"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Merthir the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2626"
msgstr ""
"Eredil the Arcanist has asked you deliver a letter to Silawen the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2627"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , our spellcasters will soon be ready to do battle against the "
"goblin hordes, or any other enemy that would be foolish enough to threaten "
"our town. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter to Silawen the Councillor, and inform her "
"that Leafhelm can rely on its spellcasters for support and protection."

msgid "start_text_quest_2628"
msgstr ""
"Report to Dinuil the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"King's Holdfast's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2629"
msgstr ""
"The latest goblin infestation in the surrounding lands, has made it quite "
"obvious that King's Holdfast needs to improve its defenses. Although the "
"goblins do not pose a major threat to our town, rather more a nuisance, an "
"attack from a much stronger and organized enemy could prove to be disastrous."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Dinuil the Blacksmith has already begun working on several defensive "
"projects the council has requested.  I want you to report to Dinuil and see "
"how you might assist him."

msgid "start_text_quest_2630"
msgstr ""
"Dinuil the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Elvallie the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2631"
msgstr ""
"Work on both of the defensive projects the council has asked for is "
"progressing well. The wall improvements will be completed very soon, and we "
"have also collected enough material to begin the construction of the guard "
"towers. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to report to Elvallie the Councillor, and inform "
"her that both the walls and the guard towers will be completed on time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2632"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the Councillor. Kill seven goblins "
"in less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2633"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have return with reports, that there is an increase in the number "
"of goblin war bands approaching King's Holdfast. As absurd as it may sound, "
"it seems that the goblins are in the process of organizing an army, and "
"preparing for an all out attack onto our town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The council has decided that we must attack the greenskins now, and stop any "
"plans they have of organizing a large army. We cannot allow a goblin army to "
"assemble anywhere near King's Holdfast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, we attack now. You can help us by killing at least seven "
"goblins in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2634"
msgstr ""
"Elvallie the Councillor has asked you to report to Aergeir the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2635"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have reported that the latest attacks against the goblin hordes "
"seem to have weaken the their numbers considerably. Still, the goblins are "
"many, and it won't be long before more greenskins start pouring out of their "
"filthy holes, to join what is left of their pathetic army. We will need the "
"strength of our spellcasters if we are to defeat the greenskins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Aergeir the Arcanist has asked for help, with preparing and organizing our "
"spellcasters. I would ask of you to report to Aergeir, and assist him with "
"his work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2636"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aergeir the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2637"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are in need of sulfur. Sulfur is also "
"another ingredient used in the art of spellcasting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Tarhal the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2638"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Aergeir the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2639"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Tarhal the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2640"
msgstr ""
"Aergeir the Arcanist has asked you deliver a letter to Elvallie the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2641"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , you have been of great help to us. Our spellcasters are ready "
"to battle the goblin hordes and drive them out of our lands for once and for "
"all.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to deliver this letter I have written to Elvallie the Councillor, "
"to inform her that King's Holdfast can rely on its spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2642"
msgstr ""
"Report to Tiyawen the Blacksmith to see how you may help with improving "
"Beladin's Rest's defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_2643"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, it has been decided that "
"Beladin's Rest needs to strengthen its defenses. A number of guard towers "
"and guard houses are planned to be built, to better protect our town and the "
"surrounding lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Tiyawen the Blacksmith is in charge of improving our town's defenses. I want "
"you to report to Tiyawen, and see if you may assist him in his work."

msgid "start_text_quest_2644"
msgstr ""
"Tiyawen the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Lysandir the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2645"
msgstr ""
"We have collected enough raw materials to start the construction of the both "
"the guard towers and guard houses. Soon, Beladin's Rest and its surrounds "
"lands will be well protected, and no goblin hordes or other unwanted "
"monsters will pose a threat to our beautiful lake district in the future.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# , I want you to report to Lysandir the Councillor, and inform "
"him that the construction of both the guard towers and houses will soon "
"begin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2646"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lysandir the Councillor. Kill seven goblins "
"in less that an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2647"
msgstr ""
"The goblin hordes continue to pour out of their tunnels, as if there is no "
"ending to their numbers. Many brave souls are now out there fighting the "
"greenskin tide. We need to move quickly, and kill as many goblins as we can. "
"Now is the time for us to attack, and drive these vermin back into their "
"filthy holes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to help Beladin's Rest one more time? We can "
"definitely use your help again. You may assist us by killing seven goblins "
"in less that an hour."

msgid "start_text_quest_2648"
msgstr ""
"Lysandir the Councillor has asked you to report to Gelwain the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2649"
msgstr ""
"Until now, the people of Beladin's Rest have been relying on the town's "
"defenses and heroes like yourself to repel off the goblin hordes. But these "
"are not the only means we have to protect ourselves from the unwanted "
"monsters. Magic, in the right hands can be a powerful weapon, and can "
"definitely be of help in defeating the goblin hordes at the moment.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gelwain our local Arcanist, is doing his part to help Beladin's Rest defeat "
"the goblin hordes. Right now Gelwain is gathering specific ingredients, "
"materials or regents if you wish to call them, that are used in the art of "
"spellcasting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Report to Gelwain the Arcanist, to see how you may help him collect the "
"ingredients, our spellcasters need."

msgid "start_text_quest_2650"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gelwain the Arcanist. Gather five units of "
"sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2651"
msgstr ""
"Our spellcasters have reported that we are running low on sulfur, another "
"ingredient that is used when casting spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sulfur can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Once you have determined "
"that the boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may begin extracting sulfur "
"using a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from "
"Miradan the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you might get your hands on sulfur, is to hunt down one of those "
"goblin shamans. It is known that goblin shamans, being the spellcasters they "
"are, sometimes carry sulfur with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of sulfur."

msgid "start_text_quest_2652"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of resin for Gelwain the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_2653"
msgstr ""
"There is another spellcasting regent we are running low on, resin. Resin can "
"be acquired from a tree, preferably a large tree. Once you have located a "
"tree that is suitable for harvesting, you may then begin the process of "
"extracting resin using a wood axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you "
"may buy one from Miradan the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Another way you can acquire resin, is to chase down and slay one of those "
"annoying goblin shamans. Being the spellcasters they are, they sometimes do "
"carry resin with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is up to you to choose, how you will gather the five units of resin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2654"
msgstr ""
"Gelwain the Arcanist has asked you deliver a letter to Lysandir the "
"Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2655"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# , I thank you for all you have done here. Our spellcasters are "
"ready to aid our town any way possible. I want you to deliver this letter to "
"Lysandir the Councillor, to inform him that Beladin's Rest can rely on its "
"spellcasters for support."

msgid "start_text_quest_2658"
msgstr "Maria Hawksgate has tasked you with killing three matayin raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_2659"
msgstr ""
"The Eanna river runs through the heart of Mercia, providing a vital link "
"between the capital of Sanguine and the inland farming communities which "
"sustain it. Lately, however, river barges on the Eanna have suffered a "
"number of attacks by a race of riverine predators known as matayin. As a "
"result, the flow of agricultural produce into Sanguine has nearly dried out, "
"and we are faced with the threat of starvation if the situation isn't dealt "
"with quickly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have determined that the matayin tribe inhabit the very spring from which "
"the Eanna flows, which is a subterranean lake in the region of Eastern "
"Brockmore. I want you to go there and deal with the monsters who are "
"threatening the survival of the Mercian capital. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill three Matayin."

msgid "start_text_quest_2660"
msgstr ""
"The Lainstone Goblin Hunt. You must kill at least ten goblins in less than "
"an hour. The more goblins you kill, the higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2661"
msgstr ""
"The goblins are starting to become a nuisance here in Lainstone, and are "
"seriously disrupting our trade routes and communities. Therefor we have "
"issued a goblin hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten goblins within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But, there is more to the Lainstone Goblin Hunt. Any kills beyond "
"the ten goblins within the hour, will also result in a higher reward. The "
"more dead goblins, the better I say!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"goblins within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2662"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to take part in Cranwyn Bay's Lizard Hunt. Kill as many "
"lizardmen as you can in less that an hour. The more you kill, the higher the "
"reward. Ten lizardmen at least are required to complete the Cranwyn Bay "
"Lizard Hunt.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2663"
msgstr ""
"The lizardmen that have moved into Cranwyn Bay, are becoming too dangerous "
"for the local communities. Therefor we have issued a lizard hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten lizardmen within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But, there is more to the Cranwyn Bay's Lizard Hunt. Any kills "
"beyond the ten lizardmen within the hour, will also result in a higher "
"reward.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"lizardmen within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2664"
msgstr ""
"The Hildershall Spider Hunt. You must kill at least ten spiders in less than "
"an hour. The more spiders you kill, the higher the reward.\r\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2665"
msgstr ""
"The spiders here in Hildershall, are becoming too many and too dangerous for "
"the local communities. Therefor we have issued a spider hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten spiders within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But, there is more to Hildershall's Spider Hunt. Any spiders "
"killed beyond the ten spiders required for the hunt, will also result in a "
"higher reward. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"spiders within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2666"
msgstr ""
"The Copperdale Giant Skeleton Hunt. You must kill at least ten giant "
"skeletons in less than an hour. The more giant skeletons you kill, the "
"higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2667"
msgstr ""
"The Giant Skeletons that are roaming the lands to the north of here, are "
"seriously becoming a threat to the local communities. Therefor we have "
"issued a Giant Skeleton hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten Giant Skeletons within an hour will be "
"well rewarded. But, that's not all. Any Giant Skeletons killed beyond the "
"ten required for the hunt, will also result in a higher reward.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"Giant Skeletons within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2668"
msgstr "You have agreed to bring four Horns to Oona Fern in {$v18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_2669"
msgstr ""
"Here in {$v18}, we craft many of the magical weapons wielded by the Mercian "
"army, and we therefore need a constant supply of  ingredients, that are use "
"in the art of enchanting.  As you may know, certain monster parts have "
"properties that render them  useful for making magical items. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the north east of here, among the swampy waters and the ruins of a long "
"forgotten race, many monsters have found refuge. Among these, it seems the "
"lowly and despicable kobolds has adapted quiet well, and even established a "
"few camps.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Fortunately, kobolds contain parts which may be turned into magical "
"enchantments by skilled magesmiths. I want you to harvest four kobold bones "
"for use in our arcane forges."

msgid "start_text_quest_2670"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Oona Fern's challenge. Kill four trolls to claim your "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2671"
msgstr ""
"The local kobolds are the vassals of a clan of trolls who live on three "
"mesas that rise in the center of the swamp. Quite probably, the trolls "
"instigated the recent kobold raids, sending their thralls out to raid and "
"plunder on their behalf. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Trolls may be a primitive species, but they are fierce fighters who possess "
"a certain malevolent cunning. Unlike the bottom-feeding kobolds, trolls "
"should be taken somewhat seriously as opponents. Make your way onto the "
"swamp-mesas they inhabit and kill four trolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2672"
msgstr ""
"The Silverley Troll Hunt. You must kill at least ten trolls in less than an "
"hour. The more trolls you kill, the higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2673"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# . The trolls are starting to become a nuisance here in "
"Silverley, and are seriously disrupting our work. Therefor we have issued a "
"troll hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten trolls within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But, that's not all. Any kills beyond the ten, within the hour, "
"will also result in a higher reward.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"trolls within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2674"
msgstr ""
"The Grayvale Hivekin Hunt. You must kill at least ten hivekins in less than "
"an hour. The more hivekins you kill, the higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2675"
msgstr ""
"The region of Grayvale to the northeast of here is being overrun by "
"numberless horde of hivekin who are busy disrupting our trade routes to and "
"from the capital Sanguine, while stripping the land of its vegetation. "
"Therefor we have issued a hivekin hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten hivekins within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But that is not all. For every hivekin killed beyond the ten "
"required for the hunt, a little more will be added to the reward .\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"hivekins within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2676"
msgstr ""
"The Zirdnal Manscorpion Hunt. You must kill at least ten manscorpions in "
"less than an hour. The more manscorpions you kill, the higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2677"
msgstr ""
"The manscorpions that have moved into this region, have seriously starting "
"disrupting the work of the Radiant Circle. Therefor we have issued a "
"manscorpion hunt, to clear the lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten manscorpions within an hour will be well "
"rewarded. But, there is more. For every manscorpion killed beyond the ten "
"required for the hunt, a little more will be added to the reward .\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, what do you think? Do you have what I takes to kill more than ten "
"manscorpions within an hour? And how many can you kill? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The duration of the hunt is one hour. No participants will be able to "
"collect their reward before the end of the time limit."

msgid "start_text_quest_2678"
msgstr ""
"The Lake Ishtra Severii Hunt. You must kill at least ten severii in less "
"than an hour. The more severii you kill, the higher the reward.\n"
"(Warning: Rewards are given at the end of the time limit. Countdown "
"continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_2679"
msgstr ""
"The undead minions of the skeleton dragon god Cyriacus, the severii, are "
"among our most hated enemies. Therefor we have issued a severii hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody who can kill at least ten severii within an hour will be well "
