msgid "start_text_quest_2908"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ensharra the Councillor. Kill two Mahirim "
"player characters, two Dwarf player characters and two Ork player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2909"
msgstr ""
"Now that you have confronted both of our pathetic neighbors, its time for "
"you to venture out to the far north. To the north, you will find our other "
"three remaining enemies. The mahirim of the Tribelands far to the northwest, "
"the dwarves of Dvergheim to the far north, and the orks of Morak to the far "
"northeast. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you previously disposed of our pathetic neighbors, it is also the will of "
"Melek to exterminate these races of the north. Nothing will stand in the way "
"of Melek and the superior alfar!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Just to inform you, the mahirim are a race of wolf-like predators, that have "
"only recently earned the right to call themselves a civilized race, if one "
"can call these two-legged beasts anything but civilized. The mahirim are a "
"wild and primitive race, so be well prepared to do some serious battle. Then "
"we have the dwarves, a short-statured race, that make up for what they lack "
"in height with raw strength and endurance. But be careful. The dwarves area "
"a stubborn and proud race, always ready for battle. And last but not least "
"the orks, a battle hungry race, convinced that through pure brute strength "
"they will eventually concur all of Agon, while enslaving all the other "
"races. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"All three of them, weak and pathetic! All three of them doomed to die!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to seek out and kill two Mahirim, two Dwarves and "
"two Orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2910"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sylanae the Councillor. Report to Ordgrim the "
"Councillor in Ymir's Tear."

msgid "start_text_quest_2911"
msgstr ""
"I have received word from Ymir's Tear, that Ordgrim the Councillor is "
"requesting help from all allies to assist the dwarves in their battle "
"against the orks of Morak.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have the dwarves of Dvergheim answered our call for "
"help, and now the time has come for us to assist them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go the Ymir's Tear and report to Ordgrim the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2912"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ordgrim the Councillor. Kill four Ork player "
"characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2913"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. You have reached Ymir's Tear, the dwarven capital city located in "
"the heart of Dvergheim. It is here within the borders of Dvergheim that we "
"dwarves under the guidence of Ymir, have lived for thousands of years, and "
"intent to live here for thousands more to come.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the help of our lawful allies, the mirdain of Mirendil and the "
"humans of Mercia, we intend to strengthen this alliance, so all three races "
"may continue to live in peace.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you have been sent here to assist us deal with the orks of "
"Morak.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The orks, a race that live for the thrill of battle, are convinced that "
"through pure brute strength, will eventually concur all of Agon while "
"enslaving all the other races, including your race the mirdain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The orks of Morak have managed to forge an alliance with our common "
"neighbor, the mahirim of the Tribelands. This has boosted their confidence, "
"and from the reports I have received, it seems the  orks have increased "
"their raids within our borders the last few weeks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, having two of the most battle hungry races of Agon from an alliance, "
"does not leave us, the mirdain or the humans with many options. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the orks of Morak to the "
"southeast of Dvergheim, and kill at least four of them. If all dwarf, "
"mirdain and human do our part, we will surely stop the growing ork hordes of "
"Morak.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay four orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2914"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Allan the Councillor. Report to Sylanae the "
"Councillor in Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_2915"
msgstr ""
"I have received word from Charybdis, that Sylanae the Councillor is "
"requesting help from all allies to assist the mirdain in their battle "
"against the mahirim of the Tribelands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have the mirdain answered our call for help, and now "
"the time has come for us to assist them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go the Charybdis and report to Sylanae the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2916"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sylanae the Councillor. Kill four Mahirim "
"player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2917"
msgstr ""
"I welcome you to Charybdis, the mirdain capital city here in the heart of "
"Mirendil. It is here within the vast Miredil forest of southwest Agon, that "
"we mirdain have lived for thousands of years our peaceful lives. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the help of our good allies, such as the humans of Mercia and "
"the dwarves of Dvergheim, we intend for all three races to continue to live "
"in peace, while battling all those that wish to threaten our alliance and "
"our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you have been sent here to assist us deal with the growing "
"threat of the Tribelands called the mahirim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mahirim, a race of wolf-like predators, have only recently earned the "
"right to call themselves a civilized race. The problem is that their actions "
"are anything but civilized. The mahirim, the wild race the are, have chosen "
"to ally themselves with the battle hungry orks of Morak. I am afraid that "
"the path the mahirim have chosen, leave us and the alliance with very little "
"options, one of them not being peace.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mahirim are growing bolder day by day, and our scouts have reported that "
"the mahirim have increased their raids within our borders the last few weeks."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the mahirim of the "
"Tribelands to the north of Mirendil, and kill at least four of them. If all "
"mirdain, human and dwarf do our part, we will surely quell the growing "
"threat of the Tribelands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay four of these mahirim beasts!"

msgid "start_text_quest_2918"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ordgrim the Councillor. Report to Allan the "
"Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2919"
msgstr ""
"I have received word from Sanguine, that Allan the Councillor is requesting "
"help from all allies to assist the humans in their battle against the alfar "
"of Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have the humans answered our call for help, and now "
"the time has come for us to assist them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go the Sanguine and report to Allan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2920"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Allan the Councillor. Kill four Alfar player "
"characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2921"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. You have reached Sanguine, the human capital city located in the "
"heart of Mercia. It is here within the borders of Mercia, that we humans "
"live our everyday lives, under the guiding light of Auros.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the help of our good allies, such as the dwarves of Dvergheim "
"and the mirdain of Mirendil, we will work hard for all three races to "
"continue to live in peace, while battling all those that wish to threaten "
"our alliance and our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you have been sent here to assist us deal with the alfar of "
"Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to all that we have learned from our allies the mirdain, the alfar "
"under the guidance of their twisted god Melek, have been molded into a dark "
"and hateful race, that only seek to destroy all life upon Agon. Their goal, "
"and that of course of their god Melek, is total domination of Agon. For "
"them, there is no room for any other race. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Reports have arrived from our scouts, that the alfar have increased their "
"raids within our borders the last few weeks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the alfar of Nagast to the "
"southwest of Mercia, and kill at least four of them. If all human, dwarf and "
"mirdain do our part, we will surely stop the growing threat of the alfar. Do "
"not feel anything for these dark twisted creatures. Remember, they are a "
"race of pure evil.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay four alfar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2922"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Izkruul the Councillor. Report to Tivasta the "
"Councillor in Red Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_2923"
msgstr ""
"I have received word from Red Moon, that Tivasta the Councillor is "
"requesting help from the orks, to assist the mahirim in their battle against "
"the mirdain of Mirendil.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have the mahirim of the Tribelands answered our call "
"for help, and now the time has come for us to honor our alliance and assist "
"them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go the Red Moon and report to Tivasta the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2924"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tivasta the Councillor. Kill four Mirdain "
"player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2925"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. You have reached Red Moon, the mahirim capital city located in the "
"heart of the Tribelands. It is here within the Tribelands that the prophet-"
"warrior Amurran united many of the heartland tribes under his rule, and laid "
"the foundations for today's modern mahirim society. And it is our duty, to "
"continue the work of the prophet-king Amurran, by following his teachings."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the help of our powerful allies the orks of Morak, we will "
"grow stronger as a race, while strengthening the alliance. This alliance "
"between mahirim and ork, is destined to become one of the most powerful "
"alliances ever to exist on Agon, and one surely to be feared by many of the "
"other races.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you have been sent here to assist us deal with the mirdain of "
"Mirendil.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mirdain are a weak and pathetic race, that foolishly continue to live by "
"their ancient ways, blindly refusing to accept the growing power of our "
"race, and that of our alliance. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the humans of Mercia and the Dwarves of Dvergheim, they have "
"formed a pathetic alliance, believing that somehow this alliance will save "
"all three of them. How foolish of them to not be able to see the truth, that "
"they are all weak and doomed to die be our hand!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for them to learn the hard way!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the mirdain of Mirendil to "
"the south of the Tribelands, and kill at least four of them. If all mahirim "
"and ork do our part, we will surely dispose of the pathetic and weak mirdain."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay four of these weak mirdain."

msgid "start_text_quest_2926"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tivasta the Councillor. Report to Izkruul the "
"Councillor in Flaming Skull."

msgid "start_text_quest_2927"
msgstr ""
"I have received word from Flaming Skull, that Izkruul the Councillor is "
"requesting help from the mahirim, to assist the orks in their battle against "
"the humans of Mercia.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many times in the past have the orks of Morak answered our call for help, "
"and now the time has come for us to honor our alliance and assist them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go the Flaming Skull and report to Izkruul the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_2928"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. You have reached FlamingSkull, the ork capital city located in the "
"heart of Morak. It is from here within the borders of Morak, that we orks "
"will begin our march across the whole of Agon, to concur all. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the help of our powerful allies the mahirim of the Tribeland, "
"we will grow stronger as a race, while strengthening the alliance. This "
"alliance between ork and the mahirim, is destined to become one of the most "
"powerful alliances ever to exist on Agon, and one surely to be feared by "
"many of the other races.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you have been sent here to assist us deal with the humans of "
"Mercia.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The humans, the pathetic race they are, continue to not see the growing "
"power of our race. Can they not understand that they are doomed? Is it "
"because of the blinding light of their pathetic sun god? \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with the mirdain of Mirendil and the Dwarves of Dvergheim, they "
"have formed an alliance, believing that somehow this alliance will save all "
"three of them. How foolish of them to not be able to see the truth, they "
"they are all weak and doomed to die be our hand!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Mwahaha! The time has come for them to learn the hard way!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the humans of Mercia to the "
"south of Morak, and kill at least four of them. If all ork and mahirim do "
"our part, we will surely exterminate the pathetic and weak humans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay four of these weak humans."

msgid "start_text_quest_2929"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tivasta the Councillor. Kill five Alfar "
"player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2930"
msgstr ""
"There is one last enemy, one race, that has of lately become a major thorn "
"in the side of the alliance. The dark and sinister alfar of Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to all that we have learned from the mirdain we had captured, the "
"alfar under the guidance of their twisted god Melek, have been molded into a "
"dark and hateful race, that seek to destroy all life upon Agon. Their goal, "
"and that of their god Melek, is total domination of Agon. For them, there is "
"no room for any other race. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"For the mahirim and the ork, two of the most powerful races upon Agon, this "
"is total nonsense. There is no race upon Agon, that is in position to even "
"dream of defeating and dominating our powerful alliance. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Still, disturbing reports have arrived from our scouts, that many alfar war "
"parties have been spotted roaming close to our borders, killing and "
"destroying everything in their path.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task #PlayerName#, will be to strike out at the alfar of Nagast to the "
"far southeast, and kill at least five of them. If all mahirim and ork do our "
"part, we will surely stop the growing threat of the alfar. Do not feel "
"anything for these dark twisted creatures. Remember, they live to only "
"destroy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and slay five alfar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2931"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Izkruul the Councillor. Kill five Alfar "
"player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2932"
msgstr ""
"Recently, the alliance has become aware of a new threat emerging from the "
"far southwest. A race so dark and sinister, that many have come to call them "
"the dark plague. I am referring to the alfar of Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our agents, after interrogating many of the human officers we had captured, "
"have managed to learn quite a bit about the alfar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The alfar, are the ultimate loners. They have no allies, but still manage to "
"survive and grow in power. Under the guidance of their twisted god Melek, "
"they seek to destroy all life upon Agon. Their goal, and that of course of "
"their god Melek, is total domination of Agon. For them, there is no room for "
"any other race. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This of course is total nonsense to us orks, and of course to our allies the "
"mahirim. As two of the most powerful races upon Agon, there is no race or "
"alliance upon Agon, that can defeat us.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Still, disturbing report have arrived from our scouts, that many alfar war "
"parties have been spotted roaming close to our borders, killing and "
"destroying everything in their path. Your task #PlayerName#, will be to "
"strike out at the alfar of Nagast to the far southwest, and kill at least "
"five of them. If all ork and mahirim do our part, we will surely stop the "
"growing threat of the alfar. Do not feel anything for these dark twisted "
"creatures. Remember, they live to only destroy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and kill five alfar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2933"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Izkruul the Councillor. Kill four Human "
"player characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_2934"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Shulazu Nightshade. Report to Arinlit "
"Icethrone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2935"
msgstr ""
"More than three centuries ago, the northwestern regions of Nagast were ruled "
"by a powerful Demon Lord. It was there in the Velmuna region, that Melek "
"sent one of his finest generals to battle the Demon Lord. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Together with her finest warriors, the general fought the Demon Warlord non-"
"stop for five days, in one of the bloodiest battles in Nagast's history. In "
"the end, the general was defeated in battle, but not before managing to "
"sever the demon's left hand. The Demon Warlord badly injured, fled the "
"region never to be seen again. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently, one of our patrols came into possession of a demon hand. The "
"patrol claims that they found the demon hand in the possession of a group of "
"Windlords, while investigating the old abandoned stronghold of Velmuna. "
"Unfortunately, the patrol lost the demon hand, once the Windlords noticed "
"the item missing from their lair. Based on the patrol's report, the demon "
"hand they came across matches that of the ancient descriptions.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Radiant Circle believes, if this is in fact the legendary demon hand, "
"that it can be used to create powerful magical items which will hold within "
"them some of the demon's power. The Radiant Circle wishes to acquire this "
"demon hand, and to study it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to travel north to the Zirdnal region, and report "
"to Arinlit Icethrone. Deliver this letter to Arinlit Icethrone. Arinlit will "
"inform you of what exactly needs to be done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2936"
msgstr ""
"To complete Arinlit Icethrone's quest, you must harvest three Wind "
"Shadowcrests from the Windlords found in Velmuna."

msgid "start_text_quest_2937"
msgstr ""
"So, the Radiant Circle is searching for the legendary Demon Hand. It was one "
"of our patrols that had found a demon hand, who's description matches that "
"of the one in the ancient texts. It was found in the Velmuna region, near "
"the old abandoned stronghold, in the possession of the Windlords. "
"Unfortunately the item was lost, after the patrol lost two of its members "
"when under attack by the Windlords.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I believe it is time for a little revenge. Time to deliver pain to those "
"Windlords. Go to the Velmuna region, and underneath the acid lake you will "
"find the Windlord roaming around the old abandoned stronghold of Velmuna. I "
"want you to harvest three Wind Shadowcrests from the Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_2938"
msgstr ""
"Arinlit Icethrone has asked you to go to the Windlord near the Velmuna "
"Outpost, and search for the legendary Demon Hand."

msgid "start_text_quest_2939"
msgstr "Deliver the Demon Hand to Arinlit Icethrone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2940"
msgstr ""
"The artifact known as the Demon's Hand, is something the Radiant Circle has "
"long wanted to possess. The Circle's researchers believe that many powerful "
"items could be crafted and enchanted by the powers of the Demon Hand.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the north of here you will find the Velmuna region, home to many "
"windlords. It is there, where centuries ago supreme general Velmuna severed "
"the Demon Warlord's hand in a bloody battle, before the Demon fled the "
"region. Although supreme general Velmuna was killed in that battle, the "
"campaign is considered victorious, since the Demon Walord was removed from "
"the region. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To honor supreme general Velmuna, her name was given to the entire region, "
"and an outpost was build in the region as a monument to all the fallen "
"warriors. Now many years later, the outpost is abandoned and no longer used, "
"and has become home to many windlords.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If the Radiant Circle is correct, the Demon Hand should be hidden somewhere "
"within the windlords possessions near the Velmuna Outpost. You will find the "
"windlords to the north of here, underneath the acid lake, among the acid "
"waterfalls."

msgid "start_text_quest_2941"
msgstr "Deliver the Demon Hand to Shulazu Nightshade at the Radiant Circle."

msgid "start_text_quest_2942"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver the Demon Hand straight to the Radiant Circle. I am "
"sure they are eager to get their hands on an artifact such as this. Go now, "
"and report to Shulazu Nightshade."

msgid "start_text_quest_2943"
msgstr "Nathar Blackorb has instructed you to report to Kaldahan Deepshadow."

msgid "start_text_quest_2944"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, an order has arrived from Shoal. The Temple of the God King is "
"to hunt down and punish a group of Melechar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"For many years, the Melechar loyally served the alfar and the God King "
"Melek. Melek had chosen these creatures to serve him, to be sent out into "
"the world to destroy his enemies. But over the years, the Melechar slowly "
"began distancing themselves from us alfar and the word of Melek. They had "
"become arrogant, and too comfortable with the idea that they as a race had "
"been chosen by Melek, and therefor will forever be in his favor. They had "
"even gone as far as disobeying orders straight from Shoal. Nobody disobeys "
"Shoal!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"After this behavior, the Melechar were banished from Nagast, and no longer "
"considered to be in the favor of Melek. The Melechar were ordered to "
"relinquish all artifacts of Melek back to Shoal. But the Melechar would not "
"accept this. They denied the fact that they were no longer in the favor of "
"Melek, and turned against the alfar. Preposterous.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now it is time to hunt down any Melechar groups, that still hold on to any "
"religious artifacts of Melek. It is an insult to the god king Melek, and to "
"all alfar, to allow these traitors, to posses such any items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You are to report to Kaldahan Deepshadow one more time, and deliver these "
"orders. Kaldahan has a great knowledge of the outer regions, and knows very "
"well where the Melechar villages are. It was Kaldahan who had reported, that "
"this Melechar group, might still be holding on the one of our religious "
"artifacts.."

msgid "start_text_quest_2945"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kaldahan Deepshadow. Kill seven Melechar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2946"
msgstr ""
"So, Shoal's patience has run out regarding these arrogant Melechar. What did "
"they think? Just because they were once the chosen of Melek, that Shoal and "
"the alfar would forget about them and leave them alone?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Shoal wishes to make an example out of these Melechar, to all that entertain "
"the thought of disobeying Shoal and the word of Melek. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to become Shoal's iron fist, and crush these traitors. "
"You are to deliver pain to these Melechar! The Melechar once lived, because "
"Melek chose so. Now that the Melechar have fallen from Melek's favor, the "
"Melechar will die!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are three Melechar villages in the outer regions to the east of here. "
"Go to these villages and kill at least seven of these traitorous Melechar. "
"Be aware of Melechar scouting parties. They are well trained fighters, not "
"to be taken lightly."

msgid "start_text_quest_2947"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kaldahan Deepshadow. Retrieve the Holy Symbol "
"of Melek from the traitorous Melechar."

msgid "start_text_quest_2948"
msgstr ""
"You have retrieved the Holy Symbol of Melek from the village of the "
"traitorous Melechar. Return to {$p22} and deliver the symbol to Kaldahan "
"Deepshadow."

msgid "start_text_quest_2949"
msgstr ""
"Shoal wishes to deeply humiliate these Melechar, stripping them of anything "
"that once connected them to the god king Melek. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"All Melechar communities were once given a Holy Symbol of Melek to signify "
"their loyalty to Melek, to the alfar and to Shoal. Shoal demands that the  "
"Holy Symbol of Melek be removed from the possession of these Melechar, and "
"returned to Shoal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I do not know in which of the three villages the holy symbol is kept, but I "
"do know it is in one of them. You are to search each village either for a "
"chest or a crate. Use the action button to investigate more closely. When "
"you have found the Holy Symbol of Melek and removed it from the Melechar, "
"return with it to me, and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_2950"
msgstr ""
"Deliver Kaldahan Deepshadow's report to Nathar Blackorb at the Temple of the "
"God King."

msgid "start_text_quest_2951"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Now that we have dealt with the traitorous Melechar, and "
"delivered Shoal's message to them, I want you to report back to Nathar "
"Blackorb at the Temple of the God King.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once more, I will ask of you to deliver this report letter to him. And once "
"again, it has been an honor working with you."

msgid "start_text_quest_2952"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Search for clues, that "
"might explain the sudden appearance of the serpentines within the old "
"severii stronghold in Sallesh."

msgid "start_text_quest_2953"
msgstr ""
"A decade ago, the Harn Mandean had launched an attack against the severii "
"stronghold beyond the borders of Nagast, to the northeast of here in the "
"Sallesh region. The campaign was quick and successful. The stronghold was "
"taken, and all the severii destroyed. Now a decade later, our agents have "
"discovered that the city is occupied once more, not by severii, but "
"serpentines. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Serpentines are creatures that faithfully serve powerful dragons by either "
"guarding their master's lair, serving as scouts, or searching for a possible "
"new lair. Knowing that Cyriacus himself is a skeleton Dragon God, we cannot "
"overlook the possibility that Cyriacus may have recruited to his cause a "
"powerful new ally. A Dragon! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Harn Mandean wants you to search the old abandon severii stronghold and "
"its environment for any clues that might show a possible connection to "
"Cyriacus, or any other power that is commanding these serpentines. Upon "
"discovering something that might offer any insight, use the action button to "
"investigate more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_2954"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Go to the Shallesh region "
"and kill three serpentines."

msgid "start_text_quest_2955"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have spotted serpentines in the Sallesh region to the northeast "
"of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Serpentines are known to serve powerful dragons, usually guarding their "
"master's lair, or are out scouting and gathering recourses. Whatever the "
"reason these serpentines have entered the Sallesh region, the Harn Mandean "
"will not risk the possibility of a powerful dragon setting a lair at "
"Nagast's doorstep! The serpentines must be stopped from whatever it is "
"they're doing, and very soon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, prepare yourself for a difficult task. You are to go and slay "
"three of these serpentines."

msgid "start_text_quest_2956"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Deliver a copy of the "
"ancient writings from the tombstone to Ninnah the Mage at Shoal."

msgid "start_text_quest_2957"
msgstr ""
"The writings upon the tombstone you copied earlier from the severii "
"stronghold, are beyond anything the Harn Mandean has every come across "
"before. It seems we are not able to decipher these ancient writings.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Shoal must be informed about this find. It is imperative that we learn who "
"or what is commanding these serpentines, and if they intend to move into the "
"severii stronghold. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Ninnah the Mage, is an expert in deciphering ancient texts. She is one if "
"Shoal's finest. I want you to report to her, hand her the copy of the "
"writings from the tombstone, and see if she is able to decipher this text. "
"Go now, do not waste time."

msgid "start_text_quest_2958"
msgstr ""
"For Ninnah the Mage to complete the deciphering of the writings, you will "
"need to bring her three units of elemental cinder from the Lesser Fire "
"Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_2959"
msgstr ""
"I am positive that the writings you copied from the tombstone you found in "
"the severii stronghold, are of an ancient demonic language which hasn't been "
"spoken for many centuries. Yes, I do believe I will be able to decipher the "
"writings from the tombstone, but I will need some time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To be able to read this ancient language, I will have to cast a powerful "
"spell that will allow me to read and speak this long forgotten language. But "
"to cast the spell, specific ingredients are needed. Most of the ingredients "
"needed are found here within Shoal except for one, elemental cinder. I need "
"at least three units of elemental cinder, if I am to unlock the speak this "
"ancient language.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the south of there in the volcanic region of Kir Janu, one can find many "
"lesser fire elementals. From these creatures, elemental cinder can be "
"harvested. I will start deciphering the ancient text. Your task will be to "
"go and bring me three units of elemental cinders."

msgid "start_text_quest_2960"
msgstr ""
"You are to go to the city of Espenhal and acquire a copy of the demonic "
"writings that Ninseri the Mage found upon a strange tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_2961"
msgstr ""
"A report had arrived a few weeks earlier from one of our agents who had "
"returned from the rogue city of Espenhal. Our agent managed to learn that "
"Ninseri the Mage who resides within Espenhal,  had come across a similar "
"tombstone with the same ancient demonic wittings carved upon it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must get a copy of the writings from the tombstone that Ninseri found. I "
"want you to go to Ninseri, and get a copy from her. I myself have dealt with "
"Ninseri in the past. She is one to not give up any of her findings for free, "
"so be prepared to take on some difficult task in exchange for a copy of the "
"writings she has found.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I must also warn you about Espenhal as a city itself. Espanhal is a chaotic "
"city, with no laws of any kind. You will come across the worse kind Agon has "
"to offer. Even an alfar like yourself must be cautious. Do not trust "
"anybody. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you accept to go to Espanhal, I suggest you go straight to Ninseri the "
"Mage. Here, take this letter an deliver it to her. This way she will know "
"that I have sent you to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_2962"
msgstr ""
"You must bring ten Cursed Darktaint to Ninseri the Mage, to acquire a copy "
"of the demonic writings Ninnah the mage has asked for."

msgid "start_text_quest_2963"
msgstr ""
"So, my dear friend Ninnah has also come across one of these ancient demonic "
"tombstones. And from what I understand, Shoal would like copy of the "
"writings from the tombstone I discovered.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Well, no Ninnah and definitely no Shoal will so easily take something from "
"to me, after all they have done to me. But, that is a story for some other "
"time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Don't you worry now. I will give you a copy of the writings, but only if you "
"do something for me first. I so happen to be in need of Elemental "
"Stormrunes. Two of them in fact.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Northeast of here in the Nurenfau region, you will find one of the demonic "
"cities that have spawned throughout the central plains. This city is guarded "
"by Shadow Knights, one of the many creatures called forth be an unknown "
"power that has emerge in the heart of the central plains. A power that is "
"slowly destroying all natural life, and changing the central plains into "
"what I believe is a mirror image of its own world.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, since you are so good at following orders, why don't you go and bring "
"me two Elemental Stormrunes. These, you will be able to harvest from the "
"Shadow Knights, once you have killed them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I think it is a fair trade. Two Elemental Stormrunes for a copy of the "
"demonic writings. Don't go asking for some grand reward now. I am sure "
"Ninnah the Mage will reward you well, once you deliver the writings to her "
"in Shoal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring me two Elemental Stormrunes."

msgid "start_text_quest_2964"
msgstr ""
"You have acquired a copy of the demonic writings from Ninseri the Mage, and "
"all that remains is for you return to Ninnah the Mage in Shoal."

msgid "start_text_quest_2965"
msgstr ""
"As I said earlier, if you did bring me two Elemental Stormrunes, I will give "
"you copy of the demonic writings that Ninnah so much desires. So here is "
"your copy of the demonic writings. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, return to Ninnah in Shoal, and collect your well earned reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2967"
msgstr ""
"The Shadow Salient have chosen you to assess the strength of the Gray Orks "
"hiding inside Saenal Dungeon. Kill three Gray Orks inside the dungeon, and "
"return with a full report of their strengths, and the dungeon layout."

msgid "start_text_quest_2968"
msgstr ""
"For several days now, our scouts have been skillfully following and "
"observing from the shadows a group of gray orks. For a while, it remained a "
"mystery to us where these gray orks had come from, but most importantly, "
"where did they go, meaning, where was their lair or hideout.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Two days ago, our scouts successfully located the gray orks hideout. There "
"is a portal in Saenal that leads to a hidden complex cave system "
"underground. Unfortunately, this portal is within the city of the undead "
"dwarves.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you may understand, the Shadow Masters of the Shadow Salient have shown a "
"great interest in this hidden complex cave system. Now the Shadow Masters "
"demand that we enter the dungeon and assess the strength of the gray orks. "
"Once we have enough information, a well planned attack will be launch into "
"the gray orks dungeon. The goal, to route them out if not completely "
"obliterate them, and to take over the dungeon complex for the Shadow "
"Salient's use.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to enter the dungeon, assess the strength of these "
"gray orks, and return with information of the dungeon's layout. Your first "
"goal is to kill three gray orks. Your second goal is to manage to return "
"here to us with your assessment. Once inside the dungeon, it is up to you to "
"locate and kill the gray orks, and then to find your own way out."

msgid "start_text_quest_2969"
msgstr "Iain Deepwode has asked you to report to Elena the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_2970"
msgstr ""
"Many legends talk about the Nithron, a race of golden-skinned giants who "
"once ruled Agon. The Nithron had build many cities across Agon, and one of "
"them is located to the east of here, in {$x20}. Elena the Mage is currently "
"looking into many of the legends that talk about artifacts and secrets left "
"behind by the Nithron. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"When word had reached her that you had successfully located and retrieved "
"the Nithron artifact, the dragon-shaped necklace known as the Dragontorc, "
"Elena requested that she speak with you. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"She believes you might be able to help her in her search regarding the "
"Nithron. If you can spare the time, please go and speak with her."

msgid "start_text_quest_2971"
msgstr "Elena the Mage has asked you to kill four Oathbound."

msgid "start_text_quest_2972"
msgstr ""
"The Nithron were godlike beings who possessed abilities and magic far beyond "
"anything seen today. Among their achievements was the creation of a magical "
"race called the Oathbound, who were blindly loyal to the Nithron, and who "
"served as their bodyguards and elite warriors.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Missing from Agon for centuries, Oathbound guardians have suddenly begun to "
"reappear in Nithron ruins, frequently in the vicinity of  important "
"artifacts, major buildings, or other reappearing aspects of Nithron culture. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to evaluate the threat posed by these returning servants. To the "
"east of here, in the {$x20} region, there is a plateau with Nithron ruins "
"upon it. It is there, among those ruins, that many have reported seeing "
"these Oathbound guardians. Seek out, fight, and destroy at least five of "
"them, and then return to me with your evaluation of their capabilities and "
"limitations."

msgid "start_text_quest_2973"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elena the Mage. Search the Bladethorpe "
"Nithron Ruins for the Chronicles of the Firstborn."

msgid "start_text_quest_2974"
msgstr ""
"You now have the Chronicles of the Firstborn in your possession. Give it to "
"Elena the Mage in {$u21} to claim a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_2975"
msgstr ""
"Unlocking the secrets of Nithron artifacts is proving to be quite a "
"challenge. There is quite simply too much we do not know about their "
"history, language and customs, and as a result, our arcanists and enchanters "
"are working and experimenting in partial darkness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the Nithron age, one of the world's greatest libraries lay in the Mercian "
"region of {$x20}. As you know, various aspects of Nithron are currently "
"reappearing throughout Agon, and with some luck, this thoroughly strange "
"phenomenon also encompasses the collections of the {$x20} library.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to search the Nithron ruins of {$x20} for a volume called the "
"Chronicles of the Firstborn. According to an old library index, this book "
"was once housed in a building in the northeastern section of the complex, "
"near a tall tower.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To search through a shelf, simply walk up to it and use the action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_2976"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elena the Mage. Bring Elena's message to "
"Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2977"
msgstr ""
"The Chronicles of the Firstborn contain a prophecy which states that the "
"Nithron will return to Agon when the stars are in a position which closely "
"matches the current configuration. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This is no longer a matter purely for the Sons of Riada. The Mercian "
"authorities must be informed of the strange and disturbing developments "
"taking place in Nithron ruins throughout the realm. Please bring this report "
"to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2978"
msgstr ""
"Sir Jeremiah Grace has asked you to report to Allan the Councillor at "
"Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2979"
msgstr ""
"It seems that your exploits in our war against the Twilight Empire, have not "
"gone unnoticed by the authorities in Sanguine. Allan the Councillor would "
"like to speak to you. From what I have heard, it seems that agents of "
"Sanguine have uncovered valuable information regarding Twilight Empire, and "
"believe you could be of help to them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go now, and report to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2980"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Allan the Councillor. Enter the Malaut "
"stronghold inside Broadherne dungeon, and steal the unholy book of Malaut."

msgid "start_text_quest_2981"
msgstr "Deliver the unholy book of Malaut to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_2982"
msgstr ""
"Welcome, I am  Allan the Councillor. You have managed to make quite a name "
"for yourself #PlayerName#. If half of what the Knights of Malregard say "
"about you in their reports is true, then you have definitely become a wanted "
"enemy of the Twilight Empire. There are many worshipers of Malaut at the "
"moment, that would give up their life for a chance to rip your heart out.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Don't be upset now. Many of our agents envy you, and would love to be in "
"your place. Malaut and his minions have been a thorn in our side, one that "
"the light of Auros demands to be removed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our agents have managed to extract valuable information from the Malaut "
"worshipers we had captured several days ago. We have learned of a portal in "
"the {$s19} region, that leads in to a well hidden Malaut dungeon stronghold. "
"We had known about the Malaut village that existed in the cliffs of the "
"{$s19} region, but had never known about the portal. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Inside this Malaut stronghold, there is a shrine dedicated to Malaut. The "
"Shine is located in a large torture chamber. It is in this torture chamber, "
"in this unholy shrine, that the unholy book of Malaut is kept.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is this unholy book of Malaut we want. With it we may have a better "
"understanding of the teachings of Malaut and the ways of his Twilight "
"Kingdom, and eventually a better understanding of how to destroy them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I must warn you, that we have no knowledge of the interior layout of the "
"stronghold. So once you have entered the dungeon, it is up to you find your "
"way to the torture chamber, locate the shrine and steal the unholy book of "
"Malaut. One thing we do know about the underground stronghold, is that you "
"cannot exit the same way you enter. There is another portal somewhere inside "
"that will lead you out.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To get to the portal in the {$s19} region, you will have to fight your way "
"through the Malaut village. This is a dangerous mission, and some would call "
"it a suicide mission. But, if you do find a few brave souls that wish to "
"accompany you on this difficult mission, I suggest you take them along.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Find the hidden Malaut stronghold, and steal the unholy book of Malaut."

msgid "start_text_quest_2983"
msgstr ""
"Maria Hawksgate has asked of you to travel to Silverley and report to Oona "
"Fern."

msgid "start_text_quest_2984"
msgstr ""
"Situated to the east of here is the town of Silverley. It is there that many "
"of the magical weapons wielded by the Mercian army are made. And in charge "
"of overseeing the manufacturing of  the enchanted weapons wielded by the "
"Mercian army, is my dear friend Oona Fern.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A letter has arrive from Oona Fern, asking of the White Order to send help "
"to Silverley. In her letter Oona states that many of her people have been "
"attacked by gray orks in {$v17}, while out gathering many of the materials "
"needed for the crafting of the enchanted weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to report to Oona Fern and to see if you could be "
"of any help to her. Here, please hand this letter I have written, to know "
"that I have personally sent you to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_2985"
msgstr ""
"Oona Fern has asked for your help. Kill at least four gray orks in the "
"{$v17} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2986"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Silverley traveler. I am Oona Fern, a member of the White Order "
"and of the church of Auros. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As Maria Hawksgate might have informed you, it is here in Silverley that "
"many of the enchanted weapons of the Mercian army of crafted. We have people "
"who search the lands for materials that are needed for the crafting of "
"magical weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently a group of enchanters from Silverley, while out gathering "
"ingredients needed for enchanting, where attacked by a group of gray orks. "
"We sent a small party to find these gray orks, and to eventually drive them "
"away, but the gray orks proved to powerful for our people. The gray orks not "
"only left the region of {$v17}, but have become more aggressive, attacking "
"anybody they see. I admit, we are not warriors, and therefor not in a "
"position to confront them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We urgently need to drive these gray orks away from {$v17}.  I believe that "
"slaying four of these gray orks, should be enough to scare them, and "
"eventually drive them out of mercians lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please, if you may, kill four of these gray orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_2987"
msgstr ""
"Maria Hawksgate has asked you to put an end to the thugs of Highmoore. You "
"are to attack the bandits stronghold in Highmoore, and kill at least three "
"Guildmasters, three Outlaws and three Highwaymen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2988"
msgstr ""
"Once one of the thriving mercian communities that existed in the region of "
"{$s17}. Highmoore was an exemplary community, one bathed in the light of "
"Auros. It was a perfect example on how mercian communities could thrive in "
"the harshness of the outer regions of mercia. And for many years Highmoore "
"did prosper. But all of this stopped, once the Shadow of Malaut covered the "
"hearts and minds of  the humans of Highmoore. Now the light of Auros now "
"longer shines in the once prosperous mercian village.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Highmoore has now become the stronghold for mercia's worst bandits and "
"renegades, where thugs and rogues regularly plan raid on other nearby "
"mercian communities for any little possessions the villages might have. They "
"have recently even gone as far as killing those unfortunate villages who are "
"unable to provide what the Guildmasters of Highmoore demand. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The authorities of Sanguine have put out a call to all able heroes under the "
"guiding light of Auros, to put an end to this village of darkness, and "
"return Highmoore once more to its previous glory.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You #PlayerName#, have proven to be a good and lawful individual, and "
"definitely one that deserves to walk in the light of Auros. I am positive "
"that you too wish to put an end to the activities of these thugs. You can "
"help be attacking the bandits stronghold in Highmoore, and removing three "
"Guildmasters, three Outlaws and three Highwaymen."

msgid "start_text_quest_2989"
msgstr ""
"Report to Aurmon the Brave, and see how you may help to calm down the "
"violent centaurs in Wolf Run."

msgid "start_text_quest_2990"
msgstr ""
"Something has greatly disturbed and angered the centaurs in the region of "
"Wolf Run. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Aurmon the Brave, a Longclaw agent, is situated near Wolf Run in Anyth. He "
"has been closely observing the centaurs and their growing aggressive "
"behavior. According to his last report, the centaurs have become so "
"aggressive, going as far as to attacking several of our communities. "
"Behavior like this we will not tolerate. The centaurs cannot be allowed to "
"roam around like this, spreading terror among our communities. If they are "
"to live here within the Tribelands, they must either respect or fear the "
"mahirim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to report to Aurmon the Brave. Aurmon will inform "
"you of what is needed to be done."

msgid "start_text_quest_2991"
msgstr ""
"Help stop the wild rampage of the centaurs of Wolf Run. Kill at least six of "
"them"

msgid "start_text_quest_2992"
msgstr ""
"The Tribelands are home to many creatures, be it from the centaurs and the "
"bears of the forests, to our racial enemies the gnolls, or even the Cult of "
"the Moon-Beast. But one thing all these inhabitance of the Tribelands have "
"in common, is their fear and respect of the rulers of theses land, the "
"mahirim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The clan of centaurs that live in Wolf Run are acting strangely of lately, "
"as if overcome by some kind of madness. They have grown wild and full of "
"rage, a behavior far beyond anything I have ever seen. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until we discover the source of the centaurs madness, we need to stop their "
"wild rampage. We cannot allow then to simply raid and destroy the local "
"communities. I want you to kill six of these wild centaurs. You will find "
"them in Wolf Run to the northeast of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_2993"
msgstr ""
"You have helped stop the rampage of the centaurs in Wolf Run. Aurmon will "
"continue to monitor the situation, while you deliver his report to Yaleria-"
"Sai at the Longclaw headquarters in Stonehold."

msgid "start_text_quest_2994"
msgstr ""
"We have done all we can for the moment, regarding the enraged centaurs of "
"Wolf Run. I will continue to monitor this unusual behavior of the centaurs, "
"until we discover the cause of this madness. You will report back to Yaleria-"
"Sai in {$i10}. Deliver this report I have prepared. There is not much else "
"that we can do."

msgid "start_text_quest_2995"
msgstr ""
"Yaleria-Sai has assigned to you the task of entering the dungeon in "
"Meldanyr, and to harvest one Elemental Cinder as proof of the existence of "
"Lesser Fire Elementals in the region."

msgid "start_text_quest_2996"
msgstr ""
"A few days ago, a merchant traveling through Meldanyr reported seeing Lesser "
"Fire Elementals. Immediately we sent two of our scouts to investigate, but "
"were unable to locate any Lesser Fire Elementals in the region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Having no reason to doubt the merchant, we sent a report to the Circle of "
"Neith. The Circle of Neith, is always interested in hearing about rare "
"monster sightings. And the last time a Fire Elemental was seen within the "
"Tribelands, was over a hundred years ago.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Circle requested if it is possible for us to search for a hidden dungeon "
"complex in Meldanyr, as maybe this could be where the Lesser Fire Elementals "
"are hiding. The Circle of Neith is interested in harvesting these creature "
"for Elemental Cinder, as this material will help them decipher an ancient "
"scroll they have found.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have managed to locate a portal in Meldanyr, which could possibly "
"lead into the hidden lair of the Fire Elementals. I want you to go to this "
"portal and enter the dungeon and investigate. Once inside, search for the "
"Lesser Fire Elementals. If you do locate these creatures of fire, take the "
"time to harvest from the one Elemental Cinder. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, because we have no knowledge of this dungeon, it is up to you "
"to search and locate these creatures alone. What we do suspect about this "
"dungeon, is that you cannot exit the way you enter. You must search for "
"another portal inside, that will lead you again to the surface. "
"#PlayerName#, find these Lesser Fire Elementals and bring back one Elemental "
"Cinder."

msgid "start_text_quest_2997"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the package with materials that Yaleria-Sai has prepared, to Katila "
"the Arcanist in Moonclaw."

msgid "start_text_quest_2998"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this package I have here to Katila the Arcanist of the "
"Circle of Neith. Inside it I have placed the Elemental Cinder you had "
"gathered earlier, together with other materials she had requested. From what "
"I understand, the Circle of Neith is keen on deciphering this ancient scroll "
"they have discovered. It is not that often that the scholars of the Circle "
"ask for outside help.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Circle of Neith is located in Moonclaw, to the southeast of here. I am "
"sure Katila is eagerly waiting for her package to arrive."

msgid "start_text_quest_2999"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has asked of you to slay at least four of the cursed Bonecrew "
"that haunt the fishing village of Fang Lake."

msgid "start_text_quest_3000"
msgstr ""
"To the southeast of the Wolfmask Headquarters lies Fang Lake, which for many "
"years has provided us its clean fresh waters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Fang Lake was also home to a small human fishing village until recently. For "
"some unknown reason its human inhabitants fell ill, as if under some unholy "
"curse, slowly turning into undead half-rotten souls known as Bonecrew. As "
"Bonecrew, they wander aimlessly among whatever is left of their village, "
"while tainting the waters of Fang Lake.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to Fang Lake and destroy four Bonecrew. Once you have "
"completed this task, return to me with your assessment of the situation."

msgid "start_text_quest_3001"
msgstr ""
"Locate and destroy the marked gravestone in {$l15} that is used as a message "
"drop-off point, between the human bandits and their mysterious leaders. You "
"must use physical force to destroy it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3002"
msgstr ""
"The humans that you encountered earlier, were not simply hiding here within "
"the Tribelands. After interrogating them, we have learned that these humans "
"are working for a secretive group, possibly even a group of mahirim "
"traitors. This is most disturbing, and a report has already been sent to the "
"authorities at Red Moon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"What it is exactly this group the human bandits are working for wish to "
"accomplish is not yet known, although we do suspect it has something to do "
"with the Elders of Red Moon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While our agents are out hunting down any other human bandits that may be "
"hiding within the Tribelands, we discovered how human bandits would "
"communicate with their employers. A marked gravestone near the ruined chapel "
"in Wolfdale, would be used as a secret location to leave messages. It is "
"this gravestone I want you to discover and destroy. You must use physical "
"force to be able to erase the marking off the gravestone. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We will show them that nobody can work behind the Wolfmasks without being "
"discovered. Find and destroy this gravestone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3003"
msgstr ""
"You have been asked to go the Gray Ork Camp in Dagnamyr and kill two Gray "
"Orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3004"
msgstr ""
"An order has arrived from Red Moon, asking the Wolfmasks to honor the "
"alliance with the Orks of Morak. It would seem that our allies the orks are "
"having a few problems of their own, and have requested our help.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There has been a sudden increase of attacks against our allies the Orks of "
"Morak, by Gray Orks. The Gray Orks live their lives mostly underground in "
"dungeon and caves, in an eternal life or death struggle with other "
"subterranean cultures. Recently however, Gray Orks have started venturing to "
"the surface throughout Agon, and for no reason are attacking all surface "
"orks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Agents of Morak suspect a Gray Ork village near our borders in {$m13}. They "
"have asked us to locate this gray ork village, and assess the strength of "
"these gray orks. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to go to {$m13}, locate this gray ork village, and to "
"kill two Gray Orks. Once you have completed the mission, return here with "
"your assessment. Dagnamyr is to the northeast of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3005"
msgstr ""
"Symyr-dan has informed you that you have been summoned by Tivasta the "
"Councillor in Red Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3006"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor in Red Moon, has requested to see you. News travels "
"fast, and it would seem that your successes in locating and recovering the "
"lost half of the sacred stone tablet, has made quite an impression in Red "
"Moon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I understand that Red Moon is very close to locating the resting place of a "
"very important figure, and I believe with your help they will eventually "
"find it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Do not let an opportunity like this go to waste. It is an honor to be "
"summoned by Red Moon, to be chosen to assist in such a operation. Go now, "
"and report to Tivasta the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_3007"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tivasta the Councillor. Search for the "
"resting place of Larren-Tai, inside Larethain dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3008"
msgstr ""
"You have heard by now the story of the prophet-king Amurran. It was Amurran "
"who united the many heartland tribes, founded the city of Red Moon, and laid "
"the foundations for today's modern mahirim society.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But Amurran was not alone. One of our scholars has discovered in the hidden "
"dark corners of our libraries, a lost diary written by Amurran himself. In "
"this diary Amurran talks about many proud and brave mahirim that faithfully "
"served him. Mahirim that guarded him, fought side by side with him and "
"accompanied him on his every journey. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But one name that stands out the most, is that of his faithful general "
"Larren-Tai. Larren-Tai is referred to as the proud but quiet hero, by "
"Amurran himself. Amurran describes how Larren-Tai gave her life for Amurran "
"in a battle in Larethain, and it is there in the dungeons of Larethain that "
"Larren-Tai now rests. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Time has come to restore the name and glory to this quiet hero, and lawful "
"servant of the mahirim people. It is the story of Larren-Tai that can "
"inspire many more mahirim to do their part in building the powerful mahirim "
"race, while quietly working in the background. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to locate Larren-Tai's resting place. The resting place of such a "
"hero, should not be forgotten and lost in time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#. There is a portal in the Larethain region, one we are sure "
"that leads into the maze of caves, corridors and dungeons where Larren-Tai "
"now rests. We want you to enter this dungeon, and locate Larren-Tai's "
"resting place."

msgid "start_text_quest_3009"
msgstr ""
"Celetia the White has requested of you, to harvest a Tribal Lifeforce for "
"the Menhir Custodians."

msgid "start_text_quest_3010"
msgstr ""
"A rare opportunity have been presented to us. A little to the east of here, "
"there is a lake with a small island in the center of it. Upon the island, "
"there is a circle of stones, possibly an old sacred site, long now "
"abandoned. What is interesting, is the appearance of menhir custodians upon "
"the island. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We believe that the menhir that have appeared on the island, have either "
"come to guard this ancient site, or are possibly drawn to the residual "
"traces of holy magic that remain in such a places. Whatever the reason, it "
"is an rare opportunity to study these mysterious creatures. I want you to go "
"to the ancient sacred site upon the island, and harvest from the menhir "
"custodians one menhir heart. One will be enough for our researchers to "
"conduct experiments, and learn as much as we can about these mysterious "
"guardians.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I understand this is a very dangerous task I am asking for, but there is no "
"hurry. Only when you feel confident enough, should you take on this mission. "
"Bring me a menhir heart, and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3011"
msgstr ""
"Celetia the White has asked you to travel to Amurranyr, to the Elders of Red "
"Moon, and report to Levynna the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_3012"
msgstr ""
"A letter has arrived from Levynna the Arcanist, from the Elders of the Red "
"Moon. It seems that Levynna has located a group of Akathar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Akathars as very rarely found in the Tribelands, so you can understand our "
"excitement when we received this news. It is an opportunity for us to not "
"only study these creatures, but to also harvest Dim Stormrunes. I am very "
"interested in acquiring some of those Dim Stormrunes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to Amurranyr, that is where the Elders of the Red Moon "
"are situated, and to report to Levynna the Arcanist. Tell here that I have "
"sent you regarding the Akathars and the Dim Stormrunes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3013"
msgstr ""
"Levynna the Arcanist has informed you of were the group of Akathars was last "
"seen. Once you have harvested three Wind Shadowcrest from the Akathars, "
"deliver them to Celetia the White at the Circle of Neith"

msgid "start_text_quest_3014"
msgstr ""
"A while back, we had received a list from Circle of Neith, a list with rare "
"creatures. If we where ever to spot any of these creatures, a report was to "
"be sent immediately to the Circle of Neith to inform them. And so it is with "
"the Akathar sightings to the south of here in the Lake Orzma region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"From what I understand, Celetia the White of the Circle of Neith would like "
"somebody to harvest Dim Stormrunes from the Akathars. It doesn't take much "
"to understand that you will be the one that will have to locate the "
"Akathars, and to harvest the Dim Stormrunes. Three Dim Stormrunes should be "
"enough for the Circle of Neith. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will mark on your map, where the Akathars were last seen. Once you have "
"harvested the three Dim Stormrunes, deliver them straight to Celetia the "
"White in Moonclaw."

msgid "start_text_quest_3015"
msgstr ""
"Travel to Inarith, and search for the gravestone located near Siritos's "
"tower, to find the book of Bad Magic. Casting a Mana Missile Spell onto the "
"correct gravestone should reveal the hidden item."

msgid "start_text_quest_3016"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Book of Bad Magic. Bring it to Caradial Elmheart, and "
"collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3017"
msgstr ""
"Miredil's past is one full of many wars and mysteries. Some about strange "
"powerful races, others about battles between the ancient gods of Agon, but "
"none as strange as the time of Bad Magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many wizards and sages of the time, describe the time of Bad Magic as a "
"period of dangerous and uncontrollable magic. The effects of the time of Bad "
"Magic were many, but none as strange as the creation of the Bad Magic areas. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These areas of concentrated Bad Magic would transform the terrain into a "
"completely new landscape, alien to the surrounding lands. Areas of snow and "
"ice would appear where once temperate warm climates existed, wastelands and "
"deserts where rich green forests once stood, acid pools of death where lakes "
"full of crystal clean waters once were.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One such Bad Magic Area still exists in Inarith. Most of the region has been "
"transformed from its original green forest landscape into a small desert-"
"like region. Now in the desert region of Inarith one can only find the many "
"undead that walk upon its dry ground, and the ruin tower in the center of "
"the region, once home to the great scholar Siritos.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Siritos, one of the great scholars of the time, wanted to understand the "
"unnatural effects of these Bad Magic Areas. He traveled to Inarith to one of "
"the Bad Magic Areas, and in the center of the newly-created desert he "
"located the source of the Bad Magic. There, he built his tower where he "
"would research deeper into mysterious powers of the Bad Magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently one of our researchers came across a book referring to Siritos's "
"work. It is said that Siritos magically hid his research of the Bad Magic "
"phenomenon, inside one of the gravestones located near his tower. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You are to travel to Inarith, go to the ruin tower of Siritos, and find the "
"gravestone that magical holds Siritos's work. Once you have found the "
"correct gravestone, use a Mana Missile Spell to retrieve the hidden item. "
"When you have successfully completed this task, return here with the item."

msgid "start_text_quest_3018"
msgstr ""
"Help the Emerald Throne clear the tower of Siritos in Inarith from the "
"undead. Destroy four ghouls."

msgid "start_text_quest_3019"
msgstr ""
"Inarith was one of the many regions hit by uncontrollable magical in the "
"time of Bad Magic. According to the old texts, Inarith was transformed in a "
"very short period into a desert region. It was this strange phenomenon that "
"caught Siritos's attention. Siritos sought to study this phenomenon, and so "
"decided to relocate to Inarith where he built his tower. There, Siritos "
"would spend the rest of his days researching this strange phenomenon.\n"
"\n"
"Siritos was a great scholar, that devoted his whole life in helping the "
"mirdain people through his research and studies in understanding the many "
"strange magical occurrences of his time. But now, the great tower of Siritos "
"stands in ruin, haunted by the many undead that roam the desert region.\n"
"\n"
"It is a pity to have such an important location, part of Miredil's history "
"left in ruin. The Elflords of the Emerald Throne wish to reclaim this "
"historical monument, and restore it to its former glory. It is these undead "
"that we will begin to slowly remove from the area. You can help by "
"destroying four ghouls."

msgid "start_text_quest_3020"
msgstr ""
"Kill four of the mercenary gray orks that are lurking beyond the "
"southwerstern borders of Mirendil, and then report to Sylanae the Councillor "
"in the mirdain capital Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3021"
msgstr ""
"For several weeks now, agents of Charybdis have been following groups of "
"mercenary gray orks that have been lurking on the southwestern borders of "
"Mirendil. The authorities in Charybdis feel uneasy having these dangerous "
"murderers at our borders. So far all the agents are gathering information, "
"so we may better understand if this in a coordinated attack, or just a "
"coincidence.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Charybdis has requesting that we allocate some of our agents to help removed "
"these unwanted guests from our borders. The Emerald Throne wants you to kill "
"five of these gray orks, and then report to Sylanae the Councillor in "
"Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3022"
msgstr ""
"Eredethil Swiftarrow has asked you to kill four gray orks that have set camp "
"in {$k20}, before three hours have passed. \r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3023"
msgstr ""
"After interrogating one of the hobgoblin officers, we have learned that the "
"hobgoblins were not working alone. While raiding our villages, the "
"hobgoblins had the support of a group of gray ork mercenaries, that have set "
"their camp to the southeast of here in the Eberathil region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will not allow these gray orks to get away with what they have done. The "
"problem is that I am running low on agents at the moment, but this cannot "
"wait. We must attack the gray ork camp before they learn of the downfall of "
"their hobgoblin friends, and choose to flee the area.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you feel the need to punish these gray orks for their "
"crimes, you could revenge the fallen by killing four gray orks. But as I "
"said, this cannot wait. Go to {$k20}, and kill four gray orks before three "
"hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_3024"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Arrowhead. You are to enter the Baradron "
"dungeon, find and kill four melechar. Once completing the mission, make your "
"way our of the dungeon and report to Eredethil Swiftarrow."

msgid "start_text_quest_3025"
msgstr ""
"Charybdis has sent an order to the Arrowhead. We are to investigate the "
"dungeon complex in Baradron for melechar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The melechar are an evil race of elves, so evil, that were once considered "
"to be in the favor of the alfar god king Melek, serving Melek and the alfar "
"fanatically. It is said that the alfar god king Melek had chosen melechar to "
"serve him and to be sent out into the world to destroy his enemies. Melek "
"had imbued the melechar with both great strength and madness, thus making "
"them extremely dangerous. But in recent years, the melechar have fallen from "
"Melek's favor, and are now considered enemies of the alfar. Still, this does "
"not make them one bit less dangerous as the evil race they are.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to investigate the Baradron dungeon. Find out if "
"melechar are hiding in the Baradron dungeon, and return with a report of "
"their strengths and weaknesses. Killing four of them should be enough for "
"you to evaluate their strength.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We currently have no knowledge of the interior of the dungeon complex. It is "
"up to you to find the melechar, gather information, and make your own way "
"out."

msgid "start_text_quest_3026"
msgstr ""
"Eredethil Swiftarrow has given toy the task to deliver his report letter to "
"Sylanae the Councillor in Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3027"
msgstr ""
"Charybdis must be informed about the melechar stronghold in Baradron. We "
"cannot allow these evil elves, who were once fanatical servants of Melek and "
"the alfar, to be anywhere near our lands. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, please deliver this report letter I have written to Sylanae "
"the Councillor in Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3028"
msgstr ""
"Report to Theila Brightstar in Lower Eredras, to receive further orders "
"regarding your mission about the melechar stronghold."

msgid "start_text_quest_3029"
msgstr ""
"Beyond our eastern borders in the Cieradan region, our agents have "
"discovered a larger melecher stronghold. We believe that the base of "
"operations for the melechar outside our borders is located within the "
"dungeon complex of Cieradan.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our agents have been monitoring this melechar stronghold for a while now. In "
"the last few days there has been an increase in activity. Many melechar have "
"arrived and entered this stronghold. We must stop whatever it is that the "
"melechar are preparing.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Five hundred years ago, when the melechar were still serving the alfar god "
"king Melek, we had discovered and entered another melechar stronghold. We "
"know now that at the heart of every melechar stronghold, there is a shrine "
"dedicated to the ever hateful alfar god Melek. The melechars faith towards "
"Melek is what holds the chaotic melechar communities together. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"And although we know that today the melechar are no longer the chosen allies "
"of the alfar, neither in the favor of Melek, we believe that even today, the "
"melechar still cling onto this belief. That one day, the favor of Melek will "
"return to them. It is this faith that we must destroy, if we are to disrupt "
"their operations and drown them in disarray and chaos. Without faith and "
"hope to guild them, we may then send in our agents to crush the evil "
"melechar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you must enter the stronghold, find the altar dedicated to "
"Melek, and steal the unholy book of Melek also known as the Words of Melek. "
"Without the unholy book of Melek, the melechar are lost children.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Theila Brightstar, who is stationed in Lower "
"Eredras. Theila has excellent knowledge of the eastern territories, and was "
"one of the agents that discover the hidden melechar stronghold. You will be "
"receiving your next orders from Theila, once you have report to her for duty."

msgid "start_text_quest_3030"
msgstr ""
"Enter the melechar stronghold inside the Cieradan dungeon, locate the altar "
"or shrine dedicated to Melek, and steal the unholy book of Melek. Once "
"completed, exit the dungeon and head straight to Sylanae the Councillor in "
"Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3031"
msgstr ""
"Report to Sylanae the Councillor in Charybdis and hand over the unholy book "
"of Melek."

msgid "start_text_quest_3032"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, your mission will be to enter the melechar stronghold in "
"Cieradan, locate the shrine or altar dedicated to Melek, and steal the "
"unholy book of Melek. If you manage to complete this task, you will be "
"delivering a powerful blow to the core of their faith, destroying any hope "
"they might have of gaining once more the favor of Melek.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Before you enter the melechar stronghold in Cieradan, I suggest you prepare "
"yourself well. Many melechar have gathered within the Cieradan dungeon, and "
"they will not be pleased to see you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Succeeding in this mission will only the beginning. Once you have stolen the "
"unholy book of Melek, therefor considerably weakening the melechar, the "
"agents of Charybdis will launch a coordinated attack against all melechar in "
"the region. Any race that seeks to favor and blessing of the alfar god king "
"Melek, deserves only to die!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, back to the mission. The melechar stronghold is located in the Cieradan "
"dungeon complex. It is to the northeast of here. The entrance to the dungeon "
"is a hidden forest portal gate, locate among the many trees of the region. "
"This I will mark on your map.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once inside, I cannot guide you to the exact location of the altar or "
"shrine. When you have successfully found the unholy book of Melek, search "
"for the portal to exit the dungeon, and head straight for Charybdis. Deliver "
"the unholy book of Melek to Sylanae the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_3033"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search for the Rod of Bad Magic. Report to Naianir "
"Treedancer in Mir Gelien for further instructions."

msgid "start_text_quest_3034"
msgstr ""
"Among the old dusty tomes in our libraries, we discovered texts that talk "
"about strange magical occurrences similar to the fluctuations in magic many "
"spellcasters have been experiencing throughout Mirendil. The ancient texts "
"of the Serene Spire talk about a time of uncontrollable and powerful magic. "
"A time where specific areas of Mirendil came to be known as Bad Magic Areas."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Since the time of Bad Magic, many of the geographic features and regional "
"names have changed, making it difficult for us to locate these areas. Still "
"we have managed to locate a handful of the Bad Magic Areas. One of those is "
"located in Upper Eredras.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to our books, during the time of Bad Magic, a powerful wizard "
"named Damanthel started experimenting with the magic found in these areas. "
"In his many experiments, Damanthel managed to tap into the mysterious powers "
"of the Bad Magic Areas. The result was the creation of a crystal green tower "
"where a poisonous acid lake once existed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The wizard created the green crystal tower from the acid waters of the lake, "
"but with a cost to his life. The wizard could not leave the tower. He was "
"bound to it. There, locked away in his tower, the wizard Damanthel continued "
"experimenting with the effects of Bad Magic. Before Damanthel died, he "
"created a powerful item, the Rod of Bad Magic. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This powerful and dangerous artifact is locked away, somewhere among the "
"many tombs in the lowest level of the crystal green tower. We cannot allow "
"such dangerous and uncontrollable magic to fall into the wrong hands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you accept to search for the Rod of Bad Magic for the Serene Spire, "
"report to Naianir Treedancer in Mir Gelien. Naianir will fill you in on "
"further details about the tower and its many perils."

msgid "start_text_quest_3035"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Crystal Green Tower in {$j16}, and to "
"search for the Rod of Bad Magic, somewhere among its many tombs. Once you "
"have found the rod, return to Aelathil Silverleaf at the Serene Spire."

msgid "start_text_quest_3036"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the Rod of Bad Magic to Aelathil Silverleaf at the Serene Spire.You "
"have found the Rod of Bad Magic. Deliver the Rod of Bad Magic to Aelathil "
"Silverleaf at the Serene Spire, and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3037"
msgstr ""
"So, the Serene Spire is searching for a dangerous artifact, hidden somewhere "
"in the crystal green tower. I myself have ventured into the tower once, and "
"do not wish to ever go there again. There is something very unnatural about "
"that place, as if it does not belong there. Inside the tower, there are many "
"undead that haunt it. Too many. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, you say that you seek a powerful rod, hidden among the tombs of the "
"tower. Yes, the lowest level of the tower is full of tombs, as if a large "
"graveyard. Why would there be a graveyard inside a tower? Very strange "
"indeed. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The crystal green tower you seek in located northeast of here in Upper "
"Eredras. I will mark its location on your map. If the rod is hidden among "
"the tombs, just head for the lowest level of the tower. There you will find "
"many tombs."

msgid "start_text_quest_3038"
msgstr ""
"The Serene Spire has asked you to destroy six Oathbound inside the Kaerdan "
"dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3039"
msgstr ""
"Many of the scrolls and books we have here within our libraries talk about "
"the Nithron, a race of golden-skinned giants who once ruled Agon. The "
"Nithron were godlike beings who possessed abilities and magic far beyond "
"anything seen today. Among their achievements was the creations of the "
"Revenant and Oathbound.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently, a small Nithron site has been located in Kaerdan that leads into a "
"hidden dungeon complex. And although many of these hidden cave systems exist "
"throughout Agon, there is something special about this one. Inside it our "
"scouts came across parts of a Nithron built dungeon. If indeed this is a "
"Nithron dungeon, it will be the first we have come across. We would like to "
"send a group of researchers inside the Kaerdan dungeon, but first we must "
"make it safe for them to enter. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you could help the Serene Spire once more by destroying six "
"Oathbound that guard the inside of Kaerdan dungeon. Once you enter the "
"dungeon, search for the Oathbouns, destroy six of them, and then find your "
"way out. According to our scouts, there is another portal inside the dungeon "
"that leads out to the surface.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Destroy six Oathbound inside the Kaerdan dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3040"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather three units of Putrid Corpseflesh for the Serene "
"Spire."

msgid "start_text_quest_3041"
msgstr ""
"Revenants are magical creatures that were created by the Nithron. Their only "
"task is to guard the cities and secrets that the mysterious and powerful "
"Nithron have left behind, until the day of their return. The creation of "
"such powerful magical creatures is beyond anything we or any other mortal "
"race today can achieve. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have discovered revenants inside the Kaerdan dungeon, and our "
"researchers would like if it is possible for you to gather three units of "
"revenant corpseflesh from the revenants. We would like to understand how "
"exactly these revenants were created, and what magic it is that gives life "
"to these constructs."

msgid "start_text_quest_3042"
msgstr ""
"Sylanae the Councillor has asked you to visit Nairath the Mage, and help him "
"out with his work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3043"
msgstr ""
"I have received today two requests from Nairath the Mage, asking for some "
"assistance with gathering some ingredients for his enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Nobody seems to be available to help poor Nairath with his work, and I feel "
"as if I have somehow let him down. I would very much appreciate it if you "
"could find the time to visit Nairath the Mage and assist him. If you can "
"spare the time, please go and report to Nairath."

msgid "start_text_quest_3044"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather four units of Timeless Blood and two Tainted "
"Hearts for Nairath the Mage, before three hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_3045"
msgstr ""
"Dear friend, I am trying to gather various ingredients that can be used to "
"craft enchanted items, like magical weapons an armors. Fortunately, a rare "
"opportunity has presented itself. To the north of here in Roendel, Swamp "
"Hags and Trolls have been spotted. Both of these creatures can be harvest "
"for some of the materials I am looking for. The problem is that, I don't "
"know for how long these creature will remain in the region, since many will "
"want to hunt them down and collect some kind of reward.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I need is for somebody to harvest four units of Troll Blood from the "
"Trolls, and two Hag Hearts from the Swamp Hags. But this must be done soon, "
"before the hunters wipe them out completely, or drive them out of the "
"region. I would appreciate it if you could gather these ingredients for me "
"within the next three hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3046"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather three Barbed Claw for Nairath the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3047"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for gathering the Troll Blood and Hag Hearts I had requested "
"earlier. They will soon be put to good use my fellow mages, creating magical "
"items. But, there is one more ingredient that we need. Gathering this one "
"will be a very dangerous task. The ingredient is Beastman Tooth. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The is one Beastman village to the east of here in Lower Eredras, next to "
"the castle of the once powerful wizard Siledin, but you will also find more "
"Beastman camps to the northeast in Kaerdan, among the mountains.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Beastmen are one of our ancient and most hated enemies. Not as hated as the "
"alfar, but hated enough that any excuse to kill Beastmen is always welcomed. "
"I want you to go and harvest for me three Beastman Teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_3048"
msgstr ""
"Nairath the Mage has asked you to deliver his package to Riathen the Mage at "
"the Emerald Throne."

msgid "start_text_quest_3049"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I thank you for helping me gather all the materials I asked "
"for. Now I can focus on my work, which is to create enchanted weapon and "
"armors for the alliance. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one more minor thing I may ask of you. Sylanae the Councillor did "
"mention to me that you had worked for a while at Imathir with the Emerald "
"Throne. If it is in your plans to return to the Emerald Throne, could you "
"deliver a package I have here for Riathen the Mage. She is a very close and "
"good friend of mine, and I had promised her that I would collect a few "
"material she had asked for.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Don't worry, its a small package, and I do not believe it will be a burden "
"for you. So, are you returning any time soon to the Emerald Throne?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3050"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Garin Silvervault. Travel to Vinterheim and "
"report to Kanute Wayfarer."

msgid "start_text_quest_3051"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, have you ever heard of Aegin's Hall? A long tome ago, the "
"northern coast of Dvergheim was ruled by an Ice Demon called Aegin. Though "
"the Ice Demon no longer exists, it is said that many hidden artifacts, such "
"as the legendary scepter of Aegin, are hidden somewhere within Aegin's Hall."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to Vinterhein and deliver this letter to Kanute. It has "
"instruction about your next mission. I will mark Kanute's position on your "
"map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3052"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kanute Wayfarer. Kill three Hobgoblins, one "
"Windgraive and two Ogre Bosses. When you have completed the task, report to "
"Garin Silvervault in Wintercrown."

msgid "start_text_quest_3053"
msgstr ""
"Many years ago, an Ice Demon called Aegin carved out a fleeting kingdom "
"along the Frostgap coast. The demon was slain by dwarven heroes, but his "
"glacier-carved fortress remains a favored haunt of the creatures that once "
"served in his army.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Quite recently, a group of Ogre Bosses took control of {$o07} and began "
"organizing its inhabitants into a rag-tag army. The Voice of Ymir wants you "
"to strike against this gathering threat immediately, before the ogre-led "
"monsters become a threat to nearby dwarven communities.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The easiest way to reach {$o07} is to travel eastward along the coast until "
"you reach the ice bridge which connects it to the mainland. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go there and kill three Hobgoblins, one Lesser Water Elemental and two Ogre "
"Bosses. Once you have completed the mission, report your success to Garin "
"Silvervault in Wintercrown."

msgid "start_text_quest_3054"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kanute Wayfarer. Travel to Aegin's Hall and "
"search  for Aegin's Scepter. Once you have successfully retrieved the "
"scepter, bring it to Garin Silvervault in Wintercrown."

msgid "start_text_quest_3055"
msgstr "Deliver Aegin's Scepter to Garin Silvervault in Wintercrown."

msgid "start_text_quest_3056"
msgstr ""
"The Voice of Ymir is searching for the long-lost scepter of Aegin, an Ice "
"Demon who ruled the northern coast of Dvergheim until he was slain by a "
"group of dwarven adventurers. Rumors hint that the current occupants of "
"{$o07}, a group of Ogre Bosses, have located the scepter, and that they are "
"keeping it hidden in their lair while they try to figure out how to activate "
"it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir wants you to search {$o07} for the legendary scepter. Once "
"you have successfully retrieved the Aegin's scepter, bring it to Garin "
"Silvervault in Wintercrown."

msgid "start_text_quest_3057"
msgstr "Garin Silvervault has asked you to report to Nidstein the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3058"
msgstr ""
"Many legends talk about the Nithron, a race of golden-skinned giants who "
"once ruled Agon. The Nithron had build many cities across Agon, and one of "
"them is located to the south of here, in {$n11}. Nidstein the Mage  is "
"currently looking into many of the legends that talk about artifacts and "
"secrets left behind by the Nithron. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"He believes you might be able to help him in his research regarding the "
"Nithron. If you can spare the time, please go and speak with him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3059"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nidstein the Mage. Search the Nithron ruins "
"in {$n11} for Eiradan's amulet."

msgid "start_text_quest_3060"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the amulet of Eiradan to Nidstein the Mage, and claim his reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3061"
msgstr ""
"Throughout the world of Agon, artifacts have begun to appear, seemingly from "
"thin air, in the ruins left by a people called the Nithron, a race of giants "
"who ruled Agon for centuries before disappearing tracelessly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The largest Nithron in western Dvergheim lies in the region of Skaranibben. "
"According to the ancient chronicles, the Nithron warlord who once ruled "
"these ruins possessed a powerful artifact called the amulet of Eiradan.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir wants you to search the nithron ruins in {$n11} for this "
"amulet, in the hope that it may have reappeared in the castle of its old "
"owner."

msgid "start_text_quest_3062"
msgstr ""
"Nidstein the Mage has instructed you to kill four of the Oathbound that are "
"guarding the Nithron city in {$n11}, and then return with a report on their "
"strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_3063"
msgstr ""
"After centuries of silence, the Nithron ruins of Skaranibben are once again "
"patrolled by Oathbound, guardian which we until recently knew only from the "
"history books. We need to measure the threat posed by these creatures, "
"especially since the recent arrivals may prove to be a mere vanguard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Voice of Ymir want you to kill four Outhbound, then return to me with a "
"report on their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_3064"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Kill five Svartdvergir "
"Summoners located inside the dungeon in Svartvann."

msgid "start_text_quest_3065"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have discovered a portal that leads into a hidden dungeon "
"complex, one we believe to be the main stronghold of the Svartdvergir in "
"northern Dvergheim. It is in there that horrid rituals are carried out, "
"transforming dwarves into the dark servants of Sahul, the Svartdvergir. The "
"Svartdvergir Summoners are the ones that carry out these rituals, and many "
"of the summoners have been seen entering this portal. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Five Beard's Trading Company wants you to enter the Svartdvergir "
"stronghold in Svartvann, and kill five of these Svartdvergir Summoners. We "
"have not knowledge of the interior of the dungeon, so it is up to you to "
"enter, located the summoners, kill them, and return back here alive."

msgid "start_text_quest_3066"
msgstr ""
"Report to Eyvind the Merchant who is located at the trading post in "
"Evigvanger, and see how you may help with the hivekin infestation."

msgid "start_text_quest_3067"
msgstr ""
"We have received a report from one of our merchants that is located at the "
"Trading Post of Evignanger. According to the report, the region is being "
"overrun by hivekin, including the trading outpost.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The hivekin are a race of foragers, whose instincts and appetites lead them "
"to invade territories that contain large amounts of edible material. It "
"would seem that the land is not providing enough to extinguish the appetite "
"of the hivekin, and now the hivekin are attacking the caravans that are "
"passing through the region. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Five Beards Trading Company wants you to report to Eyvind the Merchant, "
"and help put an end to this problem."

msgid "start_text_quest_3068"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eyvind the Merchant. Kill eight hivekin "
"soldiers that are attacking the Trading Post in Evigvanger."

msgid "start_text_quest_3069"
msgstr ""
"The Evagvanger trading post has been here for over a hundred years. Many "
"travelers and merchant caravans stop here, to rest and hear the latest news "
"involving the trade routes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Travelers stopping here at of trading post have reported an increase in "
"attacks from hivekin. I don't know the exact cause behind these hivekin "
"attacks, but until we discover it, we must protect the trading post.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have located where most of the hivekin are gathered when not hunting down "
"caravans and travelers. I would greatly appreciate it if you could help with "
"the situation. It is mostly the hivekin soldiers that are doing the damage. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help be killing eight of the hivekin soldiers. I will mark on your "
"map where most of them have been spotted."

msgid "start_text_quest_3070"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the news to Garn Runeshield in Gemstone Reach that the Trading Post "
"in Evigvanger is now free of the hivekin attacks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3071"
msgstr ""
"I would appreciate it if you could deliver a message to Garn Runeshield in "
"Gemstone Reach. I would like to get word to the Five Beard Trading Company "
"that the Evigvanger Trading Post is now safe, and that they may allow "
"travelers to continue their traveler through the region."

msgid "start_text_quest_3072"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. Search for clues to what is "
"spawning and controlling the undead dwarves within the Otredale dungeons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3073"
msgstr ""
"You have discovered a skeleton floating above a shrine dedicated to Sahul. "
"Perhaps this shrine is somehow spawning the undead dwarves within the "
"Otretdale mine. Report this finding to Garn Runeshield."

msgid "start_text_quest_3074"
msgstr ""
"The authorities of Ymir's Tear have begun a campaign to reclaim the Otredale "
"mines. Once the pride of the northern Dvergheim, these legendary mines would "
"provide the blacksmiths with ore of the most superior quality.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"About fifty years ago, the mines where attacked by orks. Although the orks "
"where successfully repelled, all the miners died. For many years the mines "
"were abandoned, which allowed many creatures to settle in, among them the "
"kobolds. Until now, the authorities of Ymir's Tear were convinced that the "
"mines where overrun by kobolds, and that the extermination of the kobolds "
"would be enough to reclaim the mines. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately our scout made a surprising discovery. The kobolds are not the "
"main problem. Inside the eastern mines of Otredale there exists a portal. A "
"portal that leads to a dungeon complex, that was unknown to us. Our scouts "
"discovered that the dungeon complex is overrun by undead dwarves. If these "
"mines are to be reclaimed, we must discover what it is that is not allowing "
"these dead miners to rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need somebody to enter the mines any search for any clues that might give "
"us an answer as to who of what is spawning and controlling the undead "
"dwarves in Otredale. Upon discovering something that might offer insight "
"into this unnatural phenomenon, use the action button to investigate the "
"object more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_3075"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Thain Strongforge quest. Kill three of the Gray Orks that "
"have fortified themselves in Istind."

msgid "start_text_quest_3076"
msgstr ""
"The Order of the Axe has been ordered to hunt down a group of gray orks that "
"have established a base in the region of Instid, which is located southwest "
"of here. According to the report that arrived from Ymir's Tear, our mirdian "
"allies are experiencing a sudden outbreak of attacks from many gray ork "
"warbands, and have requested that we assist in any way possible. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To assist our allies in this war, will be to eliminate any gray ork warbands "
"lurking near our borders. You mission #PlayerName#, will be to travel to "
"Istind where our scouts have located one of the fortified camps, and kill "
"three gray orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3077"
msgstr ""
"Search the hobgoblin camp in Fire Hall for clues for any clues that might "
"lead to the Fire Standard hobgoblin leaders."

msgid "start_text_quest_3078"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the letter you found in the hobgoblin camp in {$q11}, with the "
"information about the Fire Standard hobgoblin leaders, to Thain Strongforge."

msgid "start_text_quest_3079"
msgstr ""
"In the region of Fire Hall, Fire Standard hobgoblin grunts have established "
"a base from where they are launching raids onto nearby dwarven communities."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hobgoblins are a militaristic race, and function within a strict military "
"hierarchy. Therefor, we believe that these hobgoblin grunts are not "
"functioning on their own, but are executing orders given from elsewhere.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Order of the Axe want you to search the hobgoblin camp in Fire Hall for "
"any clues that might lead to who might be controlling the Fire Standard "
"hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3080"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Order of the Axe. Go to the hobgoblin "
"camp in {$n12} and kill three Hobgoblin Veterans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3081"
msgstr ""
"Return to Stonevault, and inform Thain Strongforge of the letter you found "
"in possession of one of the Fire Standard Hobgoblin leaders, a letter "
"containing orders sent by the Raven Standard hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3082"
msgstr ""
"Thanks to your brave efforts, we now know that the Fire Standard Hobgoblin "
"leaders have a base in {$n12}, which is to the west of here. We will attack "
"them now, before they discover that we are on to them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Order of the Axe wants you to put an end to the activities of the Fire "
"Standard hobgoblins. We must send a clear message to them, that we are "
"smarter than them, and far more dangerous than them. We will not be "
"terrorized by a bunch of stinking hobgoblins. Go to the hobgoblin camp in "
"{$n12}, and kill three Hobgoblin Veterans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3083"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Order of the Axe. You are to go to the "
"Raven Standard camp in Istind, kill three Raven Standard Grunts, and return "
"with your assessment of their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_3084"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that after many years, the army of the Raven Standard is "
"assembling again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Raven Standard Army first appeared hundreds of years ago, somewhere on "
"the jungle continent of Yssam. It was there that a charismatic hobgoblin "
"leader succeeded in uniting the hobgoblin tribes, build a powerful kingdom, "
"and formed the legendary Raven Standard Army. For many years, the hobgoblin "
"kingdom and the Raven Standard Army was very successful, before falling "
"apart during a vicious war of succession.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Order of the Axe wants you to go and assess the strength of this Raven "
"Standard Hobgoblin Camp. This will be an extremely dangerous mission, so I "
"suggest you prepare yourself for a difficult battle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go southwest of here to Istind, and find the Raven Standard camp. Our agents "
"have already identified that the camp is occupied by the weakest members of "
"the Raven Standard Army, the Raven Standard Grunts. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task will be to kill three Raven Standard Grunts and return here with "
"your assessment of their strengths and weaknesses. If the Raven Standard "
"Army has returned, we must be prepared."

msgid "start_text_quest_3085"
msgstr ""
"After locating Blackpeak's last blade, Frostinn the Mage has requested to "
"speak with you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3086"
msgstr ""
"News of your success finding Blackpeak's last blade, is already spreading "
"throughout Stonevault. The news has also reached Frostinn the Mage, who is "
"always interested in finding legendary items and artifacts.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Frostinn is convinced she has discovered the location of another legendary "
"artifact. An item that belonged to Blackpeak's mentor, the legendary "
"blacksmith Durganon. Frostinn is hoping that you may be able to help her "
"find this item. If you can spare the time, go speak with her."

msgid "start_text_quest_3087"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Frostinn the Mage. Search within the dungeon "
"complex of Fire Hall for Durganon's Brazier. The casting of a mana missile "
"spell upon it, should reveal to you its authenticity."

msgid "start_text_quest_3088"
msgstr ""
"Return to the Stonevault, and report you discovery of Durganon's Brazier "
"within the Fire Hall dungeon, to Frostinn the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3089"
msgstr ""
"Legends talk of a dwarven master blacksmith named Durganon, who was able to "
"create weapons of the most superior quality. Durganon was one of the first "
"blacksmiths to master the secrets of fire and metal. Secrets that many "
"blacksmiths even today still struggle to master.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Blackpeak, who's last blade you successfully found as I am told, was "
"Durganon's student. In his journals, Blackpeak speaks of Durganon's many "
"superior crafting skills, and describes in detail the many tools and "
"artifacts that Durganon used. Many of those artifacts and tools and safely "
"kept here in Stonevault, but one was stolen by the dark svartdvergir. "
"Durganon's Brazier. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to Blackpeak, the origins of Durganon Brazier are unknown, but "
"what is known is that the brazier is magical. Durganon could summon the "
"magical powers of the brazier, and bestow upon his superior weapons many "
"enchantments.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A portal that leads into a complex dungeon system, has been discovered in "
"Fire Hall. A dungeon complex crawling with svartdvergir. I believe that is "
"where the brazier now exists.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Order of the Axe, and I personally, want you to search this Fire Hall "
"dungeon complex, and to find out if Durganon's Brazier is located within it. "
"It is imperative that we discover if such an importance artifact of dwarven "
"history has fallen into the hands of the svartdvergir.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Upon discovering a brazier that you believe could be Durganons Brazier, by "
"casting a mana missile spell upon it, that brazier should react. According "
"to Blackpeak's journal, you should be able to feel the magical powers of the "
"brazier when casting a mana missile spell upon it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3090"
msgstr ""
"Shulazu Nightshade has asked you to report to Ninnah the Mage in Shoal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3091"
msgstr ""
"According to a report that arrived from the Temple of the God King, Nalaeds "
"and Darkweavers have been sighted in eastern Nagast, in the Zahnal region."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"An agent of the Temple of the God King discovered a hidden portal in Zahnal "
"Nithron Ruins, that leads to an unknown until now Nithron dungeon. Inside "
"this dungeon, the agent encountered strange creatures, rare in Nagast. "
"According to the descriptions of the Temple's agent, we believe that these "
"creature could be Nalaeds and Sarlid Darkweavers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Radiant Circle is very interested in finding and examining these "
"creatures. We have contacted Ninnah the Mage in Shoal, to look into this "
"mater for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Radiant Circle would like you to go to Ninnah as its representative, and "
"to examine these creatures on its behalf."

msgid "start_text_quest_3092"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to assist Ninnah the Mage and the Radiant Circle in their "
"research. Enter the Zahnal dungeon and collect one unit of Ichor from a "
"Nalaed and one unit of Numen from a Sarlid Darkweavers."

msgid "start_text_quest_3093"
msgstr ""
"First of all let me say that is it is a honor for both of us to chosen to "
"assist the Radiant Circle in their research.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is the first time in over a hundred years that anybody has seen a Nalaed "
"or a Sarlid Darkweavers within Nagast. There are very few references in our "
"books regarding these elusive creatures, and we need to find these creatures "
"to verify that they actually are what we think they are. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"From the little information we have on these creatures, we know that both "
"the Nalaed and the Darkweavers can be harvested for ingredients that can be "
"used for enchanting. Ichor from the Nalaed and Numen from the Darkweavers. "
"So one unit of Ichor from a Nalaed and one unit of Numen from a Darkweaver, "
"will help us in certify the existence of these once forgotten creatures.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"That is your mission my friend. To enter the Zahnal dungeon, to seek the "
"Nalaeds and Sarlid Darkweavers, and harvest one unit of Ichor and one unit "
"of Numen. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, I have no knowledge of the layout of the dungeon, so once you "
"have gathered the ingredients, find you way out of the dungeon, and return "
"here to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3094"
msgstr ""
"Ninnah the Mage has asked you to kill two Nalaeds and three Sarlid "
"Darkweavers inside Zahnal Dungeon. Once you have completed the mission, "
"report to Ensharra the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_3095"
msgstr ""
"The appearance of the Nalaeds and the Sarlid Darkweavers in Nagast inside "
"the Zahnal dungeon, might have created a lot of excitement among the ranks "
"of the Radiant Circle, but the same cannot be said for the authorities of "
"Shoal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While the Radiant Circle is interested in collecting information about these "
"creatures, to further its research and knowledge, the authorities of Shoal "
"would like to use this opportunity to gather their own information on these "
"new neighbors of ours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Shoal wants to learn if these creatures could pose a possible threat to the "
"Alfar in the future. Seek out, fight, and destroy at least two Nalaeds and "
"three Sarlid Darkweavers. Once you have completed the task and left the "
"dungeon, head straight to Ensharra the Councillor, and report your "
"evaluation of their capabilities and limitations."

msgid "start_text_quest_3096"
msgstr ""
"Shulazu Nightshade has asked you to report to Sriva Ghostweb at Castle Obad "
"in Obad."

msgid "start_text_quest_3097"
msgstr ""
"Many great mages and scholars have served the Radiant Circle, but few as "
"great as Adazu Nightweaver. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Adazu Nightweaver was a magnificent researcher and a brilliant mind. Towards "
"the end of his life, Adazu Nightweaver built a grand castle, where he would "
"continue his study of magic, but also to search for many strange creatures "
"and lost artifacts. And although Adazu Nightweaver has long left this world, "
"his castle now serves as an extension to the activities of the Radiant "
"Circle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Sriva Ghostweb, one of our most promising mages, is now leading the Radiant "
"Circle's activities at Nightweaver's castle, now known as Castle Obad. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you wish, you may continue to be of service to the Radiant "
"Circle by reporting to Sriva Ghostweb at Castle Obad, which is located in "
"Obad, northwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3098"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to assist Sriva Ghostweb, to gather five Vile Horn from "
"the Crogs in Obad. When you have all the ingredients in your possession, "
"return to Sriva Ghostweb and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3099"
msgstr ""
"Castle Obad was built by the great Adazu Nightweaver, legendary Mage and "
"Scholar of the Radiant Circle. It is here that Adazu Nightweaver continued "
"his studies into the unknown depths of the mysterious world of magic until "
"the end of his days. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This castle with its libraries filled with the knowledge Adazu Nightweaver, "
"accumulated throughout his lifetime, are a vast treasure of knowledge. We "
"who are fortunate enough to be stationed here at Castle Obad, continue to "
"work and walk in the steps of Adazu Nightweaver. Be it either collecting "
"ingredients used for enchanting, researching new spells, or searching for "
"many of the hidden artifacts that a buried throughout Agon, the soul purpose "
"of all here, is to work hard and to honer the great Adazu Nightweaver.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"At the moment our researchers are experimenting with enchantments. You can "
"assist them by gathering two Quartz and one Vile Spike from the Crogs that "
"are grazing in Obad, just northeast of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_31"
msgstr ""
"You agreed to help Allan by heading South to clear the farm of at least 10 "
"Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3100"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to assist Sriva Ghostweb. Gathering six Gloomy Darktaint "
"from the arthain found in Qurjah."

msgid "start_text_quest_3101"
msgstr ""
"Adazu Nightweaver was interested in magic in all its forms. Gathering rare "
"materials for spellcasting, ingredients used for enchanting, finding "
"artifacts, were some of the thing that greatly interested him. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, there was one more. Researching and studying strange creatures beyond "
"the commonly found and normal. Mostly creatures that were the result of "
"powerful dark twisted magic. Strange mutated creatures that were never "
"encountered before. In the many books Adazu had written on strange mutated "
"and twisted creatures, there are references to the arthain. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The arthain are a paranoid and hateful race, who see all outsiders as "
"necromantic raw material. The arthain were once a peaceful and civilized "
"race, but when they lost the ability to procreate, they resorted to "
"extending their lives by using a combination of fleshcrafting and "
"necromancy. The use of these necromantic methods over centuries, has driven "
"the arthain culture to the pathetic state in which it exists today.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The only thing good about the arthain, mentioned by the great Adazu "
"Nightweaver, is that the bodies of the arthain can be harvested for Resonant "
"Stormrunes. Luckily for you, who I am sure you cannot wait to be of service "
"to the Radiant Circle and to Castle Obad, there is a group of arthain to the "
"east of here in {$j23}. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"All I ask of you is to go and harvest from the arthain three Resonant "
"Stormrunes. Of course, you'll also be doing a favor to the arthain, by "
"putting an end to their pathetic existence. Return with the  Resonant "
"Stormrunes, and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3102"
msgstr "Report to Shulgan Shadowscream, head of security at Castle Obad."

msgid "start_text_quest_3103"
msgstr ""
"Not long ago, we noticed a small group of hobgoblins wandering nearby. At "
"the beginning we didn't really pay much attention to them, since they seemed "
"to be too afraid to come anywhere near Castle Obad. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Shulgan Shadowscream, who is in charge of security here at the Castle Obad, "
"was not so keen on agreeing with our assessment of the hobgoblins, that they "
"posed no threat to us. Being the stubborn character he is, Shulgan followed "
"closely this particular group of hobgoblins for the next few days. And it "
"turned out that Shulgan was correct, in not agreeing with us that the "
"hobgoblins posed no threat to Castle Obad.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The hobgoblins have now build a well fortified camp just southwest of here, "
"and Shulgan believes it will be only a matter of time before more hobgoblin "
"start to show their ugly faces here in Obad.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I recall Shulgan saying that he could do with an able pair of hands, to help "
"him with the hobgoblins. If the Radiant Circle has trusted you as one of its "
"own, to assist us here at Castle Obad, then I believe you could be just the "
"person that Shulgan Shadowscream needs right now. I would appreciate it if "
"you could report to him, and help rid the region of these hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3104"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Shulgan Shadowscream. Kill four hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3105"
msgstr ""
"The hobgoblins have built a fort nearby, just southwest of Obad Castle. In "
"the beginning when the hobgoblins first moved into the region, not many here "
"thought that they could pose any threat to the castle. As time passed and "
"the hobgoblins built their fort, and started bringing in more military "
"equipment, it became obvious to all that the threat of a future hobgoblin "
"raid against Castle Obad was quite possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is every alfar's responsibility to preserve and protect the legacy left "
"behind by the great Adazu Nightweaver. Since you are now officially working "
"for the Radiant Circle, it is your duty to protect Castle Obad.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to do your duty, by killing four of these pathetic and ignorant "
"hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3106"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Shulgan Shadowscream. Kill three Nahdruk in "
"less then two hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3107"
msgstr ""
"Melek's divine radiance is present in all places at all times. The soul-"
"shaping radiance, which is given to all alfar by the God-King Melek, is what "
"makes the alfar the superior race they are today.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, some weak alfar who's minds cannot handle Melek's divine "
"gift, end up with their weak minds twisted and lost in total darkness. These "
"twisted weak alfar, are called the Nahdruk. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Groups of Nahdruk have been seen roaming nearby, trying to take revenge for "
"their pathetic state by attacking Castle Obad. My patience has run out with "
"these pathetic Nahdruk. I want them out of this Castle, and I want it now! "
"Find where these Nahdruk are hidden, and kill three of them in less than two "
"hours. I will mark on your map were the Nahdruk were last seen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3108"
msgstr ""
"Ensharra the Councillor has asked you to report to Tialanta the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3109"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. You have proven yourself to be truly a superior alfar. You "
"have succeed in all the tasks that were assigned to you, and have returned "
"for even more.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Tell me now. Did you feel it? That alfar superiority. Did you not enjoy "
"hunting down all those other pathetic weak races? Looking them in the eye, "
"while their crushed bodies were being drain of their life. Yes, of course "
"you did. You are a hunter, a warrior, and above all, you are alfar! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It would seem that your achievements have not gone unnoticed. Tialanta who "
"is one of the finest warriors Shoal has to show, would like to have a word "
"with you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go, and report to Tialanta the Fighter. Let's see what Tialanta might have I "
"mind for you. It isn't that often that Tialanta becomes interested in "
"somebody."

msgid "start_text_quest_3110"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. Kill five Human player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3111"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you have made quite a name for yourself here in Shoal. "
"Ensharra the Councillor speaks well about you. And from what I have heard, "
"you successfully completed all tasks that were assigned to you. Yes, you "
"definitely managed to deliver a many painful blows to the other pathetic "
"races, be it human, mirdain or even the savage mahirim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want to see you do it again, but this time I'll make it a little more "
"challenging for you. I'll give you a target and a time limit. Let us see if "
"you really are who they say you are. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go out there and kill five Humans before four hours have "
"passed. Succeed, and more challenging missions will be here waiting for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3112"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. Kill five Mirdain "
"player characters in less than four hours.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3113"
msgstr ""
"Ah, the mirdain! Tall, slender, and pathetic! I have always enjoyed hunting "
"down the mirdain. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the mirdain, it is the alfar that are the cause of their weak and "
"pathetic existence. Brainwashed by their gods for centuries now, the mirdain "
"desperately try to stop the inevitable progression of the alfar, and of "
"course that of the God King Melek. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"They can keep coming at us as much as they like. And every time we will keep "
"crushing them, and pushing them into that pathetic forest that they call "
"home.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Time for you to prove to me that you are the superior alfar they say you "
"are. Go hunt down and kill five Mirdain before four hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_3114"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. Kill five Mahirim "
"player characters within four hours.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3115"
msgstr ""
"The Mahirim, this race of wolf-like predator seems to be growing confident "
"with every passing day. Although it has not been that long from when the "
"mahirim were roaming the Tribelands as wolves, I must applaud their effort "
"in trying to evolve into a civilized race.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts are reporting that the mahirim have began sending raiding parties "
"inside our borders of lately.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is very arrogant of them, not to mention stupid too, that the mahirim "
"could believe that with the little experience they have, can pose a threat "
"to the superior alfar. But what can you expect from this semi-intelligent "
"race of two-legged beasts, that is desperately trying to differentiate "
"itself from its quite recent primal past.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hunt these animals down, and show them who the true predators are! You have "
"four hours to succeed in killing four Mahirim."

msgid "start_text_quest_3116"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. Kill five Ork player "
"characters in less than four hours.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3117"
msgstr ""
"You've seen them before. Big, slow, ugly and extremely stupid. I am "
"referring to the orks, that swamp-loving race that live only for the thrill "
"of battle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"They are convinced that under the guidance of there ever sleeping dragon "
"god, and through the use of pure brute strength, they will eventually concur "
"all of Agon, while enslaving all the other races including the superior "
"alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Of course you and me both know that the only race that will eventually "
"concur all of Agon are the alfar. And I suggest that we begin by having you "
"kill five Orks in less than four hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3118"
msgstr "Aeshanta Darkspire has asked that you report to Hanthar Blackfrost."

msgid "start_text_quest_3119"
msgstr ""
"A few days ago I received letter arrived from Hanthar Blackfrost, who is a "
"very talented mage that works very closely with the Harn Mandean. Groups of "
"Nahdruk have been seen beyond the western borders of Nagast. Although "
"Hanthar does not speak of some imminent danger, I still want you to go to "
"Hanthar Blackfrost and assess the situation.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hanthar Blackfrost is located in {$k22}, which is to the southwest of here. "
"I will mark his location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3120"
msgstr "You have accepted to kill six Nahdruk for Hanthar Blackfrost."

msgid "start_text_quest_3121"
msgstr ""
"It has been a few years since anybody has seen any Nahdruk in these parts. "
"But, have you ever heard of the Nahdruk? The Nahdruk, also called the god-"
"cursed, are those unfortunate alfar who's minds could not cope with Melek's "
"soul-shaping radiance. These weak alfar, who cannot accept Melek's soul-"
"shaping radiance, do not deserve to live. They are an insult to all of us."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you understand, I have a very low tolerance for the weak, especially if "
"the weak are alfar. And so should you! So my dear #PlayerName#, do me a "
"favor and kill six of these weak Nahdruk. Succeed, and you will be rewarded "
"for your efforts.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Based on eyewitness reports, Nahdruk have been spotted hiding in two of the "
"Moradar regions. {$k21} and {$j22}. Both of these positions I will mark on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3122"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hanthar Blackfrost. Gather five units of "
"Mystical Eye."

msgid "start_text_quest_3123"
msgstr ""
"One of the most bizarre creatures found on Agon must be the bulbous floating "
"Evil Eye. This floating eyeball, with its many ever-scouting eyes can be "
"quite a challenging foe. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Evil Eye is a master of magic, and uses powerful spells that can send "
"the bravest of warriors running for their life, when not well prepared.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Groups of Evil Eyes are known to exist in the Moradar regions. One group to "
"the north in {$k21}, and another to the west in {$j22}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Evil Eyes can be harvested for some of the most rare materials. "
"Materials that can be used for creating powerful enchantments. That is what "
"makes these bizarre creatures so interesting and well sorted out by many "
"enchanters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I want is you to harvest for me two units of Evil Eye Bile."

msgid "start_text_quest_3124"
msgstr "Hanthar Blackfrost has asked you to bring him Eight Elemental Quartz."

msgid "start_text_quest_3125"
msgstr ""
"Recently, a group of Eodrin moved into {$k22}, just to the east of here. "
"These insane monsters will attack all other creatures on sight. Wildly "
"flailing their claw-like arms, they mindlessly plow into their victims.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, like many of the strange and dangerous monsters that exist throughout "
"Agon, the Eodrin can also be harvested for superior materials that can be "
"used for enchanting. And now is an excellent opportunity to harvest these "
"materials from the Eodrin, before they disappear from  the region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I ask of you is to go and harvest for me two Eodrin Eyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3126"
msgstr ""
"Hanthar Blackfrost has asked you to deliver a package to Shulazu Nightshade "
"of the Radiant Circle."

msgid "start_text_quest_3127"
msgstr ""
"Many times has the Radiant Circle supported me here with my research "
"projects. So, it is only correct that I and the Harn Mandean show our "
"appreciation with a little gift. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would ask of you #PlayerName#, to deliver a package I have here to the "
"Radiant Circle. The Radiant Circle is located northeast of here in Dun "
"Amsharra. Once you arrive at the Radiant Circle, seek out Shulazu Nightshade."

msgid "start_text_quest_3128"
msgstr ""
"Hanthar Blackfrost has requested that you kill two Gnoll Butchers that can "
"be found in {$k22}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3129"
msgstr ""
"Gnolls have lived in {$k22} for many years and have never been a problem, "
"until recently with the arrival of the Gnoll Butchers. With the addition of "
"the Gnoll Butchers among their ranks, one of the strongest of all gnolls, "
"the attitude of the gnolls here in {$k22} has begun to change. With the "
"Gnoll Butchers here, the weaker gnolls have begun to grow bolder and more "
"violent. It is only a mater of time before the gnolls decide to storm into "
"my house.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to kill two of these deadly Gnoll Butchers. That should be enough "
"to calm down the gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_3130"
msgstr "Ordgrim the Councillor has asked you to report to Hildr the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3131"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that your success in dealing with the orks did not go "
"unnoticed. Hildr who is one of the finest warriors in Ymir's Tear, has "
"request to meet you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Why don't you go and report to Hildr. I too am curious to see what challenge "
"she has in mind for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3132"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hildr the Fighter. Kill five Mahirim player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3133"
msgstr ""
"Feral, primitive and fairly young as a race, yes, it is the savage mahirim I "
"speak of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These savage and violent neighbors of ours are becoming a serious problem. "
"Their lack of experience as a race, combined with their hunger to grow and "
"to concur, has resulted in an increase of pointless skirmishes between our "
"scouts and their raiding parties along our borders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mahirim are adjusting very quickly to modern warfare, and are now "
"ranking among the most difficult enemies are fearless warriors have lately "
"faced. Many of our agents and scouts are now out there fending off the "
"mahirim raiding parties lurking at our borders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for you to prove to me all that Ordgrim the Councillor has said. "
"That you #PlayerName#, are a very capable and resourceful individual and a "
"very loyal ally. I want you to go and hunt down five mahirim before four "
"hours have passed. Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3134"
msgstr ""
"Hildr the Fighter has asked you to report to Torgard the Fighter in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_3135"
msgstr ""
"Three are the races of the alliance, the dwarves, the mirdain and the "
"humans. In the many years I've been in the alliance, and in the many battles "
"I have seen, I have met many good and brave people, and made many good "
"friends. Among those good friends that I would give my life for is Torgard, "
"a human fighter. Torgard is possible one of the bravest humans I have ever "
"met, and his loyalty to his race and the alliance comes second to none.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Torgard and I share the same views when it comes to combat techniques, "
"strategies of the battlefield, and above all, the same passion for hunting "
"down are enemies. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Torgard can be found in the human capital of Sanguine, a beautiful city "
"surrounded by water and beautiful rich lands. Visiting Sanguine is always a "
"reward itself. I will mark on your map where you can find Torgard. Should "
"you decide to ever visit Sanguine, tell Torgard how you successfully passed "
"my little challenge, and he might put you to the test."

msgid "start_text_quest_3136"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Torgard the Fighter. Kill five Ork player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3137"
msgstr ""
"Welcome I am Torgard, a member of the fighters guild here in Sanguine.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is very interesting to hear that you have successfully completed Hildr's "
"test. She must think very likely of you, if she has asked of you to visit "
"me. I have battled many times next to Hildr in the past, and I can say that "
"she is a very skillful fighter, even for a short female dwarf.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But enough with all the small talk. As with all the member races of the "
"alliance, we too are constantly at war with our neighbors. It would seem "
"that this is the fate of the good races. Always to battle the dark and evil "
"races of Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am sure you've seen them and done battle with them before. Too much brawn, "
"not enough brain. It is the orks of Morak I am referring to. The orks of "
"Morak are a crude race, full of evil and violence. Nothing good can be "
"expected from them.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go and hunt down five orks before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3138"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Torgard the Fighter. Kill five Alfar player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3139"
msgstr ""
"There is one other enemy, which I am very much aware of that is the most "
"hated enemy to all mirdain. It is the alfar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These creature, who's souls are  filled only with darkness, are probably the "
"most evil of all races upon Agon. Their minds and souls completely twisted "
"by their evil god Melek, have made the alfar a race beyond any reasoning and "
"logic. Even the violent and savage ork and mahirim are at war with the "
"alfar. That is how evil these creatures are.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am aware of the history, and the many wars between the mirdain and the "
"alfar, but mercia too has seen many battles between the humans and the "
"alfar. But with the divine guidance of our god Auros, and the help of our "
"allies, we will always repel every alfar attack, and keep our lands safe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to hunt down the alfar, and help us rid or lands of "
"these filthy presence. Kill five alfar before four hours have passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_3140"
msgstr "Sylanae the Councillor has asked you to report to Galien the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3141"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that your success in dealing with the mahirim did not go "
"unnoticed. Galein who is one of the finest warriors in Charybdis, has "
"request to meet you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Why don't you go and report to Galien. I too am curious to see what "
"challenge he has in mind for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3142"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Galien the Fighter. Kill five Alfar player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3143"
msgstr ""
"The alfar! Short, skinny, and made only of pure evil. I truly do hate them "
"all! The alfar are our worst enemy. They are obsessed with us mirdain. Their "
"hatred and jealousy is beyond logic. It is if their only goal in life is to "
"kill all mirdain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Brainwashed and twisted completely by their evil god Melek, the alfar are a "
"race beyond any logic and reasoning.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For centuries the alfar have been coming to us wave after wave, trying to "
"destroy our homeland, the beloved Mirendil forest. But we are not helpless, "
"weak, or afraid. With the divine guidance of Myrthai and Lorathai, and the "
"help of our loyal allies, we will always repel every alfar attack and raid, "
"and keep sending them crawling back into their hole in Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for you to prove to me all that Sylanae the Councillor has said. "
"That you #PlayerName#, are one extremely skillful human and a very loyal "
"ally. I want you to go and hunt down five alfar before four hours have "
"passed. This is the challenge I have for you. Succeed, and you be well "
"rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3144"
msgstr ""
"Galien the Fighter has asked you to report to Hildr the Fighter at Ymir's "
"Tear."

msgid "start_text_quest_3145"
msgstr ""
"The alliance consists of Mirdain, Human and Dwarves. Within this alliance, I "
"have met many good people, and made many good friends. Among these good "
"friends is Hildr, a dwarven female fighter that can stand up to the best of "
"warriors throughout the alliance. Her fighting skills are extraordinary, and "
"her loyalty to her race and the alliance comes second to none.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hildr, is always interested in meeting superb warriors as yourself, but also "
"putting them to the test.  If your path ever does bring you anywhere near "
"the dwarven land of Dverfheim, I want you to go visit her.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can find Hildr in the dwarven capital of Ymir's Tear, an extraordinary "
"city build completed underground. Visiting Ymir's Tear is always a reward "
"itself. I will mark on your map where you can find Hildr, if you decide to "
"ever visit Ymir's Tear and be put to the test."

msgid "start_text_quest_3146"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hildr the Fighter. Kill five Ork player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3147"
msgstr ""
"Welcome, I am Hildr a member of the fighters guild here in Ymir's Tear.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is very interesting to hear that you have successfully passed Galien's "
"test. He must think very likely of you, if he has asked of you to visit me. "
"I have battled many times next to Galien in the past, and I can say that he "
"is a very skillful fighter, even for a tall thin mirdain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, enough with all the pleasant talk. As with any other member race of the "
"alliance, we too are constantly at war with our neighbors. It would seem "
"that this is the fate of the good races. Always under attack by the dark "
"powers of Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am sure you've seen them and done battle with them before. A pity that "
"their brains do not match their strength. I am talking about the orks. "
"Strong, but dumb.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go and hunt down five ork before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3148"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hildr the Fighter. Kill five Mahirim player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3149"
msgstr ""
"It looks like I might have underestimated you. Maybe the orks were not much "
"of a challenge for you. As I said, they might be strong, but they are not "
"that bright. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I didn't expect you to complete the previous challenge, but it would seem "
"that Galien was right about you. You are one very capable human my friend. "
"The alliance can definitely do with more like yourself.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like to give you one more challenge. To the southwest of Dvergheim "
"are the Tribelands, home of the mahirim. The mahirim are a young and "
"unexperienced race, but their hunger for power combined with their physical "
"attributes, are slowly transforming this fairly young race into a power to "
"reckoned with.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill five mahirim in less than four hours is the challenge I have for you "
"this time. Do you have what it takes #PlayerName#?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3150"
msgstr "Allan the Councillor has asked you to report to Torgard the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3151"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that your success in dealing with the alfar did not go "
"unnoticed. Torgard who is one of the finest warriors in Sanguine, has "
"request to meet you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Why don't you go and report to Torgard. I too am curious to see what "
"challenge he has in mind for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3152"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Torgard the Fighter. Kill five Ork player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3153"
msgstr ""
"Brutes, bullies and nothing more. That is all they are, and all they will "
"ever be. A barbaric race they are, doomed to never advance. Never to come "
"out of the darkness and become civilized. Forever will they be stuck in "
"their crude ways. For a culture that relies only on war, nothing good awaits "
"them. It is the orks of Morak I am referring to. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many of our brave agents and scouts are out there now, defending our lands, "
"fighting off the ork raiding parties lurking at our borders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for you to prove to me all that Allan the Councillor has said. "
"That you #PlayerName#, are a very capable and resourceful individual and a "
"very loyal ally. I want you to go and hunt down five ork before four hours "
"have passed. Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3154"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to report to Galien the Fighter in "
"Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3155"
msgstr ""
"Mirdain, Human and Dwarves are the three races that make up the alliance. "
"Within this alliance, I have met many interesting people, and made many good "
"friends. Good friends such as Galien, a mirdain fighter that can stand up to "
"the best of fighters throughout the alliance. His fighting skills are "
"extraordinary, his accuracy with the bow is legendary, and his loyalty to "
"his race and the alliance comes second to none.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Galien is always interested in meeting brave warriors as yourself, and "
"putting them to the test.  If your path ever does bring you anywhere near "
"Mirendil forest, home of the mirdain, I suggest you to go visit Galien.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Galien can be found in the mirdain capital of Charybdis, a beautiful city "
"built in the heart of the ancient Miredil forest. Visiting Charybdis, is "
"always a reward itself. I will mark on your map where you can find Galien, "
"if you decide to ever visit Charybdis and be put to the test by one of the "
"most experienced fighters in the alliance."

msgid "start_text_quest_3156"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Galien the Fighter. Kill five Mahirim player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3157"
msgstr ""
"Welcome I am Galien, a member of the fighters guild here in Charybdis.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is very interesting to hear that you have successfully completed "
"Torgard's test. He must think very likely of you, if he has asked of you to "
"visit me. I have battled many times next to Torgard in the past, and I can "
"say that he is a very skillful fighter, and a valuable ally to have.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But enough with all the small talk. As with all the member races of the "
"alliance, we too are constantly at war with our neighbors. It would seem "
"that this is the fate of the good races. Always to battle the dark and evil "
"powers of Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am sure you've seen them and done battle with them before. Savage, "
"primitive and extremely violent. It is the mahirim of the Tribelands I am "
"referring to. The mahirim are a young and unexperienced race, but their "
"hunger for power combined with their physical attributes, has resulted in an "
"increase of pointless skirmishes between our scouts and their raiding "
"parties along our borders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go and hunt down five mahirim before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3158"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Galien the Fighter. Kill five Alfar player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3159"
msgstr ""
"There is another enemy, one that is the most hated of all. One that we have "
"been at war with for centuries. The dark and sinister alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"No other race on Agon is as dark and evil as the alfar. Brainwashed and "
"twisted completely by their evil god Melek, the alfar are a race beyond any "
"logic and reasoning. They are obsessed with us mirdain. Their hatred and "
"jealousy is beyond logic. It is if their only goal in life is to kill all "
"that is mirdain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For centuries the alfar have been coming to us wave after wave, trying to "
"destroy our homeland, the beloved Mirendil forest. But we are not helpless, "
"weak, or afraid. With the divine guidance of Myrthai and Lorathai, and the "
"support of our loyal allies, we will always repel every alfar attack and "
"raid, and keep sending them crawling back into their hole in Nagast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for you to prove to me all that Torgard has said. It is time to "
"honor your proud race. It is time to honor the alliance. #PlayerName#, I "
"want you to go and hunt down five alfar before four hours have passed. This "
"is the challenge I have for you. Succeed, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3160"
msgstr "Tivasta the Councillor has asked you to report to Cyreia the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3161"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that your success in dealing with the alfar and mirdain has "
"not gone unnoticed. There are many who are talking about you, and among them "
"is Cyreia, one of the finest warriors in Red Moon who has request to meet "
"you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like for you to go and report to Cyreia. I too am curious to see "
"what she wants with you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3162"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Cyreia the Fighter. Kill five Dwarven player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3163"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you have made quite a name for yourself here in Red Moon. "
"Tivasta the Councillor speaks well about you. And from what I have heard, "
"you successfully dealt with both the weak and miserable mirdain and the dark "
"and twisted alfar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want to make things a little more challenging for you this time. I'll give "
"you a target and a time limit. Let us see if you really are who they say you "
"are. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the northeast of the Tribelands is Dvergheim, land of the dwarves. These "
"short stubborn neighbors of ours, are known to never back away from a "
"challenge. Always battle ready, the dwarves of Dvergheim are a very tough "
"and resilient race.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go out there and kill five Dwarves before four hours have "
"passed. Succeed, and more challenging missions will be here waiting for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3164"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Cyreia the Fighter. Kill five Mirdain player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3165"
msgstr ""
"You have fought them before and you have return victorious. It is the "
"mirdain I am talking about. Yes, that tall, slender and weak tree hugging "
"race, that cowardly hide within their forest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, do not let their appearance fool you. As weak as they might seem, they "
"are one of the most experienced and oldest of the races on Agon. That alone "
"makes them quite deadly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, time moves on, and now it is time for both ork and mahirim to rule. I "
"want you to go and hunt down five mirdain before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded"

msgid "start_text_quest_3166"
msgstr ""
"Cyreia the Fighter has asked you to return to Flaming Skull and to report to "
"Aksmaster the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3167"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName# you have proven your worth to me, and to the alliance. I am "
"pleased we have such capable and dedicated ork allies.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are few orks that I have met that stand up to your standards my "
"friend. Among them is Aksmastar, a true master of the battlefield.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Aksmastar can always be found in the ork capital of Flaming Skull. If you "
"ever decide to return to Morak, I suggest you pay my dear friend  Aksmastar "
"a visit in Flaming Skull. Tell him that I put you to the test. I am sure "
"that he would be interested to hear your stories, and might even have "
"something installed for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3168"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmaster the Fighter. Kill five Human player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3169"
msgstr ""
"It is very interesting to hear that you have successfully passed Cyreia's "
"test. She must think very likely of you, if she has asked of you to return "
"to Flaming Skull and visit me. I have battled many times next to Cyreia in "
"the past, and I can say that she is a very skillful fighter, and a loyal "
"ally of the orks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time for you to prove to me all the Cyreia has said. That you "
"#PlayerName#, are one extremely skillful and capable ork. I am aware that "
"you have fought them in the past, but I'll just add the same rules Cyreia "
"had put in her little challenges.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go and hunt down five humans before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this for now, and we will see what else you can do."

msgid "start_text_quest_3170"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmaster the Fighter. Kill five Alfar player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3171"
msgstr ""
"Short, skinny, and completely disillusioned. It is the alfar I am referring "
"to. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It has been reported that the alfar raids within Morak have increased in the "
"past weeks. It would seem that we have been to soft with these pests of "
"Nagast. Something we must correct.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A fear is slowly starting to spread among our villages, the fear of the "
"alfar. This is total nonsense. This is an outrage. This is a joke! Let us "
"see who really is the most feared race of all. Of course you and me know "
"that is it us, the mighty orks of Morak, but the alfar seem they need to "
"discover this out the hard way. And we need to send a clear message to our "
"people, that the alfar are nothing to be feared about.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go and hunt down five alfar before four hours "
"have passed. Succeed, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3172"
msgstr ""
"Izkruul the Councillor has asked you to report to Aksmastar the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3173"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that your success in dealing with the alfar and the humans has "
"not gone unnoticed. There are many who are already talking about you, and "
"among them is Aksmaster the Fighter, who is one of the finest warriors in "
"Flaming Skull and a member of the fighters guild. He has requested to meet "
"you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go report to Aksmaster the Fighter. It is not that often that somebody grabs "
"his attention."

msgid "start_text_quest_3174"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmaster the Fighter. Kill five Dwarven "
"player characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3175"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, many are those who are talking about you here in Flaming "
"Skull, and among them Izkruul the Councillor. The Councillor speaks well "
"about you and praises your skills, especially for the way you dealt with the "
"humans of Mercia and the alfar of Nagast. All this is very impressive, but I "
"would like to see something more before we make a hero out of you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the northwest of Morak you will find Dvergheim, land of the dwarves. "
"These short stubborn neighbors of ours, are known to never back away from a "
"challenge. Always battle ready, the dwarves of Dvergheim are one of the "
"toughest races on Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I want you to do, is to hunt down and kill five Dwarves in less than "
"four hours. Manage this feat, and we might see if you have what it takes to "
"be called a hero."

msgid "start_text_quest_3176"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmaster the Fighter. Kill five Human player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3177"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you managed to kill in less than four hours five of those "
"stubborn tough dwarves. Maybe there is something to you after all. But, "
"allow me to keep my doubts. I have one more challenge for you. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the south of Morak we have Mercia, land of the humans. These humans have "
"become a thorn in the side of the alliance. Together with their allies the "
"dwarves and the mirdain, the humans have grown bold and confident, and have "
"begun to loose their fear of the orks of Morak, and soon the mahirim of the "
"Tribelands. It is time to put the fear back into these humans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to hunt down five humans before four hours have passed. Do this, "
"and I will acknowledge your skills. Show me that the mahirim are truly the "
"powerful allies they say they are."

msgid "start_text_quest_3178"
msgstr ""
"Aksmaster the Fighter has asked you to return to Red Moon and to report to "
"Cyreia the Fighter"

msgid "start_text_quest_3179"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, you have proven your worth to me and to the alliance. I am "
"honored to have met such a brave and dedicated mahirim. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have met a many mahirim within the alliance, but only a handful have "
"managed to impress me and gain my appreciation. Among them is Cyreia the "
"Fighter, a female mahirim who I have fought next to many times on the "
"battlefield. Cyreia is a true warrior and a loyal friend.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cyreia can always be found in the mahirim capital of Red Moon. Like me, she "
"too is a member of the fighters guild. You should be proud to have such "
"individuals such as Cyreia, among your kind.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If your path ever leads you back to the Tribelands, seek out Cyreia in Red "
"Moon. Tell her that I put you to the test. I am sure that she would be "
"interest to hear your stories, and might even have something installed for "
"you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3180"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Cyreia the Fighter. Kill five Mirdain player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3181"
msgstr ""
"So, you've had the honor of meeting Aksmaster, one of the finest warriors in "
"Flaming Skull, and one of the bravest orks I have ever met. I am pleased to "
"hear that you successfully completed the missions Aksmaster gave you. You "
"have shown our ork allies what it means to be mahirim. You have done well."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, I too would like to see what it is that impressed Aksmaster so much. "
"You wouldn't mind if I put you to the test now, would you?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You have fought them before and you have return victorious. It is the "
"mirdain I am referring to. Yes, that tall, slender, weak tree hugging race, "
"that cowardly hide within their forest. But, do not let their appearance "
"fool you. As weak as they might seem, they are one of the oldest races on "
"Agon, and that alone makes them dangerous. But time has moved on, and now it "
"is time for both ork and mahirim to rule. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go and hunt down five mirdain before four hours have passed. "
"Manage this feat for me, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3182"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Cyreia the Fighter. Kill five Alfar player "
"characters before four hours have passed.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3183"
msgstr ""
"The alfar are a race of pure evil, who live in darkness and paranoia. Coming "
"out of their holes in Nagast, the alfar are slowly becoming the plague of "
"Agon. Their only goal, and that of their twisted god Melek, is to destroy "
"and concur everything until the whole of Agon becomes a total wasteland, "
"similar to that of Nagast. The alfar are incapable of appreciating anything. "
"From the beauty of the Tribelands, to the undeniable growing strength of the "
"mahirim race.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It seems that we have a misunderstanding here. Because the alfar have found "
"their neighbors the mirdain and the humans weak and submissive, they somehow "
"believe the same applies for us the mahirim. This could not be more farther "
"that the truth. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Enough with these short, skinny and extremely annoying and arrogant alfar. "
"They need to be taught what it means to underestimate the mahirim. They need "
"to learn, who the weak are. They will came to understand, that it is they "
"who are going to be hunted from now on.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to kill five alfar in before four hours have "
"passed. Succeed, and you be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3184"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather six Gloomy Darktaint for Brehan Thornbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3185"
msgstr ""
"I have been researching a new spell together with my dear friend Elena the "
"Mage of the Sons of Riada. Unfortunately, I have come to a point were to be "
"able to complete the spell, I need an ingredient, and that is the Sarlid "
"Bile. I believe you can help me. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You could go and gather for me Six Sarlid Bile from the Arthain, which can "
"be found in Issanhal to the southwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3186"
msgstr ""
"Brehan Thornbrook has asked you to gather two units of Ghostly Darktaint."

msgid "start_text_quest_3187"
msgstr ""
"There are many monsters that exist on Agon. Some of them are very common, "
"and easily found, were others are very rare. Ghosts are one of those rarely "
"found throughout Agon. And where there is a verified sighting of ghosts, "
"researches as myself are always very keen to study them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Ghosts can be harvest for Ghostly Darktaint, an ingredients that is not easy "
"to come by. If you would be willing to gather for me two units of Ghostly "
"Darktaint, I will reward you well for your efforts. The ghosts have been "
"last sighted in {$x21}, to the east of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3188"
msgstr ""
"Iain Deepwode has asked you to deliver a scroll to Brehan Thornbook, to help "
"the Sons of Riada decipher it and locate a powerful artifact."

msgid "start_text_quest_3189"
msgstr ""
"Brehan Thornbrook is one of mercia's finest, if not the finest, when it "
"comes to deciphering and translating ancient texts. His knowledge of Agon's "
"ancient and mysterious past is vast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Brehan is an old and wise mage that works very closely with the Sons of "
"Riada, but also with many other scholars and researcher throughout mercia."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll for a while now, one that "
"will reveal to us the location of a powerful but dangerous artifact. We do "
"not wish for this scroll to fall into the wrong hands. But, as mush as we "
"try, we cannot decipher it. The Sons of Riada are in need of Brehan's "
"services once more. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# deliver this scroll to Brehan Thornbrook. It is very important "
"that Brehan does decipher the scroll, and locate the artifact. I will mark "
"his location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3190"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather two units of Elemental Cinder for Brehan "
"Thornbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3191"
msgstr ""
"The writings upon this scroll are definitely of a long forgotten and ancient "
"language. No wonder the Sons of Riada are finding it difficult to decipher "
"it. But no need to worry now. I will decipher it, of that I am sure.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will need specific ingredients to cast a spell that will help me decipher "
"these ancient writings. One of the ingredients I will need is Elemental "
"Cinder. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Elemental Cinder can be harvested from creatures of the element of fire. "
"Fortunately for us, to the east of here in {$v21}, Lesser Fire Elemental can "
"by found near the still active volcano. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go and gather for me two units of Elemental "
"Cinder from the Lesser Fire Elementals. Be careful not to get burnt."

msgid "start_text_quest_3192"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver a small sack with rare enchanting ingredients "
"to Niane the Arcanist in Sanguine. One you have delivered the ingredients, "
"return back to Brehan Thornbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3193"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the pouch with the enchanting ingredients to Niane the "
"Arcanist. Return to Brehan Thornbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3194"
msgstr ""
"It will take me a while to complete the deciphering of the scroll. Until I "
"complete my task, there is something that you could do for me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Deliver this small sack with rare enchanting ingredients I have collected "
"for Niane the Arcanist in Sanguine. Once you have delivered the package, "
"return back here so we may continue our work. I should have by then "
"completed my work, and the location of this artifact should be known to us."

msgid "start_text_quest_3195"
msgstr ""
"Search the Bladethorpe Nithron ruins for the King, the first of the guardian "
"statues, and cast a mana missile spell upon him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3196"
msgstr ""
"Search the Bladethorpe Nithron ruins for the Defender, the second of the "
"guardian statues and battle him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3197"
msgstr ""
"Search the Bladethorpe Nithron ruins for the Scholar, the third of the "
"guardian statues, and drain him of his power."

msgid "start_text_quest_3198"
msgstr ""
"Return to the King, the first of the guardian statues, and retrieve the "
"Healing Gem."

msgid "start_text_quest_3199"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully found the Healing Gem. Return to Brehan Thornbrook and "
"give him the gem."

msgid "start_text_quest_32"
msgstr ""
"Greetings!  I'm Allan, head of the Sanguine City Council.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the months since the minions of the dark mage Oncylus began spreading out "
"from the middle of Agon, the various races have declared a ceasefire to "
"their age old blood feud.  Since then, Sanguine has become a hub of refugees "
"fleeing the violence, and we've been struggling to keep up with feeding "
"everyone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"On top of that, I just received word that a party of Goblins is raiding the "
"farm straight South of here.  Can you believe it?  Goblins haven't been this "
"close to Sanguine in a generation!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You look sturdier and more capable than most coming through here, could you "
"help us out?  I've been authorized to offer payment to anyone who provides "
"the city with invaluable services during these dark times, and we'd be in "
"your debt if you could thin out this raiding party so our farmers could get "
"back to work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3200"
msgstr ""
"I have managed to decipher most of the ancient writings. The writings talk "
"about an powerful  ancient artifact called the Ring of Power. This powerful "
"artifact was created many centuries ago, only after a powerful Demon Lord "
"successfully combined the powers of two other artifacts together, that of "
"the Demon Ring and the Healing Gem.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Demon Ring would enhance its possessor with physical strength and the "
"ability to cast powerful necromantic spells, while the Healing Gem would "
"bless its owner with many immunities to diseases and the ability to cast "
"powerful healing spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"With the Ring of Power in his possession, the Demon Lord brought pain and "
"suffering to vast parts of central Agon, until a Nithron King decided to put "
"an end to the Demon Lord's reign. The Nithron King together with his army "
"defeated the Demon Lord, and took the Ring of Power. It is written that this "
"wise Nithron King decided to separated the gem from the ring. He understood "
"that the power of the ring was so destructive, that no mortal would ever be "
"able to control so much power without becoming corrupted.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Demon Ring was hidden somewhere in northwest Agon, possibly somewhere in "
"today's Mahirim Tribelands, while the Healing Gem is hidden very close to "
"Mercia, in the region of {$x20}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Healing Gem is guarded by three of the many Nithron statues that are "
"found in the Nithron city in {$x20}. It is these three guardian statues "
"alone that hold the secret to its location. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"On the writing on the scroll, I have managed to uncovered the location of "
"the first of the guardian statues, also referred to as the King. You must go "
"to this statue, the first of the three and cast a mana missile spell upon "
"it. Doing this will reveal to the caster of the spell a series of steps to "
"the location of the gem. Their isn't must more that I can discover from the "
"ancient writings. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, it is up to you, to follow the signs and find the gem. I can "
"help you by pointing out to you that the King, the first of the guardian "
"statues, is the only statue that shows a noble nithron warrior standing in "
"front of a lion. That statue is the King.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, a mana missile spell cast upon the statue should bring you closer "
"to the location of the gem."

msgid "start_text_quest_3201"
msgstr ""
"Maria Hawksgate has asked you to report to Colman Ashbourne in Carpendale."

msgid "start_text_quest_3202"
msgstr ""
"Over the years, many mercians have faithfully served within the ranks of the "
"White Order. Many who put the greater good of mercia and that of our allies "
"above their own needs. Many like Colman Ashbourne. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately a serious injury combined with the loss of his friends, "
"contributed in Colman's decision to retire and put an end to his life within "
"the White Order. Colman Ashbourne never managed to forgive himself for the "
"loss of his friends. Although he no longer serves among the ranks of the "
"White Order, he still continues to provide valuable services to the White "
"Older and to all mercians from his keep in Carpendale.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Colman Ashbourne has informed the White Order that groups of Ogres have been "
"attacking and robbing our people that are traveling through Brockmoore. I "
"would ask of you to go report to Colman Ashbourne in Carpendale, and help "
"drive these Ogres out of our lands."

msgid "start_text_quest_3203"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill four of the Ogres that are attacking travelers "
"passing though Brockmoore."

msgid "start_text_quest_3204"
msgstr ""
"The region of Brockmoore has been overrun with groups of bandit Ogres that "
"have been robbing and terrorizing anybody traveling through the region. "
"People are simple now afraid to travel through Brockmoore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We can not allow these groups of bandit Ogres to terrorize and rob simple "
"people who are traveling through our lands. If you wish to help, travel to "
"Brockmoore and kill at least four of these bandit Ogres. #PlayerName#, help "
"us make these lands safe again."

msgid "start_text_quest_3205"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to take revenge for Colman Ashbourne. Kill four revenants "
"in less then four hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3206"
msgstr ""
"Years ago when I was still a member of the White Order, I had accepted a "
"mission to accompany some elders to a ruin site in {$u16}. These elders were "
"scholars and researches of the White Order, well respected by all, but above "
"all very good friends of mine. It was supposed to be a simple mission. The "
"elders wanted to travel to {$u16} to explore an old ruin site, and I was to "
"keep the out of harms way.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, our visit to the ancient site did not go as planed. Once "
"there, we were greeted by revenants, ancient guardian constructed left "
"behind be the once powerful Nithron. Why the revenants were there still "
"remains a mystery, since the site was not of Nithron origin.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The revenants proved to be too much for me. I was completely overwhelmed and "
"suffered many serious injuries. Although I survived the attack, non of the "
"elders survived. It was a slaughter. After that mission I left the White "
"Order in shame. I can still hear their scream every night.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To put it simply down to you, I want revenge. I want some serious pain "
"inflicted onto those revenants. And although there are many within the White "
"Order that do not agree with my feelings, I want revenge!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four revenants. One for each of the elders. One for each of my friends! "
"Do this for me, and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3207"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Colman Ashbourne. Kill three Ork player "
"characters."

msgid "start_text_quest_3208"
msgstr ""
"In the many years I spent with the White Order, I took part in many battles "
"defending our lands from those that wished to harm us. Among those many "
"battles, I always looked forward to when it was time to battle the ork.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Their ugly faces and their awful smells were just enough to make the most "
"peace-loving of all mercians to want to kill them without a second thought."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The orks always had plans to invade our lands, destroy our way of life, and "
"our faith in Auros. But, the ever guarding presence of Auros was always "
"their to guide us and see us through.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The orks are an evil race that live only to concur and destroy all that is "
"good. #PlayerName#, you too can feel the blessing presence of Auros by "
"hunting down the evil ork. Go out there, seek, fight and kill three orks!"

msgid "start_text_quest_3209"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five Baleful Venom Sacs, to help the enchanters of "
"Silverley continue creating magical weapons for the mercian army."

msgid "start_text_quest_3210"
msgstr ""
"For many years, the enchanters of Silverley have carried on the tradition of "
"creating some of the finest enchanted weapon for the mercian army.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If we are to have Silverley to continue to provide the army with enchanted "
"weapons, weapons that will definitely be of service against our many "
"enemies, we must help the enchanters anyway we can.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"From the little I know, various materials are used in the possess of "
"creating magical weapons. Some of these can be found out in wild, and others "
"collected from the bodies of monsters. Monsters such as the Doom Spiders "
"found in Brockmoore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Brockmoore, and gather from the Doom Spiders two Venom Sacs and two "
"units of Arachnid Darktaint."

msgid "start_text_quest_3211"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Colman Ashbourne. Gather three units of "
"Tainted Hearts, from the Swamp Hags in Brockmoore."

msgid "start_text_quest_3212"
msgstr ""
"My good friend Oona Fern of Silverley, has asked me if I could harvest for "
"her ingredients from the Swamp Hags that reside in the Brockmoore swamps, "
"ingredients that can be used for enchanting weapons. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to gather two units of Bile and two Hag Hearts from the Swamp "
"Hags in Brockmoore."

msgid "start_text_quest_3213"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver Colman Ashbourne's package to Oona Fern in "
"Silverley."

msgid "start_text_quest_3214"
msgstr ""
"I need somebody to deliver a package with enchanting materials I have "
"prepared, to Oona Fern in Silverley.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, could you do this simple task for me? Silverley is not that "
"far away from here. Just a little to the Southeast."

msgid "start_text_quest_3215"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted from Maria Hawksgate. Search for the fallen agent in the "
"{$v15} dungeon, recover the Sanguine Agent Ring, and deliver it to Allan the "
"Councillor at Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_3216"
msgstr ""
"You have recovered the signet ring from the fallen Sanguine agent. Deliver "
"it to Allan the Councillor in Sanguine, and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3217"
msgstr ""
"After a long and dangerous operation, agents of Sanguine managed to uncover "
"a Malaut stronghold that was hidden within the ork lands of Morak in {$v15} "
"to the north-northeast of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once it was verified that the actual stronghold was one of the organized "
"followers of Malaut, Sanguine successfully managed to plant an agents among "
"them, to gather more information.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When the time was right, hidden agents stormed into the stronghold to put an "
"end to the activities of the Malaut followers, by taking down the leaders "
"and clerics. The operation didn't go as planned, and Sanguine abandoned the "
"operation while loosing in the process one very important agent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The White Order has been given the task to search for the body of the lost "
"agent, and if possible to recover the signet ring worn by the agent. The "
"Sanguine Agent Ring is worn only by those chosen agents of Sanguine, and it "
"would be a disgrace if it ended up in the hands of the Malaut followers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, the White Order wants you to take on this mission. You are now "
"among the best agents we have ever had, and I believe that you do have that "
"it takes to succeed in completing this mission.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You are to enter the Malaut dungeon-stronghold in {$v15}, which is to the "
"north of here, and search for the body of the fallen Sanguine agent. Once "
"you do manage to find the agent and recover the ring, head straight for "
"Sanguine and deliver the ring to Allan the Councillor. May Auros guide you "
"my friend."

msgid "start_text_quest_3218"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigclubs Trollmangler. Kill four Ork "
"Warmongers in less than three hours.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3219"
msgstr ""
"Our agents have discovered a group of  traitorous orks, hiding south of here "
"near the borders between {$u15} and {$u16}. Among them are the elusive Ork "
"Warmongers. These are the ones leading and uniting the traitorous orks "
"against Morak, wreaking havoc through the lands, damaging our communities. "
"We must attack them now.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to kill four Ork Warmongers quickly, within the "
"next three hours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3220"
msgstr ""
"Bigclubs Trollmangler has instructed you to enter the {$v15} dungeon, search "
"for the book of Malaut, and steal it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3221"
msgstr ""
"You have stolen the Book of Malaut from the Malaut stronghold in {$v15}. "
"Deliver the book of Malaut to Bigclubs Trollmangler at Swampton."

msgid "start_text_quest_3222"
msgstr ""
"Outcast humans called followers of Malaut, have been well entrenched inside "
"the {$v15} dungeon for a while. And although Malaut and his followers are "
"enemies of mercia, this does not make them our allies or friends. This does "
"not give them the right to seek refuge within Morak, or to establish a "
"stronghold within our lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our previous attempts to drive them out failed, since many more continued to "
"arrive, fleeing mercia and the mercian army. We have to find a way to drive "
"them out, before the mercian army discovers their stronghold in {$v15}, and "
"decides move in.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time to use a new tactic against these worshipers of Malaut, if we are "
"to drive them away. We will strike at the heart of their faith. At Malaut "
"himself.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to enter the Malaut stronghold in the {$v15} dungeon, and search "
"presumably for an altar or shrine dedicated to Malaut. Once you find the "
"shrine or altar dedicated to Malaut, search the Book of Malaut. Steal it, "
"and bring it here. Only then, when the faith the Malaut worshipers is weak, "
"and chaos engulfs their stonghold , our agents will attack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, the Defenders of the Swamp want you to enter the Malaut "
"stronghold in the {$v15} dungeon, and steal the Book of Malaut. "
"Unfortunately, we don't have any knowledge of the inside layout of the "
"{$v15} dungeon, so it is up to you to find the book, and then your way out "
"of the dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3223"
msgstr "Bigclubs Trollmangler has asked you to report to Amhard the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_3224"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, the Defenders of the Swamp are very pleased with all you have "
"done here. Among the many that praise you, is Amhard the Arcanist. Amhard is "
"a very important part of this organization, and she has requested if you "
"could help here with here tasks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can spare the time, I would like it if you could help her with her "
"work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3225"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amhard the Arcanist. Gather three units of "
"Putrid Corpseflesh from the Revenants near the ruins in {$u16}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3226"
msgstr ""
"The gathering of material that are used for casting spells or enchanting "
"weapon and armors, is a task that not many here seem to understand its "
"importance.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many of these material are not that difficult to find, while others can be "
"rare to come by. The rare ones are usually those that can only be gathered "
"from the bodies of monsters. This means that somebody has to first find the "
"monsters, then defeat them, and in the end skin their bodies in search for "
"the desired materials. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the south of here in {$u16}, very close to an ancient ruin site, "
"revenants have been spotted. I want you to gather three units of revenant "
"corpseflesh from them."

msgid "start_text_quest_3227"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigork Blacktongue. Search inside the {$v11} "
"dungeon for the idol of the unknown lesser god."

msgid "start_text_quest_3228"
msgstr "Deliver the idol of the lesser god to Bigork Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_3229"
msgstr ""
"A few months ago, Grand Messenger Arxanthos reveled to me that the Fire "
"Dragon craves an item, an idol of a lesser god now long dead. The Fire "
"Dragon intends to bring this lesser dead god back to life. What plans the "
"Fire Dragon might have for this lesser god when resurrected are not known to "
"me, and neither is it my place to ask.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the visions that Grand Messenger Arxanthos had received from the Fire "
"Dragon, it had been reveled to him that the idol of this unknown dead lesser "
"god is kept hidden away safe, somewhere inside some long forgotten dungeon. "
"From the descriptions that Grand Messenger Arxanthos gave to me, we are "
"searching for a secret room, with three statues and three sarcophagus inside "
"it. It is in this room that the idol of the lesser god is kept. After a long "
"search, our agents have discovered the location of the dungeon, where the "
"idol of the lesser god is kept.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you go {$v11}, enter the dungeon portal there our gents "
"discovered, and search for the idol. I will mark the entrance of the dungeon "
"on your map. Once inside, it is up to you, to locate the secret room where "
"the idol is being kept."

msgid "start_text_quest_3230"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigork Blacktongue. Kill three of the Goblin "
"Warlords that have set camp in {$v11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3231"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the letter you found on one of the Goblin Warlords to Bigork "
"Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_3232"
msgstr ""
"For the last few weeks, many of our villages have been under attack by "
"goblin hordes, the likes we have never seen before. These greenskin attacks "
"against our villages will not do any real damage, but the persistence, "
"organization, and the shear number of goblins, is far from normal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"After the goblin raids against our village, Dragonbound agents have "
"discovered a group of goblin warlords has been coordinating these attacks. "
"We know for a fact, that the goblin warlords could not have planned and "
"initiated such a vast and organized attack against us, so it is obvious that "
"others are behind these goblin attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Who is commanding the goblin warlords and giving out orders is what we want "
"to learn. But until our agents return with the answers, Grand Messenger "
"Arxanthos has demanded that we take out these pathetic goblin leaders "
"immediately. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to kill three of these goblin warlords. They have "
"set camp in {$v11}, to the northwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3233"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Dragonbound. Go to the hobgoblin camp in "
"{$w11}, kill four hobgoblins, and return to Bigork Blacktongue with your "
"assessment of their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_3234"
msgstr ""
"The letter you brought back to us from the goblin warlords camp, has "
"revealed to us exactly what we were suspecting. That the goblin attacks have "
"been administered from elsewhere. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It seems that the hobgoblins of the Raven Standard Army are back. It has "
"been many years since anybody had heard anything about the Raven Standard "
"Army. The Raven Standard Army first appeared hundreds of years ago, "
"somewhere on the jungle continent of Yssam. It was there that a hobgoblin "
"leader managed to unite the many hobgoblin clans, create a powerful  "
"kingdom, and thus creating the legendary Raven Standard Army. For many "
"years, the hobgoblin kingdom and the Raven Standard Army had been very "
"successful, before falling apart during a vicious war of succession.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have discovered a small hobgoblin war group, that have built a "
"well fortified camp along the Laurgul road to the north of here. Although we "
"are not sure that these hobgoblins are of the Raven Standard, I want you to "
"go and assess the strength of this hobgoblin camp. I want you to kill four "
"hobgoblins, and return here with your assessment of their strengths and "
"weaknesses.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the meantime, our agents are working hard to uncover anything they can of "
"the Raven Standard Army."

msgid "start_text_quest_3235"
msgstr ""
"Bigork Blacktongue has asked you to report to Marganak the Arcanist, and to "
"assist here with her work as she sees fit."

msgid "start_text_quest_3236"
msgstr ""
"There are many day to day tasks that go on here at Emberhall. One of them is "
"the gathering of  materials than can be used in for creating magical items. "
"Be it either creating magical weapons or placing enchantment upon armor, our "
"enchanters are always in need of materials to continue their important work."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Marganak the Arcanist has requested that we send somebody to help with the "
"gathering of materials needed for enchanting. I want you to report to "
"Marganak the Arcanist and assist her with her work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3237"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marganak the Arcanist. Gather three Tainted "
"Hearts."

msgid "start_text_quest_3238"
msgstr ""
"Many are the enchanted items that are crafted here in Emberhall by our "
"enchanters, and many are the materials that are used the create these items. "
"In their effort to create these enchanted weapons and armors, before our "
"enchanters know it they have usually run out of many of the materials needed."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As it happens, I have a list of ingredients here that our enchanters have "
"requested. To begin with, one of our enchanters is in need of three Hag "
"Hearts. Hag hearts can be harvested from Night Hags, such as those that are "
"found in the {$v11} swamp lands. I want you to go and gather three Hag "
"Hearts from the Night Hags in {$v11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3239"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather two Foul Venom Sacs for Marganak the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_3240"
msgstr ""
"Many strange creatures are found throughout Agon. But very few as strange "
"and bizarre as the iklits. These insect-like creatures are extremely "
"dangerous when encounters in groups. This is because the iklits share "
"communal-hive minds, and this bond allows iklit groups to act as if one "
"superior single mind was controlling and coordinating them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"All this is fascinating, but our enchanters are more interested in what the "
"bodies of the iklits can be harvested for. A few ingredients can be "
"harvested from the iklits, but at the moment it is the venom sacs we need."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest two Iklit Venom Sacs. Iklits can be found in Azak "
"Tuun, which is to the northwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_3241"
msgstr ""
"Bigork Blacktongue has asked you to report to Bigaks Stonesmasher in {$x13}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3242"
msgstr ""
"Dragonbound agents can be found stationed throughout Morak, working hard to "
"bring a solution to the many issues that threaten the Ork Empire. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bigaks Stonesmasher, one of the Dragonbound agents, is looking into a few of "
"these issues. Issues such as the sudden appearance of the undead bonecrew on "
"the eastern shores of Morak, or the rumors of a powerful ancient artifact "
"that has somehow found its way into the hands of a clan of ogres in {$x14}."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to report to Bigaks Stonesmasher who is stationed in {$x13}. "
"Bigaks will be giving you your next assignments."

msgid "start_text_quest_3243"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigaks Stonesmasher. Kill six of the bonecrew "
"that have set camps along the eastern shores."

msgid "start_text_quest_3244"
msgstr ""
"The protection of the borders of Morak is of greater importance, and the "
"Dragonbound are the protectors of the northern and eastern borders. Any "
"foreign unwanted presence within these borders will be dealt with swiftly, "
"as an example to any others that plan to set foot within Morak, and claim "
"any land as their own. Nobody sets foot within Morak without permission from "
"Flaming Skull. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This also applies for the undead bonecrew, who have begun setting up camps "
"along the eastern shores, borders we intend to keep safe and clear. So far I "
"have discovered three bonecrew camps along our eastern shores. One of them "
"in {$y13}, and another two in {$y14}. You can assist the Dragonbound by "
"clearing our shores of six of these undead pirates, these bonecrew. I will "
"mark their positions on your map. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, your mission will be to kill six bonecrew."

msgid "start_text_quest_3245"
msgstr ""
"Bigaks Stonesmasher has sent you on a mission against the gray orks in "
"{$y13}. Your task, to kill three gray orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3246"
msgstr ""
"Gray orks have lived within Morak for many years, keeping to their own, "
"living out of sight in their underground dwellings, and not creating much "
"trouble. But recently reports that have been arriving at the Dragonbound "
"headquarters, describing a group of gray orks that have begun surfacing, "
"attacking our caravans and raiding our outer villages. While obviously "
"related to the surface orks of Morak, acts like this will not go unpunished "
"by the Dragonbound. These gray orks have now crossed the line, and will pay "
"the price.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have located the camp these gray orks have set up to the east of "
"here, among the ruins of {$y13}. I want you to find this gray ork camp, and "
"kill three gray orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3247"
msgstr ""
"Bigaks Stonesmasher has asked you to search for a the artifact called the "
"Horn of Pain, somewhere in the ogre camp in {$x14}. Once you have found it, "
"head straight for Emberhall, and deliver it to Bigork Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_3248"
msgstr ""
"You now have in your possession the Horn of Pain. Head straight for "
"Emberhall, and deliver it to Bigork Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_3249"
msgstr ""
"Many are the artifacts that are appearing throughout Agon. Artifact crafted "
"by ancient races that have now long deserted Agon, while others left behind "
"by powerful figures. Figures such as the demon Morneid, who once controlled "
"a vast area of central Morak. After the demon Morneid departed Agon, many of "
"the demon's magical items were scattered throughout Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Dragonbound are searching for the Horn of Pain, a very powerful "
"artifact, which is believed to have found its way into the hands of a clan "
"of Ogres in the region of {$x14}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Horn of Pain is one of the three parts of the legendary artifact the "
"Spear of Darkness, one of the many weapons said to have been crafted for the "
"demon Morneid.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you r mission is to travel to {$x14}, and to search the ogre "
"camp for the Horn of Pain. Once you have found it, head straight for "
"Emberhall, and deliver it to Bigork Blacktongue."

msgid "start_text_quest_325"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arngard the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3250"
msgstr ""
"You accepted a mission offered by Bigaks Stonesmasher. Kill four Ogres and "
"two Hill Giants."

msgid "start_text_quest_3251"
msgstr ""
"Ogres are not something new to the region of {$x14}, but with the latest "
"addition of the hill giants into the region, the ogres have now become much "
"more confident and aggressive.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to stop these overgrown thugs before they get any ideas of moving "
"west, closer to the villages of New Flayed Elf and Metal Heart, and start "
"creating real problems. As if the annoying goblin attacks of lately were not "
"enough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName# I want you to kill four Ogres and two Hill Giants."

msgid "start_text_quest_326"
msgstr ""
"Hammerdelve is an ancient village which lies on the shores of a small "
"glacial lake. To the south of here lies the dwarven capital of {$p09}, while "
"the port town of Frostgap lies to the northeast. Most people in Hammerdelve "
"are hunters or furriers who supply these larger communities with furs and "
"cured meats.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, the mountains around our village are almost as rich in "
"goblins as they are in fur-clad mammals. Recently, some of these goblins "
"migrated down from their mountain warrens and into the Hammerdelve valley "
"itself. While these greenskins don't pose much of a threat to a seasoned "
"dwarven trapper, they hunt the animals that we depend on for meat and furs, "
"and therefore they need to be eradicated.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you can assist Hammerdelve rid itself of these annoying little "
"pests, but joining the hunt. Kill four goblins then return to me for a "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_327"
msgstr ""
"Arngard the Councillor asked you to bring him two goblin axes, and you have "
"accepted this task."

msgid "start_text_quest_328"
msgstr ""
"Hammerdelve is a community of trappers and furriers, many of whom now see "
"their livelihood threatened by migrating goblins, who prey on and scare off "
"the local prey animals. We are currently arranging a campaign of "
"annihilation against these intruders, and we could use your help.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Most goblins fight using pathetically primitive axes that they make "
"themselves. If we leave these sorry excuses for weapons laying about, new "
"goblins migrating from the mountains will pick them up and put them to use "
"again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring the axes of your goblin victims to me, so that we may "
"destroy them. To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be "
"unarmed. Then while targeting the remains, use the action button. You may "
"then drag items from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring me two goblin axes and you will be rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_329"
msgstr ""
"You have promised to return to Tordar the Blacksmith with five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3294"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin "
"Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3295"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending Nagast. And many are "
"the brave that boast that they have killed many dangerous monsters. But few "
"are those that can actually prove that they have killed a legendary number "
"of monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3296"
msgstr ""
"Tialanta the Fighter has asked you to report to Akamush the Fighter of the "
"Harn Mandean, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3297"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Dulguna and "
"talk to Akamush the Fighter of the Harn Mandean."

msgid "start_text_quest_3298"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Akamush the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3299"
msgstr ""
"Many are the achievement titles I have earned, but being the fighter I am, I "
"have always enjoyed gaining those titles of strength. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see you have already claimed the title of The Brawny, the first of the "
"strength achievement titles. Surly this alone is not enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I will give you the opportunity to claim the second of the "
"strength achievement titles, that of The Muscular.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the strength achievement title of The Muscular, you will have "
"to kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll Lords. Well, what are you waiting for?"

msgid "start_text_quest_33"
msgstr "William the Councillor has asked you to kill four of the goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_330"
msgstr ""
"As a result of the increased monster presence in this region, we are "
"planning a series of guardhouses along the road to Frostgap. I want you to "
"help us by gathering stone, which is one of the primary resources needed for "
"the project.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you first need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a "
"tool already, you may buy one from Ulfrid the Merchant, who trades near "
"Hammerdelve's inner wall.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, the procedure will be successful "
"approximately every other time."

msgid "start_text_quest_3300"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Akamush the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3301"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3302"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ensharra the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3303"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave Alfar that risk their lives fighting large numbers of "
"monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help Nagast, by hunting down many "
"of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to kill "
"extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles, as a "
"recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also titles "
"that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Tialanta the Fighter or Kalrash the Arcanist. You might even "
"find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3304"
msgstr ""
"Ensharra the Councillor has asked you to report to Nathar Blackorb of the "
"Temple of the God King, where you will be able to earn more dexterity "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3305"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Sorgom, and "
"talk to Nathar Blackorb of the Temple of the God King."

msgid "start_text_quest_3306"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nathar Blackorb. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3307"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Ensharra the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3308"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nathar Blackorb. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3309"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_331"
msgstr "You have agreed to gather five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_3310"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kalrash the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 "
"Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_3311"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But, besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3312"
msgstr ""
"Kalrash the Arcanist has asked you to report to Haneksur the Arcanist of the "
"Temple of the God King, where you may be able to earn further vitality "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3313"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Sorgom and talk to Haneksur the Arcanist of the Temple of the God "
"King."

msgid "start_text_quest_3314"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Haneksur the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3315"
msgstr ""
"You have attained the title of the Stout. The first of the achievement "
"titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can enhance ones "
"vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly responsible for ones "
"health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3316"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Haneksur the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3317"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Errak the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3318"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3319"
msgstr ""
"Errak the Merchant has asked you to report to Elmah the Merchant of the Harn "
"Mandean, where you may be able to earn further quickness achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_332"
msgstr ""
"To better protect the trade through this part of Dvergheim, we are planning "
"to build guard towers along the roads to {$p09} and Frostgap. Before work "
"can start on these structures, we need help with gathering the timber that "
"is needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If you "
"don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Ulfrid the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_3320"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Elmah the Merchant of the Harn Mandeand is ready to reward those who wish to "
"test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining more titles that "
"will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Elmah the Merchant in Dulgana. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3321"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elmah the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3322"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3323"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elmah the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3324"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3325"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Haemat the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then hand them all over to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3326"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a "
"major boost to peoples morale, knowing that their heroic efforts have not "
"gone unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3327"
msgstr ""
"Haemat the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Phyrul the Blacksmith of "
"the Shadow Salient, where you may be able to earn further wisdom achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3328"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Niasha and talk to Phyrul the Blacksmith of the Shadow Salient."

msgid "start_text_quest_3329"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 "
"iron ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to Phyrul "
"the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_333"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Gormfinn's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to him with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_3330"
msgstr ""
"I am always pleased to meet hard workers as yourself. So, you have already "
"gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained this "
"title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend Haemat the "
"Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and then bring them all to me. "
"#PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work waiting to be done, "
"if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3331"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and bring them all to Phyrul the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3332"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3333"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Torgard the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin "
"Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3334"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending Mercia and all "
"Mercians. And many are the brave that boast that they have killed many "
"dangerous monsters. But few are those that can actually prove that they have "
"killed a legendary number of monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3335"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to report to Dialynna the Fighter of the "
"White Order, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3336"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Copperdale "
"and talk to Dialynna the Fighter of the White Order."

msgid "start_text_quest_3337"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dialynna the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3338"
msgstr ""
"Many are the achievement titles I have earned, but being the fighter I am, I "
"have always enjoyed gaining those titles of strength. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see you have already claimed the title of The Brawny, the first of the "
"strength achievement titles. Surly this alone is not enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I will give you the opportunity to claim the second of the "
"strength achievement titles, that of The Muscular.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the strength achievement title of The Muscular, you will have "
"to kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll Lords. Well, what are you waiting for?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3339"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dialynna the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_334"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Ulfrid the Merchant's shop, "
"which lies along Hammerdelve's inner wall.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3340"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3341"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Allan the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3342"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave Mercians that risk their lives fighting large numbers "
"of monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help Mercia, by hunting down many "
"of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to kill "
"extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles, as a "
"recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also titles "
"that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Torgard the Fighter or Niane the Arcanist. You might even "
"find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3343"
msgstr ""
"Allan the Councillor has asked you to report to Sir Jeremiah Grace of the "
"Knights of Malregard, where you will be able to earn more dexterity "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3344"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Chilbourne, "
"and talk to Sir Jeremiah Grace of the Knights of Malregard."

msgid "start_text_quest_3345"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sir Jeremiah Grace. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3346"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Allan the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3347"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sir Jeremiah Grace. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3348"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3349"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Niane the Arcanist. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 Kobold "
"Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_335"
msgstr "Bring four teeth to Arngard the Councillor in Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_3350"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But, besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3351"
msgstr ""
"Niane the Arcanist has asked you to report to Sandra the Arcanist of the "
"White Order, where you may be able to earn further vitality achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3352"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Copperdale and talk to Sandra the Arcanist of the White Order."

msgid "start_text_quest_3353"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sandra the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3354"
msgstr ""
"You successfully attained the title of the Stout. The first of the "
"achievement titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can "
"enhance ones vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly "
"responsible for ones health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3355"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sandra the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3356"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the vitality "
"achievement titles, that of The Tough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Tough is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the vitality achievement title of The Tough, you will have to kill "
"200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3357"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Simeon the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3358"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3359"
msgstr ""
"Simeon the Merchant has asked you to report to Edwin the Merchant of the "
"Knights of Malregard, where you may be able to earn further quickness "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_336"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you know, the region of Hammerdelve has recently been overrun by a large "
"number of goblins. As we clean out these pests, we should make sure to "
"extract the parts such as the teeth, that find use in enchantment rituals.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Ulfrid the Merchant's here in Hammerdelve. Assuming "
"that you are a novice skinner, you should expect to successfully remove "
"intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3360"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Edwin the Merchant of the Knights of Malregard is ready to reward those who "
"wish to test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining more "
"titles that will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Edwin the Merchant in Chilbourne. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3361"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Edwin the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3362"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3363"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Edwin the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3364"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3365"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Talaod the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then hand them all over to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3366"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a "
"major boost to peoples morale, that their heroic efforts have not gone "
"unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3367"
msgstr ""
"Talaod the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Sigurd the Blacksmith of "
"the Sons of Riada, where you may be able to earn further wisdom achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3368"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Hildershall and talk to Sigurd the Blacksmith of the Sons of Riada."

msgid "start_text_quest_3369"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 "
"iron ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and deliver them all to "
"Warthug the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_337"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Arngard's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins in order to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3370"
msgstr ""
"I am always pleased to meet hard workers as yourself. So, you have already "
"gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained this "
"title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend Talaod the "
"Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and then bring them all to me. "
"#PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work waiting to be done, "
"if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3371"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and bring them all to Sigurd the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3372"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3373"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Galein the Fighter. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin Fighters "
"and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3374"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending Mirendil. And many are "
"the brave that boast that they have killed many dangerous monsters. But few "
"are those that can actually prove that they have killed a legendary number "
"of monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3375"
msgstr ""
"Galein the Fighter has asked you to report to Baeliel the Fighter of the "
"Arrowheads, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3376"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Krisathel "
"and talk to Baeliel the Fighter of the Arrowheads."

msgid "start_text_quest_3377"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Baeliel the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3378"
msgstr ""
"Many are the achievement titles I have earned, but being the fighter I am, I "
"have always enjoyed gaining those titles of strength. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see you have already claimed the title of The Brawny, the first of the "
"strength achievement titles. Surly this alone is not enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I will give you the opportunity to claim the second of the "
"strength achievement titles, that of The Muscular.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the strength achievement title of The Muscular, you will have "
"to kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll Lords. Well, what are you waiting for?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3379"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Baeliel the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_338"
msgstr ""
"We must use every trick available to us in our attempt to drive the "
"trespassing goblins away from Hammerdelve. One thing we should use to our "
"advantage, is the fact that goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It "
"seems that the ancestral goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, "
"and now the entire race has an ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our goblin-expelling efforts by casting twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you "
"need to wield a magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase "
"one from any arcanist shop, such as Gormfinn the Arcanist's shop. Once you "
"own a staff, you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto "
"your character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3380"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3381"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sylanae the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3382"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave Mirdain that risk their lives fighting large numbers "
"of monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help our people, by hunting down "
"many of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to "
"kill extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles "
"as a recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also "
"titles that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Galein the Fighter or Aredthil the Arcanist. You might even "
"find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3383"
msgstr ""
"Sylanae the Councillor has asked you to report to Eredethil Swiftarrow of "
"the Arrowheads, where you will be able to earn more dexterity achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3384"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Krisathel, "
"and talk to Eredethil Swiftarrow of the Arrowheads."

msgid "start_text_quest_3385"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3386"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Sylanae the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3387"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3388"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3389"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialasse the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 "
"Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_339"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Skuldvard's quest. Kill four goblins, then return to "
"Eirhjelm for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3390"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3391"
msgstr ""
"Ialasse the Arcanist has asked you to report to Taradin the Arcanist of the "
"Serene Spire, where you may be able to earn further vitality achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3392"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Iriendir and talk to Taradin the Arcanist of the Serene Spire."

msgid "start_text_quest_3393"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taradin the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3394"
msgstr ""
"You successfully attained the title of the Stout. The first of the "
"achievement titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can "
"enhance ones vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly "
"responsible for ones health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3395"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taradin the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3396"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the vitality "
"achievement titles, that of The Tough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Tough is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the vitality achievement title of The Tough, you will have to kill "
"200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3397"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eriwyn the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3398"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3399"
msgstr ""
"Eriwyn the Merchant has asked you to report to Veranna the Merchant of the "
"Emerald Throne, where you may be able to earn further quickness achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_340"
msgstr ""
"Eirhjelm is a mining community which supplies much of the raw material for "
"the countless foundries and forges that constitute the dwarven weapon and "
"armor industries. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In recent weeks, the prosperity and stability of Eirhjelm has been "
"threatened bands of goblins, who have taken up residence close to our trade "
"routes. While these diminutive monsters pose little threat to the city "
"itself, they have made a nuisance of themselves by raiding caravans and "
"outlying farms.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The time has come to remove this thorn in our side, and you are of course "
"welcome to help us in the extermination effort. Kill four goblins and return "
"here to claim your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3400"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Veranna the Merchant of the Emerald Throne is ready to reward those who wish "
"to test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining more titles "
"that will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Elmah the Merchant in Imathir. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3401"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Veranna the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3402"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3403"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Veranna the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3404"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3405"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aredthil the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then bring them all to Aredthil."

msgid "start_text_quest_3406"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a "
"major boost to peoples morale, that their heroic efforts have not gone "
"unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3407"
msgstr ""
"Aredthil the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Seraron the Blacksmith of "
"the Emerald Throne, where you may be able to earn further wisdom achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3408"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Imathir and talk to Seraron the Blacksmith of the Emerald Throne."

msgid "start_text_quest_3409"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 "
"iron ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to Seraron "
"the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_341"
msgstr "Skuldvard the Councillor has asked you to bring him two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3410"
msgstr ""
"I am always pleased to meet hard workers as yourself. So, you have already "
"gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained this "
"title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend Aredthil the "
"Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to me. "
"#PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work waiting to be done, "
"if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3411"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then deliver them all to Seraron the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3412"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3413"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Cyreia the Fighter. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin Fighters "
"and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3414"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending the Tribelands. And "
"many are the brave that boast that they have killed many dangerous monsters. "
"But few are those that can actually prove that they have killed a legendary "
"number of monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3415"
msgstr ""
"Cyreia the Fighter has asked you to report to Ellevan the Fighter of the "
"Longclaw, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3416"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Stonehold "
"and talk to Ellevan the Fighter of the Longclaw."

msgid "start_text_quest_3417"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ellevan the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3418"
msgstr ""
"Many are the achievement titles I have earned, but being the fighter I am, I "
"have always enjoyed gaining those titles of strength. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see you have already claimed the title of The Brawny, the first of the "
"strength achievement titles. Surly this alone is not enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I will give you the opportunity to claim the second of the "
"strength achievement titles, that of The Muscular.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the strength achievement title of The Muscular, you will have "
"to kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll Lords. Well, what are you waiting for?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3419"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ellevan the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_342"
msgstr ""
"Goblins are deeply stupid creatures, who have trouble engineering anything "
"more advanced than a sharpened stick. Despite their rudimentary nature, the "
"traditional goblin axes are highly prized among the greenskins, only a few "
"of whom are able to repair one that is damaged, much less make a new one "
"from scratch.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For this reason, I want you to loot the axe from any goblin that you kill in "
"the vicinity of Eirhjelm. Using this tactic, we will eventually limit the "
"number of armed warriors that the invaders are able to put in the field.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed. Then "
"while targeting the remains, use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3420"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3421"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tivasta the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3422"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave Mahirim that risk their lives fighting large numbers "
"of monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help our people, by hunting down "
"many of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to "
"kill extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles "
"as a recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also "
"titles that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Cyreia the Fighter or Natanda the Arcanist. You might even "
"find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3423"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor has asked you to report to Mardem-kai the Loyal of "
"the Wolfmasks, where you will be able to earn more dexterity achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3424"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Nightspire, "
"and talk to Mardem-kai the Loyal of the Wolfmasks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3425"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardem-kai the Loyal. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3426"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Tivasta the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3427"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardem-kai the Loyal. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3428"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3429"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Natanda the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 "
"Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_343"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ragneid the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3430"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3431"
msgstr ""
"Natanda the Arcanist has asked you to report to Levynna the Arcanist of the "
"Elders of Red Moon, where you may be able to earn further vitality "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3432"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Amurranyr and talk to Levynna the Arcanist of the Elders of Red "
"Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3433"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Levynna the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3434"
msgstr ""
"You successfully attained the title of the Stout. The first of the "
"achievement titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can "
"enhance ones vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly "
"responsible for ones health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3435"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Levynna the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3436"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the vitality "
"achievement titles, that of The Tough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Tough is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the vitality achievement title of The Tough, you will have to kill "
"200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3437"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lomrun the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3438"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3439"
msgstr ""
"Lomrun the Merchant has asked you to report to Moarlon the Merchant of the "
"Elders of Red Moon, where you may be able to earn further quickness "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_344"
msgstr ""
"So, the council has at last decided that Eirhjelm needs to improve and "
"strengthen the town walls.  Who would have thought that a goblin attack was "
"all that was needed, to get such a decision authorized. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Since we are short on raw materials, I want you to help us out by gathering "
"suitably shaped building blocks from boulders found in the wilderness "
"surrounding town. In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you "
"don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from Erling the Merchant, or "
"from any other general store.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Pointing your crosshair "
"towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is suitable for harvesting. "
"Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may "
"begin the procedure of extracting stone using your pickaxe. If you are a "
"novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure to be successful every "
"other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3440"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Moarlon the Merchant of the Elders of Red Moon is ready to reward those who "
"wish to test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining more "
"titles that will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Moarlon the Merchant in Amurranyr. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3441"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Moarlon the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3442"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3443"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Moarlon the Merchant.  To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins"

msgid "start_text_quest_3444"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3445"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Maldon the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then hand them over to Maldon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3446"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a "
"major boost to peoples morale, that their heroic efforts have not gone "
"unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3447"
msgstr ""
"Maldon the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Lissada the Blacksmith of "
"the Longclaw, where you may be able to earn further wisdom achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3448"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Stonehold and talk to Lissada the Blacksmith of the Longclaw."

msgid "start_text_quest_3449"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 "
"iron ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and then bring them all to "
"Lissada the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_345"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used to secure "
"new mineshafts."

msgid "start_text_quest_3450"
msgstr ""
"It  is always a pleasure meeting hard workers as yourself. So, you have "
"already gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained "
"this title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend Maldon "
"the Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and then bring all the crafted "
"items to me. #PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work "
"waiting to be done, if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3451"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to Lissada the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3452"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3453"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Hilrdr the Fighter. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin Fighters "
"and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3454"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending Dvergheim. And many are "
"the brave that boast that they have killed many dangerous monsters. But few "
"are those that can actually prove that they have killed a legendary number "
"of monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3455"
msgstr ""
"Hilrdr the Fighter has asked you to report to Thorgilis the Fighter of the "
"Voice of Ymir, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3456"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Thorsland "
"and talk to Thorgilis the Fighter of the Voice of Ymir."

msgid "start_text_quest_3457"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thorgilis the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3458"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thorgilis the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3459"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thorgilis the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_346"
msgstr ""
"The mines of Eirhjelm consume vast quantities of timber, which is used to "
"support the shafts and make them safe for workers. In recent weeks, goblin "
"attacks have disrupted our logging operations, and now we are running short "
"of timber.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help us with this situation, you need to bring a tool called "
"a Wood Axe to the trees around town. If you don't already own such a tool, "
"you may buy one from Erling the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_3460"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3461"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ordgrim the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3462"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave dwarves that risk their lives fighting large numbers "
"of monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help our people, by hunting down "
"many of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to "
"kill extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles "
"as a recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also "
"titles that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Hilrdr the Fighter or Rimnir the Arcanist. You might even "
"find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3463"
msgstr ""
"Ordgrim the Councillor has asked you to report to Garn Runeshield of the "
"Five Beards Trading Company, where you will be able to earn more dexterity "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3464"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Ringfain, "
"and talk to Garn Runeshield of the Five Beards Trading Company."

msgid "start_text_quest_3465"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3466"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Ordgrim the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3467"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garn Runeshield. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3468"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3469"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Rimnir the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 "
"Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_347"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Steingrima's quest. In order to complete it, you must "
"return to her with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_3470"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you"

msgid "start_text_quest_3471"
msgstr ""
"Rimnir the Arcanist has asked you to report to Gunthar the Arcanist of the "
"Order of the Axe, where you may be able to earn further vitality achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3472"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Maghnir and talk to Gunthar the Arcanist of the Order of the Axe."

msgid "start_text_quest_3473"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gunthar the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3474"
msgstr ""
"You successfully attained the title of the Stout. The first of the "
"achievement titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can "
"enhance ones vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly "
"responsible for ones health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3475"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gunthar the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3476"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the vitality "
"achievement titles, that of The Tough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Tough is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the vitality achievement title of The Tough, you will have to kill "
"200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3477"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Argin the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3478"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3479"
msgstr ""
"Argin the Merchant has asked you to report to Bolgir the Merchant of the "
"Five Beards Trading Company, where you may be able to earn further quickness "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_348"
msgstr ""
"This region produces a wealth of rare herbs that are used for brewing "
"potions. Recently, however, invading goblins have driven off the herb "
"gatherers and claimed the most fertile gathering grounds as their territory."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a consequence, I am currently running low on several key ingredients. If "
"you are heading out into the wilderness, I implore you to keep an eye out "
"for any mandrakes you see withering on the vine. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Erling the Merchant.\r\n"
" \r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3480"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Bolgir the Merchant of the Five Beards Trading Company is ready to reward "
"those who wish to test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining "
"more titles that will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Bolgir the Merchant in Ringfain. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3481"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bolgir the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3482"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3483"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bolgir the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standard Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3484"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standards Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3485"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Garmbeard the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then hand them all over to Garmbeard."

msgid "start_text_quest_3486"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a vast "
"boost to peoples morale, knowing that their heroic efforts have not gone "
"unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3487"
msgstr ""
"Garmbeard the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Glodir the Blacksmith of "
"the Order of the Axe, where you may be able to earn further wisdom "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3488"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Maghnir and talk to Glodir the Blacksmith of the Order of the Axe."

msgid "start_text_quest_3489"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 "
"iron ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to Glodir "
"the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_349"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Skuldvard the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_3490"
msgstr ""
"It is always a pleasure meeting hard workers as yourself. So, you have "
"already gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained "
"this title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend "
"Garmbeard the Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to me. "
"#PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work waiting to be done, "
"if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3491"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and deliver them all to Glodir the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3492"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3493"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmastar the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Brawny, you must kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 Goblin "
"Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_3494"
msgstr ""
"Many are those that risk their lives daily defending Morak. And many are the "
"brave that boast that they have killed many dangerous monsters. But few are "
"those that can actually prove that they have killed a legendary number of "
"monsters, and have something to show for it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual manages a heroic feat, one that can put him apart from "
"the rest, then this individual will be rewarded with an achievement title."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But these are not just any mere titles. The achievement titles, once "
"attained, will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to vitality, "
"dexterity, or even quickness. I am sure that you will be able to attain many "
"achievement titles, but only one can be equipped at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I myself am giving out such an achievement title, the title of The Brawny, "
"for any brave souls that wish to prove themselves. The title of The Brawny "
"is the first of the strength achievement titles. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain this title, all you need to do is to kill 200 Goblin Scouts, 100 "
"Goblin Fighters and 20 Goblin Shamans. No need to hurry my friend. There is "
"no time limit for this quest. It is one that you will attain slowly, in your "
"own time. Once you have gained this title, more will become available to you."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So #PlayerName#, are you ready to claim to title of The Brawny?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3495"
msgstr ""
"Aksmastar the Fighter has asked you to report to Aksmurdar the Fighter of "
"the Iron Orks, where you may be able to earn further strength achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3496"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Brawny is only the first of the strength achievement titles "
"that can be earned. If you wish to continue to proved yourself and progress "
"further, while gaining more bonuses to your strength, travel to Naergur and "
"talk to Aksmurdar the Fighter of the Iron Orks."

msgid "start_text_quest_3497"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmurdar the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll "
"Lords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3498"
msgstr ""
"Many are the achievement titles I have earned, but being the fighter I am, I "
"have always enjoyed gaining those titles of strength. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see you have already claimed the title of The Brawny, the first of the "
"strength achievement titles. Surly this alone is not enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I will give you the opportunity to claim the second of the "
"strength achievement titles, that of The Muscular.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the strength achievement title of The Muscular, you will have "
"to kill 300 Trolls and 10 Troll Lords. Well, what are you waiting for?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3499"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aksmurdar the Fighter. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Muscular, you must kill 200 Hobgoblins and 10 "
"Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_350"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The lands around Eirhjelm are crawling with goblins. The only good aspect of "
"this situation, is that goblins contain parts, most especially the teeth, "
"which may be used to make low powered versions of certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Erling the Merchant's shop, which lies near "
"Eirhjelm's eastern gate. Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should "
"be able to successfully remove intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_3500"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the strength "
"achievement titles, that of The Strong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Strong is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the strength achievement title of The Strong, you will have to kill "
"200 Hobgoblins and 10 Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_3501"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Izkruul the Councillor. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Limber, you must kill 200 Skeleton Archers and 20 "
"Deadeyes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3502"
msgstr ""
"Agon is a dangerous world, one that demands courage, strength and skill to "
"survive. The hunting and killing of monsters is part of our every day life, "
"and many are the brave orks that risk their lives fighting large numbers of "
"monsters. This is something we encourage, since the killing of these "
"monsters ensures the safety of our people and that of our way of life.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rewards are always given out for those who help our people, by hunting down "
"many of the monsters that threaten our borders. For those few who manage to "
"kill extremely vast numbers of these monsters, titles are given out. Titles "
"as a recognition for their skills and services to our people, but also "
"titles that will place these heroes apart from the rest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, these are not any simple titles. These are called achievement "
"titles, and when attained they will enhance the bearer with a bonus. A bonus "
"such as to strength or intelligence. You too will have the opportunity to "
"gain many achievement titles, but you will only be able to equip yourself "
"with one of them at a time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There are many reward achievement titles to be earned, given out by other "
"vendors such as Aksmastar the Fighter or Firetooths the Arcanist. You might "
"even find other achievement titles waiting to be earned in other towns.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these titles is the title of The Limber, which I am prepared to give "
"out to those who can prove themselves worthy of it. The title of The Limber, "
"is the first of the many achievement titles that will give you a bonus to "
"your dexterity. To attain the title of The Limber, you will have to kill 200 "
"Skeleton Archers and 20 Deadeyes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, the title of The Limber is there for the taking. #PlayerName#, are you "
"prepared to claim it as your own? A piece of advice. Take your time while "
"claiming your achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3503"
msgstr ""
"Izkruul the Councillor has asked you to report to Bigclubs Trollmanglar of "
"the Defenders of the Swamp, where you will be able to earn more dexterity "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3504"
msgstr ""
"If you desire to attain more achievement titles, and especially those that "
"will give you bonuses to your dexterity, I suggest you travel to Ondmark, "
"and talk to  Bigclubs Trollmanglar of the Defenders of the Swamp."

msgid "start_text_quest_3505"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigclubs Trollmanglar. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Agile you must kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3506"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that you have successfully completed Izkruul the "
"Councillor's little test, and attained the title of The Limber. No bad, but "
"I am sure you can do better than that.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you ready to claim the second of the dexterity achievement "
"titles, that of The Agile? This one will not be a easy as the one of the "
"Limber, but the benefits will be slightly greater.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the the dexterity achievement title of The Agile, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Centaurs and 10 Lizardmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_3507"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Bigclubs Trollmanglar. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Dextrous you must kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3508"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to truly test yourself, and claim the third of the "
"dexterity achievement titles, that of The Dextrous? This will truly be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly be proud of.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Dextrous will not be easy as that of the Limber. But, if it "
"is your dexterity that you desire to improve, than you are going to work "
"hard for it. I myself have claimed quite a few dexterity achievement titles."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To qualify for the dexterity achievement title of The Dextrous, you will "
"have to kill 50 Raptors."

msgid "start_text_quest_3509"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Firetooths the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Stout, you must kill 200 Kobold Scroungers, 200 "
"Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_351"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Skuldvard's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3510"
msgstr ""
"It is fulfilling and satisfying when one receives rewards and recognition "
"when accomplishing difficult feats, feats that require a large amount of "
"courage, and an array of skills. To these individuals that accomplish these "
"extraordinary feats, special reward titles are given out called achievement "
"titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Achievement titles are one of the ways we have chosen to reward these "
"extraordinary gifted individuals. But besides the recognition and pride "
"these titles may offer, the achievement titles have the ability to enhance "
"the bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to strength or dexterity.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles you can earn, is that of The Stout. It is "
"a title that will give you a small vitality bonus. Once you have claimed "
"this title, others will become available for you to claim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the title of The Stout as your own, you must kill 200 Kobold "
"Scroungers, 200 Kobold Scrappers and 20 Kobold Raiders.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I am confident that you are able to accomplish this feat. The "
"issue here is, are you?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3511"
msgstr ""
"Firetooths the Arcanist has asked you to report to Marganak the Arcanist of "
"the Dragonbound, where you may be able to earn further vitality achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3512"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Stout is only the first of the vitality achievement titles "
"that can be earned. And believe me, titles that give you a bonus to vitality "
"are always useful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you desire to progress further, and gain more bonuses to your vitality, "
"travel to Dragrenoth and talk to Marganak the Arcanist of the Dragonbound"

msgid "start_text_quest_3513"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marganak the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Hardy, you must kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 "
"Giant Skeletons and 10 Bone Knights."

msgid "start_text_quest_3514"
msgstr ""
"You successfully attained the title of the Stout. The first of the "
"achievement titles that grant a bonus to vitality.  Anything that can "
"enhance ones vitality is always welcomed, since vitality is greatly "
"responsible for ones health. The higher one vitality, the healthier one is."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to claim the next of the vitality achievement "
"titles, that of The Hardy? To achieve the vitality achievement title of The "
"Hardy, you will have to kill 300 Regular Skeletons, 10 Giant Skeletons and "
"10 Bone Knights. To assist you in this quest, you should know that Brittle "
"Skeletons, Skeleton Archers and Skeleton Warriors all count as Regular "
"Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3515"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Marganak the Arcanist. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Tough, you must kill 200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3516"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the vitality "
"achievement titles, that of The Tough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Tough is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the vitality achievement title of The Tough, you will have to kill "
"200 Revenants and 10 Oaklords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3517"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ogrok the Merchant. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Quick, you must kill 200 Akathars."

msgid "start_text_quest_3518"
msgstr ""
"There are always those that rise above the rest. Individuals that are "
"capable of performing feats, that were thought impossible. Feats that one "
"day will be told to future generations through songs and legends.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When an individual accomplishes an extraordinary feat, such as the killing "
"of a large number of monsters singlehandedly that threatened the safety of "
"the people, these individuals are then rewarded with achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These titles are not only given out just for the title. They are more than "
"that. They have the ability to grant the bearer an enhancement. An "
"enhancement to an attribute such as strength, intelligence or even wisdom."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the many achievement titles one can earn, is that of The Quick. The "
"title of the Quick will enhance the bearer with a small quickness bonus. To "
"attain the title of The Quick, all you need to do is kill 200 Akathars. "
"Well, do you want to gain this title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3519"
msgstr ""
"Ogrok the Merchant has asked you to report to Gorloth the Merchant of Iron "
"Maiden, where you may be able to earn further quickness achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_352"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, most goblins share an irrational fear of magic. We "
"should try to exploit this fear in our efforts to drive the invading goblins "
"out of the Eirhjelm swamps. \r\n"
" \r\n"
"Every dwarf who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast twenty "
"Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to remind them that all dwarves "
"master at least some rudimentary magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Steingrima the Arcanist. Once you own a staff, you "
"may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3520"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Quick is only the first of the quickness achievement titles "
"that can be earned. For those that have attained the title of The Quick, "
"Gorloth the Merchant of Iron Maiden is ready to reward those who wish to "
"test themselves, and prove that they are worthy of gaining more titles that "
"will enhance ones quickness.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find Gorloth the Merchant in Naergur. I will mark his position on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3521"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gorloth the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Fleet, you must kill 100 Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_3522"
msgstr ""
"One thing I have learned is that speed is of the essence. All the attributes "
"one can master, either be it strength, dexterity or intelligence are all "
"helpful, but being quick is always helpful.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am pleased to see that you have already gained the title of The Quick. "
"#PlayerName#, I can only presume that you are here because you are ready to "
"claim the next title, that of The Fleet. Am I correct?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the quickness achievement title of The Fleet as your own, you will "
"have to kill 100 Windlords. Are you ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3523"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gorloth the Merchant. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Swift, you must kill 50 Raven Standards."

msgid "start_text_quest_3524"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the quickness "
"achievement titles, that of The Swift.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Swift is a difficult title to attain, but surely will be a "
"title to boast about, one you can truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the quickness achievement title of The Swift, you will have to kill "
"50 Raven Standards."

msgid "start_text_quest_3525"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Rularak the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Thoughtful, you must gather 200 iron ore, 300 "
"stone, 300 timber and 200 fish, and then hand them all over to Rularak."

msgid "start_text_quest_3526"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rewards and titles handed out to those that accomplish "
"extraordinary feats, such as the successful killing of hundreds of dangerous "
"monsters. The recognition of these feats is good and necessary. It is a "
"major boost to peoples morale, that their heroic efforts have not gone "
"unnoticed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But what about all those who labor painstakingly, without complaining, "
"gathering all those necessary useful materials that are needed to build "
"these grand cities we safely live in, or craft the many armors that protect "
"us?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To all those that work quietly in the background, who are the real backbone "
"of our society, there are titles to be given out to them too. One of those "
"is the title of The Thoughtful, an achievement title that grants a small "
"wisdom bonus. And what more useful than wisdom, for those hard workers and "
"crafters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Thoughtful, you will need to gather 200 iron ore, "
"300 stone, 300 timber and 200 fish. Once you have gathered all the above, "
"bring them to me to claim your reward. Slowly and patiently, I am sure that "
"you will reach this goal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3527"
msgstr ""
"Rularak the Blacksmith has asked you to report to Warthug the Blacksmith of "
"the Defenders of the Swamp, where you may be able to earn further wisdom "
"achievement titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3528"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Thoughtful is only the first of the wisdom achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to continue to prove yourself and "
"progress further, while gaining more bonuses to your wisdom, travel to "
"Ondmark and talk to Warthug the Blacksmith of the Defenders of the Swamp."

msgid "start_text_quest_3529"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Warthug the Blacksmith. To obtain the "
"achievement title of The Knowledgeable, you must create 100 iron ingots, 200 "
"wood and cook 200 food items."

msgid "start_text_quest_353"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill four goblins in the vicinity of Valfather's Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_3530"
msgstr ""
"It is always a pleasure meeting hard workers as yourself. So, you have "
"already gained the title of The Thoughtful. If I'm not mistaken, you gained "
"this title working hard, gathering all the materials that my friend Rularak "
"the Blacksmith asked of you. Excellent. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Gathering materials is only the first step. Next comes the part of refining "
"these materials, transforming them from their crude raw forms as they are "
"found in nature, into the crafting materials that our blacksmiths and "
"builders need. Materials that are needed to create weapons, armors and many "
"other everyday items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Knowledgeable, you will have to create 100 iron "
"ingots, 200 wood and cook 200 food items, and bring them all to me. "
"#PlayerName#, as you can see there is a lot of hard work waiting to be done, "
"if you wish to gain this title."

msgid "start_text_quest_3531"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the achievement title of The Wise, you must craft 50 chain armor "
"pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and bring them all to Warthug the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3532"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the wisdom "
"achievement titles, that of The Wise. The title of The Wise is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about one you can truly "
"wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the wisdom achievement title of The Wise, you will have to craft 50 "
"chain armor pieces, 2000 arrows and 50 rapiers, and then bring them all to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3533"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ninnah the Mage. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Clever, you must kill 200 Zombies, 100 Zombie Warriors and 20 "
"Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_3534"
msgstr ""
"We all strive to make our way in this dangerous world we live in. Many times "
"have we been forced to push ourselves to our limits and even beyond, beyond "
"what we thought we were capable of achieving. We find ourselves performing "
"feats, feats that were thought to be impossible. Other times it might be "
"fighting off vast numbers of monsters at a time just to survive, and other "
"times defending our lands from the many enemies that surround us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"For those that can manage such incredible feats, while providing valuable "
"services to our people, there are titles waiting to be given out. These "
"titles are called achievement titles.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The achievement titles are not just any mere titles. Beyond providing the "
"recognition for ones efforts and services, these titles will enhance the "
"bearer with a bonus. A bonus such as to dexterity or wisdom.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The title of The Clever is one of the many achievement titles you can "
"earned. It is a title that will give you a small intelligence bonus. Once "
"you have claimed this title, others will become available for you to claim."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To attain the title of The Clever, you will need to kill 200 Zombies, 100 "
"Zombie Warriors and 20 Dire Zombies. #PlayerName#, are you ready to provide "
"your services, while gaining an achievement title?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3535"
msgstr ""
"Ninnah the Mage has asked you to report to Loesva the Mage of the Radiant "
"Circle, where you may be able to earn further intelligence achievement "
"titles."

msgid "start_text_quest_3536"
msgstr ""
"The title of The Clever is only the first of the intelligence achievement "
"titles that can be earned. If you wish to gain titles that will give your "
"further bonuses to your intelligence, travel to Dun Amsharra and talk to "
"Loesva the Mage of the Radiant Circle."

msgid "start_text_quest_3537"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Loesva the Mage. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Sharp, you must kill 100 Elementals."

msgid "start_text_quest_3538"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, the title of The Sharp is the next achievement title you may "
"gain, one that will raise your intelligence sightlier higher than that of "
"The Clever.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If like myself, spellcasting is what you desire to excel in, than this is "
"the path you want to follow. That of intelligence.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To achieve the intelligence achievement title of The Sharp, all you need to "
"do is to kill 100 Elementals. Manage this feat, and the title is yours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3539"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Loesva the Mage. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Smart, you must kill 10 Crypt Guards, 10 Deathless Mages, 10 "
"Black Knights and 10 Gravelords."

msgid "start_text_quest_354"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to the village of Valfather's Edge. The people here are mostly "
"weaponsmiths and armorsmiths who fuel their furnaces and forges with lava "
"from the active volcano which looms over town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Goods from Valfather's Edge are sold in shops throughout Dvergheim, and "
"beyond, and we are utterly dependent on keeping our trade routes open. "
"Unfortunately, a large tribe of goblins recently invaded from the wastelands "
"to the north, and until we can get rid of those green-skinned pests, they "
"remain a threat to merchants and other travelers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Needless to say, the local smiths and merchants are eager to see this threat "
"to their livelihood removed. Kill four goblins then return to me for a "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3540"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I believe you are ready to claim the third of the intelligence "
"achievement titles, that of The Smart. The title of The Smart is a difficult "
"title to attain, but surely will be a title to boast about, one you can "
"truly wear proudly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To claim the intelligence achievement title of The Smart, you will have to "
"kill 10 Crypt Guards, 10 Deathless Mages, 10 Black Knights and 10 "
"Gravelords. Something that might help you with this quest, is that Crypt "
"Guards are usually found inside dungeons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3541"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Jonn the Mage. To obtain the achievement "
"title of The Clever, you must kill 300 Zombies and 20 Dire Zombies."

msgid "start_text_quest_3542"
msgstr ""
