msgid "start_text_quest_3606"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Yaleria-Sai the Able. You are to travel to "
"the ice subcontinent of Niflheim, kill three Snowclan Dwarves, and return to "
"Yaleria-sai with your assessment of their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_3607"
msgstr ""
"You have performed quite well with your duties, and we believe that the time "
"has come to send our first scouting team to the ice continent of Niflheim."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have heard about a race of ice dwarves called the Snowclan. Those who "
"have managed to return from the ice subcontinent of Niflheim, talk about a "
"race of ice dwarves, much more vicious that our neighbors the dwarves of "
"Dvergheim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have information on two locations where these Snowclan Dwarves can be "
"found. I want you to travel across to the ice subcontinent of Niflheim, find "
"these Snowclan Dwarves, and kill three of them. When you have succeeded, "
"return here with your assessment of their strengths and weaknesses. We must "
"know what we are dealing with."

msgid "start_text_quest_3608"
msgstr ""
"Katila the Arcanist has asked you to gather two Elemental Quartz that "
"Samalon-tai needs to complete the deciphering of an ancient scroll."

msgid "start_text_quest_3609"
msgstr ""
"Welcome. I am Katila the Arcanist of the Circle of Neith. For over a month "
"now, I have been working very closely with Samalon-tai the Mage, to assist "
"him in deciphering an ancient scroll our agents had discovered a while ago. "
"It is believed that this ancient scroll will reveal to us the location of a "
"powerful but dangerous artifact.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Samalon-tai is very close in deciphering the ancient scroll. My part in "
"helping him is the gathering of various materials that Samalon-tai will need "
"to cast the final spell that will reveal the true meaning of the writing "
"upon the ancient scroll. Materials such as the Elemental Cinder you brought "
"to us while working closely with Yaleria-sai of the Longclaw.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one final ingredient that is needed, and that is Elemental Quartz. "
"Samalon-tai has requested that we find for him two units of Elemental "
"Quartz. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Northwest of here on Moonstone Coast, it is known that Earth Elementals can "
"be found. It is from these creatures that you could gather the two Elemental "
"Quartz that we need, to be able to decipher the ancient scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to gather two Elemental Quartz from the Earth "
"Elementals in {$g11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_361"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Yngfell's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to her with five mandrake herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_3610"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver a small package with ingredients that Katila "
"the Arcanist has prepared for Samalon-tai the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3611"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I want you to deliver this package here to Samalon-tai I have "
"prepared. In it are all the ingredients that Samalon-tai has asked for, so "
"he may complete the deciphering of the ancient scroll."

msgid "start_text_quest_3612"
msgstr ""
"Samalon-tai has asked you to search inside the {$j13} dungeon for the "
"missing scholar and retrieve the scholar's diary."

msgid "start_text_quest_3613"
msgstr "Deliver the diary of the fallen mahirim scholar to Samalon-tai."

msgid "start_text_quest_3614"
msgstr ""
"Although I have all the ingredients I need to begin the deciphering of the "
"ancient scroll, the casting of the spell required to decipher the ancient "
"writings is quiet a lengthy procedure. But until I do decipher the ancient "
"writings, there is something that you can do for me. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of our fellow scholars has been missing for over a week now. Before he "
"went missing, he had informed the Circle of Neith that he was heading into "
"the Larethain dungeon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to head for the Larethain dungeon, and to search "
"for our missing fellow scholar. Should you find his body, I want you to "
"retrieve from it his diary. All scholars that leave on an expedition, always "
"carry in them a diary, to keep an account of all that they come across. "
"Return with the diary, and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_3615"
msgstr ""
"Search the Aeodyth Nithron ruins for the King, the first of the guardian "
"statues, and cast a mana missile spell upon him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3616"
msgstr ""
"Search the Aeodyth Nithron ruins for the Defender, the second of the "
"guardian statues, and battle him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3617"
msgstr ""
"Search the Aeodyth Nithron ruins for the Scholar, the third of the guardian "
"statues, and drain him of his power."

msgid "start_text_quest_3618"
msgstr ""
"Return to the King, the first of the guardian statues before thirty minutes "
"have passed, and retrieve the Demon Ring."

msgid "start_text_quest_3619"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully found the Demon Ring. Return to Samalon-tai and give "
"him the ring."

msgid "start_text_quest_362"
msgstr ""
"With the exception of a few simple incantations, such as Mana Missile, all "
"spells are fuelled by ingredients which are expended during casting. New "
"spell ingredients are acquired as byproducts of harvesting processes, such "
"as skinning, mining and woodcutting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Agnor the Merchant's shop, which lies just inside the "
"southern gate. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3620"
msgstr ""
"The deciphering of the scroll is complete, and the ancient secreted  upon it "
"is now known to me. The scroll talks about a powerful ancient artifact "
"called the Ring of Power. This powerful artifact was created many centuries "
"ago by a powerful Demon Lord, who successfully combined the powers of two "
"other artifacts together, that of the Demon Ring and the Healing Gem.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Demon Ring would enhance its possessor with physical strength and the "
"ability to cast powerful necromantic spells, while the Healing Gem would "
"bless its owner with many immunities to diseases and the ability to cast "
"powerful healing spells.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"With the Ring of Power in his possession, the Demon Lord controlled vast "
"parts of central Agon, bringing pain and suffering to all. It was only until "
"a brave Nithron King decided to put an end to the Demon Lord's reign. The "
"Nithron King together with his army defeated the Demon Lord and took the "
"Ring of Power. It is written that this wise Nithron King decided to "
"separated the gem from the ring. He understood that the power of the ring "
"was so destructive, that no mortal would ever be able to control so much "
"power without becoming corrupted.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Healing Gem was hidden somewhere in southeast Agon, possibly in today's "
"human lands of Mercia, while the Demon Ring is hidden very close to the "
"Tribelands, in the region of {$h11}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is written that the Demon Ring is guarded by three of the many Nithron "
"statues that are found in the Nithron city in {$h11}. It is these three "
"guardian statues alone that hold the secret to its location. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have managed to uncovered the location of the first of the guardian "
"statues, also referred to as the King. You must go to this statue, the first "
"of the three, and cast a mana missile spell upon it. Doing this will reveal "
"a series of steps to the location of the gem. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, it is up to you, to follow the signs and find the gem. I can "
"help you by pointing out to you that the King, the first of the guardian "
"statues, is the only statue that shows a noble nithron warrior standing in "
"front of a lion. Remember, a mana missile spell cast upon the statue, is the "
"first step to bringing you closer to the location of the gem."

msgid "start_text_quest_3621"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Elders of Red Moon. You are to enter the "
"{$i16} dungeon, and search for the Book of Heroes. It is said that it is "
"safely hidden in a sarcophagus in one of the many Nithron rooms."

msgid "start_text_quest_3622"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Book of Heroes. Return to Amurranyr and deliver the book "
"to Symyr-dan."

msgid "start_text_quest_3623"
msgstr ""
"For the mahirim to become the powerful and proud race they are today, many "
"battles were fought, and many mahirim died. Most of these battles were "
"fought with the so called old races of Agon, who did not approve of the "
"rising of the mahirim race.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the most violent battles ever fought, was against the arrogant "
"mirdain. The mirdain had pushed well into the Tribelands, burning  and "
"destroying everything. Their goal was to destroy the morale of the mahirim "
"race, by erasing all reference of mahirim history. They destroyed statues, "
"burned important sites and stole historical items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mirdain knew that no nation can evolve and grow, if its people have no "
"past to build on, a proud an inspiring past such as that of our race. Every "
"strong nation needs to look back to see the sacrifices of its ancestors, to "
"value what they have today, but to also be inspired to continue to fight for "
"a better future.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It was in those violent times when the Elders decided that a number of "
"important religious and historical items be moved out of the Tribelands, and "
"hidden safely away into foreign lands. One of those items was the Book of "
"Heroes. This book is said to contain the names of many brave mahirim, be it "
"either warriors, priests, scholars or generals, that fought and sacrificed "
"their lives for creation of todays mahirim nation.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For a long time the hiding place of the Book of Heroes was lost to us, until "
"a scholar discovered a old stained book containing the locations of many "
"hidden historcal items, including that of the Book of Heroes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Southeast of here in the {$i16} region, there is a small Nithron site where "
"there is a portal that leads to a dungeon, a Nithron dungeon. According to "
"our findings, the Book of Hereos should be hidden within a sarcophagus in "
"one of the many Nithron rooms inside this dungeon. Your task #PlayerName# "
"will be to enter the {$i16} dungeon, find the Book of Heroes, and to return "
"it back here where it belongs. I will mark the position of the portal that "
"leads into the Nithron dungeon on your map. The rest is up to you."

msgid "start_text_quest_3624"
msgstr ""
"Symyr-dan has asked you to travel {$f15}, and remove three arthain from the "
"ancient site."

msgid "start_text_quest_3625"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Red Moon wish to send a group of researchers to the region of "
"{$f15}, to examine an ancient site that our scouts recently discovered. The "
"only problem is that the site in {$f15} are home to a group of arthain. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elders of Red Moon wish to clear the ancient site in {$f15} of the "
"arthain occupation. #PlayerName#, go to the ancient site in {$f15}, and kill "
"three of these arthain creatures."

msgid "start_text_quest_3626"
msgstr ""
"Symyr-dan has asked you to report to Naticia the Mage and to assist her with "
"her work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3627"
msgstr ""
"In the last few weeks, we have received reports about creatures migrating "
"into the surrounding lands. Creatures which until now were foreign to these "
"lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Why these creatures have chosen this time to migrate is a mystery, and the "
"Elders of Red Moon wish to gathering as much information possible on these "
"new neighbors. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Scouts have been sent out to discover possible causes behind these "
"migrations, while others are gathering information about these creatures. "
"Among those assigned to gather information on these new creatures, is "
"Naticia the Mage. I want you to report to Naticia the Mage, and to assist "
"her with her work."

msgid "start_text_quest_3628"
msgstr ""
"Naticia the Mage has asked you to gather three units of Greenleaf from the "
"Sarnakh."

msgid "start_text_quest_3629"
msgstr ""
"I have been assigned to collect information on many of the new creatures "
"that have recently migrated into the surrounding lands. The first of these "
"creatures that I want to analyze, are the Sarnakh, also called Flying "
"Snakes. It is said that from the bodies of the Sarnakh, Snake Greenleaf can "
"be harvested.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to assist me, then I ask of you to bring me three units of Snake "
"Greenleaf."

msgid "start_text_quest_363"
msgstr "You have accepted Hrafnid's quest. Return to her with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_3630"
msgstr ""
"Naticia the Mage has asked you to gather three units Cloudy Quartz from the "
"Brownies for her."

msgid "start_text_quest_3631"
msgstr ""
"Another of the creatures that has migrated recently into the surrounding "
"lands, are the Brownies. Brownies are one of the smallest and rarest "
"creatures found on Agon, and although not very dangerous, trying to located "
"and catch them can be quite a difficult and tricky task. Unfortunately for "
"the Brownies, their small bodies can be harvested for a specific material, "
"the Brownie Quartz.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have located a group of Brownies, in the region of {$f15}. If you "
"wish to assist me again, then I ask of you to bring me three Brownie Quartz."

msgid "start_text_quest_3632"
msgstr ""
"Naticia the Mage has asked you to gather two units of Ghostly Darktaint from "
"the Ghosts and Elfshades that haunt the ruins town in {$i15}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3633"
msgstr ""
"I have one more task for you, if you wish to continue to help me. Southeast "
"of here in {$i15}, there have been reports of ghost sighting. Ghosts and "
"Elfshades. Both are very dangerous, but also very rare to come by.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These apparitions have been sighted among the ruins of an old abandons town "
"that is said to once been occupied by minotaurs. It is likely that these "
"souls found a bitter death at the hands of the minotaurs, and now haunt the "
"ruin town attacking all those that disturb them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What I need is for somebody to travel to this haunted location in {$i15}, "
"and gather from these spirits, two units of Ghostly Darktaint and one unit "
"of Nith, while putting these tormented souls out of there misery. Do you "
"think you can do this for me?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3634"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai the Loyal has instructed you travel to the rogue city of "
"Hintenfau, and to seek the human Sister Lyrissa. Sister Lyrissa is prepared "
"to share information with the Wolfmasks, but for what price?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3635"
msgstr ""
"There is a human that is willing to share information with us, information "
"discerning the humans that have been infiltrating the Triblands. This human "
"goes by the name of Sister Lyrissa, and can be found in the rogue city of "
"Hintenfau. As our agents have informed me, Sister Lyrissa is prepared to "
"cooperate with us for a price.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to the rogue city of Hintenfau and talk to this Sister "
"Lyrissa. See if you can find out what it is that she so wants, in exchange "
"for the information that we seek.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I must warn you about Hintenfau. Hintenfau is a rogue city, with no laws of "
"any kind. You will come across the worse kind Agon has to offer. Even a "
"mihirim like yourself must be cautious. Do not trust anybody. Seek out this "
"Sister Lyrissa, and be quick with your dealing with this human."

msgid "start_text_quest_3636"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sister Lyrissa. You are to enter {$i11} "
"dungeon and find the hidden chest that holds the list of names Sister "
"Lyrissa wants. In exchange you will receive the information she has about "
"the humans within the Tribelands."

msgid "start_text_quest_3637"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully found the List of Names that Sister Lyrissa has asked "
"for. Exit the dungeon complex, and deliver the list to Sister Lyrissa in "
"Hintenfau."

msgid "start_text_quest_3638"
msgstr ""
"Do not be surprised that your superior Mardem-kai the Loyal has had to seek "
"my help in the past. For when it comes to humans, and especially information "
"regarding human activities within enemy lands, who knows better that Sister "
"Lyrissa.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Here within Hintenfau, everything has a price. Items, persons or "
"information. Everything can be bought, and everything can be sold. And from "
"what I see, Mardem-kai wishes to buy information. Information about the "
"growing number of humans infiltrating the Triblands. Yes, I known all about "
"it, and have known for a while.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now to business. The price you ask, the price for the information I have. "
"Yes, there is a price. I seek, no, there is an item I want! And you my dear "
"friend are going to get it for me. That is the price.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Within the Tribelands, in the {$i11} region, there is a portal that leads "
"into a dungeon complex. It is that dungeon complex that many humans are "
"using as a stronghold to build up a significant force. But, it is not the "
"humans themselves organizing this. This is the information I have, the "
"information you seek. But before I hand it to you, there is something I want."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to enter {$i11} dungeon, steal an item from the humans, and bring "
"it to me. Once you successfully delivered the item, I will give you the "
"information that  Mardem-kai so wants.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Inside {$i11} dungeon, there is a hidden and well guarded chest. And inside "
"this chest there is a list with names that I want. What these names are is "
"none of your business. All you need to know, is that I want that list.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will mark on your map the location of the portal that leads into {$i11} "
"dungeon. Once inside, it is up to you to find this chest, and retrieve the "
"list of name for me. Do not expect some grand reward from me. Once you "
"return to Mardem-kai with the information I will give you, I am sure he will "
"reward you well.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, it is pretty simple. Enter {$i11} dungeon, find the list with the names "
"on it, and bring it to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_3639"
msgstr ""
"Return to Nightspire to the Wolfmask headquarters, and deliver the letter "
"Sister Lyrissa gave you to Mardem-kai, with the information Mardem-kai so "
"seeks."

msgid "start_text_quest_364"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mountains and forests surrounding our town are teeming with green "
"skinned goblins, who are making quite a nuisance of themselves, raiding "
"farms and merchant caravans. While exterminating these invaders is priority "
"number one, we should also try to extract whatever benefits we can from the "
"situation, such as goblin teeth, which are used in several common "
"enchantment recipes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Agnor the Merchant's shop here in Valfather's "
"Edge.  Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should be able to "
"successfully remove intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_3640"
msgstr ""
"Since you kept your part of the bargain, so shall I. Here is the information "
"I promised I would deliver to my dear friend Mardem-kai.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is the Cult of the Moon-Beast that is planting the outcast humans within "
"the Tribelands. The goal is to create as many distractions as possible, so "
"the Cult may find an opportunity to attack and destroy the Elders of Red "
"Moon. They know that it is the Elders who are the soul and driving force "
"behind the mahirims progress and advancement as a race. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, it is not all that simple. Beyond the borders of the Tribelands, things "
"are even more complicated. The Cult itself seems to have allied itself with "
"a new dark power, referred to as the Dark Lord. There is a dark unknown "
"power that has emerged in the heart of the central plains. A power that is "
"slowly destroying all natural life, and changing the central plains into "
"what I believe is a mirror image of its own world. This Dark Lord, new dark "
"threat, is slowly spreading further and further across Agon. And although "
"the Cult of the Moon-Beast worships the sinister deity called the Moon-"
"Beast, the Dark Lord has somehow managed to sway the Cult to its cause, at "
"least for now.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have a letter here for you to deliver to Mardem-kai. In it is information "
"about the human activities within the Tribelands, the Cult's plans, but also "
"any information my men have gathered about this Dark Lord that has emerged "
"with in the heart of the central plains.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I suggest that you hurry back to Nightspire, and hand this information to "
"Mardem-kai. My advice would be to deal with the Cult of the Moon-Beast for "
"now, cutting off any ties they have this new dark conquerer of the central "
"plains. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I always enjoy doing business with the mahirim, and especially with Mardem-"
"kai. Give him my regards when you see him."

msgid "start_text_quest_3641"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai want you to search the moonbeast cultist village is {$m12}, for "
"any clues that might show a possible connection between the Dark Lord and "
"the Cult of the Moon-Beast."

msgid "start_text_quest_3642"
msgstr ""
"Return to Mardem-kai and report your finding about the tombstone with "
"strange symbols carved upon it, located within the cultist village in {$m12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_3643"
msgstr ""
"Based on the information given to us by Sister Lyrissa, we now know most of "
"the locations of the human hideouts within the tribelands. It is also as we "
"had suspected, that the humans are being used by the Cult of the Moon-Beast. "
"But this new information, that the Cult of the Moon-Beast is being "
"manipulated by a new dark power, this Dark Lord that has emerged from within "
"the central plains troubles me. What power? What Dark Lord? From where? And "
"what does it want?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to the information given to us by Sister Lyrissa, there should be "
"a cultist village located to the northeast of here, in {$m12}. It is there "
"within that cultist village that this Dark Lord came in contact with the "
"cult. Sister Lyrissa mentions that the Dark Lord may be using some kind of "
"controlling device, possibly in the form of a tombstone. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Before we send this information to Red Moon, we must gather information "
"about the cult's activities, and its connection with this new growing power "
"of the central plains. I want you to travel to {$m12}, enter the moonbeast "
"cultist village, and search for anything that will give us a better "
"understanding of the cult's plans, but mostly on this new ally of theirs, "
"this Dark Lord of the central plains. Upon discovering something that might "
"offer any insight, use the action button to investigate more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_3644"
msgstr ""
"The Wolfmasks want you to kill ten members of the Cult of the Moon-Beast. "
"Where and how you find them, is up to you.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3645"
msgstr ""
"Every single problem that lately arises with the triblands, seems to somehow "
"be connected to the Cult of the Moon-Beast. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Can they not see, that if it wasn't for the visions and sacrifices of great "
"individuals such as the prophet king Amurran, that the mahirim race wold "
"have not become the powerful and proud race that we are today. Do they so "
"fear progress? Are they so blind and weak?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Enough with the Cult of the Moon-Beast and their obsession with destroying "
"everything that the Elders of Red Moon have accomplished. They have taken up "
"to much of our time. Enough is enough! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Wolfmasks want you to go and kill ten members of the Cult of the Moon-"
"Beast within three hours. I don't care where and how you find them, just go "
"out there and kill ten of them. Do this, and you will be well rewarded. "
"We'll show them which is the real dark power they should be fearing!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You have three hours to kill ten members of the Cult of the Moon-Beast."

msgid "start_text_quest_3646"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver a report letter from Mardem-kai to Tivasta the "
"Councillor in Red Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_3647"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this detailed report letter to Tivasta the Councillor "
"in Red Moon. I have written in detail all that we have discovered about the "
"human activities with in the tribelands, but also all we have learned about "
"the Dark Lord and the demonic tombstone. In this report I am also sending a "
"copy of the strange symbols you found carved upon the tombstone within the "
"cultist village. Maybe somebody in Red Moon might be able to decipher them."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, the Wolfmasks are proud to have work with you once more. You "
"are truly somebody that we can really on."

msgid "start_text_quest_3648"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to travel to {$k19} and to harvest three units of Cloudy "
"Quartz, so Seirinna the Mage could begin the process of destroying the Orb "
"of Disease."

msgid "start_text_quest_3649"
msgstr ""
"I want you to go and gather three units of Brownie Quartz. If the powerful "
"mage Siledin was correct, Brownie Quartz is one of the materials needed to "
"destroy the Orb of Disease. But to acquire a Brownie Quartz, you must first "
"find and hunt down the small, rare and elusive brownies. Luckily for you, a "
"few days ago one of our scouts had spotted brownies in the region of {$k19}."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to {$k19}, and to gather three units of Brownie Quartz."

msgid "start_text_quest_365"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Hrafnid's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3650"
msgstr ""
"Seirinna the Mage has asked you to travel to {$j17}, and to gather three "
"units of Caustic Bile."

msgid "start_text_quest_3651"
msgstr ""
"According to the notes left behind by the powerful mage Siledin, for the Orb "
"of Disease to be destroyed a powerful spell must be cast that will require "
"unique materials. One of the materials is Sarlid Bile. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Fueled by venom coursing through their veins, these strange humanoids will "
"attack anybody approaching them with lunatic ferocity. Gathering bile from "
"the Sarlids will not be simple task. But if Sarlid Bile is required to "
"destroy the orb, then Sarlid Bile we must collect.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the north of here, the {$j17} region is known for the groups of Sarlids "
"that live there. If you wish you help me once more, three units of Sarlid "
"Bile will be enough."

msgid "start_text_quest_3652"
msgstr ""
"Seirinna the Mage has asked you to travel to {$j21}, and to gather two units "
"of Gloomy Darktaint from the arthain."

msgid "start_text_quest_3653"
msgstr ""
"Resonant Stormrune is the final material that is needed, to destroy the Orb "
"of Disease. As with the previous materials you gathered, Resonant Stormrunes "
"can be harvested from the bodies of powerful creatures. Unfortunately for "
"us, one of the few creatures that can be harvest for Resonant Stormrunes are "
"the arthain. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The arthain are a paranoid and hateful race, who see all outsiders as little "
"more than necromantic raw material. The arthain were once a peaceful and "
"civilized race, but when they lost the ability to procreate, they resorted "
"to extending their lives by using a combination of fleshcrafting and "
"necromancy. The use of these necromantic methods over centuries, has driven "
"the arthain society to the degraded state in which it is today. The arthain "
"continue to be considered extremely dangerous, and retain many of their "
"spellcasting abilities.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the south of here in {$j21}, you can find groups of arthian. I want you "
"to gather for me two units of Resonant Stormrunes."

msgid "start_text_quest_3654"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver a package that contains the Orb of Disease "
"together with materials and notes, to Aelathil Silverleaf of the Serene "
"Spire in Iriendir."

msgid "start_text_quest_3655"
msgstr ""
"The Orb of Disease must be delivered to the Serene Spire where it can be "
"destroyed. The Serene Spire is the safest place to conduct the powerful "
"spell that will destroy the evil artifact, but also to confine its powers if "
"anything were to go wrong. The sages and scholars of the Serene Spire are "
"the most experienced in dealing with dangerous items, such as the Orb of "
"Disease.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I would like you to deliver this package that contains the Orb "
"of Disease with the all the materials and notes I have prepared. Once you "
"reach the Serene Spire in Iriendir, hand over the package to Aelathil "
"Silverleaf. She will know what to do. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I thank you for all you have done."

msgid "start_text_quest_3656"
msgstr ""
"Eredethil Swiftarrow has asked you to travel to the Ciel Fey village in "
"{$l17}, and to search for any clues regarding the missing Arrowhead agent, "
"Annabell Lightheart."

msgid "start_text_quest_3657"
msgstr ""
"You found the missing Arrowhead agent, but unfortunately too late. What you "
"did manage to recover from the dead agent, was her Arrowhead signet ring. "
"Bring the agent's signet ring to Eredethil Swiftarrow in Krisathel."

msgid "start_text_quest_3658"
msgstr ""
"It has been over ten days now, since we last received word from our agent "
"Annabell Lightheart. Annabell was sent on a mission to gather information "
"regarding a Ciel Fey village in {$l17}. She was to survey the Ciel Fey "
"village, and return with information of the village layout, their numbers, "
"who the Ciel Fey might be working with. We have yet to receive word from "
"Annabell, and it is not like her to be late. I fear that something might "
"have gone wrong.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to {$l17} and to locate our agent. If you fail to "
"locate her, search for any clues that might supply any information on the "
"whereabouts of Annabell, or what might have become of her. Upon discovering "
"anything that you might consider useful, return here to Krisathel and report "
"your findings."

msgid "start_text_quest_3659"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. Search the beastman "
"village in {$l18}, for any kind of strange tombstone with demonic writings "
"upon it."

msgid "start_text_quest_366"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, most goblins share an irrational fear of magic. We "
"should try to exploit this fear in our efforts to drive the invading goblins "
"out. \r\n"
" \r\n"
"Every dwarf who travels through goblin territory is asked to cast twenty "
"Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to jog their memory of the fact that "
"all dwarves master at least some of the more rudimentary magical skills.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Yngfell's, here in Valfather's Edge. Once you own a "
"staff, you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your "
"character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_3660"
msgstr ""
"Many are the rumors of lately, that talk about strange tombstones appearing "
"throughout Agon. These rumors talk about demonic symbols and writings carved "
"upon these strange tombstones that appeared out of nowhere. Some even say "
"that whispers could be hear coming from these tombstone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Agents have been sent to search and locate these strange tombstones. If "
"these tombstone do exist, we need to see what is written upon them. We must "
"discover who or what has planted these tombstones, and why.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Such a tombstone is believed to exist somewhere near or inside the beastman "
"village in {$l18}. We need somebody to enter and search the beastman "
"village, to verify the existence of the demonic tombstone, and to make a "
"copy of the symbols or wittings upon it. Once we are sure of the existence "
"of the tombstone, and have a copy of these symbols, we will inform Charybdis."
"\r\n"
" \r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go an search the beastman village in {$l18}, "
"search for this tombstone, and if you find it to make a copy of the symbols "
"carved upon it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3661"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. Deliver a copy of the "
"ancient writings from the tombstone to Nairath the Mage in Charybdis."

msgid "start_text_quest_3662"
msgstr ""
"The writings upon the tombstone you copied earlier from the beastman village "
"in {$l18}, are like nothing I have ever seen. Charybdis must be informed "
"about this find. It is imperative that we learn who or what is placing these "
"tombstones, and why. We must learn what exactly these tombstones are, if at "
"all they are tombstones.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Nairath the Mage is an expert in deciphering ancient texts. I want you to "
"report to him and hand over the copy of the writings from the tombstone, and "
"see if he is able to decipher the symbols. Hurry now, I have a bad feeling "
"about this."

msgid "start_text_quest_3663"
msgstr ""
"Nairath the Mage has asked you to travel to the Emerald Throne in Imathir, "
"and bring back his book that Riathen the Mage has forgotten to return."

msgid "start_text_quest_3664"
msgstr ""
"The deciphering of the demonic texts and symbols will take me some time. "
"Meanwhile, there is something you can do for me. I need you to go to the "
"Emerald Throne in Imathir, and bring back to me a book my deer friend "
"Riathen the Mage has forgotten to return to me. By the time you have "
"returned, I should have deciphered the symbols and writings."

msgid "start_text_quest_3665"
msgstr ""
"Riathen of the Emerald Throne has handed you Nairath's book. You are to "
"return to Chaybdis, and give the book back the Nairath the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3666"
msgstr "Here it is. Nairath's book. Tell Nairath I am so sorry."

msgid "start_text_quest_3667"
msgstr ""
"Nairath the Mage has deciphered the demonic writing and symbols from the "
"strange tombstone. He has given you a letter containing the complete "
"translation of the demonic writings to deliver to Eredathil Swiftarrow in "
"Krisathel."

msgid "start_text_quest_3668"
msgstr ""
"I have good news and I have bad news. The good news is that I have "
"successfully deciphered the demonic symbols from the tombstone. The bad news "
"is that the symbols and writings talk about the Dark Lord of Agon, a "
"powerful figure that will emerge from within the central plains. From what I "
"understand, the so called Dark Lord of Agon, is most likely a powerful devil "
"or demon that has somehow managed to find a way into our world.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the writings I deciphered, the Dark Lord promises power and wealth for "
"those that will obey, and that death awaits all those that will not serve "
"the new lord. But was trouble me is that this evil figure is never referred "
"to by any name, rather only as the Dark Lord of Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I believe that the tombstones are somehow used to attract and possibly even "
"control future servants of this Dark Lord. Hence the reports that some could "
"hear whispers coming from them. I imagine that the more primitive creatures "
"of lower intelligence that are in need of power, recognition and guidance, "
"are perfect candidates for the Dark Lord of the central plains, if any of "
"this is true of course.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You must return with the deciphered text to Krisathel, and deliver it to "
"Eredethil Swiftarrow. I will inform the authorities here in Charybdis, and "
"also send messages immediately to all other factions. If any of this is "
"true, we must all by prepared. Mirdain, humans and dwarves.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, please deliver this letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow."

msgid "start_text_quest_3669"
msgstr ""
"Eredethil Swiftarrow has no other choice but to seek further information, "
"about the Dark Lord of the central plains, from Sister Lyrissa in Hintenfau. "
"He has assigned you to travel to Hintenfau, and report to Sister Lyrissa."

msgid "start_text_quest_3670"
msgstr ""
"We need to learn anything and everything we can about this Dark Lord. And we "
"need to gather as much information as possible from all sources, on what is "
"happening within the central plains. If there is any information on this "
"growing dark threat, Sister Lyrissa in Hintenfau will surely know.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will need of you to travel to Hintenfau, and speak with Sister Lyrissa. "
"You are to ask her for information regarding the tombstones, and the Dark "
"Lord. Sister Lyrissa is as smart and tricky as they come, so do not let her "
"appearance fool you. No information enters or leaves Hintenfau without "
"Sister Lyrissa knowing about it. She will not hand over any information for "
"free, so be prepared to do some kind of favor in exchange.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Before you leave, I must warn you about Hintenfau. It is a city without any "
"laws, without any form of order. It is a city completely covered in chaos. "
"No god, king, or race rules within Hintenfau. It is a city were only the "
"strong and smart survive. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you accept to travel to Hintenfau, do not waste anytime "
"wandering aimlessly within Hintenfau. Almost everybody in that city will see "
"you as an enemy. You quickly go in, speak with Sister Lyrissa, do as she "
"asks of you, get the information we seek, and return. Once you have returned "
"with the information, you will be well rewarded. This will be a dangerous "
"mission, so be well prepared."

msgid "start_text_quest_3671"
msgstr ""
"To obtain the information Eredathil seeks from sister Lyrissa, you have "
"agreed to kill three of the Shroud Knight that have taken over the small "
"town of Serpenton."

msgid "start_text_quest_3672"
msgstr ""
"Hanthar Blackfrost has asked you to search the severii city on mount {$j23}, "
"for any clues or signs that might explain the sudden appearance of the fire "
"creatures within the severii city."

msgid "start_text_quest_3673"
msgstr ""
"There is something mysterious happening in the {$j23} region. For a long "
"time now I have been searching to discover why the severii stronghold on "
"mount {$j23} is occupied by numerous fire creatures. For centuries, {$j23} "
"and in particular mount {$j23} has been part of the domain of the skeleton "
"dragon god Cyriacus. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The skeleton dragon god Cyriacus has always been an enemy of Melek and the "
"alfar, and together with his minions the severii, the skeleton dragon god "
"has done all he can to annoy the alfar. The disappearance of the severii "
"from the stronghold on mount {$j23} is something that greatly pleases me, "
"but this new occupation of the city by the fire creatures puzzles me. The "
"severii are the minions of the skeleton dragon god Cyriacus, and Cyriacus "
"would not allow any other creatures to dwell within any of his city.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to travel to mount {$j23}, and search for any clues as to why and "
"how these fire creatures are allowed inside one of Cyriacus's cities. If by "
"any means Cyriacus has somehow recruited these creatures, we must learn how "
"and why. What can the skeleton dragon god Cyriacus be planning?"

msgid "start_text_quest_3674"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ninnah the Mage. Search the Nithron City in "
"{$p22}, for any signs of Ninnah's missing apprentice."

msgid "start_text_quest_3675"
msgstr ""
"You  find the missing apprentice, but unfortunately it's too late. What you "
"do manage to recover from the dead appreciate, is a diary. Return to Shoal, "
"and deliver the apprentice's diary to Ninnah the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3676"
msgstr ""
"While I decipher the text you brought back from Espenhal, there is something "
"you can do for me. My apprentice has not returned from her little expedition "
"into the Nithron ruins in {$p22}. She had found an old tome that spoke of a "
"statue somewhere in the Nithron city, that would reveal the secret location "
"of a minor artifact. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to {$p22}, and search my apprentice. Should you in the "
"worst case find the body of apprentice, bring me back her dairy. I would "
"like to see if my foolish apprentice did discover anything at all."

msgid "start_text_quest_3677"
msgstr ""
"Ninnah the Mage has asked you to deliver her report letter to Aeshanta "
"Darkspire of the Harn Mandean in Dulguna."

msgid "start_text_quest_3678"
msgstr ""
"The deciphering of the demonic writings is complete. The writings talk about "
"the coming of the Dark Lord, a powerful figure that will emerge from within "
"the heart of Agon to conquer all. It will begin with the servants of the "
"Dark Lord that will prepare the lands for their master's arrival. They will "
"begin by slowly transforming the lands into a mirror image of that of their "
"master's world, while others will begin the process of converting many of "
"the inhabitants of this world, to the cause of their master's. The Dark Lord "
"promises wealth and power to all those that will obey, and that only death "
"awaits all those that will not.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I believe that the tombstones, like the one you discovered in Sallesh, could "
"be a kind of mind controlling devices, used to attract and possibly even "
"control future followers of this Dark Lord.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If any of this is true, the Dark Lord, which I believe is a powerful demon, "
"must have somehow found a way into our world. Deliver this letter to the "
"Harn Mandean and hand it to Aeshanta Darkspire. I will inform the "
"authorities here in Shoal and all other factions to search for any more of "
"these demon tombstones. We need to learn more about this Dark Lord."

msgid "start_text_quest_3679"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the rogue city of Hintenfau. There, you will "
"report to Sister Lyrissa, and try to gather as much information possible "
"about the Dark Lord."

msgid "start_text_quest_3680"
msgstr ""
"We will immediately sent agents to scout the lands for more of these demon "
"tombstones. Meanwhile, we must learn more about this Dark Lord. "
"Unfortunately, the only person I can think about, that might have any "
"information about this Dark Lord, and all that is unfolding within the "
"central plains, is that sly and tricky human Sister Lyrissa in Hintenfau.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to travel to Hintenfau, and learn all you call about "
"this Dark Lord from Sister Lyrissa. Do whatever is necessary to acquire any "
"information. When it comes to gathering any information from Sister Lyrissa, "
"it comes at a cost. If that annoying Sister Lyrissa asks of you something, "
"do it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Return with any useful information, and you will be well rewarded. Now go!"

msgid "start_text_quest_3681"
msgstr ""
"In order to retrieve the information Sister Lyrissa has on the Dark Lord and "
"all that might be happening within the central plains, you have accepted to "
"search the Ciel Fey Village in {$n17}, for Sister Lyrissa's stolen magical "
"box."

msgid "start_text_quest_3682"
msgstr ""
"You have found Sister's Lyrissa's magical box within the Ciel Fey village in "
"{$n17}. Return to Hintenfau and deliver the box to Sister Lyrissa."

msgid "start_text_quest_3683"
msgstr ""
"Dark Lord, demonic tombstones, central plains, yes yes, I know about these "
"things. And of course you want me to share this information with you, and "
"with the alfar. And do you know what? I will. But not before you get to do a "
"little something for me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This is Hintenfau, and nothing enters of leaves without me knowing. Be it "
"either, weapons, goods or information. You have my dear friend, are looking "
"for information.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, one of the caravans I was expecting was intercepted by the Ciel Fey in "
"{$n17}, and all of my goods were stolen. Most of those were just simple "
"supplies, things which I will manage to live without. But among all those "
"that were stolen, was an item, which is very dear to me. A small magical "
"box. What this box is or contains inside, is none of your business. Either "
"way, neither you of the Ciel Fey can open it. It is magically locked. All "
"you need to do, is to find it and bring it back to me. Do this for me, and I "
"will give you the information your superiors seek, and a small reward for "
"your efforts too.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, it is pretty simple. You go to the Ciel Fey village in {$n17}, and bring "
"me back my little box of magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_3684"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully managed to extract from Sister Lyrissa, the "
"information she has gathered about the Dark Lord. Return to the Harn Mandean "
"in Dulguna, and deliver the letter Sister Lyrissa gave you to Aeshanta "
"Darkspire."

msgid "start_text_quest_3685"
msgstr ""
"Very well. You did as I asked for and found my little magical box, and in "
"return I did say I would provide you and your superiors with all the "
"information I have on this Dark Lord.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This is the information me and my men have gathered so far. There is a dark "
"unknown power that has or will emerge from the central plains. A power that "
"is referred to for now as the Dark Lord. From what we have discovered, we "
"believe that this Dark Lord is a powerful demon, that has somehow found a "
"way into our world. Although we have no signs that the Dark Lord has yet "
"arrived, we believe that many the demon's servants are already here on Agon, "
"preparing for the Dark Lord's arrival. Where and when we do not know yet, "
"but we believe that the dark fortress that has appeared in the central Agon, "
"might be connected somehow to this demon. Over the last few years, the "
"central plains have slowly been transformed into this dark, pale and misty "
"environment that they are today. This could be part of the process, "
"preparing for the Dark Lord's arrival.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"About the tombstone you were asking earlier. We have uncovered a dozen of "
"these demon tombstones, in the lands surrounding the central plains. And we "
"are sure that many more are scattered throughout Agon. Many are the rumors "
"surrounding the demon tombstones. There are even those that insist they have "
"heard whisperers coming from the tombstones. Whispers that promise vast "
"amount of power and wealth, for all that will follow and obey the Dark Lord. "
"We have also come to the conclusion, that these tombstones could actually be "
"some kind of device, that the demon is using to recruit many of the monster "
"racers of Agon, to possibly form an army.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have prepared a letter here with all the information I have on the Dark "
"Lord. This is what your superiors are after, is it not? Go now, and return "
"to Dulgune. I suspect that Aeshanta Darkspire eagerly is waiting for your "
"return."

msgid "start_text_quest_3686"
msgstr ""
"Travel to the nithron ruins in {$p22}, and search for a hidden artifact "
"through a series of steps. First you must find the scholar and blast him "
"with enough mana missiles to activate him"

msgid "start_text_quest_3687"
msgstr ""
"To get closer to the hidden artifact within the nithron city, the statue of "
"the nithron scholar has asked of you to bring him five of each which a "
"spellcaster needs."

msgid "start_text_quest_3688"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully gathered five of each reagent for the scholar, and now "
"you must search for the shrine of the dragons and drain it of its power."

msgid "start_text_quest_3689"
msgstr ""
"You have cast a mana drain spell onto the Shrine of the Dragons and "
"temporarily drained it of its power. Search for the one who faces the golden "
"spire, and retrieve the artifact.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3690"
msgstr ""
"By following the steps and solving the riddle of the nithron city of {$p22}, "
"you have uncovered the Rod of Dragon Fire. Return to Shoal, and deliver the "
"rod the Ninnah the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3691"
msgstr ""
"According to the diary, it would seem that my dear apprentice was searching "
"for a powerful artifact hidden somewhere within the nithron city of {$p22}. "
"Although I don't place much faith on the findings of my apprentice, I cannot "
"let go of the notion that there might actually be some truth to this. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to my apprentice, the artifact can be located following a series "
"of steps hidden in the nithron city. In the diary there is only reference to "
"the first step, which is to find the scholar that stands nearby the nithron "
"building with the empty throne room. Casting a number of mana missiles upon "
"the scholar should be trigger a series of step.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to travel to {$p22} to the nithron city, and to "
"search for this artifact. I suggest that we try out this first step "
"described in my apprentice's diary. Search for the nithron building with the "
"empty throne room, and try to active the scholar with a series of mana "
"missile. How many I don't know. Whatever the outcome, I would like a full "
"report of your findings."

msgid "start_text_quest_3692"
msgstr ""
"Aeshanta Darkspire has given you a series of steps written by Ninnah the "
"Mage, on how to possibly disable the magical properties of the demon "
"tombstone. The first step is to place seven units of sulfur and seven units "
"of resin upon the demon tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3693"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the first step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast a Rend spell upon the "
"tombstone to bring out its powers."

msgid "start_text_quest_3694"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Rend spell onto the demon tombstone, brought "
"out its powers, and completed the second step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place seven units of blood, "
"five bones and one heart upon the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3695"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of blood, five bones and one heart upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the third step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast the Flesh Curse spell "
"onto the tombstone to weaken the powers of the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3696"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Flesh Curse spell onto the demon tombstone, "
"weakened its powers, and completed the fourth step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place ten units of ash upon "
"the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3697"
msgstr ""
"You have placed ten units of ash upon the demon tombstone, and completed the "
"fifth step to disabling the magical properties of the demon tombstone. Now "
"you must cast the Mana Drain spell onto the tombstone to remove all magical "
"properties from it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3698"
msgstr ""
"While you were away, an interesting letter arrived from our friend Ninnah "
"the Mage. It seems that Ninnah has continued her research into the "
"mysterious demonic tombstones, together with help from the Radiant Circle. "
"According to the Ninnah the Mage, the demonic tombstones can have their "
"powers disabled, therefor removing the Dark Lord's ability to communicate "
"and recruit monsters. Ninnah has given us a series of steps, that if "
"executed should render the demonic tombstones useless.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The first step is that seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin to be "
"placed upon the tombstone. The second step is for a Rend spell to be cast "
"afterwards upon the tombstone. This is to bring out the powers of the "
"tombstone and make the demonic tombstone vulnerable. Third step. Seven units "
"of blood, five bones and one heart must be placed on the tombstone. Fourth "
"step, a Flesh Curse spell must be cast on the tombstone. This is to weaken "
"the powers of the tombstone. Fifth step. Ten units of ash need to be placed "
"upon the tombstone. Sixth and final step, a mana drain spell cast upon the "
"demon tombstone should permanently remove the demon tombstones magical "
"abilities. Once you have disabled the demon tombstones magical properties, "
"return here with a completed report.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now go, and put an end to these annoying tombstones."

msgid "start_text_quest_3699"
msgstr ""
"You are not the first visiting me, wanting to acquire information about the "
"Dark Lord. Yes, I have heard the rumors of the coming of the Dark Lord. And "
"yes, I have heard of the tombstones with the demonic writing, whispering "
"promises of wealth and power beyond imagination. Lies, that the weak are "
"willing to believe in. If you ask me, the only wealth and power I believe in "
"is gold! Lot's of it. But you have come hear to me seeking information. Do "
"something for me, and I will give you the information your superiors seek. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the north of here in Serpenton, exists a small town that is occupied by "
"Shroud Knights. There is a noble, who has a grudge with these Shroud Knight. "
"You see, the small town the Shroud Knight are now living in, once belonged "
"to this wealthy and powerful human noble. The noble, who happens to be my "
"client, wishes to retake the small town. But, for this to be achieved, first "
"the Shroud Knights must be dealt with. Kill three Shroud Knights, and the "
"information you seek will be yours."

msgid "start_text_quest_3700"
msgstr ""
"Sister Lyrissa has kept her word, and has given you the information on the "
"Dark Lord, that Eredathil Swiftarrow has asked for. Return to Krisathel, and "
"deliver Sister Lyrissa'a letter to Eredathil Swiftarrow."

msgid "start_text_quest_3701"
msgstr ""
"You did all I asked for, and therefor the information you seek about the "
"Dark Lord is now yours. There is a dark unknown power that will or has "
"emerged in the heart of the central plains. A power, for now known as the "
"Dark Lord, that threatens to conquer all of Agon. I believe that this Dark "
"Lord is a powerful demon, that has somehow found a way into our world. We "
"have no signs yet of the Dark Lord's arrival, but we have evidence that "
"servants of the Dark Lord are already here on Agon, preparing for their "
"master's arrival. The transformation of the central region, into the dark, "
"pale and misty land it has become today, seems to be part the process for "
"preparing for the Dark Lord's arrival. And this new dark threat, this new "
"power, is slowly spreading further and further across Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Also, there is the issue of the tombstones. My men have found many of these "
"tombstones in the lands surrounding the central region. Many are the rumors "
"surrounding the demon tombstones. There are even those that talk about "
"whisperers coming from the tombstones. Whispers that promise vast amounts of "
"power and wealth for all that will follow and obey the Dark Lord. We believe "
"these tombstones are used as devices to control the new followers of the "
"dark lord.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I have a letter here, with all the information I and my men "
"have gathered in full detail. Yes, deliver this letter to Eredathil and the "
"mirdain. We must all be prepared for this Dark Lord, in the slightest chance "
"that any of this is true. Now go, do now waste time."

msgid "start_text_quest_3702"
msgstr ""
"Eredathil Swiftarrow has given you a series of steps written by Nairath the "
"Mage, on how to disable the magical properties of the demon tombstone. The "
"first step is to place seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin upon "
"the demon tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3703"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the first step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast a Rend spell upon the "
"tombstone to bring out its powers."

msgid "start_text_quest_3704"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Rend spell onto the demon tombstone, brought "
"out its powers, and completed the second step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place seven units of blood, "
"five bones and one heart upon the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3705"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of blood, five bones and one heart upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the third step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast the Flesh Curse spell "
"onto the tombstone to weaken the powers of the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3706"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Flesh Curse spell onto the demon tombstone, "
"weakened its powers, and completed the fourth step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place ten units of ash upon "
"the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_3707"
msgstr ""
"You have placed ten units of ash upon the demon tombstone, and completed the "
"fifth step to disabling the magical properties of the demon tombstone. Now "
"you must cast the Mana Drain spell onto the tombstone to remove all magical "
"properties from it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3708"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that while we were searching for information about this Dark "
"Lord and the tombstones, Nairath the Mage in Charybdis did a little "
"researching of his own. According to the Nairath the Mage, the demonic "
"tombstones can have their powers disabled, therefor removing the dark lords "
"abilities to recruit monsters. Nairath has written here a series of steps "
"that need to be done, in order to render the demonic tombstones useless.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Here are the steps. First step. Seven units of sulfur and seven units of "
"resin need to be placed upon the tombstone. Second step, a Rend spell must "
"be immediately cast upon the tombstone. This is to bring out the powers of "
"the tombstone and make the demonic tombstone vulnerable. Third step. Seven "
"units of blood, five bones and one heart must be placed on the tombstone. "
"Fourth step, a Flesh Curse spell must be cast on the tombstone. This is to "
"weaken the powers of the tombstone. Fifth step. Ten units of ash need to be "
"placed upon the tombstone. Sixth and final step, a mana drain spell cast "
"upon the demon tombstone should permanently remove the demon tombstones "
"magical abilities. Once you have disabled the demon tombstones magical "
"properties, return here with a completed report."

msgid "start_text_quest_3709"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tialanta the Fighter. Kill five Dwarven "
"player characters in less than five hours.\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_3710"
msgstr ""
"To the far north is Dvergheim, land of the dwarves, that stocky race of "
"warriors and crafters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many are the story of legendary dwarven warriors. Warriors that would not "
"abandon the battlefield, and that would fight to the death. Warriors that "
"could stand up to the best of the alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To fight and kill a dwarven warrior is a feat in it self. But you "
"#PlayerName#, are better than that. You are search for these dwarves, and "
"kill five of them in less than five hours. Manage this feat, I will truly "
"acknowledge your superior abilities. Prove to me once and for all, that you "
"are a superior alfar. It is you how must become a legendary warrior.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now go, and kill five Dwarven player characters before five hours have "
"passed."

msgid "start_text_quest_3711"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thora the Merchant. Bring back to Thora six "
"unit of meat, from either hunting deer, fox or any other animal. You will "
"need a skinner for this quest."

msgid "start_text_quest_3712"
msgstr ""
"It is that time of the year, where we hire hunters to go out and hunt for "
"meat. We organize the hunters around this time of the year, because of the "
"many groups of deer and fox that pass near our lands. Both the deer and fox "
"can be harvested for their meat. #PlayerName#, meat is one of the main "
"sources of food for the majority of our people, and we must keep our people "
"fed and happy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help us gather the meat we need, by gathering six units of meat. "
"Hunting either deer, fox, or any other animal does not really matter. If you "
"accept, you will have to track down the prey yourself. I cannot mark their "
"exact location on your map, because most of these animal are always on the "
"move. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring back six units of meat, and you will be rewarded well for your "
"services. Don't forget to take along your skinning knife."

msgid "start_text_quest_3713"
msgstr ""
"In order to start training Sandbrook's next batch of archers, William the "
"Councillor has requested that you gather five shortbows and twenty arrows, "
"and deliver them to Catherine the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3714"
msgstr ""
"It is obvious that Sandrook will have to be better prepared in the future to "
"withstand many more attacks and invasions, be it either from goblin hordes, "
"raiding orks, or any other enemy. Sending out brave warriors to slay the "
"goblins, or strengthening our wall, are only some of the many things that we "
"can do. We must also continue preparing new warriors, to protect our town "
"and its people in the future. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Catherine the Fighter will be the one training these young warriors. "
"According to Catherine, it is not in our best interest to use our finest "
"equipment for training purposes. Fortunately, Catherine has come up with an "
"excellent idea. What we can do, is to collect the weapons of our enemies, "
"and to use them as training weapons for our young warriors.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Catherine the Fighter is to soon begin training Sandbrook's new archers. To "
"train them, many bows and arrows will be needed. We have noticed that the "
"goblin scouts, who are the majority of the attacking goblins, favor the use "
"of the shortbow. It is these bows that we will be using for training "
"purposes.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to gather five shortbows and twenty arrows, and to "
"deliver them to Catherine the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3715"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to have your archery skills put to the test by Catherine "
"the Fighter. You must succeed in hitting the goblins twenty times with your "
"arrows."

msgid "start_text_quest_3716"
msgstr ""
"Thank you for bringing earlier those bows and arrows. They will definitely "
"be put to good use by our young trainee archers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Archery is a vital part of combat, be it either attacking or defending. When "
"attacking, he who is well trained in the art of archery, has a huge "
"advantage against his opponent. He can manage a many attacks against his "
"opponent, before needing to draw his sword to engage in hand to hand combat. "
"But it is also one of the best ways to defend a town or city from behind the "
"cover of its strong solid walls.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to be tested in the art of archery? I would very "
"much like to see your skills with the bow. If you agree, I have a little "
"test for you. I want you to score twenty successful hits against the goblins "
"only by using archery. Hit the goblins twenty times with your arrows."

msgid "start_text_quest_3717"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Simeon the Merchant. Bring back to Simeone "
"six unit of meat, from either hunting deer, fox or any other animal."

msgid "start_text_quest_3718"
msgstr ""
"We are preparing to organize a group of hunters to go gather meat for the "
"townsfolk. Around this time of the year, large groups of deer and fox pass "
"through our lands. This is a great opportunity to hunt both the deer and fox "
"for their meat. Not everybody agrees with the idea of a mass organized hunt, "
"but meat is one of the main sources of food for most of our people.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to, you can partake in this hunt. All you need to do is to bring "
"back at least six units of meat. Hunting either deer, fox, or any other "
"animal does not really matter. You will have to track down the prey "
"yourself. I cannot mark the exact location of the animals on your map, "
"because they are always on the move. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Bring back six units of meat, and you will be rewarded well for your "
"services."

msgid "start_text_quest_3719"
msgstr ""
"In order to start training Sanguine's next batch of archers, Allan the "
"Councillor has requested that you gather five shortbows and twenty arrows, "
"and deliver them to Torgard the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3720"
msgstr ""
"The council has requested that we hasten the training of our new recruits. "
"It is obvious that the violence will not end any time soon, and there will "
"always be somebody attacking our peaceful town. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Torgard the Fighter will be training Sanguine's young warriors. Torgard has "
"requested that instead of using up our best equipment for training purposes, "
"we should gather the weapons of our enemies, and to use them as training "
"weapons for our future warriors.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have been informed by Torgard that there is a shortage in bows and arrows. "
"If we are to prepare our next batch of archers, both are needed in great "
"numbers. We have noticed that the goblin scouts, who are the majority of the "
"attacking goblins, favor the use of the shortbow. It has been decided that "
"the shortbow will be used to train our young archers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to gather five shortbows and twenty arrows, and to "
"deliver them to Torgard the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3721"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to have your archery skills put to the test by Torgard the "
"Fighter. You must succeed in hitting the goblins twenty times with your "
"arrows."

msgid "start_text_quest_3722"
msgstr ""
"The bows and arrows you brought in earlier, are already being put to good "
"use by our young archers. Sanguine's next batch of archers will be ready in "
"no time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Archery plays a very important part in warfare. When one is well trained in "
"the art of archery, that one will have a huge advantage against his enemy. "
"While attacking, the archer has the opportunity of scoring many hits against "
"the enemy, before resorting to hand to hand combat. Hits that will have "
"tipped the balance of the battle's outcome to his or hers favor. But the "
"archer is also vital to the protection of a town and its people. Archery "
"combined with the protection of solid strong walls, is very difficult and in "
"some cases impossible to overcome.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, do you wish to have your archery skills put to the test? I "
"would very much like to see your skills with the bow. If you agree, I have a "
"simple test for you. All you need to do, is to score twenty successful hits "
"against the goblins only by using archery. Hit the goblins twenty times with "
"your arrows."

msgid "start_text_quest_3723"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isabel the Merchant. Bring back to Isabel six "
"unit of meat, from either hunting deer, fox or any other animal. You will "
"need a skinner for this quest."

msgid "start_text_quest_3724"
msgstr ""
"The hunters of our town are preparing for the annual meat hunt. Groups of "
"deer and fox, travel through our lands this time of year. You can understand "
"how difficult it is to pass by such an opportunity, to hunt these animals "
"for their meat.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hunting wild game for meat not only is a way of life for the hunters, but is "
"one of the main sources of food for our people. You can partake in the "
"annual meat hunt is you wish. You can hunt either for deer, fox, or any "
"other animal. All you have to do is bring back six units of meat.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Because these animals are always on the move, I will not be able to mark "
"their exact location on your map. You will have to track them down yourself. "
"Return with six units of meat, and you will be rewarded well for your "
"services. Don't forget to use your skinner, once you have killed your prey."

msgid "start_text_quest_3725"
msgstr ""
"Aidan the Councillor has requested that you gather five shortbows and twenty "
"arrows, and deliver them to Kai the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3726"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, as we speak, young men and women are being recruited to become "
"the future protectors of Heart of Eanna. We cannot rely forever on warriors "
"like yourself to fight off our enemies. Heart of Eanna needs to train its "
"own children, to be able protect their homes and families. It is obvious "
"that the violence will never end, and there will always be somebody "
"attacking our peaceful town. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kai the Fighter has been assigned to train Heart of Eanna's future "
"protectors. Kai has requested that we use the weapons of our enemies, as "
"training weapons for our young recruits. Weapon such as those used by the "
"goblins. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have been informed by Kai, that we are running low on bows and arrows. We "
"are under attack, and cannot afford to use our best weapons for training the "
"new. What we have noticed, is that the goblin scouts who are the majority of "
"the attacking goblins, favor the use of the shortbow. Kai has decided that "
"the shortbow will be used to train our young archers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to gather five shortbows and twenty arrows, and to "
"deliver them to Kai the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3727"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to have your archery skills put to the test by Kai the "
"Fighter. You must succeed in hitting the goblins twenty times with your "
"arrows."

msgid "start_text_quest_3728"
msgstr ""
"Very soon our new young recruits will begin training in archery. The goblins "
"attacks, although not catastrophic to our town, made it obvious that Heart "
"of Eanna needs to be better prepared in the future for similar attacks. "
"Therefor we have been recruiting many young warriors, to train them to "
"become the future defenders of our town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When defending a town, archery can provide a huge advantage. Combined "
"together with the protection of its town's strong walls, a army of well "
"trained archers can hold off an enemy for a very long time, making it in "
"some cases impossible to overcome.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I have a challenge for you. How do you feel having your "
"archery skills put to the test? I would very much like to see your skills "
"with the bow. All you need to do, is to score twenty successful hits against "
"the goblins only by using archery. Hit the goblins twenty times with your "
"arrows."

