msgid "start_text_quest_3910"
msgstr ""
"William the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's orders to "
"Catherine the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3911"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need of you to deliver these orders straight to Catherine "
"the Fighter. Catherine has been put in charge of training Sandbrook's new "
"recruits, and the council demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders "
"to Catherine."

msgid "start_text_quest_3912"
msgstr "Deliver Catherine's Weapons List to Anton the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3913"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Catherine's weapons list to Anton the Blacksmith. All "
"that remains is for you to return to Catherine the Fighter and collect your "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3914"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked of me to begin training Sandbrook's new recruits, but "
"to do this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of "
"weapons that I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Anton "
"the Blacksmith. Dear friend, deliver this list to Anton the Blacksmith, and "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3915"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Anton the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3916"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the goblin hordes. I am Anton the Blacksmith, master blacksmith "
"of Sandbrook, and I provide this town with the majority of its weapons. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To be able to craft weapons, I need iron ore, lots of iron ore. Iron ore is "
"gathered in a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time "
"for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using your pickaxe "
"begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue "
"you might have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its "
"metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder rich "
"in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3917"
msgstr ""
"Anton the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mercian capital of "
"Sanguine, and to report to Talaod the Blacksmith. Talaod will give you a "
"crate of weapons to bring back to Anton in Sandbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3918"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Talaod the Blacksmith gave you, to Anton the "
"Blacksmith in Sandbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3919"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Sanguine, the capital of Mercia, and report to "
"Talaod the Blacksmith. Although we do have enough weapons for now, Talaod is "
"willing to help Sandbrook by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Sanguine is located north of Sandbrook. When you reach Talaod, "
"just tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from Sandbrook to "
"pick up those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3920"
msgstr ""
"Leen the Arcanist from Sandbrook has asked you to travel to the Knights of "
"Malregard in Chilbourne, deliver a note to Katarina the Arcanist, and bring "
"back to Sandbrook a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_3921"
msgstr ""
"Katarina the Arcanist of the Knights of Malregard in Chilbourne, has given "
"you a first aid box to deliver back to Leen the Arcanist in Sandbrook."

msgid "start_text_quest_3922"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need you to carry out a small task for me. Our supply of "
"first aid equipment is running low, and I have promised Catherine the "
"Fighter to have a box ready for her. At the moment the only person I can "
"think of that might have an extra first aid box to spare, is Katarina the "
"Arcanist of the Knights of Malregard in Chilbourne. I would appreciate it if "
"you could travel to Chilbourne, and bring back a first aid box to me. I have "
"already written a note for Katarina, so the only thing you need to do is to "
"hand over the note, and then bring back the first aid box to me. Chilbourne "
"is located west-southwest of Sandbrook. I will mark Katarina's location on "
"your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3923"
msgstr ""
"Allan the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Simeon the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_3924"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Simeon the Merchant. Simeon forgot his bag "
"here with me, when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes "
"and document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Simeon, He must be going "
"mad by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_3925"
msgstr "Deliver Simeon's Tools List to Talaod the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3926"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Simeon's tools list to Talaod the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Simeon the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3927"
msgstr ""
"Could you do me a favor? Can you run over to Talaod the Blacksmith, and "
"deliver this letter to him. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. "
"Once you have delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3928"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Talaod the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3929"
msgstr ""
"Building defenses against the goblins is good, but defenses is not all we "
"need. We also need weapons for our fighters to use, and to drive the goblins "
"away.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a blacksmith, I provide Monkfield with many weapons. Weapons I craft "
"myself. But to craft them, I need materials. And the material I need the "
"most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of iron ore. I "
"will reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_3930"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Wyl the Blacksmith gave you, to Talaod the "
"Blacksmith in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_3931"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to Monkfield, and to bring back to Talaod the "
"Blacksmith in Sanguine a crate of weapons that Wyl the Blacksmith has "
"prepared."

msgid "start_text_quest_3932"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Monkfield, to bring back a crate "
"of weapons that Wyl the Blacksmith has prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Monkfield to the west of Sanguine. Wyl will be "
"expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3933"
msgstr ""
"Jonn the Mage from Sanguine has asked you to travel to the White Order in "
"Copperdale, deliver a letter to Hector the Mage, and to bring back to "
"Sanguine the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_3934"
msgstr ""
"Hector the Mage of the White Order in Copperdale, has given you the Book of "
"Ancient Magic to bring back to Jonn the Mage in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_3935"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll that an explorer found near "
"the ruins in Grayvale, but so far I have had very little success. I have "
"gone through our libraries, but cannot find any similar texts to the ones on "
"this mysterious ancient scroll. I will need the Book of Ancient Magic, if I "
"am to understand what exactly is written in this scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the White Order. #PlayerName#, would you do me "
"the favor and go to the White Order in Copperdale, and bring me that book? I "
"have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Hector the Mage of the "
"White Order, explaining why I need the book. All you need to do, is to "
"deliver this letter to Hector, and to bring back the Book of Ancient Magic. "
"The White Order is located northeast from here. I shall mark Hector's "
"location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3936"
msgstr ""
"Aidan the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Melia the "
"Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_3937"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be kind enough to deliver this wooden box I have "
"here to Melia the Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town "
"said he had this package for Melia, and left it here with me. I imagine "
"Melia has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_3938"
msgstr ""
"Melia the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Caradwen the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3939"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Melia gave you to Caradwen the Mage. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Melia the Arcanist and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3940"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to my friend Caradwen the Mage. "
"This scroll just arrived with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but I think I'm going to need Caradwen's help in understanding what "
"this strange scroll exactly does."

msgid "start_text_quest_3941"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Jeremiah the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3942"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are needed by our fighters, in our battle against "
"the goblin hordes. And my job as the master blacksmith of Heart of Eanna, is "
"to provide Heart of Eanna with the weapons it needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_3943"
msgstr ""
"Jeremiah the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mercian capital of "
"Sanguine, and to report to Talaod the Blacksmith. Talaod with give you a "
"crate of weapons to bring back to Heart of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_3944"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Talaod the Blacksmith gave you, to Jeremiah "
"the Blacksmith in Heart of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_3945"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Talaod the Blacksmith from the Mercian capital of "
"Sanguine, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in Heart of "
"Eanna. All I need now is for somebody to go to Sanguine, and to bring those "
"weapons here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of "
"Sanguine to the west of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3946"
msgstr ""
"Kai the Fighter from Heart of Eanna has asked you to travel to the Sons of "
"Riada in Hildershall, and to ask Halvard the Fighter for a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_3947"
msgstr ""
"Halvard the Fighter of the Sons of Riada in Hildershall, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Kai the Fighter in Heart of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_3948"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods. I have to admit that "
"it has been a very long time since I last trained any new fighters, and even "
"longer since I last read the fighters training manual. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. You see, I don't have a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual. Travel to the Sons of Riada in Hildershall, and "
"ask Halvard the Fighter to give you his copy of the Fighters Training "
"Manual. I will mark his location on your map. Just check southwest of Heart "
"of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_3949"
msgstr ""
"Irshanta the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's new "
"orders to Gaelshek the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3950"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need of you to deliver these orders straight to Gaelshek the "
"Fighter. Gaelshek has been put in charge of training Akathos's new recruits, "
"and the council demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders to "
"Gaelshek."

msgid "start_text_quest_3951"
msgstr "Deliver Gaelshek's Weapons List to Neissur the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3952"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Gaelshek's weapons list to Neissur the Blacksmith. All "
"that remains is for you to return to Gaelshek the Fighter and collect your "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3953"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked of me to begin training Akathos's new recruits, but to "
"do this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of weapons "
"that I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Neissur the "
"Blacksmith. Dear friend, deliver this list to Neissur the Blacksmith, and "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3954"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Neissur the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3955"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the goblin hordes. I am Neissur the Blacksmith, master "
"blacksmith of Akathos, and I provide this town with the majority of its "
"weapons. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To able to craft weapons, I need iron ore, lots of iron ore. Iron ore is "
"gathered in a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time "
"for one that can be harvested for metal, and again using your pickaxe begin "
"the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue you "
"might have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its "
"metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of iron ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder "
"rich in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3956"
msgstr ""
"Neissur the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Alfar capital of "
"Shoal, and to report to Haemat the Blacksmith. Haemat will give you a crate "
"of weapons to bring back to Neissur in Akathos."

msgid "start_text_quest_3957"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Haemat the Blacksmith gave you, to Neissur "
"the Blacksmith in Akathos."

msgid "start_text_quest_3958"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Shoal, the capital of Nagast, and report to Haemat "
"the Blacksmith. Although we do have enough weapons for now, Haemat is "
"willing to help Akathos by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Shoal is located west of Akathos. When you reach Haemat, just "
"tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from Akathos to pick up "
"those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3959"
msgstr ""
"Thielit the Arcanist from Akathos has asked you to travel to the Temple of "
"the God King in Sorgom, deliver her note to Haneksur the Arcanist, and then "
"bring back to Akathos a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_3960"
msgstr ""
"Haneksur the Arcanist of the Temple of the God King in Sorgom, has given you "
"a first aid box to deliver back to Thielit the Arcanist in Akathos."

msgid "start_text_quest_3961"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need you to carry out a small task for me. Our supply of "
"first aid equipment is running low, and I have promised Gaelshek the Fighter "
"to have a box ready for him. At the moment the only person I know that might "
"have an extra first aid box to spare, is Haneksur the Arcanist of the Temple "
"of the God King in Sorgom. I would appreciate it if you could travel to "
"Sorgom and bring back a first aid box to me. I have already written a note "
"for Haneksur, so the only thing you need to do is to hand over the note and "
"then bring back the first aid box to me. Sorgon is located southeast of "
"Akathos. I will also mark Haneksur's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3962"
msgstr ""
"Taelis the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Arinthu the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_3963"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Arinthu the Merchant. Arinthu forgot his "
"bag here when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes and "
"document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Arinthu, he must be going "
"mad by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_3964"
msgstr "Deliver Arinthu's Tools List to Nirgan the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3965"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Arinthu's tools list to Nirgan the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Arinthu the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3966"
msgstr ""
"Could you do me a favor? Can you run over to Nirgan the Blacksmith, and "
"deliver this letter to him. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. "
"Once you have delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3967"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Nirgan the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3968"
msgstr ""
"Building defenses against the goblins is useful, but defenses is not all we "
"need. We also need weapons for are fighters to use, and to drive the goblins "
"away.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a blacksmith, I provide Onghral with many weapons. Weapons I craft "
"myself. But to craft them, I need materials. And the material I need the "
"most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of ore. I will "
"reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_3969"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Alfar capital of Shoal, and to report to "
"Haemat the Blacksmith.  Haemat has prepared a crate of weapons which you are "
"to bring back to Nirgan the Blacksmith in Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_3970"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Haemat the Blacksmith gave you, to Nirgan the "
"Blacksmith in Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_3971"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Shoal, the capital city of "
"Nagast, to bring back a crate of weapons that Haemat the Blacksmith has "
"prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Shoal to the east of Onghral. Haemat will be "
"expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3972"
msgstr ""
"Valseri the Mage from Onghral has asked you to travel to the Radiant Circle "
"in Dun Amsharra, deliver a letter to Loevsa the Mage, and to bring back to "
"Onghral the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_3973"
msgstr ""
"Loevsa the Mage of the Radiant Circle in Dun Amsharra has given you the Book "
"of Ancient Magic to bring back to Valseri the Mage in Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_3974"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll that an explorer found near "
"the ruins in Inorgal, but so far I have had very little success. I have gone "
"through our libraries, but cannot find no similar texts to match the ones on "
"this ancient scroll. I will need the Book of Ancient Magic if I am to "
"understand what exactly is written in this scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the Radiant Circle. #PlayerName#, would you do "
"me the favor and go to the Radiant Circle in Dun Amsharra and bring me that "
"book? I have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Loevsa the Mage "
"of the Radiant Circle, explaining why I need the book. All you need to do, "
"is to deliver this letter to Loevsa, and bring back the Book of Ancient "
"Magic. The Radiant Circle is located southwest from here. I shall also mark "
"Loevsa's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_3975"
msgstr ""
"Nirgash the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Ilrak the "
"Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_3976"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be kind enough to deliver this wooden box I have "
"here to Ilrak the Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town "
"said he had this package for Ilrak, and left it here with me. I imagine "
"Ilrak has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_3977"
msgstr ""
"Ilrak the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Haenli the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_3978"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Ilrak gave you to Haenli the Mage. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Ilrak the Arcanist and collect your reward"

msgid "start_text_quest_3979"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to my friend Haenli the Mage. "
"This scroll arrived together with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but it seems I'm going to need Haenli's help in understanding what "
"exactly this strange scroll does."

msgid "start_text_quest_3980"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Mardahan the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3981"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are used by our fighters, and my job as the master "
"blacksmith of Deep Yishku, is to provide Deep Yishku with the weapons it "
"needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_3982"
msgstr ""
"Mardahan the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Alfar capital of "
"Shoal, and to report to Haemat the Blacksmith. Haemat with give you a crate "
"of weapons to bring back to Deep Yishku."

msgid "start_text_quest_3983"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Haemat the Blacksmith gave you, to Mardahan "
"the Blacksmith in Deep Yishku."

msgid "start_text_quest_3984"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Haemat the Blacksmith from the Alfar capital of "
"Shoal, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in Deep Yishku. "
"All I need now is for somebody to go to Shoal, and to bring those weapons "
"here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of Shoal "
"to the south of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3985"
msgstr ""
"Raenthar the Fighter from Deep Yishku has asked you to travel to the Harn "
"Mandean in Dulguna, and to ask Akamush the Fighter for a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_3986"
msgstr ""
"Akamush the Fighter of the Harn Mandean in Dulguna, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Raenthar the Fighter in Deep "
"Yishku."

msgid "start_text_quest_3987"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods by the book. I have "
"to admit that it has been a very long time since I last trained any new "
"fighters, and even longer since I last read the fighters training manual. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. I don't have a copy of the Fighters "
"Training Manual, and I need one as soon as possible. Travel to the Harn "
"Mandean in Dulguna, and ask Akamush the Fighter to give you his copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual. I will mark his location on your map. Just check "
"northwest of Deep Yishku."

msgid "start_text_quest_3988"
msgstr ""
"Lysandir the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's new "
"orders to Delian the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_3989"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need of you to deliver these orders straight to Delian the "
"Fighter. Delian has been put in charge of training Beladin's Rest's new "
"recruits, and the council demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders "
"to Delian."

msgid "start_text_quest_3990"
msgstr "Deliver Delian's Weapons List to Tiyawen the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3991"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Delian's weapons list to Tiyawen the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Delian the Fighter and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3992"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked of me to begin training our new recruits, but to do "
"this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of weapons that "
"I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Tiyawen the "
"Blacksmith. Dear friend, deliver this list to Tiyawen the Blacksmith, and "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_3993"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Tiyawen the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_3994"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the goblin hordes. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am Tiyawen the Blacksmith, master blacksmith of Beladin's Rest, and I "
"provide this town with the majority of its weapons. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft weapons I need iron ore, lots of iron ore. Iron ore is gathered in "
"a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time for one "
"that can be harvested for metal, and again using your pickaxe begin the "
"procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue you might "
"have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder rich "
"in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_3995"
msgstr ""
"Tiyawen the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mirdain capital of "
"Charybdis, and to report to Aredthil the Blacksmith. Aredthil will give you "
"a crate of weapons to bring back to Tiyawen in Beladin's Rest."

msgid "start_text_quest_3996"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Aredthil the Blacksmith gave you, to Tiyawen "
"the Blacksmith in Beladin's Rest."

msgid "start_text_quest_3997"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Charybdis, the capital of Mirendil, and report to "
"Aredthil the Blacksmith. Although we have enough weapons for now, Aredthil "
"is willing to help Beladin's Rest by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Charybdis is located west of Beladin's Rest. When you reach "
"Aredthil, just tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from "
"Beladin's Rest to pick up those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_3998"
msgstr ""
"Gelwain the Arcanist from Beladin's Rest has asked you to travel to the "
"Arrowhead in Krisathel, deliver a note to Tiama the Arcanist, and bring back "
"to Beladin's Rest a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_3999"
msgstr ""
"Tiama the Arcanist of the Arrowhead in Krisathel, has given you a first aid "
"box to deliver back to Gelwain the Arcanist in Beladin's Rest."

msgid "start_text_quest_40"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted William the Councillor's quest. Bring him two goblin axes "
"to earn a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4000"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be willing to carry out a small task for me? Our "
"supply of first aid equipment is running low, and I have promised Delian the "
"Fighter to have a box ready for him. At the moment the only person I can "
"think of that might have an extra first aid box to spare, is Tiama the "
"Arcanist of the Arrowhead in Krisathel. I would appreciate it if you could "
"travel to Krisathel, and bring back a first aid box to me. I have already "
"written a note for Tiama, so the only thing you need to do is to hand over "
"the note, and then bring back the first aid box to me. Krisathel is located "
"southeast of Beladin's Rest. I will mark Tiama's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4001"
msgstr ""
"Elvallie the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Tarhal the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_4002"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Tarhal the Merchant. Tarhal forgot his bag "
"here when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes and "
"document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Tarhal, he must be going mad "
"by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_4003"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Dinuil the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4004"
msgstr ""
"Building defenses against the goblins is useful, but defenses is not all we "
"need. We also need weapons for are fighters to use, and to drive the goblins "
"away.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a blacksmith, I provide King's Holdfast with many weapons. Weapons I "
"craft myself. But to craft them, I need materials. And the material I need "
"the most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of iron ore. I "
"will reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_4005"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Mirdain capital of Charybdis, and to "
"report to Aredthil the Blacksmith.  Aredthil has prepared a crate of weapons "
"which you are to bring back to Dinuil the Blacksmith in King's Holdfast."

msgid "start_text_quest_4006"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Aredthil the Blacksmith gave you, to Dinuil "
"the Blacksmith in King's Holdfast."

msgid "start_text_quest_4007"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Charybdis, the capital city of "
"Mirendil, to bring back a crate of weapons that Aredthil the Blacksmith has "
"prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Charybdis to the north of King's Holdfast. "
"Aredthil will be expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra "
"weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4008"
msgstr ""
"Ailton the Mage from King's Holdfast has asked you to travel to the Emerald "
"Throne in Imathir, deliver a letter to Riathen the Mage, and bring back to "
"King's Holdfast the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_4009"
msgstr ""
"Riathen the Mage of the Emerald Throne in Imathir, has given you the Book of "
"Ancient Magic to bring back to Ailton the Mage in King's Holdfast."

msgid "start_text_quest_4010"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll that one of our scholars "
"found near the ruins in Eirthander, but so far I have had very little "
"success. I have gone through our libraries, but cannot find any similar "
"texts to the ones on this ancient scroll. I will need the Book of Ancient "
"Magic, if I am to understand what exactly is written in this scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the Emerald Throne. #PlayerName#, would you do "
"me the favor and go to the Emerald Throne in Imathir, and bring me that "
"book? I have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Riathen the "
"Mage of the Emerald Throne, explaining why I need the book. All you need to "
"do, is to deliver this letter to Riathen, and to bring back the Book of "
"Ancient Magic. The Emerald Throne is located west-southwest from here. I "
"shall mark Riathen's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4011"
msgstr ""
"Silawen the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Eredil the "
"Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_4012"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be kind enough to deliver this wooden box I have "
"here to Eredil the Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town "
"said he had this package for Eredil, and left it here with me. I imagine "
"Eredil has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_4013"
msgstr ""
"Eredil the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Ilith the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4014"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Eredil gave you to Ilith the Mage. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Eredil the Arcanist and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4015"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to my friend Ilith the Mage. "
"This scroll arrived together with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but it seems I'm going to need Ilith's help in understanding what "
"exactly this strange scroll does."

msgid "start_text_quest_4016"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Ciredan the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4017"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are used by our fighters, and my job as the master "
"blacksmith of Leafhelm, is to provide Leafhelm with the weapons it needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_4018"
msgstr ""
"Ciredan the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mirdain capital of "
"Charybdis, and to report to Aredthil the Blacksmith. Aredthil with give you "
"a crate of weapons to bring back to Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4019"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Aredthil the Blacksmith gave you, to Ciredan "
"the Blacksmith in Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4020"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Aredthil the Blacksmith from the Mirdain capital "
"of Charybdis, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in "
"Leafhelm. All I need now is for somebody to go to Charybdis, and to bring "
"those weapons here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of "
"Charybdis to the east of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4021"
msgstr ""
"Eolindir the Fighter from Leafhelm has asked you to travel to the Serene "
"Spire in Iriendir, and to ask Amaeri the Fighter for a copy of the Fighters "
"Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_4022"
msgstr ""
"Amaeri the Fighter of the Serene Spire in Iriendir, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Eolindir the Fighter in Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4023"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods. I have to admit that "
"it has been a very long time since I last trained any new fighters, and even "
"longer since I last read the fighters training manual. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. You see, I don't have a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual, and I need it if I am to train the new according "
"to the council's orders. Travel to the Serene Spire in Iriendir, and ask "
"Amaeri the Fighter to give you her copy of the Fighters Training Manual. I "
"will mark her location on your map. Just check north of Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4024"
msgstr ""
"Arkelia the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's new "
"orders to Yman the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4025"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need of you to deliver these orders straight to Yman the "
"Fighter. Yman has been put in charge of training Leenglow's new recruits, "
"and the council demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders to Yman."

msgid "start_text_quest_4026"
msgstr "Deliver Yman's Weapons List to Molangar the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4027"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Yman's weapons list to Molangar the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Yman the Fighter and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4028"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked of me to begin training our new recruits, but to do "
"this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of weapons that "
"I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Molangar the "
"Blacksmith. Dear friend, deliver this list to Molangar the Blacksmith, and "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4029"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Molangar the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4030"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the goblin hordes. I am Molangar the Blacksmith, Leenglow's "
"master blacksmith, and I provide this town with the majority of its weapons. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft weapons I need iron ore, vast quantities of iron ore. Iron ore is "
"gathered in a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time "
"for one that can be harvested for metal, and again using your pickaxe begin "
"the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue you "
"might have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its "
"metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of iron ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder "
"rich in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4031"
msgstr ""
"Molangar the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mahirim capital of "
"Red Moon, and to report to Maldon the Blacksmith. Maldon will give you a "
"crate of weapons to bring back to Molangar in Leenglow."

msgid "start_text_quest_4032"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Maldon the Blacksmith gave you, to Molangar "
"the Blacksmith in Leenglow."

msgid "start_text_quest_4033"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Red Moon, the capital of the Tribelands, and report "
"to Maldon the Blacksmith. Although we have enough weapons for now, Maldon is "
"willing to help Leenglow by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Red Moon is located south of Leenglow. When you reach Maldon, "
"just tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from Leenglow to "
"pick up those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4034"
msgstr ""
"Amauron the Arcanist from Leenglow has asked you to travel to the Longclaw "
"in Stonehold, deliver a note to Ymeron-tel the Arcanist, and bring back to "
"Leenglow a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_4035"
msgstr ""
"Ymeron-tel the Arcanist of the Longclaw in Stonehold, has given you a first "
"aid box to deliver back to Amauron the Arcanist in Leenglow."

msgid "start_text_quest_4036"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, our supply of first aid equipment is running low, and I have "
"promised Yman the Fighter to have a box ready for him. At the moment the "
"only person I can think of that can spare an extra first aid box, is Ymeron-"
"tel the Arcanist of the Longclaw in Stonehold. I would appreciate it if you "
"could travel to Stonehold, and bring back a first aid box to me. I have "
"already written a note for Ymeron-tel, so the only thing you need to do is "
"to hand over the note and then bring back the first aid box to me. Stonehold "
"is located northwest of Leenglow. I will mark Ymeron-tel's location on your "
"map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4037"
msgstr ""
"Ialynna the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Omandyr the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_4038"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Omandyr the Merchant. Omandyr forgot his "
"bag here when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes and "
"document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Omandyr, he must be going "
"mad by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_4039"
msgstr "Deliver Omandyr's Tools List to Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4040"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Omandyr's tools list to Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Omandyr the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4041"
msgstr ""
"Could you do me a favor? Can you run over to Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith, and "
"deliver this letter to him. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. "
"Once you have delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4042"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Sa-Imdor the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4043"
msgstr ""
"Building defenses against the goblins is useful, but defenses is not all we "
"need. We also need weapons for are fighters to use, and to drive the goblins "
"away.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a blacksmith, I provide Silverspear with many weapons. Weapons I craft "
"myself. But to craft them, I need materials. And the material I need the "
"most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of iron ore. I "
"will reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_4044"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Mahirim capital of Red Moon, and to "
"report to Maldon the Blacksmith. Maldon has prepared a crate of weapons "
"which you are to bring back to Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith in Silverspear."

msgid "start_text_quest_4045"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Maldon the Blacksmith gave you, to Sa-Imdor "
"the Blacksmith in Silverspear."

msgid "start_text_quest_4046"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Red Moon, the capital city of the "
"Tribelands, to bring back a crate of weapons that Maldon the Blacksmith has "
"prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Red Moon to the east of Silverspear. Maldon will "
"be expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4047"
msgstr ""
"Livina the Mage from Silverspear has asked you to travel to the Circle of "
"Neith in Moonclaw, deliver a letter to Samalon-tai the Mage, and to bring "
"back to Silverspear the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_4048"
msgstr ""
"Samalon-tai the Mage of the Circle of Neith in Moonclaw, has given you the "
"Book of Ancient Magic to bring back to Livina the Mage in Silverspear."

msgid "start_text_quest_4049"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll that an explorer found near "
"the ruins in Eyr Sarthain, but so far I have had very little success. I have "
"gone through our libraries, but cannot find any similar texts to the ones on "
"this ancient scroll. I will need the Book of Ancient Magic if I am to "
"understand these ancient writings.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the Circle of Neith. #PlayerName#, would you do "
"me the favor and go to the Circle of Neith in Moonclaw and bring me that "
"book? I have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Samalon-tai the "
"Mage of the Circle of Neith, explaining why I need the book. All you need to "
"do is to deliver this letter to Samalon-tai, and to bring back the Book of "
"Ancient Magic. The Circle of Neith is located west from here. I shall mark "
"Samalon-tai's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4050"
msgstr ""
"Andor-Kai the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Celene "
"the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_4051"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be kind enough to deliver this wooden box I have "
"here to Celene the Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town "
"said he had this package for Celene, and left it here with me. I imagine "
"Celene has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_4052"
msgstr ""
"Celene the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Darinna the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4053"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Celene gave you to Darinna the Mage. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Celene the Arcanist and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4054"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to my friend Darinna the Mage. "
"This scroll arrived together with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but it seems I'm going to need Darinna's help in understanding what "
"exactly this strange scroll does."

msgid "start_text_quest_4055"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Felalon the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4056"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are used by our fighters, and my job as the master "
"blacksmith of Hunter's Moon, is to provide Hunter's Moon with the weapons it "
"needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_4057"
msgstr ""
"Felalon the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Mahirim capital of Red "
"Moon, and to report to Maldon the Blacksmith. Maldon with give you a crate "
"of weapons to bring back to Hunter's Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4058"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Maldon the Blacksmith gave you, to Felalon "
"the Blacksmith in Hunter's Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4059"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Maldon the Blacksmith from the Mahirim capital of "
"Red Moon, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in Hunter's "
"Moon. All I need now is for somebody to go to Red Moon, and to bring those "
"weapons here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of Red "
"Moon to the west of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4060"
msgstr ""
"Lymyan the Fighter from Hunter's Moon has asked you to travel to the "
"Wolfmasks in Nightspire, and to ask Uranyr-kan the Fighter for a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_4061"
msgstr ""
"Uranyr-kan the Fighter of the Wolfmasks in Nightspire, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Lymyan the Fighter in Hunter's "
"Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4062"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods. It has been a very "
"long time since I last trained any new fighters, and even longer since I "
"last read the fighters training manual. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. I don't have a copy of the Fighters "
"Training Manual, and the council will not be pleased to learn of this. "
"Travel to the Wolfmasks in Nightspire, and ask Uranyr-kan the Fighter to "
"give you his copy of the Fighters Training Manual. I will mark his location "
"on your map. Just check east-southeast of Hunter's Moon"

msgid "start_text_quest_4063"
msgstr ""
"Arngard the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's new "
"orders to Eikvangr the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4064"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need of you to deliver these orders straight to Eikvangr the "
"Fighter. Eikvangr has been put in charge of training Hammerdelve's new "
"recruits, and the council demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders "
"to Eikvangr."

msgid "start_text_quest_4065"
msgstr "Deliver Eikvangr's Weapons List to Tordar the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4066"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Eikvangr's weapons list to Tordar the Blacksmith. All "
"that remains is for you to return to Eikvangr the Fighter and collect your "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4067"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked of me to begin training Hammerdelve's new recruits, "
"but to do this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of "
"weapons that I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Tordar "
"the Blacksmith. Dear friend, deliver this list to Tordar the Blacksmith, and "
"then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4068"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Tordar the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4069"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the goblin hordes. I am Tordar the Blacksmith, Hammerdelve's "
"master blacksmith, and I provide this town with the majority of its weapons. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft weapons I need iron ore, vast quantities of iron ore. Iron ore is "
"gathered in a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time "
"for one that can be harvested for metal, and again using your pickaxe begin "
"the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue you "
"might have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its "
"metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of iron ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder "
"rich in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4070"
msgstr ""
"Tordar the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Dwarven capital of "
"Ymir's Tear, and to report to Garmbeard the Blacksmith. Garmbeard will give "
"you a crate of weapons to bring back to Tordar in Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_4071"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Garmbeard the Blacksmith gave you, to Tordar "
"the Blacksmith in Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_4072"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Ymir's Tear, the capital of city of Dvergheim, and "
"report to Garmbeard the Blacksmith. Although we have enough weapons for now, "
"Garnbeard is willing to help Hammerdelve by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Ymir's Tear is located south of Hammerdelve. When you reach "
"Garmbeard, just tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from "
"Hammerdelve to pick up those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4073"
msgstr ""
"Gormfinn the Arcanist from Hammerdelve has asked you to travel to the Five "
"Beards Trading Company in Ringfain, deliver a note to Nidar the Arcanist, "
"and bring back to Hammerdelve a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_4074"
msgstr ""
"Nidar the Arcanist of the Five Beards Trading Company in Ringfain, has given "
"you a first aid box to deliver back to Gormfinn the Arcanist in Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_4075"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, our supply of first aid equipment is running low, and I have "
"promised Eikvangr the Fighter to have a box ready for him. At the moment the "
"only person I can think of that might have an extra first aid box to spare, "
"is Nidar the Arcanist of the Five Beards Trading Company in Ringfain. I "
"would appreciate it if you could travel to Ringfain, and bring back a first "
"aid box to me. I have already written a note for Nidar, so the only thing "
"you need to do is to hand over the note, and then bring back the first aid "
"box to me. Ringfain is located northeast of Hammerdelve. I will mark Nidar's "
"location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4076"
msgstr ""
"Skuldvard the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Erling the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_4077"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Erling the Merchant. Erling forgot his bag "
"here when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes and "
"document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Erling, he must be going mad "
"by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_4078"
msgstr "Deliver Erling's Tools List to Ragneid the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4079"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Erling's tools list to Ragneid the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Erling the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4080"
msgstr ""
"Could you do me a favor? Can you run over to Ragneid the Blacksmith, and "
"deliver this letter to her. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. "
"Once you have delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4081"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Ragneid the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4082"
msgstr ""
"Building defenses against the goblins is useful, but defenses is not all we "
"need. We also need weapons for are fighters to use, and to drive the goblins "
"away.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a blacksmith, I provide Eirhjelm with many weapons. Weapons I craft "
"myself. But to craft them, I need materials. And the material I need the "
"most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of iron ore. I "
"will reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_4083"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Dwarven capital of Ymir's Tear, and to "
"report to Garmbeard the Blacksmith. Garmbeard has prepared a crate of "
"weapons which you are to bring back to Ragneid the Blacksmith in Eirhjelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4084"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Garmbeard the Blacksmith gave you, to Ragneid "
"the Blacksmith in Eirhjelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4085"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Ymir's Tear, the capital city of "
"Dvergheim, to bring back a crate of weapons that Garmbeard the Blacksmith "
"has prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Ymir's Tear to the east of Eirhjelm. Garmbeard "
"will be expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4086"
msgstr ""
"Draupnar the Mage from Eirhjelm has asked you to travel to the Voice of Ymir "
"in Thorsland, deliver a letter to Nidstein the Mage, and to bring back to "
"Eirhjelm the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_4087"
msgstr ""
"Nidstein the Mage of the Voice of Ymir in Thorsland, has given you the Book "
"of Ancient Magic to bring back to Draupnar the Mage in Eirhjelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4088"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher a scroll that an explorer found near the "
"ruins in Verthandir, but so far I have had very little success. I have gone "
"through our libraries, but cannot find any texts similar to the ones on this "
"mysterious scroll. I will need the Book of Ancient Magic if I am to "
"understand what exactly is written in this scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the Voice of Ymir. #PlayerName#, would you do me "
"the favor and go to the Voice of Ymir in Thorsland and bring me that book? I "
"have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Nidstein the Mage of "
"the Voice of Ymir, explaining why I need the book. All you need to do, is to "
"deliver this letter to Nidstein and to bring back the Book of Ancient Magic. "
"The Voice of Ymir is located west from here. I shall mark Nidstein's "
"location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4089"
msgstr ""
"Hrafnid the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Yngfell "
"the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_4090"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, would you be kind enough to deliver this wooden box I have "
"here to Yngfell the Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town "
"said he had this package for Yngfell, and left it here with me. I imagine "
"Yngfell has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_4091"
msgstr ""
"Yngfell the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Thrann the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4092"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Yngfell gave you to Thrann the Mage. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Yngfell the Arcanist and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4093"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to my friend Thrann the Mage. "
"This scroll arrived together with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but it seems I'm going to need Thrann's help in understanding what "
"exactly this strange scroll does."

msgid "start_text_quest_4094"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Alvmund the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4095"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are used by our fighters, and my job as the master "
"blacksmith of Valfather's Edge, is to provide Valfather's Edge with the "
"weapons it needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_4096"
msgstr ""
"Alvmund the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Dwarven capital of "
"Ymir's Tear, and to report to Garmbeard the Blacksmith. Garmbeard with give "
"you a crate of weapons to bring back to Valfather's Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_4097"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Garmbeard the Blacksmith gave you, to Alvmund "
"the Blacksmith in Valfather's Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_4098"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Garmbeard the Blacksmith from the Dwarven capital "
"of Ymir's Tear, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in "
"Valfather's Edge. All I need now is for somebody to go to Ymir's Tear, and "
"to bring those weapons here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of Ymir's "
"Tear to northwest of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4099"
msgstr ""
"Ulfrik the Fighter from Valfather's Edge has asked you to travel to the "
"Order of the Axe in Maghnir, and to ask Jorunn the Fighter for a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_41"
msgstr ""
"Sandbrook lies in a region dominated by sprawling, gargantuan ruins left by "
"the long-vanished Nithron, a race of golden-skinned giants who ruled Mercia "
"many centuries ago. For the most part, the Nithron ruins have crumbled away "
"quietly, disturbed only by small and transient monster populations.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently however, a group of goblins have invaded the region, and getting "
"rid of these pests has proven surprisingly difficult. Goblins breed at an "
"almost inconceivable rate, and a new batch of greenskins grows to maturity "
"in six to seven years. Simply killing them as they appear tends to have a "
"limited and temporary effect on goblin populations.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unrivaled procreators they may be, but goblins are much less resourceful in "
"other areas, such as weaponmaking. Taking the weapon from a fallen goblin, "
"and thus ensuring that it can't be retrieved and reused, is considered a "
"bigger blow to a goblin community than the loss of its slain wielder. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The closest goblins were observed near an abandoned farmhouse just north of "
"town. Other groups are found to the southwest and to the northwest of town."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_4100"
msgstr ""
"Jorunn the Fighter of the Order of the Axe in Maghnir, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Ulfrik the Fighter in Valfather's "
"Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_4101"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods. I have to admit that "
"it has been a very long time since I last trained any new fighters, and even "
"longer since I last read the fighters training manual. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. I don't have a copy of the Fighters "
"Training Manual, and I don't want to inform the council that I have lost it. "
"Travel to the Order of the Axe in Maghnir, and ask Jorunn the Fighter to "
"give you her copy of the Fighters Training Manual. I will mark her location "
"on your map. Just check southwest of Valfather's Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_4102"
msgstr ""
"Vilethug the Councillor has instructed you to deliver the council's new "
"orders to Biggor the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4103"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, deliver these orders to Biggor the Fighter. Biggor has been "
"put in charge of training New Flayed Elf's new recruits, and the council "
"demands results. Quickly now, deliver these orders to Biggor."

msgid "start_text_quest_4104"
msgstr "Deliver Biggor's Weapons List to Wolfork the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4105"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Biggor's weapons list to Wolfork the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Biggor the Fighter and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4106"
msgstr ""
"The council has asked me to train New Flayed Elf's new recruits, but to do "
"this I will need weapons. I have already put together a list of weapons that "
"I will need, and all that remains is to get this list to Wolfork the "
"Blacksmith. Deliver this list to Wolfork the Blacksmith, and then return to "
"me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4107"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Wolfork the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4108"
msgstr ""
"What good are all our warriors, if they don't possess the proper equipment "
"to fight off the enemies of New Flayed Elf. I am Wolfork the Blacksmith, New "
"Flayed Elf's master blacksmith, and I provide this town with the majority of "
"its weapons. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft weapons I need iron ore, vast quantities of iron ore. Iron ore is "
"gathered in a similar way as with stone. Search for a boulder, but this time "
"for one that can be harvested for metal, and again using your pickaxe begin "
"the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. The only issue you "
"might have is to locate such a boulder. But once you do, drain it of its "
"metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said, I am in need of a lot of iron ore. #PlayerName#, find a boulder "
"rich in metal, and bring me back twenty units of iron ore. Do this, and the "
"reward will be well worth it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4109"
msgstr ""
"Wolfork the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Ork capital of Flaming "
"Skull, and to report to Rularak the Blacksmith. Rularak will give you a "
"crate of weapons to bring back to Wolfork in New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_4110"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Rularak the Blacksmith gave you, to Wolfork "
"the Blacksmith in New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_4111"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Flaming Skull, the capital of city of Morak, and "
"report to Rularak the Blacksmith. Although we have enough weapons for now, "
"Rularak is willing to help New Flayed Elf by providing extra weapons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The city of Flaming Skull is located west of New Flayed Elf. When you reach "
"Rularak, just tell him I sent you. He will be expecting somebody from New "
"Flayed Elf to pick up those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4112"
msgstr ""
"Murdak the Arcanist from New Flayed Elf has asked you to travel to the "
"Dragonbound in Dragrenoth, deliver a note to Marganak the Arcanist, and "
"bring back to New Flayed Elf a first aid box."

msgid "start_text_quest_4113"
msgstr ""
"Marganak the Arcanist of the Dragonbound in Dragrenoth, has given you a "
"first aid box to deliver back to Murdak the Arcanist in New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_4114"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, our supply of first aid equipment is running low, and I have "
"promised Biggor the Fighter to have a box ready for her. The only person I "
"can think of that might have an extra first aid box to spare, is Marganak "
"the Arcanist of the Dragonbound in Dragrenoth. Go to Dragrenoth and bring "
"back a first aid box to me. I have written a note for Marganak, so the only "
"thing you need to do is to hand over the note and bring back the first aid "
"box. Dragrenoth is located north of New Flayed Elf. I will mark Marganak's "
"location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4115"
msgstr ""
"Bosork the Councillor has asked of you to deliver a bag to Gulgon the "
"Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_4116"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver this bag to Gulgon the Merchant. Gulgon forgot his bag "
"here when last visiting me. From what I see, it is full of notes and "
"document vital for his work. Hurry now, knowing Gulgon, he must be going mad "
"by now looking for this bag."

msgid "start_text_quest_4117"
msgstr "Deliver Gulgon's Tools List to Strongar the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4118"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Gulgon's tools list to Strongar the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Gulgon the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4119"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Run over to Strongar the Blacksmith, and deliver this letter "
"to him. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. Once you have "
"delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4120"
msgstr "Deliver Tarhal's Tools List to Dinuil the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4121"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered Tarhal's tools list to Dinuil the Blacksmith. All that "
"remains is for you to return to Tarhal the Merchant and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4122"
msgstr ""
"Could you do me a favor? Can you run over to Dinuil the Blacksmith, and "
"deliver this letter to him. It is just a simple list of tools that I need. "
"Once you have delivered the letter, return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4123"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Strongar the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4124"
msgstr ""
"As a blacksmith I provide Metal Heart with many weapons, weapons our "
"warriors need. But to craft these weapons, I need materials. And the "
"material I need the most is iron ore.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. "
"That's how simple it is. The only problem is that these unique boulders are "
"not that easy to find. But once located, it is worth the trouble.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you can locate such a boulder, bring me back twenty units of ore. I will "
"reward you well for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_4125"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to travel to the Ork capital of Flaming Skull, and to "
"report to Rularak the Blacksmith. Rularak has prepared a crate of weapons "
"which you are to bring back to Strongar the Blacksmith in Metal Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_4126"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Rularak the Blacksmith gave you, to Strongar "
"the Blacksmith in Metal Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_4127"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, I need somebody to travel to Flaming Skull, the capital city "
"of Morak, to bring back a crate of weapon that Rularak the Blacksmith has "
"prepared for us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will find the city of Flaming Skull to the north of Metal Heart. Rularak "
"will be expecting you. Go now, our fighters can use the extra weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4128"
msgstr ""
"Manglar the Mage from Metal Heart has asked you to travel to the Defenders "
"of the Swamp in Ondmark, deliver a letter to Kruulor the Mage, and bring "
"back to Metal Heart the Book of Ancient Magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_4129"
msgstr ""
"Kruulor the Mage of the Defenders of the Swamp in Ondmark, has given you the "
"Book of Ancient Magic to bring back to Manglar the Mage in Metal Heart."

msgid "start_text_quest_4130"
msgstr ""
"I have been trying to decipher an ancient scroll that an explorer found near "
"the ruins in Uthank, but so far I have had very little success. I have gone "
"through our libraries, but cannot find any similar texts like the ones "
"written on this mysterious scroll. I will need that big old book, the Book "
"of Ancient Magic, if I am to understand what exactly is written on this "
"scroll.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is one copy of the Book of Ancient Magic that I know of, and it is "
"located in the libraries of the Defenders of the Swamp. #PlayerName#, do me "
"the favor and go to the Defenders of the Swamp in Ondmark and bring me that "
"book. I have prepared a letter that I want you to deliver to Kruulor the "
"Mage of the Defenders of the Swamp, explaining why I need the book. All you "
"need to do is to deliver this letter to Kruulor, and then bring back the "
"Book of Ancient Magic. The Defenders of the Swamp are located southwest from "
"here. I shall mark Kruulor's location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4131"
msgstr ""
"Uzrok the Councillor has instructed you to deliver a package to Dragonmaster "
"the Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_4132"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, deliver this wooden box I have here to Dragonmaster the "
"Arcanist. A traveling merchant passing through our town said he had this "
"package for Dragonmaster, and left it here with me. I imagine Dragonmaster "
"has been expecting this package for some time."

msgid "start_text_quest_4133"
msgstr ""
"Dragonmaster the Arcanist has asked you to deliver a scroll to Bloodzkul the "
"Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4134"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the scroll Dragonmaster gave you to Bloodzkul the Mage. "
"All that remains is for you to return to Dragonmaster the Arcanist and "
"collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4135"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. Can you take this scroll over to Bloodzkul the Mage. This "
"scroll arrived together with all the other goods you delivered to me "
"earlier, but it seems I'm going to need Bloodzkul's help in understanding "
"what exactly this strange scroll does."

msgid "start_text_quest_4136"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to gather twenty units of iron ore for Bigthug the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4137"
msgstr ""
"Vast amounts of weapons are used by our fighters, and my job as the master "
"blacksmith of Chopping Necks, is to provide Chopping Necks with the weapons "
"it needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To craft the weapons many materials are needed, but none more that iron ore. "
"Iron ore is gathered in the same way that stone is. Search for a boulder, "
"but this time for one that can be harvested for its metal, and again using "
"your pickaxe begin the procedure of extracting iron ore from that bolder. I "
"must warn you, that these boulders rich in iron ore are not easy to find. So "
"when you do, consider yourself lucky.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, our fighters need weapons, and I need iron ore. Bring me back "
"twenty units of iron ore, and I will reward you well."

msgid "start_text_quest_4138"
msgstr ""
"Bigthug the Blacksmith has asked you to travel to the Ork capital of Flaming "
"Skull, and to report to Rularak the Blacksmith. Rularak with give you a "
"crate of weapons to bring back to Chopping Necks."

msgid "start_text_quest_4139"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the weapons crate that Rularak the Blacksmith gave you, to Bigthug "
"the Blacksmith in Chopping Necks."

msgid "start_text_quest_4140"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that Rularak the Blacksmith from the Ork capital of "
"Flaming Skull, has prepared a crate of weapons for our fighters here in "
"Chopping Necks. All I need now is for somebody to go to Chopping Necks, and "
"to bring those weapons here to me.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go get those weapons for me. You will find the city of Flaming "
"Skull to east of here. Hurry now. We need those weapons."

msgid "start_text_quest_4141"
msgstr ""
"Angorok the Fighter from Chopping Necks has asked you to travel to the Iron "
"Orks in Naergur, and to ask Aksmurdar the Fighter for a copy of the Fighters "
"Training Manual."

msgid "start_text_quest_4142"
msgstr ""
"Aksmurdar the Fighter of the Iron Orks in Naergur, has given you the "
"Fighters Training Manual to bring back to Angorok the Fighter in Chopping "
"Necks."

msgid "start_text_quest_4143"
msgstr ""
"The training of our new recruits is progressing well, but the council "
"insists that I follow the traditional training methods. I have to admit that "
"it has been a very long time since I last trained any new fighters, and even "
"longer since I last read the fighters training manual. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I could use your help. You see, I don't have a copy of the "
"Fighters Training Manual, and I need it now. I don't want the council to "
"discover I don't have one. Travel to the Iron Orks in Naergur, and ask "
"Aksmurdar the Fighter to give you his copy of the Fighters Training Manual. "
"I will mark his location on your map. Just check northwest of Chopping Necks."

msgid "start_text_quest_4144"
msgstr ""
"Carrad the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Lady Blackwell, and "
"if possible to retrieve the family locket that is valuable to the Blackwell "
"family. Carrad the Mage has suggested that you search near the area of were "
"the ambush on Lady Blackwell took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4145"
msgstr ""
"You have found Lady Blackwell, and retrieved from her fallen body the "
"Blackwell family locket. Return to Sandbrook and deliver the locket to "
"Carrad the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4146"
msgstr ""
"Lady Blackwell, one of the nobles of Sandbrook, was killed while returning "
"from the nearby town of Monkfield. Her escorts overwhelmed by the bandits "
"were unable to retrieve Lady Blackwell's body, and now the Blackwell family "
"has requested that we find her body. If it is not possible to return the "
"body, the family would like the return of a round locket worn by Lady "
"Blackwell, an item that is very valuable to the family.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Were the bandits have deserted Lady Blackwell's body we do not know, "
"although we believe it cannot be far from the position of the bandits ambush."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Lady Blackwell. Should you find her body, retrieve the Blackwell family "
"locket so we may return it to the Blackwell family. I shall mark on your map "
"the position of the Blackwell ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4147"
msgstr ""
"Talaod the Blacksmith has asked you to search for Eleanor Wilde, who's "
"caravan was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting Sanguine with "
"Chilbourne."

msgid "start_text_quest_4148"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Eleanor Wilde, and retrieved from her fallen body "
"her signet ring. Return to Monkfield and deliver the ring to Wyl the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4149"
msgstr ""
"A caravan I have been expecting to arrive from Chilbourne has been ambushed "
"by bandits, and I expect the worst for by dear friend Eleanor Wilde. I need "
"somebody right away to find out what has happened to Eleanor Wilde. I don't "
"care about the lost goods, just Eleanor. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, could you travel along the route that connects Monkfield with "
"Chilbourne, and search for any signs of Eleanor and the lost caravan. Should "
"you find any clues, anything about Eleanor, please return straight away back "
"to me. Any news in better than none."

msgid "start_text_quest_4150"
msgstr ""
"Kaelat the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Lord Shadowpain, and "
"retrieve the Shadowpain family locket. Kaelat the Mage has suggested that "
"you search near the area of were the ambush on Lord Shadowpain took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4151"
msgstr ""
"You have found Lord Shadowpain, and retrieved from his fallen body the "
"Shadowpain family locket. Return to Akathos and deliver the locket to Kaelat "
"the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4152"
msgstr ""
"Lord Shadowpain, one of the nobles of Akathos, has been killed while "
"returning from the nearby town of Deep Yishku. His men overwhelmed by the "
"bandits were unable to retrieve Lord Shadowpain's body, and now the "
"Shadowpain family has requested that we find his body. If for some reason it "
"is not possible to return the body, the family would like the return of a "
"round locket worn by Lord Shadowpain, an item that is very valuable to the "
"family.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We don't know were the bandits have deserted Lord Shadowpain's body, but we "
"believe it cannot be far from the location of were the ambush took place.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Lord Shadowpain. Should you find his body, retrieve the family locket so we "
"may return it to the Shadowpain family. I shall mark on your map the "
"position of the Shadowpain ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4153"
msgstr ""
"Mardahan the Blacksmith has instructed you to search for Anashek Blackstorm, "
"who's caravan was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting Deep Yishku "
"with Dulguna."

msgid "start_text_quest_4154"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Anashek Blackstorm, and retrieved from his fallen "
"body his signet ring. Return to Deep Yishku and deliver the ring to Mardahan "
"the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4155"
msgstr ""
"One of the caravans I have been expecting to arrive from Dulguna has been "
"ambushed by bandits, and I expect the worst for by dear friend Anashek "
"Blackstorm. I need somebody right away to find out what has happened to "
"Anashek.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to travel along the route that connects Deep Yishku "
"with Dulguna, and search for any signs of Anashek and the lost caravan. "
"Should you find any clues, anything about Anashek, return straight back to "
"me. I need to know what has happened."

msgid "start_text_quest_4156"
msgstr ""
"Elathar the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Lady Silverheart, "
"and if possible to retrieve the family locket that is valuable to the "
"Silverheart family. Elathar the Mage has suggested that you search near the "
"area of were the ambush on Lady Silverheart took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4157"
msgstr ""
"You have found Lady Silverheart, and retrieved from her fallen body the "
"Silverheart family locket. Return to Beladin's Rest and deliver the locket "
"to Elathar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4158"
msgstr ""
"Lady Silverheart, one of the nobles of Beladin's Rest, has been killed while "
"returning from the nearby town of King's Holdfast. Her escorts overwhelmed "
"by the bandits were unable to retrieve Lady Silverheart's body, and now the "
"Silverheart family has requested that we find her body. If it is not "
"possible to return the body, the family would like the return of a round "
"locket worn by Lady Silverheart, an item that is very valuable to the family."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Were the bandits have deserted Lady Silverheart's body we do not know, "
"although we believe it cannot be far from the position of the bandits ambush."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Lady Silverheart. Should you find her body, retrieve the Silverheart family "
"locket so we may return it to the Silverheart family. I shall mark on your "
"map the position of the Silverheart ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4159"
msgstr ""
"Dinuil the Blacksmith has asked you to search for Ferendir Nightsong, who's "
"caravan was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting King's Holdfast "
"with Krisathel."

msgid "start_text_quest_4160"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Ferendir Nightsong, and retrieved from his fallen "
"body his signet ring. Return to King's Holdfasr and deliver the ring to "
"Dinuil the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4161"
msgstr ""
"One of the caravans I have been expecting to arrive from Krisathel has been "
"ambushed by bandits, and I expect the worst for by dear friend Ferendir "
"Nightsong. I need to find out what has happened to Ferendir. I have a bad "
"feeling.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, could you travel along the route that connects King's Holdfast "
"with Krisathel, and search for any signs of Ferendir and the lost caravan. "
"Should you find any clues, anything about Ferendir, please return straight "
"away back to me. Any news in better than none."

msgid "start_text_quest_4162"
msgstr ""
"Lenyi the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Ynna-tel Moonhunter, "
"and if possible to retrieve the family locket that is valuable to the "
"Moonhunter family. Lenyi the Mage has suggested that you search near the "
"area of were the ambush on Ynna-tel Moonhunter took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4163"
msgstr ""
"You have found Ynna-tel Moonhunter, and retrieved from her fallen body the "
"Moonhunter family locket. Return to Leenglow and deliver the locket to Lenyi "
"the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4164"
msgstr ""
"Ynna-tel Moonhunter, one of the nobles of Leenglow, has been killed while "
"returning from the nearby town of Silverspear. Her escorts overwhelmed by "
"the bandits were unable to retrieve Ynna-tel's body, and now the Moonhunter "
"family has requested that we find her body. If it is not possible to return "
"the body, the family would like the return of a round locket worn by Ynna-"
"tel Moonhunter, an item that is very valuable to the family.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Were the bandits have deserted Ynna-tel's body we do not know, but we "
"believe it cannot be far from the position of were the ambush took place.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Ynna-tel Moonhunter. Should you find her body, retrieve the Moonhunter "
"family locket so we may return it to the Moonhunter family. I shall mark on "
"your map the position of the Moonhunter ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4165"
msgstr ""
"Felalon the Blacksmith has asked you to search for Vestianna, who's caravan "
"was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting Hunter's Moon with "
"Nightspire."

msgid "start_text_quest_4166"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Vestianna, and retrieved from her fallen body her "
"signet ring. Return to Hunter's Moon and deliver the ring to Felalon the "
"Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4167"
msgstr ""
"One of the caravans I have been expecting to arrive from Nightspire has been "
"ambushed by bandits, and I expect the worst for my dear friend Vestianna. I "
"need somebody to find out what has happened to Vestianna. There have been "
"too many of these ambushes lately.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, travel along the route that connects Hunter's Moon with "
"Nightspire, and search for any signs of Vestianna and the lost caravan. "
"Should you find any clues, anything about Vestianna, return straight away "
"back to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_4168"
msgstr ""
"Draupnar the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Lady Wildbrew, and "
"if possible to retrieve the family locket that is valuable to the Wildbrew "
"family. Draupnar the Mage has suggested that you search near the area of "
"were the ambush on Lady Wildbrew took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4169"
msgstr ""
"You have found Lady Wildbrew, and retrieved from her fallen body the "
"Wildbrew family locket. Return to Eirhjelm and deliver the locket to "
"Draupnar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4170"
msgstr ""
"Lady Wildbrew, one of the nobles of Eirhjelm, has been killed while "
"returning from the nearby town of Wintercrown. Her escorts overwhelmed by "
"the bandits were unable to retrieve Lady Wildbrew's body, and now the "
"Wildbrew family has requested that we find her body. If it is not possible "
"to return the body, the family would like the return of a round locket worn "
"by Lady Wildbrew, an item that is very valuable to the family.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Were the bandits have deserted Lady Wildbrew's body we do not know, although "
"we believe it cannot be far from the position of the bandits ambush.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Lady Wildbrew. Should you find her body, retrieve the family locket so we "
"may return it to the Wilbdrew family. I shall mark on your map the location "
"of the Wildbrew ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4171"
msgstr ""
"Alvmund the Blacksmith has asked you to search for Iorrid Snowhelm, who's "
"caravan was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting Valfather's Edge "
"with Stonevault."

msgid "start_text_quest_4172"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Iorrid Snowhelm, and retrieved from her fallen "
"body her signet ring. Return to Valfather's Edge and deliver the ring to "
"Alvmund the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4173"
msgstr ""
"One of the caravans I have been expecting to arrive from Stonevault has been "
"ambushed by bandits, and I expect the worst for by dear friend Iorrid "
"Snowhelm. I need somebody right away to find out what has happened to Iorrid "
"Snowhelm.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, could you travel along the route that connects Valfather's "
"Edge with Stonevault, and search for any signs of Iorrid and the lost "
"caravan. Should you find any clues, anything about Iorrid, return straight "
"away back to me. Any news in better than none."

msgid "start_text_quest_4174"
msgstr ""
"Manglar the Mage has asked you to search for the body of Lord Bloodskull, "
"and if possible to retrieve the family locket that is valuable to the "
"Bloodskull family. Manglar the Mage has suggested that you search near the "
"area of were the ambush on Lord Bloodskull took place."

msgid "start_text_quest_4175"
msgstr ""
"You have found Lord Bloodskull, and retrieved from his fallen body the "
"Bloodskull family locket. Return to Metal Heart and deliver the locket to "
"Manglar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4176"
msgstr ""
"Lord Bloodskull, one of the nobles of Metal Heart, has been killed while "
"returning from the nearby town of Swampton. His men overwhelmed by the "
"bandits were unable to retrieve Lord Bloodskull's body, and now the "
"Bloodskull family has requested that we find his body. If it is not possible "
"to return the body, the family would like the return of a round locket worn "
"by Lord Bloodskull, an item that is very valuable to the family.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Were the bandits have deserted Lord Bloodskull's body we do not know, "
"although we believe it cannot be far from the position of the bandits ambush."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the area of the ambush for any signs of "
"Lord Bloodskull. Should you find his body, retrieve the Bloodskull family "
"locket so we may return it to the Bloodskull family. I shall mark on your "
"map the location of the Bloodskull ambush."

msgid "start_text_quest_4177"
msgstr ""
"Bigthug the Blacksmith has asked you to search for Malgorag Stonecutter, "
"who's caravan was ambushed by bandits alone the route connecting Chopping "
"Necks with Iron Maiden."

msgid "start_text_quest_4178"
msgstr ""
"You have found the body of Malgorag Stonecutter, and retrieved from his "
"fallen body his signet ring. Return to Chopping Necks and deliver the ring "
"to Bigthug the Blacksmith."

msgid "start_text_quest_4179"
msgstr ""
"One of the caravans I have been expecting to arrive from Iron Maiden has "
"been ambushed by bandits, and I expect the worst for by friend Malgorag "
"Stonecutter. I need to find out what has happened to Malgorag.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, could you travel along the route that connects Chopping Necks "
"with Iron Maiden, and search for any signs of Malgorag and the lost caravan. "
"Should you find any clues, anything about Malgorag, return straight to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_4180"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor has instructed you to report to Ayrdyr-dan the Mage "
"in Red Moon, and hand over to him the scroll with the demonic symbol and "
"writings your copied for the strange demonic tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4181"
msgstr ""
"This information you have brought to us about the Dark Lord of the central "
"plains, and the demonic tombstones is very interesting. There is a lot the "
"we must learn, and we will begin by examining the writings from the demonic "
"tombstone. Therefor I am sending you to Ayrdyr-dan the Mage, who I believe "
"will be able to decipher these symbols. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, deliver the scroll with the demonic symbols to Ayrdyr-dan the "
"Mage. You will find him here within Red Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4182"
msgstr ""
"Ayrdyr-dan the Mage has asked you to travel to Hintenfau, and to report to "
"Varlia-yne the Witch. You are to deliver a letter to Varlia-yne that Ayrdyr-"
"dan has prepared, in the hopes of convincing her to hand over a scroll that "
"is needed to decipher the demonic writings."

msgid "start_text_quest_4183"
msgstr ""
"The writings on the scroll you brought to me earlier are truly that of an "
"ancient demonic language. I do believe I can decipher these writings and "
"symbols, but in order to begin the deciphering I must first be able to read "
"and speak this long forgotten ancient language. To achieve this, an spell "
"must be cast that will allow me to read and speak this ancient demonic "
"language. Unfortunately, there is a small problem. To cast this ancient "
"spell I will need a scroll, a scroll which I do not have. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is somebody that does have such a scroll, and that somebody is Varlia-"
"yne the Witch in Hintenfau. Varlia-yne was once an arcanist of the Circle of "
"Neith, but her extreme beliefs and arrogant behavior got her exiled from the "
"Tribelands. Your task will be to travel to Hintenfau and to convince Varlia-"
"yne to hand over that scroll. I have prepared a letter for you to deliver to "
"Varlia-yne, were I will try to explain the importance of the situation "
"discerning the Demon Lord and the demonic tombstones. Let us hope that we "
"can acquire that scroll somehow from Varlia-yne. You will be rewarded well, "
"once you have returned from Hintenfau with the scroll."

msgid "start_text_quest_4184"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search for the Skull of Gems that is hidden somewhere "
"in the demonic city of {$p16} as requested by Varlia-yne the Witch, for to "
"exchange for the scroll of Demon Speaking."

msgid "start_text_quest_4185"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Skull of Gems, and all that remains is to return to "
"{$n16} and to hand over the skull to Varlia-yne the Witch in exchange for "
"the scroll of Demon Speaking that Ayrdyr-dan the Mage has asked for."

msgid "start_text_quest_4186"
msgstr ""
"Ayrdyr-dan has sent you to me to acquire the scroll of Demon Speaking.  "
"#PlayerName#, I don't need to read the letter you handed me to figure out "
"why Ayrdyr-dan needs it for. I know very well why he needs it. But I too am "
"curious to know that the demon writings say, and I know that Ayrdyr-dan is "
"one of the few that could actually decipher the demons texts. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The scroll will come at a price. You will do something for me, and if you "
"succeed I will hand the scroll over to you. If you fail, no scroll for  "
"Ayrdyr-dan, and no reward for you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is said that the Skull of Gems, a powerful artifact with necromantic "
"powers, is hidden somewhere in the demonic city of {$p16}. It is this item "
"that I want you to find for me, in exchange for the scroll of Demon Speaking."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Demonic City of {$p16} is located to the east. I will mark its location "
"on your map. If you succeed in returning to me with the item, then I shall "
"give the the scroll."

msgid "start_text_quest_4187"
msgstr ""
"Varlia-yne the Witch has given you the scroll of Demon Speaking to deliver "
"to Ayrdyr-dan the Mage in {$j12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4188"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, here is the scroll of Demon Speaking that Ayrdyr-dan has "
"requested. Go now, and tell Ayrdyr-dan to inform me about all he discovers, "
"once he has completed the deciphering of the demonic wittings. Tell him he "
"owes me that much. He will understand."

msgid "start_text_quest_4189"
msgstr ""
"Ayrdyr-dan the Mage has asked you to deliver a package to Nomri the Mage in "
"{$i10}, while he casts the ancient spell that will allow him to read and "
"decipher the demonic writing from the demon tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4190"
msgstr ""
"You have delivered the package that  Ayrdyr-dan gave you to Nomri the Mage "
"in {$i10}, and all that remains is to return to Ayrdyr-dan in {$j12} and to "
"collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4191"
msgstr ""
"It will take me a while to complete casting the ancient spell of Demon "
"Speaking and to begin the deciphering of the demonic writing you uncovered. "
"While I do this, I have a small task for you. I want you to deliver this "
"package with arcane equipment I have prepared here, to Nomri the Mage in "
"{$i10}. All you have to do is deliver the package to Nomri, and return back "
"to me. By then, I should have completed the deciphering, and have answers to "
"our many questions."

msgid "start_text_quest_4192"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to deliver Ayrdyr-dan's letter to Mardem-kai the Loyal at "
"the Wolfmask headquarters in {$l14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4193"
msgstr ""
"While you were away in {$i10}, not only did I complete deciphering the demon "
"writings, but also uncovered with the help of fellow scholars the true "
"powers of the demonic tombstone. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Let me begin with the demonic writings that were carved upon the tombstone. "
"The writings talk about the coming of the Dark Lord, a powerful figure at "
"will emerge from within the heart of Agon to conquer all. It will begin with "
"the servants of the Dark Lord that will prepare the lands for their master's "
"arrival. They will begin by slowly transforming the lands into a mirror "
"image of that of their master's world, while others will begin the process "
"of converting many of the inhabitants of this world, to the cause of their "
"master's. The Dark Lord promises wealth and power to all those that will "
"obey, and that only death awaits all those that will not.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But this is not all I and my fellow researchers have discovered. After a lot "
"of work, we have come to the conclusion that the demonic tombstone is a kind "
"of mind controlling device, used to attract and control future followers of "
"the Dark Lord. If this is so, then we believe it might be possible to "
"disable the powers of the demon tombstone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If any of this is true, the Dark Lord which I believe is a powerful demon, "
"must have somehow found a way into our world. Return to the Wolfmasks and "
"deliver this letter to Mardem-kai. In this letter I explain in detail all I "
"have discovered about the Dark Lord, and instructions on who to possibly  "
"disable the powers of the demon tombstone. I will inform the authorities "
"here in {$j12} and all other factions to search for any more of these demon "
"tombstones. We must learn more about this Dark Lord."

msgid "start_text_quest_4194"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has given you a series of steps written by Ayrdyr-dan the Mage, "
"on how to possibly disable the magical properties of the demon tombstone. "
"The first step is to place seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin "
"upon the demon tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4195"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of sulfur and seven units of resin upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the first step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast a Rend spell upon the "
"tombstone to bring out its powers."

msgid "start_text_quest_4196"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Rend spell onto the demon tombstone, brought "
"out its powers, and completed the second step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place seven units of blood, "
"five bones and one heart upon the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4197"
msgstr ""
"You have placed seven units of blood, five bones and one heart upon the "
"demon tombstone, and completed the third step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must cast the Flesh Curse spell "
"onto the tombstone to weaken the powers of the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4198"
msgstr ""
"You have successfully cast the Flesh Curse spell onto the demon tombstone, "
"weakened its powers, and completed the fourth step to disabling the magical "
"properties of the demon tombstone. Now you must place ten units of ash upon "
"the tombstone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4199"
msgstr ""
"You have placed ten units of ash upon the demon tombstone, and completed the "
"fifth step to disabling the magical properties of the demon tombstone. Now "
"you must cast the Mana Drain spell onto the tombstone to remove all magical "
"properties from it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4200"
msgstr ""
"Ayrdyr-dan  has done us all a great service by discovering this information "
"about the so called Dark Lord, but also providing us with his instructions "
"on how to disable the demon's foul devices, the demon tombstones. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, listen closely as I read to you Ayrdyr-dan's instruction on "
"how to destroy the demon tombstone. Yes, it is you the Wolfmasks have chosen "
"to destroy the demon tombstone. Here are the steps. Step one. Seven units of "
"sulfur and seven units of resin need to be placed upon the tombstone. Step "
"two, a Rend spell must be immediately cast upon the tombstone. This is to "
"bring out the powers of the tombstone and make the demonic tombstone "
"vulnerable. Step three. Seven units of blood, five bones and one heart must "
"be placed on the tombstone. Step four, a Flesh Curse spell must be cast on "
"the tombstone. This is to weaken the powers of the tombstone. Step five. Ten "
"units of ash need to be placed upon the tombstone. Sixth and final step, a "
"Mana Drain spell cast upon the demon tombstone should permanently remove the "
"demon tombstones magical abilities. Once you have disabled the demon "
"tombstone's magical properties, return to me with a full report."

msgid "start_text_quest_4201"
msgstr ""
"Sir Jeremiah Grace has asked you to travel to the city of Ottenhal and to "
"seek out Cornelius the Merchant. Your task is to learn all you can about a "
"mysterious group that might be involved in the theft of Lightbringer "
"greatsword from the Knights of Malregard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4202"
msgstr ""
"Dear friend. A Lightbringer greatsword, one very valuable to the Knights of "
"Malregard, has been stolen from our headquarters. How and when the "
"Lightbringer was stolen, we do not know. But we are sure that whoever stole "
"it had help from inside.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While my men search for the traitor within our ranks, I want you to travel "
"to Ottenhal. A traveler that arrived from Ottenhal, after learning about the "
"theft of the Lightbringer, remembered he had heard from a merchants named "
"Cornelius about a mysterious group of humans that passed through Ottenhal "
"asking about a Lightbringer.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Ottenhal, find this Cornelius, and learn all you can about this "
"mysterious group of humans. Once you have finished your investigation and "
"gathered all the information you can, return back here to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_4203"
msgstr ""
"Cornelius the Merchant has asked you to search the northwest part of "
"Ottenhal for his hidden stash of wine, and to bring him back one bottle. "
"Only then will he share with you what little he knows about the mysterious "
"group of humans, who could be behind the theft of the Lightbringer sword."

msgid "start_text_quest_4204"
msgstr ""
"You have found Cornelius's hidden stash of wine. Deliver one bottle of extra "
"fine wine to Cornelius the Merchant, so he may share with you what the knows "
"about the mysterious group of humans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4205"
msgstr ""
"So, Sir Jeremiah Grace has sent you here to Ottenhal to gather information "
"about a mysterious group of humans that might be linked to the theft of the "
"Lightbringer. I'll tell you what I know, if you can help me forget what I've "
"done. Find my hidden stash of wine here within Ottenhal, and bring me one "
"bottle of that extra fine wine. I was so drunk after what I did, that I "
"decided to hide away my wine never to drink again. But now it is all too "
"late. The sword has been stolen, the damage is done, and I cannot remember "
"were I hid my wine. All I remember is that it is somewhere in the northwest "
"part of the city.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Search Ottenhal for my wine, and bring me back one bottle. Then I will tell "
"you what I know."

msgid "start_text_quest_4206"
msgstr ""
"Cornelius the Merchant confined in you, that it was he who without knowing "
"helped the mysterious group of humans steal the Lightbringer from the "
"Knights of Malregard. Return to the Knights of Malregard, and report this "
"find to Sir Jeremiah Grace."

msgid "start_text_quest_4207"
msgstr ""
"As I had promised you, I shall share with you what I know about the theft of "
"the Lightbringer, and your mysterious group of traveling humans. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A shady group of humans wearing robes did come to me asking questions about "
"a Lightbringer greatsword. They were interested in a very special "
"Lightbringer, one that belonged once to the most virtue of men, one of the "
"greatest knights of Malredard, Rowan Brightwood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This robe-wearing group of humans was well prepared, and knew exactly what "
"they wanted. They somehow knew about my past, knew that I had information "
"about the Knights of Malregard, knew were and how to find me, and also knew "
"about my weakness for wine. It didn't take long for them to gain my trust "
"after a few drinks, and get me singing about all I knew about the Knights of "
"Malregard, and the Lightbringer they were searching for. They also managed "
"to convince me to sell them my old cloak, one worn only by the Knights of "
"Malregard. That is how I believe they got inside the Knights of Malregard. "
"Yes, I was once one of the Knights of Malregard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"That is all I know. Return to the Knights of Malregard and inform Sir "
"Jeremiah Grace that it was I, Cornelius Oakenheart, who helped the strangers "
"steal the Lightbringer. Tell him I am sorry for whatever damage I might have "
"done."

msgid "start_text_quest_4208"
msgstr ""
"Cornelius the Merchant has asked you to ask around Ottenhal, anything about "
"the mysterious robe-wearing humans, in the hopes of discovering who might "
"have lead the mysterious group to Cornelius."

msgid "start_text_quest_4209"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Karharias the Mage. Karharias is prepared to "
"talk to you about the mysterious robe-wearing humans, only if you manage to "
"convince Malren-Dor the Arcanist to give you the book, “Blood Potions of the "
"Full Moon”."

msgid "start_text_quest_4210"
msgstr ""
"Malren-Dor the Arcanist has agreed to give you the book of Blood Potions of "
"the Full Moon, only if you gather for him six units of the following "
"materials. Hellbore, Archangelica, Baneberry, Snakeweed and Blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_4211"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the book “Blood Potions of the Full Moon” to Karharias the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4212"
msgstr ""
"You have discovered that it was Karharias the Mage who lead the mysterious "
"group of robe-wearing humans to Cornelius the Merchant. Report this find to "
"Cornelius the Merchant."

msgid "start_text_quest_4213"
msgstr ""
"I need to find out how this group of thieving robe-wearing strangers who "
"stole the Lightbringer, knew so must about me. I can't help but think, that "
"these strangers might have had a little help from a few individuals here in "
"Ottenhal. Ottenhal is a lawless city with no allegiance to anyone, an the "
"same goes for everyone that lives and works here. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to work for me. Ask around if anybody knows "
"anything about this group of robe-wearing strangers. See what you can find "
"out. Ah, and don't mention that you are working for me. If they ask, just "
"say you are working with the Knights of Malregard. Nobody here really cares "
"about them."

msgid "start_text_quest_4214"
msgstr ""
"To participate in Sanguine's Ember Fest Celebrations, all you need to do is "
"bring five units of sulfur to Allan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_4215"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to the Ember Fest!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once a year the denizens of Agon enjoy a very brief lull in the relentless "
"pursuit of dominion to celebrate the Ember Fest. The Ember represents the "
"spark of life and fire that flickers and crackles in each one of them, "
"fueling their lust for battle, warming their passion and creativity and "
"burning their souls with a thirst for domination to such a scale as can only "
"be found in the steely hearts of the races of Agon.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is generally agreed, insofar as the races ever agree to anything, that "
"the first Ember Fest celebrations mark the first years of the world, and as "
"such the festival also serves as an anniversary for Agon itself.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Anybody can be part of Ember Fest. As a tradition, anybody that wishes to "
"participate in the Ember Fest celebrations, must bring five units of sulfur. "
"The sulfur signifies the explosive spark that swells in the soul of each and "
"every Agonian."

msgid "start_text_quest_4216"
msgstr ""
"To participate in Shoal's Ember Fest Celebrations, all you need to do is "
"bring five units of sulfur to Ensharra the Councillor."

