msgid "start_text_quest_4228"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search the goblin village of the shamans near Sandbrook "
"for the goblin shrine, and to destroy it using physical force with any of "
"your melee weapons. According to Carrad the Mage, twenty solid hits should "
"be enough to destroy the goblin shrine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4229"
msgstr ""
"All goblins worship the goblin deity Ngobil, but none more than the goblin "
"shamans. The goblin shamans believe that Ngobil has chosen them as his "
"favorite to defend and guide the goblin race. That is why he has blessed "
"them with the spellcasting abilities which they have, to be able to fulfill "
"this important role that has been given to them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But intelligent as the goblin shamans might be, they are still goblins, they "
"are still primitive. Where there are goblins shamans, there is always a "
"goblin shrine dedicated to Ngobil the goblin god. By protecting this shrine, "
"the shamans believe that they are protecting the spellcasting abilities "
"given to them. Destroy the shrine, and you destroy the shamans. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Destroying the shrine will not actually remove the spellcasting abilities of "
"the shamans, but will surely remove them from the battle while they run "
