"twenty solid hits should be enough to destroy the goblin shrine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4285"
msgstr ""
"The goblin shamans are causing problems by leading the goblin hordes against "
"our people. It is imperative that we find a way to stop them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The shamans believe that Ngobil, the father and creator of the goblin race, "
"created the goblin shamans to guide the goblins. Therefor Ngobil blessed the "
"shamans with the ability of spellcasting. If we can somehow destroy the "
"goblins shamans faith in Ngobil, we might be able to disrupt the shamans "
"work.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the goblin shamans village near Valfather's Edge, there should be a "
"shrine dedicated to the goblin god Ngobil. By destroying the shrine, the one "
"thing that represents their connection to their god, we can destroy the "
"shamans. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Search the goblin shaman village for the goblin shrine. When you have "
"located the shrine, wielding any of your melee weapons use physical force to "
"desecrate it. Twenty solid hits should be enough to destroy it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4286"
msgstr ""
"Thrann the Mage has instructed you attack the goblin shaman village and to "
"kill four goblin shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4287"
msgstr ""
"After observing the goblins, we have come to the conclusion that the goblin "
"shamans are the ones coordinating the goblin attacks. Therefor it is logical "
"that to weaken the goblin attacks against Valfather's Edge, we must attack "
"the goblin shamans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, attack the goblin shaman village, and kill four goblin "
"shamans. Once you have completed this simple but vital task, report back to "
"me."

msgid "start_text_quest_4288"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search the goblin shaman village in {$w13} for the "
"goblin shrine, and to destroy it using physical force with any of your melee "
"weapons. According to Skullgor the Mage, twenty solid hits should be enough "
"to destroy the goblin shrine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4289"
msgstr ""
"All goblins worship the goblin deity Ngobil, but none more than the goblin "
"shamans. The goblin shamans believe that Ngobil has chosen them as his "
"favorite to defend the goblin race. That is why he has blessed them with the "
"spellcasting abilities which they have, to be able to fulfill this important "
"role that has been given to them. Smart as the goblin shamans might be, they "
"are still goblins.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Where there are goblins shamans, there is always a goblin shrine dedicated "
"to Ngobil the goblin god. By protecting this shrine, the shamans believe "
"that they are protecting the spellcasting abilities given to them. Destroy "
"the shrine, and you destroy the shamans. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task  #PlayerName# will be to search the goblin shaman village in "
"{$w13} for the goblin shrine. When you have located the shrine, while "
"wielding any of your melee weapons, use physical force to desecrate it. "
"Twenty solid hits should do the trick."

msgid "start_text_quest_4290"
msgstr ""
"Skullgor the Mage has instructed you to attack the goblin shaman village and "
"kill four of the annoying goblin shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4291"
msgstr ""
"As the leaders of the goblin attacks upon New Flayed Elf, the goblin shamans "
"must be destroyed. #PlayerName#, I want you to attack the goblin shaman "
"village, and kill four goblin shamans. Enough with their pathetic little "
"spells. We will stop their attacks by crippling them from the top of "
"whatever hierarchy they might seem to have."

msgid "start_text_quest_4292"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search the goblin shaman villages in {$v14} for the "
"goblin shrine, and to destroy it. According to Manglar the Mage, twenty "
"solid hits should be enough to destroy the goblin shrine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4293"
msgstr ""
"The goblin shamans believe that is it the goblin god Ngobil that has given "
"them the ability to cast spells. They believe that they are the chosen ones "
"that must guide and protect the goblin race. It is from this faith in their "
"god, that the goblin shamans draw their strength from.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Somewhere in the goblin shamans village, their should be a shrine dedicated "
"to the goblin god Ngobil. It is through the power of the shrine that the "
"shamans believe that they attain their spellcasting abilities. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task  #PlayerName# will be to search the goblin shaman village in "
"{$v14} and to destroy the goblin shrine, therefor destroying the shamans "
"belief in their spellcasting abilities. When you have located the shrine, "
"wielding any of your melee weapons use physical force to desecrate it. "
"Twenty solid hits should be enough to destroy it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4294"
msgstr ""
"Manglar the Mage has instructed you to attack the goblin shaman village and "
"kill four goblin shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4295"
msgstr ""
"It is obvious by now, that it is the goblin shamans are the ones leading the "
"goblin attacks. If they are the true leaders or are following orders from "
"elsewhere, I do not know. What I do know is that by attacking the goblin "
"shamans and weaken them, we will be delivering a crippling blow to the "
"goblins as a whole.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to attack the goblin shaman village, and kill four "
"goblin shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4296"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to search the goblin shaman village in {$u13} for the "
"goblin shrine, and to destroy it. According to Bloodzkul the Mage, twenty "
"solid hits should be enough to destroy the goblin shrine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4297"
msgstr ""
"The goblin shamans are causing problems by leading the goblin hordes against "
"our people. It is imperative that we find a way to stop them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The shamans believe that Ngobil, the father and creator of the goblin race, "
"created the goblin shamans to guide the goblins. Therefor Ngobil blessed the "
"shamans with the ability of spellcasting. If we can somehow destroy the "
"goblins shamans faith in Ngobil, we might be able to disrupt the shamans "
"work.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the goblin shamans village near Chopping Necks, there should be a shrine "
"dedicated to the goblin god Ngobil. By destroying the shrine, the one thing "
"that represents their connection to their god, we can destroy the shamans. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Search the goblin shaman village for the goblin shrine. When you have "
"located the shrine, wielding any of your melee weapons use physical force to "
"desecrate it. Twenty solid hits should be enough to destroy it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4298"
msgstr ""
"Bloodzkul the Mage has instructed you to attack the goblin shaman village "
"and kill four goblin shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_4299"
msgstr ""
"After observing the goblins, we have come to the conclusion that the goblin "
"shamans are the ones coordinating the goblin attacks. Therefor it is logical "
"that to weaken the goblin attacks against Chopping Necks, we must attack the "
"goblin shamans.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, ttack the goblin shaman village and kill four goblin shamans. "
"Once you have completed this simple but vital task, report back to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_4300"
msgstr ""
"Kai the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Adrian Strong, and "
"to retrieve from it Adrian's mighty blow horn. Kai suggested that you search "
"the goblin shaman village near Heart of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_4301"
msgstr ""
"You have found Adrian Strong, and retrieved from his fallen body his mighty "
"blow horn. Return to Heart of Eanna and deliver the blow horn to Kai the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4302"
msgstr ""
"Many brave mercians have sacrificed their lives protecting Heart of Eanna "
"against its many enemies. Among those we have lost is Adrian Strong, one of "
"Heart of Eanna's finest officers. The council wishes to find the body of "
"Adrian Strong, and if possible to retrieve from it the blow horn he always "
"carried with him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Adrian's mighty blow horn is important to Heart of Eanna, as it is part of "
"this town's history. Adrian would be the first to alert the town of any "
"approaching danger, with mighty blasts coming from his horn. It was a sound "
"that we all had grown accustomed to, a sound that bestowed a feeling of "
"security to everyone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Adrian fell while battling the goblin hordes, to protect the people of Heart "
"of Eanna. Although his body was not found on the battlefield, we believe "
"that the goblins have taken Adrian's body to  the goblin shaman village to "
"keep as a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the goblin shaman village for the body of "
"Adrian Strong, recover the mighty blow horn, and to return it back to Heart "
"of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_4303"
msgstr ""
"Zulgal the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Adalia "
"Ghostscream, and to retrieve from it the mighty blow horn Adalia always "
"carried. Zulgal suggested that you search the goblin shaman village in "
"Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_4304"
msgstr ""
"You have found Adalia Ghostscream, and retrieved from her fallen body the "
"mighty blow horn. Return to Onghral and deliver the blow horn to Zulgal the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4305"
msgstr ""
"Many brave alfar have sacrificed their lives protecting Onghral from its "
"many enemies. Among those who have fallen is Adalia Ghostscream, one of "
"Onghral's finest officers. The council of Onghral wishes to find the body of "
"Adalia Ghostscream, and retrieve from it the mighty blow horn she always "
"carried with her.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Adalia's mighty blow horn is important to Onghral, as it is part of this "
"town's history. Adalia would be the first to alert the town of any "
"approaching danger, with mighty blasts coming from her blow horn. It was a "
"sound that we all had grown accustomed to, a sound that bestowed a feeling "
"of security to everyone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Adalia fell while battling the goblin hordes, to protect the people of "
"Onghral. Although her body was not found on the battlefield, we believe that "
"the goblins have taken Adalia's body to the goblin shaman village to keep as "
"a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the goblin shaman village for the body of "
"Adalia Ghostscream, recover the mighty blow horn, and to return it back to "
"Onghral."

msgid "start_text_quest_4306"
msgstr ""
"Eolindir the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Narandir "
"Frostwind, and to retrieve from it the fine longsword. Eolindir suggested "
"that you search the goblin shaman village near Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4307"
msgstr ""
"You have found Narandir Frostwind, and retrieved from his fallen body his "
"fine longsword. Return to Leadhelm and deliver the longsword to Eolindir the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4308"
msgstr ""
"Many brave mirdain have sacrificed their lives protecting Leafhelm against "
"its many enemies. Among those we have lost is Narandir Frostwind, one of "
"Leafhelm's finest officers. The council of Leafhelm wants to locate the body "
"of Narandir Frostwind, and if possible to retrieve from it the fine "
"longsword Narandir always carried with him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The longsword that Narandir carried with him is important to Leafhelm, as it "
"is part of the town's history. Narandir would lead every charge against any "
"enemies approaching Leafhelm, while raising his fine longsword up high for "
"all to see. The sight of Narandir's longsword leading every charge, always "
"bestowed a sense of security and pride to the townsfolk.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately Narandir fell, while protect the people of Leafhelm from the "
"goblin hordes. Although his body was not found on the battlefield, we "
"believe that the goblin shamans have taken Narandir's body to their village "
"to keep as a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the nearby goblin shaman village for the "
"body of Narandir Frostwind, recover his fine longsword, and to return it "
"back to Leafhelm."

msgid "start_text_quest_4309"
msgstr ""
"Uryar the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Kilenran, and to "
"retrieve from it the keen longsword. Uryar suggested that you search the "
"goblin shaman village near Silverspear."

msgid "start_text_quest_4310"
msgstr ""
"You have found Kilenran, and retrieved from his fallen body his keen "
"longsword. Return to Silverspear and deliver the longsword to Uryar the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4311"
msgstr ""
"Many brave mahirim have sacrificed their lives protecting Silverspear "
"against its many enemies. Among those we have lost is Kilenran, one of "
"Silverspear's finest officers. The council of Silverspear wishes to find the "
"body of Kilenran, and if possible to retrieve from it the keen longsword "
"Kilenran always carried with him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The longsword that Kilenran carried with him is important to Silverspear, as "
"it is part of the town's history. Kilenran would lead every charge against "
"enemies approaching Silverspear, while raising his fine longsword up high "
"for all to see. The sight of Kilenran longsword leading every charge, always "
"bestowed a sense of security and pride to all the townsfolk.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kilenran fell while battling the goblin hordes, to protect the people of "
"Silverspear. Although his body was not found on the battlefield, we believe "
"that the goblins have taken Kilenran's body to the nearby goblin shaman "
"village to keep as a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the goblin shaman village for the body of "
"Kilenran, recover the longsword, and to return it back to Silverspear."

msgid "start_text_quest_4312"
msgstr ""
"Eikvangr the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Drogan "
"Greybeard, and to retrieve from it Drogan's heavy shield. Eikvangr suggested "
"that you search the goblin shaman village near Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_4313"
msgstr ""
"You have found Drogan Greybeard, and retrieved from his fallen body his "
"heavy shield. Return to Hammerdelve and deliver the shield to Eikvangr the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4314"
msgstr ""
"Many brave dwarves have sacrificed their lives protecting Hammerdelve "
"against its many enemies. Among those we have lost is Drogan Greybeard, one "
"of Hammerdelve's finest officers. The council of Hammerdelve has instructed "
"that we locate the body of Drogan Greybeard, and if possible to retrieve the "
"heave shield he always carried with him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Drogan's heavy shield is important to Hammerdelve, as it is part of this "
"town's history. Drogan would be the first to stand in front of our towns "
"defenses, holding off with his heavy shield any who would try to enter our "
"gates. Knowing that Drogan with his strong heavy shield was always there to "
"protect our town, bestowed a sense of security and pride to all the "
"townsfolk.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Drogan fell while battling the goblin hordes, to protect the people of "
"Hammerdelve. Although his body was not found on the battlefield, we believe "
"that the goblins have taken Drogan's body to the nearby goblin shaman "
"village to keep as a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the goblin shaman village for the body of "
"Drogan Greybeard, recover the his heavy shield, and to return it back to "
"Hammerdelve."

msgid "start_text_quest_4315"
msgstr ""
"Biggor the Fighter has asked you to search for the body of Galtanok "
"Ironhead, and to retrieve from it Galtanok's mighty blow horn. Biggor "
"suggested that you search the goblin shaman village near New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_4316"
msgstr ""
"You have found Galtanok Ironhead, and retrieved from her fallen body her "
"mighty blow horn. Return to New Flayed Elf and deliver the blow horn to "
"Biggor the Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4317"
msgstr ""
"Many brave orks have sacrificed their lives protecting New Flayed Elf "
"against its many enemies. Among those we have lost is Galtanok Ironhead, one "
"of our finest officers. The council wishes to locate the body of Galtanok "
"Ironhead, and retrieve from it the blow horn she always carried with her.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mighty blow horn is important to New Flayed Elf, as it is part of this "
"town's history. Galtanok would be the first to alert the town of any "
"approaching danger, with mighty blasts coming from her horn. It was a sound "
"that we all had grown accustomed to, a sound that bestowed a feeling of "
"security to everyone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Galtanok fell while battling the goblin hordes, protecting the people of "
"this town. Although her body was not found on the battlefield, we believe "
"that the goblins have taken Galtanok's body to the goblin shaman village to "
"keep as a trophy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to search the goblin shaman village for the body of "
"Galtanok Ironhead, recover the mighty blow horn, and to return it back to "
"New Flayed Elf."

msgid "start_text_quest_4318"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh that have appeared "
"northwest of Sandbrook, and deliver them to Carrad the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4319"
msgstr ""
"The goblin teeth you gathered earlier are already being put to good use. "
"Carrad the Mage has requested if possible, for another enchanting material "
"to be gathered. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Strange creature called Sarnakh, that could be described as flying snakes, "
"have appeared northwest of Sandbrook, in the vicinity of the old ruined "
"nithron towers. As I have been informed by Carrad, the Sarnakh can be "
"harvest for Snake Greenleaf, a material sort out by those that delve in the "
"art of crafting enchanted items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What exactly has lured these flying snakes near our village is unknown, but "
"as Carrad the Mage has put it, it is a good opportunity to gather some more "
"enchanting materials.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh and "
"deliver them the Carrad the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4320"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared inside "
"the old mining site in the Greycloak mountains, and deliver them to Jonn the "
"Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4321"
msgstr ""
"Many years ago, a large group of ogres had wandered into western Mercian, "
"and invaded the western side of the Greycloak mountains. A large force was "
"gathered to drive the ogres out of the mountains and Mercia, in an effort to "
"reclaim the Greycloak mountains and save our mining operations. After many "
"long and bloody battles, the ogres eventually were driven out of the "
"mountains, and the mining sites were saved but for one. The mining site was "
"never rebuilt, but left as a memorial to remind us of those who had died so "
"violently to save Monkfield. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now for reasons we cannot understand, undead have started to rise in the "
"vicinity of the old mining site. If these undead are the tortured souls of "
"the many warriors and miners that died while fighting the ogres in the "
"Greycloak mountains, we cannot know. But, Selensha the Mage has requested "
"that four units of Zombie Corpseflesh be gathered, so he may analyze if "
"these undeads were once our people or not.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I understand this is a gruesome task, but I ask of you to go "
"to the old mining site and gather four units of Zombie Corpseflesh. Once you "
"have gathered the four units of Zombie Corpseflesh, deliver them to Jonn the "
"Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4322"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have appeared "
"along the old dirt road that leads to Cranwyn Bay, and deliver them to "
"Caradwen the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4323"
msgstr ""
"Travelers arriving at Heart of Eanna have reported sighting various spiders "
"attacking southeast of here along the old dirt road that leads to Cranwyn "
"Bay. This news has quickly spread through Heart of Eanna and has created "
"some concern among citizens of our town, since many have suffered from the "
"goblin attacks and now fear a possible spider invasion.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But there are those that could benefit from these eight legged visitors, "
"such as Caradwen the Mage. As soon as Caradwen heard about the spiders, she "
"politely requested if four units of Arachnid Venom Sacs could be harvested "
"from the spiders and delivered to her. Caradwen would like to use the "
"Arachnid Venom Sacs to create various enchanted items, as she likes to do "
"every now and then.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you have no fear of spiders and would like to assist "
"Caradwen in her work, gather four units of Arachnid Venom Sac and deliver "
"them to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4324"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Greenleaf from the Sarnakh that have appeared west of "
"Akathos, and deliver them to Kaelat the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4325"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed that the goblin teeth you gathered earlier, are already "
"being put to good use. Kaelat the Mage has requested for another enchanting "
"material to be gathered. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Flying snakes called Sarnakh have been sighted west of Akathos, on the route "
"that leads towards Shoal. Kaelat has explained to me that the Sarnakh can be "
"harvest for Snake Greenleaf, a material sort out by those that delve in the "
"art of crafting enchanting items. And as Kaelat the Mage has put it, it is a "
"good opportunity to gather some more enchanting materials.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh and "
"deliver them the Carrad the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4326"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared inside "
"the ruin site within the swamp lands near Ongral, and deliver them to "
"Valseri the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4327"
msgstr ""
"The ruins that lie at the far side of the swamp lands, are one of the many "
"reminders left of a once powerful ancient race. The site, like many others, "
"has never been of much interest to us until recently. Scouts have reported "
"sighting undead that has risen within the ruin site, attacking anybody that "
"approaches.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Why and how these undead guardians have appeared we do not know. If it is "
"the work of a powerful wizard who is raising the dead for personal reasons, "
"or the previous occupants of the site that have returned to reclaim the "
"site, is yet to be discovered. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Valseri the Mage has requested that samples be gathered from the zombies, so "
"she may analyze the powers behind the sudden appearance of the undead.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to assist Valseri the Mage in her work by gathering  "
"four units of Zombie Corpseflesh, and delivering them to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4328"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have appeared "
"in the swamp east of Deep Yishku, and deliver them to Haenlithe the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4329"
msgstr ""
"Our patrols have reported encountering groups of spiders to the east, beyond "
"the cliffs in the vicinity of the swamps. While these spiders do not pose "
"any threat to Deep Yishku, the spiders could pose a threat along the nearby "
"trade route from traveling merchants.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As we are about to begin removing these spiders from the trade routes, "
"Haenlithe the Mage has put in a request. Haenlithe has requested that "
"Arachnid Venom Sacs be harvested from the spiders and delivered to her. "
"Haenlithe would like to use the Arachnid Venom Sacs to create various "
"enchanted items, as she likes to do every now and then.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you have no fear of spiders and would like to assist "
"Haenlithe in her work, gather four units of Arachnid Venom Sac and deliver "
"them to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4330"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Greenleaf from the Sarnakh that have appeared on the "
"shores of the sacred river, and deliver them to Elethar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4331"
msgstr ""
"Fishermen have reported seeing strange creatures on the far shores of the "
"sacred river, creatures that resemble flying snakes. In the beginning the "
"fishermen where terrified to see such creatures, and believed that these "
"strange creatures were demons. But after closer examination, Elethar the "
"Mage informed the council that these creatures, these flying snakes, are "
"magical creatures called Sarnakh. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Sarnakh pose no threat what so ever to Beladin's Rest, and will not "
"bother anybody if not provoked. What exactly has brought the Sarnakh to the "
"shores of sacred river is unknown, but as Elethar the Mage has put it, it is "
"a good opportunity to gather some more enchanting materials.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh and "
"deliver them the Elethar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4332"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared inside "
"the Forest of Whispers, and deliver them to Ailton the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4333"
msgstr ""
"To the north of Kings Holdfast is the Forest of Whispers, a forest as old as "
"as Mirendil itself. The Forest of Whispers has been part of King Holdfast's "
"everyday life, be it either for gathering wood and herbs, hunting, or just "
"traveling between other major towns and cities throughout Mirendil.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But recently the tranquility and beauty of the forest, has been poisoned by "
"the sudden appearance of undead. Rumors have always talked about strange "
"spirits haunting the Forest of Whispers, but never has there been reference "
"of any sort of undead. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The council has decided to begin an operation to remove as many of the "
"undead from inside the forest as possible. Meanwhile, Ailton the Mage has "
"requested that four units of Zombie Corpseflesh be gathered, so Ailton may "
"analyze if these undeads were once our people or not.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I understand this is a gruesome task, but I ask of you to go "
"to the old mining site and gather four units of Zombie Corpseflesh. Once you "
"have gathered the four units of Zombie Corpseflesh, deliver them to Ailton "
"the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4334"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have been "
"sighted outside the southwestern walls of Leafhelm, and deliver them to "
"Ilith the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4335"
msgstr ""
"Spiders have dangerously approached close to our town walls, on the "
"southwest side. So far nobody has been hurt, but the spiders have definitely "
"put the fear back into our people who haven't completely recovered from the "
"goblin attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One person who not only has been feared by the spiders, but on the contrary "
"could even benefit from their presence, in Ilith the Mage. Ilith has asked "
"me if I could find anyone willing, to attack these spiders and harvest from "
"them four units of  Arachnid Venom Sac. As she informed me, the  Arachnid "
"Venom Sacs can be used to enchant various items, such as weapons and armors."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you believe you could assist Ilith in her work, and have no "
"fear of spiders, gather four units of Arachnid Venom Sac and deliver them to "
"her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4336"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have been "
"sighted east-northeast of Leenglow, and deliver them to Lenyi the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4337"
msgstr ""
"Groups of spiders have been sighted on the far side of the river to the east-"
"northeast of Leenglow, and Lenyi the Mage has wasted no time in requesting "
"for four units of Arachnid Venom Sac be harvested from the spiders and "
"delivered to her. Lenyi would like to use the Arachnid Venom Sacs to "
"experiment with enchanting various items, as she often does every now and "
"then.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you have no fear of spiders and would like to assist Lenyi "
"in her work, gather four units of Arachnid Venom Sac and deliver them to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4338"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Greenleaf from the Sarnakh that have appeared in the "
"woodlands southeast of Silverspear, and deliver them to Livina the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4339"
msgstr ""
"Our enchanters were pleased to receive the goblin teeth you gathered "
"earlier, and soon they will be put to good use. Livina the Mage who "
"represents our enchanters, has requested for another enchanting material to "
"be gathered.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Magical creature called Sarnakh, that could be described as flying snakes, "
"have made an appearance southeast of Silverspear in the vicinity of the "
"woodlands next to the path that leads to Moonclaw. As I have been informed "
"by Livina, the Sarnakh can be harvest for Snake Greenleaf, a material sort "
"out by those that delve in the art of crafting enchanted items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh and "
"deliver them the Livina the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4340"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared near "
"the walls, on the south side of Hunter's Moon, and deliver them to Darinna "
"the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4341"
msgstr ""
"Zombies have been sighted close to our walls, on the south side of Hunter's "
"Moon. So far no incidents have been reported, but the zombies have created a "
"fair amount of concern among our people, who are still dealing with the "
"goblin attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"What truly has puzzled the council, is the location which these zombies have "
"appeared. Apparently, the zombies seem to be bound to an area, one that is "
"full of strange stone structures that we still have no idea what they are. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Meantime Darinna the Mage has requested, that while the council ponders what "
"to do about this strange zombie gathering, if I could find anyone willing to "
"attack these zombies and harvest from them four units of  Zombie Corpseflesh."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you have the time to do this small favor for Darinna, go "
"gather fours units of Zombie Corpseflesh and deliver them to Darinna the "
"Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4342"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have appeared "
"northwest of Hammerdelve, and deliver them to Rothrin the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4343"
msgstr ""
"The goblin teeth you gathered earlier are being put to good use by our "
"enchanters, and Rothrin the Mage has requested for another enchanting "
"material to be gathered. Rothrin the Mage has requested for four units of  "
"Arachnid Venom Sac be gathered from the spiders that have been sighted "
"roaming northwest of Hammerdelve, and delivered to him.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Rothrin has always help Hammerdelve whenever it was ask of him without "
"complaining, and it is only right to assist him in his work, as a small "
"token of our appreciation for all he has done for our town.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I ask of you to gather four units of  Arachnid Venom Sac and "
"deliver them to Rothrin the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4344"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Zombie Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared "
"near the outpost ruins in the swamplands southwest of Eirhjelm, and deliver "
"them to Draupnar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4345"
msgstr ""
"The swamplands that exist today southwest of Eirhjelm, were once an area "
"covered by a large forest rich in wildlife. Eirhjelm was proud to have such "
"a beautiful forest nearby, one almost as beautiful as the forests of "
"Mirendil. The council of Eirhjelm had ordered an outpost to be built inside "
"the forest to guard it, but to also notify Eirhjelm if any threat came to "
"the forest.  And for a long time the outpost guarded the forest, and the "
"people enjoyed its beauty. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But one day Eirhjelm stop receiving reports from the forest outpost. Scouts "
"were sent to the forest to see why the outpost had stopped communicating. "
"When arriving there, what they found horrified them. The forest itself was "
"in an extremely poor condition, as if ill, and all wildlife had disappeared. "
"The forest outpost was in ruins, and all the forest guards dead. No signs of "
"any struggle or intrusion were ever found. Nothing.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the next three years the forest died, and turned into the swamplands it "
"is today. And now undead have now risen withing the swamplands, bringing "
"back awful memories to Eirhjelm. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Draupnar the Mage has asked that four units of Zombie Corpseflesh be "
"gathered from the undead, in the hopes of finding answers to what happened "
"to the forest, but also why are dead rising with in the swamps today.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go to swamplands and gather four units of Zombie Corpseflesh "
"from the undead that have risen near the outpost ruins. Once you have "
"gathered the four units of Zombie Corpseflesh, deliver them to Draupnar the "
"Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4346"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Greenleaf from the Sarnakh that are attacking along the "
"eastern route outside Valfarther's Edge, and deliver them to Thrann the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4347"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have reported sighting strange creatures that resemble flying "
"snakes, attacking travelers arriving at Valfather's Edge via the eastern "
"route. This news has spread through Valfarther's Edge and has created some "
"concern among citizens of our town, after many have suffered from the goblin "
"attacks and now fear a possible invasion from these strange creatures.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But as soon as Thrann the Mage heard about the flying snakes, he informed us "
"that these flying snakes are magical creatures called Sarnakh. Thrann would "
"like to study the Sarnakh, and has asked for four units of Snake Greenleaf "
"to be harvested from the Sarnakh and delivered to him. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, if you would like to assist Thrann in his work, gather four "
"units of Snake Greenleaf and deliver them to him."

msgid "start_text_quest_4348"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Venom Sac from the Sarnakh that are have been sighted "
"on Grimclaw Island, and deliver them to Skullgor the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4349"
msgstr ""
"Fishermen returning to New Flayed Elf reported sighting strange creatures on "
"the small island of Grimclaw, which is found east of here. The creatures "
"were described as flying snakes, and after closer examination Skullgor the "
"Mage informed the council that these creatures are magical creatures called "
"Sarnakh. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It has been determined that the Sarnakh cannot leave the small island and "
"therefor pose no threat to New Flayed. What exactly has brought the Sarnakh "
"to the Grimclaw Island is a mystery, but as Skullgor the Mage has put it, it "
"is a good opportunity to gather some more enchanting materials.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of Snake Greenleaf from the Sarnakh and "
"deliver them the Skullgor the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4350"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Corpseflesh from the Zombies that have appeared within "
"the swamp pit, and deliver them to Manglar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4351"
msgstr ""
"Southwest of Metal Heart lies the swamp pit. A large natural canyon filled "
"with putrid waters and rotting plants. For years the swamp pit was home to a "
"large clan of trolls. Whenever fooling mercians adventurers would approach "
"Metal Heart, we would simple capture them and throw them into the swamp pit, "
"while waging bets on how long they would survive before the trolls would "
"tear them into pieces. Yes my friend, those where the good days. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But then the trolls disappeared, and with them all the fun the swamp pit "
"offered us. Some say that the trolls disappeared because of the excessive "
"hunting against them, while other believe the troll population grew to large "
"for the swamp pit.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Fortunately, fun seems to have returned to the swamp pit. Zombies have now "
"risen from within the swamp pit, and aimlessly roam about. Manglar the Mage "
"has asked that four units of Zombie Corpseflesh be gathered from the "
"zombies, to determine if these walking dead are the many mercians that once "
"offered Metal Heart do much entertainment.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go to swamp pit and gather four units of Zombie Corpseflesh "
"from the zombies that have risen. Once you have gathered the four units of "
"Zombie Corpseflesh, deliver them to Manglar the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4352"
msgstr ""
"Gather four units of Baleful Venom Sac from the Spiders that have appeared "
"north of Chopping Necks  in the ruin village of Broken Skull, and deliver "
"them to Bloodzkul the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4353"
msgstr ""
"I have been informed by Bloodzkul the Mage, that the goblin teeth you "
"gathered earlier are being put to good use by our enchanters. Bloodzkul has "
"put in a new request for another enchanting material to be gathered. She has "
"requested for four units of  Arachnid Venom Sac be gathered from the spiders "
"that have been sighted roaming north of Chopping Necks, in the ruin village "
"of Broken Skull. I believe that the  Arachnid Venom Sacs can be used to "
"enchant various items, such as weapons and armors.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, gather four units of  Arachnid Venom Sac and deliver them to "
"Bloodzkul the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4375"
msgstr ""
"Symyr-dan the Firm has asked you to deliver the letter you found in the "
"possession of the human bandits to Merdem-kai the Loyal of the Wolfmasks."

msgid "start_text_quest_4376"
msgstr ""
"I want you to deliver the letter you found in the possession of the humans "
"bandits in Kekerdan, to Mardem-kai the Loyal of the Wolfmasks. The Wolfmasks "
"are investigating why these human bandits are within the Tribelands, with "
"who they are working with, and why.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, deliver this letter to Mardem-kai that it might help the "
"Wolfmasks with their very important work."

msgid "start_text_quest_4377"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has instructed you to enter the {$j14} dungeon, were the "
"Wolfmasks suspect the Gray Ork leaders may be hiding, and to kill two Gray "
"Ork Chieftains."

msgid "start_text_quest_4378"
msgstr ""
"A very interesting discovery has temporarily stopped us from sending a "
"report to our allies the Orks of Morak, about the Gray Orks you successfully "
"encountered earlier. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"High ranking Gray Orks, the Gray Ork Chieftains, have been sighted near the "
"portal the leads into the {$j14} dungeon. This is a very good opportunity to "
"show our commitment to our alliance with the Orks of Morak. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task will be to enter the {$j14}, and search for these hight ranking "
"Gray Orks, and kill two Gray Ork Chieftain. This is an dangerous mission, so "
"I suggest you only accept it when you are ready."

msgid "start_text_quest_4379"
msgstr ""
"The Wolfmasks have chosen you as their worthy representative, to deliver a "
"report-letter to the Iron Orks. You are to travel to Morak, and deliver the "
"Wolfmask letter to Krushar Breakskull of the Iron Orks in Naergur."

msgid "start_text_quest_4380"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. Not only have we assisted our allies by attacking the Gray Orks "
"that had set camp in {$m13}, but have also uncovered a Gray Ork hideout in "
"the {$j14} dungeon and killed two of the highest ranking Gray Orks, the Gray "
"Ork Chielftains. Our allies will surely be more than please to be informed "
"of our success, and you #PlayerName# have been chosen to deliver this news "
"to our allies.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, the Wolfmasks proudly ask of you to travel far east across "
"Agon to Morak, and to deliver this letter to Krushar Breakskull or the Iron "
"Orks in Naergur."

msgid "start_text_quest_4381"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has asked you to search the humans bandits hideout in the "
"Nightspire ruins, for any clues that might reveal the mahirim traitor group "
"the human bandits are working for."

msgid "start_text_quest_4383"
msgstr ""
"You have discovered a coded letter hidden within the human bandits hideout "
"in the Nightspire ruins. This letter if uncoded, could possibly reveal vital "
"information about the human bandits allies within the Tribelands. Bring this "
"letter to Mardem-kai the Loyal."

msgid "start_text_quest_4384"
msgstr ""
"The destruction of the gravestone, that was being used by the humans bandits "
"and the traitor mahirim to communicate between each other, has already "
"brought results.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Members of the mahirim traitor group were sighted by our agents entering the "
"ruins where the human bandits are hiding. Therefor we can only suspect, that "
"after our discovery of the fake gravestone and its destruction, the mahirm "
"traitors were forced to delivered a message directly to the human bandits."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to revisit the human bandits hideout within the ruins, "
"and search for any clues that might give an insight on this mahirim traitors."

msgid "start_text_quest_4385"
msgstr ""
"Isinda-dai has asked you to discover why Menhir have come to Neithstone "
"Hall. You have accepted to venture to the top of Neithstone Hall, and to "
"search for any clues to this mystery."

msgid "start_text_quest_4386"
msgstr ""
"Menhir have been sighted upon the very top of Neithstone Hall, a sign which "
"indicates that the ancient ruins of Neithstone Hall must be of some "
"importance. Either the site was once home to a powerful ancient race and the "
"Menhir have come to guard it, or there could be a powerful source of magic "
"that the Menhir are attracted to, or even using.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to venture to the top of Neithstone Hall, and try to find answers "
"to this mystery. What is it that makes the ruins of Neithstone Hall so "
"important, that even the mysterious Menhir would come to visit it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4387"
msgstr ""
"Isinda-dai  has instructed you to search for clues inside the {$l12} caves, "
"and discover why the hobgoblins seem to be obsessed with {$l12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4388"
msgstr ""
"You have found parts of an old map, inside the hobgoblin caves in {$i12}, "
"together with instructions to search for an ancient artifact called the "
"Night Stone. Return to Isinda-dai and report these important finds to her."

msgid "start_text_quest_4389"
msgstr ""
"Although the many attacks we have launched against the hobgoblins lately in "
"{$l12}, and the many casualties they have suffered, the hobgoblins are "
"showing no signs of moving out of the region. Our agents have reported "
"sighting ogres within the caves, something that definitely shows that the "
"hobgoblins are here on serious businesses. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These hobgoblins seem to be guarding something within the {$l12} caves, and "
"I want to know what it is, and why they are here. There is no other "
"explanation! Why would they keep returning to {$l12} year after year?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Getting inside the {$l12} caves will not be any easy task. Neither will it "
"be avoiding those ogres. But we must discover what it is they are guarding "
"inside those caves! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This item, thing, secret, or whatever it might be, might reveal to us why "
"the hobgoblins have been over the years so persistent in trying to control "
"the region of {$l12}, and generally the eastern Tribeland territories.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to get past the hobgoblins and search inside the cave for any "
"clues. Also, watch out for the ogres."

msgid "start_text_quest_4394"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has asked you punish to Gnolls in Hunter's Run, for working with "
"the Ogres while trying to take over the region of Hunter's Moon. You have "
"been instructed to kill four Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_4395"
msgstr ""
"According to the latest report from our agents, the Ogres and Gnolls of "
"Hunter's Run seem to have formed a small alliance in an effort to take "
"control of the entire region. Hunter's Run is located right next to "
"Nightspire, and we cannot simple allow these foolish barbarian to take "
"control of Hunter's Run.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Ogres have their camp located in the northeastern part of Hunter's Run, "
"while the Gnolls are located in the southeastern part. These two camps were "
"until recently separated by River Ocrim. But now, and path and a bridge are "
"connecting these once upon a time enemies.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"This pathetic alliance between the Ogres and the Gnolls must not be allowed "
"to grow. We will begin by attacking the Gnolls. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go to the Gnoll camp and kill four Gnolls. I will mark the "
"location of the Gnoll camp on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4396"
msgstr ""
"The Wolfmasks want to end the Ogres plans of controlling Hunter's Run with "
"the help of the Gnolls. Mardem-kai has instructed you to kill three Ogres."

msgid "start_text_quest_4397"
msgstr ""
"For all we know, it is the Ogres that initiated this pathetic alliance with "
"the Gnolls, in an effort to control the region of Hunter's Run. This we "
"cannot tolerate. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Gnolls have already received the message that Hunter's Run belongs to "
"the Wolfmasks, and now all that remains is to make sure that the Ogres too "
"receive the same message. #PlayerName#, I trust that you will successfully "
"deliver this message to the Ogres. Go to the Ogre camp in Hunter's Run and "
"kill three of them. The Ogres will never control Hunter's Run."

msgid "start_text_quest_4398"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai has asked you to report to Tamari the Arcanist, and to assist the "
"Wolfmasks in discovering the identity of the troublemakers of Hornwood "
"Forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_4399"
msgstr ""
"The Sylvan creatures within Hornwood Forest, and especially the Forest "
"Prophets, continue their annoying games with attacking our patrols. Our "
"previous effort to send the Forest Prophets the message that we will not "
"tolerate these attacks any longer, seems to have not reached their ears.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"All Forest Prophets belong to groups called Circles, and each of these "
"Circles overlooks a large region supposedly protecting the forests from all "
"invaders. At the very top of each Circle's hierarchy are the Forest Prophet "
"Elders, who rule each Circle until the day they die. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The time has come to discover which is that Circle, that has been creating "
"all the problems within Hornwood Forest, and then to send a clear message to "
"the Elders of that Circle.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Tamari the Arcanist has been assigned to lead this investigation, and to end "
"the annoying games of the Forest Prophets. Report to Tamari the Arcanist, "
"and see if you can help us out an end to the problems of Hornwood Forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_44"
msgstr ""
"You have promised to return to Talaod the Blacksmith with five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4400"
msgstr ""
"Tamari the Arcanist  has asked you to the search Hornwood Forest for the "
"beast totem, that will reveal the identity of the Circle of Forest Prophets "
"that control Hornwood Forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_4401"
msgstr ""
"You have found a beast totem that symbolized a raging brown bear in the "
"vicinity of the Forest Prophets. Perhaps this is the symbol that Tamari is "
"looking for. Return to Nightspire and report this find to Tamari the "
"Arcanist."

msgid "start_text_quest_4402"
msgstr ""
"If we are to successfully send a message to the Forest Prophets, that we "
"will no longer allow them to disrupt the peace of Hornwood Forest, first we "
"must discover which Forest Prophet Circle it is we are dealing with.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"All Forest Prophet Circles have a symbol, which they use to mark the "
"territories which they believe they control. Usually this symbol in in the "
"form of a beast totem. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to Horwood Forest, and search for such a beast totem. We "
"will discover the identity of this annoying group of Forest Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_4403"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Destroy two of the Black "
"Knights that guard the floating island in {$n25}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4404"
msgstr ""
"To the west in {$n25}, there is a lave lake that has bean created from the "
"constant stream of lava that pours from mount {$o25}. Above that lava lake "
"there is a floating island, where once a secretive group of powerful wizards "
"lived their conducting experiments, researching powerful spells and creating "
"magical items. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Although the wizards are now long gone, and their home in ruin, powerful "
"Black Knights occupy this strange mystical island attacking anyone that "
"dares to approach.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Shadow Masters have expressed an interest in {$n25}, and especially the "
"wizards floating island. The only problem is the presence of the Black "
"Knights.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, assist us clear the floating island in {$n25} of the Black "
"Knights, by destroying two of them. Do this for the Shadow Salient. Do this "
"for the Alfar. Do this for Melek."

msgid "start_text_quest_4405"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to kill six Akathars and one of the Windlords that have "
"returned to {$o11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4406"
msgstr ""
"A long time ago, the valley of {$o11} that is now occupied by ogres was once "
"known as the Valley of the Stormlords, taking its name from the numerous "
"Akathars and Windlords that use to live their. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These strange magical birdlike creatures that could summon the magics of air "
"and lighting, and at times would make the whole valley light up during the "
"night with their spells, therefor give the name Valley of the Stormlords to "
"the valley. But the arrival of the ogres into the valley forced the Akathars "
"and Windlords to leave.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now the Akathars and the Windlords are slowly returning to {$o11}, and have "
"made their home up high in the mountains. But, they seem to blame us for the "
"invasion of the ogres into their home, and have begun coming down from the "
"mountain at night, attacking our people and allies that travel through the "
"region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task will be to go up into the mountains of {$o11} and kill four "
"Akathars and one Windlord. We must also remind them that we have not "
"forgotten how once upon a time they too almost drove us out of our homes "
"with their powerful magic."

msgid "start_text_quest_4407"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to kill four of the Forest Prophets that have take over "
"the Order of the Axe's small logging camp in {$p12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4408"
msgstr ""
"It would seem that our logging operations in {$p12} have not gone unnoticed, "
"and have grabbed the attention of the forest prophets. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have done our best so far to keep our logging operations to a minimum, "
"and to not damaged the natural balance of the forest. For this we can thank "
"our mirdain allies, since they have a vast knowledge of the forests and "
"nature in general. But this seems to not be enough for the forest prophets, "
"who have now taken over our small logging camp in {$p12}, after killing all "
"the workers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These so called protectors of the forests, are nothing more than a bunch of "
"cold blooded killers that must pay for their actions. The Order of the Axe "
"wants you to bring justice to the families of the murdered workers, by "
"killing four of these Forest Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_4409"
msgstr ""
"Allan the Councillor has asked you to report to Torgard the Fighter to begin "
"your combat training. Torgard the Fighter has been highlighted on your map. "
"To interact with Torgard the Fighter, use the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4410"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Sanguine. Unfortunately, you seem to have arrived at a difficult "
"time. Sanguine has been surrounded by many goblins, creating problems and "
"threatening the safety of our people. But before I ask of you to help us "
"clear the surrounding lands of the goblins, I must make sure that you are "
"well prepared. Torgard the Fighter and Jonn the Mage will be the ones "
"preparing you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"First, you will begin your combat training with Torgard the Fighter. Torgard "
"the Fighter is highlighted on your map. Walk up to Torgard, and interact "
"with him using the G key. Once you have reported for training, use the F key "
"to talk to Torgard again, and then select the quest tab to see what tasks "
"Torgard might have for you. To accept a quest, simply hit the accept button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4411"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has instructed you to hit the training dummies with your "
"Leafblade five times. The training dummies are located next to Torgard the "
"Fighter."

msgid "start_text_quest_4412"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, together we will be going through combat basics. We will start "
"with melee combat.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I see that in your possession you already have a Leafblade. We will begin "
"our training using this weapon. Nearby there is a training area with four "
"training dummies. This is where you will be training. Your first task is to "
"hit the training dummies five times using your Leafblade.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To equip yourself with the Leafblade, go to your backpack and double click "
"on your Leafblade, or drag it to the weapon slot on your paperdoll. You can "
"also drag it from your backpack into your hotbar, to any slot you wish. This "
"way you can begin organizing your hotbar, something that will surely help "
"you in the future.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To unsheathe and sheathe your weapon, simply use the R key.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, go and practice your melee combat skills on the training dummies. "
"Scoring five successful hits against the training dummies using your "
"Leafblade will be enough. Once you have equipped yourself with the "
"Leafblade, all you need to do is to aim at any training dummy and attack it "
"by simply pressing your left mouse button. The location of the training area "
"will be highlighted on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4413"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has instructed you to attack the archery targets five "
"times using archery. The location of the training area has been highlighted "
"on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4414"
msgstr ""
"You now should have in your possession a bow and a few arrows. As you "
"understand, it is time to begin your archery training. As you did with the "
"Leafblade, drag the bow into another slot on your hotbar. You must also drag "
"the arrows into the arrow slot on your paperdoll, or else you will not be "
"able to fire arrows from your bow.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can sheathe and unsheathe your bow using the T key. Now that you have "
"two weapons placed on your hotbar, you can switch between these two weapons "
"by pressing the corresponding number key buttons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, your second task will be to attack the archery targets using "
"archery. The goal here is to hit the archery targets five times. Once you "
"have equipped yourself with the bow and have placed the arrows on your "
"paperdoll, all you need to do is to aim at an archery target and to shoot an "
"arrow onto it by pressing your left mouse button. The location of the "
"training area will be highlighted on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4415"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to use the Sprint skill. Simple press the "
"SHIFT key while moving forward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4416"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to use the Parry skill. First, you must "
"equip yourself with a melee weapon. Next, just hold down the V key to Parry."

msgid "start_text_quest_4417"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to use the Crouch Walk skill to move "
"stealthily. To Crouch Walk, hold down the C key and move forward."

msgid "start_text_quest_4418"
msgstr ""
"Torgard the Fighter has asked you to use the Rest skill. The Rest skill is "
"located under General Skills. To rest, make sure you are not holding any "
"weapon. Next select the Rest skill, and then simply press your left mouse "
"button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4419"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#. You have learned the basics of combat. Before I send you off "
"to Jonn the Mage to begin you basic magic training, there are a few useful "
"tips I would like to share with you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"First of all, there is Sprinting. To Sprint, all you need to do is the press "
"the SHIFT key while running. You will need to use this skill many times, be "
"it either for hunting your enemies, or in the worst case running away from "
"them when things get a little too rough.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go ahead, and show me that you are able to Sprint."

msgid "start_text_quest_4420"
msgstr ""
"After completing your basic combat training with Torgard the Fighter, you "
"will now report to Jonn the Mage to begin your magic basics training. Jonn "
"the Mage has been highlighted on your map. To interact with Jonn the Mage "
"use the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4421"
msgstr ""
"We have completed your basic combat training. You will now continue training "
"with Jonn the Mage, learning the basics of magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Jonn the Mage is highlighted on your map. Simple walk over to him and "
"interact using the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4422"
msgstr ""
"Jonn the Mage has asked you to strike the mage totem with five Mana Missiles "
"using your staff. The mage totem is located close to Selensha the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4423"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, together we will learn the basics of magic. Magic is as "
"important as combat itself. Many of your enemies may be using magic against "
"you, so it is wise that you too should be able to use magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In your possession you should have a staff. As you did previously with your "
"weapons, place the staff onto your hotbar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To equip yourself with the staff, you must press the number key that "
"corresponds to the slot you have placed the staff in. Then by simply using "
"the R key, you should be able unsheathe the staff and use it. But, you will "
"also need to select what spell to cast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Except for Mana Missile and Heal Self, all spells consume materials called "
"reagents. Six are the reagents used for casting spells. Mandrake, Resin, "
"Sulfur, Nacre, Bone and Ashes. For now, we will learn to cast these two "
"spells that do not require any reagents.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We will start with the offensive spell called Mana Missile. To select Mana "
"Missile go to Spells, and under Lesser Magic Spells search for Mana Missile. "
"Next drag the Mana Missile spell onto your hotbar. To cast the Mana Missile, "
"first equip yourself with the staff. Next select Mana Missile by pressing "
"the number key that corresponds to the slot were you placed the Mana Missile "
"spell. Now, all that is left to do, is for you to aim at a target, and by "
"simply pressing your left mouse button to cast a Mana Missile spell.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task will be to strike the the mage totem which is nearby, with five "
"Mana Missiles using your staff. Once you have completed this simple yet very "
"important training exercise, return to me so we may continue with your "
"training. The location of the mage totem will be highlighted on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4424"
msgstr "Jonn the Mage has asked you to cast a Heal Self spell."

msgid "start_text_quest_4425"
msgstr ""
"So far, you have learned how to attack your enemies using melee attacks, "
"archery attacks and even magic attacks. But to survive, you must also learn "
"how to take care of yourself. Quite often, you will need healing and resting."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Torgard the Fighter has taught you that by simply resting, you can regain "
"health, stamina and mana. But sometimes, you might not have the luxury of "
"time to just simply sit down and rest. You might need that something extra. "
"Why not take care of yourself using a little magic?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The staff you used earlier to cast Mana Missiles, can also be used to cast "
"spells that can heal you. Go to Spells, and from Lesser Magic Spells drag "
"the Heal Self spell onto your hotbar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, cast a Heal Self spell."

msgid "start_text_quest_4426"
msgstr ""
"Simeon the Merchant has asked you to use the bank that is located in "
"Sanguine, and if you wish you may even store some of your possessions there. "
"To access the bank, simply walk up close to it, and press the F key while "
"facing it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4427"
msgstr ""
"After completing your basic magic training with Jonn the Mage, Jonn has "
"informed you that Simeon the Merchant would like to have a word with you "
"before you return to the Councillor and end your basic training.\r\n"
"Simeon the Merchant has been highlighted on your map. Interact with Simeon "
"the Merchant, using the G key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4428"
msgstr ""
"#PlayerName#, by now you have collected a few rewards. It would not be wise "
"to carry all your belongings around with you, especially once you have left "
"the safety of the town's guard towers. What I suggest is that you store some "
"of your possessions somewhere safe. You can do this by using the bank.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Banks are found all over Agon, almost in every town and city. Once you have "
"used a bank to store your belongings, you and only you can access those "
"items again. Also you will be able can access your belongings at any bank "
"that you are able to use. In other terms, the banks throughout Agon are all "
"connected.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is a bank located here in Sanguine. I want you to go and access it, "
"and if you wish you may also store some of your belongings. The location of "
"the bank is highlighted on your map with a blue dot. To access the bank, "
"simply walk up close to it, and press the F key while facing it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4429"
msgstr ""
"Report to Allan the Councillor to complete your basic training in Sanguine."

msgid "start_text_quest_4430"
msgstr ""
"I believe that Allan the Councillor is waiting to hear how your basic "
"training has come along. #PlayerName#, report to Allan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_4431"
msgstr ""
"William the Councillor has asked you to report to Catherine the Fighter to "
"begin your combat training. Catherine the Fighter has been highlighted on "
"your map. To interact with Catherine the Fighter, use the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4432"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Sandbrook. My dear friend, you seem to have arrived at a "
"difficult time. Sandbrook has been under attack by many goblins, and we fear "
"the situation could get worse. I would ask of you to help us remove the "
"goblins from the surrounding lands, but first I must make sure that you are "
"well prepared.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will go and speak with Catherine the Fighter who will be teaching you "
"the basics of combat. Catherine is highlighted on your map. Walk up to "
"Catherine, and interact with her using the F key. One you have reported for "
"training, use the F key to talk to Catherine again, and then select the "
"quest tab to see what tasks Catherine might have for you. To accept a quest, "
"simply hit the accept button."

