msgid "start_text_quest_4467"
msgstr ""
"Well met #PlayerName#, I will be teaching you the basics of magic. Magic is "
"as important as combat itself. Many of your enemies will be using magic "
"against you, so it is wise that you too should be able to use magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In your possession you should have a staff. As you did previously with your "
"weapons, place the staff onto your hotbar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To equip yourself with the staff, you must press the number key that "
"corresponds to the slot you have placed the staff in. Then by simply using "
"the R key, you should be able unsheathe the staff and use it. But, you will "
"also need to select what spell to cast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Except for Mana Missile and Heal Self, all spells consume materials called "
"reagents. Six are the reagents used for casting spells. Mandrake, Resin, "
"Sulfur, Nacre, Bone and Ashes. For now, we will learn to cast these two "
"spells that do not require reagents.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We will start with the offensive spell called Mana Missile. To select Mana "
"Missile go to Spells and, under Lesser Magic Spells, search for Mana "
"Missile. Then drag the Mana Missile spell onto your hotbar. To cast the Mana "
"Missile, first equip yourself with the staff. Next select Mana Missile by "
"pressing the number key that corresponds to the slot where you placed the "
"Mana Missile spell. This will activate that spell as your current cast.  "
"Now, all that is left to do is for you to aim at a target, and by simply "
"pressing your left mouse button to cast a Mana Missile spell.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task will be to strike the the mage totem which is nearby, with five "
"Mana Missiles using your staff. Once you have completed this simple yet very "
"important training exercise, return to me so we may continue with your "
"training. The location of the mage totem will be highlighted on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_4468"
msgstr "Caradwen the Mage has asked you to cast a Heal Self spell."

msgid "start_text_quest_4469"
msgstr ""
"You have learned how to attack your enemies using melee attacks, archery "
"attacks and even magic attacks. But to survive, you must also learn how to "
"take care of yourself. Quite often you will need healing and resting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kai the Fighter taught you that by simply resting you can regain health, "
"stamina and mana. But not always will you have the luxury of time to just "
"simple sit down and rest. You might need that something extra. Why not take "
"care of yourself using a little magic?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The staff you used earlier to cast Mana Missiles, can also be used to cast "
"spells that can heal you. Go to Spells, and from Lesser Magic Spells drag "
"the Heal Self spell onto your hotbar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now, cast a Heal Self spell."

msgid "start_text_quest_447"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialynna the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_4470"
msgstr ""
"After completing your basic magic training with Caradwen the Mage, Caradwen "
"has informed you that Isabel the Merchant would like to have a word with you "
"before you return to the Councillor and end your basic training.\r\n"
"Isabel the Merchant has been highlighted on your map. To interact with "
"Isabel the Merchant, use the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4471"
msgstr ""
"Isabel the Merchant has asked you to use the bank that is located in the "
"Heart of Eanna, and if you wish you may even store some of your possessions "
"there. To access the bank, simply walk up close to it, and press the F key "
"while facing it."

msgid "start_text_quest_4472"
msgstr ""
"We have completed your basic magic training. Before you return to Aidan the "
"Councillor to end your training, I have been informed that Isabel the "
"Merchant would like to speak to you about using the bank.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Isabel the Merchant is highlighted on your map. Simple walk over to her and "
"interact using the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4474"
msgstr ""
"Report to Aidan the Councillor to complete your basic training in the Heart "
"of Eanna."

msgid "start_text_quest_4475"
msgstr ""
"Aidan the Councillor is waiting to hear how your basic training has come "
"along. #PlayerName#, please report to Aidan the Councillor."

msgid "start_text_quest_448"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Silverspear, a village which started life as a site for "
"trademeets between nomadic mahirim tribes which once occupied this part of "
"the Tribelands. Under the civilizing influence of the Elders of {$j12}, "
"these tribes grew steadily more sophisticated and sedentary, before finally "
"settling permanently in Silverspear and other villages like it.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until quite recently, a large mirdain village lay a short distance west of "
"Silverspear, atop a huge, two-tiered plateau. During one of the many wars "
"between the mahirim and the mirdain nation of Mirendil, this village of "
"exiles was attacked, and its inhabitants were either killed or driven south "
"towards the great forest.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As an unforeseen consequence of this purge, a tribe of goblins have settled "
"in the abandoned mirdain village. With access to plenty of food and shelter, "
"this tribe is now breeding out of control, threatening to overwhelm "
"Silverspear with their sheer numbers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Help us get the situation under control by killing four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_449"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialynna the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_4497"
msgstr ""
"We have completed your basic magic training. Before you return to William "
"the Councillor to end your training, I have been informed that Thora the "
"Merchant would like to speak to you about using the bank.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Thora the Merchant is highlighted on your map. Simply walk over to her and "
"interact using the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4498"
msgstr ""
"We have completed your basic magic training. Before you return to Aidan the "
"Councillor to end your training, I have been informed that Isabel the "
"Merchant would like to speak to you about using the bank.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Isabel the Merchant is highlighted on your map. Simple walk over to her and "
"interact using the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_4499"
msgstr ""
"You have almost reached the end of your basic training, but before you "
"return to the Councillor to end your training, I have been informed that "
"Simeon the Merchant would like to speak to you about using the bank.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Simeon the Merchant is highlighted on your map. Simple walk over to her and "
"interact using the F key."

msgid "start_text_quest_45"
msgstr ""
"Goblins have gathered in record numbers in the Greycloak Mountains, and we "
"have little doubt that they are preparing an all-out assault on Sanguine. "
"This year's crop is easily the largest goblin horde of my lifetime, and if "
"we fail to prepare properly, the greenskins might actually overwhelm us this "
"time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to avoid such an ignominious fate, we need to improve our defenses. "
"I want you gather stone that we may use to strengthen the town wall.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Pointing your crosshair "
"towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is suitable for harvesting. "
"Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may "
"begin the procedure of extracting stone using your pickaxe. If you don't own "
"such a tool already, you may buy one from Eanna the Merchant, or from any "
"other general store. If you are a novice stonecutter, the procedure will be "
"successful approximately every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to gather five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_450"
msgstr ""
"Goblins have occupied a nearby plateau which previously was home to a "
"community of mirdain elves. These goblins are now breeding extremely "
"swiftly, and we must curtail their growth before they become too numerous to "
"handle.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In combat, goblins tend to use primitive axes which they make themselves. If "
"we leave these weapons laying about, new goblins swarming down from the "
"plateau will pick them up and use them as weapons and harvesting tools. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The elders of Silverspear want you to take two goblin axes from the local "
"goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_4500"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Halbein Grimpeak. Kill 2 Cave Hags that can "
"be found inside the Banegorge caves."

msgid "start_text_quest_4501"
msgstr ""
"Hey. How would you like to help clear out these hag infested caves. You up "
"to the task? Hmmm, not sure eh. Well, I'll tell you what. The Banegorge "
"caves are crawling with Cave Hags. So many, that even the Fangs of Ottenhal "
"could do with the extra  help in dealing with them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is good pay for those that assist the Fangs in clearing these caves. "
"That is all that I can say. You can begin by hunting down 2 of those filthy "
"Cave Hags. Manage this small feat, and the Fangs of Ottenhal might just have "
"a job for you."

msgid "start_text_quest_4502"
msgstr ""
"You have spoken to Halbein Grimpeak, and accepted to take part in the "
"Banegorge Dungeon Cave Hag Hunt. Kill 15 Cave Hags that can be found inside "
"Banegorge Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4503"
msgstr ""
"Want to kill more Cave Hags. Can't blame you. The Fangs of Ottenhal are "
"rewarding anybody who can kill 15 Cave Hags. But, there is one rule. Once "
"you have completed the hunt, you will be able to take part in the Banegorge "
"Dungeon Cave Hag Hunt again after 21 hours. That is the only rule. Are you "
"ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4504"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mordhan Blackridge. Kill 4 Crypt Guards that "
"can be found inside Mabria Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4505"
msgstr ""
"The halls and corridors of this well maintained dungeon are believed to once "
"be home to the Knights of Mabria, an knightly order dedicated to the "
"extermination of all mages and any who supported the use for magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Knights of Mabria were extremest, and according to the few documented "
"fragments that have been uncovered by the Simiran Order, the Knights of "
"Mabria were once Agon's most feared group of magehunters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Simiran Order wishes to begin explorations into the dungeon and its well "
"kept secrets of the Knights of Mabria. But, it is not that easy. Crypt "
"Guards haunt the dungeon complex, attacking any who enter. It is not yet "
"determined if these dungeon guardians are the Knights of Mabria, who have "
"returned from the afterlife waiting once more to begin there magehunts "
"across Agon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Simiran Order is searching for volunteers to assist in clearing the "
"dungeon. Any who wish to assist will of course be rewarded, but must first "
"pass a small test. Succeed in killed 4 Crypt Guards, and then we will talk "
"again to see if you could hunt for the Simiran Order."

msgid "start_text_quest_4506"
msgstr ""
"You have spoken to Mordhan Blackridge, and accepted to take part in the "
"Mabria Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt. Kill 30 Crypt Guards inside Mabria Dungeon."
"\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4507"
msgstr ""
"The Simiran Order wishes to clear Mabria Dungeon of the many Crypt Guards "
"that roam its halls, and will reward well those few brave souls that are "
"willing assist them in this operation.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Simiran Order has declared the Mabria Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt. The hunt "
"is for 30 Crypt Guards. Not one less, not one more. Every time you complete "
"the Mabria Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt, you will be able to participate in the "
"hunt again after 21 hours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"My friend, are you one of those brave souls ready to take part in the Mabria "
"Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4508"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Damantia Dreamwalker. Kill 3 Sarlid "
"Darkweavers that can be found inside the Larethain caves."

msgid "start_text_quest_4509"
msgstr ""
"Could I interest you in a little extra work? Don't be alarmed my friend. The "
"rewards are good for\r\n"
"those that assist the Hintenfau Sisterhood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The caves further into the Larethain dungeon are home to Darkweavers, the "
"most dangerous of the Sarlid family. These Darkweavers are interfering with "
"the Sisterhood's plans. All that we ask is that you assist us in removing "
"them from the caves, or at least help us decrease there numbers as much as "
"possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Darkweavers are located in the later parts of the dungeon, beyond the "
"first room that is full of undead guardians. Manage to get past these "
"skeleton guardians, and you will discover the caves and tunnel that are "
"crawling with Darkweavers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To begin with, kill 3 Sarlid Darkweavers. Complete this small task, and be "
"sure that more work will follow."

msgid "start_text_quest_451"
msgstr "You have accepted a quest from Sa-Imdor. Gather five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4510"
msgstr ""
"Damantia Dreamwalker has managed to convince you to partake in the Larethain "
"Dungeon Darkweaver Hunt. Kill 25 Sarlid Darkweavers that have infested "
"Larethain Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4512"
msgstr ""
"Excellent. You have decided to work once more for the Sisterhood. I am "
"pleased. The Hintenfau Sisterhood has declared a Darkweaver hunt within "
"these caves. Anybody who accepts to hunt down and kill 25 Sarlid Darkweavers "
"will be well rewarded. But that is not all. Once you have completed the hunt "
"and have killing 25 Darkweavers, you may partake again in the Larethain "
"Dungeon Darkweaver Hunt after 21 hours. Are you ready to hunt?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4513"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Fotel-ayn the Calm. Kill one of the Tomb "
"Iklits that can be found Ahu Ishtra Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4514"
msgstr ""
"The Ahu Ishtra caves were once home to a few pathetic goblins, until Tomb "
"Iklits moved in and took over the majority of the caves.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Hintenfau Sisterhood wants to examine this strange event closely, and "
"possibly uncover how and why the fearless Tomb Iklits, the most powerful of "
"all Iklits, have migrated into these caves. There is good pay for those that "
"assist the Sisterhood, and further rewards for those that prove their value "
"to the Sisterhood. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you believe you could provide some services to the Sisterhood, you can "
"begin by killing one of these dangerous Tomb Iklits."

msgid "start_text_quest_4515"
msgstr ""
"You have spoken to Fotel-ayn the Calm, and accepted to take part in the Ahu "
"Ishtra Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt. Kill 10 Tomb Iklits that can be found inside "
"the Ahu Ishtra caves.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4516"
msgstr ""
"Ah, are you ready to hunt more Tomb Iklits? Would you like to participate in "
"the Ahu Ishtra Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt? Two are the rules to the hunt. One, "
"you will be rewarded each time you accept to hunt 10 Tomb Iklits. Two, once "
"you have completed the hunt you may partake again in the Ahu Ishtra Dungeon "
"Tomb Iklit Hunt after 21 hours. Are we clear?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4517"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ultunuk Heartstabber. Kill one Tomb Iklit "
"inside Istind Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4518"
msgstr ""
"Rumors always existed of a lost city located somewhere south of Dvergheim, "
"and the Lords of Espenhal suspect that this here dungeon could lead to it."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The researchers of Espenhal although well renowned for their knowledge of "
"the ancients world, are also known for their poor fighting and survival "
"skills. They must begin exploring this dungeon for signs that might lead to "
"the lost city. Therefor, the Lords are willing to pay those that will help "
"clear this dungeon of the many dangerous monsters, to allow the researchers "
"to begin their work.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the most dangerous monsters found inside this dungeon are the Tomb "
"Iklits. It is these monsters the Lords wish to eradicate from withing Istind "
"Dungeon. If you wish to assist the Lords of Espenhall, you can begin by "
"killing one of the Tomb Iklits. Succeed, and I am sure that more challenges "
"will follow."

msgid "start_text_quest_4519"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Ultunuk Heartstabber's offer, to take part in the Istind "
"Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt. Kill 10 Tomb Iklits inside Istind Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_452"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the elders of Silverspear have "
"decided to expand and improve the walls around our city. Since we are short "
"on raw materials, I want you to help us out by gathering suitably shaped "
"building blocks from boulders found in the wilderness surrounding town.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Omarandyr the Merchant, which lies within "
"Silverspear.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_4520"
msgstr ""
"So, you wish to kill Tomb Iklits. It takes a lot of courage to go against "
"these creatures. The Lords of Espenhal too desire to see these Tomb Iklits "
"dead. They have gone as far as declaring a sort of hunt, for those brave "
"enough to face these creatures. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is the Istind Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt, and any that manage to kill 10 "
"Tomb Iklits will receive a handsome reward. There are only two rules to the "
"hunt. One, to kill 10 Tomb Iklits. Two, once you have completed the hunt you "
"may partake again in the Istind Dungeon Tomb Iklit Hunt after 21 hours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So brave hunter, are you ready to hunt some Tomb Iklits?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4521"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kandra Dragonaxe. Kill 3 Crypt Guards that "
"can be found inside the Meldanyr Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4522"
msgstr ""
"Many stories have been passed down through the ages about the dark acts took "
"place within the halls of this dungeon. Stories of a group of mad wizards "
"called the Circle of Death and Fire, who were obsessed with experimenting "
"and combining necromancy with the element of fire. Tales talk of the twisted "
"and dark experiments the wizards conducted on the many fire elementals that "
"once ruled these dungeons.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If any of these stories are true, then surely some sort of documentation of "
"the mad wizards work must be hidden somewhere within the many rooms of this "
"dungeon. My superiors are interested in finding any such documents if they "
"exist, before they fall into the wrong hands. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Searching the dungeon will not be easy, since it is overrun by numerous "
"Crypt Guards. Therefor, there is a reward for those, that assist us in the "
"search. Destroy 3 Crypt Guards for me, and if you succeed, we might come to "
"a better agreement."

msgid "start_text_quest_4523"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Kandra Dragonaxe's offer, to partake in the Meldanyr "
"Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt. Kill 30 Crypt Guards that guard the halls of "
"Meldanyr Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4524"
msgstr ""
"Back for more I see. Hahaha. Excellent. These Crypt Guard will not beat the "
"Fangs of Ottenhal. Here is the offer. Every time you manage to destroy 30 of "
"the Crypt Guards that guard the secret of this dungeon, I will reward you. "
"But wait, there is more. Once you have completed the hunt you may partake "
"again in the Meldanyr Dungeon Crypt Guard Hunt after 21 hours. Are you ready "
"to destroy some Crypt Guards?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4525"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Urdan-tai the Tough. Kill 2 Undead Dwarves "
"inside Otredale Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4526"
msgstr ""
"The Otredale mines, once the glory of the dwarven empire, have been "
"completely abandoned since the dark curse that struck the miners years ago. "
"Overrun by Undead Dwarves, the mines have been reduced to nothing more than "
"a frozen tomb.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If the authorizes in Ymir's Tear do not intend to do something about the "
"situation, then why not have someone else take over the mines and restore "
"them to their former glory. Somebody strong, like the White Hunters of "
"Niflheim.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is good pay for those that assist the White Hunters. Clear the Undead "
"Dwarves from these mines, and benefit from a strong partnership with the "
"White Hunters. If you succeed in killing 2 of these Undead Dwarfs, I am sure "
"we could come to some sort of agreement."

msgid "start_text_quest_4527"
msgstr ""
"You have spoken with Urdan-tai the Tough, and accepted to take part in the "
"Otredale Dungeon Undead Dwarf Hunt. Kill 15 Undead Dwarves inside the "
"Otredale mines.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4528"
msgstr ""
"The White Hunters offer good pay to those who assist in removing Undead "
"Dwarves from within these frozen mines. The pay is for 15 Undead Dwarves. It "
"is called the Otredale Dungeon Undead Dwarf Hunt.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Every time you complete the hunt you will receive your pay, and be able to "
"participate in another hunt after 21 hours. Ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4529"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Muruk Blackspike. Kill 4 Cave Trolls that can "
"be found inside Scarbourne Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_453"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sa-Imdor the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_4530"
msgstr ""
"Tempted in earning a little extra gold? Maybe even some other interesting "
"rewards? Well, it so happens that you my friend are lucky. The Silverswords "
"have decided to offer you that unique opportunity to earn that extra "
"something. Oh, don't worry. There isn't much you need to do. Just assist us "
"in clearing these cave from the Cave Trolls, and that's about it. What do "
"you say? Hmm, let's make this easy for you. How about you just kill 4 Cave "
"Trolls. Do this, and then we can talk big business."

msgid "start_text_quest_4531"
msgstr ""
"Muruk Blackspike has managed to convince you to take part in the Scarbourne "
"Dungeon Cave Troll Hunt. Kill 40 Cave Trolls that crawl inside Scarbourne "
"Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4532"
msgstr ""
"Hey! If it's Cave Trolls you feel like hunting, look no further! These caves "
"are crawling with Cave Trolls, and the Silverswords reward well those who "
"accept to hunt 40 Cave Trolls. But wait, there is more. Once you have "
"completed the hunt, you may partake again in another Scarbourne Dungeon Cave "
"Troll Hunt after 21 hours. So my friend, are you ready to hunt?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4533"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Stelak the Tall. Kill 2 Cave Hags that can be "
"found inside Sirith Dain dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4534"
msgstr ""
"Hey you! You look like one of those tough adventurers that will kill "
"anything for the right price. Good. The Mirrorsea Union in looking for "
"people like you. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cave Hags that have infested parts of this dungeon, are in the way of the "
"Union's plans. What plans is none of your business. What does concern you, "
"is that there is good pay for those that can manage to stay alive and kill "
"as many of these stinking Cave Hags.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Each adventurer must first pass a small test, before being employed by the "
"Union. Go and kill 2 stinking Cave Hags, and then we'll talk business."

msgid "start_text_quest_4535"
msgstr ""
"You have spoken to Stelak the Tall, and accepted to take part in the Sirith "
"Dain Dungeon Cave Hag Hunt. Kill 15 Cave Hags inside the Sirith Dain Dungeon."
"\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4536"
msgstr ""
"The Sirith Dain Dungeon Cave Hag Hunt. That's the job. Kill 15 of these "
"Stinking Cave Hags that stand in the way of the Mirrorsea Union, and you'll "
"receive a handsome reward. Once you have completed the hunt you will be able "
"to hunt again after 21 hours. Well, what are you waiting for? I want 15 of "
"the stinking Cave Hags dead!"

msgid "start_text_quest_4537"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Parras Darkblood. Kill 3 Cave Spiders that "
"can be found inside the Kaerdan Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_4538"
msgstr ""
"The Kaerdan dungeon, is one of the very few Nithron Dungeons that can be "
"found throughout Agon. These powerful giants of the past had uncovered many "
"secrets of the ancient world in the years of there dominance. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Lords of Espenhal wish to study and explore this Nithron Dungeon, and "
"uncover many of these ancient secrets that are surely buried deep inside it. "
"But to begin with, the Lords need to establish a save base of operations.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is an opening that leads to a natural cave system, away from the "
"Nithron Dungeon. This is where the Lords of Espenhal wish to establish a "
"base. The problem is that this particular part of the dungeon is crawling "
"with Cave Spiders. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Brave volunteers will be needed to assist in clearing this part of the "
"dungeon. Each volunteers that wishes to assist the Lords of Espenhal, must "
"first prove their worth. This can be achieved by killing 3 Cave Spiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_4539"
msgstr ""
"Parras Darkblood's has managed to convince you to take part in the Kaerdan "
"Dungeon Cave Spider Hunt. Kill 30 Cave Spiders that have infested parts of "
"Kaerdan Dungeon\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_454"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Silverspear have decided to build more guard towers along the "
"road which connects our village to the mahirim capital of {$j12}. Before "
"work can start on these structures, however, we need help with gathering the "
"timber needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood "
"Axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Omarandyr "
"the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_4540"
msgstr ""
"Welcome back. Are you prepared to assist once more the Lords of Espenhal? Of "
"course you are.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Lords have declared a small hunt within these caves, the Kaerdan Dungeon "
"Cave Spider Hunt. The hunt is for 30 Cave Spiders, and the pay is well worth "
"it. The only rule to the hunt is that once you have completed the hunt, you "
"will be able to partake in the hunt again after 21 hours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Are you ready to begin slaying these Cave Spiders?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4543"
msgstr ""
"Hanthar Blackfrost has instructed you to travel to the Harn Mandean "
"headquarters in Dulguna, and report to Hanthar the Mage to discovery of the "
"strange fire pillar within the abandoned severii stronghold in {$j23}."

msgid "start_text_quest_4544"
msgstr ""
"I want you to travel to Dulguna to the Harn Mandean headquarters, go to "
"Hanthar the Mage, yes he does share the same name with me, and report to him "
"the strange find of the fire pillar within the severii stronghold in {$j23}. "
"Tell him to search the library records for any reference to any sort of "
"similar structure he might find. This is too strange to ignore. First the "
"severii disappearing from one of their most important strongholds, and then "
"the fire creatures and the strange fire pillar."

msgid "start_text_quest_4545"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thanial Nightlight. Kill 3 Shadow Spirits "
"that haunt Hardruk Dungeon. Thanial has informed you that the Shadow Spirits "
"are immune to physical damage."

msgid "start_text_quest_4547"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Thanial Nightlight's offer, to partake in the Hardruk "
"Dungeon Shadow Spirit Hunt. Kill 20 Shadow Spirits that haunt Hardruk "
"Dungeon. Thanial has informed you that the Shadow Spirits are immune to "
"physical damage.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4548"
msgstr ""
"Ah, back for another round of Shadow Spirit hunting I presume. Excellent. "
"The Loremasters of Janhalek are willing to reward well, for anybody who "
"accepts to hunt down 20 of these Shadow Spirits.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you have completed this daring task, having killing 20 Shadow Spirits, "
"you may partake again in another Hardruk Dungeon Shadow Spirit Hunt after 21 "
"hours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Let me remind you that Shadow Spirits are immune to physical damage. Only "
"magic will work against them. So, ready to begin the hunt?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4549"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Corsal Greyhouse. Kill 3 Shade Salamanders "
"that can be found inside the Velmuna caves."

msgid "start_text_quest_455"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Murion-tai the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_4552"
msgstr ""
"The Velmuna caves are home to a rare bread of Salamander, the Shade "
"Salamander. Unlike their surface cousins the common Salamanders, the Shade "
"Salamanders are much tougher, more aggressive, and extremely poisonous.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Shade Salamanders do not take well to anybody who enters their home. "
"They will instantly attack anybody insight, and will not stop until the "
"intruders dies, or they die. They are true warriors to the very end.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am looking for brave adventures to assist in clearing these caves. Why, is "
"not something I can exactly share with you at the moment. All I can share "
"with you is that the Lords of Espenhal, the organization which I happed to "
"work for, are prepared to pay well for anybody who is willing to help in "
"this cleaning operation.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To begin with, I will first need to test you. All you need to do, is to kill "
"3 Shade Salamanders. If you managed to complete this test, then I will have "
"much more work for you if you so desire, and the pay will by good."

msgid "start_text_quest_4553"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Corsal Greyhouse. Kill 25 Shade Salamanders "
"that can be found inside the Velmuna caves.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4554"
msgstr ""
"So, you wish to continue hunting more Shade Salamanders. Very well. My "
"superiors are prepared to pay well for you to continue hunting Shade "
"Salamanders. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The task is to kill 25 Shade Salamanders. Once you have completed the hunt, "
"you will be able to hunt again after 21 hours. That is the deal. Do you "
"accept?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4555"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sira Deathcry. Kill 3 Cave Spiders that can "
"be found inside the Winterworth caves."

msgid "start_text_quest_4556"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to the dark and spider infested Winterworth caves. I am Sira "
"Deathcry of the Hintenfau Sisterhood, and I have a proposition for you.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Sisterhood has a small interest in claiming these caves of strategical "
"value. But to achieve this, the population of the Cave Spiders must be "
"reduced as much as possible. Rewards will be given to those that assist us "
"in cleaning these caves. But first, each individual must prove their worth "
"before allowed to hunt for the Sisterhood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill 3 of the Cave Spiders that crawl inside these caves, and then I will "
"share with you the terms of the hunt."

msgid "start_text_quest_4557"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Sira Deathcry. Kill 30 Cave Spiders that can "
"be found inside the Winterworth caves.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4558"
msgstr ""
"Do you wish to continue hunting more Cave Spiders? Very well then. Here are "
"the terms of the hunt. You will be rewarded every time you accept to hunt 30 "
"Cave Spiders. Once you have completed the hunt, you will be able to hunt "
"again after 21 hours. Do you accept?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4559"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Balac Stonetooth. Kill 4 Cave Trolls that can "
"be found inside the Myntharn caves."

msgid "start_text_quest_456"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Omarandyr the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_4560"
msgstr ""
"Hey, you want to kill some Cave Trolls? Or are you to scared to fight. The "
"Fangs of Ottenhal are looking for, erm, brave warriors to kill all Cave "
"Trolls inside Myntharn Dungeon. And give good reward too. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But first, brave warriors must pass small test, before take part in big Cave "
"Troll hunt. Go kill 4 Cave Trolls, and then we talk."

msgid "start_text_quest_4561"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Balac Stonetooth. Kill 40 Cave Trolls that "
"can be found inside the Myntharn caves.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_4562"
msgstr ""
"Haha, you want to kill more Cave Trolls. This is good. Killing many Cave "
"Troll is fun. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Fangs of Ottenhal has good deal. Every time you kill 40 Cave Trolls, you "
"get reward. But deal say, that when kill 40 Cave Troll, you can kill again "
"after 21 hours. This is deal. You like?"

msgid "start_text_quest_4563"
msgstr ""
"Allan the Councillor has asked you to help clear out the Scumlings from "
"Sanguine's sewer system. Kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling Guard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4564"
msgstr ""
"Sanguine has a large sewer system, mostly due to the need to divert water "
"during the seasonal floods. The sewers are something of a nightmare to "
"administrate, and there is always something down there that needs to be "
"maintained, unclogged, or killed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Maintenance workers have reported sightings of hunched humanoids with rodent "
"features, which indicate that Scumlings have found their way into the "
"sewers. The Scumlings have established a major presence in the Sanguine's "
"sewers, doubtlessly after breaking through the walls of some obscure and "
"decaying part of the network.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Just like their surface cousins the Hivekin, the Scumlings multiply at an "
"alarming rate. Therefor it is imperative to keep the Scumlings population to "
"a minimum, before our sewers are completely overrun with them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help us in our efforts to control the Scumlings population, by "
"accepting to enter the Sanguine's sewer system and killing 4 Scumling "
"Workers and 1 Scumling Guard. You can enter the city sewer system via an "
"entrance, the location of which I shall mark on your map. To enter, all you "
"need to do is to use the action button on the sewer entrance. When you have "
"competed this task, search for the sewer exit to return to the surface, "
"again using action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4565"
msgstr ""
"Ensharra the Councillor has asked you to help clear out the Scumlings from "
"Shoal's sewer system. Kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling Guard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4566"
msgstr ""
"Sylanae the Councillor has asked you to help clear out the Scumlings from "
"Charybdis's sewer system. Kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling Guard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4567"
msgstr ""
"Charybdis's sewer system has helped for many years dispose of most of the "
"city's wastes. Unfortunately, the city's wastes are not all that have "
"entered in the sewer system. Unwanted intruders regularly find their way "
"into the system, and sometimes they have time to nest and multiply before we "
"become aware of their presence. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of these unwanted intruders are the Scumlings, that are attracted to the "
"filthy environment of the sewers. The Scumlings have broken into the sewer "
"system, possibly through some decaying part of the network.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Scumlings breed at an alarming rate just like their surface cousins the "
"Hivekin. Therefor it is necessary to conduct occasional sewer sweeps, to "
"maintain the Scumlings population as low as possible.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help us reduce the Scumlings population by accepting to enter the "
"Charybdis's sewer system and killing 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling "
"Guard. You can enter the city sewer system via an entrance, the location of "
"which I shall mark on your map. To enter the sewer system, all you need to "
"do is to use the action button on the sewer entrance. When you have competed "
"this task, search for the sewer exit to return to the surface, again using "
"action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4568"
msgstr ""
"Tivasta the Councillor has asked you to help clear out the Scumlings "
"infestation Red Moon's sewer system. Kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling "
"Guard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4569"
msgstr ""
"Red Moon has a large sewer system, mostly due to the need to divert water "
"during the seasonal floods. The sewers are something of a nightmare to "
"administrate, and there is always something down there that needs to be "
"maintained, unclogged, or killed.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Maintenance workers have reported sightings of hunched humanoids with rodent "
"features, which indicate that Scumlings have found their way into the "
"sewers. The Scumlings have established a major presence in the Red Moon's "
"sewers, doubtlessly after breaking through the walls of some obscure and "
"decaying part of the network.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Scumlings breed at an alarming rate, just like their surface cousins the "
"Hivekin. Therefor it is imperative to keep the Scumlings population to a "
"minimum, before our sewers are completely overrun by them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can help Red Moon reduce the Scumlings population, by accepting to enter "
"the sewer system and to kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling Guard. You "
"can enter the city sewer system via an entrance, the location of which I "
"shall mark on your map. To enter, all you need to do is to use the action "
"button on the sewer entrance. When you have competed this task, search for "
"the sewer exit to return to the surface, again using action button."

msgid "start_text_quest_457"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ialynna the Councillor. Gather four Teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_4571"
msgstr ""
"Hundred of year ago, a sewer system was built under Ymir's Tear to accept "
"and dispose of most of the city's wastes. Unfortunately over the years, some "
"parts of the sewer walls began decaying, making it possible for creatures to "
"enter the sewer system. Creature such as the Scumlings, who seek out filthy "
"environment such that of our sewers to call their home.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Scumlings are cousins of the surface Hivekin, and relatively harmless. But "
"just like the Hivekin, the Scumlings too can breed at an almost "
"inconceivable pace. In the case of Ymir's Tear with its sewer system, the "
"worst case scenario involves the Scumlings breeding out of control, "
"establishing a permanent infestation, and eventually threatening the safety "
"and health of our people.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can assist us control the Scumlings population, by accepting to enter "
"the Ymir's Tear's sewer system and killing 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling "
"Guard. You can enter the city sewer system via an entrance, the location of "
"which I shall mark on your map. To enter, all you need to do is to use the "
"action button on the sewer entrance. When you have competed this task, "
"search for the sewer exit to return to the surface, again using action "
"button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4572"
msgstr ""
"Izkruul the Councillor has asked you to help clear out a Scumlings "
"infestation from Flaming Skull's sewer system. Kill 4 Scumling Workers and 1 "
"Scumling Guard."

msgid "start_text_quest_4573"
msgstr ""
"Hundreds of years ago, a sewer system was built under Flaming Skull to "
"accept and dispose of most of the city's wastes. A sewer system build by "
"many of our svartdvergir slaves at the time. And for hundred of years, the "
"sewer system has served us well.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A sewer system like the one here in Flaming Skull, requires hard work to "
"maintain in its working condition. There is always something down there that "
"needs to either be unclogged or killed. Unwanted intruders find their way "
"into the system, sometimes having enough time to nest and multiply before we "
"become aware of their presence. Creatures such as the Scumlings, hunched "
"humanoids with rodentlike features.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Scumlings are relatively harmless individually, but given half a chance, a "
"group of them will breed at an almost inconceivable pace. We must "
"immediately take those steps, to stop the Scumlings from breeding out of "
"control, establishing a permanent infestation, and eventually threatening "
"the safety of the surface population. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will enter Flaming Skull's sewer system, and kill 4 Scumling Workers and "
"1 Scumling Guard. You will do what it takes, to stop the Scumling "
"infestation. You can enter the city sewer system via an entrance, the "
"location of which I shall mark on your map. To enter, all you need to do is "
"to use the action button on the sewer entrance. When you have competed this "
"task, search for the sewer exit to return to the surface, again using action "
"button."

msgid "start_text_quest_4574"
msgstr ""
"A large sewer system exists underneath Shoal, were all the city's wastes are "
"funneled into. Unfortunately the sewer system that serves us well, can also "
"become home to many unwanted intruders, who enter the sewer system after "
"breaking through the walls of some decaying part of the network. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Maintenance workers have reported that Scumlings, hunched humanoids with "
"rodent features, have found their way into the sewers. These unwanted "
"intruders regularly find their way into the sewer system, and sometimes have "
"time to nest and multiply before we become aware of their presence. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Just like their surface cousins the Hivekin, the Scumlings too multiply at "
"an alarming rate. Our goal, will be to keep the Scumlings numbers as low as "
"possible, since it will be almost impossible to completely eradicate them."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will assist us in our efforts to control the Scumlings population, by "
"entering Shoal's sewer system and killing 4 Scumling Workers and 1 Scumling "
"Guard. You can enter the city sewer system via an entrance, the location of "
"which I shall mark on your map. To enter, all you need to do is to use the "
"action button on the sewer entrance. When you have competed this task, "
"search for the sewer exit to return to the surface, again using action "
"button."

msgid "start_text_quest_458"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The abandoned mirdain village to the west of here has been overrun by a "
"large number of goblins. As we clean out these pests, we should make sure to "
"extract the parts such as the teeth, that find use in enchantment rituals.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Omarandyr the Merchant.  Assuming that you are a "
"novice skinner, you should be able to remove intact teeth every other time "
"you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_459"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Ialynna the Councillor. Cast twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_46"
msgstr ""
"You have promised to return to Anton the Blacksmith with five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_460"
msgstr ""
"We must use every trick available to us in our attempt to expel the goblins "
"from Silverspear. One thing we should use to our advantage, is the fact that "
"goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It seems that the ancestral "
"goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, and now the entire race "
"has a deeply ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our efforts by casting twenty Mana Missiles against the "
"Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Murion-tai the Arcanist. Once you own a staff, you "
"may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_461"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Andor-kai s quest. Kill four goblins, then return to "
"Hunter's Moon for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_462"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Hunter's Moon, a village located near some of the finest hunting "
"grounds in the Tribelands. Unfortunately, these grounds have become infested "
"by hordes of goblins who are stripping the vegetation clean of anything that "
"is even vaguely edible, while hunting prey animals to the verge of "
"extinction. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The plague of goblins must be dealt with as quickly as possible, before they "
"do irreparable damage to the local hunting grounds. Hunt down and kill four "
"of the goblins that have infested our hunting grounds."

msgid "start_text_quest_463"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Andor-kai the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_464"
msgstr ""
"This region has been overrun by a tribe of goblins who have devoured or "
"simply displaced the herds of prey animals that previously inhabited the "
"plains to the east of here. We want to eradicate the goblins and reestablish "
"this region as one of the prime hunting grounds in the Tribelands. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"When hunting and skinning, as well as in combat, goblins use primitive axes "
"made of flint. Despite their rudimentary nature, these axes are highly "
"prized by the greenskins, since only a few of them are capable of making "
"such tools. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes taken from the greenskins that infest "
"the wilderness around Hunter's Moon."

msgid "start_text_quest_465"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Felalon the Blacksmith. Gather five unites of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_466"
msgstr ""
"As a result of the increased monster presence in this region, we are "
"planning a series of guardhouses which will protect the hunting grounds to "
"the east of here. I want you to help us by gathering stone, which is one of "
"the primary resources needed for this project.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you first need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a "
"tool already, you may buy one from Agrina the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you are a novice stonecutter, the procedure will be successful "
"approximately every other time."

msgid "start_text_quest_467"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Felalon the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_469"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Celene the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_47"
msgstr ""
"Due to increased monster activity in the area, we now wish to strengthen our "
"walls around Sandbrook. We are short on raw materials, however, and I want "
"you to help us out by gathering stone from boulders found in the wilderness "
"surrounding town.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Thora the Merchant's shop, which lies near the "
"center of Sandbrook village, or from any other general store.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_470"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Agrina the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_471"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Andor-Kai the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_472"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you know, the region of Hunter's Moon has been overrun by a large number "
"of scavenging goblins. As we clear out these pests, we should make sure to "
"extract the parts such as the teeth, that find use in enchantment rituals.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Agrina the Merchant. Assuming that you are a novice "
"skinner, you should expect to successfully remove intact teeth every other "
"time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_473"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Andor-kai's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_474"
msgstr ""
"We must spare no effort in our attempt to drive the goblins away from our "
"hunting grounds. One thing we should use to our advantage, is the fact that "
"goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It seems that the ancestors of "
"today's goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, and now the "
"entire race has an ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our goblin-expelling efforts by casting twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you "
"need to wield a magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase "
"one from any arcanist shop, such as Celene the Arcanist. Once you own a "
"staff, you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your "
"character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_475"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arkelia the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_476"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Leenglow, a mining town that depends to a large extent from the "
"mining trade. Recently however, goblin bands have begun created problems to "
"the mining trade, either by attacking the mines to the north, or the "
"caravans along the trade routes the the east.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help us expel these creatures from the old mine. Kill four "
"goblins then return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_477"
msgstr ""
"YYou have accepted a quest from Arkelia the Councillor. Collect two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_478"
msgstr ""
"Goblins have been sighted at the mine to the north of here, using it as a "
"base for raids against farms, while another group has been seen to the east "
"attacking the eastern trade route. We wish to exterminate these goblins and "
"make the lands around of Leenglow safe again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Goblins are deeply stupid creatures, who have trouble engineering anything "
"more advanced than a sharpened stick. For this reason, the traditional "
"goblin axes are highly prized among the greenskins, only a few of whom are "
"able to actually make such tools from scratch.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For this reason, I want you to loot the axe from any goblin that you kill in "
"the vicinity of Leenglow.  Using this tactic, we will eventually limit the "
"number of armed defenders of the old ormham mine. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_479"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Molangar the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_480"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the Leenglow council has decided "
"to strengthen and expand the walls around our city. Since we are short on "
"raw materials, I want you to help us out by gathering suitably shaped "
"building blocks from boulders found in the wilderness surrounding town.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Levasta-ine the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Pointing your crosshair "
"towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is suitable for harvesting. "
"Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may "
"begin the procedure of extracting stone using your pickaxe. If you are a "
"novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure to be successful every "
"other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_481"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Molangar the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_482"
msgstr ""
"The mines of Leenglow consume vast quantities of timber, which is used to "
"support the shafts and make them safe for workers. In recent weeks, goblin "
"attacks have disrupted our logging operations, and now we are running short "
"of timber.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help us with this situation, you need to bring a tool called "
"a Wood Axe to the trees around town. If you don't already own such a tool, "
"you may buy one from Levasta-ine the merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_483"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Amauron the Arcanist.  In order to complete "
"it, you must return to him with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_484"
msgstr ""
"This region produces a wealth of rare herbs that are used for brewing "
"potions. Recently, however, invading goblins have driven off the herb "
"gatherers and claimed the most fertile gathering grounds as their territory."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a consequence, I am currently running low on several key ingredients. If "
"you are heading out into the wilderness, I implore you to keep an eye out "
"for any mandrakes you see withering on the vine. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Levasta-ine the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're holding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_485"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Arkelia the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_486"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The mines to the north of here are crawling with goblins. The only good "
"aspect of this situation, is that goblins contain parts, most especially the "
"teeth, which may be used to make low powered versions of certain "
"enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Levasta-ine the Merchant. Assuming that you are a "
"novice skinner, you should be able to successfully remove intact teeth every "
"other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_487"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Arkelia's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_488"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, most goblins share an irrational fear of magic. We "
"should try to exploit this fear in our efforts to drive the invading goblins "
"out of abandoned mine.\r\n"
" \r\n"
"Every mahirim who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast "
"twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to remind them that all "
"mahirim master at least some rudimentary magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Amuron the Arcanist. Once you own a staff, you may "
"equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_489"
msgstr ""
"To guard against future monster incursions, we are planning to build a chain "
"of guard towers on the outskirts of the hunting grounds to the east of here. "
"Before work can start on these structures, we need help with gathering the "
"timber that is needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If you "
"don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Agrina the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_490"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Taelis the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_492"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Onghral, a village which lies within the hollowed-out remains of "
"an abandoned and partially flooded stone quarry. All around Onghral, the "
"scars and pits left behind by centuries of stonecutting may be seen, and to "
"the east of here, a huge, many-tiered quarry has become infested by goblins."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While the people of Onghral have no use for this abandoned stoneworks, we "
"cannot allow a goblin infestation to thrive and breed that close to our "
"village. I want you to help us clear out the threat by killing four goblins "
"in the swamp-inundated hollow which lies directly to the east of our village."

msgid "start_text_quest_493"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taelis the Councillor. Gather two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_494"
msgstr ""
"Goblins have settled in a giant hollow which borders our village to the "
"east. These greenskin are now breeding extremely swiftly, and we must "
"curtail their growth before they become too numerous to handle.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In combat, the local goblins tend to use stone axes which they make "
"themselves using stone from the quarry. While far too primitive to be used "
"by alfar warriors or craftsmen, these tools are more than good enough for "
"the slaves that toil on our behalf.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed. Then "
"while targeting the remains, use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Return to me with two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_495"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgan the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_496"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Onghral have demanded the walls around our city be expand and "
"improve, and that is what we will do. But first we need to make sure that we "
"have all the raw materials that we need, such as blocks of stone.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help us out by gathering suitably shaped building blocks from "
"boulders found in and around the abandoned stone quarries near the village.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Arinthu the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_497"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgan the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_498"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Onghral have decided to build more guardtowers along the road "
"which connects our village to the alfar capital of Shoal. Before work can "
"start on these structures, however, we need help with gathering timber "
"needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood "
"Axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Arinthu the "
"Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_499"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kalshar the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_50"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used in "
"strengthening the {$u19} defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_500"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\n"
"\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Arinthu the Merchant. \n"
"\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack.\n"
"\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_5000"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dulog Painchopper. Locate and kill 5 Menhir "
"Custodian, 5 Thainlord, 5 Menhir Stoneguard inside the Iyrtan's Shadow "
"Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_5001"
msgstr ""
"The Blades of Tolenque have asked you to scout the dungeon and note down the "
"dangers found within.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to assist the Blades of Tolenque you can begin by killing 5 "
"Menhir Custodian, 5 Thainlord, 5 Menhir Stoneguard. Succeed, and I am sure "
"that more challenges will follow."

msgid "start_text_quest_5002"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Dulog Painchopper's offer, to take part in the Iyrtan's "
"Shadow Dungeon purge. Kill 15 Menhir Custodian, 10 Menhir Stoneguard and 5 "
"Thainlord inside Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_5003"
msgstr ""
"So, you wish to join the purging of Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon. It takes a lot "
"of courage to go against these creatures. The Blades of Tolenque too desire "
"to see these foul monsters dead. They have gone as far as declaring a sort "
"of purge, for those brave enough to face these creatures. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is the Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon purge, and any that manage to Kill 15 "
"Menhir Custodian, 10 Menhir Stoneguard and 5 Thainlord will receive a "
"handsome reward. There are only two rules to the hunt. One, to Kill 15 "
"Menhir Custodian, 10 Menhir Stoneguard and 5 Thainlord. Two, once you have "
"completed the hunt you may partake again in the Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon "
"purge after 21 hours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So brave hunter, are you ready to purge the Iyrtan's Shadow Dungeon?"

msgid "start_text_quest_5004"
msgstr ""
