"general store, including Arinthu the Merchant's shop, which lies near "
"Onghral's northern gate. Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should "
"be able to remove intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_5020"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Glumstein Snowbeard. Locate and kill 5 "
"Svartdvergir Summoner, 5 Svartdvergir Nightaxe, 5 Svartdvergir Initiate, "
"2 Svartdvergir General and 1 Svartdvergir Doombringer inside the svartvann "
"Dungeon."

msgid "start_text_quest_5021"
msgstr ""
"The White Hunters have asked you to scout the dungeon and note down the "
"dangers found within.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you wish to assist the White Hunters you can begin by killing 5 "
"Svartdvergir Summoner, 5 Svartdvergir Nightaxe, 5 Svartdvergir Initiate, "
"2 Svartdvergir General and 1 Svartdvergir Doombringer. Succeed, and I am "
"sure that more challenges will follow."

msgid "start_text_quest_5022"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Glumstein Snowbeard's offer, to take part in the svartvann "
"Dungeon purge. Kill 20 Svartdvergir Summoner, 20 Svartdvergir Nightaxe, "
"20 Svartdvergir Initiate, 7 Svartdvergir General and "
"5 Svartdvergir Doombringer inside svartvann Dungeon.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_5023"
msgstr ""
"So, you wish to join the purging of Svartvann Dungeon. It takes a lot of "
"courage to go against these creatures. The White Hunters too desire to see "
"these foul monsters dead. They have gone as far as declaring a sort of "
"purge, for those brave enough to face these creatures. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is the Svartvann Dungeon purge, and any that manage to Kill 20 "
"Svartdvergir Summoner, 20 Svartdvergir Nightaxe, 20 Svartdvergir Initiate, "
"7 Svartdvergir General and 5 Svartdvergir Doombringer will receive a "
"handsome reward. There are only two rules to the hunt. One, to Kill the "
"Svartdvergirs. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Two, once you have completed the hunt you may partake again in the Svartvann "
"Dungeon purge after 21 hours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So brave hunter, are you ready to purge the Svartvann Dungeon?"

msgid "start_text_quest_5024"
msgstr ""
"There is no time to dally, locate Ironbeard Heavyfist and Hjor the Great, "
"kill them and return home in one piece.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "start_text_quest_5025"
msgstr ""
"I have here for you two letters, please read them. If you accept, be sure to "
"kill each monster twice. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Operation Heavyfist\r\n"
"I’m sure you’ve noticed the lack of cheer in the city as of late, our people "
"have succumbed to feelings of doom. You see, a monstrosity known as "
"Ironbeard Heavyfist has found his home here on Niflheim...he’s already laid "
"many good men to rest, several of our best among them. A twisted mockery of "
"dwarvenkind, whether he be the sadistic offspring of Heimar, or yet another "
"minion of Oncylus, I cannot say. His forces grow stronger by the day, we "
"cannot allow him to breathe another breath. Seek out his lair and eliminate "
"him before all is lost.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"King of the Jarls\r\n"
"I’ve something to ask of you...consider my request carefully because this is "
"extremely dangerous work. The jarls of Niflheim have been a problem for our "
"ancestors and to this day they ravage these lands. We’ve managed to hold our "
"ground up until now, but the jarls have found a new king, Hjor the Great. He "
"is indeed great, a great pain in our collective ass. I’ve lost count of how "
"many ships he’s sunk, men he’s slain, and wills he has broken. I fear it is "
"only a matter of time before he makes his move on the city, and you can be "
"sure he will bring the full force of the jarls with him. We will be "
"crushed...unless we strike first. I can show you where he resides. Are you "
"ready?"

msgid "start_text_quest_5026"
msgstr ""
"Against your better judgement you’ve agreed to hunt down Ironbark the "
"Ancient and Grand TIkoloshe. May your blades be sharp and your mind ready."
"\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "start_text_quest_5027"
msgstr ""
"Here are the reports from our men. You will find mercenary work inside. If "
"you accept, be sure to kill each monster twice. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Vengeance of Chuharacua Bay\r\n"
"Let me tell you a story, friend. I was roused from my dreams by my panicked "
"wife, somehow oblivious to the sounds of the jungle shaking around me. Still "
"groggy from sleep, I felt a terror overcome me like none before. Whatever it "
"was, I knew it was something huge...something dangerous. It was my "
"responsibility to save the city, a duty I’d gladly give my life for. I "
"packed my gear and brought the few soldiers brave enough to join me. We "
"followed the sound of loud steps in the distance, eventually finding the "
"source, a gargantuan forest golem towering above.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It was a quick and bloody skirmish, I am deeply ashamed to say that the "
"soldiers did not survive, I almost joined them in an early demise. The golem "
"swung once and broke my arm, I was lucky it did not come off completely. I "
"managed to escape into the thick of the jungle and return home to report my "
"failure. I swore vengeance but no matter how much I train, I cannot restore "
"the power I once had. I am no match. This monstrosity is known as Ironbark "
"the Ancient and we cannot allow him to live. Will you exact vengeance on my "
"behalf and keep our city safe? You’re the only one I can count on.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Deadliest Wildtribe\r\n"
"Have you heard the rumors about the most sinister of all wildtribe goblins, "
"Grand Tikoloshe? Well, I can confirm the rumors are true. He is a threat "
"like no other. Highly charismatic. It is conceivable that he could unite the "
"wildtribe goblins near and far, and if so, we would be annihilated. We have "
"sent mercenaries which did not return, it is safe to assume they are dead. "
"Now we turn to you, hero. Gather your most trusted companions, seek out "
"Grand Tikoloshe, and slay him before this whole situation spirals out of "
"control."

msgid "start_text_quest_5028"
msgstr ""
"Seek out and eliminate Warlord Choppah and Chieftain Khalos. We cannot allow "
"them to wreak havoc any longer.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "start_text_quest_5029"
msgstr ""
"Our allies seek assistance, please take a look at these letters. If you "
"accept, be sure to kill each monster twice. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Chieftain’s Demise\r\n"
"It has been a long road, my friend. Our assaults on Chieftain Khalos’ forces "
"were a success, hundreds of his giant brothers have been slain. However, our "
"efforts may be in vain as he has somehow managed to recruit minotaurs as his "
"new guards. This is the first time in recorded history that giants and "
"minotaurs have joined forces, and if I’m being honest, I’m nervous about the "
"future. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"With our own forces depleted from months of combat, we haven’t many options "
"left. If you would consider taking your men to finish the job, we’d all be "
"grateful. Chieftain Khalos has only recruited the minotaurs thus far, but we "
"can’t be sure that he won’t manage to unite even more of the monsters. "
"That’s something we simply cannot risk. I don’t mean to rush you but the "
"sooner this quest is completed, the better. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Heroes of Dayar\r\n"
"I have a very important task to ask of you, something I think you’d excel "
"at. The gray ork boss known as Warlord Choppah has been causing us many "
"problems as of late, even more than usual. We hoped he’d launch an assault "
"on either the minotaurs or the giants, and then we’d swoop in for the kill. "
"Clearly, that has not happened. I’ve heard you and your mates have already "
"done a lot of good for us, if it wouldn’t be too much to ask, we’d like you "
"to be the ones to put down Warlord Choppah. I realize it’s a lot to ask and "
"if you decline I’ll certainly understand."

msgid "start_text_quest_503"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Taelis the Councillor. Cast twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_5030"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Kholesh Councillor's offer, to take part in the Agon "
"Champion Hunt. Defeat Fenris Alpha and Vlad Duskward twice.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)."

msgid "start_text_quest_5031"
msgstr ""
"Hero, I bring forth letters requesting assistance. Please consider them "
"carefully, as there is no time to waste and no one else to ask. If you "
"accept, be sure to kill each monster twice. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Fall of Vlad Duskward \r\n"
"I’m looking for an able warrior to deal with a local problem, so far, nobody "
"has been up to the task. A doomed soul trapped in forsaken armor has been "
"marauding the land around these parts, he goes by the name Vlad Duskward, or "
"so I’m told. His acts of evil are so gruesome and barbaric I can’t bring "
"myself to think about them and believe me, I’ve seen my fair share of ugly "
"situations. Something needs to be done. Now. Will you be the savior this "
"city needs and vanquish Vlad Duskward?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Beheading the Beast\r\n"
"It takes guts to live here at the edge of the pall, each one of us has risen "
"to the occasion by keeping the darkness at bay. In recent times the chaos "
"and dread have been worse, some might say palpable. I’m sure you’ve heard of "
"the one they call Fenris Alpha, rumor has it he’s found a new home inside "
"the Watcher Wastes. Best be careful, he is said to possess razor-like claws "
"and an insatiable appetite for the flesh of man. Don’t be fooled though, his "
"prowess in the dark arts is equally formidable. Your mission will not be "
"easy, but if you can put down this horrific beast I’ll be sure to reward "
"you. What do you say?"

msgid "start_text_quest_5032"
msgstr ""
"Find Siharo Darkbinder and Hellfire Juggernaught. Slay them both.\r\n"
"(Warning: This quest will be available again, 21 hours after its completion)"

msgid "start_text_quest_5033"
msgstr ""
"My friend, have a look at these letters. I was asked to deliver them to you "
"personally. If you accept, be sure to kill each monster twice. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Preemptive Strike\r\n"
"Travelers often refer to this city as the jewel of Rubaiyat, it makes me "
"smile every time I hear the words. Unfortunately, the prestige of this place "
"has essentially painted a target on all our backs. The khamset have been "
"kept at bay for centuries, but not without taking a heavy toll on our ranks. "
"I’m afraid we’re in a compromised position and it takes time to train new "
"soldiers, let alone find folks brave enough. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I’ve heard whispers of the erodachs negotiating with Hellfire Juggernaught, "
"some say they plan to capture Ghanalaj. A preemptive strike is in order, "
"wouldn’t you agree? With our diminished forces, we simply lack the might "
"required to challenge him, but I’ve heard you can work miracles with your "
"band of heroes. Is it too outlandish to ask you to launch the assault "
"yourselves? I’d gladly reward each of you and you’d have the eternal "
"gratitude of everyone in the city. Will you help?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Witch’s Plot\r\n"
"These are dangerous times, friend, the shadows grow darker by the day. If "
"it’s not an ambitious enemy force making a move on our great city, it’s a "
"band of monsters growing just a bit too large for comfort. Siharo Darkbinder "
"is perhaps the greatest threat of all, and she’s been seen east of here "
"rallying her forces. Believe me, I’ve tried to coax the military into "
"putting her down but they seem petrified at the prospect. Many fear it would "
"be their last expedition. I suppose you see where I’m going with this, you "
"are our last hope."

msgid "start_text_quest_504"
msgstr ""
"We must use every trick available to us in our attempt to expel the goblins "
"from the abandoned quarries near Onghral. One thing we should use to our "
"advantage, is the fact that goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It "
"seems that the ancestral goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, "
"and now the entire race has a deeply ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Help us in our efforts by casting twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins. "
"In order to cast this or any other spell, you need to wield a magestaff. If "
"you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any arcanist shop, such "
"as Kalshar the Arcanist's, which lies here in Onghral. Once you own a staff, "
"you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your "
"character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_505"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_506"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to {$n22}, a small village which stands near the crumbling ruins "
"left by a race of giants called the Nithron. Today, these ancient structures "
"serve as shelter for a ragtag band of goblins who have taken to staging "
"opportunistic raids along the roads leading from our village to Onghral and "
"{$o23}. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This filthy vermin must be dealt with as quickly and as harshly as possible. "
"I want you to go out and kill four goblins before returning to me for a "
"reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_507"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_508"
msgstr ""
"A number of ruins near this village have become infested by goblins. Through "
"sheer numbers, rather than individual strength or resourcefulness, these "
"greenskins have managed to disrupt several trade routes leading out of this "
"village. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In combat, goblins tend to use primitive axes made of flint. Despite their "
"rudimentary nature, these axes are highly prized by the greenskins, most of "
"whom lack the skills necessary to make tools of any kind. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed. Then "
"while targeting the remains, use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes taken from the greenskins that infest "
"the ruins near {$n22}."

msgid "start_text_quest_509"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardahan the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_51"
msgstr ""
"Sanguine is facing one of the largest goblin hordes ever assembled. If we "
"are to withstand the onslaught, we need to repair and upgrade the city "
"walls. In order to perform this work, we need large quantities of building "
"materials, such as wood.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire wood, you must cut down trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If "
"you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Simeon the Merchant."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your "
"woodaxe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_510"
msgstr ""
"With the latest goblin raids upon our trading routes, it has been decided "
"that we need need to build a  number of guard houses to protect them. I want "
"you to help us in this task by gathering some of the stone we need for "
"building the guard houses. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you first need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a "
"tool already, you may buy one from Kaelit the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, the procedure will be successful "
"approximately every other time."

msgid "start_text_quest_511"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardahan the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_512"
msgstr ""
"We are planning to increase the number of guard towers along the roads which "
"connect our village to the outside world. Before work can start on these "
"structures, we need help with gathering the timber that is needed for their "
"construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If you "
"don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Kaelit the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_513"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ilrak the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_514"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Kaelit the Merchant's shop, "
"which lies along the western wall of {$n22}. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_515"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_516"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"By now you must be aware that a large portion of {$n22}, is overrun by many "
"scavenging goblins. As we clear out these pests, we should make sure to "
"extract the parts such as the teeth, that find use in enchantment rituals.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Kaelit the Merchant's shop, which lies along "
"{$n22}'s western wall. Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should "
"expect to successfully remove intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_517"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nirgash the Councillor. Cast twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_518"
msgstr ""
"We must spare no effort in our attempt to drive the goblins away from our "
"hunting grounds. One thing we should use to our advantage, is the fact that "
"goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It seems that the ancestors of "
"today's goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, and now the "
"entire race has an ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Help us in our goblin expelling efforts by casting twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you need to "
"wield a magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from "
"Ilrak the Arcanist. Once you own a staff, you may equip it by dragging it "
"from your inventory and onto your character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_519"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Irshanta the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_52"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to gather five units of timber which will be used in "
"strengthening the Sandbrook defenses."

msgid "start_text_quest_520"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to {$o23}, a village built halfway inside the Cave of Birth, the "
"sacred place where Melek's will turned lowly mirdain into the noble "
"ancestors of the alfar race. Approximately half of Akathos stands inside the "
"legendary cave, while the remainder lies among the crags of a wild and rocky "
"surface terrain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The valleys and gorges surrounding Akathos have recently become home to a "
"minor infestation of goblins. While this is too trifling a matter to involve "
"the Harn Mandean or the army, clearing out the goblins might be a fitting "
"task for beginning adventurers. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Most of the goblins have been sighted to the south of Akathos. Seek out "
"their pathetic little camps and kill four of their number."

msgid "start_text_quest_521"
msgstr "You have accepted Irshanta's quest. Gather two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_522"
msgstr ""
"Goblin refugees who were driven from their original homes by stronger, more "
"fearsome monsters  have settled among the narrow valleys to the east of "
"here.   \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These goblins use primitive axes that might be used, as tools for the slaves "
"of {$o23} village. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed. Then "
"while targeting the remains, use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to hunt and loot greenskins until you can present me with two "
"goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_523"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Neissur the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_524"
msgstr ""
"The goblins that have settled to the east of here will eventually be "
"captured and turned into slaves. Before that can happen, though, we must "
"expand our slave pens in order to accommodate their number. I want you to "
"help us in this work by gathering some of the stone that we need for this "
"work.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Talduk the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. Pointing your crosshair "
"towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is suitable for harvesting. "
"Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable for harvesting, you may "
"begin the procedure of extracting stone using your pickaxe. If you are a "
"novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure to be successful every "
"other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone"

msgid "start_text_quest_525"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Neissur the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_526"
msgstr ""
"We are planning to build a series of new watchtowers along the roads to "
"{$n23} and Yishku. In order to complete this project, we first need to "
"accumulate large amounts of timber, which is the most important building "
"material in the towers we plan to build.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If you want to help us with this, you need to bring a tool called a Wood Axe "
"to the trees around town. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy "
"one from Talduk the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_527"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Thielit the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_528"
msgstr ""
"This region produces a wealth of rare herbs that are used for brewing "
"potions. Recently, however, invading goblins have driven off the herb "
"gatherers and claimed the most fertile gathering grounds as their territory."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As a consequence, I am currently running low on several key ingredients. If "
"you are heading out into the wilderness, I implore you to keep an eye out "
"for any mandrakes you see withering on the vine. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Talduk the Merchant's shop, which lies in the subterranean "
"part of {$o23}\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_529"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted another quest from Irshanta the Councillor. Gather four "
"teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_530"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you know, the valleys to the south of here are crawling with goblins. The "
"only good aspect of this situation, is that goblins contain parts, most "
"especially the teeth, which may be used to make low powered versions of "
"certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Talduk the Merchant's shop, which lies in the "
"subterranean part of {$o23}. Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you "
"should be able to successfully remove intact teeth every other time you try. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_531"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Irshanta the Councillor. Cast twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_532"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, most goblins share an irrational fear of magic. We "
"should try to exploit this fear in our efforts to drive the goblins pests "
"out of the valleys east of {$o23}. \r\n"
" \r\n"
"Every alfar who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast twenty "
"Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to remind them that all alfar master "
"at least some rudimentary magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Thielit the Arcanist's. Once you own a staff, you may "
"equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_538"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Silawen the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_539"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Leafhelm, a village which is thrice blessed by the waters of the "
"sacred Caelie river. Due to its natural beauty and its many seasonal "
"festivals, Leafhelm is a popular destination for both pilgrims and more "
"pleasure seeking travelers. The Mirdain capital of {$h18} lies to the east "
"of here, while the Serene Spire, an ancient center of magical study, lies to "
"the north. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, the tranquility of Leafhelm has recently been disturbed by "
"the arrival of a wandering band of goblins. These green skinned brigands "
"have proved to be quite resourceful, and so far they have eluded the hunting "
"parties of our city guard. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The village council would like you to seek out and kill the goblins, who "
"were last seen to the northeast of Leafhelm, dangerously close to the {$h18} "
"road. Kill four goblins then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_540"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Silawen the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_541"
msgstr ""
"The wilderness around our beautiful town has become infested with an elusive "
"group of goblin brigands. Needless to say, these filthy degenerates have no "
"respect for sacred trees or natural beauty, and they have already inflicted "
"ugly scars on our precious forest. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to prevent further defilement, we not only seek to kill as many "
"goblins as possible, but also to confiscate their primitive axes, which "
"might otherwise be picked up and used by other goblins. Since goblins are "
"notoriously inept and lazy, it will take them a long time to make and "
"replace any axes that are taken by us.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Return to me with two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_542"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Ciredan the Blacksmith. Gather five units "
"of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_543"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the elflords of Leafhelm have "
"decided to strengthen our town's defenses. We need to repair and upgrade the "
"city walls. In order to perform this work, we need large quantities of "
"building materials, such as stone. I want you to help us out by gathering "
"suitably shaped building blocks from boulders found in the forest around the "
"village. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool already, you may buy one from Merthir "
"the Merchant, or from any other general store. If you are a novice "
"stonecutter, you should expect this procedure to be successful every other "
"time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_544"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Ciredan the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_545"
msgstr ""
"The elflords of Leafhelm have decided to build more guard towers along the "
"road which connects our town to the mirdain capital of Charybdis. Before "
"work can start on these structures, however, we need help with gathering "
"timber needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood "
"Axe. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Merthir the "
"Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of wood."

msgid "start_text_quest_546"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Eredil the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_547"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Merthir the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_548"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Silawen the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_549"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The lands to the north of here are overrun by goblins. As we clean out these "
"pests, we should make sure to extract the parts such as the teeth, that find "
"use in enchantment rituals.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Merthir the Merchant. Assuming that you are a "
"novice skinner, you should be able to remove intact teeth every other time "
"you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_550"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Silawen's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_551"
msgstr ""
"We must use every trick available to us in our attempt to expel the goblins "
"from forests around Leafhelm. One thing we should use to our advantage, is "
"the fact that goblins have an exaggerated fear of magic. It seems that the "
"ancestral goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, and now the "
"entire race has a deeply ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our efforts by casting twenty Mana Missiles against the "
"Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Eredil the Arcanist's. Once you own a staff, you may "
"equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_552"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lysandir the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_553"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Beladin's Rest, a mirdain village built among the roots and "
"branches of Eryasil, the world's largest and oldest tree. This living giant "
"is nourished by the waters of a nearby sacred river, which gives strength "
"and life to everything that grows within the reach of its waters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, goblin have entered the region in a coordinated attempt to "
"attack our town. The goblins must be cleared out before their presence "
"further befouls the waters of the sacred river. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hunt down and kill four of the goblins that have infested the once beautiful "
"lake district."

msgid "start_text_quest_554"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lysandir the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_555"
msgstr ""
"The goblins that have settled near Beladin's Rest, have begun chopping down "
"trees along the shores of the sacred river to use as firewood. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Because of their almost supernatural fecundity, getting rid of a goblin "
"infestations is both difficult and time consuming. While this work is still "
"underway, we should confiscate as many axes as possible from the goblins, "
"whose ability to replace lost tools doesn't match their ability to replace "
"fallen goblins. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me two goblin axes taken from the greenskins that infest "
"the forests around the sacred spring to the southeast of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_556"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Tiyawen the Blacksmith. Gather five units "
"of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_557"
msgstr ""
"As a result of the increased monster presence in this region, we are "
"planning to build a series of guardhouses which will protect the road to the "
"capital. I want you to help us in this work by gathering stone, which is one "
"of the primary resources needed for this project.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather stone, you first need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a "
"tool already, you may buy one from Miradan the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, the procedure will be successful "
"approximately every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_558"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Tiyawen the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_559"
msgstr ""
"To safeguard against future monster incursions, we are planning to build a "
"chain of guard towers on the outskirts of the hunting grounds to the east of "
"here. Before work can start on these structures, we need help with gathering "
"the timber that is needed for their construction.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To acquire timber, you must cut trees using a tool called a Wood Axe. If you "
"don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Miradan the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_56"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Jonn's quest. In order to complete it, you must return to "
"him with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_560"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Gelwain the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_561"
msgstr ""
"In order to cast spells you need to spend ingredients, which are found as "
"byproducts of certain harvesting processes. Right now I personally am short "
"of an ingredient called mandrake, which is found every now and then by "
"people who gather herbs. Since I'm busy at the moment, I'm looking for "
"someone who can help me resupply.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to gather herbs, you need to use a tool called a sickle. If you "
"don't own one already, you may buy a sickle from Miradan the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_562"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Lysandir the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_563"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you've seen, the Sacred River which lies to the east of Beladin's Rest, "
"has been overrun by a large number of scavenging goblins. As we clear out "
"these pests, we should make sure to extract the parts such as the teeth, "
"that find use in enchantment rituals.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Miradan the Merchant's shop here in Beladin's Rest. "
"Assuming that you are a novice skinner, you should expect to successfully "
"remove intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_564"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted another mission from Lysandir the Councillor. Cast twenty "
"Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_565"
msgstr ""
"We must spare no effort in our attempt to drive the goblins away from our "
"forest. One thing we should use to our advantage, is the fact that goblins "
"have an exaggerated fear of magic. It seems that the ancestors of today's "
"goblins were blasted by too one too many fireballs, and now the entire race "
"has an ingrained fear of spellcasters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please help us in our efforts by casting twenty Mana Missiles against the "
"Goblins. In order to cast this or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Gelwain the Arcanist's shop. Once you own a staff, "
"you may equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your "
"character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To complete this mission, cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_566"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the Councillor. Kill four goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_567"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to King's Holdfast, a village built atop the two concentric levels "
"of a circular stone plateau. Throughout its long history, the Mirendil "
"forest has seen countless invasions and insurrections, but the stronghold of "
"King's Holdfast has never once fallen to an enemy, and its citizens have "
"always remained loyal to the elflords of {$h18} and their elected king.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"King's Holdfast is a more or less impregnable fortress, but the territory "
"around it is sometimes infiltrated by small monster groups. Our scouts have "
"spotted goblin camps to the southeast and to the north of here, from where "
"the goblins are staging increasingly frequent raids against local farms and "
"villages.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to help us deal with this nuisance. Kill four greenskins then "
"return to me for a reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_568"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the Councillor. Gather two goblin "
"axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_569"
msgstr ""
"Goblin camps have been discovered to the southeast and to the north of here. "
"Since these greenskins are proving to be something of a nuisance, we have "
"decided to eradicate them with all possible expediency. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Goblins are deeply stupid creatures, who have trouble crafting anything more "
"advanced than a sharpened stick. For this reason, the traditional goblin "
"axes are highly prized among the greenskins, only a few of whom are able to "
"actually craft such tools on their own.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For this reason, I want you to loot the axe from any goblin that you kill in "
"the vicinity of King's Holdfast. Using this tactic, we will eventually "
"reduce the number of armed defenders of the local goblin village until "
"finally we can conquer and raze it without much mirdain bloodshed. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To access a fallen goblin's possessions, you must first be unarmed, and then "
"while targeting the remains use the action button. You may then drag items "
"from his backpack and into yours. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me two goblin axes."

msgid "start_text_quest_57"
msgstr ""
"With the exception of a few simple incantations, such as Mana Missile, all "
"spells are fueled by ingredients which are expended during casting. New "
"spell ingredients are acquired as byproducts of harvesting processes, such "
"as skinning, mining and woodcutting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Here in Sanguine, we are preparing to cast Magic Shield on as many of the "
"city's warriors as possible, as part of our defense against an imminent and "
"large-scale goblin attack. However, we are running short on a spell "
"ingredient called mandrake, which is a byproduct of herb gathering.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Simeon the Merchant's shop, which lies in the southern part "
"of Sanguine\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_570"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dinuil the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_571"
msgstr ""
"In light of the current monster situation, the King's Holdfast council has "
"decided to strengthen and expand the walls around our city. Since we are "
"short on raw materials, I want you to help us out by gathering suitably "
"shaped building blocks from boulders found in the wilderness surrounding "
"town.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to harvest stone, you need a pickaxe. If you don't own such a tool "
"already, you may buy one from Tarhal the Merchant. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Perhaps predictably, stone can be extracted from any sizable boulder. "
"Pointing your crosshair towards it, you will be informed if the bolder is "
"suitable for harvesting. Once you have determined that a boulder is suitable "
"for harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting stone using your "
"pickaxe. If you are a novice stonecutter, you should expect this procedure "
"to be successful every other time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of stone."

msgid "start_text_quest_572"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dinuil the Blacksmith. Gather five units of "
"timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_573"
msgstr ""
"The King's Holdfast council has decided to erect a chain of guard towers "
"which will protect the village's hinterlands against future monster "
"incursions. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to build these towers, we need plenty of timber. If you want to "
"help us out, you need to bring a tool called a Wood Axe to the trees around "
"town. If you don't already own such a tool, you may buy one from Tarhal the "
"Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Only larger trees are suitable for woodcutting. When you're facing such a "
"tree while holding a Wood Axe, you will be informed if the tree is suitable "
"for harvesting. When you have determined that the tree is suitable for "
"harvesting, you may begin the procedure of extracting timber using your Wood "
"Axe.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to bring me five units of timber."

msgid "start_text_quest_574"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aergeir the Arcanist. Gather five mandrake "
"herbs."

msgid "start_text_quest_575"
msgstr ""
"This region produces a wealth of rare herbs that are used for brewing "
"potions. Recently, however, invading goblins have driven off the herb "
"gatherers and claimed the most fertile gathering grounds as their territory. "
"As a consequence, I am currently running low on several key ingredients. If "
"you are heading out into the wilderness, I implore you to keep an eye out "
"for any mandrakes you see withering on the vine. \n"
"\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Tarhal the Merchant.\n"
"\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \n"
"\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_576"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the Councillor. Gather four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_577"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"By now you should have noticed that the surrounding lands have become "
"infested by goblins. The only good aspect of this situation, is that goblins "
"contain parts, most especially the teeth, which may be used to make low "
"powered versions of certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Tarhal the Merchant. Assuming that you are a novice "
"skinner, you should be able to successfully remove intact teeth every other "
"time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Please bring me four goblin teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_578"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Elvallie the Councillor. Cast twenty Mana "
"Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_579"
msgstr ""
"For some unknown reason, most goblins share an irrational fear of magic. We "
"should try to exploit this fear in our efforts to drive the invading goblins "
"out of our lands. \r\n"
" \r\n"
"Every mirdain who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast "
"twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to remind them that all "
"mirdain master at least some rudimentary magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Aergeir the Arcanist. Once you own a staff, you may "
"equip it by dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's "
"paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cast twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_58"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Carrad's quest. In order to complete it, you must return "
"to him with five mandrake ingredients."

msgid "start_text_quest_59"
msgstr ""
"With the exception of a few simple incantations, such as Mana Missile, all "
"spells are fuelled by ingredients which are expended during casting. New "
"spell ingredients are acquired as byproducts of harvesting processes, such "
"as skinning, mining and woodcutting. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We are preparing to cast Magic Shield on as many of the Sandbrook's "
"guardians as possible, as part of our defense against an imminent goblin "
"attack. However, we are running short on a spell ingredient called mandrake, "
"which is a byproduct of herb gathering.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to harvest three mandrakes using a tool called a sickle, which is "
"a prerequisite for herb gathering. If you don't own a sickle already, you "
"may buy one from Thora the Merchant.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you're wielding a sickle, look for a bush of any kind. If your chosen "
"bush contains herbs, an icon will appear near your crosshair target, "
"informing you that the bush is suitable for harvesting. Once you have "
"determined that a bush is suitable for harvesting, you may begin the "
"procedure of extracting herbs using your sickle. If your attempt is "
"successful, a random herb or byproduct will appear in your backpack. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Repeat this process until the bush has produced at least five mandrakes."

msgid "start_text_quest_617"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardem-kai the Loyal. Kill four of the humans "
"bandits that are hiding within the ruins in Nightspire."

msgid "start_text_quest_618"
msgstr ""
"The mountain you see in front of you is Nightspire, home of the Wolfmasks. "
"The Wolfmasks are an order of elite warriors who serve as enforcers for the "
"Elders of Red Moon. Our primary duty is to deal directly with any trouble "
"within the Tribelands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have located a small group of humans who have entered the Tribelands, and "
"have taken refuge among the ruins located northwest of here. We do not know "
"the reason these human are here, nor do we care. The only thing we are "
"certain of, is that these humans have been seen attacking our patrols.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When a mahirim is found for any reason in human territory, that mahirim is "
"hunted down without a second thought. The humans believe that they are "
"superior and more civilized than the mahirim. How mistaken they are. These "
"are the Tribelands, and humans are not safe here. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to enter the ruins and kill four of these human bandits. These "
"humans must die. I will mark their position on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_619"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a mission from Mardem-kai the Loyal. Gather two Timeless "
"Blood from the centaurs in Hornwood forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_62"
msgstr "You have accepted Allan's quest. Return to him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_620"
msgstr ""
"Located to the north of here is the forest of Hornwood. Within the forest "
"dwell several sylvan species, amongst them the Centaur and the Ciel Fey.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A tribe of Centaurs based in Hornwood forest, has attacked and slaughtered "
"one of our patrolling parties. Minor attacks against the Wolfmasks are known "
"to happen, especially when entering their forest, but brutality of this kind "
"has never been heard of. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until we can discover the reasons behind this savage attack, the Centaurs "
"must be dealt with, before they attack another of our scouting parties.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go to Hornwood forest and punish these centaurs. "
"I want you to take the time to cut out their hearts. Such an act will "
"definitely put some fear into them. #PlayerName#, bring me back two Centaur "
"Hearts."

msgid "start_text_quest_621"
msgstr ""
"The Wolfmasks demand that you kill two Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Shamans, who have been posing as Elders of Red Moon. They were last seen "
"northwest of Hornwood forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_622"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have returned with disturbing news. Moonbeast Disciples and "
"Moonbeast Shamans have been seen torturing Ciel Fey northwest of Hornwood "
"forest, while posing as Elders of Red Moon. This would explain the attacks "
"against our patrols, by the occupants of Hornwood Forest. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Cult of the Moonbeast is using any means possible to spread chaos "
"throughout the Tribelands. If they succeed in creating enough chaos, they "
"will diminish the work and the stature of the Elders, and all that they "
"stand for. This we can not allow! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will sent a report to the Elders of Red Moon, and inform them of these "
"disturbing findings. You #PlayerName#, must quickly move against the "
"cultists located northwest of Hornwood forest, and put a stop to their "
"plans. Show them the true meaning of torture. How dare they disrespect the "
"Elders! Such an insult shall not go unpunished! \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Wolfmasks want you to kill two Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_623"
msgstr ""
"Mardem-kai of the Wolfmasks has instructed you to travel to the cultist "
"village in {$k14}, and to kill two Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Berserkers."

msgid "start_text_quest_624"
msgstr ""
"A group called the Cult of the Moonbeast, has been dangerously gaining "
"support amongst traditionalist mahirim throughout and beyond the Tribelands. "
"This group worships an old and sinister deity called the Moonbeast. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The cult sees the civilizing efforts of the Elders of Red Moon, as a "
"dangerous experiment which is slowly turning the mahirm soft and weak.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have located one of the cult's villages to the west of here in "
"{$k14}. It is a good opportunity to gather information about the cult and "
"the village. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go to this cultist village in {$k14} and kill two Moonbeast "
"Disciples and two Moonbeast Berserkers. When you are done, return to me with "
"an assessment of their strengths and weaknesses."

msgid "start_text_quest_625"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Mardem-kai the Loyal. Kill two Forest "
"Prophets, two Ciel Fey Druids and two Ciel Fey Foresters."

msgid "start_text_quest_626"
msgstr ""
"It seems that we were a little too late in discovering the cultists who were "
"torturing the forest dwellers, while posing as Elders of Red Moon. Now the "
"Forest Prophets and the Ciel Fey are demanding revenge for their tortured "
"kin, and have declared war against us. \n"
"\n"
"Reasoning with them is not an option. Their minds have been poisoned by "
"revenge and hatred, and are too blind to see the truth. Truly disappointing. "
"I expected a little more wisdom from them. If they can so easily be "
"manipulated by these cultists, then they are truly weak. Go now, and put "
"them all out of their misery. Kill two Forest Prophets, two Ciel Fey Druids "
"and two Ciel Fey Foresters. \n"
"\n"
"You will find them all hiding within Hornwood forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_627"
msgstr "Mardem-kai has ordered you to report to Isinda-dai in {$k13}."

msgid "start_text_quest_628"
msgstr ""
"Hobgoblins have constantly been a problem in the Tribelands eastern "
"territories, and the Wolfmasks have always been there in defeating them and "
"driving them out. But in our last battle at {$l12}, the unspeakable "
"happened. We were defeated. We suffered many casualties in our attempt to "
"drive them out. We had underestimated them. It was a humiliating defeat, and "
"a deep scar to the Wolfmask's pride. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I personal have chosen you to restore the pride of the "
"Wolfmasks. Go report to Isinda-dai. She will give you detail regarding your "
"mission. Isinda-dai is stationed in {$k13}. I will mark her position on your "
"map."

msgid "start_text_quest_629"
msgstr ""
"You have been chosen by the Wolfmasks to restore their pride. Go to the "
"{$l12}, and kill seven Hobgoblins."

msgid "start_text_quest_63"
msgstr ""
"Enchantment is the art of imbuing items with magical properties, such as "
"supernatural sharpness or a fiery aura. There are dozens of different "
"enchantment recipes, each of which requires four different ingredients taken "
"from the bodies of slain monsters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The region of Monkfield is currently crawling with goblins, amassed in such "
"numbers that they threaten to overrun our town. The only good aspect of this "
"situation, is that goblins contain parts, most especially the teeth, which "
"may be used to make low powered versions of certain enchantments. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To extract the teeth from slain goblins, equip your skinner and use it on "
"their corpses. If don't already own a skinner, you may buy one from any "
"general store, including Simeon the Merchant's here in Sanguine. Assuming "
"that you are a novice skinner, you should be able to successfully remove "
"intact teeth every other time you try. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The nearest goblins are a group of scouts who have camped by the shores of a "
"lake to the southwest. A small village stands in the forest to the "
"southeast, while a large goblin settlement lies somewhere inside the "
"mountains to the northeast.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would like you to harvest four goblin teeth and bring them to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_630"
msgstr ""
"The Hobgoblins managed the impossible in our last battle. They defeated us. "
"It was a slaughter. Many of my comrades had fallen in that battle. From that "
"day, many Wolfmasks do not dare walk into Issar Ruins. Not out of fear, but "
"out of shame.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Hobgoblins have established a hold in Issar Ruins, which is located to "
"the northeast of here. The time has come to amend for our fallen comrades, "
"so that their sacrifice may not go in vain. We cannot afford to be careless "
"this time. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, this mission has been given to you by the Wolfmasks. Show the "
"Wolfmasks what you are truly made of. Go now, slay seven Hobgoblins, and "
"restore the pride of the Wolfmasks."

msgid "start_text_quest_631"
msgstr ""
"Isinda-dai has requested that you help clear out an importance site in "
"{$k14}, from its unwanted visitors. Kill four Windlords."

msgid "start_text_quest_632"
msgstr ""
"Atop of a ridge to the south of here, lies the ruin site of Neithstone Hall. "
"The site is of strategical value to us, and many brave Wolfmasks have fallen "
"defending it. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"However, dew to many years of neglect, the site is now overrun by Windlords, "
"a primitive race of birdmen that will fiercely defend the ridge which they "
"see as their home. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to Neithstone Hall and kill four Windlords. It is vital to get this site "
"under our control as soon as possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_633"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Isinad-dai. You are to hunt down and kill the "
"most terrifying of the Cult of the Moonbeast. Kill the Moonbeast Ravager in "
"{$k14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_634"
msgstr ""
"When the influence of the sacred moon Theia is at its strongest, the Cult of "
"the Moonbeast run and hunt with their god, losing themselves in a savage "
"hunt of death and destruction. The violent nature of this savage hunt comes "
"at a cost to the cultists themselves. Each time a cultist immerses himself "
"in the presence of the Moonbeast, he is influenced by the savage energy "
"which emanates from the ancient deity. Eventually, the cultist loses all "
"sophistication, becoming a creature of pure predatory instinct and rage. The "
"cultist becomes a Ravager. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A Ravager has been seen south of here, near one of the cultists villages. "
"Killing the Ravager will definitely weaken the resolve of the cultists, and "
"instill doubts amongst them about the power of their god.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go and kill the Moonbeast Ravager."

msgid "start_text_quest_635"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to attack the Moonbeast cultist base in {$j14}, and kill "
"four Moonbeast Officers. When you have completed the mission, head straight "
"to the Wolfmask headquarters and report to Mardem-kai."

msgid "start_text_quest_636"
msgstr ""
"The threat of the Moonbeast grows. Reports from all across the Tribelands "
"have arrived about an increase in cultist sightings and activities. We can "
"not allow the worshipers of the Moonbeast to simply obliterate everything "
"the Elders and the mahirim have achieved. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts have located what seems to be a cultists base. We have been "
"ordered to move against the cultist base, and put an end to their plans!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Prepare yourself for a bloody battle. This is what every Wolfmask lives for! "
"They will come to see who's claws cut the deepest. Nobody is to survive this "
"attack. Nobody! Your orders are to kill four Moonbeast Officers.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The cultist base is located to the southwest of here in {$j14}. When you are "
"done slaughtering the Officers and have completed your mission, return to "
"Nightspire and report to Mardem-kai."

msgid "start_text_quest_637"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Celetia the White. Harvest two units of "
"Baleful Venom Sac from the Ghost Spiders."

msgid "start_text_quest_638"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Moonclaw, home to the Circle of Neith. For years our researchers "
"and scholars have been collecting magical items and artifacts from all "
"corners of Agon. Our goal is to study them and unlock the many forgotten "
"secrets of the past. Our race might be young, but our hunger to learn is "
"great that any others.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many have assisted our cause, and have accepted to travel to strange and far "
"lands to search for such items of greater importance. But before the Circle "
"can entrust you with such important missions, there is a minor but important "
"task you might be able to assist us with at the moment. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have been informed that we are running low on a particular ingredient used "
"for enchanting items, Arachnid Darktaint. Fortunately for us, Ghost Spiders "
"that can provide us with Arachnid Darktaint have been spotted roaming "
"southeast of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Should you accept to assist the Circle of Neith, hunt down these Ghost "
"Spiders and harvest two units of Arachnid Darktaint from them."

msgid "start_text_quest_639"
msgstr ""
"Celetia the White has asked you to report to Avarran-yth, a researcher of "
"the Circle of Neith. Avarran-yth can be found in {$h11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_64"
msgstr "You have accepted William's quest. Return to him with four teeth."

msgid "start_text_quest_640"
msgstr ""
"Long now has the blue moon Neith guided the Circle in its quest for "
"knowledge and magic. And once again, we have been blessed by the blue moon "
"Neith. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently we have acquired information on the whereabouts of an ancient "
"scroll, that speaks of a ancient artifact of great knowledge. It is said "
"that this artifact may hold many secrets of Agon's past, knowledge that is "
"lost to all, by the passing of time.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We believe that this scroll might be hidden in one of the ancient Nirthron "
"cities located north of here. Avarran-yth, one of our researchers, has been "
"sent to search for this scroll. I want you to report to him, and assist him "
"anyway possible in our search for this scroll."

msgid "start_text_quest_641"
msgstr ""
"Avarran-yth has asked you to kill four of the Jackal Revenants that are "
"guarding the first plateau of the ancient Nithron city in {$h11}."

msgid "start_text_quest_642"
msgstr ""
"Legends talk about many secrets left behind by the Nithron, a race of golden-"
"skinned giants who once ruled Agon. The Nithron had build many cities across "
"Agon, just like the one located here in {$h11}. We believe that a scroll of "
"great importance is located here, one that will help the Circle acquire "
"knowledge of Agon's past. But, there is a problem.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Revenants, ancient magical constructs, have appeared in the Nithron city. "
"Although their creators  the Nithron have long abandoned Agon, the Revanants "
"still guard the home of their masters. If we are to continue our search for "
"this scroll, we must first dispose of these ancient guardians.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill four Jackal Revenants located on the first plateau of the ancient "
"Nithron city. The plateau can be accessed via an elevator located on the "
"east side of the plateau. This should be enough to get us started."

msgid "start_text_quest_643"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Avarran-yth. Locate one of the Earth "
"Elementals found on the {$g11}, and harvest one Quartz."

msgid "start_text_quest_644"
msgstr ""
"While I continue my task of searching the ancient Nithron City for the "
"scroll and other hidden secrets of the past, there is something I would ask "
"of you. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"West of here on the Moonstone Coast, Earth Elementals can be found. These "
"entities of earth and stone are importance to the Circle of Neith, because "
"of the Quartz that can be harvested from them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Quartz is one of the many materials used in the art of enchanting items and "
"weapons, and the Circle of Neith is always interested in acquiring such "
"superior ingredients. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, go to the Moonstone Coast, find an Earth Elemental and bring "
"back one Quartz."

msgid "start_text_quest_645"
msgstr ""
"Avarran-yth has asked you to kill four of the Oathbound, that are located on "
"the second plateau of the Nithron City. These four Oathbound are guarding "
"the information Avarran-yth seeks."

msgid "start_text_quest_646"
msgstr ""
"Writings on a wall, not a scroll, but writings on a wall! It was there, and "
"nobody had ever seen it! The Circle presumed that this ancient lost text "
"would be in the form of a scroll. Surely the blue moon Neith has chosen this "
"moment to reveal this ancient knowledge to us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"But there is one final piece of the ancient text missing. The writings talk "
"of the Oathbound, horrid undead guardians who the Nithron left behind to "
"guard their cities and sacred places. Four of these Oathbound where assigned "
"to guard the last piece of the text, related to the whereabouts of the "
"artifact the Circle seeks. Destroying them will reveal this information to "
"us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Oathbound are located on the second plateau of the Nithron City. Go and "
"destroy the four Oathbound guardians."

msgid "start_text_quest_647"
msgstr "Deliver the scroll Avarran-yth gave you to Celetia the White."

msgid "start_text_quest_648"
msgstr ""
"I have written the complete text here in its ancient form as the Nithron "
"wrote it, but I am unable to completely understand it. There must be some "
"secret in deciphering this ancient piece of text, and this is not the place "
"to do it. Acquiring the information we need to find this ancient artifact, "
"is proving to be a difficult task.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, deliver this scroll to Celetia the White, so the Circle of "
"Neith may decipher the ancient text, and discover the secret location of the "
"artifact. I will remain here to continue my work."

msgid "start_text_quest_649"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Celetia the White. Kill six of the "
"Svartvergir that are moving towards {$h12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_650"
msgstr ""
"Many legends and ancient books talk about the artifacts and the many magical "
"items, that were created by the powerful Nithron, a race of giants who ruled "
"Agon for centuries before disappearing without a trace. These artifact can "
"prove to be a curse to us all, if they find their way into the wrong hands."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As you might understand, the Circle of Neith is very keen on locating and "
"retrieving such items. But it seems that we are not alone in this quest. Our "
"agents have discovered a group of Svartdvergir, worshipers of the vile god "
"Sahul, moving towards our headquarters here in Moonclaw.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"These Svartdvergir must be swiftly dealt with, so we may send a message to "
"all that nobody can interfere with the Circle of Neith. The Svartdvergir "
"were last seen in the Mathyra region south of here. #PlayerName#, the Circle "
"of Neith wants you to kill six Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_651"
msgstr ""
"Celetia the White has instructed you to harvest two Vile Horns from the "
"Crogs that can be found in {$g13}."

msgid "start_text_quest_652"
msgstr ""
"With the divine guidance of the blue moon Neith, our scholars and "
"researchers are very close to complete deciphering the ancient writing from "
"the Nithron city. But for them to compete their work, and therefor discover "
"the secret location of the artifact we seek, three Vile Spikes are needed.  "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Vile Spikes can be harvested from Crogs, which often roam the grounds "
"southwest of here in {$g13}. Go now, locate the Crogs and harvest two Vile "
"Spikes. We are so close to acquiring the secrets of the past."

msgid "start_text_quest_653"
msgstr ""
"Celetia the White wants you to help the Circle of Neith by killing four Ogre "
"Bullies and two Ogre Bosses that have been sighted to the west in {$g12}."

msgid "start_text_quest_654"
msgstr ""
"Ogres have been sighted along the coast to the west of here in {$g12}. The "
"Ogres normally would never dare come this close to Moonclaw, unless some "
"other higher power is behind these attacks.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until our agents can discover the real threat behind these attacks, the "
"Circle of Neith would ask of you to take care with these annoying Ogres "
"immediately. Go kill four Ogre Bullies and two Ogre Bosses."

msgid "start_text_quest_655"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Celetia the White. Retrieve the Moonstaff of "
"Knowledge, that is magically hidden within a statue on Velle's Peak in "
"{$g12}. Casting a mana drain on the statue should release the artifact."

msgid "start_text_quest_656"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Moonstaff of Knowledge. Return to Moonclaw and deliver to "
"staff to Celetia the White."

msgid "start_text_quest_657"
msgstr ""
"Blue moon Neith had blessed the Circle once again. Our scholars and "
"researchers have completed deciphering the ancient writing from the wall of "
"the ancient Nithron City, and the location and name of the artifact we so "
"desire is now known to us. The artifact is called the Moonstaff of "
"Knowledge, and according to the ancient writings, he who possesses it will "
"acquire a vast amount of knowledge of the ancient world now lost to us. In "
"other words, the Moonstaff of Knowledge is a window into the past.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Moonstaff is located inside a statue on an island known as Velle's Peak. "
"According to the ancient writings, breaking the statue will not reveal the "
"Moonstaff, but magic will. You will have to strike the statue with a Mana "
"Drain spell to recover the staff. The island is located to the west of here. "
"Find the hidden statue and cast a Mana Drain spell on it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Circle of Neith would ask of you to search the island of Velle's Peak in "
"{$g12} for this statue, retrieve the Moonstaff and return it to us. Do this, "
"and you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_658"
msgstr ""
"Kill three Revenants so the Radiant Circle may continue its experiments."

msgid "start_text_quest_659"
msgstr ""
"In Melek's name I greet you to Dun Amsharra, home of the Radiant Circle. "
"Here within these hollow remains of a once fierce and powerful dragon, the "
"Radiant Circle strives to create spells and magical items for the God-King "
"Melek in his quest for world domination.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently we have been researching new spells, that have yet to be tested. "
"Because of the unpredictable nature of each new spell, our mages are in need "
"of an area to safely conduct their experiments. Such an area has been "
"located, ideal for our experiments, except for one problem. Revenants, "
"magical constructs created by the once powerful Nithron, guard this area. "
"Clear out the area to the west, so our mages may conduct their experiments. "
"Killing three of the Revenants should be enough."

msgid "start_text_quest_660"
msgstr ""
"Shulazu Nightshade has instructed you to gather three units of troll blood, "
"blood that will be used to created a powerful disease."

msgid "start_text_quest_661"
msgstr ""
"For the creation of spells and magical items, an array of components is "
"needed. Our researchers are experimenting with a new spell, a disease, that "
"would weaken all of the non-alfar races of Agon, and therefor bringing Melek "
"one step closer to world domination. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The blood of a troll is an ideal candidate for our new spell. These filthy "
"horrid creatures, are the breeding grounds for various diseases. Three units "
"of troll blood should be enough create a powerful disease.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Trolls can be found roaming east of here in {$m24}. Go now, and return when "
"you have acquired three units of Troll blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_662"
msgstr ""
"Report to Naelah Ghostshard, and assist the Radiant Circle's search for "
"Kalruk's book of necromancy."

msgid "start_text_quest_663"
msgstr ""
"Many years ago there lived a powerful mage called Kalruk, who was a master "
"of necromancy. Isolated in his tower, he would research, experiment and "
"discover new spells involving the dark magic of necromancy.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Over the years, his knowledge and understanding of the art of necromancy "
"grew, and with it grew his fame and power. This attracted others who desired "
"to learn from the powerful necromancer, but also gained the attention of the "
"skeletal Dragon God Cyriacus, an enemy of Melek. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Cyriacus promised Kalruk power and knowledge, if he would abandon Melek and "
"lawfully serve him. Kalruk agreed, and turned away from Melek to serve his "
"new god. While serving Cyriacus, it is said that the necromancer Kalruk had "
"completed writing a book containing his life's work into  necromancy. The "
"Radiant Circle wishes to acquire this book and use all this knowledge as "
"Melek desires. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Naelah Ghostshard, one of the Radiant Circle, has traveled to an ancient "
"severii stronghold southeast of here, to find this book. You are to go to "
"her, and assist us in locating this book."

msgid "start_text_quest_664"
msgstr "Search the Severii Citadel in Fahral for Kalruk's book of necromancy."

msgid "start_text_quest_665"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Book of Greater Necromancy, the life's work of the "
"powerful necromancer Kalruk. You must now deliver the book to Naelah "
"Ghostshard."

msgid "start_text_quest_666"
msgstr ""
"I have found the location, which we believe is where the life's work of the "
"traitorous necromancer Kalruk is to be found. It is a severii citadel to the "
"south of here in {$m25}. The difficulty is that the stronghold is well "
"guarded by many undead, servants of the skeleton Dragon God Cyriacus.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will definitely need to fight your way into the guarded city. Once "
"inside, look out for either a bookcase or chest that might hold the book. "
"Use the action button to investigate more closely. Once you have the book in "
"your possession, return straight back to me."

msgid "start_text_quest_667"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Naelah Ghostshard. Kill six Trolls and two "
"Troll Shamans."

msgid "start_text_quest_668"
msgstr ""
"It seems that I have underestimated the will and stubbornness of the trolls. "
"Though I could take care of them, time is pressing me to continue my work "
"here for the Radiant Circle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The trolls just seem set on the idea of annoying me, until I leave the area. "
"How insulting! As if this area belongs to them! This is Nagast, and it "
"belongs only to the Alfar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These trolls need to be taught a lesson. Go now, and kill six Trolls and two "
"Troll Shamans. That should be enough to make them think of ever even looking "
"at an Alfar again!"

msgid "start_text_quest_669"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the Book of Greater Necromancy to Shulazu Nightshade in Dun Amsharra."

msgid "start_text_quest_670"
msgstr ""
"I will ask of you to deliver the Book of Greater Necromancy to Shulazu in "
"Dun Amsharra. I entrust you with this very important task, do not fail.\n"
"\n"
"Many of the Radiant Circle will envy you, or even resent you, for being the "
"one to deliver this book.  Among them myself. You have proven to be one very "
"resourceful and capable individual, and I can only but acknowledge that.\n"
"\n"
"I will remain here to continue my work for the Radiant Circle. Go now, do "
"not waste time."

msgid "start_text_quest_671"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Shulazu Nightshade. Kill five Manscorpions "
"that have entered the region of {$l23}."

msgid "start_text_quest_672"
msgstr ""
"North of Dun Amsharra in {$l23}, there is a large acid lake that is divided "
"into two levels, which are connected via a waterfall. The acid lake is an "
"important site for the Radiant Circle. It is an area of rare materials and a "
"source of strange and powerful magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Occasionally Manscorpions have been seen roaming by the lake. The "
"Manscorpions were never of much interest to us, except when we needed some "
"willing subjects for our experiments. All that until recently. Reports have "
"arrived of a growing number of Manscorpions migrating into the area "
"surrounding the acid lake, and setting up camps. I believe that they wish to "
"stay there, and maybe even call it their home. How pathetic. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Radiant Circle wants you to rid the area of the unwanted Manscorpion "
"infestation. Killing five Manscorpions should suffice."

msgid "start_text_quest_673"
msgstr ""
"Locate the fortress island in Fahral, and harvest two units of Nightmare "
"Bile from a Flesh Golems."

msgid "start_text_quest_674"
msgstr ""
"The Book of Greater Necromancy is proving to be an excellent source of "
"knowledge, into the dark world of necromancy. With this newly acquired "
"knowledge we can only add to the strength of the Alfar, and thus to the God-"
"King Melek. Melek is surely to be pleased, especially now that the work of "
"the traitorous necromancer Kalruk, is no longer in the hands of Cyriacus and "
"his mindless minions.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While reading through Kalruk's writings, our researchers have discovered not "
"only a number of powerful spell, but instructions for creating magical "
"items. One of these particularly has caught our attention. It is called the "
"Staff of Rotting Flesh, and by its description it will definitely be a "
"powerful weapon in the our quest to dominate Agon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Most of the materials required to fabricate the staff are available or "
"easily acquired, except for one. Golem Bile. According to the book, Kalruk "
"had created Flesh Golems a long time ago, to guard many of his secrets on a "
"fortified island. This island is located southeast of Dun Amsharra in the "
"region of Fahral.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is quite a trip to get to the island, but if you do accept this mission "
"and bring us the Golem Bile, you will be well rewarded. Two units of Golem "
"Bile will be enough."

msgid "start_text_quest_675"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Shulazu Nightshade. Search the severii "
"citadel in {$l25} for Kalruk's tomb, and bring Kalruk's skull to the Radiant "
"Circle in Dun Amsharra."

msgid "start_text_quest_676"
msgstr ""
"Deliver the skull of the traitorous necromancer Kalruk to Shulazu Nightshade "
"in Dun Amsharra."

msgid "start_text_quest_677"
msgstr ""
"Word has reached the Horned Circle in Shoal, about our success in acquiring "
"the Book of Greater Necromancy. While this has bought much satisfaction to "
"the Circle, it has also reminded them of how the Skeleton Dragon God "
"Cyriacus managed to robe Melek of one of his most gifted mages. Now they "
"feel it is time for revenge. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Horned Circle are a group of powerful individuals chosen by Melek, and "
"no Alfar alive would dare to oppose them. Their word is the word of Melek, "
"and it seems we of the Radiant have been given a task. We have been chosen "
"by the Horned Circle to deliver a message to Cyriacus. To the south of here "
"in the {$l25}, there is a severii citadel, one of the largest in Nagast. It "
"is known to us that inside this fortified city is located the resting place "
"of one of Cyriacus's most favored servants, Kalruk. We are to infiltrate the "
"city, find the Kalruk's tomb, and remove his skull. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The tomb is located in the southern part of the city. Should you accept to "
"take on this mission, be prepared to do battle. Many of Cyriacus's undead "
"minions are surely to be within the city, guarding the city from any "
"intruder. Return with Kalruk's skull, and you will be well rewarded. Now go!"
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once you have found the tomb, use the action button to be able to interact."

msgid "start_text_quest_678"
msgstr ""
"Nathar Blackord has instructed you to kill four Severii in less than an "
"hour. \n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_679"
msgstr ""
"The mountain you see before you is Darkthrone, Home to the Temple of the God "
"King. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Thousands of years ago, the God King Melek arrived at Dun Mardukar, a large "
"cave at the heart of the subterranean land known today as Nagast. There the "
"God King Melek, patiently over many years, molded and prepared our ancestors "
"into the superior race we are today, the Alfar.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"All the other races of Agon envy, fear and despise the Alfar because of this "
"superiority. And the Alfar, despise all of them for their stupidity and "
"weakness. Pathetic, all of them. They are all truly inferior. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of those pathetic races are the Severii, undead minions of the skeleton "
"Dragon God Cyriacus. Situated nearby, is one of their cities. Normally, we "
"would have demolished their pathetic city, but the only reason we allow them "
"to exist here, is because we use their pathetic city as a training ground "
"for new agents.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can prove your worth to the Temple of the God King, by entering the "
"Severii city and killing four Severii in less than an hour. Well, are you "
"worthy of the Temple of the God King?\r\n"
"\r\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_68"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted Allan's latest challenge. Cast twenty Mana Missiles "
"against the Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_680"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nathar Blackorb. Kill three Centaurs and "
"three Ciel Fey inside Sorgom forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_681"
msgstr ""
"Slaves are an important part of  Alfar society. It is only natural that the "
"other races of Agon serve as slaves to the superior Alfar. The slaves "
"depending on their race, are assigned to different tasks. Stronger races "
"like the humans and dwarfs are either used for woodcutting or mining, where "
"weaker races such that of the Sarkih are kept for more simple domestic tasks."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently a group of human slaves escaped while working in the forest area "
"surrounding Sorgom lake. It is highly unlikely that the inferior humans "
"escaped without any outside help.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"It seems that the forest dwellers, Ciel Fey and Centaurs, do not approve of "
"our woodcutting activities. I want you to go to the forest area located to "
"the east of here, and create enough confusion so that our agents may move in "
"and assess their strength.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill three Centaurs and three Ciel Fey! That should be enough to disturb "
"them!"

msgid "start_text_quest_682"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nathar Blackorb. Report to Kaldahan "
"Deepshadow."

msgid "start_text_quest_683"
msgstr ""
"Many of our agents have been dispatched throughout Agon. Kaldahan "
"Deepshadow, one of our field agents, is currently looking into several "
"problems. He is located at north of here in the Zahnal region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Deliver this letter I have written to Kaldahan, so he may be informed that "
"the Temple sends you to assist him as he sees fit. Now go!"

msgid "start_text_quest_684"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kaldahan Deepshadow. Kill three Hobgoblin "
"Grunts and one Hobgoblin Veteran that are positioned at the hobgoblin "
"guardhouse."

msgid "start_text_quest_685"
msgstr ""
"The hobgoblins have always known their place when dealing with the Alfar. "
"They have never  posed a threat to the Alfar, and that is how we would like "
"to keep it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Southeast of here, there is a hobgoblin village. Our scouts have spotted a "
"number of hobgoblin war parties arriving at the village over the last few "
"days. This can only mean that the hobgoblins are preparing for battle, and "
"we can only suspect that they are aiming for our headquarters. How pathetic!"
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Just outside the south wall of the hobgoblin village is a guardhouse. "
"Approach the guardhouse but do not enter the village. Take out the guards "
"posted there, so our agents may move in and assess the situation. Kill three "
"Hobgoblin Grunts and one Hobgoblin Veteran positioned at the hobgoblin "
"guardhouse. That should be enough for our agents to move in and do their job."

msgid "start_text_quest_686"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kaldahan Deepshadow. Kill three Jackal "
"Revenants, three Hawk Revenants and two Oathbound."

msgid "start_text_quest_687"
msgstr ""
"The Temple of the God King is always searching for new grounds to expand its "
"operations. Our agents have been searching throughout east Nagast to locate "
"possible sites, that may accommodate the Temple's needs.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is an ancient Nithron city located here in the Zahnal region, long now "
"abandoned by the Nithron. This city is ideal to house the Temple's new "
"operations, but there is one small problem. Revenants and Oathbound have "
"been sited within the city. These ancient guardians, have been left behind "
"by the Nithron to protect their cities.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need somebody to enter the city and clear out the Revenants and the "
"Oathbound. I believe you could take on this assignment. Go to the Nitron "
"city, and kill three Jackal Revenants, three Hawk Revenants and two "
"Oathbound. The city is located to the east of here. Once you return, our "
"agents will take care of the rest."

msgid "start_text_quest_688"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Kaldahan Deepshadow. Kill five Hobgoblin "
"Grunts, one Hobgoblin Veteran and one Hobgoblin Officer in Shargal."

msgid "start_text_quest_689"
msgstr ""
"Our agents managed to capture a hobgoblin scout and bring him in for "
"interrogation. Before our guest politely departed, we learned that the "
"hobgoblins are preparing an attack against Temple's headquarters. How "
"foolish.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We will strike the hobgoblin fort in Shargal, which is located to the north "
"of here, and eliminate any plans they might have of even starting an attack "
"against us. Use any means necessary to enter the hobgoblin village, and show "
"them what it means to go against the Alfar!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, are you prepared to prove your worth to the Temple of the God "
"King, or would you have your name just fade out and forever be forgotten? Go "
"now, and return to the Temple of the God King only when victorious. Go to "
"Shargal, and kill five Hobgoblin Grunts, one Hobgoblin Veteran and one "
"Hobgoblin Officer."

msgid "start_text_quest_69"
msgstr ""
"One thing we should use to our advantage against the goblins, is the fact "
"that they have an exaggerated fear of human spellcasters. It seems that the "
"ancestral goblins were blasted by too many human fireballs, and now the "
"entire race has an ingrained fear of Mercians in pointy hats.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We wish to remind the goblins of the ubiquity of spellcasting ability among "
"humans. Every human who travels through greenskin territory is asked to cast "
"twenty Mana Missiles against the Goblins, just to jog their racial memory. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"In order to cast Mana Missile, or any other spell, you need to wield a "
"magestaff. If you don't own one already, you may purchase one from any "
"arcanist shop, such as Niane's. Once you own a staff, you may equip it by "
"dragging it from your inventory and onto your character's paperdoll. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"While wielding your magestaff, from your Spells options select Lesser Magic. "
"Finally choose Mana Missile to ready this specific spell for use. You may "
"now unleash Mana Missile repeatedly. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The nearest Goblin are found in the mountains to the northwest and "
"northeast. Goblins have also been observed in a small camp which lies to the "
"southeast of Monkfield."

msgid "start_text_quest_690"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to return to the Temple of the God King in Sorgom, and "
"deliver Kaldahan's report letter to Nathar Blackorb."

msgid "start_text_quest_691"
msgstr ""
"Return to the Temple's headquarters in Sorgom, and deliver this letter to "
"Nathar Blackorb. It is a  report of all we have archived so far. Your help "
"has been most valuable, and you have definitely made a name for yourself "
"among our agents. #PlayerName#, the Alfar could do with more like yourself. "
"Now swiftly, be off."

msgid "start_text_quest_692"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Nathar Blackorb. Kill one Oaklord inside "
"Sorgom forest."

msgid "start_text_quest_693"
msgstr ""
"Our agents have completed their search in the forest area around Sorgom "
"lake, about the human slave's escape. The forest dwellers, the Ciel Fey and "
"Centaurs, did indeed help the humans escape, but only after a higher power "
"of the forest had instructed them.\n"
"\n"
"It seems that the Oaklords have become some kind of guarding figures of the "
"forest, and all the other weak forest dwellers have united under their "
"leadership.\n"
"\n"
"To avoid any similar problems within the forest area in the future, we must "
"eliminate these Oaklords. #PlayerName#, go to the forest area near the lake, "
"and kill one of the Oaklords. That should send a clear messaged to the rest "
"of them, that we rule here in Sorgom."

msgid "start_text_quest_696"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to be put to the test by the Arrowhead. Destroy four "
"skeletons in less than an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_697"
msgstr ""
"Welcome traveler, I am Eredethil Swiftarrow. You have reached Krisathel, "
"home of the Arrowhead.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"For centuries, the Arrowhead have patrolled these forests and the "
"surrounding lands, keeping them safe from unwanted intruders and local "
"troublemakers. Anybody who considers that they may be of help to the "
"Arrowheads, is most welcomed. But first, they must complete our little "
"trial. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Just beyond our forest to the southeast, there is a circular rock formation "
"where skeletons keep rising time after time. If you would like to prove your "
"worth to the Arrowhead, then go and destroy four skeletons in less than an "
"hour. When you have finished with them, return here, so we may see how good "
"you are."

msgid "start_text_quest_698"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. Kill four of the "
"troublesome Ciel Fey located in {$j20}."

msgid "start_text_quest_699"
msgstr ""
"Mirendil forest has been home to the Mirdain and the Ciel Fey for thousands "
"of years. The two races are closely related, but unfortunately over the "
"thousands of years have grown apart, mostly culturally and philosophically. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Ciel Fey remain trapped in the old ways, where their ancient culture "
"forbids them contact with other races. Our relationship with them is not on "
"best terms, and often there are times when we have gone at each others "
"throats.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Ciel Fey are always up to something, stirring up trouble within the "
"forest. And while the Arrowhead have successfully dealt with similar "
"problems in the past, this time there is something different, something more "
"sinister. Their attacks are more violent and  more persistent than usual. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our scouts are out gathering information on anything that might indicate the "
"true cause behind these latest attacks. But until our scouts return, I will "
"need somebody to deal the Ciel Fey. I would ask of you to kill at least four "
"of them. They are located to south of here in {$j20}. I will mark the "
"location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_70"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted William's mission. Cast twenty Mana Missiles against the "
"Goblins to complete it."

msgid "start_text_quest_700"
msgstr ""
"The Arrowhead have asked you to kill four of the hobgoblins that have "
"fortified themselves in {$i20}, and to return with your assessment of their "
"strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_701"
msgstr ""
"Small hobgoblin scouting parties have always been known to enter the "
"surrounding lands, and our scout have always managed to quickly drive them "
"out. But it has come to our attentions, that a group of hobgoblins seems to "
"be set on establishing a permanent presence in the Heneldon region, which is "
"southwest of out headquarters.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have received reports that these hobgoblins have begun launching raids "
"against local communities. As you clearly understand, this is something that "
"we cannot allow and must do everything we can to stop the hobgoblins from "
"hurting our people. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"What we need at the moment, is for somebody to assess the strength of this "
"hobgoblin camp in Heneldon. #PlayerName#, if you agree, the Arrowhead would "
"ask of you to do travel to {$i20}, kill four hobgoblins, and return back to "
"us with your assessment of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_702"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Arrowhead. Go to the Lake of Stars in "
"{$j20}, and kill four of the Forest Prophets who are responsible for the "
"Ciel Fey attacks."

msgid "start_text_quest_703"
msgstr ""
"Based on the reports arriving daily at the Arrowhead headquarter, the Ciel "
"Fey continue to create problems within southeast Mirendil. Our scouts "
"managed to capture one of the troublesome Ciel Fey and extract some very "
"useful information. We have discovered that a group of  Forest Prophets are "
"behind the recent Ciel Fey attacks within the area. Somehow this group of "
"Forest Prophets have gained control over the local Ciel Fey, using them as "
"their soldiers to attack our people. But why the Forest Prophets have "
"instigated these attacks, we do not know.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"According to the information we extracted from the captured Ciel Fey, this "
"particular group of Forest Prophets are based to the south of here in the "
"Lake of Stars in the Baradron region.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Your task should you agree, will be to go to the Forest Prophets base, and "
"take out four of them. Without them, the Ciel Fey will likely loose the will "
"to fight. The Arrowhead will make it clear to the Forest Prophets that "
"nobody disrupts the peace of our lands. Go now, and kill four of these "
"troublesome Forest Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_704"
msgstr ""
"The Arrowhead have asked that you enter the tunnel that lead beneath the "
"hobgoblin camp in {$i20}, and kill four Hobgoblin Grunts, one Hobgoblin "
"Veteran and one Hobgoblin Officer."

msgid "start_text_quest_705"
msgstr ""
"A unique opportunity has presented itself to the Arrowhead, to deal a "
"significant blow to the hobgoblins in Heneldon. Our scouts have discovered "
"tunnels leading straight beneath the hobgoblin fortified base in Heneldon. "
"We believe that those tunnel lead to their main base and hideout. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I mentioned, this could be a unique chance to deliver a significant blow "
"to the hobgoblins. #PlayerName#, enter the tunnels that lead to their main "
"hide out, and destroy them from within. The Arrowhead ask of you to slay at "
"least four Hobgoblin Grunts, one Hobgoblin Veteran and one Hobgoblin "
"Officer. It is time to show them some Mirdain hospitality. I will mark on "
"your map the tunnel entrance."

msgid "start_text_quest_706"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Eredethil Swiftarrow. To be considered a true "
"Arrowhead, you must kill four Beastmen."

msgid "start_text_quest_707"
msgstr ""
"One of the most ancient enemies of the Mirdain are the Beastmen. To slay a "
"Beastman, has always been a true test of valor for any Mirdain. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Tradition says, for one to become a true Arrowhead, one must venture into a "
"beastman village alone and slay four of them. And the Arrowhead have no "
"reason to not continue such a tradition. Luckily for you, there is a "
"beastman village to the north. Such a grand opportunity should not go "
"wasted. I won't even bother to ask if you will accept the challenge. All I "
"will tell you is that you must kill at least four of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_708"
msgstr "Eredethil Swiftarrow has asked you to report to Seirinna the Mage."

msgid "start_text_quest_709"
msgstr ""
"Seirinna is our local mage, and one of the high ranking Arrowhead. Do not "
"let her title or appearance fool you. Besides being a mage, she is also a "
"gifted archer. Seirinna has been looking into the more, lets say, magical "
"matters for the Arrowhead. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently she has been investigating a mysterious illness that has been "
"slowly spreading throughout these lands. I suggest that you go pay her a "
"visit, and see if you could assist her. I would go myself to help her, but I "
"have other more pressing matters to attend to. Seirinna is usually found "
"somewhere around here."

msgid "start_text_quest_710"
msgstr ""
"Seirinna the Mage has asked you to kill six of the Ciel Fey that new reside "
"within Siledin's abandon castle in {$j18}."

msgid "start_text_quest_711"
msgstr ""
"I have been busy trying to discover the cause of a mysterious illness that "
"has appeared in these parts of Merendil. One of our scouts found the dead "
"body of the powerful mage Siledin just outside his castle, which is to the "
"north of here. After examining the body, I discovered that the cause of the "
"death was a disease. A powerful and deadly disease indeed, if it could "
"defeat Siledin.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Reports have also arrived from local communities which are set close to "
"Siledin's castle, also falling ill to some unknown illness or disease. This "
"is disturbing news, and the Arrowhead cannot allow such a disease to spread "
"across the lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I believe that somewhere inside Siledin's castle, there are answers to be "
"found. Answers regarding the origins of this disease. Two of our scouts are "
"ready to enter the mage's castle to search for clues. I would greatly "
"appreciate it, if you could help us. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now that Siledin is no longer with us, his castle is overrun by Ciel Fey. If "
"you could take care of at least six Ciel Fey, that should give our scouts "
"enough time to search the castle."

msgid "start_text_quest_712"
msgstr ""
"Search Siledin's Castle in {$j18} for the statue that holds the Orb of "
"Disease magical inside it. A Mana Drain spell should reveal the orb."

msgid "start_text_quest_713"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Orb of Disease. Deliver it to Seirinna the Mage in "
"Krisathel."

msgid "start_text_quest_714"
msgstr ""
"It seems that the Alfar could be the ones behind the disease outbreak within "
"east Mirendil. In his diary, Siledin mentions finding an Alfar near his "
"castle. This Alfar was greatly ill and very soon died, but in his possession "
"was a strange magical orb. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It was only too late, when Siledin realized that he had been tricked by the "
"Alfar. The Alfar knew that the powerful mage would not pass such an "
"opportunity to study this strange orb, and therefor bring it into Mirdain "
"territory. By the time he had discovered that the orb was spreading the "
"powerful disease, Siledin was too weak to do anything. He didn't even have "
"enough strength left in him to cast a simple healing spell. Barely alive, he "
"managed to write in his diary instructions on how to destroy the orb and "
"where he has hidden it, in the hopes that somebody would find it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Orb of Disease as he calls it, is magically hidden within a statue in "
"his castle. The statue is described as a Female Mirdain Warrior.  A simple "
"Mana Drain spell should reveal the orb."

msgid "start_text_quest_715"
msgstr ""
"Seirinna has asked you to deliver her report letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow."

msgid "start_text_quest_716"
msgstr ""
"If you would be kind enough to deliver this letter to Eredethil Swiftarrow, "
"I would mostly appreciate it. It is a report about all we had discovered "
"about the disease."

msgid "start_text_quest_717"
msgstr ""
"Aelathil Silverleaf  has asked you to gather three units of Timeless Blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_718"
msgstr ""
"I am  Aelathil Silverleaf, and I welcome you to Iriendir, home of the Serene "
"Spire. For thousands of years, even before the Mirdain clans were united "
"into a single nation, the Spire has been studying magic, in all its forms. "
"Be it either spells, magical items or ancient artifacts of a forgotten past, "
"the Spire has always been there first. While some members of the Serene "
"Spire study, discover and create new powerful spells, others labor to create "
"enchanted magical items of unsurpassed quality. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"To create enchanted item, be it either weapon or armors, many material are "
"needed, and some of those materials can only be found in the bodies of "
"monsters. Fortunately for the enchanters of the Spire, trolls have entered "
"the lands surrounding Serene Spire. Troll blood is one the the enchanting "
"materials used to create some of the magical items crafted here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Serene Spire would ask of you, if you could gather three units of troll "
"blood. Of course, you will be rewarded for this service."

msgid "start_text_quest_719"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aelathil Silverleaf. Kill four centaurs in "
"Dirithel."

msgid "start_text_quest_720"
msgstr ""
"A group of centaurs has been running wildly through the lands north of here, "
"terrorizing local communities. Similar reports have arrived from other parts "
"of Mirendil and we believe that this is the same group of centaurs, that is "
"raging throughout the lands.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Agents have been dispatched to located and capture some of these wild "
"centaurs, so we may discover the cause of this irrational behavior. But to "
"achieve this, we will need your help. You will travel to {$g16} where the "
"centaurs currently are, attack the centaurs directly, in our efforts to "
"drive them into our ambush. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to kill four centaurs in Dirithel. This should be "
"enough to stop their attacks and turn them around."

msgid "start_text_quest_721"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted to kill four Sadayel found near Aer Tithil Lake. When you "
"have completed the mission, report to Aelathil Silverleaf."

msgid "start_text_quest_722"
msgstr ""
"Strange magical occurrences have been reported throughout Mirendil. "
"Spellcasters and researchers, have been reporting about  fluctuations in "
"magic, be it spells or magical items. When magic becomes unsteady and "
"unpredictable, it becomes dangerous. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The center of these magical incidents seems to be Aer Tithil Lake, which is "
"located southwest of here. Along the eastern shores of the lake, stand huge "
"crystal formations. The origins of these crystals are unknown to us. What we "
"do know is that these crystal formations have always emitted  small amounts "
"of magical energy. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"A small group of researchers is ready to leave for Aer Tithil Lake and study "
"the crystals. There is only one small problem. The Sadayel.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Sadayel are a  primitive race of lizard folk. Though primitive, they are "
"known to be exceptionally good spellcasters. Over the years, the Sadayel "
"have been drawn towards the magic of the crystals, and eventually have "
"established villages along the shores of the lake. They have come to see the "
"crystals as a gift from their god, and therefore will attack anybody who "
"goes near them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Serene Spire would ask of your help. Go to the Sadayel villages in "
"{$f18}, and kill four Sadayel. That should be enough to draw their attention "
"away from the crystals, and allow our researchers to do their work."

msgid "start_text_quest_723"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aelathil Silverleaf. Kill four Forest "
"Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_724"
msgstr ""
"We have made a disturbing discovery concerning the enraged centaurs. It "
"seems that they have been magically infected with madness. The evil nature "
"of this madness is responsible for twisting the minds of the centaurs, while "
"inflicting vast amounts of pain to their bodies. It is obvious that the "
"centaurs are not responsible for their actions. They are just pawns, serving "
"some darker sinister plan. We must quickly discover who or what is behind "
"this. Such powerful and dark magic is a threat to all of Mirendil.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"For now, we can only suspect the Forest Prophets. Although friendly to the "
"centaurs, the Forest Prophets have been known to conducting dark experiments "
"on other creature in the past. It is time to pay a visit to the Forest "
"Prophets, and discover what part they have played in these latest "
"developments. The Forest Prophets are located northwest of here in the "
"Mynthran region. The Serene Spire would ask of you to slay four Forest "
"Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_725"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aelathil Silverleaf. Search for the location "
"the sacred tree within the green dragon's lair, in the {$f16} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_726"
msgstr ""
"The Forest Prophets have always been our enemies. That is a fact. This alone "
"made us suspect them of being behind the centaurs madness. We were wrong. It "
"seems that the Forest Prophet have also encountered similar problems with "
"other sylvan creatures of the forest. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"They have managed to detect the source of this madness. Not far from their "
"village which is located northwest of here in the {$f16} region, is an "
"ancient underground cavern that once was the lair of a green dragon. Within "
"this cave, there is a very special tree. They call it, the Sacred tree. This "
"tree is spiritually connected with the sylvan creatures of the surrounding "
"lands. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The tree has fallen ill, infected by some unknown source. As a result, many "
"of the sylvan creature throughout northwest Mirendil are slowly being driven "
"mad, not able to withstand the tree's pain.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We want you to go to this cave and see if what the Forest Prophets are "
"telling us true. Once you have located this Sacred Tree, return to us, so we "
"may send our healers to revive and heal the sacred tree."

msgid "start_text_quest_727"
msgstr ""
"Kill four Undead Dwarves located in the old keep in Lulliathel, and find the "
"Ring of Crystals if possible."

msgid "start_text_quest_728"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Ring of Crystals. Bring it to Aelathil Silverleaf in "
"Iriendir, and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_729"
msgstr ""
"One of our researchers had come up with an idea, on how to locate the source "
"of the recent magical fluctuations. He had constructed a ring, the Ring of "
"Crystals, made from the huge crystal formations near {$f18} lake. The idea "
"was that by wearing the ring, the bearer would locate the source of the "
"magical fluctuations. It was a good plan, but not without it's flaws.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The ring did lead our researcher to a magical source, but not the right one. "
"Instead, he ended up in Lulliathel, a region southwest of here. Once there, "
"the ring brought our curious researcher to an old keep, that was occupied by "
"a group of undead dwarves. The researcher managed to escape the furious "
"undead dwarves, but not before loosing three of his fingers and the Ring of "
"Crystals. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I would ask of you to go to this keep, kill the four of the undead dwarves "
"and find the ring if possible. We would like to enhance the power of the "
"ring and have our agents use it more carefully."

msgid "start_text_quest_730"
msgstr ""
"Gather three units of Elemental Cinder and return to Aelathil Silverleaf."

msgid "start_text_quest_731"
msgstr ""
"To the west of here in the region of Phyrathel, stands the only volcano "
"found in Mirendil. Firedreamer. After many centuries of sleeping, "
"Firedreamer has now awoken, spewing lava and ash, and burning the beautiful "
"forests that once stood there.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But lava isn't the only thing that the volcano brought. Fire Elementals have "
"found there way out through the volcano, and now occupy the lava lake "
"created by the volcano. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"As unfortunate as it may be that the volcano has destroyed a large part of "
"the forest, the appearance of the Fire Elementals is quite interesting. Fire "
"Elementals can be harvested for Elemental Cinder, a wonderful ingredient for "
"creating magic items.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Travel to the lava lake in Phyrathel, and bring me back three units of "
"Elemental Cinder. You will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_732"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aelathil Silverleaf. Kill six Giant Skeletons "
"in Pyrathel."

msgid "start_text_quest_733"
msgstr ""
"Before the awakening of Firedreamer, a clan of powerful ogres lived in the "
"cave at the base of the dormant volcano. The sudden reawakening of the "
"volcano had caught everybody unprepared, especially the ogres. As the "
"volcano violently came to life, the ogres cave quickly filled with lava and "
"rocks, turning it into a massive tomb.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The recent magical fluctuations in the area, seem to have brought the ogres "
"back. Not to life, but as Giant Undead Skeletons. Now these Giant Skeletons "
"mindlessly attack anybody with the vicinity of their cave.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Giant Skeletons must be put back to sleep. Go to the ogres in {$f17}, "
"cave locates beneath the volcano and destroy six Giant Skeletons."

msgid "start_text_quest_734"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aelathil Silverleaf. Kill five beastmen in "
"{$h16}."

msgid "start_text_quest_735"
msgstr ""
"Our scouts have at last located the source of the magical fluctuations with "
"the help of the Crystal Ring. The source is an ancient artifact, a shard, "
"which somehow has found its way into Beastman hands. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The shard is hidden somewhere within the beastman village, located northeast "
"from here in {$h16}. It is imperative that we find this shard and bring it "
"to the Serene Spire. Here we will analyze it, study it and then confine its "
"power. And if that is not possible, we will destroy it. The shard is too "
"dangerous to be left in the hands of the Beastmen.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Serene Spire will ask of your help once more. Kill five beastmen in "
"{$h16}. Weaken their numbers enough, that our agents may move in and "
"retrieve the shard."

msgid "start_text_quest_736"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to kill four of the Hill Giant Sluggers in {$f13}, so the "
"Elders of Red Moon may begin excavating the region for ore."

msgid "start_text_quest_737"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Symyr-dan the Firm. Kill four of the Human "
"Guildmasters who are leading the human bandit attacks against the mahirim "
"patrols."

msgid "start_text_quest_738"
msgstr ""
"You have discovered a letter in the possession of the Human Guildmasters, "
"one containing vital information regarding mahirm patrol routes and other "
"defensive locations. Report this find to Symyr-dan the Firm."

msgid "start_text_quest_739"
msgstr ""
"Welcome friend. You have found your way to Amurranyr, home of the Elders of "
"Red Moon. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Four hundred years ago, the prophet-warrior Amurran united many of the "
"heartland tribes under his rule. It was the prophet-king Amurran who founded "
"the city of Red Moon and laid the foundations  for today's modern Mahirim "
"society. We, the Elders of Red Moon, live by the teachings of the prophet-"
"king Amurran, and continue his work until today. But unfortunately, there "
"are those among us who see the civilizing effort of the Elders as a threat. "
"Mostly traditionalist Mahirim, who cannot understand that a new age has "
"arrived upon Agon, and that it is time for the Mahirim to change, adapt and "
"move forward. One of these groups is the Cult of the Moon-Beast, who has "
"been gaining support amongst these traditionalist Mahirim. The cultists "
"believe that the civilizing efforts of the Elders will turn the Mahirim into "
"a soft and weak race. But the truth is, that the backward future-fearing "
"mentality of these cultist, and their denial to embrace progress will be "
"their downfall. But enough with my talk.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"A report has arrived from the Wolfmasks, that humans bandits have "
"infiltrated the Tribelands and have begun attacking some of our patrols. The "
"Wolfmasks has asked us to hunt down these human bandits, and stop them from "
"doing anymore damage.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We have located two human sites to the east of here, in {$i14}. If you "
"desire to assist us in hunting down these humans and putting and end to "
"their any destructive plans, go to the human settlement which is located "
"furthest to the east, and kill four Human Guildmasters. Once we kill the "
"Guildmasters, the rest of these humans will probably flee the Tribelands in "
"fear. I shall mark their location on your map."

msgid "start_text_quest_740"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to take part in the Elder's troll hunt in Amurranyr. Kill "
"three Troll Lords in less than half an hour.\n"
"(Warning: Countdown continues even after logging out)."

msgid "start_text_quest_741"
msgstr ""
"We, the Elders of Red Moon, seek to transform the Tribelands into a "
"civilized and powerful nation. But we also have the responsibility to all "
"Mahirim, and that of our allies, to maintain the reputation as the most "
"fearsome hunters upon Agon.  And what better way than a hunt.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"In the gorge right below us, there is a trolls lair. Many brave hunters "
"venture down into the gorge for what has now become known as the Troll Hunt. "
"The Troll Lords provided quite a challenge, and a good opportunity to "
"sharpen our hunting skills.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"You can partake in the Troll Hunt if you wish. All you must do, is kill "
"three Troll Lords in less than half an hour. Succeed, and you will be "
"rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_742"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Symyr-dan the Firm. Kill five of the "
"Svartvergir in {$h13} that are attacking the trade routes."

msgid "start_text_quest_743"
msgstr ""
"While the Wolfmasks are working to uncover any Cultists within the "
"tribelands, we seem to be having problems with the Svartdvergir. Reports "
"have arrived of Svartdvergir raiding one of our trade routes to the north of "
"here. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The trade routes play a vital part in the modernization of the Tribelands. "
"With these routes, we can bring new technologies and civilization to all "
"within the Tribelands, while simultaneously spreading the teachings of "
"Amurran. These routes must be kept open at any cost, if we are to succeed to "
"unit all Mahirim into one powerful nation.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Svartdvergir must be stopped. The Elders of Red Moon want you to kill "
"five Svartdvergir."

msgid "start_text_quest_744"
msgstr ""
"Symyr-dan has asked you removed the Night Hags from the old burial site. "
"Kill four Night Hags."

msgid "start_text_quest_745"
msgstr ""
"The grounds to the east of here were once used as burial grounds, and many "
"of the Elders that no longer are among us are buried there. Over the years "
"we seem to have forgotten and neglected the old burial site, and as a result "
"of this neglect Night Hags have appeared on the burial grounds. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"These vile disgusting creatures now haunt the grounds, and attack anybody "
"how approaches the old burial grounds. We must clear the grounds of these "
"Night Hags immediately, and show our respect to those that are no longer "
"among us. The Elders of Red Moon want you to kill four Night Hags."

msgid "start_text_quest_746"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Symyr-dan the Firm. Go to the Lone Tower in "
"{$l14}, and search lost half of the sacred tablet known as the Words of "
"Amurran."

msgid "start_text_quest_747"
msgstr ""
"You have found the lost half of the sacred stone tablet. Return it to Symyr-"
"dan and claim your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_748"
msgstr ""
"A report has arrived from the Wolfmasks. They have managed to extract "
"valuable information from one of the priests of the Cult of the Moon-Beast."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The humans had been recruited by the Cult to safe keep an item. An item that "
"is of greatest value to us. An item which can install a sense of unity "
"amongst the Mahirim. The item I am referring to is the missing half of the "
"legendary stone tablet called the Words of Amurran. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is said that when the prophet-king Amurran founded the city of Red Moon "
"and laid the path for todays modern Mahirim society, he had ordered the "
"construction of a stone tablet. This stone tablet would carry a few simple "
"words, that Amurran had spoken. These simple words embody the essence of "
"Amurran's vision, of a united and powerful Mahirim nation. The sacred tablet "
"came to be  known as the Words of Amurran.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"When and how the sacred tablet was divided into two parts nobody knows. The "
"Wolfmasks have discovered that the Lone Tower is where the humans have "
"hidden the broken tablet piece. We must quickly find this other half of the "
"tablet. To have the sacred tablet whole, to be able to read  the Words of "
"Amurran as once spoken my the prophet-king himself, has only been a lost "
"dream until now. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to the Lone Tower and search for the other half of the stone tablet. I "
"suggest that you search for a chest or a crate. Use the action button to "
"investigate more closely. The Lone Tower is located to the east of here in "
"{$l14}, near the human settlements. Return with it, and you will be well "
"rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_749"
msgstr ""
"New sites rich in ore have been located west of here in {$f13}, and the "
"Elders of Red Moon are interested to begin mining this ore as soon as "
"possible.\n"
"\n"
"But there is one problem. The region is overrun by Hill Giants. If the Elder "
"are to begin mining these sites for ore, we need to drive the Hill Giants "
"out. #PlayerName#, the Elder of Red Moon want you to kill four of these Hill "
"Giant Sluggers."

msgid "start_text_quest_750"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Red Moon have requested that you clear the ancestral hunting "
"grounds from the undead. Kill two Skeletons, two Zombies and one Gravelord "
"that now haunt {$g14}."

msgid "start_text_quest_751"
msgstr ""
"The region of Greenveil to the west of here, was once home to many mahirim "
"tribes. It was one of our ancestors biggest hunting grounds. And although we "
"have much advanced since those times, these hunting grounds will always "
"remain sacred to all mahirim. They are part of our history, they are where "
"we came from, and above all, remind us how far we have come as a race.  And "
"all of this because of the visions and beliefs of one gifted mahirim, the "
"prophet-king Amurran.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Unfortunately, many undead haunt these hunting grounds today. Skeleton and "
"zombies who mindlessly walk the lands of our ancestors. No! This is an "
"insult to our race, and an insult to the memory of our ancestors. If we are "
"to progress and become a civilized nation, we must also learn to protect and "
"preserve our past, our heritage.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We must send these undead back to the pits that spawned them. #PlayerName#, "
"the Elders would ask of you to destroy two skeletons, two zombies and one "
"Gravelord."

msgid "start_text_quest_752"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Symyr-dan. Harvest two quartz from the Crogs "
"in {$g13}."

msgid "start_text_quest_753"
msgstr ""
"While some of us are occupied with the creation and discovery of new "
"technologies, there are those who are lured to the mysterious world of "
"magic. Agon is a world full of magic, and if one is to truly be part of "
"Agon, one must also understand magic. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is a group of mahirim spellcasters who take special interest in "
"magical item and ancient artifacts. They are the Circle of Neith. The Elders "
"of Red Moon wish to support the work of the Circle of Neith. This can be "
"done by providing them with the ingredients and tools they need, to continue "
"their experiments and research into the world of magic.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to gather two quartz gems. Quartz can be harvested from Crogs, "
"which can be found roaming the Moon Plains, northwest of here."

msgid "start_text_quest_754"
msgstr ""
"Aeshanta Darkspire has instructed you to kill two Night Hags. You have been "
"info informed that the Night Hags will only appear during the night."

msgid "start_text_quest_755"
msgstr ""
"You are now in the domain of the Harn Mandean, Shoal's front line of defense "
"against all enemies. We are the eyes and ears of all Alfar throughout these "
"lands. It is the Harn Mandean that will detect any threat against the Alfar. "
"Nothing will stand in the way of the Alfar and the God-King Melek.  \r\n"
"\r\n"
"So, you are here now to assist the Harn Mandean, are you not? Yes, of course "
"you are, and that is what you will do. Start off by removing those sneaky "
"Night Hags that have appeared in the vicinity of our headquarters. As their "
"name suggests, these Hags will appear only during the night hours, so  there "
"is no use in going out there and waiting all day for them to appear.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Night Hags were last seen wandering south of here. Your task will be to "
"kill two of them."

msgid "start_text_quest_756"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Kill four Ogres located "
"in Gul Kral."

msgid "start_text_quest_757"
msgstr ""
"Our patrols have been dealing with an increasing amount of attacks within "
"Nagast lately. Somehow, our beloved enemies seem to have grown a spine. I "
"believe they call it courage. How wonderful for them. A pity it won't last. "
"Human, Mirdain, Orc or whatever other pathetic race they may be, will all "
"submit to the superiority of the Alfar. The Harn Mandean will have it no "
"other way.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the west of here, in the region of Gul Kral, Ogres have been interrupting "
"our patrols. Go and dispose of these Ogres. Four should suffice. We cannot "
"afford to have our patrols waste time playing with these overgrown morons. "
"Go now, and report to me only when you have dealt with them."

msgid "start_text_quest_758"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspite. Report to Lushar "
"Wraithglider."

msgid "start_text_quest_759"
msgstr ""
"The Harn Mandean has officers placed throughout Nagast. Each of these "
"officers has been assigned to a specific task, be it in charge of a patrol "
"route, spying on an enemy city or interrogating enemies for information.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Lashur Wraithglider, one of our officer's, has been monitoring two enemy "
"cities. Both of these cities belong to the Severii, undead servants of the "
"skeleton Dragon God Cyriacus. In his last report, Lashur mentioned about a "
"suspicious increase in movement amongst the Severii cities in the Ishtra "
"territories. You are to go and report to him. Lushar is located east of here "
"in the {$n21} region."

msgid "start_text_quest_760"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted quest from Lashur Wraithglider. Destroy six Severii in Ahu "
"Ishtra."

msgid "start_text_quest_761"
msgstr ""
"The Ishtra regions are home to two of the larges Severii cities. It is here "
"that the undead Severii worship and serve their god Cyriacus. For centuries, "
"Cyriacus and his mindless minions have been a thorn in our side. And every "
"time they have attempted to move against Shoal, the Harn Mandean have been "
"there to stop them.    \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Once more it would seem, that the Severii are up to something. There has "
"been a lot of movement between the two Severii strongholds in this region. "
"History has shown us, that the Severii do not move between their cities "
"unless they are preparing for war. Against who, we do not know yet. That is "
"why we must immediately investigate.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I have sent an agent to gather information from their island city located "
"here in the Lake Ishtra. You on the other hand, will go to their fortress "
"city in the Ahu Ishtra region. That is to the east of here. You will enter "
"the city, destroy six Severii, and return to me with an assessment of the "
"strength. We must be prepared."

msgid "start_text_quest_762"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Lashur Wraithglider. Search the Severii "
"stronghold in {$o21}, for the lost Holy Symbol of Melek."

msgid "start_text_quest_763"
msgstr ""
"You have found the holy Symbol of Melek, together with a detailed map of the "
"Alfar capital Shoal. Return to Lashur Wraithglider an report this disturbing "
"finding."

msgid "start_text_quest_764"
msgstr ""
"We have received orders to assist the Temple of the God King. One of the "
"Temple's priest had fallen in their last raid into the Severii stronghold "
"located in the Ahu Ishtra region. Though the Temple did manage to retrieve "
"the body of their fallen priest, they did not find his amulet. The amulet is "
"of great importance. It is a holy symbol of Melek worn by all priests of "
"Melek, and should not remain in the possession of the Severii.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I am running low on men at the moment. We have been spread out due to the "
"Severii attacks throughout these parts. You will have to take on this "
"mission alone. It is imperative that you fine this amulet.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Severii stronghold is located in the mountains to the east of here. You "
"are to enter the stronghold and search for the amulet. Once inside, I "
"suggest that you search for a chest or a crate. Use the action button to "
"investigate more closely. Return to me with the Holy Symbol of Melek, and "
"you will be well rewarded."

msgid "start_text_quest_765"
msgstr ""
"You accepted a quest from Lashur Wraithglider. Kill six Severii that guard "
"the isle dedicated to the Severii Dragon God Cyriacus"

msgid "start_text_quest_766"
msgstr ""
"So, it would seem we have a traitor that is giving valuable information to "
"the Severii. We must inform headquarters of this disturbing finding. But "
"first, there is something we can do. We will disrupt the Severii's plans, "
"and lure their attention elsewhere.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"On one of the islands in the Lake Ishtra, there is a site dedicated to the "
"Severii god Cyriacus. The site is guarded. Take out enough Severii guards to "
"create the illusion that they are under attack. Six should be enough. Then "
"return to me. The Severii will not outsmart the Harn Mandean!"

msgid "start_text_quest_767"
msgstr ""
"You accepted a quest from Lashur Wraithglider. Report to Aeshanta Darkspire."

msgid "start_text_quest_768"
msgstr ""
"The Severii have fallen for our little ploy. While they franticly patrol the "
"area around the lake, you are to go to headquarters and deliver this letter "
"to Aeshanta. I have written a report of all that we have uncovered. "
"#PlayerName#, you have served me well. Go now. We must move quickly, before "
"the Severii discover that they have been fooled."

msgid "start_text_quest_769"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Go to the Gul'Kral region "
"and kill two Hill Giant Sluggers and four Ogre Bosses."

msgid "start_text_quest_770"
msgstr ""
"While we wait for orders from Shoal, there is more that has to be done. The "
"Ogres have returned once more in the Gul Kral region. This time it seems "
"that they have brought some help along with them, some Hill Giants. How "
"wonderful. As if we didn't have enough on our hands with the Severii. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"It is time to put an end to these annoying overgrown morons and their stupid "
"giant friends. You are to go and explain to them, that we do not find their "
"little games charming any more. Kill two Hill Giant Sluggers and four Ogre "
"Bosses."

msgid "start_text_quest_771"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. Harvest three units to "
"Timeless Blood."

msgid "start_text_quest_772"
msgstr ""
"A unusual order has arrived from {$n23}. It would seem that the Radiant "
"Circle is in need of Troll Blood. They are developing some new powerful "
"disease, and we are to assist them.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Radiant Circle is a group of robe wearing Mages who specialize in "
"creating magical items and spells. While I am one who favors pure physical "
"combat to spellcasting and book reading, the idea of creating a powerful "
"disease, one that will be used against our beloved neighbors, does seem "
"rather interesting.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Trolls have been sighted to the northeast of here. How fortunate. Three "
"units of Troll Blood should be enough. Let us be done with this minor task "
"quickly."

msgid "start_text_quest_773"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Aeshanta Darkspire. You will attack the "
"Severii Stronghold located in Lake Ishtra, and kill seven Severii and one "
"Gravelord."

msgid "start_text_quest_774"
msgstr ""
"Word has arrived from Shoal that a  full scale military operation against "
"the Severii is underway. Alfar superiority at it's finest. The Harn Mandean "
"has been asked to do its part in this military operation. We are to weaken "
"the Severii by destroying as many as we can. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until now, you have proven yourself worthy, and successfully executed every "
"assignment the Harn Mandean has entrusted you with. Therefor, I see no "
"reason why you should not be partake in this very important mission.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"We are going to attack the island city located within the Lake Ishtra. It is "
"well guarded, and the Severii have some of their finest units within the "
"city. The Gravelords. But we are the Harn Mandean, and this is what we do "
"best! Go now, and send those undead back to their graves! Kill seven Severii "
"and one Gravelord."

msgid "start_text_quest_781"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Caradial Elmheart. Kill four gnolls that have "
"been cuasing problems along the river Sirith."

msgid "start_text_quest_782"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. Kill five Akathars in "
"{$f19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_783"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. Kill four Revenants in "
"{$g20}."

msgid "start_text_quest_784"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Caradial Elmheart. Kill five Forest Prophets "
"in {$f19}."

msgid "start_text_quest_785"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. You are to search near "
"the abandoned tower in {$e19}, for a statue that contains a very important "
"mirdain artifact."

msgid "start_text_quest_786"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Orb of Mirdain History. Bring to orb to Caradial Elmheart "
"and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_787"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. Kill three Bonecrew "
"Mutineers and one Bonecrew Mariner in {$f20}."

msgid "start_text_quest_788"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. Search the ruins at lake "
"Garnadar for a sealed well and the orb of history."

msgid "start_text_quest_789"
msgstr ""
"You have found the Orb of Mirendil's History. Bring to orb to Caradial "
"Elmheart and collect your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_790"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from the Emerald Throne. Kill two Raven Standard "
"Grunts and one Raven Standard Veteran."

msgid "start_text_quest_791"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Imathir. I am Caradial Elmheart of the Emerald Throne, and "
"representative for the Elflords. The Elflords are a major power in Mirendil, "
"and their history goes far back before the founding of the mirdian capital "
"Charybdis. As you might understand, the Elflords play a major role in all "
"decision making throughout Mirendil, from military campaigns against our "
"enemies to the welfare of out citizens.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Reports have arrived of a group of gnolls that have been raiding our trade "
"ships along the river Sirith. The gnolls are using the ruins along the banks "
"of the river Sirith as a base for their raids. The river is an important "
"trade route, and the Elflords wish to rid the lands of these savage "
"creatures before they cause any further disruption.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Should you accept to assist the Emerald Throne, go to the gnolls base and "
"slay four of them. The Emerald Throne will reward you for your efforts."

msgid "start_text_quest_792"
msgstr ""
"Strange birdlike creatures called Akathars have appeared north of here in "
"{$f19}. Although no reports have arrived of the creatures creating any "
"problems with the locals of the surrounding areas, the Emerald Throne is not "
"very pleased with their presence within Mirendil. The lands the akathars "
"have moved into belong to one of the Elflords. As you understand, this is "
"unacceptable. \n"
"\n"
"The creatures must immediately be driven off these lands, before more of "
"them arrive and start creating real problems. The Emerald Throne would ask "
"of you to deal with these creatures immediately. If you accept to assist the "
"Emerald Throne, please go rid the lands of these creatures. Killing five "
"akathars should be enough to drive them away."

msgid "start_text_quest_793"
msgstr ""
"The Emerald Throne has always been interest in Mirendil's past. Many ancient "
"legends talk about secrets left behind by the Nithron, a race of golden-"
"skinned giants who once ruled Agon. Secrets that hold answers to Agons past, "
"and thus that of Mirendil's past too.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"To the east of here in {$g20}, there are Nithron ruins. The Emerald Throne "
"is very interested in sending a group of scholars and researches to explore "
"these Nithron ruins. The problem is that most of the Nithron ruins are "
"guarded by ancient magical constructs called revenants. Created by the "
"Nithron, the revenants guard the homes of their masters, who have long "
"abandoned Agon, until the day of their return.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"If we are to investigate these ruins, first we must make them safe for our "
"scholars and researches to visit. The Emerald Throne will reward you, if you "
"accept to clear out the Nithron ruins in {$g20} of these ancient guardians. "
"Please destroy four revenants."

msgid "start_text_quest_794"
msgstr ""
"The Emerald Throne is planning to building a new trading port. The goal of "
"this project is to improve and strengthen Mirendil's trading relationships "
"with its allies. A location along the northern banks of the river Sirith in "
"{$f19} has been selected for the new port, but unfortunately very little "
"progress has been made. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Forest Prophets have moved into the area where the new trading port will be "
"built. It seems that the Forest Prophets do not approve of the new port, and "
"have started attacking the workers, therefore delaying the construction of "
"the new trading port.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elflords will not tolerate such interference in the progress of "
"Mirendil, and that of the mirdain people. It should be made clear to the "
"Forest Prophets that Mirendil belongs to the mirdain, and that the Elflords "
"rule Mirendil. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Construction of our new trading port shall continue. This is the will of the "
"Elflords. The Emerald Throne asks of you to kill five Forest Prophets."

msgid "start_text_quest_795"
msgstr ""
"As our exploration team was searching the Nithron ruins, they came across a "
"small treasure. They discovered an old container buried at the base of one "
"of the walls. Inside the container was a scroll. The scroll is of mirdain "
"origin, dated back to when the mirdain people where under attack and almost "
"annihilated by the alfar. It is dated back to the dark years of mirdain "
"history. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"This scroll was hidden among the nithron ruins, in the hopes that when the "
"mirdain did recover from the alfar, they would find it. Now hundreds of "
"years later, the Emerald Throne has found it. The writings on the scroll "
"talk about two very important artifacts. Artifacts that have recorded upon "
"them the historical events that lead to Melek's rebellion, and thus to the "
"rise of the hateful alfar. These artifacts are extremely important. They "
"shed light on what happened to the proud Mirdain people during the dark "
"years.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Northwest of here in {$e19}, there is a old abandoned tower that once "
"belonged to a powerful wizard. If we are correct, somewhere nearby the tower "
"there should be a statue. That is where the one of the artifacts is hidden. "
"The Emerald Throne would ask of your help, in recovering these important "
"artifacts. When you locate the statue, use the action button to investigate "
"more closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_796"
msgstr ""
"Over a hundred years ago, the Elflords had financed a campaign against the "
"pirates of Imathir. The pirates were based on an island at the mouth of the "
"river Sirith, and from there were controlling the river. It was imperative "
"that the Elflords gained control of this island because of its strategical "
"position. The military campaign against the pirates was successful. While "
"pirates where beaten, but the Elflords had suffered many losses. Most of the "
"brave mirdain warriors who had taken part in the campaign had fallen. It is "
"said that the battle was so horrid, that the ground upon the island remained "
"blood stained red with the blood of the fallen for a hundred years.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now undead pirates have begun appearing upon the island. If they traveled to "
"the island by sea, or if the island itself spawned them, is a mystery. The "
"undead pirates are using the island as a base for attacks on merchant ships. "
"We must remove this threat to Mirendil's trade. The Emerald Throne wishes to "
"clear the island of these thieving undead pirates, and use it for the "
"benefit of the mirdain people by establishing a naval base upon it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Emerald Throne asks that you go to the pirate island and kill three "
"Bonecrew Mutineers and one Bonecrew Mariner."

msgid "start_text_quest_797"
msgstr ""
"Our scholars believe they have discovered the possible location of the "
"second orb of history. We believe it is hidden somewhere in the old ruins by "
"lake Garnadar. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Emerald Throne is very keen in acquiring this second orb. Once we have "
"both orbs, we will have a complete picture of the events and mistakes and "
"lead to the most tragic part of mirdain history, the dark years. The Emerald "
"Throne wishes for all mirdain to learn from these historic events, so nobody "
"may never have to live through such dark times again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"As I said earlier, the other orb is hidden somewhere in the old ruins by "
"lake Garnadar. Based on the information we have, it is hidden in some kind "
"of sealed well. We do not know if this structure still remains intact unit "
"today. Nevertheless, we can only hope. The Emerald Throne would ask of you "
"to go to lake Garnadar, and search for the orb. If you accept, when you find "
"the possible location of the orb, use the action button to investigate more "
"closely."

msgid "start_text_quest_798"
msgstr ""
"The hobgoblin culture is extremely militaristic, and has little love for "
"anything other than the glory of battle. Hobgoblins are renowned as a race "
"of ruthless mercenaries, ready to fighter any war for the highest bidder. "
"And it would seem that the hobgoblins are preparing to fight somebody's war "
"again.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our agents have been spying on a particular hobgoblin war group that have "
"established a camp on one of the islands beyond our shores. From the reports "
"it would seem that the hobgoblins have sent some of their best battle units. "
"But the most interesting fact is, that this specific war group is fighting "
"under the colors of the Raven Standard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hundred of years ago, a hobgoblin leader rose in the jungle wilderness of "
"Yssam. United under his Raven Standard, the hobgoblins were able to carve "
"out a sizable kingdom which lasted for several generations before falling "
"apart during a vicious war of succession. Now once again, under the colors "
"of the Raven Standard a new hobgoblin army is assembling.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"While our agents are gathering intelligence to discover who has hired these "
"hobgoblins, but mostly who is reassembling the Raven Standard Army, we need "
"somebody to assess the strength of the hobgoblin presence on the island. "
"This is an extremely dangerous mission. If you accept to take on this "
"mission, I suggest you prepare yourself for a difficult battle. You are to "
"go and assess the strength of the hobgoblins. Go to the island northwest of "
"here in {$e19}, and kill two Raven Standard Grunts and one Raven Standard "
"Veteran."

msgid "start_text_quest_799"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Yaleria-Sai. Kill three doom spiders that are "
"occupying the new mining site."

msgid "start_text_quest_800"
msgstr ""
"Yaleria-Sai has requested that you assist the Longclaw by removing the "
"Gnolls that have set camp next to the new mining site {$j10}. Kill four "
"Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_801"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to help the Longclaw put an end to the Ogre threat to the "
"northern trade routes in {$k10}. Kill four Ogre Bullies and two Ogre Bosses."

msgid "start_text_quest_802"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Yaleria-Sai. Weaken the the Cult of the "
"Moonbeast in {$j10}, by killing four Moonbeast Disciples and two Moonbeast "
"Berserkers."

msgid "start_text_quest_803"
msgstr ""
"Yalerai-Sai has asked you to destroy six Bonecrew Mutineers that have "
"occupied the island of Ebonyth."

msgid "start_text_quest_804"
msgstr ""
"You have agreed to destroy four Shroud Knights that are haunting the ancient "
"ruins in Yithmoore."

msgid "start_text_quest_805"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Yaleria-Sai the Able. Gather two Tribal "
"Lifeforce."

msgid "start_text_quest_806"
msgstr ""
"The Longclaw have asked of you to help clear the island of Fangwall by "
"killing five Hobgoblin Veterans and two Hobgoblin Officers."

msgid "start_text_quest_807"
msgstr ""
"Welcome to Stonehold mountains. For many years the Longclaw have been "
"operating the stonehold mines, supplying the majority of the tribelands with "
"stone, metal and ore. We are about to begin mining on a new site, but "
"unfortunately we have stumbled upon a nest of doom spiders. If we are to "
"begin mining, the mines must be cleared of the spider infestation. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You seem able enough to take on this task. Kill three Doom Spiders and you "
"will be well rewarded. The site is located on the other side of this "
"mountains, right behind the waterfall. I will mark its position on your map. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Kill three Doom Spiders and then return to me for your reward."

msgid "start_text_quest_808"
msgstr ""
"The Longclaw have successfully been operating the mines here within the "
"Stonehold mountains, and for many years more to come this is the way we want "
"to continue. But these mountains are not the only area we want our mining "
"operations restricted to. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Recently we have discovered a new site rich in ore to the east of here. The "
"problem is that gnolls have set camp near our mining site and are doing all "
"they can to disrupt our work. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"For many centuries the mahirim and the gnoll have fought for control over "
"these lands. And although in recent times the gnolls have lost much ground "
"to the mahirim, there are many large and small gnoll tribes that still roam "
"the Tribelands, creating problems whenever they can. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The gnolls cannot interfere with our mining operations. The Longclaw want "
"you to go to the new mining site in {$j10} to the east of here, and kill "
"four Gnolls."

msgid "start_text_quest_809"
msgstr ""
"Ogres have been attacking our trade routes to the east of here in {$k10}. "
"Most of the Tribelands depend on us to sent out caravans full of stone and "
"ore. It is our responsibility the keep the caravan routes open and safe. \n"
"\n"
"The Ogre threat to our trade routes must be dealt with as soon as possible. "
"We cannot allow these stupid thugs to terrorize the Tribelands. The Longclaw "
"want you to put an end to the Ogre threat along our northern trade routes. "
"Go to {$k10} to the east of here, and kill four Ogre Bullies and two Ogre "
"Bosses."

msgid "start_text_quest_810"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Red Moon have requested that the Longclaw assist them in the "
"fight against the Cult of the Moon-Beast. We have received information of a "
"cultist Moon-Beast village situated to the east of here in {$j10}.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Cult of the Moon-Beast is a group of traditionalist mahirim, who "
"disapprove of all civilizing efforts made by the Elders of Red Moon to "
"modernize the mahirim race. They fear that progress will diminish the "
"strength of the mahirim, and turn them into a  race weak. Nonsense. It is "
"they who are weak and small!\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elders are preparing to attack the cultist village. Information from "
"agents shows that it is being used as a recruiting center for new cult "
"members. Our task is to prepare the grounds for the main attack by weakening "
"them. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, you are to go to the cultist village and kill four Moonbeast "
"Disciples and two Moonbeast Berserkers. That should be enough."

msgid "start_text_quest_811"
msgstr ""
"Years ago, the fishing village of Ebonyth was attacked by pirates. Greatly "
"outnumbered and unable to sent out word for help, on their own the villages "
"fought bravely to the very end. It was a slaughter, and not one soul "
"survived. The pirates took over the island and started using it as a base. "
"And suddenly without a trace, the pirates disappeared.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now a  group of undead pirates have started using the small  fishing village "
"as a base, and have begun attacks upon mahirim vessels. The undead pirates "
"appeared on the island out of nowhere overnight, the same way the pirates "
"back then had disappeared. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Many believe that those same pirates who had slaughtered the fishing village "
"and suddenly disappeared, have now returned. Until we discover the truth "
"behind this mystery, all we can do is to  remove this threat from our waters."
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go to Ebonyth, it is located to west of here, "
"and destroy six Bonecrew Mutineers. There is still a ship that leaves "
"regularly for the island of Ebonyth. You may use it if you wish."

msgid "start_text_quest_812"
msgstr ""
"The Circle of Neith, a group of spellcasters who take special interest in "
"magical item and ancient artifacts, have requested our help. It looks like "
"they have acquired information about an artifact buried somewhere within an "
"ancient city to the northeast of here, in Yithmoore. The Circle of Neith "
"plan to send a group of archaeologists to the site, and have asked of us to "
"clear the site out. Usually we don't accept requests of this kind, but this "
"request coincides with our own needs. We were planning to clear out the "
"ancient city, but only because we had discovered that the ancient city is "
"build on a site rich in metal.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Go to the ancient site northeast of here in Yithmore, and destroy four "
"Shroud Knights. That should be enough for the Circle of Neith to conduct "
"their search. And if any more of these undead knights appear, let the Circle "
"of Neith can do some work for a change."

msgid "start_text_quest_813"
msgstr ""
"Mysterious creatures called Menhir have been appearing at various sites "
"throughout the Tribelands. Some believe they are sent by the gods to guard "
"holy grounds abandoned by their worshipers, while others say they are "
"sinister monsters who are attracted to the residual traces of holy magic "
"that remain in such places. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The problem is that these creatures not only guard these sites, but attack "
"anybody passing near. One of these sites is located northeast of here in "
"Yithmoore. We have tried destroying them, but they just keep reappearing at "
"the site a few days later.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"After consolidating with the Elders of Red Moon, it has been decided that we "
"are to harvest the hearts from these guardians, so that we may discover what "
"exactly they are. You are to go to the sacred site northeast of here, and "
"harvest two Menhir Hearts from the Menhir Custodians."

msgid "start_text_quest_814"
msgstr ""
"Besides mining and guarding the northern tribelands, the Longclaw are also "
"interested in exploring new lands beyond the boarders. We are planning to "
"send an expedition party across the seas onto the ice continent of Niflheim. "
"The expedition has a double purpose. To search for new recourses upon the "
"frozen continent, and to seek out new lands for the Longclaw and the Mahirin "
"to expand to.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But for such an operation to succeed, we must first clear the path toward "
"the continent, and establish safe camps along the way. The island of "
"Fangwall to the northwest of here, is ideal because of it's position, except "
"for one minor problem. Our scouts have reported that hobgoblins have been "
"seen upon the island of Fangwall. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"We need to eliminate the hobgoblin presents on the island of Fangwall. You "
"can help by killing five Hobgoblin Veterans and two Hobgoblin Officers."

msgid "start_text_quest_815"
msgstr ""
"The Elders of Red Moon have asked of you to assess the strength of the Raven "
"Standard hobgoblins in {$h15}. Kill three Raven Standard hobgoblins, and "
"return to Symyr-dan to report your assessment of their strength."

msgid "start_text_quest_816"
msgstr ""
"Our agents have located a hobgoblin war party in {$h15} to the south of "
"here, not very far from our headquarters. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Hobgoblins are known for their love of war, and as a race, they are always "
"prepared for battle. But this is no ordinary hobgoblin war party. These "
"hobgoblins are carrying the colors of the Raven Standard.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Raven Standard Army first appeared hundreds of years ago, somewhere on "
"the jungle continent of Yssam. It was there that a powerful hobgoblin leader "
"managed to unite the hobgoblins, create a powerful kingdom, and the "
"legendary hobgoblin Raven Standard Army. For many years, the hobgoblin "
"kingdom and the Raven Standard Army had been very successful. But according "
"to legends, it all ended and fell apart, after a vicious war of succession. "
"\r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Elders of Red Moon want to learn, if the threat of a new Raven Standard "
"Army is true. You are to go and assess the strength of the hobgoblin war "
"party in {$h15}. This will be an extremely dangerous mission, so I suggest "
"you prepare yourself for a difficult battle. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"I will mark on your map the location of where the Raven Standard hobgoblins "
"were last seen. I want you to kill three Raven Standard hobgoblins, and then "
"return here with a full report of your findings."

msgid "start_text_quest_817"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Kill four Manscorpions "
"that have taken over the Niasha isles."

msgid "start_text_quest_818"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Harvest an Elemental "
"Quartz from the Earth Elemental."

msgid "start_text_quest_819"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Kill five undead dwarves "
"in Saenal."

msgid "start_text_quest_820"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Search for the artifact of "
"the unknown god, that is hidden in the undead city of Fire's Edge."

msgid "start_text_quest_821"
msgstr ""
"You have retrieved the strange artifact that was hidden inside the shrine of "
"the unknown god in the city of Fire's Edge. Return to Niasha and deliver the "
"artifact to Dekazu Fearweaver."

msgid "start_text_quest_822"
msgstr ""
"You have accepted a quest from Dekazu Fearweaver. Go to the Chamber of Fire "
"within mount {$o25}, and search for the legendary artifact known as "
"Durganon's Flame."

msgid "start_text_quest_823"
msgstr "Deliver Durganon's Flame back to Dekazu Fearweaver in Niasha."

msgid "start_text_quest_825"
msgstr ""
"So, you have somehow managed to find your way to Niasha and to the "
"headquarters of the Shadow Salient. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You might be asking yourself, who and what the Shadow Salient are. To many "
"we are an organization of secrets, to others a network of shadows. An agenda "
"not easily defined by many, a group with no clear purpose to others. That is "
"the way of the Shadow Salient. To be everywhere but never seen. To know "
"everything, but never speak.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"But, since you are here, let's give you something to do. A group of "
"Manscorpions recently appeared north of here, on some of the connecting "
"islands. We need those pathetic creatures removed immediately from here. You "
"will go and kill four Manscorpions. When you have completed this simple "
"task, return to me, so we may see what else to do with you."

msgid "start_text_quest_826"
msgstr ""
"We have almost reached that time of the year, where the Shadow Salient "
"prepares for the Ritual of the Fire. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"The Ritual of the Fire is an ancient ritual that signifies Melek's burning "
"desire to concur all, and is performed only by the Shadow Masters. It "
"involves the burning of all those elements that represent the many aspects "
"of Agon. Once all the elements are collected, the Shadow Masters will begin "
"the ritual at the fire shrine which is located on one of the connected "
"islands north of here.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"One of the ingredients used for the ritual is Elemental Quartz. Fortunately, "
"Earth Elementals that can by harvested for Elemental Quartz can be found "
"nearby. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"#PlayerName#, I want you to go and harvest an Elemental Quartz from one of "
"those Earth Elementals. When done, return here with the Elemental Quartz, "
"and you will be rewarded. Go now, the Masters are waiting."

msgid "start_text_quest_827"
msgstr ""
"Hundreds of years ago, the dwarven city of Fire's Edge to the west of here "
"in {$o25} was destroyed by the massive volcanic eruption of mount {$o25}. "
"Mount {$o25} had lain dormant for so long, that it was thought to be dead. "
"Unfortunately for the pathetic dwarves, the sudden reawakening of a volcano "
"put an end to their little reign of glory. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Now years later, the dwarves have returned to their city, with one minor "
"difference. The dwarves have returned as undead, and seem to be busy "
"rebuilding and fortifying their old city. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"Until the Shadow Master can uncover the powers behind this strange event, "
"these pathetic lifeless shells must be destroyed. You are to go Fire's Edge "
"and destroy five undead dwarves."

msgid "start_text_quest_828"
msgstr ""
"Once the dwarves of Fire's Edge returned from the dead, not only have they "
"rebuilt the city of Fire's Edge, but have also found faith in a new god. We "
"must discover who this new god is. Only then would we be able to weaken the "
"strength of the undead dwarves, and send them back to sleep.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"Our shadow agents have returned with information about a shrine inside the "
"undead city of Fire's Edge. Inside this shine there is an item, an artifact. "
"This artifact is believed to be from their new found god. It is this item, "
"this artifact, that is giving new found strength to the undead dwarves. It "
"is this item that seems to have brought the dwarves back from the dead. \r\n"
"\r\n"
"You will infiltrate the city, find the shine, and bring back this artifact. "
"Go into the undead city, and bring back this artifact of this unknown god "
"the undead dwarves are worshiping."

msgid "start_text_quest_829"
msgstr ""
"Before the volcano of mount {$o25} wiped out the dwarven city of Fire's "
"Edge, legends spoke of a dwarven master blacksmith named Durganon who was "
"able to create weapons of superior quality. Durganon had in his possession "
"an artifact left behind by the powerful Nithron. It is this artifact that "
"gave Durganon and the dwarves the power and knowledge to be able to create "
"weapons of superior quality.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"There is a cave complex within the volcano, that leads to a chamber. It is "
"called the Chamber of Fire. Inside it are many Fire Elementals that guard "
"the chamber and its treasure, the legendary artifact known as the Durganon's "
"Flame. We must acquire this artifact, before the undead dwarves re-discover "
"it.\r\n"
"\r\n"
"I want you to go to the Chamber of Fire, and retrieve the legendary artifact "
"Durganon's Flame."
